WEBVTT

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:18.059
Scholastic audio presents Wings of Fire

00:00:18.059 --> 00:00:23.039
Book 7, Winter Turning, by 2ET Sutherland

00:00:23.039 --> 00:00:25.980
read by Shannon McManus.

00:00:44.039 --> 00:00:51.179
The Jade Mountain Prophecy.

00:00:51.299 --> 00:00:55.439
Beware the darkness of dragons.

00:00:55.500 --> 00:00:58.439
Beware the stalker of dreams.

00:00:58.500 --> 00:01:02.100
Beware the talons of power and fire.

00:01:02.159 --> 00:01:05.459
Beware one who is not what she seems.

00:01:05.519 --> 00:01:09.479
Something is coming to shake the earth.

00:01:09.599 --> 00:01:12.420
Something is coming to scorch the

00:01:12.420 --> 00:01:13.019
ground.

00:01:13.079 --> 00:01:16.319
Jade Mountain will fall beneath thunder

00:01:16.319 --> 00:01:17.040
and ice.

00:01:17.099 --> 00:01:19.799
Unless the lost city of night can be

00:01:19.799 --> 00:01:20.040
found.

00:01:32.099 --> 00:01:35.099
Prologue.

00:01:35.159 --> 00:01:36.659
Two years ago.

00:01:36.719 --> 00:01:40.260
It was one of those days so blue and

00:01:40.260 --> 00:01:41.939
sunny that you had to be flying.

00:01:42.060 --> 00:01:45.000
The sky reached in your window 1st thing

00:01:45.000 --> 00:01:46.859
in the morning and dragged you out

00:01:46.859 --> 00:01:50.280
flinging you up and up and up into the

00:01:50.280 --> 00:01:51.900
beautiful wing catching wind.

00:01:51.959 --> 00:01:55.439
You had to soar and spin and dive, because

00:01:55.439 --> 00:01:57.239
a day this perfect might never come

00:01:57.239 --> 00:01:57.480
again.

00:01:57.540 --> 00:02:00.420
And sometimes you had to take your little

00:02:00.420 --> 00:02:03.060
brother with you, and sometimes you had

00:02:03.060 --> 00:02:04.980
to hurl his cautious tail into wonderful

00:02:04.980 --> 00:02:08.039
danger, because the wind was roaring, and

00:02:08.039 --> 00:02:10.740
the sky was glorious, and the sunlight

00:02:10.740 --> 00:02:12.780
promised that nothing bad could possibly

00:02:12.780 --> 00:02:13.139
happen.

00:02:13.199 --> 00:02:16.139
Hailstorm did a flip in the air

00:02:16.139 --> 00:02:16.439
laughing.

00:02:16.500 --> 00:02:19.620
The currents are mine to command, he

00:02:19.620 --> 00:02:20.039
shouted.

00:02:20.099 --> 00:02:21.300
Can you catch me?

00:02:21.360 --> 00:02:22.680
No, you cannot.

00:02:22.740 --> 00:02:23.699
No one can.

00:02:23.759 --> 00:02:25.259
I'm the commander of the sky.

00:02:25.319 --> 00:02:28.139
I think the Sky Wings would disagree

00:02:28.139 --> 00:02:29.520
Winter called.

00:02:29.580 --> 00:02:31.919
He twisted to scan the cloudless blue

00:02:31.919 --> 00:02:32.819
emptiness around them.

00:02:32.939 --> 00:02:36.840
Stop worrying, Hailstorm said, spinning

00:02:36.840 --> 00:02:37.680
into a dive.

00:02:37.740 --> 00:02:39.539
There weren't any dragons within flight

00:02:39.539 --> 00:02:39.960
site.

00:02:40.020 --> 00:02:42.599
It was a perfect day for winter's 1st

00:02:42.599 --> 00:02:44.699
expedition into Skywing territory

00:02:44.759 --> 00:02:47.280
especially if he really wanted to find a

00:02:47.280 --> 00:02:47.759
scavenger.

00:02:47.819 --> 00:02:51.659
This doesn't feel safe, Winter observed

00:02:51.659 --> 00:02:52.259
as they landed.

00:02:52.319 --> 00:02:55.319
His talons sank into a pile of leaves, and

00:02:55.319 --> 00:02:57.060
he jumped back, eyeing them with

00:02:57.060 --> 00:02:57.479
suspicion.

00:02:57.539 --> 00:02:58.860
Yikes!

00:02:58.919 --> 00:03:00.659
What are all these flappy things on the

00:03:00.659 --> 00:03:00.840
ground?

00:03:00.900 --> 00:03:03.120
They come from the trees.

00:03:03.180 --> 00:03:04.979
Hailstorm said, laughing.

00:03:05.099 --> 00:03:06.780
No need to panic, little brother.

00:03:06.840 --> 00:03:09.180
We're here for your weird little

00:03:09.180 --> 00:03:10.979
obsession, so get excited.

00:03:11.039 --> 00:03:14.400
He took a deep breath, inhaling the

00:03:14.400 --> 00:03:16.680
smells of the forest, and sneezed

00:03:16.680 --> 00:03:17.099
loudly.

00:03:17.159 --> 00:03:20.159
Winter protested.

00:03:20.280 --> 00:03:22.319
This is the Sky Kingdom.

00:03:22.379 --> 00:03:24.000
There could be enemy soldiers

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:24.300
everywhere.

00:03:24.360 --> 00:03:27.659
Lounging around in the woods near a

00:03:27.659 --> 00:03:28.439
scavenger den?

00:03:28.500 --> 00:03:31.139
Hellstorms said skeptically.

00:03:31.319 --> 00:03:31.740
Doubtful.

00:03:31.800 --> 00:03:33.900
He flicked his brother's wing with his

00:03:33.900 --> 00:03:34.139
tail.

00:03:34.199 --> 00:03:36.960
Winter was only three, but he was very

00:03:36.960 --> 00:03:39.599
amusing, a lot more fun to tease than

00:03:39.599 --> 00:03:39.960
their sister.

00:03:40.020 --> 00:03:43.500
He also tried so hard, and still had so

00:03:43.500 --> 00:03:44.819
much trouble with the rankings.

00:03:44.879 --> 00:03:46.620
Poor dragon.

00:03:46.680 --> 00:03:48.479
Hailstorm wished he could relax a little

00:03:48.479 --> 00:03:48.719
bit.

00:03:48.780 --> 00:03:51.000
Not everyone could be the best at

00:03:51.000 --> 00:03:53.280
everything, although it most likely

00:03:53.280 --> 00:03:54.780
didn't help that his big brother actually

00:03:54.780 --> 00:03:55.080
was.

00:03:55.199 --> 00:03:58.680
Despite his worry, Winter couldn't hide

00:03:58.680 --> 00:04:00.240
the excitement spilling over his face.

00:04:00.300 --> 00:04:03.240
Is there really a scavenger den here?

00:04:03.300 --> 00:04:06.360
He blinked at the trees. as if hoping a

00:04:06.360 --> 00:04:07.860
scavenger would suddenly fall out of one

00:04:07.860 --> 00:04:08.099
of them.

00:04:08.159 --> 00:04:12.240
That's what the patrol reported, Hellstorm

00:04:12.240 --> 00:04:13.020
said with a shrug.

00:04:13.080 --> 00:04:15.780
They said they saw at least 5 scavengers

00:04:15.780 --> 00:04:17.819
and that many usually means a den

00:04:17.819 --> 00:04:18.300
nearby.

00:04:18.360 --> 00:04:21.420
Now that they were surrounded by trees

00:04:21.420 --> 00:04:23.579
though, he had no idea how they were

00:04:23.579 --> 00:04:25.319
going to find one of the little creatures

00:04:25.319 --> 00:04:25.740
for winter.

00:04:25.800 --> 00:04:27.959
Hailstorm had never actually seen one

00:04:27.959 --> 00:04:28.319
himself.

00:04:28.379 --> 00:04:31.079
There were 100s of furry smells in the

00:04:31.079 --> 00:04:33.060
forest, but he couldn't even figure out

00:04:33.060 --> 00:04:35.279
which ones were scavengers, and which

00:04:35.279 --> 00:04:36.540
ones were squirrels.

00:04:36.600 --> 00:04:38.939
The only thing he was sure of was that

00:04:38.939 --> 00:04:40.620
none of them were polar bears.

00:04:40.680 --> 00:04:44.220
What are you going to do if we do catch

00:04:44.220 --> 00:04:44.459
one?

00:04:44.519 --> 00:04:47.459
Hailstorm asked, turning over a fallen

00:04:47.459 --> 00:04:48.660
log and checking underneath.

00:04:48.720 --> 00:04:50.879
Nope, no scavengers there.

00:04:50.939 --> 00:04:53.339
You know they can't survive in the ice

00:04:53.339 --> 00:04:53.759
kingdom.

00:04:53.819 --> 00:04:55.560
You won't be able to keep it.

00:04:55.620 --> 00:04:58.500
I just want to look at it, Winter said.

00:04:58.560 --> 00:05:00.899
Have you ever seen a scavenger up close?

00:05:01.019 --> 00:05:04.019
I read that they wear other animals' skins

00:05:04.019 --> 00:05:05.339
on top of their own skin.

00:05:05.399 --> 00:05:07.019
Isn't that bizarre?

00:05:07.259 --> 00:05:08.100
Why would they do that?

00:05:08.160 --> 00:05:11.279
Same reason mother has that necklace of

00:05:11.279 --> 00:05:12.000
sky wing teeth?

00:05:12.120 --> 00:05:14.339
Hailstorm said authoritatively?

00:05:14.399 --> 00:05:16.800
To make themselves seem more dangerous

00:05:16.800 --> 00:05:19.079
and scare off any possible predators

00:05:19.079 --> 00:05:19.980
obviously.

00:05:20.040 --> 00:05:22.680
Winter glanced at the sky.

00:05:22.740 --> 00:05:25.019
Speaking of sky wings.

00:05:25.139 --> 00:05:29.819
We're fine, hailstorm insisted, tempted

00:05:29.819 --> 00:05:31.860
to jab Winter's worrying snout with one

00:05:31.860 --> 00:05:32.579
of his claws.

00:05:32.639 --> 00:05:35.160
Where several mountains away from Queen

00:05:35.160 --> 00:05:36.240
Scarlet's palace.

00:05:36.300 --> 00:05:37.800
No one is going to find us here.

00:05:37.860 --> 00:05:40.439
But won't father be furious?

00:05:40.500 --> 00:05:42.839
Winter asked, twitching slightly.

00:05:42.899 --> 00:05:46.079
Hailstorm ruffled his wings, as though he

00:05:46.079 --> 00:05:47.339
was trying to shake the idea of their

00:05:47.339 --> 00:05:48.720
parents right off his scales.

00:05:48.779 --> 00:05:50.399
Who cares?

00:05:50.399 --> 00:05:51.180
he said.

00:05:51.240 --> 00:05:54.000
I'm going to be 2nd in command of the ice

00:05:54.000 --> 00:05:54.899
wing army one day.

00:05:54.959 --> 00:05:56.939
Queen Glacier already said so.

00:05:57.060 --> 00:05:59.160
Mother and father can't do anything to

00:05:59.160 --> 00:05:59.339
me.

00:05:59.459 --> 00:06:03.540
They can do plenty to me, Winter said.

00:06:03.600 --> 00:06:05.639
Not if you get high enough in their

00:06:05.639 --> 00:06:07.980
rankings, Hellstorm said with a grin.

00:06:08.040 --> 00:06:10.680
Which you do by being brave and strong

00:06:10.680 --> 00:06:11.519
and bold.

00:06:11.579 --> 00:06:14.639
I thought it was by being smart and

00:06:14.639 --> 00:06:16.740
following orders, Winter said.

00:06:16.800 --> 00:06:19.860
Hailstorm dismissed this with a wave of

00:06:19.860 --> 00:06:20.339
his tail.

00:06:20.399 --> 00:06:23.639
Dragons in the 3rd circle and below can

00:06:23.639 --> 00:06:24.779
worry about following orders.

00:06:24.839 --> 00:06:27.600
First circle dragons have to prepare to

00:06:27.600 --> 00:06:28.379
be leaders one day.

00:06:28.439 --> 00:06:31.740
Besides, I'm the best fighter in the ice

00:06:31.740 --> 00:06:31.980
kingdom.

00:06:32.040 --> 00:06:34.800
Even if we do get caught, I think I can

00:06:34.800 --> 00:06:36.060
take a couple of sky wings.

00:06:36.120 --> 00:06:37.740
Oh, really?

00:06:37.800 --> 00:06:40.199
Said a mocking voice behind them.

00:06:40.259 --> 00:06:43.680
How about 14 Sky Wings?

00:06:43.740 --> 00:06:47.699
Hailstorm world around, red and orange

00:06:47.699 --> 00:06:49.920
dragons were slithering between the trees

00:06:49.920 --> 00:06:51.060
surrounding them.

00:06:51.120 --> 00:06:53.699
Their eyes glittered in the golden light

00:06:53.699 --> 00:06:56.040
and their enormous wings were tucked in

00:06:56.040 --> 00:06:58.319
close to avoid the snarling branches

00:06:58.319 --> 00:06:58.680
above.

00:06:58.740 --> 00:07:00.540
His heart sank.

00:07:00.660 --> 00:07:02.399
This couldn't be happening.

00:07:02.459 --> 00:07:05.160
Bad luck wasn't a thing that ever

00:07:05.160 --> 00:07:07.740
wandered into Hillstorm's life, and this

00:07:07.740 --> 00:07:09.600
was the worst luck he could have

00:07:09.600 --> 00:07:10.139
imagined.

00:07:10.199 --> 00:07:13.500
14 Sky Wing warriors were more than he

00:07:13.500 --> 00:07:14.100
could fight alone.

00:07:14.160 --> 00:07:16.560
Definitely more than he could fight and

00:07:16.560 --> 00:07:17.939
still keep his little brother safe.

00:07:18.000 --> 00:07:22.800
Second in command, the ice wing army, said

00:07:22.800 --> 00:07:23.699
the one who'd spoken.

00:07:23.759 --> 00:07:26.399
A dark red female dragon with an

00:07:26.399 --> 00:07:27.839
unusually long neck and tail.

00:07:27.899 --> 00:07:30.959
Small rubies glittered from between the

00:07:30.959 --> 00:07:33.600
scales around her eyes, larger ones

00:07:33.600 --> 00:07:35.879
clicked together on spiky silver rings

00:07:35.879 --> 00:07:37.019
around her claws.

00:07:37.079 --> 00:07:39.480
Then you are a prize, aren't you?

00:07:39.540 --> 00:07:42.420
Mother will be so interested to meet

00:07:42.420 --> 00:07:42.660
you.

00:07:42.720 --> 00:07:46.680
Let us go, Winter said fiercely.

00:07:46.740 --> 00:07:48.899
Queen Glacier will have your heads on

00:07:48.899 --> 00:07:50.939
spikes by morning if you dare touch us.

00:07:51.000 --> 00:07:52.920
Oh?

00:07:52.980 --> 00:07:55.560
Very attached to you, is she?

00:07:55.620 --> 00:07:58.620
The dragon said, arching her brows.

00:07:58.680 --> 00:08:02.220
That's absolutely our favorite kind of

00:08:02.220 --> 00:08:02.879
prisoner.

00:08:02.939 --> 00:08:05.639
Seize them, she ordered the other sky

00:08:05.639 --> 00:08:06.180
wings.

00:08:06.240 --> 00:08:10.019
Perhaps you can take us, Hillstorm said

00:08:10.019 --> 00:08:11.699
drawing in a hissing breath.

00:08:11.759 --> 00:08:13.800
But how many of you are going to die

00:08:13.800 --> 00:08:14.160
first?

00:08:14.220 --> 00:08:16.800
Do you know what happens when frost

00:08:16.800 --> 00:08:17.939
breath touches your eyes?

00:08:18.000 --> 00:08:20.339
Do you know what it feels like to watch

00:08:20.339 --> 00:08:22.500
your legs snap like a broken icicle?

00:08:22.560 --> 00:08:25.800
Or how long it takes frozen ears to turn

00:08:25.800 --> 00:08:27.060
black and fall off?

00:08:27.120 --> 00:08:29.100
His voice was cold.

00:08:29.160 --> 00:08:31.560
His threats slicing the air between them

00:08:31.560 --> 00:08:32.460
like a freezing wind.

00:08:32.519 --> 00:08:35.820
Winter raised his tail and inhaled

00:08:35.820 --> 00:08:37.980
working up a gust of frost breath of his

00:08:37.980 --> 00:08:38.460
own.

00:08:38.519 --> 00:08:41.159
So a few dragons die.

00:08:41.220 --> 00:08:43.799
So the female sky wing with a shrug.

00:08:43.860 --> 00:08:46.740
The other sky wings exchanged uneasy

00:08:46.740 --> 00:08:47.039
looks.

00:08:47.100 --> 00:08:50.100
You'll be our prisoners in the end either

00:08:50.100 --> 00:08:50.399
way.

00:08:50.460 --> 00:08:54.539
Here's another idea, said Hillstorm.

00:08:54.600 --> 00:08:57.539
Take me and let winter go, and nobody has

00:08:57.539 --> 00:08:57.840
to die.

00:08:57.899 --> 00:08:59.460
What?

00:08:59.519 --> 00:09:00.779
Winter cried.

00:09:00.899 --> 00:09:03.960
You don't need him, Hellstorm said

00:09:03.960 --> 00:09:04.980
ignoring his brother.

00:09:05.039 --> 00:09:06.720
He's completely useless.

00:09:06.779 --> 00:09:09.240
Queen Glacier won't trade any prisoners

00:09:09.240 --> 00:09:09.539
for him.

00:09:09.600 --> 00:09:12.299
Nobody back in the Ice Kingdom would care

00:09:12.299 --> 00:09:13.500
whether they ever saw him again.

00:09:13.559 --> 00:09:15.659
And you wouldn't even be interesting in

00:09:15.659 --> 00:09:16.620
your queen's arena.

00:09:16.620 --> 00:09:17.700
He can barely fight.

00:09:17.759 --> 00:09:19.799
He'd be dead in 2 heartbeats.

00:09:19.860 --> 00:09:22.740
Winter looked as though the world was

00:09:22.740 --> 00:09:24.539
crumbling beneath his talons.

00:09:24.600 --> 00:09:25.799
Is that true?

00:09:25.860 --> 00:09:27.059
He whispered.

00:09:27.120 --> 00:09:29.580
Hillstorm, is that really what you

00:09:29.580 --> 00:09:29.820
think?

00:09:29.879 --> 00:09:34.320
If he's so useless, the sky wing asked

00:09:34.320 --> 00:09:36.360
why do you care if we let him go?

00:09:36.419 --> 00:09:39.779
Hailstorm lifted, and settled his wings

00:09:39.779 --> 00:09:40.019
again?

00:09:40.080 --> 00:09:42.299
Call me sentimental.

00:09:42.360 --> 00:09:44.820
He's my little brother, and I quite like

00:09:44.820 --> 00:09:45.059
him.

00:09:45.120 --> 00:09:47.580
Even if I wouldn't want him beside me in

00:09:47.580 --> 00:09:47.879
a battle.

00:09:47.940 --> 00:09:51.120
Besides, I know I'm worth trading.

00:09:51.179 --> 00:09:53.399
Whereas he'll be bones in your arena

00:09:53.399 --> 00:09:54.720
sands before the month is up.

00:09:54.779 --> 00:09:58.259
Ouch, said the Sky Wing.

00:09:58.379 --> 00:10:00.960
Giving winter an amused, pitying look.

00:10:01.080 --> 00:10:04.019
I think I'd probably rather die in battle

00:10:04.019 --> 00:10:06.779
than listen to my brother talk about me

00:10:06.779 --> 00:10:07.080
that way.

00:10:07.139 --> 00:10:09.419
I'm not useless.

00:10:09.480 --> 00:10:11.279
Winter said furiously.

00:10:11.340 --> 00:10:12.899
Bite me and you'll see.

00:10:13.019 --> 00:10:17.820
Oh, go home, Hellstorm said, swatting

00:10:17.820 --> 00:10:18.600
winter's wing.

00:10:18.659 --> 00:10:20.039
You want to be useful?

00:10:20.100 --> 00:10:20.820
Fine.

00:10:20.879 --> 00:10:22.139
Get out of here.

00:10:22.200 --> 00:10:23.580
Go tell our parents where I am.

00:10:23.639 --> 00:10:28.200
I'm not leaving you, Winter protested, in

00:10:28.200 --> 00:10:29.159
a half choked voice.

00:10:29.279 --> 00:10:31.500
I'm not going to hand you over to them

00:10:31.500 --> 00:10:33.659
without even trying to save you.

00:10:33.720 --> 00:10:37.139
Yes, you are, Hailstorm said.

00:10:37.200 --> 00:10:39.960
This is the real war, little brother.

00:10:40.019 --> 00:10:42.779
Go away and let the true warriors fight

00:10:42.779 --> 00:10:43.019
it.

00:10:43.080 --> 00:10:45.419
Nobody wants to watch you pathetically

00:10:45.419 --> 00:10:47.279
flail around and then die pointlessly.

00:10:47.340 --> 00:10:51.299
Oh my, I can't even listen to this

00:10:51.299 --> 00:10:53.399
anymore, said the Sky Wing.

00:10:53.460 --> 00:10:54.960
I swing.

00:10:55.019 --> 00:10:57.299
I'm going to be more merciful than your

00:10:57.299 --> 00:10:59.460
heartless brother and let you go.

00:10:59.580 --> 00:11:02.759
You can tell Queen Glacier that Queen

00:11:02.759 --> 00:11:04.740
Scarlet will consider a trade.

00:11:04.799 --> 00:11:07.620
If she'd like to send a messenger to open

00:11:07.620 --> 00:11:08.519
negotiations.

00:11:08.639 --> 00:11:11.100
Trade for who?

00:11:11.159 --> 00:11:12.960
Hailstorm wondered.

00:11:13.080 --> 00:11:15.419
The Ice Wings didn't have any political

00:11:15.419 --> 00:11:16.559
prisoners of importance.

00:11:16.620 --> 00:11:18.179
Where would they even keep them?

00:11:18.240 --> 00:11:21.179
The ice palace was too cold for dragons

00:11:21.179 --> 00:11:22.980
from any other tribe to survive it for

00:11:22.980 --> 00:11:23.580
long.

00:11:23.639 --> 00:11:27.059
He shoved winter away, trying to ignore

00:11:27.059 --> 00:11:28.620
the anguished look in his brother's

00:11:28.620 --> 00:11:28.980
eyes.

00:11:29.039 --> 00:11:33.240
Fly away, he growled, right now.

00:11:33.299 --> 00:11:36.179
He could see that the only way to make

00:11:36.179 --> 00:11:38.519
winter leave was to be as cruel as

00:11:38.519 --> 00:11:39.000
possible.

00:11:39.059 --> 00:11:41.820
He lowered his voice and shoved in the

00:11:41.820 --> 00:11:42.600
last blade.

00:11:42.659 --> 00:11:45.779
Don't be a mewling rain wing in front of

00:11:45.779 --> 00:11:46.440
our enemies.

00:11:46.500 --> 00:11:50.700
Winter stepped back, tense, like a wolf

00:11:50.700 --> 00:11:51.299
about to spring.

00:11:51.360 --> 00:11:54.720
He stared into hailstorm's eyes for one

00:11:54.720 --> 00:11:57.240
long final moment, and then he suddenly

00:11:57.240 --> 00:11:58.620
pivoted and leaped into the air.

00:11:58.679 --> 00:12:02.039
His pale blue scales glinted orange red

00:12:02.039 --> 00:12:04.019
as they caught the sun, and then he

00:12:04.019 --> 00:12:06.419
swooped into the wide sky, heading west.

00:12:06.480 --> 00:12:08.340
He's safe.

00:12:08.399 --> 00:12:10.620
Hillstorm thought with relief.

00:12:10.679 --> 00:12:13.860
Even if he hates me now, at least he's

00:12:13.860 --> 00:12:13.980
alive.

00:12:14.100 --> 00:12:16.740
Winter wasn't useless.

00:12:16.799 --> 00:12:19.259
But it was true that his current ranking

00:12:19.259 --> 00:12:21.600
wouldn't make him worth rescuing, and it

00:12:21.600 --> 00:12:23.879
was also true that Hailstorm didn't want

00:12:23.879 --> 00:12:25.799
to see his brother die in Scarlet's

00:12:25.799 --> 00:12:26.820
notorious arena.

00:12:26.879 --> 00:12:30.179
The Skywing smiled as Hailstorm turned

00:12:30.179 --> 00:12:30.659
back to her.

00:12:30.720 --> 00:12:33.480
Aren't we civilized?

00:12:33.480 --> 00:12:34.379
she said.

00:12:34.440 --> 00:12:37.559
Somebody club this ice wing over the head

00:12:37.559 --> 00:12:39.360
and let's drag him off to prison.

00:12:39.419 --> 00:12:41.820
That's not ness.

00:12:41.820 --> 00:12:44.039
Hellstorm started to protest.

00:12:44.100 --> 00:12:46.860
But suddenly a sharp bolt of pain cleaved

00:12:46.860 --> 00:12:48.539
through his head, and everything went

00:12:48.539 --> 00:12:48.840
dark.

00:12:48.899 --> 00:12:54.000
He woke up in a bright throne room, so

00:12:54.000 --> 00:12:55.980
bright, he instantly got a headache.

00:12:56.039 --> 00:12:58.080
Although the brightness of the sun on

00:12:58.080 --> 00:12:59.399
eyes had never bothered him.

00:12:59.460 --> 00:13:02.399
But here the sun reflected hotly in all

00:13:02.399 --> 00:13:04.919
corners of the room, and every surface

00:13:04.919 --> 00:13:07.860
seemed to be plastered with gold, loud

00:13:07.860 --> 00:13:11.100
and gaudy and yellow, and way, way too

00:13:11.100 --> 00:13:11.399
shiny.

00:13:11.460 --> 00:13:16.500
Oh, finally. said an impatient voice

00:13:16.500 --> 00:13:17.039
nearby.

00:13:17.100 --> 00:13:19.559
You've been so horribly boring.

00:13:19.679 --> 00:13:22.019
I hope you intend to be exceptionally

00:13:22.019 --> 00:13:23.460
thrilling now to make up for it.

00:13:23.519 --> 00:13:27.179
Hailstorm gathered his wings and stood up

00:13:27.179 --> 00:13:28.679
slowly, rubbing his head.

00:13:28.740 --> 00:13:32.159
Chains weighed down his talons, and

00:13:32.159 --> 00:13:34.320
strange metal bands prevented his wings

00:13:34.320 --> 00:13:36.899
from unfurling all the way, but there

00:13:36.899 --> 00:13:37.980
were no guards around him.

00:13:38.039 --> 00:13:40.320
Only one other dragon was in the room.

00:13:40.379 --> 00:13:43.080
He lifted his eyes to the throne.

00:13:43.200 --> 00:13:47.879
Orange scales. glittering rubies, a

00:13:47.879 --> 00:13:49.500
circlet of gold and diamonds.

00:13:49.559 --> 00:13:52.019
Yellow eyes peered down at him through

00:13:52.019 --> 00:13:53.220
veils of smoke.

00:13:53.340 --> 00:13:56.340
He'd only seen the sky wing queen from a

00:13:56.340 --> 00:13:58.860
distance once, hearing a battle, but

00:13:58.860 --> 00:14:00.179
there was no doubt this was her.

00:14:00.240 --> 00:14:04.080
Greetings, your majesty, he said.

00:14:04.139 --> 00:14:06.240
I'm sorry we have to meet this way.

00:14:06.299 --> 00:14:10.080
She studied him for a moment, and then an

00:14:10.080 --> 00:14:12.179
unexpected smile quirked the corners of

00:14:12.179 --> 00:14:12.659
her mouth.

00:14:12.720 --> 00:14:15.059
Instead of in combat.

00:14:15.179 --> 00:14:16.620
She guessed.

00:14:16.679 --> 00:14:19.679
He gave her a similarly small smile in

00:14:19.679 --> 00:14:20.220
return.

00:14:20.340 --> 00:14:21.419
Yes.

00:14:21.480 --> 00:14:24.299
The battlefield is where I prefer to meet

00:14:24.299 --> 00:14:24.960
all my enemies.

00:14:25.019 --> 00:14:28.139
Although then the acquaintance doesn't

00:14:28.139 --> 00:14:28.620
last very long.

00:14:28.679 --> 00:14:31.080
Arrogant.

00:14:31.139 --> 00:14:32.879
Queen Scarlet mused.

00:14:33.000 --> 00:14:34.980
Like all eyes wings.

00:14:35.039 --> 00:14:37.980
Take a note of that, she said over her

00:14:37.980 --> 00:14:38.279
shoulder.

00:14:38.340 --> 00:14:41.580
Hailstorm saw the shadows move behind the

00:14:41.580 --> 00:14:43.919
queen, as if something were pushing

00:14:43.919 --> 00:14:45.419
itself slowly out of the wall.

00:14:45.480 --> 00:14:49.379
He blinked, feeling a strange shiver of

00:14:49.379 --> 00:14:50.340
eerie fear.

00:14:50.399 --> 00:14:53.399
But when he looked again, an ordinary sky

00:14:53.399 --> 00:14:55.259
wing soldier was standing beside Queen

00:14:55.259 --> 00:14:57.600
Scarlet, riding on a small scroll.

00:14:57.659 --> 00:15:01.440
He hadn't seen her come in, but maybe all

00:15:01.440 --> 00:15:03.960
the gold had dazzled his eyes, so he'd

00:15:03.960 --> 00:15:04.860
just missed her before.

00:15:04.919 --> 00:15:08.580
She was an orange color, very close to

00:15:08.580 --> 00:15:10.919
the golden yellow of the room, with warm

00:15:10.919 --> 00:15:11.879
amber eyes.

00:15:11.940 --> 00:15:14.639
She looked young, and quiet.

00:15:14.700 --> 00:15:17.879
Her voice when she finally spoke, was

00:15:17.879 --> 00:15:18.120
soft.

00:15:18.179 --> 00:15:20.700
Are you sure you want to do this?

00:15:20.759 --> 00:15:22.080
Your majesty?

00:15:22.080 --> 00:15:22.799
she asked.

00:15:22.860 --> 00:15:24.600
Yes.

00:15:24.720 --> 00:15:27.059
Queen Scarlet said with a hiss.

00:15:27.120 --> 00:15:29.460
He's dangerous the way he is.

00:15:29.519 --> 00:15:30.899
Anyone can see that.

00:15:31.019 --> 00:15:34.019
I can't use him in my arena if I want to

00:15:34.019 --> 00:15:34.679
trade him later.

00:15:34.740 --> 00:15:37.019
And I don't want to deal with any messy

00:15:37.019 --> 00:15:39.000
escape or rescue attempts.

00:15:39.059 --> 00:15:42.419
You understand, I'm not sure what the

00:15:42.419 --> 00:15:44.940
consequences will be, said the soldier.

00:15:45.059 --> 00:15:48.179
If we stick to your unusual

00:15:48.179 --> 00:15:50.100
specifications, I mean.

00:15:50.159 --> 00:15:53.940
I told you I'd only use you for special

00:15:53.940 --> 00:15:54.720
cases.

00:15:54.840 --> 00:15:56.940
The queen lashed her tail.

00:15:57.000 --> 00:15:59.460
This is one.

00:15:59.519 --> 00:16:01.139
Very well.

00:16:01.259 --> 00:16:04.740
Then he's gone, said the other Sky Wing.

00:16:04.799 --> 00:16:07.259
No one will ever be able to find him.

00:16:07.320 --> 00:16:08.940
Trust me.

00:16:09.000 --> 00:16:11.519
Queen Scarlet snorted.

00:16:11.580 --> 00:16:14.159
Not one of my favorite activities

00:16:14.159 --> 00:16:17.039
trusting other dragons, she said.

00:16:17.100 --> 00:16:19.440
But I'll give it a whirl, just this

00:16:19.440 --> 00:16:19.740
once.

00:16:19.799 --> 00:16:20.759
He's all yours.

00:16:20.820 --> 00:16:24.659
The dragon smiled sideways at Hailstorm

00:16:24.659 --> 00:16:27.539
and for the 1st time in his life, he felt

00:16:27.539 --> 00:16:31.019
cold all the way through his bones and

00:16:31.019 --> 00:16:31.440
claws.

00:16:31.559 --> 00:16:34.860
She stepped toward him, reaching for

00:16:34.860 --> 00:16:37.019
something around her neck, but he was too

00:16:37.019 --> 00:16:39.960
hypnotized by her eyes to run, or fight

00:16:39.960 --> 00:16:40.860
or even scream.

00:16:40.919 --> 00:16:44.580
Her eyes were not normal sky wing eyes

00:16:44.580 --> 00:16:44.940
anymore.

00:16:45.000 --> 00:16:46.799
They were dark black.

00:16:46.919 --> 00:16:50.159
Black is the darkest abyss in the ocean

00:16:50.159 --> 00:16:52.559
and they were coming to swallow him

00:16:52.559 --> 00:16:52.860
whole.

00:16:52.919 --> 00:16:57.360
Part one.

00:16:57.419 --> 00:16:59.340
A cold wind.

00:16:59.399 --> 00:17:03.240
Chapter one.

00:17:03.360 --> 00:17:06.660
The first time Winter disappointed his

00:17:06.660 --> 00:17:07.019
family.

00:17:07.079 --> 00:17:08.279
He was 2 years old.

00:17:08.339 --> 00:17:11.759
Or at least the 1st time he knew he'd

00:17:11.759 --> 00:17:12.599
disappointed them.

00:17:12.599 --> 00:17:15.059
Perhaps it had been happening all along

00:17:15.059 --> 00:17:17.399
and they'd hidden it behind the stern

00:17:17.399 --> 00:17:19.919
demanding faces they showed all the royal

00:17:19.919 --> 00:17:20.699
dragonettes.

00:17:20.759 --> 00:17:22.980
He could remember the dawn that day.

00:17:23.039 --> 00:17:26.759
The morning of his 11th hunt, the subzero

00:17:26.759 --> 00:17:29.460
chill in the air, the paling purple of

00:17:29.460 --> 00:17:32.640
the sky. 2 moons still high overhead

00:17:32.640 --> 00:17:35.220
while the 3rd slid its thin crescent

00:17:35.220 --> 00:17:36.720
slivered down below the horizon.

00:17:36.839 --> 00:17:39.720
A snowy owl was perched on one of the

00:17:39.720 --> 00:17:42.480
palace outcroppings, its talons digging

00:17:42.480 --> 00:17:45.059
into the ice, it glowered beatily at

00:17:45.059 --> 00:17:47.400
winter, as if it saw his disgrace

00:17:47.400 --> 00:17:47.759
coming.

00:17:47.819 --> 00:17:50.579
His sister icicle was in the hunting

00:17:50.579 --> 00:17:50.759
party.

00:17:50.819 --> 00:17:53.940
And his brother, Hailstorm too, along

00:17:53.940 --> 00:17:56.400
with 2 of Glaciers' dragonettes, one of

00:17:56.400 --> 00:17:59.279
Winter's royal uncles, 3 attendants, and

00:17:59.279 --> 00:18:02.099
Winter's parents, Tundra, and Narwhal.

00:18:02.160 --> 00:18:04.619
They gathered in the courtyard of the Ice

00:18:04.619 --> 00:18:06.960
Palace, stamping their feet and beating

00:18:06.960 --> 00:18:09.299
their wings as the glorious freezing air

00:18:09.299 --> 00:18:10.500
filled their lungs.

00:18:10.619 --> 00:18:12.779
The sharp crunch of snow beneath their

00:18:12.779 --> 00:18:14.279
claws broke the stillness of the

00:18:14.279 --> 00:18:14.579
morning.

00:18:14.640 --> 00:18:17.400
Winter remembered looking up at his

00:18:17.400 --> 00:18:18.900
mother as she hissed for attention.

00:18:18.960 --> 00:18:22.200
This hunt is for the table of the queen

00:18:22.200 --> 00:18:22.619
herself.

00:18:22.680 --> 00:18:24.420
Tundra growled.

00:18:24.480 --> 00:18:27.480
Whoever brings down the 1st polar bear

00:18:27.480 --> 00:18:30.119
will be invited to sit at her side this

00:18:30.119 --> 00:18:30.359
evening.

00:18:30.480 --> 00:18:33.539
She shot a glittering look at icicle

00:18:33.539 --> 00:18:34.859
coiled beside winter.

00:18:34.920 --> 00:18:38.759
Icicle was only 2 years old as well, but

00:18:38.759 --> 00:18:40.380
she already knew the future her parents

00:18:40.380 --> 00:18:41.400
had planned for her.

00:18:41.460 --> 00:18:42.900
So did winter.

00:18:42.960 --> 00:18:45.180
Although he suspected he wasn't supposed

00:18:45.180 --> 00:18:45.359
to.

00:18:45.420 --> 00:18:47.940
He couldn't remember how he knew.

00:18:48.000 --> 00:18:50.759
Had he overheard his parents whispering

00:18:50.759 --> 00:18:52.619
when they thought he was too young to

00:18:52.619 --> 00:18:53.099
understand.

00:18:53.160 --> 00:18:55.319
Or had he figured it out from their

00:18:55.319 --> 00:18:56.700
behavior over the years.

00:18:56.759 --> 00:18:58.200
But he did know.

00:18:58.259 --> 00:18:59.579
One day.

00:18:59.640 --> 00:19:02.640
Icicle would challenge their aunt, Queen

00:19:02.640 --> 00:19:04.500
Glacier, for the throne.

00:19:04.559 --> 00:19:07.559
That was the reason she was hatched, and

00:19:07.559 --> 00:19:10.079
the destiny she was trained for, to kill

00:19:10.079 --> 00:19:12.299
Glacier, and become Queen herself.

00:19:12.359 --> 00:19:14.940
The only question was when.

00:19:15.059 --> 00:19:18.720
Glacier grew older and larger and

00:19:18.720 --> 00:19:19.920
stronger each year.

00:19:19.980 --> 00:19:22.980
And Icicle had to strike before one of

00:19:22.980 --> 00:19:24.779
Glacier's own daughters seized the

00:19:24.779 --> 00:19:25.380
queenship.

00:19:25.440 --> 00:19:28.740
Daughters, sisters, or nieces could try

00:19:28.740 --> 00:19:29.339
for the throne.

00:19:29.400 --> 00:19:32.519
Cousins could not, neither could sisters

00:19:32.519 --> 00:19:35.099
in law, or tundra surely would have

00:19:35.099 --> 00:19:36.299
thrown down the challenge herself.

00:19:36.420 --> 00:19:38.940
So Winter's parents couldn't wait

00:19:38.940 --> 00:19:39.240
forever.

00:19:39.299 --> 00:19:42.119
But they also needed to be sure Icicle

00:19:42.119 --> 00:19:42.480
was ready.

00:19:42.539 --> 00:19:44.579
She'd have only one chance.

00:19:44.700 --> 00:19:46.799
Kill or die?

00:19:46.859 --> 00:19:48.059
That was how it worked.

00:19:48.119 --> 00:19:51.720
Isaacle lifted her snout and returned her

00:19:51.720 --> 00:19:53.460
mother's arch calculating look.

00:19:53.519 --> 00:19:57.599
It'll be me, she said, sounding almost

00:19:57.599 --> 00:19:58.259
bored.

00:19:58.319 --> 00:19:59.819
Signed a polar bear?

00:19:59.880 --> 00:20:00.359
Easy.

00:20:00.420 --> 00:20:02.519
I have a much better nose than these

00:20:02.519 --> 00:20:02.819
two.

00:20:02.880 --> 00:20:05.339
She flicked her tail dismissively at

00:20:05.339 --> 00:20:06.299
Hellstorm and Winter.

00:20:06.359 --> 00:20:08.099
We'll see about that.

00:20:08.220 --> 00:20:09.900
Hellstorm said.

00:20:09.960 --> 00:20:12.180
He grinned and hopped from foot to foot

00:20:12.180 --> 00:20:14.220
full of energy the way he always was.

00:20:14.279 --> 00:20:17.400
Winter often wished some of his brother's

00:20:17.400 --> 00:20:19.259
confidence would spill over onto him.

00:20:19.380 --> 00:20:23.460
The 5 dragonettes set out first, flying

00:20:23.460 --> 00:20:25.079
away from the palace in 5 different

00:20:25.079 --> 00:20:25.500
directions.

00:20:25.559 --> 00:20:28.980
At their age, every hunt was still a test

00:20:28.980 --> 00:20:31.619
a chance to prove your worth, and climb

00:20:31.619 --> 00:20:32.640
higher in the rankings.

00:20:32.700 --> 00:20:34.859
Not that Hailstorm needed to climb any

00:20:34.859 --> 00:20:35.099
higher.

00:20:35.160 --> 00:20:37.619
He'd been at the very top since he was

00:20:37.619 --> 00:20:39.000
not quite 2 years old himself.

00:20:39.059 --> 00:20:41.700
He made the top of the list the same day

00:20:41.700 --> 00:20:43.799
icicle and winter hatched, in fact.

00:20:43.799 --> 00:20:46.019
Winter knew it was risky.

00:20:46.079 --> 00:20:48.539
But he decided to try flying out to sea

00:20:48.539 --> 00:20:49.019
to hunt.

00:20:49.079 --> 00:20:51.960
Sometimes polar bears could be found on

00:20:51.960 --> 00:20:54.359
the islands off the coast, or drifting on

00:20:54.359 --> 00:20:56.579
the icebergs, or swimming from one to

00:20:56.579 --> 00:20:56.819
another.

00:20:56.880 --> 00:21:00.000
He had yet to catch a polar bear after 10

00:21:00.000 --> 00:21:03.480
hunts, and as a result, his place in the

00:21:03.480 --> 00:21:05.579
rankings was lower than anyone in their

00:21:05.579 --> 00:21:06.660
family had ever been.

00:21:06.720 --> 00:21:10.680
Hailstorm killed a polar bear the 1st

00:21:10.680 --> 00:21:11.700
time we took him out hunting.

00:21:11.759 --> 00:21:15.000
His mother would observe coldly during

00:21:15.000 --> 00:21:17.940
their tense family meals, sliding a bowl

00:21:17.940 --> 00:21:19.140
of dripping meat down the table.

00:21:19.200 --> 00:21:22.619
Icicle has killed 3 so far.

00:21:22.680 --> 00:21:24.779
You obviously need to try harder.

00:21:24.839 --> 00:21:27.960
He scanned the waves for a long time

00:21:27.960 --> 00:21:30.359
hoping to see a bobbing white head.

00:21:30.420 --> 00:21:33.960
Nothing moved, except the sea itself, and

00:21:33.960 --> 00:21:35.640
the shifting reflections of the rising

00:21:35.640 --> 00:21:35.880
sun.

00:21:35.940 --> 00:21:39.180
Finally, he swerved down toward one of

00:21:39.180 --> 00:21:41.400
the larger islands, not much bigger than

00:21:41.400 --> 00:21:43.799
the ice palace, but studded with caves

00:21:43.799 --> 00:21:44.819
where bears might hide.

00:21:44.880 --> 00:21:47.279
And suddenly, there.

00:21:47.400 --> 00:21:50.339
Standing at the edge of the water, staring

00:21:50.339 --> 00:21:54.299
south, she was huge, with a yellowish

00:21:54.299 --> 00:21:56.039
tinge to her dingy white fur.

00:21:56.099 --> 00:21:58.440
The wind was blowing his scent away from

00:21:58.440 --> 00:22:00.059
her, and he was gliding.

00:22:00.119 --> 00:22:02.579
She hadn't heard him or smelled him yet.

00:22:02.640 --> 00:22:05.279
In a few heartbeats, he could be down

00:22:05.279 --> 00:22:07.440
there, sinking his claws into her

00:22:07.440 --> 00:22:07.799
shoulders.

00:22:07.920 --> 00:22:10.619
She'd put up a fight, but he would win.

00:22:10.680 --> 00:22:14.579
He'd bring home a polar bear at last, and

00:22:14.579 --> 00:22:16.799
if he hurried, it might even be him

00:22:16.799 --> 00:22:18.420
sitting next to the queen at dinner

00:22:18.420 --> 00:22:21.000
tonight, while Queen Glacier ate his

00:22:21.000 --> 00:22:21.660
polar bear.

00:22:21.720 --> 00:22:24.660
He wheeled upward, ready to dive.

00:22:24.720 --> 00:22:27.359
And then a movement caught at the corner

00:22:27.359 --> 00:22:29.640
of his eye, and he tilted his head toward

00:22:29.640 --> 00:22:30.059
the caves.

00:22:30.180 --> 00:22:34.380
A pair of tiny cubs was wobbling out onto

00:22:34.380 --> 00:22:35.579
the snow.

00:22:35.640 --> 00:22:38.339
One of them tripped and sprawled out, paws

00:22:38.339 --> 00:22:40.680
flopping every which way, and the other

00:22:40.680 --> 00:22:42.900
growled with delight and tackled him.

00:22:42.900 --> 00:22:46.079
They rolled, wrestling playfully, and

00:22:46.079 --> 00:22:47.519
their mother swung her head around to

00:22:47.519 --> 00:22:48.059
grunt at them.

00:22:48.119 --> 00:22:50.099
Winter hesitated.

00:22:50.160 --> 00:22:53.460
Don't be a fool, he told himself.

00:22:53.519 --> 00:22:55.079
Just kill them too.

00:22:55.200 --> 00:22:57.240
That's the way to impress mother and

00:22:57.240 --> 00:22:57.539
father.

00:22:57.599 --> 00:23:00.660
But there was something else watching the

00:23:00.660 --> 00:23:01.140
bears.

00:23:01.200 --> 00:23:04.619
It was well hidden, higher up among the

00:23:04.619 --> 00:23:07.559
rocks above the cave, but Winter's sharp

00:23:07.559 --> 00:23:10.140
ice wing eyes spotted it when it moved.

00:23:10.200 --> 00:23:11.640
A scavenger.

00:23:11.700 --> 00:23:13.619
A scavenger here?

00:23:13.680 --> 00:23:15.000
This far north?

00:23:15.119 --> 00:23:17.819
The creature was wrapped in so many

00:23:17.819 --> 00:23:18.180
furs.

00:23:18.299 --> 00:23:20.460
At 1st winter almost thought it was

00:23:20.460 --> 00:23:21.779
another polar bear cub.

00:23:21.839 --> 00:23:24.539
But there was no mistaking those clever

00:23:24.539 --> 00:23:27.720
thin brown paws for the great clumsy paws

00:23:27.720 --> 00:23:28.200
of bears.

00:23:28.259 --> 00:23:30.900
The scavenger was carrying a kind of

00:23:30.900 --> 00:23:33.480
rough spear, and its eyes were fixed on

00:23:33.480 --> 00:23:36.000
the polar bears, so it hadn't noticed the

00:23:36.000 --> 00:23:37.319
dragon overhead yet either.

00:23:37.380 --> 00:23:40.920
Winter scanned the island and spotted a

00:23:40.920 --> 00:23:42.900
wooden canoe that had been hauled onto

00:23:42.900 --> 00:23:43.799
the pebbly beach.

00:23:43.859 --> 00:23:46.799
How far had this scavenger traveled

00:23:46.799 --> 00:23:48.480
through the rough Arctic water?

00:23:48.599 --> 00:23:51.779
Was it hunting the bears for prey, just

00:23:51.779 --> 00:23:52.559
like winter was?

00:23:52.619 --> 00:23:55.380
If so, why wasn't it moving?

00:23:55.500 --> 00:23:58.680
Why had it lowered its spear as if it was

00:23:58.680 --> 00:23:59.400
already giving up?

00:23:59.460 --> 00:24:03.059
Winter stared intently, tracking the

00:24:03.059 --> 00:24:04.079
scavengers gaze.

00:24:04.200 --> 00:24:06.539
The way it was watching the cubs.

00:24:06.599 --> 00:24:09.839
Was it hesitating the way he had?

00:24:09.900 --> 00:24:12.359
Did it feel sorry for them too?

00:24:12.420 --> 00:24:15.299
Surely that was ridiculous.

00:24:15.480 --> 00:24:17.160
Scavengers couldn't feel pity.

00:24:17.220 --> 00:24:19.740
A hungry scavenger wouldn't spare the

00:24:19.740 --> 00:24:21.779
life of a bear just to protect her cubs.

00:24:21.839 --> 00:24:23.339
Would it?

00:24:23.400 --> 00:24:26.339
He wished he could scoop up the scavenger

00:24:26.339 --> 00:24:27.420
and study it more closely.

00:24:27.480 --> 00:24:29.700
What is wrong with you?

00:24:29.759 --> 00:24:32.759
Tundra's voice suddenly shrieked across

00:24:32.759 --> 00:24:33.240
the sky.

00:24:33.299 --> 00:24:35.640
Winter nearly leaped out of his scales.

00:24:35.700 --> 00:24:38.039
Are you hunting or sightseeing?

00:24:38.099 --> 00:24:40.440
Are you an ice wing or a rain wing?

00:24:40.500 --> 00:24:41.880
Kill that bear?

00:24:41.940 --> 00:24:45.599
Winter twisted around and saw, to his

00:24:45.599 --> 00:24:48.000
horror, that his mother, father, and

00:24:48.000 --> 00:24:50.339
uncle, were all winging toward him with

00:24:50.339 --> 00:24:51.359
disgusted expressions.

00:24:51.420 --> 00:24:54.480
Right behind them was icicle, with a

00:24:54.480 --> 00:24:56.220
polar bear carcass dangling from her

00:24:56.220 --> 00:24:56.579
claws.

00:24:56.640 --> 00:25:00.480
He dove frantically toward the bear, but

00:25:00.480 --> 00:25:02.220
the noise had alerted her to the danger

00:25:02.220 --> 00:25:04.619
and she was already charging up the slope

00:25:04.619 --> 00:25:06.480
and bundling her cubs back into the

00:25:06.480 --> 00:25:06.779
cave.

00:25:06.839 --> 00:25:10.500
Winter beat his wings and lunged with his

00:25:10.500 --> 00:25:13.140
talons outstretched, but they closed on

00:25:13.140 --> 00:25:13.740
empty air.

00:25:13.799 --> 00:25:16.440
As the 3 polar bears vanished into a

00:25:16.440 --> 00:25:19.019
narrow, stony passageway where dragons

00:25:19.019 --> 00:25:20.220
would never be able to follow.

00:25:20.220 --> 00:25:23.400
Winter scrabbled at the cave entrance for

00:25:23.400 --> 00:25:25.079
a moment, but there was nothing he could

00:25:25.079 --> 00:25:25.259
do.

00:25:25.380 --> 00:25:26.880
The bears were gone.

00:25:26.940 --> 00:25:29.940
He carefully forced himself not to look

00:25:29.940 --> 00:25:30.960
up at the scavenger.

00:25:31.019 --> 00:25:33.779
If his parents knew it was there, they'd

00:25:33.779 --> 00:25:36.119
make him kill it for the dinner feast, and

00:25:36.119 --> 00:25:37.500
for some reason he didn't want to.

00:25:37.559 --> 00:25:40.319
He couldn't imagine anyone eating those

00:25:40.319 --> 00:25:43.019
little paws, or the scavenger's head with

00:25:43.019 --> 00:25:44.220
its wide dark eyes.

00:25:44.279 --> 00:25:46.319
A shiver went through his wings.

00:25:46.440 --> 00:25:48.900
How could you let it get away?

00:25:48.960 --> 00:25:52.019
Narwhal roared, landing beside him.

00:25:52.079 --> 00:25:54.839
Winter's father slammed one talon into

00:25:54.839 --> 00:25:56.579
the side of the cliff, and a small

00:25:56.579 --> 00:25:58.799
avalanche of snow crashed over Winter's

00:25:58.799 --> 00:25:59.099
head.

00:25:59.160 --> 00:26:00.420
It was right there.

00:26:00.480 --> 00:26:02.220
No kill could be easier.

00:26:02.279 --> 00:26:04.920
Maybe he was worried about the little

00:26:04.920 --> 00:26:05.819
baby bears.

00:26:05.880 --> 00:26:08.940
Icicle offered, coming down with a thump

00:26:08.940 --> 00:26:10.859
and a splattering of bare blood.

00:26:10.920 --> 00:26:13.019
Maybe he didn't want to leave them all

00:26:13.019 --> 00:26:14.940
alone with no mummy to take care of

00:26:14.940 --> 00:26:15.180
them.

00:26:15.240 --> 00:26:16.920
Poor wittle 4 balls.

00:26:16.980 --> 00:26:19.920
Her voice was sneering and triumphant.

00:26:19.980 --> 00:26:22.799
No, winter cried.

00:26:22.859 --> 00:26:24.000
That wasn't it.

00:26:24.059 --> 00:26:26.700
I was, I was just watching for a minute.

00:26:26.759 --> 00:26:28.380
I would have gotten it if.

00:26:29.220 --> 00:26:31.319
If you hadn't been wasting time mooning

00:26:31.319 --> 00:26:33.660
around, narwhal hissed.

00:26:33.720 --> 00:26:35.339
We have to report this, you know.

00:26:35.400 --> 00:26:37.619
Your uncle saw the whole thing.

00:26:37.680 --> 00:26:40.859
Winter stared miserably at his talents.

00:26:40.920 --> 00:26:43.079
He knew his parents would have reported

00:26:43.079 --> 00:26:45.420
it anyway, even with no other witnesses.

00:26:45.480 --> 00:26:48.180
They believed in the strict ice wing

00:26:48.180 --> 00:26:49.140
codes of behavior.

00:26:49.200 --> 00:26:51.839
They agreed that the only way to make him

00:26:51.839 --> 00:26:54.359
strong was to expose all his weaknesses.

00:26:54.420 --> 00:26:58.259
Shame and fear were powerful weapons for

00:26:58.259 --> 00:26:59.700
teaching young dragonettes.

00:26:59.759 --> 00:27:01.920
If everyone was disappointed in him

00:27:01.920 --> 00:27:04.019
surely he would fight harder to prove

00:27:04.019 --> 00:27:04.500
himself.

00:27:04.559 --> 00:27:07.680
I will, he thought fiercely.

00:27:07.740 --> 00:27:09.000
I will be better.

00:27:09.059 --> 00:27:12.059
I will claw my way up the rankings.

00:27:12.119 --> 00:27:13.619
I won't make a mistake like this again.

00:27:13.740 --> 00:27:16.500
But he still did not tell his parents

00:27:16.500 --> 00:27:18.240
about the scavenger hiding nearby.

00:27:18.299 --> 00:27:21.779
He glanced back only once, as they were

00:27:21.779 --> 00:27:23.759
all swooping away, to make sure it was

00:27:23.759 --> 00:27:24.059
all right.

00:27:24.119 --> 00:27:27.720
That incident sent him down into the 5th

00:27:27.720 --> 00:27:30.180
circle, above only one year old

00:27:30.180 --> 00:27:32.400
dragonettes, in families that barely

00:27:32.400 --> 00:27:33.539
counted as aristocrats.

00:27:33.599 --> 00:27:36.180
For months, his mother had made him

00:27:36.180 --> 00:27:39.359
memorize long sagas about dragons who'd

00:27:39.359 --> 00:27:41.160
attempted the diamond trial to get back

00:27:41.160 --> 00:27:44.160
into the 1st circle, including about 100

00:27:44.160 --> 00:27:46.799
verses, speculating how gruesomely they

00:27:46.799 --> 00:27:47.220
might have died.

00:27:47.339 --> 00:27:51.000
The trial was a last resort, rarely used

00:27:51.000 --> 00:27:53.640
but she made it clear that no dragnet of

00:27:53.640 --> 00:27:56.279
hers would reach his 7th hatching day any

00:27:56.279 --> 00:27:58.980
lower than 2nd circle, even if it meant

00:27:58.980 --> 00:28:01.740
turning to an ancient mysterious, most

00:28:01.740 --> 00:28:03.000
likely deadly ritual.

00:28:03.059 --> 00:28:06.660
With that thread hanging over him, he had

00:28:06.660 --> 00:28:08.279
struggled to claw his way back up to the

00:28:08.279 --> 00:28:11.400
rankings, bit by bit, and he had tried as

00:28:11.400 --> 00:28:13.500
hard as he could for so long.

00:28:13.559 --> 00:28:17.400
And then, losing hailstorm, actually

00:28:17.400 --> 00:28:20.400
weaving hailstorm, abandoning him to his

00:28:20.400 --> 00:28:22.859
fate without a fight, had wiped out all

00:28:22.859 --> 00:28:25.380
that work, and he'd had to start all over

00:28:25.380 --> 00:28:26.700
from the 6th circle.

00:28:26.759 --> 00:28:30.180
Which I deserved, he thought.

00:28:30.240 --> 00:28:32.460
It was my fault we were on that

00:28:32.460 --> 00:28:32.880
mountain.

00:28:32.940 --> 00:28:34.559
My fault he got caught.

00:28:34.619 --> 00:28:37.380
My stupid, cowardly decision to leave him

00:28:37.380 --> 00:28:37.619
there.

00:28:37.680 --> 00:28:40.140
But everything was different now.

00:28:40.200 --> 00:28:43.799
Now he knew Hellstorm was alive, not dead

00:28:43.799 --> 00:28:44.819
as they'd all thought.

00:28:44.880 --> 00:28:47.759
Queen Scarlet still held him prisoner

00:28:47.819 --> 00:28:49.200
hidden somewhere secret.

00:28:49.259 --> 00:28:51.720
And Icicle had been bargaining for

00:28:51.720 --> 00:28:54.539
hailstorm's life before winter had ruined

00:28:54.539 --> 00:28:54.900
her plan.

00:28:54.960 --> 00:28:58.019
She'd agreed to kill the dragonettes of

00:28:58.019 --> 00:29:00.000
destiny in exchange for Hellstorm.

00:29:00.059 --> 00:29:01.920
But winter had stopped her.

00:29:01.980 --> 00:29:05.759
Which meant, if Scarlet killed Hailstorm

00:29:05.759 --> 00:29:08.279
now, it would be even more winter's

00:29:08.279 --> 00:29:08.579
fault.

00:29:08.640 --> 00:29:11.099
He clenched his talons.

00:29:11.220 --> 00:29:13.500
But maybe he could get to her before that

00:29:13.500 --> 00:29:13.799
happened.

00:29:13.859 --> 00:29:17.160
If he could find Scarlet, maybe there was

00:29:17.160 --> 00:29:18.900
still a chance to save his brother.

00:29:18.960 --> 00:29:22.619
He swiped raindrops off his face

00:29:22.619 --> 00:29:23.039
inhaling.

00:29:23.099 --> 00:29:25.440
The downpour was incessant and

00:29:25.440 --> 00:29:26.460
repulsive.

00:29:26.519 --> 00:29:28.920
He'd take a howling snowstorm over this

00:29:28.920 --> 00:29:31.500
dripping, soggy horribleness any day.

00:29:31.559 --> 00:29:34.500
The forest floor squashed between his

00:29:34.500 --> 00:29:37.319
claws, and the wet tree branches lashed

00:29:37.319 --> 00:29:39.240
his wings as they swayed in the storm.

00:29:39.359 --> 00:29:43.200
Below him, his pet scavenger stood in the

00:29:43.200 --> 00:29:45.000
open doorway of the cage winter had

00:29:45.000 --> 00:29:45.420
built.

00:29:45.660 --> 00:29:48.480
Bandit squinted up at the dragon, and the

00:29:48.480 --> 00:29:49.079
thunderstorm.

00:29:49.140 --> 00:29:52.259
I'm letting you go, Winter said

00:29:52.259 --> 00:29:52.920
impatiently.

00:29:52.980 --> 00:29:54.240
Don't just stand there.

00:29:54.299 --> 00:29:56.579
I can't carry a pet with me while I'm

00:29:56.579 --> 00:29:58.740
searching for hailstorm, especially not

00:29:58.740 --> 00:30:00.539
one that flops around moping all the

00:30:00.539 --> 00:30:01.019
time.

00:30:01.079 --> 00:30:03.900
He rattled the cage, and the scavenger

00:30:03.900 --> 00:30:04.440
flinched.

00:30:04.500 --> 00:30:08.039
Winter had spent days and days on

00:30:08.039 --> 00:30:09.900
planning and constructing this cage

00:30:09.900 --> 00:30:12.720
making it beautiful for his very 1st pet

00:30:12.720 --> 00:30:13.380
scavenger.

00:30:13.500 --> 00:30:16.980
And then, Bandit hadn't appreciated it at

00:30:16.980 --> 00:30:17.160
all.

00:30:17.220 --> 00:30:19.440
He'd never used the swing or the running

00:30:19.440 --> 00:30:19.859
wheel.

00:30:19.920 --> 00:30:22.500
Mostly he'd cowered under the furs and

00:30:22.500 --> 00:30:24.660
squeaked, or he tried to run away.

00:30:24.720 --> 00:30:27.660
Isn't this what you wanted?

00:30:27.720 --> 00:30:28.799
Winter demanded.

00:30:28.920 --> 00:30:32.279
Bandit was the most disappointing pet of

00:30:32.279 --> 00:30:32.700
all time.

00:30:32.759 --> 00:30:34.740
But winter couldn't help it.

00:30:34.799 --> 00:30:36.240
He still cared about him.

00:30:36.299 --> 00:30:39.720
Otherwise, he could have abandoned Bandit

00:30:39.720 --> 00:30:41.220
to be someone's dinner back at Jade

00:30:41.220 --> 00:30:41.579
Mountain.

00:30:41.700 --> 00:30:44.579
Winter still remembered the expression on

00:30:44.579 --> 00:30:47.279
that 1st hunter scavenger's face all

00:30:47.279 --> 00:30:50.220
these years later, the curiosity, and the

00:30:50.220 --> 00:30:51.900
dragon like sympathy in its eyes.

00:30:51.960 --> 00:30:54.779
He'd hoped to see something like that in

00:30:54.779 --> 00:30:55.319
bandit one day.

00:30:55.380 --> 00:30:57.420
But it didn't matter now.

00:30:57.480 --> 00:31:00.119
Nothing mattered, except finding

00:31:00.119 --> 00:31:00.779
Hillstorm.

00:31:00.839 --> 00:31:05.220
Go on, get out of here, Winter grumbled.

00:31:05.279 --> 00:31:08.220
He poked a bandit with one claw, but the

00:31:08.220 --> 00:31:10.440
scavenger dodged, and retreated farther

00:31:10.440 --> 00:31:12.059
into the cage, covering his head.

00:31:12.180 --> 00:31:14.880
Winter felt a flash of pity for the

00:31:14.880 --> 00:31:17.339
creature, and then felt furious with

00:31:17.339 --> 00:31:19.319
himself for caring, when there were more

00:31:19.319 --> 00:31:20.279
important things to worry about.

00:31:20.339 --> 00:31:23.759
I know it's raining, but it's better than

00:31:23.759 --> 00:31:25.140
the Ice Kingdom, trust me.

00:31:25.200 --> 00:31:27.599
If I take him with me to the ice

00:31:27.599 --> 00:31:28.079
kingdom.

00:31:28.140 --> 00:31:30.779
He'll either freeze to death or be eaten

00:31:30.779 --> 00:31:31.680
within the 1st day.

00:31:31.740 --> 00:31:34.859
Queen Glacier had granted him permission

00:31:34.859 --> 00:31:37.019
to have an exotic pet while at the

00:31:37.019 --> 00:31:39.900
academy, but where he saw an exotic pet

00:31:39.900 --> 00:31:41.759
his parents were likely to see a

00:31:41.759 --> 00:31:42.599
delicious snack.

00:31:42.660 --> 00:31:47.400
Winter, he heard a voice yell, somewhere

00:31:47.400 --> 00:31:48.539
off in the trees.

00:31:48.599 --> 00:31:51.480
A plume of fire lit up the faces of 4

00:31:51.480 --> 00:31:53.640
dragons, hurrying toward him through the

00:31:53.640 --> 00:31:53.940
forest.

00:31:54.000 --> 00:31:56.940
To his astonishment, it was the rest of

00:31:56.940 --> 00:31:58.380
his winglet from the Jade Mountain

00:31:58.380 --> 00:31:58.859
Academy.

00:31:58.920 --> 00:32:03.359
Kibley, Turtle, Kinkajoo, and Moon.

00:32:03.359 --> 00:32:06.000
He pushed back against the little jump

00:32:06.000 --> 00:32:07.799
that his heart made when he saw her.

00:32:07.859 --> 00:32:10.019
Just what I need right now.

00:32:10.079 --> 00:32:12.539
A bunch of glaciers slowing me down.

00:32:12.599 --> 00:32:15.539
By all the snow monsters.

00:32:15.599 --> 00:32:16.500
What are you doing here?

00:32:16.559 --> 00:32:17.940
Winter demanded.

00:32:18.059 --> 00:32:19.740
How had they even found him?

00:32:19.799 --> 00:32:20.519
And why?

00:32:20.579 --> 00:32:22.980
Looking for you?

00:32:23.099 --> 00:32:24.480
Moon said simply.

00:32:24.539 --> 00:32:27.660
Her eyes caught on his, shining in the

00:32:27.660 --> 00:32:29.160
bits of moonlight that fought through the

00:32:29.160 --> 00:32:29.880
storm clouds.

00:32:29.940 --> 00:32:32.339
She always looked at him as if she could

00:32:32.339 --> 00:32:33.839
see more of him than anyone else.

00:32:33.960 --> 00:32:37.259
As if she saw dazzling mountain peaks

00:32:37.259 --> 00:32:39.539
whereas parents saw nothing but a lump of

00:32:39.539 --> 00:32:40.079
gray ice.

00:32:40.140 --> 00:32:43.680
And we found you, Kinkachu added.

00:32:43.740 --> 00:32:44.819
We're amazing.

00:32:44.880 --> 00:32:47.940
She flapped her wings as Kibley sent out

00:32:47.940 --> 00:32:50.339
another burst of flame, and Winter could

00:32:50.339 --> 00:32:51.660
see that she had turned bright yellow

00:32:51.660 --> 00:32:52.859
with purple spots.

00:32:52.920 --> 00:32:54.779
Ridiculous.

00:32:54.839 --> 00:32:58.079
That's what rain wings were, all of them

00:32:58.079 --> 00:33:01.019
flamboyant and ridiculous, with their

00:33:01.019 --> 00:33:03.000
feelings splattered all over their scales

00:33:03.000 --> 00:33:03.420
like that.

00:33:03.480 --> 00:33:05.519
It was embarrassing to be around.

00:33:05.640 --> 00:33:08.160
Winter glanced down at Bandit.

00:33:08.220 --> 00:33:10.619
He couldn't let these dragons distract

00:33:10.619 --> 00:33:10.920
him.

00:33:10.980 --> 00:33:14.279
I'm not going back to Jade Mountain, he

00:33:14.279 --> 00:33:16.859
said firmly, no matter what they said

00:33:16.859 --> 00:33:17.819
they wouldn't change his mind.

00:33:17.880 --> 00:33:20.039
I'm going to look for my brother.

00:33:20.099 --> 00:33:23.279
I thought so, Moon said.

00:33:23.400 --> 00:33:26.160
Her voice quiet, but as determined as

00:33:26.160 --> 00:33:26.400
his.

00:33:26.460 --> 00:33:28.380
We want to help you.

00:33:28.440 --> 00:33:30.059
We do?

00:33:30.180 --> 00:33:32.519
Turtle said, stamping his feet.

00:33:32.579 --> 00:33:34.980
Yes, Kinkachu said.

00:33:35.039 --> 00:33:37.200
I didn't know we did, but now I totally

00:33:37.200 --> 00:33:37.619
do.

00:33:37.680 --> 00:33:40.019
No way.

00:33:40.140 --> 00:33:41.160
Absolutely not.

00:33:41.220 --> 00:33:42.779
I can't be around them.

00:33:42.839 --> 00:33:44.339
Not even moon.

00:33:44.400 --> 00:33:47.279
I mean, especially Moon.

00:33:47.339 --> 00:33:51.480
He saw Kibley staring intently at him, as

00:33:51.480 --> 00:33:53.039
though the sand wing was figuring out his

00:33:53.039 --> 00:33:53.460
next move.

00:33:53.579 --> 00:33:56.339
Ghibli had done that all the time in a

00:33:56.339 --> 00:33:58.740
cave they shared on Jade Mountain, and it

00:33:58.740 --> 00:34:00.480
had been very unsettling to live with.

00:34:00.539 --> 00:34:03.240
Winter could just imagine what it would

00:34:03.240 --> 00:34:05.700
be like to have the sand wings black eyes

00:34:05.700 --> 00:34:07.980
inspecting everything he did on the path

00:34:07.980 --> 00:34:09.179
to finding hailstorm.

00:34:09.239 --> 00:34:12.539
You can't come with me, he said.

00:34:12.659 --> 00:34:14.459
I'm going to Queen Glacier.

00:34:14.519 --> 00:34:17.340
I need to explain it all to her and get

00:34:17.340 --> 00:34:18.840
her to help me find Hellstorm.

00:34:18.900 --> 00:34:21.480
Perhaps you would give him a wing of

00:34:21.480 --> 00:34:22.860
soldiers of his own to command.

00:34:22.920 --> 00:34:25.260
Or perhaps she would send out all her

00:34:25.260 --> 00:34:27.539
warrior dragons to search for Hailstorm.

00:34:27.599 --> 00:34:30.480
Regardless, he knew he needed the power

00:34:30.480 --> 00:34:32.099
of the ice wing queen to save his

00:34:32.099 --> 00:34:32.340
brother.

00:34:32.400 --> 00:34:35.760
That was the smart thing to do, wasn't

00:34:35.760 --> 00:34:35.880
it?

00:34:35.940 --> 00:34:38.699
Wouldn't it make more sense to go to the

00:34:38.699 --> 00:34:39.539
Sky Kingdom?

00:34:39.599 --> 00:34:40.920
Kinkachu asked.

00:34:40.980 --> 00:34:42.960
Your brother must be imprisoned there

00:34:42.960 --> 00:34:43.679
somewhere, right?

00:34:43.739 --> 00:34:46.799
We can all look for him in like all the

00:34:46.799 --> 00:34:47.819
mountain caves or something.

00:34:47.880 --> 00:34:51.539
Or you could go after icicle, Kibley

00:34:51.539 --> 00:34:51.840
said.

00:34:51.900 --> 00:34:53.880
Try to find out more about what Scarlett

00:34:53.880 --> 00:34:54.239
told her.

00:34:54.300 --> 00:34:58.019
This was exactly what he didn't want, more

00:34:58.019 --> 00:35:00.539
options, more doubt.

00:35:00.599 --> 00:35:01.679
Kibley was right.

00:35:01.739 --> 00:35:04.380
Icicle was the only one who knew anything

00:35:04.380 --> 00:35:05.880
about Hellstorm and Scarlet.

00:35:05.940 --> 00:35:09.539
Following Icicle would make sense, except

00:35:09.539 --> 00:35:12.119
I don't know where she's gone.

00:35:12.239 --> 00:35:13.980
Winter said bitterly.

00:35:14.039 --> 00:35:16.440
Back to the Ice Kingdom, he hoped.

00:35:16.500 --> 00:35:18.780
Although she had to know Queen Glacier

00:35:18.780 --> 00:35:20.400
would be furious about her breaking the

00:35:20.400 --> 00:35:21.420
Jade Mountain truce.

00:35:21.480 --> 00:35:24.719
I have a guess, Kibley said.

00:35:24.780 --> 00:35:26.280
Of course he did.

00:35:26.340 --> 00:35:29.880
You won't like it, though, he added

00:35:29.880 --> 00:35:31.260
nodding at Kinkachoo.

00:35:31.320 --> 00:35:33.300
I think she's gone to the rainforest.

00:35:33.360 --> 00:35:35.880
She knows the one Scarlet hates the most

00:35:35.880 --> 00:35:36.659
is glory.

00:35:36.719 --> 00:35:38.219
Everyone knows that.

00:35:38.280 --> 00:35:40.619
If they know the story of what glory did

00:35:40.619 --> 00:35:41.159
to her face.

00:35:41.219 --> 00:35:44.460
So I think Isaacle might think that if

00:35:44.460 --> 00:35:47.039
she kills glory, Scarlet will forgive her

00:35:47.039 --> 00:35:48.179
for failing to kill the others.

00:35:48.300 --> 00:35:51.059
Nobody spoke for a long moment.

00:35:51.179 --> 00:35:55.500
Thrice cursed moons, Winter thought.

00:35:55.559 --> 00:35:56.519
He's right.

00:35:56.579 --> 00:35:58.500
That's exactly what she would think.

00:35:58.559 --> 00:36:02.099
Icicle is brilliant, dangerous, and

00:36:02.099 --> 00:36:03.059
prefers to hunt alone.

00:36:03.119 --> 00:36:05.579
She would find a way to solve this

00:36:05.579 --> 00:36:07.500
problem instead of running for help.

00:36:07.559 --> 00:36:10.199
Thunder rumbled overhead.

00:36:10.260 --> 00:36:14.579
Then I'm going to the rainforest, Kinkachu

00:36:14.579 --> 00:36:15.300
said fiercely.

00:36:15.360 --> 00:36:17.519
I'm not letting her kill my awesome

00:36:17.519 --> 00:36:17.880
queen.

00:36:17.940 --> 00:36:21.480
Suddenly moon let out a yell of pain. and

00:36:21.480 --> 00:36:23.820
crumpled forward, her wings collapsing

00:36:23.820 --> 00:36:24.179
around her.

00:36:24.239 --> 00:36:27.360
Winter stepped toward her, but Kinkachu

00:36:27.360 --> 00:36:29.400
was faster, catching the night wing in

00:36:29.400 --> 00:36:29.760
her wings.

00:36:29.820 --> 00:36:31.260
Moon?

00:36:31.320 --> 00:36:33.659
She cried, staggering sideways.

00:36:33.719 --> 00:36:36.960
A flash of lightning lit up Moon's face

00:36:36.960 --> 00:36:39.659
as the black dragon lifted her snout to

00:36:39.659 --> 00:36:40.199
the sky.

00:36:40.199 --> 00:36:42.780
Something blank and weird had taken over

00:36:42.780 --> 00:36:45.119
her eyes, like frost on a lake.

00:36:45.239 --> 00:36:48.659
And then she began to speak, in a voice

00:36:48.659 --> 00:36:49.500
nothing like her own.

00:36:49.559 --> 00:36:53.340
Beware the darkness of dragons.

00:36:53.400 --> 00:36:56.159
Beware the stalker of dreams.

00:36:56.219 --> 00:36:59.760
Beware the talons of power and fire.

00:36:59.820 --> 00:37:03.300
Beware one who is not what she seems.

00:37:03.420 --> 00:37:06.420
Something is coming to shake the earth.

00:37:06.480 --> 00:37:09.119
Something is coming to scorch the

00:37:09.119 --> 00:37:09.539
ground.

00:37:09.659 --> 00:37:12.719
Jade Mountain will fall beneath thunder

00:37:12.719 --> 00:37:17.760
and ice, unless, unless the lost city of

00:37:17.760 --> 00:37:20.099
night can be found.

00:37:20.159 --> 00:37:24.659
The voice lurched to a stop, and Moon

00:37:24.659 --> 00:37:26.880
closed her eyes, releasing all the

00:37:26.880 --> 00:37:27.840
tension out of her wings.

00:37:27.900 --> 00:37:31.559
Everyone stared at her, Winter's heart

00:37:31.559 --> 00:37:33.239
was hammering, like the pelting

00:37:33.239 --> 00:37:34.139
raindrops.

00:37:34.199 --> 00:37:35.219
Those words.

00:37:35.340 --> 00:37:38.039
That couldn't be what it sounded like

00:37:38.039 --> 00:37:38.460
could it?

00:37:38.519 --> 00:37:41.340
By all the snakes.

00:37:41.400 --> 00:37:43.139
Kibley said at last.

00:37:43.199 --> 00:37:46.139
Winter met his eyes in the next flash of

00:37:46.139 --> 00:37:46.500
lightning.

00:37:46.559 --> 00:37:50.340
Kibley looked as terrified as he felt, as

00:37:50.340 --> 00:37:51.780
shaken as he'd been the day of the

00:37:51.780 --> 00:37:53.460
explosion in their history class.

00:37:53.519 --> 00:37:55.019
What was that?

00:37:55.079 --> 00:37:58.380
That's what you've been muttering in your

00:37:58.380 --> 00:38:00.840
sleep, Kinkachu said to Moon.

00:38:00.900 --> 00:38:03.960
It sounded like a prophecy.

00:38:04.019 --> 00:38:07.380
Winter said slowly, but it couldn't be.

00:38:07.440 --> 00:38:09.900
The Night Wings had sworn to everyone

00:38:09.900 --> 00:38:11.219
that their powers were gone.

00:38:11.340 --> 00:38:14.820
Tsunami, sunny, Starflight, clay, and

00:38:14.820 --> 00:38:16.260
glory had confirmed it.

00:38:16.320 --> 00:38:17.940
No more mind reading.

00:38:18.000 --> 00:38:20.400
No more prophecies.

00:38:20.460 --> 00:38:21.659
Ever again.

00:38:21.719 --> 00:38:24.059
That was what they'd said.

00:38:24.119 --> 00:38:24.360
Exactly.

00:38:24.480 --> 00:38:26.579
So someone was lying.

00:38:26.639 --> 00:38:27.960
But who?

00:38:28.019 --> 00:38:31.139
Moon shook her head and pressed herself

00:38:31.139 --> 00:38:33.000
upright, her wings unsteady.

00:38:33.059 --> 00:38:35.940
Turtle, she said.

00:38:36.000 --> 00:38:38.039
Please give him one of the rocks.

00:38:38.099 --> 00:38:41.579
The sea wing fumbled with the arm band he

00:38:41.579 --> 00:38:42.059
always wore.

00:38:42.119 --> 00:38:44.340
Winter could see that a couple of the

00:38:44.340 --> 00:38:46.739
black stones were missing from it, and as

00:38:46.739 --> 00:38:49.079
he watched, Turtle pried out another one

00:38:49.079 --> 00:38:50.280
and passed it to Winter.

00:38:50.400 --> 00:38:53.639
The stone was small, about the size of a

00:38:53.639 --> 00:38:56.340
dragon's tooth, and had a strange sheen

00:38:56.340 --> 00:38:58.739
to it, although that might have been the

00:38:58.739 --> 00:39:01.019
effect of the rain and the lightning, it

00:39:01.019 --> 00:39:02.940
was jagged around the edges, but not

00:39:02.940 --> 00:39:03.300
sharp.

00:39:03.420 --> 00:39:05.820
It looked fairly ordinary.

00:39:05.820 --> 00:39:07.739
What's this?

00:39:07.739 --> 00:39:08.699
he asked.

00:39:08.760 --> 00:39:10.559
What does this have to do with

00:39:10.559 --> 00:39:11.280
prophecies?

00:39:11.340 --> 00:39:16.019
I have a lot to explain, Moon said.

00:39:16.079 --> 00:39:18.960
She sounded nervous, as though he might

00:39:18.960 --> 00:39:21.179
stab her with his tail spikes any moment

00:39:21.179 --> 00:39:23.639
which he'd refrained from doing to anyone

00:39:23.639 --> 00:39:25.739
so far, so he thought that was rather

00:39:25.739 --> 00:39:26.219
unfair.

00:39:26.280 --> 00:39:28.320
Everything.

00:39:28.380 --> 00:39:29.940
The whole truth.

00:39:30.000 --> 00:39:32.039
I'm going to tell you everything.

00:39:32.099 --> 00:39:36.900
That sounds ominous, Winter said.

00:39:36.960 --> 00:39:40.679
No more ominous then, Jade Mountain will

00:39:40.679 --> 00:39:43.320
fall beneath thunder and ice, Kibley

00:39:43.320 --> 00:39:43.500
said.

00:39:43.559 --> 00:39:45.420
I hope we're all planning to talk about

00:39:45.420 --> 00:39:48.539
that, because I'm extremely unsettled

00:39:48.539 --> 00:39:48.780
right now.

00:39:48.840 --> 00:39:52.500
She said we have to find the lost city of

00:39:52.500 --> 00:39:54.179
night, Kinkachu said.

00:39:54.239 --> 00:39:56.699
That's all, and then everything will be

00:39:56.699 --> 00:39:57.780
fine, right?

00:39:57.840 --> 00:39:59.820
Isn't that what everyone else heard?

00:39:59.880 --> 00:40:01.920
I'm pretty sure.

00:40:01.920 --> 00:40:04.199
I heard that we're all going to die

00:40:04.199 --> 00:40:05.639
Turtles said.

00:40:05.699 --> 00:40:08.880
Death, death, monsters everywhere, death.

00:40:08.940 --> 00:40:10.679
Is that it?

00:40:10.739 --> 00:40:12.300
Kibli Ass Moon.

00:40:12.360 --> 00:40:13.380
Is that what you saw?

00:40:13.440 --> 00:40:15.599
Jade Mountain is going to fall on us

00:40:15.599 --> 00:40:15.840
all?

00:40:15.900 --> 00:40:18.960
I don't know, Moon said.

00:40:19.019 --> 00:40:21.780
I've had visions, but none of them ever

00:40:21.780 --> 00:40:23.400
came out in words like that before.

00:40:23.519 --> 00:40:25.380
I don't know what it means.

00:40:25.440 --> 00:40:27.840
Visions.

00:40:27.900 --> 00:40:30.179
Winter didn't like the sound of that.

00:40:30.239 --> 00:40:32.699
He closed his claws around the rock

00:40:32.699 --> 00:40:35.760
frowning at her, but Moon had gone quiet

00:40:35.760 --> 00:40:38.699
staring into the dark as though she were

00:40:38.699 --> 00:40:39.300
hearing something else.

00:40:39.360 --> 00:40:42.840
A few moments passed, and then she seemed

00:40:42.840 --> 00:40:44.039
to snap back into herself.

00:40:44.099 --> 00:40:46.739
Winter, she said.

00:40:46.800 --> 00:40:49.260
There are a few things you need to know

00:40:49.260 --> 00:40:49.679
about me.

00:40:49.739 --> 00:40:52.800
I'm listening, he said.

00:40:52.860 --> 00:40:55.079
Not that I have a choice, apparently.

00:40:55.139 --> 00:40:58.139
It's true what you've heard about the

00:40:58.139 --> 00:40:59.639
Night Wings, she said.

00:40:59.699 --> 00:41:02.099
They really have lost their powers.

00:41:02.159 --> 00:41:04.800
There hasn't been a night wing who could

00:41:04.800 --> 00:41:09.239
read minds or see the future in, well, a

00:41:09.239 --> 00:41:09.840
very long time.

00:41:09.900 --> 00:41:12.119
She took a deep breath.

00:41:12.179 --> 00:41:14.219
Until me.

00:41:14.340 --> 00:41:17.159
Winter's tail twitched.

00:41:17.219 --> 00:41:19.679
His heart felt like the rock in his

00:41:19.679 --> 00:41:21.599
talons, small and hard.

00:41:21.659 --> 00:41:25.679
Because I hatched in the rainforest, she

00:41:25.679 --> 00:41:26.039
went on.

00:41:26.099 --> 00:41:29.579
Under 2 full moons, I can do both.

00:41:29.639 --> 00:41:31.559
Both what?

00:41:31.679 --> 00:41:34.559
He forced out past the claws that seemed

00:41:34.559 --> 00:41:36.119
to be closing around his throat.

00:41:36.179 --> 00:41:38.579
See visions of the future.

00:41:38.639 --> 00:41:41.460
She said, then hesitated.

00:41:41.519 --> 00:41:44.820
And read minds.

00:41:44.880 --> 00:41:49.079
Chapter 2.

00:41:49.320 --> 00:41:51.539
No.

00:41:51.599 --> 00:41:54.599
Thunder rumbled through the dark clouds

00:41:54.599 --> 00:41:56.460
like boulders sliding down a mountain.

00:41:56.519 --> 00:41:59.219
What had Moon seen in his mind?

00:41:59.280 --> 00:42:00.420
What did she know?

00:42:00.480 --> 00:42:02.940
Did she know that he felt?

00:42:03.000 --> 00:42:05.519
That he'd been thinking about her?

00:42:05.579 --> 00:42:08.400
Her eyes and the way she tilted her

00:42:08.400 --> 00:42:08.639
head?

00:42:08.699 --> 00:42:11.400
Her claws that could gently shield his

00:42:11.400 --> 00:42:13.800
scavenger one moment, and rip apart a

00:42:13.800 --> 00:42:14.519
goat the next?

00:42:14.639 --> 00:42:17.159
The way she stood up to him the 1st time

00:42:17.159 --> 00:42:17.699
they met?

00:42:17.820 --> 00:42:20.280
But looked at him as though he was worth

00:42:20.280 --> 00:42:20.940
listening to.

00:42:21.000 --> 00:42:24.000
She must know that he thought about her

00:42:24.000 --> 00:42:24.539
all the time.

00:42:24.659 --> 00:42:26.940
Stop thinking about it.

00:42:27.000 --> 00:42:27.840
Don't think it.

00:42:27.900 --> 00:42:29.159
Don't let her see anymore.

00:42:29.219 --> 00:42:32.820
But you're safe now, I promise, she said

00:42:32.820 --> 00:42:33.420
quickly.

00:42:33.480 --> 00:42:35.519
Reaching toward him as he leaped back.

00:42:35.579 --> 00:42:37.739
The rock you're holding?

00:42:37.800 --> 00:42:39.119
It's Skyfire.

00:42:39.179 --> 00:42:41.340
It can shield your thoughts for me.

00:42:41.400 --> 00:42:43.679
As long as you're holding it or wearing

00:42:43.679 --> 00:42:46.199
it close to your scales, I can't hear

00:42:46.199 --> 00:42:47.099
anything you're thinking.

00:42:47.159 --> 00:42:51.420
Sounds like another nightwing lie, Winter

00:42:51.420 --> 00:42:51.900
snarled.

00:42:51.960 --> 00:42:54.000
What have you seen in my head?

00:42:54.119 --> 00:42:55.860
He thought fiercely.

00:42:55.920 --> 00:42:59.280
Moon wiped raindrops from her eyes and

00:42:59.280 --> 00:43:00.360
took a deep breath.

00:43:00.420 --> 00:43:02.579
I promise you, Winter.

00:43:02.639 --> 00:43:04.980
I can't hear anything in your mind right

00:43:04.980 --> 00:43:05.219
now.

00:43:05.280 --> 00:43:09.840
And even before, it was very... confusing.

00:43:09.900 --> 00:43:11.760
Behind her.

00:43:11.820 --> 00:43:14.400
Kibli let out a snort that sounded a bit

00:43:14.400 --> 00:43:15.900
too amused.

00:43:15.960 --> 00:43:18.480
That's how I knew about Icicle and

00:43:18.480 --> 00:43:20.159
Scarlet, Moon said.

00:43:20.219 --> 00:43:22.739
I heard them talking in icicle's dream.

00:43:22.800 --> 00:43:25.380
And I heard Icicle planning to kill

00:43:25.380 --> 00:43:27.420
Starflight on her way to the library.

00:43:27.480 --> 00:43:29.820
But I can only hear what dragons are

00:43:29.820 --> 00:43:31.260
thinking right at that moment.

00:43:31.320 --> 00:43:34.260
I can't reach in and rummage around in

00:43:34.260 --> 00:43:35.699
anyone's brain or anything like that.

00:43:35.760 --> 00:43:39.059
Winter found this image not very

00:43:39.059 --> 00:43:40.079
reassuring at all.

00:43:40.139 --> 00:43:43.019
You've been listening to us from the

00:43:43.019 --> 00:43:46.619
moment you met us, he said. deceiving us

00:43:46.619 --> 00:43:47.880
spying on us.

00:43:47.940 --> 00:43:51.000
He hissed out a wisp of frost breath

00:43:51.000 --> 00:43:53.039
turning the raindrops around him into

00:43:53.039 --> 00:43:55.380
tiny chunks of ice that clattered to the

00:43:55.380 --> 00:43:55.559
ground.

00:43:55.619 --> 00:43:58.199
I should have expected as much from a

00:43:58.199 --> 00:43:58.800
night wing.

00:43:58.860 --> 00:44:01.619
But not from this night wing.

00:44:01.619 --> 00:44:03.480
He thought moon was different.

00:44:03.599 --> 00:44:06.119
He'd begun to think she might be the only

00:44:06.119 --> 00:44:07.739
night wing in the world he could trust.

00:44:07.860 --> 00:44:11.579
And the whole time, she'd been lying, and

00:44:11.579 --> 00:44:14.400
snooping around in his thoughts, he must

00:44:14.400 --> 00:44:16.380
be the most dim witted dragon who'd ever

00:44:16.380 --> 00:44:17.340
lived.

00:44:17.400 --> 00:44:19.260
I shouldn't have let my guard down.

00:44:19.320 --> 00:44:21.840
I've always been taught that nightwings

00:44:21.840 --> 00:44:24.119
are conniving underhanded backstabbers.

00:44:24.239 --> 00:44:26.579
I know the history of what they did to

00:44:26.579 --> 00:44:26.820
us.

00:44:26.880 --> 00:44:29.159
This is just more proof of that.

00:44:29.219 --> 00:44:33.000
Go back to Jade Mountain, all of you

00:44:33.000 --> 00:44:33.900
Winter said.

00:44:33.960 --> 00:44:34.980
Leave me alone.

00:44:35.039 --> 00:44:38.039
He turned to the cage where his scavenger

00:44:38.039 --> 00:44:40.380
was still standing, staring mournfully

00:44:40.380 --> 00:44:41.099
out of the rain.

00:44:41.159 --> 00:44:43.860
And you, get out of here.

00:44:43.980 --> 00:44:46.199
He roared as loud as he could.

00:44:46.260 --> 00:44:49.320
Bandit stumbled back with a cry of terror

00:44:49.320 --> 00:44:50.940
then bolted out of the cage.

00:44:51.000 --> 00:44:53.280
The little creature tripped and sprawled

00:44:53.280 --> 00:44:55.440
on the wet leaves, scrambled upright

00:44:55.440 --> 00:44:57.480
again, and went galloping off into the

00:44:57.480 --> 00:44:57.960
dark forest.

00:44:58.019 --> 00:45:01.679
Winter saw the look on Moon's face as she

00:45:01.679 --> 00:45:02.820
watched Bandit go.

00:45:02.880 --> 00:45:06.539
Sympathetic, pitying, curious.

00:45:06.599 --> 00:45:08.820
No one else had ever been as interested

00:45:08.820 --> 00:45:10.260
in scavengers as he was.

00:45:10.320 --> 00:45:13.559
He curled his talons around the Skyfire

00:45:13.559 --> 00:45:13.920
Rock.

00:45:13.980 --> 00:45:16.320
I mean it, go away.

00:45:16.380 --> 00:45:19.079
I'm going to the Ice Kingdom, and if you

00:45:19.079 --> 00:45:20.519
follow me, you'll die.

00:45:20.579 --> 00:45:22.679
He paused for a moment.

00:45:22.739 --> 00:45:25.139
Not that I have any objection to your

00:45:25.139 --> 00:45:26.579
debts just to be clear.

00:45:26.639 --> 00:45:28.800
I just don't want to listen to you all

00:45:28.800 --> 00:45:30.659
breathing and flapping and saying stupid

00:45:30.659 --> 00:45:31.559
things all the way there.

00:45:31.619 --> 00:45:36.539
That can't be your plan, Kibley said.

00:45:36.599 --> 00:45:39.719
The sandwing was using his annoying, let's

00:45:39.719 --> 00:45:41.820
be sensible about this voice.

00:45:41.880 --> 00:45:43.619
Go home and beg for help.

00:45:43.739 --> 00:45:45.480
By the time you get there.

00:45:45.539 --> 00:45:46.739
Your brother might be dead.

00:45:46.800 --> 00:45:49.500
Your best chance is to catch icicle.

00:45:49.559 --> 00:45:53.760
Before she kills Queen Glory, Kinkachu

00:45:53.760 --> 00:45:54.360
said fiercely.

00:45:54.420 --> 00:45:57.000
The little rain wing was now a mango

00:45:57.000 --> 00:45:59.400
orange color, with streaks of black along

00:45:59.400 --> 00:45:59.940
her wings.

00:46:00.059 --> 00:46:02.219
She looked ready to fly into battle.

00:46:02.280 --> 00:46:05.760
But Icicle was a deadly warrior who could

00:46:05.760 --> 00:46:08.340
kill a vegetarian rainforest dragon with

00:46:08.340 --> 00:46:09.119
a snap of her tail.

00:46:09.179 --> 00:46:12.000
I don't need help from any of you.

00:46:12.059 --> 00:46:14.940
He growled, especially you.

00:46:15.000 --> 00:46:18.480
He threw a glare at Moon, who folded her

00:46:18.480 --> 00:46:20.639
wings closer around herself, but didn't

00:46:20.639 --> 00:46:20.880
look away.

00:46:20.940 --> 00:46:25.019
You do, actually. said Kibley.

00:46:25.079 --> 00:46:27.300
You won't get 2 steps into the rainforest

00:46:27.300 --> 00:46:27.960
without our help.

00:46:28.019 --> 00:46:30.360
It's full of night wings now, and

00:46:30.360 --> 00:46:32.280
everyone knows they don't like ice

00:46:32.280 --> 00:46:32.760
wings.

00:46:32.880 --> 00:46:36.300
And if you find Scarlet, Do you think

00:46:36.300 --> 00:46:37.500
she'll just tell you where your brother

00:46:37.500 --> 00:46:37.860
is?

00:46:37.920 --> 00:46:40.739
Wouldn't it be useful and much more

00:46:40.739 --> 00:46:42.900
efficient to have a mind reader with

00:46:42.900 --> 00:46:43.260
you?

00:46:43.320 --> 00:46:46.559
Oh, is that what you are now?

00:46:46.619 --> 00:46:48.300
Winter asked Moon.

00:46:48.420 --> 00:46:51.239
A clever tool that can be used by whoever

00:46:51.239 --> 00:46:52.139
needs some quick answers.

00:46:52.199 --> 00:46:56.880
I won't let anyone use me, she said with

00:46:56.880 --> 00:46:57.659
a flash of anger.

00:46:57.719 --> 00:47:00.659
But if I can do something good with this

00:47:00.659 --> 00:47:03.480
this gift I didn't ask for.

00:47:03.539 --> 00:47:06.059
Then yes, I'll do it.

00:47:06.119 --> 00:47:10.139
Um, turtle interjected.

00:47:10.199 --> 00:47:13.019
Winter shifted his glare to the sea wing

00:47:13.019 --> 00:47:15.300
who had been quietly pacing in circles

00:47:15.300 --> 00:47:17.219
splashing through the puddles with his

00:47:17.219 --> 00:47:18.119
huge talons.

00:47:18.179 --> 00:47:21.480
Excuse me, what about the creepy

00:47:21.480 --> 00:47:22.079
prophecy?

00:47:22.139 --> 00:47:23.880
Is Jade Mountain in danger?

00:47:23.940 --> 00:47:27.599
Shouldn't we, you know, warn someone?

00:47:27.659 --> 00:47:31.019
I'm not worried, Kinkachu said.

00:47:31.079 --> 00:47:33.360
We know where the lost city of night is.

00:47:33.420 --> 00:47:35.340
The Night Wings abandoned it when the

00:47:35.340 --> 00:47:37.619
volcano erupted, but we can still get to

00:47:37.619 --> 00:47:39.000
the island from the rainforest.

00:47:39.059 --> 00:47:39.900
That's easy.

00:47:39.960 --> 00:47:43.019
So we go to the Lost City, and then all

00:47:43.019 --> 00:47:45.239
those awful things won't happen, and Jade

00:47:45.239 --> 00:47:46.739
Mountain will be fine, right?

00:47:46.860 --> 00:47:48.539
Nothing to panic about.

00:47:48.599 --> 00:47:51.300
Kimley let out a plume of fire

00:47:51.300 --> 00:47:53.699
illuminating Moon's doubtful expression.

00:47:53.820 --> 00:47:56.940
I don't think it's that simple, she

00:47:56.940 --> 00:47:57.179
said.

00:47:57.239 --> 00:48:00.119
The things I saw when the words came.

00:48:00.179 --> 00:48:03.239
The things I see in my nightmares.

00:48:03.300 --> 00:48:06.420
I can't imagine that just visiting the

00:48:06.420 --> 00:48:08.760
volcanic island could stop any of that

00:48:08.760 --> 00:48:09.300
from happening.

00:48:09.360 --> 00:48:12.539
Well, let's try it and see.

00:48:12.659 --> 00:48:15.239
Kingaju said enthusiastically.

00:48:15.420 --> 00:48:19.860
But if it doesn't work, Turtles said

00:48:19.860 --> 00:48:23.219
fidgeting nervously with his claws, all

00:48:23.219 --> 00:48:25.860
those dragons at Jade Mountain, my

00:48:25.860 --> 00:48:29.880
sisters, Hey, I agree with you, Kibley

00:48:29.880 --> 00:48:30.179
said.

00:48:30.239 --> 00:48:32.340
I'm completely feeling the doom right

00:48:32.340 --> 00:48:32.519
now.

00:48:32.639 --> 00:48:34.619
But do you think anyone will believe

00:48:34.619 --> 00:48:34.860
her?

00:48:34.980 --> 00:48:36.599
He nodded at Moon.

00:48:36.719 --> 00:48:38.880
When they've been told the Nightwings

00:48:38.880 --> 00:48:39.719
have no powers now?

00:48:39.780 --> 00:48:43.079
Sonny will, Kinkachu said.

00:48:43.139 --> 00:48:44.579
Tsunami might not.

00:48:44.639 --> 00:48:46.679
She doesn't like prophecies much.

00:48:46.739 --> 00:48:48.659
And then what?

00:48:48.719 --> 00:48:51.599
Shut down the whole school based on a

00:48:51.599 --> 00:48:52.739
maybe prophecy?

00:48:52.800 --> 00:48:54.239
Kibley went on.

00:48:54.300 --> 00:48:55.619
I don't think they'll do that.

00:48:55.679 --> 00:48:58.440
Besides, winter's problem is urgent.

00:48:58.500 --> 00:49:00.780
We have to find his brother before

00:49:00.780 --> 00:49:01.860
Scarlet kills him.

00:49:01.920 --> 00:49:03.360
So I vote.

00:49:03.420 --> 00:49:05.820
We do that now, and deal with the

00:49:05.820 --> 00:49:07.320
impending apocalypse afterward.

00:49:07.380 --> 00:49:10.260
Me too, Moon said.

00:49:10.320 --> 00:49:13.260
What in the world made these dragons

00:49:13.260 --> 00:49:15.659
think his problem was their problem?

00:49:15.719 --> 00:49:18.780
Finding Hailstorm was urgent to winter

00:49:18.780 --> 00:49:22.019
but it made no sense for any not ice

00:49:22.019 --> 00:49:23.340
wings to get involved at all.

00:49:23.400 --> 00:49:26.639
Winter narrowed his eyes at Turtle

00:49:26.639 --> 00:49:28.920
dripping forlornly into the puddles

00:49:28.920 --> 00:49:29.639
around his claws.

00:49:29.699 --> 00:49:32.519
It was easy to forget that the sea wing

00:49:32.519 --> 00:49:34.920
was a royal prince as well, the son of

00:49:34.920 --> 00:49:35.940
Queen Coral.

00:49:36.059 --> 00:49:38.519
He never acted like royalty.

00:49:38.579 --> 00:49:41.280
Instead, Turtle behaved as though he

00:49:41.280 --> 00:49:43.860
didn't want to be noticed at all, mumbly

00:49:43.860 --> 00:49:46.079
sticking to the background, agreeing to

00:49:46.079 --> 00:49:46.440
anything.

00:49:46.440 --> 00:49:48.420
Was he afraid of something?

00:49:48.480 --> 00:49:50.340
Or just boring.

00:49:50.400 --> 00:49:53.940
If an ice wing acted the way turtle does

00:49:53.940 --> 00:49:56.340
he'd be stuck in the 7th circle forever.

00:49:56.400 --> 00:49:59.340
Which meant winter could get rid of him

00:49:59.340 --> 00:50:00.480
by applying the right pressure.

00:50:00.539 --> 00:50:04.619
You should go back, he said, making

00:50:04.619 --> 00:50:05.400
turtle jump.

00:50:05.460 --> 00:50:08.039
You don't want to tramp around Pyria

00:50:08.039 --> 00:50:09.300
looking for my deadly sister.

00:50:09.360 --> 00:50:11.280
Who will kill you on site?

00:50:11.280 --> 00:50:13.619
Or my brother, who might do the same

00:50:13.619 --> 00:50:16.679
because, by the way, killing Sea Wings

00:50:16.679 --> 00:50:17.880
was a specialty of his?

00:50:17.880 --> 00:50:20.400
Go keep an eye on Jade Mountain instead.

00:50:20.460 --> 00:50:23.820
Turtles glow in the dark scales flickered

00:50:23.820 --> 00:50:26.460
illuminating his anxious face with pale

00:50:26.460 --> 00:50:27.239
greenish light.

00:50:27.300 --> 00:50:30.599
But what if the mountain falls on me?

00:50:30.659 --> 00:50:32.159
Is it dangerous?

00:50:32.280 --> 00:50:36.539
Not as dangerous as following me, Winter

00:50:36.539 --> 00:50:36.960
hissed.

00:50:37.079 --> 00:50:39.420
It's not going to fall on you because

00:50:39.420 --> 00:50:40.320
we're going to stop it.

00:50:40.440 --> 00:50:42.960
Kinkachu said, but don't you want to stay

00:50:42.960 --> 00:50:43.320
with us?

00:50:43.380 --> 00:50:48.360
I can't decide what sounds worse, Turtle

00:50:48.360 --> 00:50:48.960
admitted.

00:50:49.019 --> 00:50:52.920
Chasing killer dragons across Pyria, or

00:50:52.920 --> 00:50:55.019
sitting at school, waiting for some kind

00:50:55.019 --> 00:50:57.599
of thunder and ice catastrophe to drop on

00:50:57.599 --> 00:50:57.900
my head.

00:50:58.019 --> 00:51:01.380
It's all right, Moon said.

00:51:01.440 --> 00:51:03.840
Turtle, you can go back to Jade

00:51:03.840 --> 00:51:04.380
Mountain.

00:51:04.440 --> 00:51:06.360
You can tell them that we're safe and

00:51:06.360 --> 00:51:06.960
where we've gone.

00:51:07.019 --> 00:51:11.159
That's true he said, perking up.

00:51:11.219 --> 00:51:13.860
That would be useful of me, wouldn't it?

00:51:13.920 --> 00:51:16.920
Probably, Kibley agreed.

00:51:16.980 --> 00:51:19.920
Although, you could be useful with us too

00:51:19.920 --> 00:51:21.960
but it's your choice.

00:51:22.019 --> 00:51:24.360
Turtles shuffled backward.

00:51:24.420 --> 00:51:27.659
I'll tell tsunami and the others not to

00:51:27.659 --> 00:51:28.139
worry about you.

00:51:28.199 --> 00:51:31.019
And I did promise mother to watch out for

00:51:31.019 --> 00:51:34.199
anemone, so I should, uh, I should really

00:51:34.199 --> 00:51:35.340
do that, you know?

00:51:35.400 --> 00:51:39.239
But you go catch the bad guys and stop

00:51:39.239 --> 00:51:39.960
the prophecy.

00:51:40.019 --> 00:51:42.239
And then I'll see you all when you get

00:51:42.239 --> 00:51:42.900
back to school.

00:51:42.960 --> 00:51:43.980
Okay?

00:51:44.039 --> 00:51:47.460
A moment later, the sea wing had slipped

00:51:47.460 --> 00:51:49.619
away into the trees, and soon they heard

00:51:49.619 --> 00:51:51.659
muffled, wet wing beats as he flew away.

00:51:51.719 --> 00:51:53.460
Hmm.

00:51:53.579 --> 00:51:55.320
Kinkachu said with a frown.

00:51:55.440 --> 00:51:57.119
That was disappointing.

00:51:57.179 --> 00:51:59.820
How can we be the 2nd coming of the 5

00:51:59.820 --> 00:52:02.460
dragonettes of destiny, if there's only 4

00:52:02.460 --> 00:52:02.760
of us?

00:52:02.820 --> 00:52:06.179
I highly doubt we're destined for

00:52:06.179 --> 00:52:07.980
anything special, Winter said.

00:52:08.039 --> 00:52:10.619
You're not getting rid of the rest of us

00:52:10.619 --> 00:52:11.219
that easily.

00:52:11.280 --> 00:52:14.519
Kibley said sharply to Winter as though

00:52:14.519 --> 00:52:16.139
he knew exactly what Winter was trying to

00:52:16.139 --> 00:52:16.320
do.

00:52:16.380 --> 00:52:20.039
All right, Winter growled.

00:52:20.099 --> 00:52:20.760
Fine.

00:52:20.820 --> 00:52:23.099
Let's all go to the rainforest together

00:52:23.099 --> 00:52:25.500
like a sloppy pile of mudwing siblings.

00:52:25.559 --> 00:52:28.079
I can look for icicle, and you can go dig

00:52:28.079 --> 00:52:29.280
around in the ashes of the night

00:52:29.280 --> 00:52:29.699
kingdom.

00:52:29.760 --> 00:52:33.900
And I can save Queen Glory, Kinkaju said

00:52:33.900 --> 00:52:34.920
weeping into the air.

00:52:34.980 --> 00:52:39.360
Besides, Kibley pointed out, flicking his

00:52:39.360 --> 00:52:40.199
tail at winter.

00:52:40.260 --> 00:52:42.480
That'll actually bring you closer to the

00:52:42.480 --> 00:52:43.079
Ice Kingdom.

00:52:43.139 --> 00:52:45.960
Since then, you can use the tunnel that

00:52:45.960 --> 00:52:47.820
comes out north of Queen Thorn's

00:52:47.820 --> 00:52:48.420
stronghold.

00:52:48.480 --> 00:52:50.460
That was true.

00:52:50.579 --> 00:52:54.239
Winter disliked it intensely when Kibley

00:52:54.239 --> 00:52:56.519
made clever observations like that, and

00:52:56.519 --> 00:52:57.840
it happened about 40 times a day.

00:52:57.900 --> 00:53:02.219
I know, he said, looking down his nose at

00:53:02.219 --> 00:53:03.059
the sand wing.

00:53:03.119 --> 00:53:04.980
Obviously, I figured that out.

00:53:05.099 --> 00:53:07.440
That's the only reason I'm agreeing to

00:53:07.440 --> 00:53:07.619
this.

00:53:07.679 --> 00:53:11.699
Oh, Kibley said, with a rakish grin.

00:53:11.760 --> 00:53:14.400
I thought perhaps it was because I'm so

00:53:14.400 --> 00:53:15.599
charming and convincing.

00:53:15.659 --> 00:53:17.820
You are neither.

00:53:17.880 --> 00:53:19.199
Winter said.

00:53:19.260 --> 00:53:21.599
In fact, if you don't shut up at once, I

00:53:21.599 --> 00:53:22.619
will change my mind.

00:53:22.679 --> 00:53:25.619
Kibli pretended to wrap invisible chains

00:53:25.619 --> 00:53:27.599
around his snout, and lifted his front

00:53:27.599 --> 00:53:28.800
talons innocently.

00:53:28.860 --> 00:53:33.360
Let's go, Moon said, spreading her wings

00:53:33.360 --> 00:53:35.940
and lifting off, Kibli and Kinkajoo

00:53:35.940 --> 00:53:36.539
leaped after her.

00:53:36.599 --> 00:53:40.260
Winter hesitated for a moment, watching

00:53:40.260 --> 00:53:42.480
the lightning flash in the sky beyond the

00:53:42.480 --> 00:53:43.320
flying dragons.

00:53:43.380 --> 00:53:45.780
Why was he agreeing to this?

00:53:45.840 --> 00:53:48.420
An ice wing warrior didn't need help from

00:53:48.420 --> 00:53:49.019
anyone else?

00:53:49.079 --> 00:53:51.840
Least of all, a pack of misguided dragons

00:53:51.840 --> 00:53:53.400
from other tribes.

00:53:53.460 --> 00:53:55.019
Take it, Kibli.

00:53:55.079 --> 00:53:57.599
Everyone knew Sandwings were nearly as

00:53:57.599 --> 00:54:00.300
untrustworthy as Nightwings, except half

00:54:00.300 --> 00:54:02.579
as smart, and twice as likely to betray

00:54:02.579 --> 00:54:03.780
you for golden treasure.

00:54:03.900 --> 00:54:05.760
And a rain wing?

00:54:05.820 --> 00:54:07.920
They weren't even worth mentioning in the

00:54:07.920 --> 00:54:10.079
great ice wing sagas that told the

00:54:10.079 --> 00:54:10.800
history of this world.

00:54:10.860 --> 00:54:13.800
Lazy, and insignificant, and weak.

00:54:13.920 --> 00:54:16.199
There was no benefit to be gained from

00:54:16.199 --> 00:54:17.820
knowing them or befriending them.

00:54:17.880 --> 00:54:21.480
Worst of all, how could he ally himself

00:54:21.480 --> 00:54:24.780
with a night wing, even temporarily, even

00:54:24.780 --> 00:54:26.400
if he went into it knowing not to trust

00:54:26.400 --> 00:54:26.699
her.

00:54:26.760 --> 00:54:30.059
To travel with Moon, to spend a single

00:54:30.059 --> 00:54:32.579
moment longer with her, knowing what he

00:54:32.579 --> 00:54:33.059
knew now.

00:54:33.119 --> 00:54:37.500
And yet, still feeling something that he

00:54:37.500 --> 00:54:41.039
should not be feeling, I should stay as

00:54:41.039 --> 00:54:42.300
far away from her as I can.

00:54:42.360 --> 00:54:45.480
Mother and father would be more than

00:54:45.480 --> 00:54:46.380
disappointed in me.

00:54:46.500 --> 00:54:49.380
If they heard of this, any potential

00:54:49.380 --> 00:54:50.940
position in the palace would be gone

00:54:50.940 --> 00:54:51.239
forever.

00:54:51.300 --> 00:54:54.659
I'd land at the bottom of the 7th circle

00:54:54.659 --> 00:54:56.579
and have to choose between a diamond

00:54:56.579 --> 00:54:59.280
trial, or being stationed on an Arctic

00:54:59.280 --> 00:55:01.199
island outpost for the rest of my life.

00:55:01.260 --> 00:55:04.679
He could see their faces so clearly.

00:55:04.800 --> 00:55:06.780
That look they got whenever he did

00:55:06.780 --> 00:55:10.139
something wrong, the look that said, if

00:55:10.139 --> 00:55:12.360
only we'd lost you instead of hailstorm

00:55:12.360 --> 00:55:15.719
if only you met any of our expectations

00:55:15.719 --> 00:55:18.659
if only you were everything an ice wing

00:55:18.659 --> 00:55:19.019
should be.

00:55:19.139 --> 00:55:21.059
Winter.

00:55:21.119 --> 00:55:22.920
Kibley called from above.

00:55:22.980 --> 00:55:25.559
The others were hovering up there, waiting

00:55:25.559 --> 00:55:25.980
for him.

00:55:26.099 --> 00:55:27.179
Come on.

00:55:27.239 --> 00:55:30.539
This was only temporary, he reminded

00:55:30.539 --> 00:55:30.960
himself.

00:55:31.019 --> 00:55:33.179
Get to the rainforest.

00:55:33.239 --> 00:55:33.960
Look for icicle.

00:55:34.019 --> 00:55:36.239
Then he could rescue Hailstorm by

00:55:36.239 --> 00:55:36.780
himself.

00:55:36.840 --> 00:55:39.539
That's what a true ice wing prince would

00:55:39.539 --> 00:55:39.659
do.

00:55:39.780 --> 00:55:42.599
He wasn't really working with Moon and

00:55:42.599 --> 00:55:42.960
the others.

00:55:43.019 --> 00:55:45.840
He didn't have to listen to them, and he

00:55:45.840 --> 00:55:47.099
certainly wouldn't ask them for help.

00:55:47.159 --> 00:55:51.000
Most of all, he would never, never trust

00:55:51.000 --> 00:55:54.000
them. especially that lying night wing.

00:55:54.119 --> 00:55:57.059
Shaking rain off his tail with a clatter

00:55:57.059 --> 00:56:00.059
of spikes, he ascended into the storm

00:56:00.059 --> 00:56:02.340
wheeled around in a circle, and took off

00:56:02.340 --> 00:56:04.980
toward the rainforest without a glance at

00:56:04.980 --> 00:56:05.760
the other dragons.

00:56:05.820 --> 00:56:10.139
Chapter 3.

00:56:10.380 --> 00:56:14.340
Winter was not surprised to discover that

00:56:14.340 --> 00:56:16.860
the rainforest was horrifying and awful.

00:56:16.920 --> 00:56:19.860
For starters, there was something

00:56:19.860 --> 00:56:21.360
blocking Winter's view in every

00:56:21.360 --> 00:56:21.900
direction.

00:56:21.960 --> 00:56:25.739
Giant trees to the left, tangles of vines

00:56:25.739 --> 00:56:28.320
to the right, a thick canopy of leaves

00:56:28.320 --> 00:56:28.739
overhead.

00:56:28.800 --> 00:56:31.440
He could barely see 5 feet in front of

00:56:31.440 --> 00:56:31.739
him.

00:56:31.800 --> 00:56:33.179
Never mind the horizon.

00:56:33.239 --> 00:56:36.239
How could any dragon keep watch in a

00:56:36.239 --> 00:56:36.719
place like this?

00:56:36.780 --> 00:56:39.179
How could you ever know if you were being

00:56:39.179 --> 00:56:41.400
attacked or buy how many dragons?

00:56:41.460 --> 00:56:44.280
It was an indefensible quagmire.

00:56:44.340 --> 00:56:46.920
Also, a literal quagmire.

00:56:46.980 --> 00:56:49.559
Every time they landed, the mud was

00:56:49.559 --> 00:56:51.119
nearly enough to make him want to claw

00:56:51.119 --> 00:56:51.960
off his own scales.

00:56:52.079 --> 00:56:55.260
Moreover, the whole place was

00:56:55.260 --> 00:56:56.099
overwhelming.

00:56:56.159 --> 00:56:58.139
Too many bright colors.

00:56:58.199 --> 00:57:01.619
What self respecting bird would ever need

00:57:01.619 --> 00:57:04.679
to have red, yellow, blue, and green

00:57:04.679 --> 00:57:05.460
feathers?

00:57:05.519 --> 00:57:06.960
Black and white.

00:57:07.019 --> 00:57:09.420
Those were the only feather colors for a

00:57:09.420 --> 00:57:10.260
dignified bird.

00:57:10.320 --> 00:57:13.019
Too many strange noises.

00:57:13.079 --> 00:57:15.360
What kind of animal howled like that?

00:57:15.420 --> 00:57:18.059
Why could he hear a waterfall for what

00:57:18.059 --> 00:57:21.000
seemed like hours, and yet never see it?

00:57:21.059 --> 00:57:25.440
And what was that infernal nonstop

00:57:25.440 --> 00:57:26.039
buzzing?

00:57:26.099 --> 00:57:30.539
Also, far, far, far too many weird

00:57:30.539 --> 00:57:31.260
smells.

00:57:31.320 --> 00:57:34.019
Winter couldn't decide which was the

00:57:34.019 --> 00:57:34.500
worst part.

00:57:34.559 --> 00:57:36.719
The bugs or the heat.

00:57:36.780 --> 00:57:40.800
It was painfully, oppressively hot, in a

00:57:40.800 --> 00:57:41.579
sweltering.

00:57:41.639 --> 00:57:43.860
We are being boiled alive in our scales

00:57:43.860 --> 00:57:44.400
kind of way.

00:57:44.460 --> 00:57:47.579
He thought he'd experienced heat

00:57:47.579 --> 00:57:49.860
traveling through the kingdom of sand, but

00:57:49.860 --> 00:57:52.739
this was also damp and sticky, and more

00:57:52.739 --> 00:57:54.599
miserable than anything he'd ever felt

00:57:54.599 --> 00:57:55.260
before.

00:57:55.320 --> 00:57:59.400
Then, there were the insects, swarming

00:57:59.400 --> 00:58:01.559
around them, finding every spot between

00:58:01.559 --> 00:58:04.199
the dragons' scales to wriggle in and

00:58:04.199 --> 00:58:04.980
suck their blood.

00:58:05.039 --> 00:58:07.920
He'd already shaken 2 green striped

00:58:07.920 --> 00:58:11.039
caterpillars, a walking twig thing, and

00:58:11.039 --> 00:58:13.139
an alarmingly furry spider out of his

00:58:13.139 --> 00:58:13.380
ears.

00:58:13.500 --> 00:58:16.500
His wings kept catching on enormous

00:58:16.500 --> 00:58:19.199
spider webs, and creatures with 1000000s

00:58:19.199 --> 00:58:21.719
of legs had scurried over his talons at

00:58:21.719 --> 00:58:22.619
least a dozen times.

00:58:22.679 --> 00:58:26.820
He itched unbearably from his horns to

00:58:26.820 --> 00:58:28.380
his forlornly muddy tail.

00:58:28.500 --> 00:58:31.079
Was Icicle really here?

00:58:31.139 --> 00:58:33.480
He couldn't imagine her putting up with

00:58:33.480 --> 00:58:33.900
any of this.

00:58:33.960 --> 00:58:36.599
He couldn't imagine her with even a speck

00:58:36.599 --> 00:58:37.559
of mud on her.

00:58:37.619 --> 00:58:40.260
She had always returned from battle as

00:58:40.260 --> 00:58:43.260
pristine as when she'd left, apart from a

00:58:43.260 --> 00:58:45.179
few bleeding blue scratches here and

00:58:45.179 --> 00:58:45.300
there.

00:58:45.360 --> 00:58:48.300
Perhaps she'd taken 2 steps into this

00:58:48.300 --> 00:58:50.699
rainforest, and decided that murdering

00:58:50.699 --> 00:58:52.920
the rain wing queen wasn't worth it.

00:58:52.980 --> 00:58:55.440
You must hate this place.

00:58:55.500 --> 00:58:58.260
Moon said, appearing beside him.

00:58:58.320 --> 00:59:01.619
They'd stopped to rest near a river, and

00:59:01.619 --> 00:59:03.599
winter was crouched on a large boulder

00:59:03.599 --> 00:59:05.699
trying to dip his talons in the water

00:59:05.699 --> 00:59:08.519
without stepping in the oozing black mud

00:59:08.519 --> 00:59:09.420
that lined the banks.

00:59:09.480 --> 00:59:12.960
He narrowed his eyes at her, reaching

00:59:12.960 --> 00:59:14.940
unconsciously over the small wolfskin

00:59:14.940 --> 00:59:16.860
pouch, he kept tied to one of his ankles

00:59:16.860 --> 00:59:18.780
where he'd hidden the skyfire.

00:59:18.840 --> 00:59:20.460
She sighed.

00:59:20.519 --> 00:59:23.460
No, I didn't get that from your head.

00:59:23.519 --> 00:59:25.739
I just figured an ice wing would probably

00:59:25.739 --> 00:59:26.400
hate it here.

00:59:26.519 --> 00:59:28.920
It must be the polar opposite of the ice

00:59:28.920 --> 00:59:32.639
kingdom, the anti-polar opposite, she

00:59:32.639 --> 00:59:35.519
added, then scrunched her snout, trying

00:59:35.519 --> 00:59:36.659
not to laugh at her own joke.

00:59:36.719 --> 00:59:40.199
Is this merely idle conversation?

00:59:40.260 --> 00:59:42.119
What would be the point of that?

00:59:42.179 --> 00:59:44.519
Or is she trying to trick some

00:59:44.519 --> 00:59:45.539
information out of me?

00:59:45.599 --> 00:59:48.960
It is, he said finally.

00:59:49.019 --> 00:59:50.340
And I do.

00:59:50.400 --> 00:59:55.199
This is where I grew up, she said, waiting

00:59:55.199 --> 00:59:56.519
a few steps into the river.

00:59:56.579 --> 00:59:59.460
The water eddied around her legs with

00:59:59.460 --> 01:00:01.019
glints of reflected sunlight.

01:00:01.079 --> 01:00:03.239
It's not so bad, actually.

01:00:03.300 --> 01:00:05.219
Humph.

01:00:05.280 --> 01:00:06.539
Winter snorted.

01:00:06.599 --> 01:00:07.980
Not so bad?

01:00:08.039 --> 01:00:10.500
Kinkachu said indignantly from the other

01:00:10.500 --> 01:00:10.920
bank.

01:00:10.980 --> 01:00:13.079
This is the most beautiful part of

01:00:13.079 --> 01:00:13.800
Pyria.

01:00:13.860 --> 01:00:15.840
Other dragons would be lucky to live

01:00:15.840 --> 01:00:16.079
here.

01:00:16.139 --> 01:00:19.320
The rain wing bounded into the water with

01:00:19.320 --> 01:00:21.960
a splash, the drenched winter's nose and

01:00:21.960 --> 01:00:22.199
tail.

01:00:22.320 --> 01:00:25.260
A fat orange toad burst out of the river

01:00:25.260 --> 01:00:27.659
and made a clumsy dash for the reeds

01:00:27.659 --> 01:00:29.460
trying to get away from the dragons.

01:00:29.519 --> 01:00:32.820
Moon tilted her head at it, then flared

01:00:32.820 --> 01:00:34.920
her wings at Kibley as he sat up from the

01:00:34.920 --> 01:00:35.519
middle of the river.

01:00:35.579 --> 01:00:38.760
Don't eat it, she warned him.

01:00:38.820 --> 01:00:41.760
Seriously, one of those gave me hiccups

01:00:41.760 --> 01:00:42.239
for days.

01:00:42.300 --> 01:00:44.699
Also, some really weird dreams.

01:00:44.760 --> 01:00:47.039
I thought for a while I was having

01:00:47.039 --> 01:00:49.860
visions of a possible future where newts

01:00:49.860 --> 01:00:51.360
and ant eaters took over the world.

01:00:51.360 --> 01:00:53.340
Kinkichu giggled.

01:00:53.460 --> 01:00:55.920
Here, try these instead.

01:00:55.980 --> 01:00:57.119
Moon offered.

01:00:57.239 --> 01:00:59.460
She reached into one of the overhanging

01:00:59.460 --> 01:01:02.039
trees and pulled a few strange fruits

01:01:02.039 --> 01:01:03.420
from the branches.

01:01:03.480 --> 01:01:05.460
They were a curious reddish pink on the

01:01:05.460 --> 01:01:08.039
outside, with flaps like folded up flower

01:01:08.039 --> 01:01:10.500
petals, but as she sliced them open with

01:01:10.500 --> 01:01:13.139
her claws, winter saw that on the inside

01:01:13.139 --> 01:01:15.599
they were white, with small black flex.

01:01:15.659 --> 01:01:18.840
She handed one to Kibley, then glanced

01:01:18.840 --> 01:01:19.679
sideways at winter.

01:01:19.739 --> 01:01:21.539
Absolutely not.

01:01:21.599 --> 01:01:24.840
He said, do not get that vile stickiness

01:01:24.840 --> 01:01:25.679
anywhere near me.

01:01:25.739 --> 01:01:26.940
Fruit.

01:01:27.000 --> 01:01:27.780
Yuck.

01:01:27.900 --> 01:01:31.019
His stomach growled, and he tried to hide

01:01:31.019 --> 01:01:32.880
it by scraping his claws along the rock.

01:01:32.940 --> 01:01:36.539
You are so, so weird.

01:01:36.599 --> 01:01:39.480
Kinkaju said to him, how can you not love

01:01:39.480 --> 01:01:39.780
it here?

01:01:39.840 --> 01:01:42.059
Don't you come from a place with no

01:01:42.059 --> 01:01:43.019
colors and no life?

01:01:43.079 --> 01:01:45.840
He thought of the 1000 different

01:01:45.840 --> 01:01:47.699
shimmering shades of blue in the ice

01:01:47.699 --> 01:01:48.300
palace.

01:01:48.360 --> 01:01:50.820
He remembered the distant splashes of

01:01:50.820 --> 01:01:53.760
whales and seals, the way sound carried

01:01:53.760 --> 01:01:55.500
across the cool, quiet ice.

01:01:55.559 --> 01:01:57.900
He thought of how he could smell polar

01:01:57.900 --> 01:02:01.380
bears or arctic foxes from miles away, and

01:02:01.380 --> 01:02:03.300
how all of his senses could detect the

01:02:03.300 --> 01:02:05.280
smallest changes in the frozen world.

01:02:05.340 --> 01:02:08.940
Here, it was just too much.

01:02:09.059 --> 01:02:11.639
White is a color.

01:02:11.699 --> 01:02:13.800
He snapped at the rain wing.

01:02:13.860 --> 01:02:15.059
Blue is a color.

01:02:15.119 --> 01:02:17.460
That is an eyesore.

01:02:17.519 --> 01:02:20.760
He pointed to a violently red flower as

01:02:20.760 --> 01:02:21.840
big as one of his talons.

01:02:21.900 --> 01:02:25.500
We also have these, Moon said.

01:02:25.559 --> 01:02:28.320
She lifted a dark green leaf on one of

01:02:28.320 --> 01:02:30.539
the trees and revealed a spiraling

01:02:30.539 --> 01:02:32.820
tendril of delicate white blue flowers

01:02:32.820 --> 01:02:35.280
glowing like snowflakes against the brown

01:02:35.280 --> 01:02:35.760
trunk.

01:02:35.820 --> 01:02:38.760
Oh, and look, there's a sloth.

01:02:38.820 --> 01:02:42.000
She pointed to a furry gray shape that

01:02:42.000 --> 01:02:44.280
was clambering slowly along a branch far

01:02:44.280 --> 01:02:44.760
overhead.

01:02:44.820 --> 01:02:49.320
Thank the moons, Winter said, leaping to

01:02:49.320 --> 01:02:49.619
his feet.

01:02:49.679 --> 01:02:51.659
I knew there had to be something worth

01:02:51.659 --> 01:02:52.380
eating around here.

01:02:52.440 --> 01:02:56.099
He shot into the air, his claws reaching

01:02:56.099 --> 01:02:58.619
for the sloths exposed wide underbelly.

01:02:58.679 --> 01:03:00.659
Wait, Moon cried.

01:03:00.780 --> 01:03:03.360
There was a twin shriek of dismay from

01:03:03.360 --> 01:03:04.079
Kinkaju.

01:03:04.139 --> 01:03:07.440
The sloth peered over its shoulder, and

01:03:07.440 --> 01:03:10.139
blinked enormous, confused eyes at him

01:03:10.139 --> 01:03:12.000
and then, wham!

01:03:12.059 --> 01:03:14.280
Something slammed into Winter's side and

01:03:14.280 --> 01:03:15.539
smashed him against a tree.

01:03:15.599 --> 01:03:19.079
He saw a flash of red scales and sharp

01:03:19.079 --> 01:03:21.239
teeth and thought, Skywing.

01:03:21.300 --> 01:03:25.019
Could it be Queen Scarlet, here, attacking

01:03:25.019 --> 01:03:25.500
him?

01:03:25.559 --> 01:03:28.079
He whirled and lashed out with his tail

01:03:28.079 --> 01:03:30.719
but just missed the enemy dragon as a

01:03:30.719 --> 01:03:31.380
dove under him.

01:03:31.440 --> 01:03:34.619
Winter spun again and clawed at the air

01:03:34.619 --> 01:03:36.599
where the dragon should have been, but

01:03:36.599 --> 01:03:38.579
once again, it whisked out of his reach.

01:03:38.639 --> 01:03:41.579
The red dragon swooped up to the branch

01:03:41.579 --> 01:03:45.059
snatched the sloth in its talons, paused

01:03:45.059 --> 01:03:47.159
to glare at winter, and then vanished.

01:03:47.219 --> 01:03:50.880
Winter warred with surprise and fury.

01:03:50.940 --> 01:03:52.980
Calm down!

01:03:53.099 --> 01:03:54.780
Kibley shouted in his ear.

01:03:54.900 --> 01:03:57.420
The sand wing ducked as winter swiped at

01:03:57.420 --> 01:03:57.719
him.

01:03:57.780 --> 01:03:59.219
Winter stop.

01:03:59.280 --> 01:04:01.440
There was a sky wing.

01:04:01.500 --> 01:04:02.760
Winter snarled.

01:04:02.820 --> 01:04:05.280
It attacked me and stole my prey and then

01:04:05.280 --> 01:04:06.119
disapp...

01:04:06.480 --> 01:04:07.920
Oh, seal guts.

01:04:07.980 --> 01:04:10.380
Not a sky wing.

01:04:10.440 --> 01:04:13.139
Kibley pointed out, although Winter had

01:04:13.139 --> 01:04:14.400
obviously figured that out already.

01:04:14.460 --> 01:04:16.139
I know!

01:04:16.199 --> 01:04:18.900
Winter warred, beating the air with his

01:04:18.900 --> 01:04:19.440
wings.

01:04:19.500 --> 01:04:22.199
Come out and face me, you cowardly lunch

01:04:22.199 --> 01:04:23.460
stealing rain wing.

01:04:23.579 --> 01:04:26.280
The dragon suddenly materialized on the

01:04:26.280 --> 01:04:28.860
branch again, her scales shifting to a

01:04:28.860 --> 01:04:31.559
furious red, with splatters of black and

01:04:31.559 --> 01:04:31.860
orange.

01:04:31.920 --> 01:04:35.940
Topher is nobody's lunch, she shouted.

01:04:36.000 --> 01:04:38.579
Those nasty black dragons have already

01:04:38.579 --> 01:04:39.840
eaten one of my sloths.

01:04:39.900 --> 01:04:41.400
I'm not letting it happen again.

01:04:41.460 --> 01:04:44.639
She flexed her claws and bared her fangs

01:04:44.639 --> 01:04:44.940
at him.

01:04:45.059 --> 01:04:48.900
Don't make her mad, Kibley said quickly

01:04:48.900 --> 01:04:50.519
grabbing Winter's shoulder.

01:04:50.579 --> 01:04:53.219
I mean, don't make her more mad.

01:04:53.280 --> 01:04:56.340
The heat emanating from the sand wings

01:04:56.340 --> 01:04:58.619
yellow scales was uncomfortable, and

01:04:58.619 --> 01:04:59.519
winter shook him off.

01:04:59.579 --> 01:05:02.820
As if a rain wing would ever dare fight

01:05:02.820 --> 01:05:03.239
me.

01:05:03.300 --> 01:05:06.420
Winter scoffed, as if I couldn't claw off

01:05:06.420 --> 01:05:07.980
her face as easily as breathing.

01:05:08.039 --> 01:05:11.099
What is with you and faces?

01:05:11.099 --> 01:05:12.239
Kibley said.

01:05:12.300 --> 01:05:14.639
You should try threatening someone's

01:05:14.639 --> 01:05:17.219
elbows or ankles once in a while. just

01:05:17.219 --> 01:05:18.000
for change of pace.

01:05:18.119 --> 01:05:21.119
Kinkachu landed on the branch beside the

01:05:21.119 --> 01:05:23.639
angry rain wing, angling herself between

01:05:23.639 --> 01:05:25.260
the furious dragon in winter.

01:05:25.320 --> 01:05:27.360
Exquisite.

01:05:27.420 --> 01:05:28.860
It's me. she said.

01:05:28.920 --> 01:05:30.239
I'm sorry about this.

01:05:30.300 --> 01:05:32.460
I promise we were about to stop him.

01:05:32.519 --> 01:05:34.079
Ha!

01:05:34.139 --> 01:05:35.099
Winter barked.

01:05:35.159 --> 01:05:38.699
Winter, do you have a part of your brain

01:05:38.699 --> 01:05:40.139
that can handle empathy?

01:05:40.199 --> 01:05:41.340
Kibley asked.

01:05:41.400 --> 01:05:43.260
That sloth is her pet.

01:05:43.320 --> 01:05:45.300
Just like bandit was your pet.

01:05:45.360 --> 01:05:47.940
Can you by any chance remember about a

01:05:47.940 --> 01:05:50.340
week ago when someone tried to eat your

01:05:50.340 --> 01:05:51.420
pet?

01:05:51.480 --> 01:05:52.860
Winter hesitated.

01:05:52.920 --> 01:05:54.960
Of course he remembered that.

01:05:55.019 --> 01:05:57.599
And he remembered how Moon had saved his

01:05:57.599 --> 01:05:59.940
scavenger in her quiet, but resolute

01:05:59.940 --> 01:06:00.179
way.

01:06:00.239 --> 01:06:01.860
Kibley was right.

01:06:01.920 --> 01:06:03.300
Again.

01:06:03.360 --> 01:06:06.840
There was nothing more infuriating in the

01:06:06.840 --> 01:06:07.500
entire world.

01:06:07.559 --> 01:06:12.000
Bandit is much smarter than a flea ridden

01:06:12.000 --> 01:06:12.539
sloth.

01:06:12.599 --> 01:06:13.920
Winter snapped.

01:06:13.980 --> 01:06:16.260
Landing on one of the fat branches of a

01:06:16.260 --> 01:06:16.920
nearby tree.

01:06:16.980 --> 01:06:20.039
He flinched as a centipede as long as his

01:06:20.039 --> 01:06:22.199
foot, immediately scuttled over his

01:06:22.199 --> 01:06:22.559
claws.

01:06:22.619 --> 01:06:24.000
But fine.

01:06:24.119 --> 01:06:26.099
I won't eat any stupid slaws.

01:06:26.159 --> 01:06:28.139
Is there anything else that's off limits

01:06:28.139 --> 01:06:28.980
that I should know about?

01:06:29.039 --> 01:06:32.460
beloved armadillos, hairy giant spiders

01:06:32.460 --> 01:06:33.960
that someone is terribly attached to.

01:06:34.019 --> 01:06:36.840
I think the tamarind monkeys are really

01:06:36.840 --> 01:06:37.079
cute.

01:06:37.139 --> 01:06:39.719
Moon offered, swooping up beside them.

01:06:39.780 --> 01:06:41.940
It'd be great if you could not eat

01:06:41.940 --> 01:06:42.179
those.

01:06:42.239 --> 01:06:45.179
Winter scowled at her.

01:06:45.239 --> 01:06:47.280
As often happened with Moon, he couldn't

01:06:47.280 --> 01:06:48.059
tell if she was joking.

01:06:48.119 --> 01:06:51.780
Would you really eat a hairy spider

01:06:51.780 --> 01:06:52.139
anyway?

01:06:52.199 --> 01:06:55.199
Kibley asked, with genuine curiosity.

01:06:55.260 --> 01:06:58.619
Exquisite clutched her sloth closer

01:06:58.619 --> 01:07:01.199
hissed at Kinkajoo and Winter, and

01:07:01.199 --> 01:07:01.860
vanished again.

01:07:01.980 --> 01:07:04.679
This time Winter could see the ripple of

01:07:04.679 --> 01:07:06.599
her scales changing, and the slight

01:07:06.599 --> 01:07:08.460
weirdness of the air when she moved.

01:07:08.519 --> 01:07:11.519
A moment later, the branch shook as she

01:07:11.519 --> 01:07:13.920
took off, and he saw leaves thrashing

01:07:13.920 --> 01:07:16.199
about as the camouflaged dragon flapped

01:07:16.199 --> 01:07:16.380
away.

01:07:16.440 --> 01:07:20.280
Moon landed next to winter. and suddenly

01:07:20.280 --> 01:07:22.019
reached out to brush his wing with hers.

01:07:22.139 --> 01:07:25.679
Unlike Kibley's, Moon's scales were cool

01:07:25.679 --> 01:07:28.380
and smooth, like the icy walls of his

01:07:28.380 --> 01:07:29.519
room back in the palace.

01:07:29.579 --> 01:07:32.099
How dare she touch me?

01:07:32.159 --> 01:07:33.480
Winter thought.

01:07:33.539 --> 01:07:36.780
But then, he found himself keeping as

01:07:36.780 --> 01:07:39.119
still as he could, so their wings would

01:07:39.119 --> 01:07:39.599
stay connected.

01:07:39.719 --> 01:07:42.900
What is wrong with me?

01:07:42.960 --> 01:07:45.480
Moon's eyes were far away.

01:07:45.539 --> 01:07:47.820
And he wondered if she even knew she was

01:07:47.820 --> 01:07:48.239
touching him.

01:07:48.360 --> 01:07:51.539
Someone's coming, she whispered.

01:07:51.599 --> 01:07:53.760
Someone with dark thoughts.

01:07:53.880 --> 01:07:57.119
Did she see darkness in my mind?

01:07:57.179 --> 01:07:58.559
Winter wondered.

01:07:58.619 --> 01:08:00.840
How did she feel about the way I hate

01:08:00.840 --> 01:08:01.800
other dragons?

01:08:01.860 --> 01:08:05.219
What's a dark thought?

01:08:05.280 --> 01:08:08.400
Kibley asked, with something odd in his

01:08:08.400 --> 01:08:10.139
voice, nervousness?

01:08:10.199 --> 01:08:12.780
Was he also worried about what Moon had

01:08:12.780 --> 01:08:13.679
found inside him?

01:08:13.739 --> 01:08:15.780
What had she seen in his head?

01:08:15.900 --> 01:08:18.659
It's obsidian.

01:08:18.720 --> 01:08:21.420
He's thinking he hates being on guard

01:08:21.420 --> 01:08:25.199
duty, Moon said thoughtfully, especially

01:08:25.199 --> 01:08:26.939
with the rain wing he's been assigned as

01:08:26.939 --> 01:08:27.420
a partner.

01:08:27.479 --> 01:08:30.299
He hates being told what to do by rain

01:08:30.299 --> 01:08:30.839
wings.

01:08:30.899 --> 01:08:33.599
He wishes the night wings could overthrow

01:08:33.599 --> 01:08:35.879
Queen Glory and rule the rainforest

01:08:35.879 --> 01:08:36.659
themselves.

01:08:36.720 --> 01:08:37.979
She paused.

01:08:38.039 --> 01:08:40.619
All right, we're safe.

01:08:40.680 --> 01:08:41.399
They've gone by.

01:08:41.460 --> 01:08:44.399
She realized her wing was still touching

01:08:44.399 --> 01:08:46.380
Winters, and pulled away with an

01:08:46.380 --> 01:08:47.760
apologetic expression.

01:08:48.119 --> 01:08:49.680
He tried to pretend he hadn't even

01:08:49.680 --> 01:08:49.920
noticed.

01:08:49.979 --> 01:08:53.759
So, we're all on board with avoiding

01:08:53.759 --> 01:08:54.599
night wings, then?

01:08:54.659 --> 01:08:55.739
Kibley said.

01:08:55.800 --> 01:08:56.819
Excellent.

01:08:56.880 --> 01:08:59.039
Present company accepted, of course.

01:08:59.100 --> 01:09:03.000
Maybe not all night wings, but definitely

01:09:03.000 --> 01:09:04.800
him, Moon said.

01:09:04.859 --> 01:09:05.939
She sighed.

01:09:06.060 --> 01:09:08.699
I should probably tell the queen what I

01:09:08.699 --> 01:09:11.220
can do, so I can warn her about dragons

01:09:11.220 --> 01:09:11.520
like this.

01:09:11.579 --> 01:09:14.220
Her tail flicked the leaves below them.

01:09:14.279 --> 01:09:15.779
But I worry.

01:09:15.840 --> 01:09:19.260
I mean, should dragons be punished for

01:09:19.260 --> 01:09:19.800
their thoughts?

01:09:19.859 --> 01:09:22.019
Even if they never act on them?

01:09:22.079 --> 01:09:24.600
But what if warning her means they'll

01:09:24.600 --> 01:09:26.520
never do whatever terrible thing they're

01:09:26.520 --> 01:09:26.760
thinking of?

01:09:26.819 --> 01:09:28.139
I don't know.

01:09:28.199 --> 01:09:31.140
I don't want anyone to use me as a way to

01:09:31.140 --> 01:09:32.520
spy on the private thoughts of her

01:09:32.520 --> 01:09:33.000
subjects.

01:09:33.119 --> 01:09:35.399
Really?

01:09:35.460 --> 01:09:36.539
Kibley said.

01:09:36.600 --> 01:09:38.760
But it would be useful to know if a coup

01:09:38.760 --> 01:09:40.199
or an assassination is coming.

01:09:40.260 --> 01:09:42.659
If you could prevent that, wouldn't it be

01:09:42.659 --> 01:09:43.979
worth spying on a few dragons?

01:09:44.039 --> 01:09:46.859
No, Winter snapped.

01:09:46.920 --> 01:09:49.199
Nothing justifies invading another

01:09:49.199 --> 01:09:50.039
dragon's mind.

01:09:50.159 --> 01:09:53.699
But that's how she stopped icicle from

01:09:53.699 --> 01:09:54.539
killing Starflight.

01:09:54.600 --> 01:09:56.100
Kibley pointed out.

01:09:56.159 --> 01:09:58.380
Aren't you grateful she did that?

01:09:58.439 --> 01:10:01.920
Winter glared down at Kingaju, who had

01:10:01.920 --> 01:10:03.239
gone back to splashing in the river

01:10:03.239 --> 01:10:03.600
below.

01:10:03.659 --> 01:10:06.899
I still don't like it, he said.

01:10:06.960 --> 01:10:08.939
In the wrong talons.

01:10:09.000 --> 01:10:12.119
I mean, Moon could tell Queen Glory, she

01:10:12.119 --> 01:10:14.220
heard someone planning a murder, and that

01:10:14.220 --> 01:10:16.199
dragon could be punished, and who could

01:10:16.199 --> 01:10:16.739
prove her wrong?

01:10:16.800 --> 01:10:19.079
I wouldn't lie.

01:10:19.199 --> 01:10:21.960
Moon said, looking outraged.

01:10:22.020 --> 01:10:23.699
How do we know that?

01:10:23.760 --> 01:10:25.020
Winter asked.

01:10:25.079 --> 01:10:26.819
You hid your powers from us?

01:10:26.880 --> 01:10:28.319
Why should we trust you?

01:10:28.380 --> 01:10:30.239
And even if you wouldn't lie?

01:10:30.300 --> 01:10:31.979
What about other night wings?

01:10:32.039 --> 01:10:33.779
They've lied before, haven't they?

01:10:33.899 --> 01:10:36.479
They lied about having powers for years

01:10:36.479 --> 01:10:36.899
apparently.

01:10:36.960 --> 01:10:40.739
The entire tribes full of liars, going

01:10:40.739 --> 01:10:43.680
back 1000s of years, to the dark stalker

01:10:43.680 --> 01:10:45.659
and his cursed mother, Beauslayer.

01:10:45.779 --> 01:10:49.500
Moon jumped, overbalanced, and fell off

01:10:49.500 --> 01:10:51.479
the branch with a lot of wild thrashing.

01:10:51.539 --> 01:10:54.479
Startled, winter peered down at her as

01:10:54.479 --> 01:10:55.199
she climbed back up.

01:10:55.260 --> 01:10:57.539
Three moons.

01:10:57.600 --> 01:10:58.619
What was that about?

01:10:58.680 --> 01:11:00.960
Kibley asked when she was settled again.

01:11:01.020 --> 01:11:02.819
Are you all right?

01:11:02.939 --> 01:11:05.699
Moon was breathing in a funny, almost

01:11:05.699 --> 01:11:06.600
panicked way.

01:11:06.720 --> 01:11:08.819
Dark stalker?

01:11:08.880 --> 01:11:10.140
she said to Winter.

01:11:10.199 --> 01:11:11.699
How do you know about him?

01:11:11.760 --> 01:11:15.359
Everyone knows about him, Winter said.

01:11:15.420 --> 01:11:16.859
I don't.

01:11:16.920 --> 01:11:18.119
Kibley offered.

01:11:18.180 --> 01:11:21.539
Everyone, Winter said pointedly.

01:11:21.600 --> 01:11:22.800
Who's anyone?

01:11:22.859 --> 01:11:24.840
Ah, I see.

01:11:24.960 --> 01:11:26.279
Kibley said.

01:11:26.340 --> 01:11:27.420
You mean ice wings.

01:11:27.479 --> 01:11:31.920
And Night Wings, Moon said, he's our

01:11:31.920 --> 01:11:35.579
legend, Nightmare, Ghost Monster from the

01:11:35.579 --> 01:11:36.899
Beyond, whatever.

01:11:37.079 --> 01:11:39.060
Ours too.

01:11:39.119 --> 01:11:40.859
Winter said grimly.

01:11:40.920 --> 01:11:41.819
Trust me.

01:11:41.880 --> 01:11:43.560
Why?

01:11:43.619 --> 01:11:45.840
What did he ever do to the ice wings?

01:11:45.899 --> 01:11:46.920
Moon asked.

01:11:46.979 --> 01:11:50.699
Killed one of our princes, Winter said

01:11:50.699 --> 01:11:53.340
stole our royal heritage, ruined

01:11:53.340 --> 01:11:54.060
everything forever.

01:11:54.119 --> 01:11:58.260
Oh my, forever?

01:11:58.319 --> 01:12:00.060
Kidley asked.

01:12:00.119 --> 01:12:02.100
He gave the sunlit rainforest a mock

01:12:02.100 --> 01:12:03.899
serious, nodding inspection.

01:12:03.960 --> 01:12:05.520
Well, that explains it.

01:12:05.579 --> 01:12:07.859
I was wondering why everything was so

01:12:07.859 --> 01:12:09.060
very ruined all the time.

01:12:09.119 --> 01:12:11.880
Thank goodness there's one ancient dead

01:12:11.880 --> 01:12:13.140
dragon we can blame for it all.

01:12:13.260 --> 01:12:16.380
You wouldn't joke if you knew the whole

01:12:16.380 --> 01:12:16.739
story.

01:12:16.859 --> 01:12:18.300
Winter snapped.

01:12:18.359 --> 01:12:21.840
Moon closed her eyes, then shook her head

01:12:21.840 --> 01:12:23.100
with an expression that looked like

01:12:23.100 --> 01:12:23.640
frustration.

01:12:23.699 --> 01:12:27.899
I want to know the whole, she began, and

01:12:27.899 --> 01:12:29.640
then her eyes popped open in alarm.

01:12:29.699 --> 01:12:31.260
They're coming back.

01:12:31.319 --> 01:12:33.659
Obsidian and the rain wing guard, we

01:12:33.659 --> 01:12:35.039
should, hello?

01:12:35.100 --> 01:12:37.680
Kankaju called, waving her wings.

01:12:37.739 --> 01:12:39.180
Hi, over here.

01:12:39.239 --> 01:12:41.880
Not do that.

01:12:41.939 --> 01:12:45.060
Kibley finished for moon as she winced.

01:12:45.119 --> 01:12:46.800
It was too late.

01:12:46.859 --> 01:12:48.779
Winter hissed softly.

01:12:48.840 --> 01:12:50.939
There was no chance of sneaking through

01:12:50.939 --> 01:12:51.840
the rainforest now.

01:12:51.899 --> 01:12:54.000
The guards were heading straight for

01:12:54.000 --> 01:12:54.239
them.

01:12:54.300 --> 01:12:58.619
Chapter 4.

01:12:58.920 --> 01:13:02.939
A black dragon, the one with ugly

01:13:02.939 --> 01:13:05.640
thoughts, slowly stalked along the banks

01:13:05.640 --> 01:13:08.640
of the river, staring at Kingajou, his

01:13:08.640 --> 01:13:10.800
forked black tongue flicked in and out

01:13:10.800 --> 01:13:13.020
and his expression was calculating.

01:13:13.079 --> 01:13:15.539
A few steps ahead of him was a rain

01:13:15.539 --> 01:13:16.079
wing.

01:13:16.140 --> 01:13:18.720
Dappled green like the forest, but not

01:13:18.720 --> 01:13:19.859
completely camouflaged.

01:13:19.920 --> 01:13:22.140
She splashed into the river and over to

01:13:22.140 --> 01:13:23.460
Kinkaju, frowning.

01:13:23.579 --> 01:13:25.920
Oh, it's you.

01:13:25.979 --> 01:13:27.600
Kinkachu said.

01:13:27.659 --> 01:13:30.300
Winter had never heard that tone of gloom

01:13:30.300 --> 01:13:32.100
from the little rain wing before.

01:13:32.220 --> 01:13:34.199
Hi, Bromeliad.

01:13:34.319 --> 01:13:35.819
I thought you were orchid.

01:13:35.880 --> 01:13:38.760
What are you doing back here?

01:13:38.819 --> 01:13:40.680
Brumiliad demanded.

01:13:40.739 --> 01:13:42.899
You were supposed to stay at that school

01:13:42.899 --> 01:13:44.279
the queen sent you to.

01:13:44.340 --> 01:13:47.640
I told her you were a terrible student

01:13:47.640 --> 01:13:51.479
and would definitely fail or run off, but

01:13:51.479 --> 01:13:52.260
would she listen?

01:13:52.319 --> 01:13:55.260
Mysteriously not.

01:13:55.319 --> 01:13:56.159
And now here you are.

01:13:56.220 --> 01:13:58.439
So I suppose, I was right.

01:13:58.500 --> 01:14:01.140
I'm doing something important.

01:14:01.199 --> 01:14:02.819
Kinkachu snapped.

01:14:02.880 --> 01:14:04.859
I'm here to save the queen, if you must

01:14:04.859 --> 01:14:05.220
know.

01:14:05.279 --> 01:14:08.460
Winter caught the shifty expression that

01:14:08.460 --> 01:14:10.619
crossed Obsidian's face.

01:14:10.680 --> 01:14:11.699
Maybe Moon was right.

01:14:11.760 --> 01:14:14.039
Maybe this dragon's thoughts were as

01:14:14.039 --> 01:14:15.119
dangerous as they sounded.

01:14:15.180 --> 01:14:18.539
Then Obsidian looked up, and his gaze

01:14:18.539 --> 01:14:19.319
landed on winter.

01:14:19.380 --> 01:14:22.439
His tail began lashing furiously.

01:14:22.500 --> 01:14:24.659
And I swing.

01:14:24.720 --> 01:14:25.739
He hissed.

01:14:25.800 --> 01:14:27.420
Now a rainforest.

01:14:27.479 --> 01:14:29.579
Don't just look in the trees, friend.

01:14:29.579 --> 01:14:30.960
Come down and say hello.

01:14:31.020 --> 01:14:33.960
That sounded like just about the last

01:14:33.960 --> 01:14:36.600
thing Winter wanted to do, but picking a

01:14:36.600 --> 01:14:38.039
fight with a night wing would waste

01:14:38.039 --> 01:14:38.340
time.

01:14:38.399 --> 01:14:40.380
Time he needed to find his sister.

01:14:40.439 --> 01:14:42.479
He reluctantly spread his wings.

01:14:42.600 --> 01:14:44.819
Don't let him bully you.

01:14:44.880 --> 01:14:47.939
Moon whispered, catching one of Winter's

01:14:47.939 --> 01:14:49.260
talons before he could lift off.

01:14:49.319 --> 01:14:50.819
He's afraid of you.

01:14:50.939 --> 01:14:53.760
He's planning how to be as cruel and

01:14:53.760 --> 01:14:55.920
commanding as possible, because he wants

01:14:55.920 --> 01:14:57.000
to see you squirm.

01:14:57.060 --> 01:14:59.760
I don't squirm for anyone.

01:14:59.819 --> 01:15:02.279
Winter snarled under his breath.

01:15:02.340 --> 01:15:04.739
I know, Moon said.

01:15:04.800 --> 01:15:05.760
You shouldn't.

01:15:05.819 --> 01:15:07.859
You're a much better dragon than he is.

01:15:07.920 --> 01:15:08.939
You're.

01:15:09.899 --> 01:15:11.460
You're a much better dragon than most

01:15:11.460 --> 01:15:11.939
anyone.

01:15:12.060 --> 01:15:14.520
She ducked her head to look down at her

01:15:14.520 --> 01:15:14.939
claws.

01:15:15.000 --> 01:15:17.340
Winter blinked at her.

01:15:17.399 --> 01:15:19.079
Was that really what she thought?

01:15:19.140 --> 01:15:21.239
Even after looking inside him?

01:15:21.300 --> 01:15:24.180
Not me though, right?

01:15:24.239 --> 01:15:27.420
Kibley said, nudging Moon with a grin.

01:15:27.479 --> 01:15:28.739
He's not better than me.

01:15:28.800 --> 01:15:30.479
I'm awesome, right?

01:15:30.600 --> 01:15:32.640
Like, the most awesome.

01:15:32.699 --> 01:15:35.939
The way she smiled back at the sand wing

01:15:35.939 --> 01:15:37.920
like she couldn't help herself, made

01:15:37.920 --> 01:15:40.560
Winters scales feel all crawly and too

01:15:40.560 --> 01:15:40.859
warm.

01:15:40.920 --> 01:15:43.619
He spent away from them and leaped down

01:15:43.619 --> 01:15:43.979
to the ground.

01:15:44.039 --> 01:15:47.100
The night wing guard sat back on his

01:15:47.100 --> 01:15:49.260
haunches, inspecting the dragons

01:15:49.260 --> 01:15:51.840
suspiciously, as Moon and Kibley landed

01:15:51.840 --> 01:15:52.739
on the river bank as well.

01:15:52.800 --> 01:15:55.439
Having a night wing's gaze on him

01:15:55.439 --> 01:15:57.779
traveling over him as though he was a

01:15:57.779 --> 01:16:00.600
half eaten seal carcass, made Winter want

01:16:00.600 --> 01:16:02.279
to smash in some faces with his tail.

01:16:02.399 --> 01:16:05.640
He scraped his serrated claws through the

01:16:05.640 --> 01:16:07.020
damp layer of leaves on the forest

01:16:07.020 --> 01:16:07.319
floor.

01:16:07.380 --> 01:16:12.300
You're the peculiar dragonette, Obsidian

01:16:12.300 --> 01:16:14.340
said finally, narrowing his eyes at

01:16:14.340 --> 01:16:14.699
Moon.

01:16:14.819 --> 01:16:16.859
Failed school already.

01:16:16.920 --> 01:16:19.199
Did they realize you can't talk and send

01:16:19.199 --> 01:16:19.560
you back?

01:16:19.619 --> 01:16:22.319
What's with a multi-colored escort?

01:16:22.380 --> 01:16:24.539
He squinted at the dragons around her.

01:16:24.600 --> 01:16:26.699
Exactly who are you?

01:16:26.760 --> 01:16:30.840
None of your business, Winter growled.

01:16:30.960 --> 01:16:33.840
Obsidian's brows went up, and he eyed

01:16:33.840 --> 01:16:34.859
Winter even more closely.

01:16:34.979 --> 01:16:37.380
Winter wondered if it would be a bad

01:16:37.380 --> 01:16:39.960
start if he slashed that superior

01:16:39.960 --> 01:16:41.880
expression right off the black dragon's

01:16:41.880 --> 01:16:42.119
face.

01:16:42.239 --> 01:16:46.739
We're here to see Queen Glory, Kibley

01:16:46.739 --> 01:16:47.039
said.

01:16:47.100 --> 01:16:49.319
Winter was interested to hear a note of

01:16:49.319 --> 01:16:51.119
hostility in Kibley's voice as well.

01:16:51.180 --> 01:16:54.479
From what he'd seen so far, the Sandwing

01:16:54.479 --> 01:16:56.699
usually got along with everyone, or tried

01:16:56.699 --> 01:16:58.380
to, especially right at first.

01:16:58.439 --> 01:17:01.619
And trust me, she'll want to see us.

01:17:01.680 --> 01:17:03.720
So don't be a camel sniffer about it.

01:17:03.779 --> 01:17:07.380
I have to take you to the night village

01:17:07.380 --> 01:17:09.000
Obsidian said haughtily.

01:17:09.060 --> 01:17:11.640
That's the protocol for new dragons in

01:17:11.640 --> 01:17:12.239
the rainforest.

01:17:12.300 --> 01:17:15.840
We'll send her a message, and if she

01:17:15.840 --> 01:17:16.560
wants to see you.

01:17:16.619 --> 01:17:18.239
She'll come find you there.

01:17:18.300 --> 01:17:22.439
Um, no, Kinkachu said.

01:17:22.560 --> 01:17:25.739
Hello, I am a rain wing, not a new

01:17:25.739 --> 01:17:26.520
dragon.

01:17:26.579 --> 01:17:27.300
I live here.

01:17:27.359 --> 01:17:29.939
I'm practically the queen's best friend.

01:17:30.000 --> 01:17:32.220
And I am taking my new friends to see her

01:17:32.220 --> 01:17:33.359
right now.

01:17:33.420 --> 01:17:37.199
The Nightwing shifted his wings slightly

01:17:37.199 --> 01:17:38.880
and flicked his tongue through his sharp

01:17:38.880 --> 01:17:39.119
teeth.

01:17:39.180 --> 01:17:43.380
Kinkachoo, Moon said, touching her claw

01:17:43.380 --> 01:17:44.159
mate's shoulder.

01:17:44.220 --> 01:17:47.640
Actually, if we go to the village, I

01:17:47.640 --> 01:17:49.979
could see my mother, and we could ask

01:17:49.979 --> 01:17:51.779
whether anyone's seen icicle.

01:17:51.899 --> 01:17:54.600
Oh, all right.

01:17:54.659 --> 01:17:55.979
Kingichu agreed.

01:17:56.039 --> 01:17:58.619
But I'm going because I want to, not

01:17:58.619 --> 01:18:00.779
because anyone is telling me to.

01:18:00.779 --> 01:18:03.479
She flared the rough behind her ears at

01:18:03.479 --> 01:18:05.699
Obsidian, turning it orange as she did.

01:18:05.760 --> 01:18:08.520
He smiled nastily.

01:18:08.579 --> 01:18:11.340
Well, come along then.

01:18:11.399 --> 01:18:16.020
I'll go tell Queen Glory you're here, said

01:18:16.020 --> 01:18:18.119
Bromeliad, lifting off into the trees.

01:18:18.180 --> 01:18:21.000
Winter followed Kibley and the others

01:18:21.000 --> 01:18:23.220
staying a few steps behind so he could

01:18:23.220 --> 01:18:24.420
keep an eye on Obsidian.

01:18:24.539 --> 01:18:27.060
He had imagined visiting the home of the

01:18:27.060 --> 01:18:29.399
night wings many times, but in those

01:18:29.399 --> 01:18:30.060
fantasies.

01:18:30.180 --> 01:18:32.220
He always arrived at the head of a

01:18:32.220 --> 01:18:33.420
battalion of ice wings.

01:18:33.479 --> 01:18:36.539
His visions, generally involved, swooping

01:18:36.539 --> 01:18:39.479
down in vengeful glory, blasting frost

01:18:39.479 --> 01:18:41.939
breath across the entire city, and wiping

01:18:41.939 --> 01:18:44.159
out the whole tribe in one icy attack.

01:18:44.220 --> 01:18:47.579
Nightwings had been the sworn enemies of

01:18:47.579 --> 01:18:49.380
ice wings for 100s of years.

01:18:49.500 --> 01:18:51.720
But there hadn't been any action between

01:18:51.720 --> 01:18:53.340
them during winter's lifetime.

01:18:53.399 --> 01:18:55.920
The ice wings had been too busy with the

01:18:55.920 --> 01:18:58.739
war of sand wings succession, fighting

01:18:58.739 --> 01:19:00.779
nearly every other tribe, to worry about

01:19:00.779 --> 01:19:02.880
the secretive, impossible to find night

01:19:02.880 --> 01:19:03.359
wings.

01:19:03.420 --> 01:19:06.239
But then the news had arrived about the

01:19:06.239 --> 01:19:07.979
massacre at the Sky Wing Palace.

01:19:08.039 --> 01:19:11.100
When the tribe heard that Nightwings had

01:19:11.100 --> 01:19:13.260
descended on Scarlet's arena, and

01:19:13.260 --> 01:19:15.180
slaughtered all the ice wing prisoners

01:19:15.180 --> 01:19:17.460
while they were still chained and bound.

01:19:17.819 --> 01:19:20.340
Well, winter wasn't the only one who'd

01:19:20.340 --> 01:19:21.180
sworn vengeance.

01:19:21.239 --> 01:19:24.180
Finding the secret night wing home had

01:19:24.180 --> 01:19:25.979
become the ambition of every young ice

01:19:25.979 --> 01:19:26.460
wing.

01:19:26.520 --> 01:19:29.819
And now here he was, about to walk right

01:19:29.819 --> 01:19:30.300
into it.

01:19:30.359 --> 01:19:34.380
This wasn't the secret home, of course.

01:19:34.439 --> 01:19:37.380
This was their new home, the one they'd

01:19:37.380 --> 01:19:39.420
been driven to after the volcano erupted

01:19:39.420 --> 01:19:40.979
and wiped out their last home.

01:19:41.039 --> 01:19:42.899
Everyone knew about this one.

01:19:42.960 --> 01:19:45.479
Just like everyone knew the night wings

01:19:45.479 --> 01:19:47.520
had no more powers, that they were

01:19:47.520 --> 01:19:49.920
resettling in the rainforest, and that a

01:19:49.920 --> 01:19:51.779
seven-year-old rain wing was their new

01:19:51.779 --> 01:19:52.380
queen.

01:19:52.439 --> 01:19:54.659
They heard the village before they saw

01:19:54.659 --> 01:19:54.899
it.

01:19:54.960 --> 01:19:57.899
Wing beats, branches being ripped off

01:19:57.899 --> 01:19:59.880
trees, something that sounded like

01:19:59.880 --> 01:20:00.479
hammering.

01:20:00.539 --> 01:20:03.300
Winter could also smell meat cooking over

01:20:03.300 --> 01:20:05.520
fire, and he wished he could order his

01:20:05.520 --> 01:20:07.739
stomach not to growl and embarrass him.

01:20:07.800 --> 01:20:11.220
Then he saw black scales ahead, and felt

01:20:11.220 --> 01:20:12.659
his talons start tingling.

01:20:12.720 --> 01:20:15.539
Two dragons were pacing across a path

01:20:15.539 --> 01:20:16.800
that had been cleared through the trees

01:20:16.800 --> 01:20:18.359
evidently guarding it.

01:20:18.479 --> 01:20:21.000
Obsidian went on ahead to speak to them

01:20:21.000 --> 01:20:21.779
in low murmurs.

01:20:21.840 --> 01:20:25.079
The Night Wings glanced over, and

01:20:25.079 --> 01:20:26.939
Winter's claws curled in.

01:20:27.000 --> 01:20:29.279
If he had to die fighting night wings.

01:20:29.340 --> 01:20:31.079
That would be a fine way to go out.

01:20:31.140 --> 01:20:33.239
Will they kill me?

01:20:33.300 --> 01:20:35.100
Like they killed Hillstorm?

01:20:35.159 --> 01:20:36.659
He caught himself.

01:20:36.720 --> 01:20:39.600
It was instinct to see a night wing and

01:20:39.600 --> 01:20:41.279
think of his brother's death, but

01:20:41.279 --> 01:20:43.680
according to Queen Scarlet, Hailstorm

01:20:43.680 --> 01:20:47.159
wasn't dead. 12 other ice wing prisoners

01:20:47.159 --> 01:20:49.439
definitely were, though, and somewhere in

01:20:49.439 --> 01:20:51.239
this village were the dragons who killed

01:20:51.239 --> 01:20:51.479
them.

01:20:51.600 --> 01:20:54.720
Obsidian beckoned Winter and the others

01:20:54.720 --> 01:20:57.300
forward with his tail, and the 2 guards

01:20:57.300 --> 01:21:00.000
stepped aside to let them pass, smirking

01:21:00.000 --> 01:21:02.220
in a horribly superior night wing sort of

01:21:02.220 --> 01:21:02.399
way.

01:21:02.460 --> 01:21:06.000
What do you think those smug expressions

01:21:06.000 --> 01:21:06.359
are for?

01:21:06.420 --> 01:21:09.180
Kibley said loudly to winter?

01:21:09.239 --> 01:21:11.579
Doesn't seem like night wings have

01:21:11.579 --> 01:21:13.260
anything left to be smug about, right?

01:21:13.319 --> 01:21:16.380
I mean, they've gone from claiming to be

01:21:16.380 --> 01:21:19.020
the most powerful tribe in Pyria, to

01:21:19.020 --> 01:21:21.239
homeless and pathetic, and bowing to rain

01:21:21.239 --> 01:21:21.600
wings.

01:21:21.720 --> 01:21:24.899
All 3 guards bristled, flaring their

01:21:24.899 --> 01:21:25.199
wings.

01:21:25.260 --> 01:21:28.619
What's wrong with bowing to a rain wing?

01:21:28.680 --> 01:21:29.939
Kinkaju demanded.

01:21:30.000 --> 01:21:33.060
Kibli, quit making things worse.

01:21:33.180 --> 01:21:34.560
Moon hissed.

01:21:34.619 --> 01:21:39.420
I was just wondering, he said calmly, with

01:21:39.420 --> 01:21:40.319
a wink at winter.

01:21:40.380 --> 01:21:43.800
Winter knew what he was doing, and it had

01:21:43.800 --> 01:21:44.039
worked.

01:21:44.100 --> 01:21:46.319
Kibley's words had riled up the night

01:21:46.319 --> 01:21:48.600
wings, and made Winter feel better at the

01:21:48.600 --> 01:21:48.840
same time.

01:21:48.960 --> 01:21:52.500
All of his senses were on high alert as

01:21:52.500 --> 01:21:54.539
they walked into the village, and more

01:21:54.539 --> 01:21:56.159
and more night wings appeared around

01:21:56.159 --> 01:21:56.399
them.

01:21:56.460 --> 01:21:59.640
His eyes darted around, assessing their

01:21:59.640 --> 01:22:00.000
activity.

01:22:00.060 --> 01:22:03.180
He expected plotting and scheming and

01:22:03.180 --> 01:22:03.960
battle training.

01:22:04.020 --> 01:22:06.720
But most of the night wings seemed to be

01:22:06.720 --> 01:22:09.060
busily engaged in very ordinary things.

01:22:09.119 --> 01:22:12.600
A group of 10 were grappling with vines

01:22:12.600 --> 01:22:15.420
and bushes and stunted trees, trying to

01:22:15.420 --> 01:22:16.619
expand the open space.

01:22:16.680 --> 01:22:19.020
Three more were washing fruit in the

01:22:19.020 --> 01:22:21.300
river, near a set of cooking fires dug

01:22:21.300 --> 01:22:23.699
into the ground, where another 4 night

01:22:23.699 --> 01:22:25.260
wings were roasting what looked like

01:22:25.260 --> 01:22:26.159
small pigs.

01:22:26.220 --> 01:22:29.279
Several others were working on shoring up

01:22:29.279 --> 01:22:31.140
their ramshackle huts that dotted the

01:22:31.140 --> 01:22:31.560
cleared area.

01:22:31.619 --> 01:22:34.920
Winter saw a young dragon scramble onto a

01:22:34.920 --> 01:22:37.979
roof to add more giant palm leaves, only

01:22:37.979 --> 01:22:39.960
to have the entire structure cave in

01:22:39.960 --> 01:22:40.500
underneath her.

01:22:40.560 --> 01:22:43.020
She plummeted to the ground with a yell

01:22:43.020 --> 01:22:45.539
and a crash, and a few other night wings

01:22:45.539 --> 01:22:46.439
began shouting at her.

01:22:46.560 --> 01:22:49.380
There were a few rain wings who might

01:22:49.380 --> 01:22:50.460
have helped them build all this.

01:22:50.520 --> 01:22:53.699
Kinkaju explained suddenly. glancing at

01:22:53.699 --> 01:22:54.539
Winter and Kibley.

01:22:54.659 --> 01:22:56.699
We could have showed them how to set up

01:22:56.699 --> 01:22:58.920
their village in the treetops, like ours

01:22:58.920 --> 01:23:00.659
but the night wings didn't want help.

01:23:00.720 --> 01:23:02.939
Plus they thought it was too sunny up

01:23:02.939 --> 01:23:03.180
there.

01:23:03.239 --> 01:23:05.100
Like, what does that even mean?

01:23:05.220 --> 01:23:07.739
How could it ever be too sunny?

01:23:07.800 --> 01:23:10.500
It was cooler down on the rainforest

01:23:10.500 --> 01:23:12.659
floor, but it was all so muddier.

01:23:12.720 --> 01:23:15.539
Winter wasn't sure which option he'd

01:23:15.539 --> 01:23:17.460
prefer, but he was glad he didn't have to

01:23:17.460 --> 01:23:18.060
live here at all.

01:23:18.119 --> 01:23:20.579
He wondered if the Night Wings really

01:23:20.579 --> 01:23:22.260
founded an improvement over their last

01:23:22.260 --> 01:23:22.619
home.

01:23:22.680 --> 01:23:26.399
Mother, Moon cried suddenly.

01:23:26.460 --> 01:23:28.979
Her whole face lit up, like the sun

01:23:28.979 --> 01:23:30.420
sparkling off a glacier.

01:23:30.479 --> 01:23:32.579
She flew across the clearing and threw

01:23:32.579 --> 01:23:35.159
her wings around a tall, thin dragon, who

01:23:35.159 --> 01:23:36.899
looked a lot like moon, without the

01:23:36.899 --> 01:23:39.000
silver teardrop scales near her eyes.

01:23:39.060 --> 01:23:40.859
Moon.

01:23:40.920 --> 01:23:42.420
The night wing gasped.

01:23:42.539 --> 01:23:45.539
Her expression went from quietly tired, to

01:23:45.539 --> 01:23:48.180
startled to overjoyed, and she wrapped

01:23:48.180 --> 01:23:49.800
the dragonette in close to her with

01:23:49.800 --> 01:23:50.819
fierce affection.

01:23:50.880 --> 01:23:53.699
Winter felt a strange twinge watching

01:23:53.699 --> 01:23:54.300
them.

01:23:54.359 --> 01:23:56.699
Ice wings don't hug like that.

01:23:56.760 --> 01:23:58.439
He reminded himself.

01:23:58.500 --> 01:24:00.960
At least royal ones don't.

01:24:01.079 --> 01:24:03.119
It would be undignified.

01:24:03.180 --> 01:24:06.359
He couldn't imagine his mother or father

01:24:06.359 --> 01:24:08.760
wrapping their wings around him, or

01:24:08.760 --> 01:24:10.260
looking that happy to see him, for that

01:24:10.260 --> 01:24:10.439
matter.

01:24:10.500 --> 01:24:13.619
Was this how all night wings were with

01:24:13.619 --> 01:24:14.399
their dragonettes?

01:24:14.460 --> 01:24:17.100
He glanced around the clearing, looking

01:24:17.100 --> 01:24:19.319
for dragons younger than himself, and

01:24:19.319 --> 01:24:21.359
realized they were almost none.

01:24:21.420 --> 01:24:23.939
It took him a while to finally spot one

01:24:23.939 --> 01:24:25.859
by the river, leaning against his

01:24:25.859 --> 01:24:27.720
mother's side and helping to wash fruit.

01:24:27.779 --> 01:24:30.600
She had one wing tented protectively over

01:24:30.600 --> 01:24:30.840
him.

01:24:30.960 --> 01:24:33.899
And there was another small dragonette

01:24:33.899 --> 01:24:36.239
over by a fallen tree, practicing her

01:24:36.239 --> 01:24:36.720
flying.

01:24:36.779 --> 01:24:39.000
A dragon who might be her father stood

01:24:39.000 --> 01:24:40.979
beside her, catching her when she fell

01:24:40.979 --> 01:24:41.579
awkwardly.

01:24:41.640 --> 01:24:44.220
There was something protective and proud

01:24:44.220 --> 01:24:45.539
about the way he was standing too.

01:24:45.600 --> 01:24:49.260
Winter pulled his gaze away and noticed

01:24:49.260 --> 01:24:51.899
odd looks on the other dragonette's faces

01:24:51.899 --> 01:24:53.460
Kibli and Kinkaju.

01:24:53.579 --> 01:24:55.739
There was something faintly wistful in

01:24:55.739 --> 01:24:57.239
their expressions as they watched Moon

01:24:57.239 --> 01:24:57.840
and her mother.

01:24:57.899 --> 01:25:00.359
He caught himself starting to wonder what

01:25:00.359 --> 01:25:01.560
their family stories were.

01:25:01.680 --> 01:25:05.520
They look like lonely cows, he thought

01:25:05.520 --> 01:25:06.300
ferociously.

01:25:06.359 --> 01:25:08.880
I refuse to moon about like that over

01:25:08.880 --> 01:25:09.300
anything.

01:25:09.359 --> 01:25:11.819
My parents are perfect the way they are.

01:25:11.880 --> 01:25:15.060
They made me strong and dangerous, a true

01:25:15.060 --> 01:25:17.399
dragon, stronger than anyone else here

01:25:17.399 --> 01:25:18.000
that's for sure.

01:25:18.060 --> 01:25:21.479
I may not be as fearsome as Hellstorm, but

01:25:21.479 --> 01:25:24.239
still, I'm an ice wing, the greatest

01:25:24.239 --> 01:25:25.439
tribe in Pyria.

01:25:25.500 --> 01:25:28.979
I must act like one, especially here, with

01:25:28.979 --> 01:25:31.260
so many night wing eyes on me, like

01:25:31.260 --> 01:25:33.119
father says, be strong.

01:25:33.180 --> 01:25:36.479
Be vigilant, strike 1st, and trust

01:25:36.479 --> 01:25:37.500
nobody.

01:25:37.560 --> 01:25:39.899
What are you doing here?

01:25:39.960 --> 01:25:42.840
Moon's mother asked, holding Moon by her

01:25:42.840 --> 01:25:43.140
shoulders.

01:25:43.199 --> 01:25:45.960
Moon curled her wings in, her face

01:25:45.960 --> 01:25:46.319
falling.

01:25:46.380 --> 01:25:48.359
I didn't get thrown out.

01:25:48.420 --> 01:25:51.840
She said in a soft voice, I didn't do

01:25:51.840 --> 01:25:53.579
anything wrong, and nobody...

01:25:53.640 --> 01:25:55.439
That didn't happen, mother.

01:25:55.560 --> 01:25:59.279
Winter realized that Moon was responding

01:25:59.279 --> 01:26:01.020
to something her mother was thinking.

01:26:01.079 --> 01:26:04.020
He touched his Skyfire pouch again, and

01:26:04.020 --> 01:26:05.699
wondered if the little rock could protect

01:26:05.699 --> 01:26:08.579
him from all the night wings here, or if

01:26:08.579 --> 01:26:10.439
there were other secret mind readers

01:26:10.439 --> 01:26:11.939
invading his thoughts right now.

01:26:11.939 --> 01:26:16.500
Shh, said the older dragon, pulling moon

01:26:16.500 --> 01:26:19.020
close again, she eyed Winter and Kibli

01:26:19.020 --> 01:26:19.439
warily.

01:26:19.500 --> 01:26:23.520
But I did make friends, Moon said.

01:26:23.579 --> 01:26:25.619
She wriggled out of her mother's grasp.

01:26:25.739 --> 01:26:27.000
You should meet them.

01:26:27.060 --> 01:26:29.279
She turned toward the others, and her

01:26:29.279 --> 01:26:30.000
eyes went wide.

01:26:30.060 --> 01:26:32.579
No, stop, she shouted.

01:26:32.640 --> 01:26:33.239
He's not?

01:26:33.359 --> 01:26:36.300
Suddenly, Claus encircled Winter's neck

01:26:36.300 --> 01:26:37.979
and his body was thrown to the ground

01:26:37.979 --> 01:26:39.420
with a jarring thud.

01:26:39.479 --> 01:26:41.819
Someone bigger and heavier leaped on top

01:26:41.819 --> 01:26:43.260
of him, pinning him down.

01:26:43.319 --> 01:26:47.159
Don't ball the struggling ice wing, said

01:26:47.159 --> 01:26:48.119
an unfamiliar voice.

01:26:48.180 --> 01:26:50.039
You're under arrest.

01:26:50.159 --> 01:26:54.300
Chapter 5.

01:26:54.600 --> 01:26:58.140
Winter warred with fury, struggling to

01:26:58.140 --> 01:27:00.300
fight back, but his attacker had him

01:27:00.300 --> 01:27:01.680
expertly immobilized.

01:27:01.739 --> 01:27:03.359
Stop it.

01:27:03.420 --> 01:27:04.140
Get off him.

01:27:04.260 --> 01:27:05.460
Moon yelled.

01:27:05.579 --> 01:27:07.979
Winter couldn't see much, with his snout

01:27:07.979 --> 01:27:10.260
pressed into the ground, but he felt the

01:27:10.260 --> 01:27:12.180
weight of dragons pushing and grappling

01:27:12.180 --> 01:27:12.779
on his wings.

01:27:12.840 --> 01:27:14.880
He's on our side.

01:27:14.939 --> 01:27:18.060
Kingachu cried, or he was, before you

01:27:18.060 --> 01:27:19.800
randomly attacked him for no reason.

01:27:19.859 --> 01:27:21.840
Now he'll never like us again.

01:27:21.899 --> 01:27:24.180
I wasn't going to anyway.

01:27:24.239 --> 01:27:27.840
Winter bellowed as best he could, seething

01:27:27.840 --> 01:27:29.279
with rage and humiliation.

01:27:29.340 --> 01:27:31.079
I didn't like you before either.

01:27:31.199 --> 01:27:32.279
I don't like any of you.

01:27:32.340 --> 01:27:35.039
And I'm going to murder this night wing.

01:27:35.159 --> 01:27:37.079
I don't know.

01:27:37.140 --> 01:27:41.520
It sounds kind of murder e, Kinkachu, said

01:27:41.520 --> 01:27:41.880
the voice.

01:27:41.939 --> 01:27:44.819
And we heard there's an extra dangerous

01:27:44.819 --> 01:27:47.039
ice swing on the loose right now, so I'm

01:27:47.039 --> 01:27:48.779
going to keep sitting on him until I get

01:27:48.779 --> 01:27:49.439
further instructions.

01:27:49.500 --> 01:27:51.659
I'm instructing you.

01:27:51.720 --> 01:27:53.279
Kinkaju yelped.

01:27:53.340 --> 01:27:54.779
He's not the dangerous one.

01:27:54.899 --> 01:27:56.340
That's his sister.

01:27:56.460 --> 01:27:58.500
It's true.

01:27:58.560 --> 01:28:00.359
Kibli chimed in.

01:28:00.420 --> 01:28:01.859
This one is honorable.

01:28:01.920 --> 01:28:04.319
He's no sneak in the night assassin.

01:28:04.380 --> 01:28:05.939
Hey.

01:28:06.060 --> 01:28:09.119
Ouch. said the dragon on top of winter.

01:28:09.180 --> 01:28:11.579
Nothing wrong with assassins.

01:28:11.640 --> 01:28:13.380
Who said there was anything dishonorable

01:28:13.380 --> 01:28:14.220
about assassins?

01:28:14.279 --> 01:28:17.579
They're just not allowed to kill my... my

01:28:17.579 --> 01:28:18.000
queen.

01:28:18.060 --> 01:28:21.000
It's my job to stop them, and drop some

01:28:21.000 --> 01:28:23.399
violence on their heads, but I'm not

01:28:23.399 --> 01:28:24.960
judging them, Sheesh.

01:28:25.020 --> 01:28:28.319
He's not here to kill glory, Moon said.

01:28:28.380 --> 01:28:31.140
If he were, he would tell you, and he'd

01:28:31.140 --> 01:28:32.279
challenge her in open combat.

01:28:32.340 --> 01:28:34.319
Would I?

01:28:34.380 --> 01:28:35.579
Winter wondered.

01:28:35.640 --> 01:28:36.840
True.

01:28:36.899 --> 01:28:38.880
I wouldn't hurt a nothing rain wing.

01:28:38.939 --> 01:28:41.039
But if I'd had a chance to kill the night

01:28:41.039 --> 01:28:41.760
wing queen.

01:28:41.819 --> 01:28:43.920
Would I have done it the honorable way?

01:28:43.920 --> 01:28:45.300
Or any way possible?

01:28:45.359 --> 01:28:47.939
What would mother have wanted me to do?

01:28:48.000 --> 01:28:51.239
Anyway possible, he guessed.

01:28:51.300 --> 01:28:53.939
That was how Icicle and Hellstorm had

01:28:53.939 --> 01:28:54.300
been trained.

01:28:54.420 --> 01:28:56.520
Death Bringer.

01:28:56.640 --> 01:28:59.520
Another new voice thundered, loud enough

01:28:59.520 --> 01:29:01.140
to rattle the leaves overhead.

01:29:01.199 --> 01:29:02.819
What are you doing?

01:29:02.880 --> 01:29:05.340
Saving you?

01:29:05.399 --> 01:29:06.779
Protecting the forest?

01:29:06.840 --> 01:29:09.899
Defending our new home, sitting on a very

01:29:09.899 --> 01:29:13.500
cold ice wing, said the night wing, from

01:29:13.500 --> 01:29:14.760
his perch on Winters back.

01:29:14.819 --> 01:29:16.859
You know, the usual.

01:29:16.920 --> 01:29:19.439
A murmur eddied through the village as

01:29:19.439 --> 01:29:20.699
footsteps approached.

01:29:20.760 --> 01:29:22.619
Winter tried to wriggle around to see who

01:29:22.619 --> 01:29:25.020
was coming, but Death Bringer reached out

01:29:25.020 --> 01:29:26.460
and gently pinned his head to the ground

01:29:26.460 --> 01:29:26.760
again.

01:29:26.880 --> 01:29:30.000
A grotesque greenish brown beetle with

01:29:30.000 --> 01:29:33.119
about 4000 legs came scuttling up and

01:29:33.119 --> 01:29:35.399
began creeping curiously onto Winter's

01:29:35.399 --> 01:29:35.939
nose.

01:29:36.119 --> 01:29:40.079
Stop arresting my guests, said the

01:29:40.079 --> 01:29:42.119
newcomer, pausing beside winter.

01:29:42.180 --> 01:29:45.119
It's not romantic or heroic, it's

01:29:45.119 --> 01:29:45.479
annoying.

01:29:45.539 --> 01:29:47.640
I've told you this before.

01:29:47.699 --> 01:29:51.840
I know, Deathbringer said. sounding

01:29:51.840 --> 01:29:52.380
aggrieved.

01:29:52.439 --> 01:29:55.260
But look, it's an ice wing.

01:29:55.319 --> 01:29:57.600
Sonny specifically said an ice wing tried

01:29:57.600 --> 01:29:59.340
to kill all the prophecy dragonettes.

01:29:59.399 --> 01:30:01.500
This is definitely opinion before asking

01:30:01.500 --> 01:30:03.060
questions kind of situation.

01:30:03.119 --> 01:30:05.699
All right, off.

01:30:05.760 --> 01:30:07.739
Glory said firmly.

01:30:07.800 --> 01:30:09.960
The weight on top of winter suddenly

01:30:09.960 --> 01:30:12.420
lifted. as if she'd hauled Death Bringer

01:30:12.420 --> 01:30:13.319
off with her own talons.

01:30:13.439 --> 01:30:16.079
I am going to replace you as my

01:30:16.079 --> 01:30:16.680
bodyguard.

01:30:16.739 --> 01:30:18.420
If you seriously can't tell the

01:30:18.420 --> 01:30:20.279
difference between a male ice wing

01:30:20.279 --> 01:30:22.800
traveling with my friends, Kinkaju and

01:30:22.800 --> 01:30:25.380
Moon Watcher, and a lone female ice wing

01:30:25.380 --> 01:30:26.039
out to kill me.

01:30:26.100 --> 01:30:28.140
Pay a little more attention to detail

01:30:28.140 --> 01:30:28.979
Deathbringer.

01:30:29.039 --> 01:30:31.920
Also, by the way, you're one to talk

01:30:31.920 --> 01:30:33.840
about killing prophecy dragonettes.

01:30:33.899 --> 01:30:37.319
Winter scrambled upright, flinging the

01:30:37.319 --> 01:30:39.300
beetle off his nose and baring his teeth

01:30:39.300 --> 01:30:40.079
as he spun around.

01:30:40.140 --> 01:30:43.260
His attacker was a night wing a few years

01:30:43.260 --> 01:30:46.260
older than him, wiry and graceful, and

01:30:46.260 --> 01:30:47.819
clearly trained to fight from the way he

01:30:47.819 --> 01:30:49.920
stood, and the way he was assessing

01:30:49.920 --> 01:30:50.279
winter.

01:30:50.340 --> 01:30:53.579
Winter lunged toward him, and found his

01:30:53.579 --> 01:30:55.800
way blocked by a dark green dragon with

01:30:55.800 --> 01:30:58.079
flares of orange around her ears, and

01:30:58.079 --> 01:30:59.399
along the underside of her wings.

01:30:59.460 --> 01:31:01.979
She reached out and took one of Winter's

01:31:01.979 --> 01:31:04.560
talons, pressing it between hers, and

01:31:04.560 --> 01:31:06.060
lowering her head in a small bow.

01:31:06.119 --> 01:31:09.899
We are so honored to have Queen Glacier's

01:31:09.899 --> 01:31:12.060
nephew in our forest, she said.

01:31:12.119 --> 01:31:15.479
I sincerely apologize for the outrageous

01:31:15.479 --> 01:31:17.579
behavior of my brain dead bodyguard.

01:31:17.640 --> 01:31:20.100
You should have been escorted at once to

01:31:20.100 --> 01:31:23.039
my royal pavilion, not attacked in such a

01:31:23.039 --> 01:31:24.119
disrespectful manner.

01:31:24.180 --> 01:31:27.119
She glanced around the gawking night

01:31:27.119 --> 01:31:27.600
wings.

01:31:27.659 --> 01:31:29.399
Everyone back to work?

01:31:29.460 --> 01:31:30.659
Right now.

01:31:30.720 --> 01:31:33.359
To winter's surprise, they obeyed her.

01:31:33.420 --> 01:31:35.460
Although there were a few muttered

01:31:35.460 --> 01:31:37.500
grumbles and 2 or 3 dragons who moved

01:31:37.500 --> 01:31:39.119
deliberately slowly.

01:31:39.180 --> 01:31:40.500
He hesitated.

01:31:40.560 --> 01:31:43.260
Every bone in his body wanted to fly into

01:31:43.260 --> 01:31:45.840
a rage and rip Deathbringer's wings off.

01:31:45.899 --> 01:31:48.239
He couldn't let a night wing treat him

01:31:48.239 --> 01:31:50.579
that way, especially in front of all the

01:31:50.579 --> 01:31:52.380
other night wings, and get away with it.

01:31:52.439 --> 01:31:55.260
But he'd never been greeted as visiting

01:31:55.260 --> 01:31:57.359
royalty before, and there was something

01:31:57.359 --> 01:31:59.340
irresistibly compelling about the way

01:31:59.340 --> 01:32:01.560
Queen Glory beckoned him to walk beside

01:32:01.560 --> 01:32:03.119
her. as if they were equals.

01:32:03.180 --> 01:32:05.819
Will he be punished?

01:32:05.880 --> 01:32:06.840
Winter demanded.

01:32:06.899 --> 01:32:08.460
Oh yes.

01:32:08.520 --> 01:32:11.520
Glory said, frowning at Deathbringer

01:32:11.520 --> 01:32:13.800
creatively and firmly.

01:32:13.859 --> 01:32:15.960
Very well.

01:32:16.020 --> 01:32:17.399
Winter said.

01:32:17.460 --> 01:32:19.739
He shook as much dirt off his wings as he

01:32:19.739 --> 01:32:21.899
could, and stepped up regally beside

01:32:21.899 --> 01:32:22.260
Glory.

01:32:22.319 --> 01:32:24.720
I don't have time to punish him myself

01:32:24.720 --> 01:32:25.199
anyway.

01:32:25.260 --> 01:32:27.300
We have urgent matters to discuss.

01:32:27.359 --> 01:32:31.859
Indeed, said the queen, turning to lead

01:32:31.859 --> 01:32:32.880
the way out of the village.

01:32:32.939 --> 01:32:35.640
Behind him, Winter heard Moon saying

01:32:35.640 --> 01:32:37.260
goodbye to her mother, and the others

01:32:37.260 --> 01:32:38.220
hurrying to join him.

01:32:38.279 --> 01:32:41.819
Sunny told me some of the details, but I

01:32:41.819 --> 01:32:42.720
hope you can fill in the rest.

01:32:42.779 --> 01:32:47.279
I can, Kinkaju offered, bouncing up on

01:32:47.279 --> 01:32:48.180
Glory's other side.

01:32:48.239 --> 01:32:52.260
Winter sister, icicle, who is like wicked

01:32:52.260 --> 01:32:54.239
scary, by the way, was secretly

01:32:54.239 --> 01:32:56.640
conspiring with Queen Scarlet, because it

01:32:56.640 --> 01:32:59.220
turns out Winter's brother is like

01:32:59.220 --> 01:33:02.699
actually alive, not dead like everyone

01:33:02.699 --> 01:33:05.159
thought, and Scarlet's totally got him

01:33:05.159 --> 01:33:06.000
locked up somewhere.

01:33:06.119 --> 01:33:09.060
So icicle was going to kill Starflight to

01:33:09.060 --> 01:33:12.840
get him back, except then Moon and Kibley

01:33:12.840 --> 01:33:15.479
and Winter, completely heroically stopped

01:33:15.479 --> 01:33:18.539
her, and it was apparently amazing, and I

01:33:18.539 --> 01:33:19.199
missed the whole thing.

01:33:19.260 --> 01:33:20.760
Can you believe it?

01:33:20.819 --> 01:33:23.939
And so then Icicle flew off, and we

01:33:23.939 --> 01:33:26.460
figure she's coming here to kill you.

01:33:26.520 --> 01:33:28.319
So we're here to completely heroically

01:33:28.319 --> 01:33:30.899
stop her, again, and also find out what

01:33:30.899 --> 01:33:32.939
she knows, so we can rescue Winter's

01:33:32.939 --> 01:33:33.479
brother ourselves.

01:33:33.539 --> 01:33:36.539
Also, hello, school is awesome.

01:33:36.659 --> 01:33:37.619
How are you?

01:33:37.680 --> 01:33:40.140
You are in as much trouble as

01:33:40.140 --> 01:33:40.800
Deathbringer.

01:33:40.859 --> 01:33:43.439
Gloria said sternly, looking down at the

01:33:43.439 --> 01:33:44.159
dragonette.

01:33:44.220 --> 01:33:45.539
What were you thinking?

01:33:45.600 --> 01:33:47.039
Leaving school without permission?

01:33:47.039 --> 01:33:48.960
When everyone was already in such a

01:33:48.960 --> 01:33:49.380
state?

01:33:49.500 --> 01:33:51.600
Do you know how worried Sonny and Clay

01:33:51.600 --> 01:33:51.899
have been?

01:33:51.960 --> 01:33:55.380
Kinkachu stopped in her tracks with an

01:33:55.380 --> 01:33:57.479
expression of deep dismay, and an

01:33:57.479 --> 01:33:59.279
explosion of dark blue splotches across

01:33:59.279 --> 01:33:59.819
her scales.

01:33:59.939 --> 01:34:02.520
Oh no, she cried.

01:34:02.579 --> 01:34:03.659
I'm sorry?

01:34:03.779 --> 01:34:05.760
didn't turtle tell them where we went?

01:34:05.819 --> 01:34:09.960
Yes, and that certainly helped, Glory

01:34:09.960 --> 01:34:10.800
said with a snort.

01:34:10.859 --> 01:34:12.300
Good news.

01:34:12.539 --> 01:34:13.800
Four of your students have gone off to

01:34:13.800 --> 01:34:15.659
find a dragon who just tried to kill you

01:34:15.659 --> 01:34:18.180
in order to find another dragon who has

01:34:18.180 --> 01:34:20.399
tried to kill you about 90 dozen times.

01:34:20.460 --> 01:34:21.539
Oh, excellent.

01:34:21.600 --> 01:34:22.619
Thanks, turtle.

01:34:22.680 --> 01:34:24.300
Now I don't have to worry at all.

01:34:24.359 --> 01:34:26.880
I mean, we were hoping somebody would

01:34:26.880 --> 01:34:28.619
take care of the vengeful and deadly

01:34:28.619 --> 01:34:31.319
Queen Scarlet Forest, probably a bunch of

01:34:31.319 --> 01:34:32.159
5 year olds.

01:34:32.279 --> 01:34:34.199
Very reassuring indeed.

01:34:34.260 --> 01:34:36.720
Moon ducked her head.

01:34:36.779 --> 01:34:40.680
Sorry, Your Majesty, she said, and this

01:34:40.680 --> 01:34:42.479
felt urgent.

01:34:42.539 --> 01:34:46.020
She glanced sideways at winter, and an

01:34:46.020 --> 01:34:48.119
odd flicker of something like gratitude

01:34:48.119 --> 01:34:49.319
went off in his chest.

01:34:49.380 --> 01:34:53.340
Stupid, stupid, as if he cared that she

01:34:53.340 --> 01:34:54.960
knew how important it was to find his

01:34:54.960 --> 01:34:55.140
brother.

01:34:55.199 --> 01:34:58.739
I didn't ask for help, and I don't need

01:34:58.739 --> 01:34:58.979
it.

01:34:59.039 --> 01:35:01.380
It is urgent.

01:35:01.439 --> 01:35:02.819
Kinkachu said.

01:35:02.880 --> 01:35:05.939
We think Icicle is coming here next to

01:35:05.939 --> 01:35:06.479
kill you.

01:35:06.600 --> 01:35:09.899
That's what I said.

01:35:10.020 --> 01:35:13.140
Offered Deathbringer, who was trailing

01:35:13.140 --> 01:35:14.460
behind them with an expression that

01:35:14.460 --> 01:35:16.500
looked closer to amused than repentant.

01:35:16.560 --> 01:35:18.180
Ahem.

01:35:18.180 --> 01:35:19.560
Ahem.

01:35:19.680 --> 01:35:22.380
Glory considered kinkaju thoughtfully.

01:35:22.439 --> 01:35:24.000
Do you really think so?

01:35:24.060 --> 01:35:27.840
Absolutely, Kibley interjected.

01:35:27.899 --> 01:35:30.000
You're the only target she has left.

01:35:30.060 --> 01:35:31.739
It's the smart choice for her.

01:35:31.800 --> 01:35:34.260
I'd wager a month of lizards on it.

01:35:34.319 --> 01:35:36.840
That would be irritating.

01:35:36.899 --> 01:35:38.039
Glory said.

01:35:38.100 --> 01:35:40.859
If Deathbringer turns out to be right, I

01:35:40.859 --> 01:35:40.979
mean.

01:35:41.039 --> 01:35:43.079
It makes him really insufferable.

01:35:43.199 --> 01:35:47.579
I am here to search for my sister, Winter

01:35:47.579 --> 01:35:48.600
said to Queen Glory.

01:35:48.659 --> 01:35:51.180
I just need your assurance that no one

01:35:51.180 --> 01:35:52.920
will interfere with me while I do that.

01:35:52.979 --> 01:35:56.220
He cast a dark glands over his shoulder

01:35:56.220 --> 01:35:56.939
at Deathbringer.

01:35:57.000 --> 01:36:00.239
I think we can do better than that said

01:36:00.239 --> 01:36:00.600
the queen.

01:36:00.659 --> 01:36:03.359
She stopped and tilted her snout at one

01:36:03.359 --> 01:36:04.260
of the branches overhead.

01:36:04.319 --> 01:36:05.760
Banana?

01:36:05.880 --> 01:36:07.439
Winter frowned.

01:36:07.500 --> 01:36:09.060
No, thank you.

01:36:09.119 --> 01:36:12.359
But as he spoke, he noticed a shimmering

01:36:12.359 --> 01:36:14.220
in the air around the branch, and then

01:36:14.220 --> 01:36:16.380
all at once, there was a dragon sitting

01:36:16.380 --> 01:36:18.840
there, in a rather hideous shade of pink

01:36:18.840 --> 01:36:20.279
that winter had never seen before.

01:36:20.340 --> 01:36:24.239
Actually, it's heliconia, Your Majesty

01:36:24.239 --> 01:36:26.460
said the rain wing, but good guess.

01:36:26.579 --> 01:36:28.560
Glory flicked her tail.

01:36:28.680 --> 01:36:30.000
Heliconia.

01:36:30.060 --> 01:36:32.100
Please tell my scout captains to meet me

01:36:32.100 --> 01:36:33.539
at the pavilion as soon as possible.

01:36:33.600 --> 01:36:37.079
The pink dragon scales started fading

01:36:37.079 --> 01:36:38.039
into shades of blue.

01:36:38.100 --> 01:36:40.619
But I shouldn't leave you unguarded

01:36:40.619 --> 01:36:41.039
majesty.

01:36:41.100 --> 01:36:44.340
The rain wing queen waved her talons at

01:36:44.340 --> 01:36:45.180
the surrounding trees.

01:36:45.239 --> 01:36:48.479
I think 7 guards are quite sufficient.

01:36:48.539 --> 01:36:52.380
One might call it overkill, in fact, one

01:36:52.380 --> 01:36:54.539
might even infer that somebody doesn't

01:36:54.539 --> 01:36:56.340
think he can do his job properly on his

01:36:56.340 --> 01:36:56.579
own.

01:36:56.640 --> 01:36:59.520
Also that he must think I'm either blind

01:36:59.520 --> 01:37:02.520
and deaf or recently hit on the head, that

01:37:02.520 --> 01:37:04.319
I wouldn't notice the addition of 5 more

01:37:04.319 --> 01:37:05.760
dragons following me around.

01:37:05.819 --> 01:37:10.260
The whole point of a top secret invisible

01:37:10.260 --> 01:37:10.680
guard.

01:37:10.739 --> 01:37:13.800
Deathbringer said severely, is for them

01:37:13.800 --> 01:37:15.420
to be invisible and secret.

01:37:15.479 --> 01:37:18.600
Therefore, it is extremely unhelpful for

01:37:18.600 --> 01:37:21.060
certain queens to go pointing them out

01:37:21.060 --> 01:37:22.859
and discussing them loudly with the

01:37:22.859 --> 01:37:23.760
entire rainforest.

01:37:23.819 --> 01:37:28.680
Go now, Glory said to Heliconia, ignoring

01:37:28.680 --> 01:37:29.220
Deathbringer.

01:37:29.279 --> 01:37:31.739
The rain wing guard bowed immediately and

01:37:31.739 --> 01:37:32.279
vanish.

01:37:32.340 --> 01:37:34.560
Winter could barely hear her wing beats

01:37:34.560 --> 01:37:36.659
flapping away over the buzzing, dripping

01:37:36.659 --> 01:37:37.739
sounds of the rainforest.

01:37:37.800 --> 01:37:40.439
He curled his talons and stared up at the

01:37:40.439 --> 01:37:40.680
trees.

01:37:40.800 --> 01:37:43.979
There were 7 other dragons up there

01:37:43.979 --> 01:37:44.819
watching them.

01:37:44.939 --> 01:37:47.340
He couldn't see any sign of even one.

01:37:47.460 --> 01:37:50.520
All right, he admitted to himself

01:37:50.520 --> 01:37:51.420
grudgingly.

01:37:51.479 --> 01:37:53.460
That's kind of an impressive skill.

01:37:53.579 --> 01:37:56.640
Ice wings were good at hiding in the snow

01:37:56.640 --> 01:37:59.220
of course, but here in the rainforest, he

01:37:59.220 --> 01:38:01.920
stuck out like a broken wing, which means

01:38:01.920 --> 01:38:03.479
icicle wheel 2 at least.

01:38:03.539 --> 01:38:06.960
The pavilion is a short flight this way.

01:38:07.020 --> 01:38:08.760
Glory explained to winter.

01:38:08.819 --> 01:38:11.340
I had it built halfway between the night

01:38:11.340 --> 01:38:12.840
wings and the rain wings for anything

01:38:12.840 --> 01:38:13.319
official.

01:38:13.380 --> 01:38:16.380
She took to the air and Winter and the

01:38:16.380 --> 01:38:17.100
others followed her.

01:38:17.159 --> 01:38:19.500
He strained his ears to listen for the

01:38:19.500 --> 01:38:22.020
sound of 7 extra pairs of wings flying

01:38:22.020 --> 01:38:24.119
alongside them, but it was impossible to

01:38:24.119 --> 01:38:25.979
separate them out from the others.

01:38:26.039 --> 01:38:29.880
Queen Glory's royal pavilion was a vast

01:38:29.880 --> 01:38:31.859
platform in the air, built on the

01:38:31.859 --> 01:38:34.020
branches of a circle of tall, overlapping

01:38:34.020 --> 01:38:34.319
trees.

01:38:34.380 --> 01:38:37.199
Winter guessed, that it was about midway

01:38:37.199 --> 01:38:38.819
between the ground and the treetops

01:38:38.819 --> 01:38:41.039
middle ground for the night wings and

01:38:41.039 --> 01:38:41.640
rain wings.

01:38:41.699 --> 01:38:43.680
It had a roof made of the same

01:38:43.680 --> 01:38:45.600
translucent leaves he'd seen in the

01:38:45.600 --> 01:38:47.159
library windows at Jade Mountain

01:38:47.159 --> 01:38:49.739
constructed atop twisted wooden columns

01:38:49.739 --> 01:38:52.079
instead of walls, so the pavilion was

01:38:52.079 --> 01:38:53.880
open to the air, but sheltered from the

01:38:53.880 --> 01:38:54.060
rain.

01:38:54.180 --> 01:38:57.060
Purple and blue morning glory flowers

01:38:57.060 --> 01:38:59.399
hung like bells from the vines that wound

01:38:59.399 --> 01:39:02.039
around each column, and delicate white

01:39:02.039 --> 01:39:04.800
orange pink orchids, grew from the mossy

01:39:04.800 --> 01:39:05.699
crevices of the trees.

01:39:05.760 --> 01:39:09.539
They landed one by one, shaking out their

01:39:09.539 --> 01:39:11.520
wings and sinking their talons into the

01:39:11.520 --> 01:39:12.600
claw marked wooden floor.

01:39:12.659 --> 01:39:15.720
Winter's gay swept over the interior of

01:39:15.720 --> 01:39:17.699
the pavilion, which was almost empty.

01:39:17.819 --> 01:39:20.939
Two scroll racks stood on either side of

01:39:20.939 --> 01:39:23.640
a simple raised days, only a few inches

01:39:23.640 --> 01:39:25.020
higher than the rest of the platform.

01:39:25.079 --> 01:39:27.659
Not much of a throne.

01:39:27.720 --> 01:39:30.720
Winter reflected, as Glory climbed onto

01:39:30.720 --> 01:39:32.220
it and settled herself with her tail

01:39:32.220 --> 01:39:33.060
around her claws.

01:39:33.180 --> 01:39:38.399
Now, she said, I know who you all are, but

01:39:38.399 --> 01:39:39.539
let's officially meet anyway.

01:39:39.600 --> 01:39:42.779
I'm glory, queen of the rain wings and

01:39:42.779 --> 01:39:43.380
the night wings.

01:39:43.439 --> 01:39:46.619
My overenthusiastic bodyguard there is

01:39:46.619 --> 01:39:47.159
Death Bringer.

01:39:47.279 --> 01:39:50.640
She lifted one talon into the air, and a

01:39:50.640 --> 01:39:52.680
sleek, beautiful gray sloth clambered

01:39:52.680 --> 01:39:54.300
down from the roof beams to curl up on

01:39:54.300 --> 01:39:54.600
her shoulder.

01:39:54.720 --> 01:39:56.939
And this is silver.

01:39:57.000 --> 01:40:01.319
Royal Pet, not royal lunch.

01:40:01.380 --> 01:40:03.899
Kibley said to Winter, nudging his wing.

01:40:04.020 --> 01:40:06.840
So try not to eat it, if you can restrain

01:40:06.840 --> 01:40:07.140
yourself.

01:40:07.199 --> 01:40:10.260
I'm Kibli, your majesty, one of Queen

01:40:10.260 --> 01:40:11.159
Thorn's advisors.

01:40:11.220 --> 01:40:12.779
Welcome.

01:40:12.840 --> 01:40:15.899
And then we have Moon Watcher, Kinkajoo

01:40:15.899 --> 01:40:18.300
and of course, Prince Winter, said

01:40:18.300 --> 01:40:18.720
Glory.

01:40:18.840 --> 01:40:21.180
My friends will be very relieved that

01:40:21.180 --> 01:40:21.720
you're all safe.

01:40:21.779 --> 01:40:24.420
Jade Mountain is a bit of a mess right

01:40:24.420 --> 01:40:26.220
now, and it didn't help to have one

01:40:26.220 --> 01:40:27.899
entire winglet disappear.

01:40:27.960 --> 01:40:31.619
Sorry, Kinkachu squeaked.

01:40:31.680 --> 01:40:35.039
Sorry, Moon agreed, looking down at her

01:40:35.039 --> 01:40:35.520
talons.

01:40:35.579 --> 01:40:37.800
There was a pause.

01:40:37.859 --> 01:40:40.619
The queen gazed sternly down her nose at

01:40:40.619 --> 01:40:41.340
the other dragons.

01:40:41.460 --> 01:40:43.199
All right.

01:40:43.260 --> 01:40:46.140
I'm sorry for making them worry, Kibley

01:40:46.140 --> 01:40:48.420
said, but winter can't go searching for

01:40:48.420 --> 01:40:50.100
icicle and hailstorm all by himself.

01:40:50.159 --> 01:40:54.600
Yes, I can, Winter said sharply.

01:40:54.659 --> 01:40:56.159
That's the entire plan.

01:40:56.220 --> 01:40:57.720
That's what I'm going to do.

01:40:57.779 --> 01:41:00.300
It suddenly occurred to him to wonder

01:41:00.300 --> 01:41:02.460
what would happen if someone else found

01:41:02.460 --> 01:41:04.979
icicle before he did, when they tried to

01:41:04.979 --> 01:41:05.340
hurt her.

01:41:05.399 --> 01:41:07.500
They'd end up dead if they did.

01:41:07.560 --> 01:41:10.800
She was bigger, more ferocious, and 10

01:41:10.800 --> 01:41:12.539
times better trained than any of these

01:41:12.539 --> 01:41:13.260
little dragons.

01:41:13.319 --> 01:41:16.920
His insides gave a weird lurch as he

01:41:16.920 --> 01:41:18.479
imagined what would happen if she found

01:41:18.479 --> 01:41:19.680
moon unguarded.

01:41:19.739 --> 01:41:21.840
Icicle would definitely kill her.

01:41:21.899 --> 01:41:24.359
The night wing who'd foiled her plan to

01:41:24.359 --> 01:41:25.260
kill Starflight.

01:41:25.319 --> 01:41:27.420
The Nightwing, who was already too close

01:41:27.420 --> 01:41:29.279
to her brother from Icicle's point of

01:41:29.279 --> 01:41:29.520
view.

01:41:29.579 --> 01:41:32.399
If she knew how I've been feeling about

01:41:32.399 --> 01:41:34.979
Moon, she'd be even more likely to kill

01:41:34.979 --> 01:41:36.720
her, he realized.

01:41:36.779 --> 01:41:38.939
Not that he felt that way about Moon

01:41:38.939 --> 01:41:39.420
anymore.

01:41:39.479 --> 01:41:40.859
He couldn't.

01:41:40.920 --> 01:41:44.100
Moon had lied to him and invaded his

01:41:44.100 --> 01:41:44.340
mind.

01:41:44.399 --> 01:41:46.800
He could put her safely back in the

01:41:46.800 --> 01:41:49.500
category of despicable conniving night

01:41:49.500 --> 01:41:49.739
wings.

01:41:49.800 --> 01:41:50.100
I hate.

01:41:50.159 --> 01:41:53.039
He glanced over at her as she lifted her

01:41:53.039 --> 01:41:53.819
head and met his eyes.

01:41:53.880 --> 01:41:57.300
Something in her expression said, I will

01:41:57.300 --> 01:41:58.739
help you whether you let me or not.

01:41:58.800 --> 01:42:01.979
Much like the 1st time they'd met, when

01:42:01.979 --> 01:42:03.720
she'd protected his scavenger, no matter

01:42:03.720 --> 01:42:04.859
how he threatened her.

01:42:04.920 --> 01:42:06.960
It doesn't mean anything.

01:42:07.020 --> 01:42:09.899
This twisting feeling in my chest.

01:42:09.960 --> 01:42:13.199
I can hate her, and still not want Icicle

01:42:13.199 --> 01:42:13.619
to kill her.

01:42:13.680 --> 01:42:16.380
It doesn't mean that I care about her.

01:42:16.439 --> 01:42:18.539
Well, let's see.

01:42:18.600 --> 01:42:21.180
Glory said, sitting up alertly.

01:42:21.239 --> 01:42:22.920
Here come my watchers.

01:42:22.979 --> 01:42:26.159
Dragons began appearing out of the leaves

01:42:26.159 --> 01:42:28.439
materializing like the sun coming out

01:42:28.439 --> 01:42:29.279
from behind a cloud.

01:42:29.340 --> 01:42:32.279
In alarmingly bright shades of yellow

01:42:32.279 --> 01:42:34.500
blue, and pink, they swooped into the

01:42:34.500 --> 01:42:36.539
pavilion and landed in a row in front of

01:42:36.539 --> 01:42:39.060
Queen Glory, until there were 6 dragons

01:42:39.060 --> 01:42:39.659
lined up.

01:42:39.720 --> 01:42:42.119
Although a line was hardly the right

01:42:42.119 --> 01:42:44.039
description for the slipshod way they

01:42:44.039 --> 01:42:44.399
were standing.

01:42:44.460 --> 01:42:47.460
Some of them with their wings akimbo, or

01:42:47.460 --> 01:42:49.140
their tails flopping all over the place.

01:42:49.199 --> 01:42:52.920
No discipline, Winter thought

01:42:52.920 --> 01:42:53.699
disapprovingly.

01:42:53.760 --> 01:42:56.699
Remembering the rigid, perfectly coiled

01:42:56.699 --> 01:42:58.619
lines of guards that attended Queen

01:42:58.619 --> 01:42:59.159
Glacier.

01:42:59.220 --> 01:43:01.920
He also remembered practicing for hours

01:43:01.920 --> 01:43:05.159
to get that stance just right, his wings

01:43:05.159 --> 01:43:07.920
folded exactly so, his tail in the right

01:43:07.920 --> 01:43:10.439
position, his snout up, and shoulders

01:43:10.439 --> 01:43:10.680
back.

01:43:10.739 --> 01:43:13.680
It was agony to hold that pose for too

01:43:13.680 --> 01:43:15.899
long, but his mother had made him stand

01:43:15.899 --> 01:43:18.359
like that before every meal, making him

01:43:18.359 --> 01:43:19.979
wait until she approved before letting

01:43:19.979 --> 01:43:20.399
him eat.

01:43:20.520 --> 01:43:24.239
These rain wings need someone to whip

01:43:24.239 --> 01:43:24.840
them into shape.

01:43:24.960 --> 01:43:27.960
He thought, resettling his tail with a

01:43:27.960 --> 01:43:29.340
small rattle of spikes.

01:43:29.399 --> 01:43:32.520
I called you in to ask if any of you have

01:43:32.520 --> 01:43:34.439
seen any sign of an ice wing today.

01:43:34.500 --> 01:43:36.060
Queen Glory said.

01:43:36.119 --> 01:43:38.579
For those of you who don't remember the

01:43:38.579 --> 01:43:40.920
lessons, those are the white or blue

01:43:40.920 --> 01:43:43.020
dragons with spiked tails and cold

01:43:43.020 --> 01:43:43.800
scales.

01:43:43.859 --> 01:43:47.100
One of the rain wings leaned toward her.

01:43:47.159 --> 01:43:49.199
In a loud whisper that carried to the

01:43:49.199 --> 01:43:51.060
other side of the pavilion, he hissed

01:43:51.060 --> 01:43:54.239
Your majesty, I think there's one of

01:43:54.239 --> 01:43:54.479
them.

01:43:54.600 --> 01:43:56.579
Right behind me.

01:43:56.640 --> 01:44:00.060
The dragon next to him looked around in

01:44:00.060 --> 01:44:02.220
alarm, spotted winter, and leaped

01:44:02.220 --> 01:44:04.079
backward, nearly knocking one of her

01:44:04.079 --> 01:44:05.220
companions off the platform.

01:44:05.279 --> 01:44:08.340
Oh my gosh, is that what they look like?

01:44:08.460 --> 01:44:09.479
She cried.

01:44:09.600 --> 01:44:11.880
Why is it pointy all over?

01:44:11.939 --> 01:44:14.880
Look at its tail. yelped another.

01:44:14.939 --> 01:44:17.039
It really is all spiky.

01:44:17.100 --> 01:44:19.859
And can you feel how cold it is?

01:44:19.920 --> 01:44:21.960
Whoa that's so weird.

01:44:22.020 --> 01:44:25.380
Said a 4th, reaching for Winter's wing

01:44:25.380 --> 01:44:27.479
Winter twitched back and growled at her.

01:44:27.539 --> 01:44:30.779
Glory exhaled slowly through her nose.

01:44:30.840 --> 01:44:32.939
This is our guest.

01:44:33.000 --> 01:44:35.220
Prince Winter of the Ice Wings.

01:44:35.279 --> 01:44:38.039
Have you seen any dragons today that look

01:44:38.039 --> 01:44:38.579
like him?

01:44:38.699 --> 01:44:40.319
No?

01:44:40.380 --> 01:44:42.960
They all answered, almost in unison.

01:44:43.020 --> 01:44:45.359
Would have noticed if I did.

01:44:45.420 --> 01:44:46.859
One of them offered.

01:44:46.920 --> 01:44:48.720
Look at how sparkly he is.

01:44:48.779 --> 01:44:51.180
Like raindrops on a cobweb or something.

01:44:51.239 --> 01:44:54.479
I'll say, agreed another.

01:44:54.539 --> 01:44:56.579
Plus brr.

01:44:56.640 --> 01:44:58.739
I think I had woken up if something that

01:44:58.739 --> 01:44:59.939
cold went by me.

01:45:00.000 --> 01:45:03.659
Me too, said a third.

01:45:03.720 --> 01:45:06.119
The queen closed her eyes eloquently.

01:45:06.239 --> 01:45:08.340
Death bringer cleared his throat.

01:45:08.460 --> 01:45:10.920
Permission to check with the backup night

01:45:10.920 --> 01:45:11.640
wing guards?

01:45:11.640 --> 01:45:12.420
he asked.

01:45:12.479 --> 01:45:16.260
Yes, yes, Glory said, waving him away.

01:45:16.319 --> 01:45:18.539
But make sure you tell them if they do

01:45:18.539 --> 01:45:20.939
see an ice wing, they are to follow her

01:45:20.939 --> 01:45:23.220
not attack her, especially if they're on

01:45:23.220 --> 01:45:23.520
their own.

01:45:23.579 --> 01:45:26.520
Deathbringer bowed and spread his wings.

01:45:26.579 --> 01:45:29.939
And that includes you, Glory yelled after

01:45:29.939 --> 01:45:31.020
him as he flew away.

01:45:31.079 --> 01:45:33.060
Keep your claws to yourself.

01:45:33.119 --> 01:45:35.399
Can't hear you.

01:45:35.460 --> 01:45:37.140
He called back cheerfully.

01:45:37.199 --> 01:45:40.800
Winter glanced sideways at Moon, and

01:45:40.800 --> 01:45:42.600
found her staring intently at one of the

01:45:42.600 --> 01:45:43.739
rain wing watchers.

01:45:43.800 --> 01:45:46.319
Um, Moon said.

01:45:46.380 --> 01:45:47.939
Your Majesty?

01:45:48.000 --> 01:45:49.199
Can I ask?

01:45:49.319 --> 01:45:52.619
Yes, Glory said, waving her talons.

01:45:52.680 --> 01:45:53.340
Speak up.

01:45:53.399 --> 01:45:56.399
Just, even if they didn't see an ice

01:45:56.399 --> 01:45:56.819
wing?

01:45:56.939 --> 01:45:59.640
Moon blurted in a hurry, anything

01:45:59.640 --> 01:46:02.399
suspicious, like something frozen or

01:46:02.399 --> 01:46:03.420
colder than usual.

01:46:03.539 --> 01:46:04.920
She trailed off.

01:46:04.979 --> 01:46:08.760
She knows that Rain Wing saw something

01:46:08.760 --> 01:46:10.380
Winter guest.

01:46:10.439 --> 01:46:11.819
She saw it in his head.

01:46:11.939 --> 01:46:14.760
But of course, she hadn't told Queen

01:46:14.760 --> 01:46:16.199
Glory she could read minds yet.

01:46:16.319 --> 01:46:18.479
Well?

01:46:18.720 --> 01:46:21.840
There was this weird spot near the oldest

01:46:21.840 --> 01:46:23.159
giant banyan tree.

01:46:23.220 --> 01:46:26.460
The rain wing scout mused, almost to

01:46:26.460 --> 01:46:26.760
himself.

01:46:26.819 --> 01:46:29.520
I did notice something funny there.

01:46:29.579 --> 01:46:31.500
What do you mean?

01:46:31.560 --> 01:46:32.880
Gloria asked him.

01:46:32.939 --> 01:46:36.300
There was a spot on the ground that was

01:46:36.300 --> 01:46:37.979
all shriveled up, kind of.

01:46:38.039 --> 01:46:39.840
The rain wing answered.

01:46:39.899 --> 01:46:43.020
His scales were royal blue, dotted with

01:46:43.020 --> 01:46:44.220
little swirls of dark pink.

01:46:44.279 --> 01:46:47.100
It looked like something had killed all

01:46:47.100 --> 01:46:48.539
the plants in a circle there.

01:46:48.600 --> 01:46:52.020
And they were kind of crusty and whitish

01:46:52.020 --> 01:46:54.060
and the berries were as hard as rocks.

01:46:54.119 --> 01:46:56.699
Oh, and kind of cold too.

01:46:56.760 --> 01:46:58.439
Do you think that's important?

01:46:58.500 --> 01:47:01.260
Winter flared his wings.

01:47:01.319 --> 01:47:02.939
Where was this?

01:47:03.000 --> 01:47:03.899
he demanded.

01:47:04.020 --> 01:47:04.979
How far away?

01:47:05.039 --> 01:47:07.920
I know where the banyan tree is.

01:47:07.979 --> 01:47:10.199
Glory said, already rising.

01:47:10.260 --> 01:47:13.199
She untangled silver from her neck and

01:47:13.199 --> 01:47:15.239
deposited the sloth on a nearby branch.

01:47:15.239 --> 01:47:17.039
We can be there in a few minutes.

01:47:17.100 --> 01:47:18.779
The rest of you, stay here.

01:47:18.840 --> 01:47:21.060
Can't I come too?

01:47:21.119 --> 01:47:22.319
Moon asked.

01:47:22.380 --> 01:47:23.579
I can be useful.

01:47:23.640 --> 01:47:26.220
I. She stopped, struggling for words.

01:47:26.340 --> 01:47:28.979
Winter realized that she was hoping her

01:47:28.979 --> 01:47:29.939
mind reading could help.

01:47:30.000 --> 01:47:32.760
Me too, Kinkachu cried.

01:47:32.819 --> 01:47:33.779
I want to come.

01:47:33.840 --> 01:47:37.560
No, Queen Glory said firmly.

01:47:37.619 --> 01:47:41.460
I am your queen, both of you, and I'm

01:47:41.460 --> 01:47:42.779
ordering you to stay here.

01:47:42.840 --> 01:47:45.659
Winter wished he could insist on going by

01:47:45.659 --> 01:47:46.079
himself.

01:47:46.140 --> 01:47:48.060
But he needed someone to show him the

01:47:48.060 --> 01:47:48.300
way.

01:47:48.359 --> 01:47:51.600
And if he was perfectly honest, someone

01:47:51.600 --> 01:47:53.699
who could sense Icicle's mind nearby

01:47:53.699 --> 01:47:55.500
would probably come in handy.

01:47:55.560 --> 01:48:00.119
Moon can come, he said, with what he

01:48:00.119 --> 01:48:01.560
hoped was an offhanded shrug.

01:48:01.619 --> 01:48:02.579
That's fine.

01:48:02.640 --> 01:48:03.840
Not her, though.

01:48:03.899 --> 01:48:05.819
She's far too loud.

01:48:05.880 --> 01:48:08.039
He jerked his chin at Kinkaju.

01:48:08.100 --> 01:48:09.840
I am not.

01:48:09.960 --> 01:48:11.640
Kinkaju protested.

01:48:11.699 --> 01:48:12.960
That's so unfair.

01:48:13.020 --> 01:48:15.180
Kinkaju?

01:48:15.239 --> 01:48:17.640
You wanted me to be queen, and now you

01:48:17.640 --> 01:48:19.680
have to listen to me, Glory said.

01:48:19.739 --> 01:48:23.340
Stay here, because if you get killed by

01:48:23.340 --> 01:48:25.859
an ice wing, I'm going to be extremely

01:48:25.859 --> 01:48:26.579
mad at you.

01:48:26.640 --> 01:48:29.939
She glanced from winter to moon, a

01:48:29.939 --> 01:48:31.439
wrinkle of puzzlement on her forehead.

01:48:31.500 --> 01:48:34.380
But all right, Moon, come along.

01:48:34.439 --> 01:48:37.199
Soon the 3 of them were soaring through

01:48:37.199 --> 01:48:39.659
the trees, well, trying to soar.

01:48:39.720 --> 01:48:42.239
Winter kept getting his wings tangled in

01:48:42.239 --> 01:48:44.939
unexpected vines, or spider webs, or

01:48:44.939 --> 01:48:48.239
branches, or once, snagged on the nest of

01:48:48.239 --> 01:48:50.159
a large beaked, indignant red bird.

01:48:50.220 --> 01:48:53.520
After a few minutes of lying, Queen Glory

01:48:53.520 --> 01:48:54.840
stopped abruptly and swung around.

01:48:54.960 --> 01:48:58.739
That is a level of noisy that makes me

01:48:58.739 --> 01:49:00.119
think you aren't even trying to be

01:49:00.119 --> 01:49:01.619
stealthy, she said.

01:49:01.680 --> 01:49:03.119
Come on out.

01:49:03.180 --> 01:49:06.479
Kibli emerged sheepishly from behind a

01:49:06.479 --> 01:49:07.859
tree with huge leaves.

01:49:07.979 --> 01:49:10.680
I was trying to be stealthy.

01:49:10.739 --> 01:49:13.380
He protested, but there's too many things

01:49:13.380 --> 01:49:14.939
to crash into.

01:49:15.000 --> 01:49:16.979
I'm a wide open desert kind of dragon.

01:49:17.100 --> 01:49:20.220
Winter shook off a tangle of moss and

01:49:20.220 --> 01:49:22.619
branches, disgruntled to realize he

01:49:22.619 --> 01:49:23.939
agreed with a sandwing about something.

01:49:24.000 --> 01:49:27.479
What did I say about staying put?

01:49:27.539 --> 01:49:28.680
Glory asked.

01:49:28.739 --> 01:49:32.579
You're a great queen, I hear, but with

01:49:32.579 --> 01:49:35.100
all due respect, you're not my queen

01:49:35.100 --> 01:49:37.560
Kibley said, setting his jaw.

01:49:37.619 --> 01:49:39.359
I go where they go.

01:49:39.479 --> 01:49:41.819
Besides, winter wants me along.

01:49:41.880 --> 01:49:42.899
He just can't admit it.

01:49:42.960 --> 01:49:44.819
I don't.

01:49:44.880 --> 01:49:46.079
Winter said.

01:49:46.140 --> 01:49:47.939
You can send him back to the kingdom of

01:49:47.939 --> 01:49:49.020
Sand for all I care.

01:49:49.079 --> 01:49:52.260
He adores me, Kibley said.

01:49:52.319 --> 01:49:54.000
Glory willed her eyes.

01:49:54.060 --> 01:49:56.100
Fine, enough arguing.

01:49:56.159 --> 01:49:57.000
Let's go.

01:49:57.060 --> 01:50:00.300
Kibli shot Winter a delighted grin, and

01:50:00.300 --> 01:50:01.859
flapped over to fly beside Moon.

01:50:01.920 --> 01:50:04.680
She was surprisingly dexterous at moving

01:50:04.680 --> 01:50:06.600
between the trees and dodging stray

01:50:06.600 --> 01:50:07.020
branches.

01:50:07.079 --> 01:50:09.420
Even glory still ran into things

01:50:09.420 --> 01:50:11.819
occasionally, but moon slipped easily

01:50:11.819 --> 01:50:14.100
through the forest like a seal diving in

01:50:14.100 --> 01:50:14.460
the waves.

01:50:14.520 --> 01:50:17.520
Soon they were descending toward an

01:50:17.520 --> 01:50:20.399
absolutely enormous fat tree, with

01:50:20.399 --> 01:50:22.500
bulging branches and knobbly roots

01:50:22.500 --> 01:50:24.060
sticking out of the undergrowth.

01:50:24.119 --> 01:50:26.699
From the air, Winter spotted the circle

01:50:26.699 --> 01:50:27.960
the rain wing had mentioned.

01:50:28.079 --> 01:50:30.539
The frozen berries had melted into mushy

01:50:30.539 --> 01:50:32.760
puddles of purple, while the leaves and

01:50:32.760 --> 01:50:34.319
undergrowth were all black and damp.

01:50:34.380 --> 01:50:36.840
But it wasn't a neat circle.

01:50:36.899 --> 01:50:39.180
There were patches of green still left

01:50:39.180 --> 01:50:41.279
within the circumference of it, which

01:50:41.279 --> 01:50:43.380
meant something had been blocking icicles

01:50:43.380 --> 01:50:46.979
frost breath in those spots, something, or

01:50:46.979 --> 01:50:47.399
someone.

01:50:47.460 --> 01:50:51.119
Glory and Moon circled the tree, while

01:50:51.119 --> 01:50:53.100
Winter and Kibbledy landed and studied

01:50:53.100 --> 01:50:54.180
the rainforest floor.

01:50:54.180 --> 01:50:56.760
A sharp headache was starting to work its

01:50:56.760 --> 01:50:58.020
way through Winter's brain.

01:50:58.020 --> 01:50:59.760
He didn't want this to be true.

01:50:59.819 --> 01:51:03.060
He wanted to find icicle, but he didn't

01:51:03.060 --> 01:51:04.260
want to find out that she'd done

01:51:04.260 --> 01:51:05.220
something else terrible.

01:51:05.279 --> 01:51:08.340
The layers of leaves and bracken were

01:51:08.340 --> 01:51:10.439
disturbed here, as if something had been

01:51:10.439 --> 01:51:10.920
dragged away.

01:51:11.039 --> 01:51:13.079
Kibling noticed it too.

01:51:13.140 --> 01:51:15.060
His snout wrinkled with concern.

01:51:15.180 --> 01:51:18.180
Winter followed the trail, trying to

01:51:18.180 --> 01:51:19.260
guess what he would have done in this

01:51:19.260 --> 01:51:19.560
situation.

01:51:19.619 --> 01:51:22.199
Hidden the body.

01:51:22.260 --> 01:51:24.359
To give myself more time before I was

01:51:24.359 --> 01:51:24.659
caught.

01:51:24.720 --> 01:51:26.699
But she couldn't have dragged it far.

01:51:26.760 --> 01:51:29.460
Maybe I'm just imagining the worst.

01:51:29.520 --> 01:51:32.399
Maybe she killed a rainforest boar.

01:51:32.460 --> 01:51:34.560
A really big one?

01:51:34.680 --> 01:51:36.720
And dragged it off to eat?

01:51:36.779 --> 01:51:37.859
Maybe?

01:51:37.979 --> 01:51:41.340
Winter paced over to a wall of bushes

01:51:41.340 --> 01:51:42.840
where the ground began to slope up.

01:51:42.899 --> 01:51:46.260
The banyan's roots extended this far, some

01:51:46.260 --> 01:51:47.880
of them nearly as fat around as a

01:51:47.880 --> 01:51:48.479
dragon.

01:51:48.539 --> 01:51:51.239
Between one of the roots and the bushes

01:51:51.239 --> 01:51:54.300
was a mound of leaves, dirt, moss, and

01:51:54.300 --> 01:51:56.579
mulch that looked too big to be natural.

01:51:56.640 --> 01:51:58.619
His heart sinking.

01:51:58.680 --> 01:52:00.720
Winter started to clear away the debris.

01:52:00.779 --> 01:52:03.539
Moon and Kibley joined him, helping

01:52:03.539 --> 01:52:04.079
silently.

01:52:04.140 --> 01:52:07.500
The corpse of a nightwing guard lay

01:52:07.500 --> 01:52:09.659
beneath the dirt in a hastily dug hollow

01:52:09.659 --> 01:52:12.359
his face contorted in frozen rage.

01:52:12.420 --> 01:52:15.180
His throat slashed, and his scales

01:52:15.180 --> 01:52:16.619
ravaged by frost breath.

01:52:16.680 --> 01:52:19.560
Icicle was definitely here.

01:52:19.619 --> 01:52:24.239
Chapter 6.

01:52:24.300 --> 01:52:29.579
Moons, Glory muttered, staring over

01:52:29.579 --> 01:52:31.140
Winter's shoulder at the corpse.

01:52:31.199 --> 01:52:33.779
Clouds of dark red were gathering along

01:52:33.779 --> 01:52:34.920
her wings and spine.

01:52:34.979 --> 01:52:37.020
This is bad winter.

01:52:37.079 --> 01:52:40.199
Bad for your sister, bad for the peace of

01:52:40.199 --> 01:52:40.920
the rainforest.

01:52:40.979 --> 01:52:44.159
The night wings are going to set their

01:52:44.159 --> 01:52:44.939
heads on fire.

01:52:45.000 --> 01:52:46.439
Kibli agreed.

01:52:46.500 --> 01:52:47.760
No wait.

01:52:47.819 --> 01:52:49.619
They're going to set the closest ice

01:52:49.619 --> 01:52:50.579
wings head on fire.

01:52:50.640 --> 01:52:51.840
Winter?

01:52:51.899 --> 01:52:53.880
I hope your skull is as thick as it

01:52:53.880 --> 01:52:54.060
looks.

01:52:54.119 --> 01:52:56.520
Winter didn't want to ask.

01:52:56.579 --> 01:52:58.920
He really believed that reading another

01:52:58.920 --> 01:53:01.680
dragon's mind was wrong, but if it meant

01:53:01.680 --> 01:53:03.479
stopping icicle before she did something

01:53:03.479 --> 01:53:06.300
like this again, and finding her before a

01:53:06.300 --> 01:53:09.300
vengeful troop of night wings did, he

01:53:09.300 --> 01:53:11.520
gazed at Moon until she looked up and met

01:53:11.520 --> 01:53:11.939
his eyes.

01:53:12.000 --> 01:53:15.119
He tilted his chin questioningly, and she

01:53:15.119 --> 01:53:15.600
shook her head.

01:53:15.659 --> 01:53:18.420
She couldn't hear icicles mind nearby.

01:53:18.479 --> 01:53:22.439
If icicle sees you for, she'll know

01:53:22.439 --> 01:53:23.340
you're here to stop her.

01:53:23.399 --> 01:53:24.840
Glory said.

01:53:24.899 --> 01:53:26.819
She gave Moon a worried glance.

01:53:26.880 --> 01:53:28.739
Let's get you somewhere safe.

01:53:28.800 --> 01:53:32.220
And you, Moon pointed out.

01:53:32.279 --> 01:53:34.800
The queen snorted, as though she was

01:53:34.800 --> 01:53:36.960
pretty sure she could handle anything and

01:53:36.960 --> 01:53:38.520
led the way back to the royal pavilion.

01:53:38.579 --> 01:53:40.500
What happened?

01:53:40.560 --> 01:53:43.260
Kinkachu yelped as soon as she saw them.

01:53:43.319 --> 01:53:46.079
She leaped up, her scales shifting into

01:53:46.079 --> 01:53:47.939
spirals of orange and lavender.

01:53:48.000 --> 01:53:48.960
Did you find her?

01:53:49.020 --> 01:53:51.479
Uh-oh, winter looks mad.

01:53:51.539 --> 01:53:53.699
Well, actually, that's how he always

01:53:53.699 --> 01:53:54.119
looks.

01:53:54.180 --> 01:53:55.079
Is he mad?

01:53:55.140 --> 01:53:55.800
What happened?

01:53:55.920 --> 01:53:58.199
Deathbringer was there too.

01:53:58.319 --> 01:54:00.600
Stamping around, making the platform

01:54:00.600 --> 01:54:02.939
shake, and accidentally ripping flowers

01:54:02.939 --> 01:54:03.720
off the vines.

01:54:03.779 --> 01:54:05.699
By yourself.

01:54:05.760 --> 01:54:08.279
He warred at glory, with 3 little

01:54:08.279 --> 01:54:09.420
dragonettes to protect you.

01:54:09.479 --> 01:54:11.460
Excuse me?

01:54:11.520 --> 01:54:12.659
Winter objected.

01:54:12.720 --> 01:54:15.300
Dragons my age are seasoned warriors

01:54:15.300 --> 01:54:16.020
where I come from.

01:54:16.140 --> 01:54:18.359
We guard the queen all the time in the

01:54:18.359 --> 01:54:18.840
ice kingdom.

01:54:18.899 --> 01:54:21.479
Don't get your tail in a knot.

01:54:21.539 --> 01:54:23.340
Glory said to Death Bringer.

01:54:23.399 --> 01:54:25.859
Her sloth was already clambering up her

01:54:25.859 --> 01:54:26.819
tail onto her back again.

01:54:26.880 --> 01:54:30.000
My top secret invisible guard was

01:54:30.000 --> 01:54:31.319
following us too, and you know it.

01:54:31.380 --> 01:54:34.619
But I wasn't, he protested.

01:54:34.680 --> 01:54:37.560
She gave him an exasperated look.

01:54:37.619 --> 01:54:42.479
You can't always be, she said, in a low

01:54:42.479 --> 01:54:44.699
surprisingly affectionate voice, that

01:54:44.699 --> 01:54:46.380
suddenly made Winter rethink everything

01:54:46.380 --> 01:54:48.239
he had assumed about the queen and her

01:54:48.239 --> 01:54:49.020
bodyguard.

01:54:49.079 --> 01:54:52.260
So calm down and trust me to take care of

01:54:52.260 --> 01:54:52.859
myself.

01:54:52.920 --> 01:54:56.340
Says the dragon, who got herself chained

01:54:56.340 --> 01:54:57.359
up in a lava prison.

01:54:57.420 --> 01:54:59.100
Deathbringer muttered.

01:54:59.159 --> 01:55:02.220
The important thing is that we know the

01:55:02.220 --> 01:55:04.380
ice wing is here, Glory said.

01:55:04.439 --> 01:55:05.939
She is?

01:55:06.000 --> 01:55:08.220
Kinkachu squeaked.

01:55:08.279 --> 01:55:08.880
Actually here?

01:55:09.000 --> 01:55:10.260
In the rainforest?

01:55:10.380 --> 01:55:12.060
Right this minute.

01:55:12.119 --> 01:55:14.340
Right this minute.

01:55:14.460 --> 01:55:15.600
Winter thought.

01:55:15.720 --> 01:55:17.159
She's close by.

01:55:17.220 --> 01:55:20.880
His perfect overachieving sister was

01:55:20.880 --> 01:55:23.279
somewhere in this damp mud hole, hiding

01:55:23.279 --> 01:55:25.199
from rain wings and planning a murder.

01:55:25.260 --> 01:55:27.659
How far would she be willing to go?

01:55:27.779 --> 01:55:29.699
If Winter tried to stop her?

01:55:29.760 --> 01:55:32.460
Would she kill one brother in order to

01:55:32.460 --> 01:55:33.060
save the other?

01:55:33.119 --> 01:55:36.359
Don't leave out the key adjectives in

01:55:36.359 --> 01:55:36.600
there.

01:55:36.659 --> 01:55:39.779
Kill one low ranked, disappointing

01:55:39.779 --> 01:55:42.180
brother in order to save the long lost

01:55:42.180 --> 01:55:43.500
hero with a bright future.

01:55:43.560 --> 01:55:46.140
That makes the equation a bit easier.

01:55:46.199 --> 01:55:50.039
Glory's tail lashed back and forth as she

01:55:50.039 --> 01:55:50.939
began issuing orders.

01:55:51.000 --> 01:55:54.300
We need to organize teams to search

01:55:54.300 --> 01:55:55.680
starting here and spreading outward.

01:55:55.739 --> 01:55:57.720
I also need you to come look at something

01:55:57.720 --> 01:55:58.260
for me.

01:55:58.319 --> 01:56:01.619
She brushed Deathbringer's tail lightly

01:56:01.619 --> 01:56:02.159
with her own.

01:56:02.220 --> 01:56:04.500
To identify the body.

01:56:04.560 --> 01:56:06.060
Winter guest.

01:56:06.119 --> 01:56:08.100
Before she tells the other night wings

01:56:08.100 --> 01:56:08.699
what we found.

01:56:08.760 --> 01:56:11.100
So she can tell them who's dead.

01:56:11.159 --> 01:56:16.079
As for you all, Glory said, turning to

01:56:16.079 --> 01:56:17.579
Winter and Moon and Kibli.

01:56:17.640 --> 01:56:19.800
I think the safest place is the

01:56:19.800 --> 01:56:20.939
Dragonette Wingery.

01:56:20.939 --> 01:56:22.079
It's not far.

01:56:22.140 --> 01:56:24.600
It's already well fortified, and I'll

01:56:24.600 --> 01:56:25.680
double the guard to protect you.

01:56:25.739 --> 01:56:27.479
What?

01:56:27.539 --> 01:56:29.819
Winter cried. flaring his wings.

01:56:29.880 --> 01:56:32.279
You can't lock us up with a bunch of new

01:56:32.279 --> 01:56:33.600
hatched dragonettes.

01:56:33.659 --> 01:56:35.100
I need to look for my sister.

01:56:35.159 --> 01:56:37.140
Glory shook her head.

01:56:37.199 --> 01:56:40.020
I'm sorry, Winter, but if anything

01:56:40.020 --> 01:56:42.359
happens to you, the ice wings will

01:56:42.359 --> 01:56:44.520
declare war on us, and I wouldn't blame

01:56:44.520 --> 01:56:44.699
them.

01:56:44.760 --> 01:56:47.340
Keeping you safe is the most important

01:56:47.340 --> 01:56:47.760
thing.

01:56:47.760 --> 01:56:49.319
She hesitated.

01:56:49.380 --> 01:56:51.960
I promise to let you speak with her when

01:56:51.960 --> 01:56:52.319
we find her.

01:56:52.380 --> 01:56:56.520
Unless an overzealous nightwing kills her

01:56:56.520 --> 01:56:58.199
first, Winter shouted.

01:56:58.260 --> 01:57:00.239
He lashed his tail furiously.

01:57:00.300 --> 01:57:02.340
You can't promise me you'll keep her

01:57:02.340 --> 01:57:02.640
alive.

01:57:02.699 --> 01:57:04.439
I know how night wings are.

01:57:04.500 --> 01:57:06.119
They'll kill her the moment they see

01:57:06.119 --> 01:57:06.359
her.

01:57:06.420 --> 01:57:12.060
I am their queen, Glory said, with steely

01:57:12.060 --> 01:57:14.520
ferocity, and I will not let them do

01:57:14.520 --> 01:57:14.939
that.

01:57:15.000 --> 01:57:18.720
She's my sister, Winter Ward.

01:57:18.779 --> 01:57:21.600
Exactly, Glory snapped back.

01:57:21.659 --> 01:57:24.659
So you're in danger from her and from the

01:57:24.659 --> 01:57:26.460
entire tribe of Nightwings.

01:57:26.520 --> 01:57:27.600
Once they find out what she did.

01:57:27.720 --> 01:57:31.020
I'm not having any more dead dragons in

01:57:31.020 --> 01:57:31.920
my rainforest today.

01:57:32.039 --> 01:57:35.939
Warm claws step down hard on Winter's

01:57:35.939 --> 01:57:36.420
back foot.

01:57:36.479 --> 01:57:38.340
He whirled around, snarling.

01:57:38.399 --> 01:57:40.979
Stop arguing with her.

01:57:41.039 --> 01:57:42.960
Kibley whispered through his teeth.

01:57:43.020 --> 01:57:45.479
She's not going to give in.

01:57:45.539 --> 01:57:46.859
Kinkaju agreed.

01:57:46.920 --> 01:57:49.920
Behind her, Moon nodded, adding the

01:57:49.920 --> 01:57:51.359
weight of a mind reader to that opinion.

01:57:51.420 --> 01:57:54.060
Glory was already turning back to

01:57:54.060 --> 01:57:55.979
Deathbringer, and a pair of scout

01:57:55.979 --> 01:57:57.180
captains.

01:57:57.239 --> 01:57:58.439
Winter shoved Kibley away.

01:57:58.560 --> 01:58:00.720
He was not done fighting about this.

01:58:00.720 --> 01:58:02.699
There was no way he was going to sit

01:58:02.699 --> 01:58:05.039
quietly with a bunch of baby dragons

01:58:05.039 --> 01:58:07.020
while an enemy tribe chased down his

01:58:07.020 --> 01:58:07.260
sister.

01:58:07.319 --> 01:58:11.520
Listen, Kibley hissed, shoving him back.

01:58:11.579 --> 01:58:14.399
If you keep arguing, she'll add even more

01:58:14.399 --> 01:58:14.819
guards.

01:58:14.880 --> 01:58:17.460
Just agree, and then we'll sneak off.

01:58:17.579 --> 01:58:18.840
It's the only way.

01:58:18.960 --> 01:58:22.619
Kinkachu's eyes went wide, and her scales

01:58:22.619 --> 01:58:24.659
turned an odd shade of yellowish green

01:58:24.659 --> 01:58:26.399
but Moon was nodding again.

01:58:26.460 --> 01:58:29.760
We'll figure it out, she agreed in a

01:58:29.760 --> 01:58:30.119
whisper.

01:58:30.180 --> 01:58:32.399
We'll make sure you're the 1st one to

01:58:32.399 --> 01:58:33.000
find your sister.

01:58:33.119 --> 01:58:35.939
Winter ground his teeth together.

01:58:36.000 --> 01:58:38.520
He'd spent a lifetime being told what to

01:58:38.520 --> 01:58:38.760
do.

01:58:38.880 --> 01:58:40.859
But that was by other ice wings.

01:58:40.920 --> 01:58:43.439
No rain wing could order him around.

01:58:43.500 --> 01:58:45.119
And you didn't have to listen to

01:58:45.119 --> 01:58:47.220
whispered advice from a sandwing either.

01:58:47.279 --> 01:58:49.800
Mother and father would want him to fight

01:58:49.800 --> 01:58:50.279
right now.

01:58:50.340 --> 01:58:51.600
He was sure of it.

01:58:51.720 --> 01:58:54.180
They'd wreck this pavilion and fight the

01:58:54.180 --> 01:58:56.279
entire tribe, both tribes.

01:58:56.340 --> 01:58:58.739
If anyone tried to stop them from hunting

01:58:58.739 --> 01:58:59.279
for icicle.

01:58:59.340 --> 01:59:01.560
But if he fought everyone now.

01:59:01.619 --> 01:59:04.680
Glory would see him as a threat, just

01:59:04.680 --> 01:59:05.579
like Icicle.

01:59:05.640 --> 01:59:09.899
Whereas, if he waited, and snuck off to

01:59:09.899 --> 01:59:11.699
search for her as Kibley suggested.

01:59:11.760 --> 01:59:13.979
It was horrible.

01:59:14.039 --> 01:59:16.619
Winter could almost see his ranking

01:59:16.619 --> 01:59:17.819
plummeting.

01:59:17.880 --> 01:59:20.640
Everything he'd ever worked for, vanishing

01:59:20.640 --> 01:59:23.159
as he bowed his head to obey a rainbow

01:59:23.159 --> 01:59:25.500
bright dragonette, queen of the night

01:59:25.500 --> 01:59:25.920
wings.

01:59:26.039 --> 01:59:28.859
It'll be worth it if I come back with

01:59:28.859 --> 01:59:31.439
hailstorm, he told himself fiercely.

01:59:31.500 --> 01:59:34.380
Even if I'm the bottom ranked ice wing

01:59:34.380 --> 01:59:37.020
for the rest of my life, saving Hillstorm

01:59:37.020 --> 01:59:38.579
would make all of this worthwhile.

01:59:38.640 --> 01:59:41.100
And so he agreed.

01:59:41.220 --> 01:59:44.220
He nearly changed his mind when he saw

01:59:44.220 --> 01:59:45.659
the rainforest wingery, though.

01:59:45.779 --> 01:59:48.539
It was even worse than he'd feared

01:59:48.539 --> 01:59:51.420
exactly the sort of soft, cuddly, lazy

01:59:51.420 --> 01:59:53.460
stupid setup, he should have expected

01:59:53.460 --> 01:59:54.779
from a bunch of rain wings.

01:59:54.840 --> 01:59:57.180
They didn't care if their dragon heads

01:59:57.180 --> 01:59:59.039
grew up to be feeble and non

01:59:58.260 --> 01:59:59.039
threatening.

01:59:59.159 --> 02:00:01.380
So of course they left them to roll

02:00:01.380 --> 02:00:04.079
around like mammal cubs, instead of

02:00:04.079 --> 02:00:05.340
launching their training the moment they

02:00:05.340 --> 02:00:05.760
hatched.

02:00:05.819 --> 02:00:08.880
The main play area was an enormous

02:00:08.880 --> 02:00:11.579
trampoline made of springy vines and

02:00:11.579 --> 02:00:14.159
leaves, strung between several trees high

02:00:14.159 --> 02:00:15.119
above the ground.

02:00:15.420 --> 02:00:18.000
It was surrounded on all sides by tall

02:00:18.000 --> 02:00:20.579
soft, woven mats of branches that kept

02:00:20.579 --> 02:00:22.439
the baby dragons from falling over the

02:00:22.439 --> 02:00:23.100
edge.

02:00:23.159 --> 02:00:25.739
Six full grown dragons guarded the

02:00:25.739 --> 02:00:28.859
perimeter. 3 night wings and 3 rain wings

02:00:28.859 --> 02:00:31.260
all of whom looked more alert and tense

02:00:31.260 --> 02:00:33.239
than anyone else winter had seen so far.

02:00:33.300 --> 02:00:36.600
One of the night wings inspected each of

02:00:36.600 --> 02:00:38.039
them carefully before allowing them

02:00:38.039 --> 02:00:38.520
inside.

02:00:38.579 --> 02:00:41.399
She poked their small skyfire bags

02:00:41.399 --> 02:00:44.520
sniffed the rocks, studied Winter's snout

02:00:44.520 --> 02:00:46.680
with a worried expression, and spent a

02:00:46.680 --> 02:00:48.659
full minute examining Kibley's deadly

02:00:48.659 --> 02:00:49.319
tail barb.

02:00:49.380 --> 02:00:51.420
It's very safe.

02:00:51.479 --> 02:00:52.979
Kibley promised her.

02:00:53.039 --> 02:00:56.340
Sandwing dragonettes learn early how to

02:00:56.340 --> 02:00:58.079
avoid accidentally stabbing anyone.

02:00:58.140 --> 02:01:01.500
He coiled his tail protectively inward

02:01:01.500 --> 02:01:02.340
and the guard jumped back.

02:01:02.399 --> 02:01:04.500
I don't like it.

02:01:04.560 --> 02:01:07.439
She said to Heliconia, the rain wing

02:01:07.439 --> 02:01:08.880
who'd escorted them to the wingery.

02:01:08.880 --> 02:01:11.159
We're supposed to keep complete strangers

02:01:11.159 --> 02:01:13.260
away from the dragonettes, and this one

02:01:13.260 --> 02:01:16.020
looks the mildest word I can think of is

02:01:16.020 --> 02:01:16.439
hostile.

02:01:16.500 --> 02:01:18.060
She frowned at winter.

02:01:18.119 --> 02:01:22.199
That's just his face, said Kibley, and

02:01:22.199 --> 02:01:22.800
his personality.

02:01:22.859 --> 02:01:26.100
He would never harm a dragonette.

02:01:26.159 --> 02:01:27.000
Moon promised.

02:01:27.060 --> 02:01:29.760
I can speak for myself.

02:01:29.880 --> 02:01:31.260
Winter snapped.

02:01:31.319 --> 02:01:34.500
Grumbling under her breath, the Nightwing

02:01:34.500 --> 02:01:35.760
finally let them pass.

02:01:35.819 --> 02:01:38.159
They flew up and over the woven wall

02:01:38.159 --> 02:01:40.140
landing lightly on the platforms around

02:01:40.140 --> 02:01:41.159
the trampoline inside.

02:01:41.220 --> 02:01:44.819
Winter scanned the space, and saw that it

02:01:44.819 --> 02:01:47.159
was full of peculiar toys that didn't

02:01:47.159 --> 02:01:49.619
appear to teach anything or impart any

02:01:49.619 --> 02:01:51.000
valuable skills whatsoever.

02:01:51.000 --> 02:01:54.720
Inside the wingery were 9 dragonettes

02:01:54.720 --> 02:01:55.619
less than a year old.

02:01:55.680 --> 02:01:58.560
At first glance, Winter thought they were

02:01:58.560 --> 02:02:00.479
all night wings, because they all had

02:02:00.479 --> 02:02:02.579
black scales, and were wrestling in a

02:02:02.579 --> 02:02:03.180
pile together.

02:02:03.239 --> 02:02:05.399
But when the newcomers landed on the

02:02:05.399 --> 02:02:07.859
platforms around them, 9 tiny heads

02:02:07.859 --> 02:02:10.859
popped up, and 7 of them became suddenly

02:02:10.859 --> 02:02:12.060
vibrantly pink and yellow.

02:02:12.119 --> 02:02:14.760
Pretty new dragons!

02:02:14.819 --> 02:02:17.520
one of them cheered, and 8 dragonettes

02:02:17.520 --> 02:02:19.859
came rampaging over, staggering on the

02:02:19.859 --> 02:02:21.539
bouncy surface and flapping their

02:02:21.539 --> 02:02:22.500
unwieldy wings.

02:02:22.560 --> 02:02:25.619
Winter backed up all the way until his

02:02:25.619 --> 02:02:27.840
wings hit the wall, but that didn't stop

02:02:27.840 --> 02:02:30.359
3 tiny rain wings from closing in on

02:02:30.359 --> 02:02:30.539
him.

02:02:30.659 --> 02:02:33.779
Glittery, yelped one.

02:02:33.840 --> 02:02:36.000
I can do that, said another.

02:02:36.060 --> 02:02:37.020
Look, look, look.

02:02:37.079 --> 02:02:40.560
He crouched, concentrating, and a wave of

02:02:40.560 --> 02:02:42.720
icy blue surged across his scales.

02:02:42.779 --> 02:02:45.359
A moment later, he looked like a

02:02:45.359 --> 02:02:47.520
miniature version of winter, without the

02:02:47.520 --> 02:02:49.680
extra ice dragon spikes and horns.

02:02:49.800 --> 02:02:52.199
He held out his claws and cooed

02:02:52.199 --> 02:02:53.279
admiringly himself.

02:02:53.340 --> 02:02:56.640
Nice work, Kinkaju said.

02:02:56.699 --> 02:02:58.859
She squinted at winter as though he were

02:02:58.859 --> 02:03:00.779
an ice sculpture that needed improving.

02:03:00.840 --> 02:03:03.239
You could add a little more dark blue

02:03:03.239 --> 02:03:05.279
shading around the spine and edges of the

02:03:05.279 --> 02:03:05.520
wings.

02:03:05.579 --> 02:03:07.140
Sure.

02:03:07.199 --> 02:03:09.420
The dragonette clicked his teeth together

02:03:09.420 --> 02:03:12.119
thoughtfully, and a moment later, a

02:03:12.119 --> 02:03:13.439
subtle shift went through some of his

02:03:13.439 --> 02:03:16.140
scales, making the jagged ridge along his

02:03:16.140 --> 02:03:18.420
back look sharper and taller, a little

02:03:18.420 --> 02:03:19.739
more like an ice wings.

02:03:19.859 --> 02:03:23.699
Try this one, called a dragonette, who

02:03:23.699 --> 02:03:24.899
was circling around Kibley.

02:03:24.960 --> 02:03:27.420
The sand wing wrinkled his nose at her

02:03:27.420 --> 02:03:28.680
and she wrinkled hers right back.

02:03:28.739 --> 02:03:31.380
Her scales were already shifting to the

02:03:31.380 --> 02:03:32.760
same pale yellow as his.

02:03:32.819 --> 02:03:35.520
She spread her wings and studied the

02:03:35.520 --> 02:03:37.739
underside of them, then reached out and

02:03:37.739 --> 02:03:39.840
poked Kibley until he opened his wings

02:03:39.840 --> 02:03:40.619
for her to examine.

02:03:40.680 --> 02:03:43.619
Hmm, she said.

02:03:43.680 --> 02:03:46.319
A shimmer of gold and bronze appeared on

02:03:46.319 --> 02:03:48.840
her chest, and then slowly melted into a

02:03:48.840 --> 02:03:51.000
color that almost exactly matched

02:03:51.000 --> 02:03:52.260
Kibley's underscales.

02:03:52.319 --> 02:03:54.600
Woo, she cried.

02:03:54.659 --> 02:03:56.279
Let's see if I can do is snout.

02:03:56.340 --> 02:03:59.699
Winter watched tiny brown freckles in a

02:03:59.699 --> 02:04:02.640
small, dark zigzag that matched Kibley's

02:04:02.640 --> 02:04:04.260
scar appear on her scales.

02:04:04.319 --> 02:04:06.479
He tried to squash his amazement.

02:04:06.539 --> 02:04:09.119
Dragonette, less than a year old, could

02:04:09.119 --> 02:04:09.600
do that?

02:04:09.659 --> 02:04:12.119
Winter glanced around the wingery.

02:04:12.180 --> 02:04:14.279
Maybe they weren't completely wasting

02:04:14.279 --> 02:04:15.359
their time in here after all.

02:04:15.420 --> 02:04:19.140
Of course, camouflage scales weren't as

02:04:19.140 --> 02:04:21.600
impressive or useful as hunting and

02:04:21.600 --> 02:04:23.039
fighting and survival skills.

02:04:23.100 --> 02:04:25.739
Hailstorm had battled a killer whale

02:04:25.739 --> 02:04:26.880
before he was one year old.

02:04:26.939 --> 02:04:29.399
Winter had been sent out to spend an

02:04:29.399 --> 02:04:31.079
entire night in a blizzard alone.

02:04:31.140 --> 02:04:34.380
Icicle was already combat training with

02:04:34.380 --> 02:04:36.720
dragons 3 times her size by her 1st

02:04:36.720 --> 02:04:37.079
birthday.

02:04:37.140 --> 02:04:40.380
These dragonettes wouldn't last a minute

02:04:40.380 --> 02:04:41.279
in ice wing training.

02:04:41.340 --> 02:04:43.319
They wouldn't make a dent in their

02:04:43.319 --> 02:04:44.220
rankings at all.

02:04:44.279 --> 02:04:47.340
His gaze fell on the one dragonette who

02:04:47.340 --> 02:04:48.060
was hanging back.

02:04:48.119 --> 02:04:51.119
A small, nervous looking night wing with

02:04:51.119 --> 02:04:52.739
a leaf bandage wrapped around one

02:04:52.739 --> 02:04:53.279
foreleg.

02:04:53.340 --> 02:04:56.279
The dragonette met his eyes, squeaked

02:04:56.279 --> 02:04:58.140
nervously, and tucked his head under his

02:04:58.140 --> 02:04:58.500
wings.

02:04:58.560 --> 02:05:02.699
Don't mind him, said the dragonette, who

02:05:02.699 --> 02:05:04.079
turned himself the color of winter.

02:05:04.140 --> 02:05:06.420
He's so useless.

02:05:06.539 --> 02:05:08.939
Said the other night wing dragonette.

02:05:09.000 --> 02:05:12.119
She was sleek and glossy, like a seal, and

02:05:12.119 --> 02:05:13.619
was studying the newcomers with more

02:05:13.619 --> 02:05:16.020
reserve than the wild curiosity of the

02:05:16.020 --> 02:05:16.619
rain wings.

02:05:16.680 --> 02:05:19.739
He still having nightmares about the

02:05:19.739 --> 02:05:21.840
volcano every night, even though that was

02:05:21.840 --> 02:05:22.619
months ago.

02:05:22.680 --> 02:05:25.199
Toughen up, lizard, she barked at him.

02:05:25.260 --> 02:05:28.140
The bandaged night wing slowly drew his

02:05:28.140 --> 02:05:30.180
head out and folded his wings back

02:05:30.180 --> 02:05:31.979
shivering from horns to tail.

02:05:32.100 --> 02:05:34.500
Winter could see him fighting back his

02:05:34.500 --> 02:05:36.779
terror as he squared his shoulders and

02:05:36.779 --> 02:05:38.159
faced the new dragons.

02:05:38.220 --> 02:05:40.859
Some night wing he is.

02:05:40.920 --> 02:05:42.960
The female dragonette snorted.

02:05:43.020 --> 02:05:45.659
We keep telling him what an important

02:05:45.659 --> 02:05:48.239
dangerous tribe we are, but frankly, I'm

02:05:48.239 --> 02:05:49.619
not sure he'll ever measure up.

02:05:49.680 --> 02:05:51.899
I guess some dragons are just.

02:05:52.619 --> 02:05:55.680
Hatched in the wrong tribe, Moon finished

02:05:55.680 --> 02:05:56.279
softly.

02:05:56.340 --> 02:05:58.739
Winter tilted his head at her.

02:05:58.800 --> 02:06:01.319
Did she wish she weren't a night wing?

02:06:01.380 --> 02:06:03.720
Or had she heard other dragons wishing

02:06:03.720 --> 02:06:04.979
they could be something different?

02:06:05.039 --> 02:06:06.840
Not me.

02:06:06.899 --> 02:06:09.479
He couldn't imagine not being a nice

02:06:09.479 --> 02:06:09.899
wing.

02:06:09.960 --> 02:06:12.239
His whole life was about trying to be a

02:06:12.239 --> 02:06:13.500
true ice wing warrior.

02:06:13.560 --> 02:06:16.800
All he'd ever wanted was to rise to the

02:06:16.800 --> 02:06:19.079
top of the rankings and prove himself to

02:06:19.079 --> 02:06:20.760
his parents and the rest of the tribe.

02:06:20.819 --> 02:06:22.859
That was all he should want.

02:06:22.920 --> 02:06:25.439
Until I met her.

02:06:25.500 --> 02:06:28.859
And now I want, What?

02:06:28.979 --> 02:06:31.020
To understand a night wing?

02:06:31.079 --> 02:06:33.000
To have her care about me?

02:06:33.119 --> 02:06:36.119
No wonder he hated himself.

02:06:36.180 --> 02:06:38.579
All right, scoot.

02:06:38.640 --> 02:06:41.159
Kibley said suddenly, flapping his wings

02:06:41.159 --> 02:06:42.239
at the dragonettes.

02:06:42.300 --> 02:06:45.960
Leave us alone and go play, quietly, over

02:06:45.960 --> 02:06:46.319
there.

02:06:46.380 --> 02:06:48.840
He herded the dragonettes to the other

02:06:48.840 --> 02:06:50.939
side of the enclosure and came back

02:06:50.939 --> 02:06:52.260
ducking his head toward moon.

02:06:52.319 --> 02:06:53.880
Are you all right?

02:06:53.939 --> 02:06:55.079
He whispered.

02:06:55.140 --> 02:06:57.539
Winter realized Moon was rubbing her

02:06:57.539 --> 02:06:57.960
temples.

02:06:58.020 --> 02:07:00.300
He'd forgotten that she must be hearing

02:07:00.300 --> 02:07:01.859
the thoughts of all the dragons around

02:07:01.859 --> 02:07:02.460
them.

02:07:02.520 --> 02:07:04.739
While the baby dragons were bombarding

02:07:04.739 --> 02:07:07.140
the newcomers with words, they must also

02:07:07.140 --> 02:07:09.180
be blasting the inside of Moon's head

02:07:09.180 --> 02:07:09.899
with their thoughts.

02:07:09.960 --> 02:07:11.699
I'm fine.

02:07:11.760 --> 02:07:13.560
I just need to adjust.

02:07:13.680 --> 02:07:16.979
Moon said, dropping her claws and shaking

02:07:16.979 --> 02:07:17.819
out her wings.

02:07:17.880 --> 02:07:19.619
We can't sneak away yet.

02:07:19.680 --> 02:07:21.899
The guards are too focused on us.

02:07:21.960 --> 02:07:23.699
She glanced at Winter.

02:07:23.760 --> 02:07:25.560
I'll keep listening.

02:07:25.619 --> 02:07:28.319
Her talons went back to her head, and she

02:07:28.319 --> 02:07:29.100
closed her eyes.

02:07:29.159 --> 02:07:30.779
Guess what?

02:07:30.840 --> 02:07:32.279
Kinkaju said.

02:07:32.340 --> 02:07:34.199
Lightly bouncing the vines below her.

02:07:34.260 --> 02:07:37.020
Her claws had all turned dark green to

02:07:37.020 --> 02:07:39.300
match the wingery, so it almost looked as

02:07:39.300 --> 02:07:40.920
though she had no feet at all if you

02:07:40.920 --> 02:07:41.460
didn't look closely.

02:07:41.520 --> 02:07:43.500
I think I figured it out.

02:07:43.560 --> 02:07:45.840
I was thinking about Moon's prophecy

02:07:45.840 --> 02:07:47.460
while you were off chasing icicle.

02:07:47.520 --> 02:07:49.500
The stalker of dreams.

02:07:49.560 --> 02:07:52.619
That must be Scarlet, using the dream

02:07:52.619 --> 02:07:54.300
visitor to bother people, right?

02:07:54.359 --> 02:07:57.840
Maybe, Kibley said.

02:07:57.899 --> 02:07:59.460
Although there's something a little

02:07:59.460 --> 02:08:02.579
ominous about darkness and stalker so

02:08:02.579 --> 02:08:04.140
close to each other in the prophecy.

02:08:04.199 --> 02:08:06.720
What if there's a connection to that dark

02:08:06.720 --> 02:08:08.220
stalker you mentioned, Winter?

02:08:08.340 --> 02:08:11.039
Winter scoffed.

02:08:11.100 --> 02:08:12.960
He's been dead for centuries.

02:08:13.020 --> 02:08:16.140
If the prophecy is about him, it's a

02:08:16.140 --> 02:08:16.680
little out of date.

02:08:16.800 --> 02:08:20.819
Was it his imagination, or did Moon just

02:08:20.819 --> 02:08:22.500
press her eyes closed even harder?

02:08:22.619 --> 02:08:26.880
Everybody, shush, Kinkaju ordered.

02:08:27.000 --> 02:08:27.840
I'm telling you something.

02:08:27.899 --> 02:08:31.199
So I thought, if Scarlet is the stalker

02:08:31.199 --> 02:08:35.039
of dreams, maybe the talons of power and

02:08:35.039 --> 02:08:37.859
fire is that freaky sky wing everyone's

02:08:37.859 --> 02:08:39.479
afraid of, what's her name again?

02:08:39.539 --> 02:08:41.279
Peril.

02:08:41.340 --> 02:08:42.840
Winter growled.

02:08:42.899 --> 02:08:45.000
Of course it could be peril.

02:08:45.060 --> 02:08:47.399
The dragon who could burn other dragons

02:08:47.399 --> 02:08:48.899
to death just by touching them.

02:08:48.960 --> 02:08:52.319
She'd stared at him with her creepy, fiery

02:08:52.319 --> 02:08:54.600
blue eyes, standing there in the entrance

02:08:54.600 --> 02:08:56.819
hall of Jade Mountain, as though she

02:08:56.819 --> 02:08:58.020
could go wherever she pleased.

02:08:58.140 --> 02:09:01.020
After everything she'd done, and everyone

02:09:01.020 --> 02:09:01.800
she'd killed.

02:09:01.859 --> 02:09:03.899
Free and unpunished.

02:09:03.960 --> 02:09:05.399
It wasn't right.

02:09:05.460 --> 02:09:07.560
I could believe it.

02:09:07.619 --> 02:09:09.779
She's murder waiting to happen.

02:09:09.840 --> 02:09:11.819
Kibley shook his head.

02:09:11.880 --> 02:09:14.159
But she saved Clay's life.

02:09:14.220 --> 02:09:15.359
I was there.

02:09:15.420 --> 02:09:15.899
I saw it.

02:09:15.960 --> 02:09:18.119
I don't think she's working with Scarlet

02:09:18.119 --> 02:09:18.359
anymore.

02:09:18.420 --> 02:09:21.300
Then you're an even bigger fool than you

02:09:21.300 --> 02:09:22.979
look, Winter snapped.

02:09:23.039 --> 02:09:27.239
Hey, hey, quit being mean, Kinkaju said.

02:09:27.300 --> 02:09:30.300
Maybe that's what one who is not what she

02:09:30.300 --> 02:09:31.260
themes is about.

02:09:31.319 --> 02:09:34.680
Peril seems like she's changed, but

02:09:34.680 --> 02:09:36.659
actually, she is totally going to betray

02:09:36.659 --> 02:09:39.239
the dragonettes, and scorched the earth

02:09:39.239 --> 02:09:41.579
and kill everyone and all the other bad

02:09:41.579 --> 02:09:42.239
things at once.

02:09:42.300 --> 02:09:43.739
She paused.

02:09:43.800 --> 02:09:46.199
Suddenly, I am not enjoying this

02:09:46.199 --> 02:09:47.760
conversation as much as I thought I

02:09:47.760 --> 02:09:47.939
would.

02:09:48.000 --> 02:09:50.279
Did you see anything?

02:09:50.279 --> 02:09:51.960
In Peril's mind.

02:09:52.020 --> 02:09:55.140
Kibley asked Moon, nudging her gently.

02:09:55.199 --> 02:09:57.720
Was she planning anything terrible?

02:09:57.779 --> 02:10:01.439
Peril's mind is almost impossible to

02:10:01.439 --> 02:10:01.739
read.

02:10:01.800 --> 02:10:04.319
Moon said, opening her eyes.

02:10:04.380 --> 02:10:07.619
It's all fire in there, like she's

02:10:07.619 --> 02:10:08.760
burning from the inside too.

02:10:08.819 --> 02:10:12.899
I think, I think she's not a happy dragon

02:10:12.899 --> 02:10:14.819
but I'm not sure she's evil.

02:10:14.880 --> 02:10:16.560
I don't really know though.

02:10:16.619 --> 02:10:19.619
I mean, no one is completely evil.

02:10:19.680 --> 02:10:22.199
What are you talking about?

02:10:22.260 --> 02:10:23.579
Winter demanded.

02:10:23.640 --> 02:10:26.100
Plenty of dragons are completely evil.

02:10:26.159 --> 02:10:28.920
Not when you see what's going on inside

02:10:28.920 --> 02:10:29.279
them.

02:10:29.340 --> 02:10:31.500
Moon shook her head fiercely.

02:10:31.560 --> 02:10:33.659
Dragons are complicated.

02:10:33.720 --> 02:10:35.939
Some are kinder than others.

02:10:36.000 --> 02:10:38.579
She looked up at Kibley, then quickly

02:10:38.579 --> 02:10:39.000
away.

02:10:39.060 --> 02:10:41.340
Or braver than others.

02:10:41.399 --> 02:10:44.279
Here she glanced mysteriously at winter

02:10:44.279 --> 02:10:45.479
and he shivered.

02:10:45.539 --> 02:10:48.720
And some of them do really cruel things

02:10:48.720 --> 02:10:51.300
but everyone has both good thoughts and

02:10:51.300 --> 02:10:53.699
bad thoughts, and reasons for what they

02:10:53.699 --> 02:10:56.699
do, reasons they believe are important.

02:10:56.760 --> 02:10:58.920
I don't have bad thoughts.

02:10:58.979 --> 02:10:59.819
Do I?

02:10:59.939 --> 02:11:01.800
Kinkaju asked Moon.

02:11:01.859 --> 02:11:02.939
Moon laughed.

02:11:03.000 --> 02:11:05.880
True, not that I ever heard, she

02:11:05.880 --> 02:11:06.300
admitted.

02:11:06.359 --> 02:11:09.600
I'd better have them all now, quick, while

02:11:09.600 --> 02:11:13.079
I can, Kinkaju said, touching her Skyfire

02:11:13.079 --> 02:11:13.979
pout with a grin.

02:11:14.039 --> 02:11:17.039
Winter puzzled over Moon's words for a

02:11:17.039 --> 02:11:17.220
moment.

02:11:17.340 --> 02:11:20.340
He would have assumed that hearing other

02:11:20.340 --> 02:11:22.619
dragons' thoughts would confirm that most

02:11:22.619 --> 02:11:24.899
of them were evil, or at least halfway

02:11:24.899 --> 02:11:25.079
there.

02:11:25.199 --> 02:11:27.960
How could Moon be immersed in other mines

02:11:27.960 --> 02:11:30.180
all day, and still believe in the

02:11:30.180 --> 02:11:31.319
goodness of dragons?

02:11:31.439 --> 02:11:34.800
She hasn't met very many other dragons.

02:11:34.920 --> 02:11:36.060
He told himself.

02:11:36.119 --> 02:11:39.180
Growing up in the rainforest, hidden

02:11:39.180 --> 02:11:39.359
away.

02:11:39.420 --> 02:11:42.779
But she'd met the whole night wing tribe

02:11:42.779 --> 02:11:45.359
which surely was full of evil.

02:11:45.420 --> 02:11:49.260
And Peril, and Sora, the dragon who'd

02:11:49.260 --> 02:11:51.840
tried to kill Winter's sister, and Moon

02:11:51.840 --> 02:11:52.920
had met Icicle.

02:11:52.979 --> 02:11:55.920
Don't you think icicle is evil?

02:11:55.979 --> 02:11:56.939
He blurted.

02:11:57.000 --> 02:12:01.739
I mean, I don't, but no, Moon said.

02:12:01.800 --> 02:12:02.880
That's what I mean.

02:12:02.939 --> 02:12:05.640
She's doing what she thinks she has to do

02:12:05.640 --> 02:12:06.359
to save her brother.

02:12:06.420 --> 02:12:09.420
I wouldn't make the choices she's made.

02:12:09.479 --> 02:12:10.979
And she needs to be stopped.

02:12:11.100 --> 02:12:13.619
But I think I understand them.

02:12:13.680 --> 02:12:17.159
It is very cold and intense inside her

02:12:17.159 --> 02:12:17.460
head.

02:12:17.520 --> 02:12:22.020
I guess, I think it would be hard, growing

02:12:22.020 --> 02:12:24.359
up like she did. always knowing your

02:12:24.359 --> 02:12:28.920
parents are expecting, Um, expecting big

02:12:28.920 --> 02:12:30.539
um, things of you.

02:12:30.600 --> 02:12:34.319
She trailed off, giving Winter a sideways

02:12:34.319 --> 02:12:34.739
glance.

02:12:34.800 --> 02:12:38.039
She knows what my parents want from

02:12:38.039 --> 02:12:38.760
icicle.

02:12:38.819 --> 02:12:40.979
Winter realized with a jolt.

02:12:41.039 --> 02:12:43.920
She knows Icicle is supposed to grow up

02:12:43.920 --> 02:12:46.739
to challenge Queen Glacier, but she's

02:12:46.739 --> 02:12:48.060
keeping that secret.

02:12:48.119 --> 02:12:51.119
Perhaps just to show me that she can keep

02:12:51.119 --> 02:12:51.659
secrets.

02:12:51.720 --> 02:12:53.579
Don't trust her.

02:12:53.640 --> 02:12:55.199
He reminded himself.

02:12:55.260 --> 02:12:57.359
Nightwings are manipulative.

02:12:57.420 --> 02:12:59.699
She's probably just saying what I want to

02:12:59.699 --> 02:12:59.880
hear.

02:12:59.939 --> 02:13:03.899
Moon shifted her wings, turning to look

02:13:03.899 --> 02:13:06.180
at the playing dragonettes, and a fan of

02:13:06.180 --> 02:13:07.920
sunshine brushed across her scales.

02:13:07.979 --> 02:13:11.100
They're not just black.

02:13:11.159 --> 02:13:12.420
Winter thought.

02:13:12.479 --> 02:13:14.279
They're more of a dark purple.

02:13:14.340 --> 02:13:17.279
With shades of dark blue and green mixed

02:13:17.279 --> 02:13:17.460
in.

02:13:17.520 --> 02:13:21.840
Back to the prophecy, he said irritably

02:13:21.840 --> 02:13:22.739
trying to focus.

02:13:22.800 --> 02:13:25.739
So perhaps scarlet imperil are

02:13:25.739 --> 02:13:26.279
conspiring.

02:13:26.340 --> 02:13:28.979
Maybe they're planning to take down Jade

02:13:28.979 --> 02:13:29.640
Mountain together.

02:13:29.699 --> 02:13:32.159
What does the old night wing home have to

02:13:32.159 --> 02:13:32.520
do with that?

02:13:32.579 --> 02:13:36.539
We should go there and see, Kinkachu

02:13:36.539 --> 02:13:36.840
said.

02:13:36.899 --> 02:13:38.159
It's not far from here.

02:13:38.220 --> 02:13:41.819
Maybe, there's something there we can use

02:13:41.819 --> 02:13:42.300
to stop them.

02:13:42.420 --> 02:13:43.979
Kibley suggested.

02:13:44.039 --> 02:13:47.939
The 3rd dream visitor, Moon said

02:13:47.939 --> 02:13:48.420
suddenly.

02:13:48.539 --> 02:13:50.939
She sat up and flicked her tail over her

02:13:50.939 --> 02:13:51.479
talons.

02:13:51.539 --> 02:13:54.119
Starflight said it was lost when the

02:13:54.119 --> 02:13:55.079
volcano exploded.

02:13:55.140 --> 02:13:56.939
Maybe we can find it.

02:13:57.000 --> 02:14:00.420
Then we would need to hunt for icicle.

02:14:00.479 --> 02:14:02.460
Kibley said, turning to Winter.

02:14:02.520 --> 02:14:05.340
You could contact Scarlet yourself and

02:14:05.340 --> 02:14:06.420
ask about Hillstorm.

02:14:06.479 --> 02:14:09.779
I can't, Winter said.

02:14:09.899 --> 02:14:12.420
I've never seen Queen Scarlet.

02:14:12.479 --> 02:14:14.760
Icicle was part of the delegation that

02:14:14.760 --> 02:14:16.800
went to negotiate for Hellstorm's release

02:14:16.800 --> 02:14:18.960
unsuccessfully, obviously.

02:14:19.020 --> 02:14:22.140
So they met, and that's why Scarlet can

02:14:22.140 --> 02:14:22.859
get into her dreams.

02:14:22.920 --> 02:14:25.800
But I couldn't do it, even if I had a

02:14:25.800 --> 02:14:26.399
dream visitor.

02:14:26.520 --> 02:14:28.500
There was a pause.

02:14:28.560 --> 02:14:31.319
Kimberly tapped his claws together softly

02:14:31.319 --> 02:14:32.100
thoughtfully.

02:14:32.159 --> 02:14:35.220
I might be able to, he said.

02:14:35.279 --> 02:14:39.479
I saw her once, from far away, but I

02:14:39.479 --> 02:14:40.500
think I could dream visit her.

02:14:40.560 --> 02:14:42.539
So let's go.

02:14:42.600 --> 02:14:44.220
Kinkaju whispered.

02:14:44.279 --> 02:14:45.720
Moon, how about now?

02:14:45.840 --> 02:14:48.899
Moon tipped her head sideways, then

02:14:48.899 --> 02:14:49.380
nodded.

02:14:49.439 --> 02:14:52.680
I think they're calming down, she said

02:14:52.680 --> 02:14:54.840
but the little ones are still very

02:14:54.840 --> 02:14:55.500
interested in us.

02:14:55.560 --> 02:14:58.079
They'll put up a huge fuss if we try to

02:14:58.079 --> 02:14:58.619
leave.

02:14:58.680 --> 02:15:01.020
Oh, I have a plan for that.

02:15:01.079 --> 02:15:03.300
Kinkaju said confidently.

02:15:03.359 --> 02:15:05.399
Watch, it'll be hilarious.

02:15:05.460 --> 02:15:08.579
She fluffed out her wings, turned herself

02:15:08.579 --> 02:15:11.340
in iridescent blue like a dragonfly, and

02:15:11.340 --> 02:15:13.319
sauntered over to where the baby dragons

02:15:13.319 --> 02:15:15.840
were arguing in loud whispers about why

02:15:15.840 --> 02:15:18.119
Winter and Kibley had such weird tales.

02:15:18.180 --> 02:15:20.279
Hello?

02:15:20.340 --> 02:15:22.979
Kinkachu said to them, once play a game?

02:15:23.039 --> 02:15:24.539
Yes!

02:15:24.600 --> 02:15:26.460
They all shrieked in chorus.

02:15:26.579 --> 02:15:28.739
It's basically hide and seek.

02:15:28.800 --> 02:15:29.880
Kinkaju said.

02:15:29.939 --> 02:15:32.579
You know, where you try to find the

02:15:32.579 --> 02:15:33.960
camouflaged dragons.

02:15:34.020 --> 02:15:36.600
The 4 of us have a bet that we can each

02:15:36.600 --> 02:15:38.579
hide better than the others, even though

02:15:38.579 --> 02:15:41.340
I'm clearly going to win, because I'm the

02:15:41.340 --> 02:15:42.239
only rain wing.

02:15:42.359 --> 02:15:45.180
She lifted her talons and dramatically

02:15:45.180 --> 02:15:46.079
changed them red.

02:15:46.140 --> 02:15:50.039
Ooh. went all the dragonettes.

02:15:50.100 --> 02:15:53.159
So you all close your eyes and we'll

02:15:53.159 --> 02:15:53.579
hide.

02:15:53.640 --> 02:15:57.000
And whoever finds one of us 1st wins, said

02:15:57.000 --> 02:15:57.779
Kinkachu.

02:15:57.840 --> 02:16:00.359
All right, make sure you count to a 1000

02:16:00.359 --> 02:16:01.380
so we have enough time.

02:16:01.439 --> 02:16:05.520
Okay. squealed one of the rain wings

02:16:05.520 --> 02:16:06.479
covering her eyes.

02:16:06.539 --> 02:16:11.579
One, two, three, six, 17.

02:16:11.760 --> 02:16:14.039
The others all cover their eyes as well

02:16:14.039 --> 02:16:16.260
and began shouting random numbers along

02:16:16.260 --> 02:16:16.619
with her.

02:16:16.680 --> 02:16:20.579
Whoops, Kingajoo said, galloping back to

02:16:20.579 --> 02:16:20.880
Moon.

02:16:20.939 --> 02:16:24.180
I forgot about how most rain wings can't

02:16:24.180 --> 02:16:24.420
count.

02:16:24.479 --> 02:16:25.920
We'd better move fast.

02:16:25.979 --> 02:16:27.899
Which way?

02:16:28.020 --> 02:16:29.460
Kibli asked Moon.

02:16:29.520 --> 02:16:30.779
Where are the guards?

02:16:30.840 --> 02:16:34.260
Moon closed her eyes, and pointed at 6

02:16:34.260 --> 02:16:36.059
spots around the circumference of the

02:16:36.059 --> 02:16:36.840
trampoline walls.

02:16:36.959 --> 02:16:40.079
And 2 of them are also watching the sky

02:16:40.079 --> 02:16:41.999
to make sure we don't fly out.

02:16:42.059 --> 02:16:44.339
She added, opening her eyes again.

02:16:44.399 --> 02:16:47.700
So we go down, Winter said.

02:16:47.760 --> 02:16:48.719
Over here.

02:16:48.780 --> 02:16:52.020
He crossed to a corner with more shadows

02:16:52.020 --> 02:16:54.479
than the others, where a few curiously

02:16:54.479 --> 02:16:57.000
shaped branches and large seed pods were

02:16:57.000 --> 02:16:58.739
piled, as if were playing with.

02:16:58.860 --> 02:17:01.920
He moved them aside, and touched the

02:17:01.920 --> 02:17:03.420
place where the wall met the woven

02:17:03.420 --> 02:17:03.840
vines.

02:17:03.899 --> 02:17:07.260
If we make a hole here, they might not

02:17:07.260 --> 02:17:09.600
notice for a few minutes, long enough for

02:17:09.600 --> 02:17:10.079
us to get away.

02:17:10.200 --> 02:17:14.459
I can burn a hole, Kibley offered, small

02:17:14.459 --> 02:17:16.860
flames spurting from his nose.

02:17:16.920 --> 02:17:20.340
Put those away, Kinkachu said, batting it

02:17:20.340 --> 02:17:20.940
is snout.

02:17:21.000 --> 02:17:22.860
No fire in my forest, thank you.

02:17:22.920 --> 02:17:26.819
This will be safer, Winter said.

02:17:26.879 --> 02:17:30.059
He crouched, clenched his jaw, and

02:17:30.059 --> 02:17:32.339
summoned the cold from deep inside him.

02:17:32.399 --> 02:17:34.799
It hissed into his throat, like a

02:17:34.799 --> 02:17:36.000
building snowstorm.

02:17:36.059 --> 02:17:39.239
Finally, he opened his mouth and shot a

02:17:39.239 --> 02:17:41.159
shimmering blast of frost breath at the

02:17:41.159 --> 02:17:42.299
web of leaves and branches.

02:17:42.360 --> 02:17:45.780
He throws a spot just large enough for a

02:17:45.780 --> 02:17:48.360
dragon to crawl through, a small, icy

02:17:48.360 --> 02:17:49.920
circle of silver vegetation.

02:17:49.979 --> 02:17:54.479
600 One of the dragonettes bellowed

02:17:54.479 --> 02:17:56.459
suddenly, leaping ahead a few hundred.

02:17:56.520 --> 02:18:02.040
The others gleefully joined in, 609, 642.

02:18:02.340 --> 02:18:04.920
Quick, Moon whispered.

02:18:04.979 --> 02:18:07.680
Winter leaned forward and wrapped sharply

02:18:07.680 --> 02:18:09.120
on the ice with his front claws.

02:18:09.180 --> 02:18:12.120
The circle cracked, and then shattered

02:18:12.120 --> 02:18:14.639
into tiny frozen splinters, leaving a

02:18:14.639 --> 02:18:16.020
jagged hole at the base of the wall.

02:18:16.079 --> 02:18:18.299
What was that?

02:18:18.420 --> 02:18:20.819
One of the night wing dragonettes asked

02:18:20.819 --> 02:18:22.379
but he was drowned out by the others

02:18:22.379 --> 02:18:26.760
shouting, 698, 895.

02:18:27.000 --> 02:18:28.680
Go, go, go.

02:18:28.739 --> 02:18:30.659
Kingaju whispered frantically.

02:18:30.719 --> 02:18:33.359
Winter dove through the hole first

02:18:33.420 --> 02:18:35.520
catching his wings on a few remaining

02:18:35.520 --> 02:18:36.479
shards of ice.

02:18:36.540 --> 02:18:39.120
Moon was right behind him as he shot

02:18:39.120 --> 02:18:41.040
toward the ground and plunged into a

02:18:41.040 --> 02:18:42.239
thicket of enormous leaves.

02:18:42.360 --> 02:18:45.840
A moment later, Hibli and Kinkaju landed

02:18:45.840 --> 02:18:47.340
beside them with soft thuds.

02:18:47.399 --> 02:18:50.940
Kingachu's scales immediately shifted, and

02:18:50.940 --> 02:18:53.159
she vanished like a snowball thrown back

02:18:53.159 --> 02:18:53.579
into the snow.

02:18:53.639 --> 02:18:57.119
Moon was still as an iceberg beside

02:18:57.119 --> 02:18:59.519
winter, her wings folded to hide the

02:18:59.519 --> 02:19:01.559
silver scales that sparkled underneath

02:19:01.559 --> 02:19:04.259
her eyes closed and brow furrowed.

02:19:04.379 --> 02:19:06.419
He leaned closer to whisper into her

02:19:06.419 --> 02:19:06.659
ear.

02:19:06.719 --> 02:19:08.759
Did anyone see us?

02:19:08.819 --> 02:19:10.319
She shook her head.

02:19:10.379 --> 02:19:13.919
But I can't imagine those dragonettes are

02:19:13.919 --> 02:19:15.899
going to believe we're somehow hiding in

02:19:15.899 --> 02:19:16.379
there for very long.

02:19:16.440 --> 02:19:18.899
You'd be surprised.

02:19:18.959 --> 02:19:20.159
Kinkaju said.

02:19:20.219 --> 02:19:23.819
Hide and seek is our favorite game in

02:19:23.819 --> 02:19:24.959
kind of an obsessive way.

02:19:25.020 --> 02:19:27.659
They'll search every square inch of the

02:19:27.659 --> 02:19:28.559
wingery before giving up.

02:19:28.620 --> 02:19:31.020
I pulled a few things over to hide the

02:19:31.020 --> 02:19:31.440
hole.

02:19:31.500 --> 02:19:33.600
So with luck, we'll have a few minutes at

02:19:33.600 --> 02:19:33.840
least.

02:19:33.899 --> 02:19:38.100
This way, Moon said, slipping off into

02:19:38.100 --> 02:19:38.879
the trees.

02:19:38.940 --> 02:19:41.219
Winter tried to stay low and in the

02:19:41.219 --> 02:19:42.780
shadows as he hurried after her.

02:19:42.840 --> 02:19:45.239
He spotted the flicker of black wings

02:19:45.239 --> 02:19:47.879
overhead, as one of the guards circled

02:19:47.879 --> 02:19:50.040
around the wingery, but no one raised an

02:19:50.040 --> 02:19:50.579
alarm yet.

02:19:50.700 --> 02:19:53.459
How am I going to find icicle?

02:19:53.579 --> 02:19:56.040
He whispered to her, before anyone else

02:19:56.040 --> 02:19:56.340
does.

02:19:56.399 --> 02:19:59.760
She hesitated, giving him a worried

02:19:59.760 --> 02:20:00.719
sideways look.

02:20:00.780 --> 02:20:03.479
I don't know how much you want to hear

02:20:03.479 --> 02:20:04.379
about what I can do.

02:20:04.500 --> 02:20:06.000
She whispered back.

02:20:06.059 --> 02:20:08.579
I've never had anyone to talk to about it

02:20:08.579 --> 02:20:11.639
before, except, well, no one really.

02:20:11.700 --> 02:20:13.799
But I don't want to freak you out.

02:20:13.860 --> 02:20:17.459
It is disturbing, he admitted.

02:20:17.520 --> 02:20:20.159
But tell me anyway, if it's about

02:20:20.159 --> 02:20:20.700
icicle.

02:20:20.760 --> 02:20:23.520
I can't sense her anywhere.

02:20:23.579 --> 02:20:25.319
Moon shook her head.

02:20:25.379 --> 02:20:27.659
I've been listening as hard as I can

02:20:27.659 --> 02:20:29.879
since we got to the rainforest, but

02:20:29.879 --> 02:20:30.719
there's no sign of her.

02:20:30.780 --> 02:20:34.920
Maybe she left already, Winter said.

02:20:34.979 --> 02:20:37.920
Maybe, she figured out where Scarlet is

02:20:37.920 --> 02:20:39.120
and went to confront her.

02:20:39.180 --> 02:20:42.959
He checked behind him and saw only Kibley

02:20:42.959 --> 02:20:44.520
battling the vines and mud.

02:20:44.579 --> 02:20:47.280
If Kinkaju was there, it was impossible

02:20:47.280 --> 02:20:47.879
to tell.

02:20:47.879 --> 02:20:50.579
What he wouldn't give for camouflage

02:20:50.579 --> 02:20:51.059
scales.

02:20:51.120 --> 02:20:54.180
Then, he could slip through the trees

02:20:54.180 --> 02:20:56.879
without glory or any guards spotting him

02:20:56.879 --> 02:20:59.760
he could find icicle, and get her away

02:20:59.760 --> 02:21:01.139
from here before anything terrible

02:21:01.139 --> 02:21:01.559
happened.

02:21:01.620 --> 02:21:04.979
Anything else terrible, that is.

02:21:05.100 --> 02:21:08.760
Are you really wishing you were a rain

02:21:08.760 --> 02:21:09.420
wing right now?

02:21:09.540 --> 02:21:11.340
He scolded himself.

02:21:11.399 --> 02:21:13.860
Wouldn't mother and father love to hear

02:21:13.860 --> 02:21:14.219
about that?

02:21:14.280 --> 02:21:17.819
Now was the time to ditch these dragons

02:21:17.819 --> 02:21:19.860
before his thoughts got any more

02:21:19.860 --> 02:21:20.520
entangled.

02:21:20.579 --> 02:21:23.639
He could fall behind Kibley, wait until

02:21:23.639 --> 02:21:25.379
no one was paying attention, and then

02:21:25.379 --> 02:21:25.920
take off.

02:21:25.920 --> 02:21:29.159
Now that he had the sky fire, Moon

02:21:29.159 --> 02:21:30.659
wouldn't be able to find him by his

02:21:30.659 --> 02:21:30.899
thoughts.

02:21:31.020 --> 02:21:34.200
He'd hunt down icicle, and they'd go get

02:21:34.200 --> 02:21:35.040
Hellstorm together.

02:21:35.100 --> 02:21:37.979
Or if he couldn't find her, he'd go back

02:21:37.979 --> 02:21:40.139
to the ice kingdom on his own, like he'd

02:21:40.139 --> 02:21:40.860
originally planned.

02:21:40.920 --> 02:21:44.459
He paused for half a step, letting Moon

02:21:44.459 --> 02:21:45.479
slip ahead of him.

02:21:45.540 --> 02:21:49.799
Another minute, and then, Moon suddenly

02:21:49.799 --> 02:21:52.079
froze, digging her talons into the

02:21:52.079 --> 02:21:52.559
ground.

02:21:52.559 --> 02:21:55.260
Instinctively, Winter and Kibli froze

02:21:55.260 --> 02:21:55.500
too.

02:21:55.559 --> 02:21:58.680
Search party coming this way, she

02:21:58.680 --> 02:21:59.159
whispered.

02:21:59.219 --> 02:22:00.360
We have to hide.

02:22:00.420 --> 02:22:03.420
She turned and pushed winter toward a

02:22:03.420 --> 02:22:06.120
nearby fallen tree, covered with moss and

02:22:06.120 --> 02:22:07.559
winding yellow flower vines.

02:22:07.620 --> 02:22:09.780
Under there. you fit?

02:22:09.840 --> 02:22:12.000
I'd rather fight them.

02:22:12.059 --> 02:22:13.379
Winter objected.

02:22:13.440 --> 02:22:16.020
They'll thank your icicle and lock you

02:22:16.020 --> 02:22:16.200
up.

02:22:16.260 --> 02:22:18.299
Kinkaju's voice said from the air.

02:22:18.360 --> 02:22:21.719
Unless they kill you first, Kibley said

02:22:21.719 --> 02:22:23.700
which I realize I should be more

02:22:23.700 --> 02:22:25.860
enthusiastic about, but for some reason

02:22:25.860 --> 02:22:26.219
I'm not.

02:22:26.280 --> 02:22:27.059
Come on.

02:22:27.120 --> 02:22:30.299
He tugged on one of winter's wings, then

02:22:30.299 --> 02:22:32.760
dove under the tree himself, rolling into

02:22:32.760 --> 02:22:33.840
a ball in the shadows.

02:22:33.899 --> 02:22:37.260
Winter reluctantly followed, crouching

02:22:37.260 --> 02:22:39.059
until his underbelly was sliding across

02:22:39.059 --> 02:22:39.899
the wet leaves.

02:22:39.959 --> 02:22:43.260
Dangling curls of damp moss caught on his

02:22:43.260 --> 02:22:45.479
horns, and something scuttled down his

02:22:45.479 --> 02:22:47.700
spine as he wedged himself in next to

02:22:47.700 --> 02:22:48.959
Kibley's warm scales.

02:22:49.020 --> 02:22:52.500
Oh, why are you so glittery?

02:22:52.620 --> 02:22:55.139
Kinkaju fretted from outside the hiding

02:22:55.139 --> 02:22:55.500
hole.

02:22:55.559 --> 02:22:57.540
Nothing natural is that color.

02:22:57.600 --> 02:23:00.959
It's all right, Moon whispered back.

02:23:01.020 --> 02:23:03.780
Just try to cover us and stay as still as

02:23:03.780 --> 02:23:04.020
you can.

02:23:04.139 --> 02:23:07.620
I'll have you know, I was a hide and seek

02:23:07.620 --> 02:23:08.520
champion.

02:23:08.579 --> 02:23:10.139
Kinkaju started.

02:23:10.200 --> 02:23:13.979
No one, shh, Moon said, and a moment

02:23:13.979 --> 02:23:16.200
later, Winter was startled to feel her

02:23:16.200 --> 02:23:17.520
sliding in beside him.

02:23:17.520 --> 02:23:20.280
The silver scales by her eyes caught the

02:23:20.280 --> 02:23:22.319
light for a moment as she turned her head

02:23:22.319 --> 02:23:23.040
listening.

02:23:23.100 --> 02:23:25.559
He could feel the whole length of her

02:23:25.559 --> 02:23:28.139
body breathing softly, anxiously.

02:23:28.200 --> 02:23:31.559
That's better, Kinkaju whispered.

02:23:31.620 --> 02:23:32.819
I can't see him anymore.

02:23:32.879 --> 02:23:36.600
Winter covered the Skyfire pouch with one

02:23:36.600 --> 02:23:38.159
of his talons and tried to breathe.

02:23:38.219 --> 02:23:41.340
Maybe this was what Moon had meant when

02:23:41.340 --> 02:23:43.079
she said reading his mind was confusing.

02:23:43.139 --> 02:23:45.180
He couldn't even tell what he was

02:23:45.180 --> 02:23:45.540
feeling.

02:23:45.600 --> 02:23:50.219
Furious, trapped, frustrated, grateful

02:23:50.219 --> 02:23:55.500
safe, alone, protected, on fire.

02:23:55.559 --> 02:23:59.219
Wanting the wrong things, hating himself

02:23:59.219 --> 02:24:02.340
confused, confused, confused.

02:24:02.399 --> 02:24:06.479
His mind flashed back to the 1st time

02:24:06.479 --> 02:24:08.940
he'd done a ranking test out in a storm

02:24:08.940 --> 02:24:10.739
with hailstorm and icicle.

02:24:10.799 --> 02:24:13.020
They'd lost him as soon as they could

02:24:13.020 --> 02:24:15.180
each striking out on their own.

02:24:15.180 --> 02:24:18.059
It made sense, even to a one year old

02:24:18.059 --> 02:24:19.500
dragonette struggling through a

02:24:19.500 --> 02:24:19.860
blizzard.

02:24:19.920 --> 02:24:22.200
Nobody wanted to risk letting someone

02:24:22.200 --> 02:24:23.879
else drag down their ranking number.

02:24:23.940 --> 02:24:26.399
So what were these dragons doing?

02:24:26.459 --> 02:24:28.860
Why were they risking the wrath of their

02:24:28.860 --> 02:24:30.000
queens by helping him?

02:24:30.059 --> 02:24:33.600
Moon's scales rippled as she shifted

02:24:33.600 --> 02:24:34.020
quietly.

02:24:34.079 --> 02:24:36.600
Was that her heartbeat he could feel?

02:24:36.659 --> 02:24:38.819
Thundering in the places where their

02:24:38.819 --> 02:24:40.020
wings were pressed together?

02:24:40.079 --> 02:24:42.180
Or was that his own?

02:24:42.299 --> 02:24:44.700
He closed his eyes and tried to stop

02:24:44.700 --> 02:24:45.120
thinking.

02:24:45.180 --> 02:24:49.139
A few eternities passed, and then finally

02:24:49.139 --> 02:24:51.360
moon whispered, They're gone.

02:24:51.420 --> 02:24:54.719
Then get out of the way and let me out

02:24:54.719 --> 02:24:57.899
Winter said, in a strangled voice that

02:24:57.899 --> 02:24:59.459
came out more harshly than he'd meant it

02:24:59.459 --> 02:24:59.700
to.

02:24:59.760 --> 02:25:02.639
She rolled instantly away, and he

02:25:02.639 --> 02:25:04.260
wriggled after her until he stood

02:25:04.260 --> 02:25:06.299
blinking in the green rainforest light

02:25:06.299 --> 02:25:06.540
again.

02:25:06.600 --> 02:25:09.600
Kimley emerged, stretching out his wings

02:25:09.600 --> 02:25:10.500
and shaking his tail.

02:25:10.559 --> 02:25:14.219
Careful with that thing, Winter snapped

02:25:14.219 --> 02:25:16.620
glaring in the poisonous barb as it swung

02:25:16.620 --> 02:25:17.280
back and forth.

02:25:17.340 --> 02:25:21.239
If you ever get stabbed by my tail, I

02:25:21.239 --> 02:25:22.620
promise it won't be by accident.

02:25:22.680 --> 02:25:24.780
Kibley said haughtily.

02:25:24.840 --> 02:25:26.340
Moon, wait up.

02:25:26.399 --> 02:25:29.280
She was already moving away, toward the

02:25:29.280 --> 02:25:31.440
sound of a waterfall in the distance, and

02:25:31.440 --> 02:25:32.760
the sand wing hurried after her.

02:25:32.819 --> 02:25:34.920
I could leave now.

02:25:34.979 --> 02:25:37.799
Winter thought, feeling as though his

02:25:37.799 --> 02:25:39.899
talons were paralyzed with indecision.

02:25:39.959 --> 02:25:42.180
I should leave now.

02:25:42.239 --> 02:25:45.600
That would be the smart ice wing thing to

02:25:45.600 --> 02:25:45.780
do.

02:25:45.840 --> 02:25:49.139
The words you're looking for are, thank

02:25:49.139 --> 02:25:52.139
you, Kinkachu said, materializing

02:25:52.139 --> 02:25:53.159
suddenly beside him.

02:25:53.219 --> 02:25:54.299
Winter jumped.

02:25:54.360 --> 02:25:57.780
Thank you, Moon, for warning me and

02:25:57.780 --> 02:26:00.180
hiding me and helping me, even though I

02:26:00.180 --> 02:26:02.459
am an enormous super jerk sometimes.

02:26:02.459 --> 02:26:05.340
She flounced off into the trees.

02:26:05.399 --> 02:26:08.100
Her orange scales fading back into the

02:26:08.100 --> 02:26:09.000
green of the leaves.

02:26:09.059 --> 02:26:12.299
Winter hesitated, and then followed her.

02:26:12.360 --> 02:26:15.659
They're still useful to me, he thought.

02:26:15.719 --> 02:26:18.420
I have a better chance of finding icicle

02:26:18.420 --> 02:26:19.020
if I stay with them.

02:26:19.079 --> 02:26:20.639
But just for now.

02:26:20.700 --> 02:26:24.059
Soon, he promised himself.

02:26:24.120 --> 02:26:26.040
I'll leave soon.

02:26:26.100 --> 02:26:30.479
Chapter 7.

02:26:30.540 --> 02:26:34.500
When winter caught up to the others, they

02:26:34.500 --> 02:26:36.239
were gathered at the base of a huge tree

02:26:36.239 --> 02:26:38.819
beside a waterfall, staring up at a hole

02:26:38.819 --> 02:26:40.920
in the trunk, there was something

02:26:40.920 --> 02:26:43.920
immediately and indefinably uncomfortable

02:26:43.920 --> 02:26:44.819
about this place.

02:26:44.819 --> 02:26:47.399
It was like a spot of thin ice on a

02:26:47.399 --> 02:26:49.979
frozen lake, where the cool safety of the

02:26:49.979 --> 02:26:52.200
upper world came too close to the dark

02:26:52.200 --> 02:26:53.159
depths below.

02:26:53.219 --> 02:26:56.040
That's the tunnel to the night wing

02:26:56.040 --> 02:26:56.700
island.

02:26:56.760 --> 02:26:58.500
Kinkaju said softly.

02:26:58.559 --> 02:27:01.079
Her voice was never that quiet or

02:27:01.079 --> 02:27:01.680
wobbly.

02:27:01.739 --> 02:27:03.360
Winter squinted at her.

02:27:03.420 --> 02:27:05.100
Was she afraid of the place for some

02:27:05.100 --> 02:27:05.280
reason?

02:27:05.340 --> 02:27:08.040
You can wait here if you want.

02:27:08.100 --> 02:27:11.219
Moon said, brushing Kinkaju's tail with

02:27:11.219 --> 02:27:11.459
her own.

02:27:11.520 --> 02:27:14.940
If it's too... to anything.

02:27:15.000 --> 02:27:18.540
I'm all right, Kingaju said.

02:27:18.600 --> 02:27:21.180
She flared the rough behind her ears, and

02:27:21.180 --> 02:27:22.680
deliberately turned her scales dark

02:27:22.680 --> 02:27:23.040
blue.

02:27:23.100 --> 02:27:26.159
I just haven't been back since the whole

02:27:26.159 --> 02:27:27.540
thing.

02:27:27.659 --> 02:27:32.100
Whoa, Kibley said, making the connection

02:27:32.100 --> 02:27:32.879
before winter did.

02:27:32.940 --> 02:27:35.340
I didn't realize you were.

02:27:35.459 --> 02:27:37.860
You're one of the rain wings they...

02:27:38.459 --> 02:27:40.500
Imprisoned and experimented on.

02:27:40.559 --> 02:27:42.360
Moon finished for him.

02:27:42.420 --> 02:27:46.920
It wasn't quite as horrible as it sounds

02:27:46.920 --> 02:27:48.239
Kinkachu said.

02:27:48.299 --> 02:27:50.819
Only, mostly that horrible.

02:27:50.879 --> 02:27:54.420
Winter had to take a deep breath, and

02:27:54.420 --> 02:27:56.280
poke the feeling he was having to be sure

02:27:56.280 --> 02:27:57.000
he was having it.

02:27:57.000 --> 02:27:59.280
Respect for Kinkaju?

02:27:59.340 --> 02:28:02.219
Surprised that a dragon as silly as her

02:28:02.219 --> 02:28:03.899
could have survived what the night wings

02:28:03.899 --> 02:28:04.920
did to the rain wings.

02:28:05.040 --> 02:28:08.340
He'd heard only rumors, really. stories

02:28:08.340 --> 02:28:10.139
that had spread after the war ended.

02:28:10.200 --> 02:28:13.200
Tales of night wings abducting harmless

02:28:13.200 --> 02:28:15.299
rain wings, dragging them back to the

02:28:15.299 --> 02:28:17.940
volcanic island, chaining them up, and

02:28:17.940 --> 02:28:19.680
forcing them to use their venom so the

02:28:19.680 --> 02:28:21.180
night wings could study it.

02:28:21.239 --> 02:28:23.579
It sounded unforgivable to him.

02:28:23.639 --> 02:28:26.459
But Kinkachu did not act like a dragon

02:28:26.459 --> 02:28:27.299
with a grudge.

02:28:27.360 --> 02:28:29.520
She didn't seem to hate the night wings

02:28:29.520 --> 02:28:31.739
at all, even though she clearly should.

02:28:31.799 --> 02:28:34.799
Yet she treated Moon like a best friend.

02:28:34.860 --> 02:28:39.479
Because moon is different, whispered his

02:28:39.479 --> 02:28:41.940
treacherous mind, because she would never

02:28:41.940 --> 02:28:43.559
do what the other night wings did.

02:28:43.620 --> 02:28:47.459
But you don't hate them, Kibley said

02:28:47.459 --> 02:28:48.899
echoing Winter's thoughts.

02:28:48.959 --> 02:28:50.579
That's fascinating.

02:28:50.639 --> 02:28:55.739
Well, they're not my favorite dragons

02:28:55.739 --> 02:28:58.739
Kinkaju admitted, squirming, except Moon

02:28:58.739 --> 02:29:00.719
of course, and Deathbringer is usually

02:29:00.719 --> 02:29:01.139
pretty great.

02:29:01.200 --> 02:29:04.139
But, you know, they're trying to change.

02:29:04.200 --> 02:29:05.280
They have to.

02:29:05.340 --> 02:29:08.280
And with glory as their queen, they won't

02:29:08.280 --> 02:29:09.360
do any more awful things.

02:29:09.420 --> 02:29:13.200
We'll see, Winter muttered.

02:29:13.260 --> 02:29:15.899
Moon flew up to the hole and stepped

02:29:15.899 --> 02:29:17.819
inside, then twisted to look back at

02:29:17.819 --> 02:29:18.120
them.

02:29:18.180 --> 02:29:20.219
Winter, come look at this.

02:29:20.280 --> 02:29:24.000
Just inside the mouth of the tunnel was a

02:29:24.000 --> 02:29:26.459
squashed wet leaf, shaped a bit like a

02:29:26.459 --> 02:29:27.420
scavenger's paw.

02:29:27.479 --> 02:29:30.600
When winter crouched to sniff it, it felt

02:29:30.600 --> 02:29:32.159
colder than the tunnel around them.

02:29:32.219 --> 02:29:34.319
Did she go this way?

02:29:34.440 --> 02:29:35.819
He asked Moon.

02:29:35.879 --> 02:29:37.319
I don't know.

02:29:37.379 --> 02:29:38.340
She said.

02:29:38.399 --> 02:29:41.399
I still can't hear her, but maybe that's

02:29:41.399 --> 02:29:41.819
why.

02:29:41.879 --> 02:29:43.500
If she's at the volcano.

02:29:43.559 --> 02:29:46.680
Winter started down the tunnel, walking

02:29:46.680 --> 02:29:48.780
straight into that unsettling, wrong

02:29:48.780 --> 02:29:49.739
feeling air.

02:29:49.799 --> 02:29:51.719
He heard the shuffling wings of the

02:29:51.719 --> 02:29:52.979
others falling in behind him.

02:29:52.979 --> 02:29:56.280
Heat crackled along his scales as he

02:29:56.280 --> 02:29:58.079
glimpsed the end of the tunnel, and he

02:29:58.079 --> 02:29:58.440
paused.

02:29:58.559 --> 02:30:01.559
This was worse than the damp rainforest

02:30:01.559 --> 02:30:01.979
heat.

02:30:02.040 --> 02:30:04.319
This was the kind of heat, where he

02:30:04.319 --> 02:30:05.819
wouldn't be able to use his frost

02:30:05.819 --> 02:30:06.239
breath.

02:30:06.299 --> 02:30:08.340
And there was something blurring his

02:30:08.340 --> 02:30:08.819
sight.

02:30:08.879 --> 02:30:11.879
Bits of ash, maybe, drifting through the

02:30:11.879 --> 02:30:12.120
air.

02:30:12.180 --> 02:30:14.879
He took a deep breath and stepped out

02:30:14.879 --> 02:30:15.600
into a cave.

02:30:15.659 --> 02:30:18.600
His talons sinking instantly into a layer

02:30:18.600 --> 02:30:20.100
of ash that covered the floor.

02:30:20.219 --> 02:30:23.219
It was dark, and nearly impossible to see

02:30:23.219 --> 02:30:26.100
but a faint gray light scraped the walls

02:30:26.100 --> 02:30:27.120
on either side of him.

02:30:27.180 --> 02:30:30.120
Winter took a step forward as Moon

02:30:30.120 --> 02:30:32.520
emerged behind him and breathed out a

02:30:32.520 --> 02:30:33.420
small plume of fire.

02:30:33.540 --> 02:30:37.139
Sharp claws seized winter's heart.

02:30:37.200 --> 02:30:39.899
The shape of a huge dragon loomed

02:30:39.899 --> 02:30:42.600
overhead, its wings outstretched, its

02:30:42.600 --> 02:30:43.920
talons reaching toward him.

02:30:43.979 --> 02:30:48.059
He's dead, Moon said quickly, whoever he

02:30:48.059 --> 02:30:49.379
is, he's gone.

02:30:49.440 --> 02:30:52.020
This is just the shape of him left

02:30:52.020 --> 02:30:52.319
behind.

02:30:52.379 --> 02:30:55.680
She edged forward and tapped one of the

02:30:55.680 --> 02:30:56.639
grasping talons.

02:30:56.700 --> 02:30:58.620
The dragon didn't move.

02:30:58.680 --> 02:30:59.760
I wonder who it was.

02:30:59.879 --> 02:31:03.659
Winter's breath slowly returned.

02:31:03.719 --> 02:31:05.819
He carefully made his way around the

02:31:05.819 --> 02:31:08.399
petrified dragon, trying not to touch the

02:31:08.399 --> 02:31:10.139
statue of hardened ash.

02:31:10.200 --> 02:31:12.600
There was a tunnel he could just squeeze

02:31:12.600 --> 02:31:15.239
into, although it was clogged with ash

02:31:15.239 --> 02:31:17.819
and the floor was a field of cooled lava

02:31:17.819 --> 02:31:19.500
that was still too hot for winter's

02:31:19.500 --> 02:31:19.799
liking.

02:31:19.860 --> 02:31:23.280
It was a relief when he reached open air

02:31:23.280 --> 02:31:25.260
and was able to spread his wings and

02:31:25.260 --> 02:31:25.680
fly.

02:31:25.739 --> 02:31:29.700
This, then, at last, was the secret home

02:31:29.700 --> 02:31:30.600
of the night wings.

02:31:30.659 --> 02:31:34.079
He circled, studying everything below him

02:31:34.079 --> 02:31:36.899
and felt his triumph dimming.

02:31:37.020 --> 02:31:39.540
The island was smaller than winter could

02:31:39.540 --> 02:31:40.139
have imagined.

02:31:40.200 --> 02:31:43.079
It made him feel instantly claustrophobic

02:31:43.079 --> 02:31:46.620
even with, or perhaps because of, the

02:31:46.620 --> 02:31:48.780
vast ocean lurking in all directions

02:31:48.780 --> 02:31:52.020
dense black ripples of lava flows covered

02:31:52.020 --> 02:31:54.420
everything he could see, still glowing

02:31:54.420 --> 02:31:57.000
orange and yellow in places, where liquid

02:31:57.000 --> 02:31:58.379
fire was spilling through the cracks.

02:31:58.440 --> 02:32:02.520
A mountain cut jaggedly into the sky, the

02:32:02.520 --> 02:32:05.399
volcano itself, but it looked as if the

02:32:05.399 --> 02:32:07.920
top had been smashed in, leaving a

02:32:07.920 --> 02:32:08.399
smoking hole.

02:32:08.459 --> 02:32:11.459
Had the air been this impossible to

02:32:11.459 --> 02:32:13.440
breathe before the volcano erupted?

02:32:13.500 --> 02:32:16.860
Thick gray clouds, heavy with ash and

02:32:16.860 --> 02:32:19.260
smoke, and sizzling with lightning

02:32:19.260 --> 02:32:20.340
stretched across the sky.

02:32:20.399 --> 02:32:24.659
Everything smelled of sulfur and fire, and

02:32:24.659 --> 02:32:24.959
death.

02:32:25.020 --> 02:32:28.079
Winter couldn't imagine anyone actually

02:32:28.079 --> 02:32:28.739
living here.

02:32:28.799 --> 02:32:31.739
What did the night wings eat in a place

02:32:31.739 --> 02:32:32.579
so empty of life?

02:32:32.639 --> 02:32:34.620
How could they sleep?

02:32:34.680 --> 02:32:37.559
With a promise of fiery death smoking and

02:32:37.559 --> 02:32:39.239
muttering over their heads all the time?

02:32:39.299 --> 02:32:42.000
Who would raise their dragonettes in such

02:32:42.000 --> 02:32:42.719
a hideous place?

02:32:42.780 --> 02:32:46.319
It felt like a whale smacking him in the

02:32:46.319 --> 02:32:46.559
face.

02:32:46.620 --> 02:32:49.260
How suddenly and completely, he

02:32:49.260 --> 02:32:51.360
understood Moon's mother, and her

02:32:51.360 --> 02:32:53.639
decision to hide Moon in the rainforest.

02:32:53.819 --> 02:32:56.340
The stranger question was why other night

02:32:56.340 --> 02:32:57.659
wings hadn't done the same.

02:32:57.719 --> 02:33:00.840
Afraid to disobey their queen, probably.

02:33:00.899 --> 02:33:02.219
He guessed.

02:33:02.280 --> 02:33:05.159
Ice Wings followed Queen Glacier's orders

02:33:05.159 --> 02:33:07.559
with unquestioning obedience as they were

02:33:07.559 --> 02:33:09.059
handed down through the levels of the

02:33:09.059 --> 02:33:09.780
aristocracy.

02:33:09.840 --> 02:33:11.879
It was like obeying your parents.

02:33:11.940 --> 02:33:14.100
No one would ever think to do otherwise.

02:33:14.159 --> 02:33:17.159
But Ice Wings had the entire Ice

02:33:17.159 --> 02:33:17.520
Kingdom.

02:33:17.579 --> 02:33:20.040
The safest and most purely beautiful

02:33:20.040 --> 02:33:21.840
place to live in all of Pyria.

02:33:21.899 --> 02:33:24.180
It was the polar opposite of this

02:33:24.180 --> 02:33:24.780
nightmare.

02:33:24.840 --> 02:33:27.059
Queen Glacier took care of them.

02:33:27.120 --> 02:33:29.700
The night wing queen could not have cared

02:33:29.700 --> 02:33:31.799
about her subjects at all if she kept

02:33:31.799 --> 02:33:33.180
them rotting in a place like this.

02:33:33.239 --> 02:33:37.860
Oh, Kinkachu gasped, soaring up beside

02:33:37.860 --> 02:33:39.059
him with Moon and Kibley.

02:33:39.120 --> 02:33:41.280
Look, they're fortress.

02:33:41.340 --> 02:33:42.959
It's totally destroyed.

02:33:43.079 --> 02:33:45.840
She pointed to the smoking volcano.

02:33:45.899 --> 02:33:48.600
Winter hadn't even noticed the outline of

02:33:48.600 --> 02:33:50.940
walls poking through the lava, but now

02:33:50.940 --> 02:33:52.620
that he looked, he could see the clear

02:33:52.620 --> 02:33:54.120
shape of the wrecked structure.

02:33:54.180 --> 02:33:57.000
One of the towers looked eerily like his

02:33:57.000 --> 02:33:59.280
own flight training tower in Glaciers

02:33:59.280 --> 02:33:59.639
Palace.

02:33:59.700 --> 02:34:02.879
I had no idea, Moon said.

02:34:02.940 --> 02:34:05.700
I mean, I've seen the island in their

02:34:05.700 --> 02:34:07.440
heads, but I never felt this.

02:34:07.500 --> 02:34:11.700
Mother never said, It's so horrible.

02:34:11.760 --> 02:34:16.319
Holy smoking vipers, Kibley said.

02:34:16.379 --> 02:34:18.840
The sand wing swooped down toward a river

02:34:18.840 --> 02:34:20.940
of molten lava, and then back up to

02:34:20.940 --> 02:34:21.239
winter.

02:34:21.299 --> 02:34:24.600
If I ever had nightmares, they'd be about

02:34:24.600 --> 02:34:25.979
this place from now on.

02:34:26.040 --> 02:34:28.739
I think this might take care of my

02:34:28.739 --> 02:34:29.399
nightmares.

02:34:29.520 --> 02:34:30.719
Kinkaju said.

02:34:30.780 --> 02:34:33.360
Imagine having your home devastated like

02:34:33.360 --> 02:34:33.719
this.

02:34:33.780 --> 02:34:35.280
Poor night wings.

02:34:35.340 --> 02:34:39.239
Poor night wings. winter exploded.

02:34:39.299 --> 02:34:40.379
He would not.

02:34:40.440 --> 02:34:43.559
Would not feel sorry for night wings.

02:34:43.620 --> 02:34:45.299
Are you serious?

02:34:45.360 --> 02:34:46.559
What is wrong with you?

02:34:46.620 --> 02:34:48.600
Don't you remember what they were doing

02:34:48.600 --> 02:34:49.500
to your tribe?

02:34:49.559 --> 02:34:50.459
To you?

02:34:50.520 --> 02:34:52.799
How they planned to steal the rainforest

02:34:52.799 --> 02:34:54.000
and probably kill you all?

02:34:54.059 --> 02:34:57.299
Kinkaju flinched away from him, covering

02:34:57.299 --> 02:34:57.659
her eyes.

02:34:57.719 --> 02:35:01.079
I know, she said in a small voice.

02:35:01.139 --> 02:35:03.239
But isn't it still sad?

02:35:03.299 --> 02:35:05.639
They deserve this.

02:35:05.700 --> 02:35:06.959
Winter spat.

02:35:07.020 --> 02:35:08.639
After everything they've done.

02:35:08.700 --> 02:35:11.100
The night wings deserve to lose their

02:35:11.100 --> 02:35:12.059
home like this.

02:35:12.120 --> 02:35:13.979
How can you say that?

02:35:14.100 --> 02:35:15.239
Moon asked.

02:35:15.299 --> 02:35:17.399
How could any tribe deserve this?

02:35:17.459 --> 02:35:21.000
Seriously, Kibley said.

02:35:21.059 --> 02:35:23.219
What did they do to the ice wings to make

02:35:23.219 --> 02:35:24.000
you hate them so much?

02:35:24.059 --> 02:35:27.360
Winter twisted away from them, flying

02:35:27.360 --> 02:35:28.139
toward the volcano.

02:35:28.200 --> 02:35:31.139
His training had never covered this.

02:35:31.260 --> 02:35:33.239
He'd grown up knowing the old stories

02:35:33.239 --> 02:35:35.399
about night wings, and he'd always

02:35:35.399 --> 02:35:36.899
assumed everybody else did too.

02:35:36.959 --> 02:35:40.020
They were a part of his bones, and the

02:35:40.020 --> 02:35:41.159
bones of every ice wing.

02:35:41.280 --> 02:35:43.680
We hate night wings.

02:35:43.739 --> 02:35:45.120
They stole from us.

02:35:45.180 --> 02:35:47.760
They're all liars and backstabbers and

02:35:47.760 --> 02:35:48.239
monsters.

02:35:48.299 --> 02:35:50.760
Was it a secret?

02:35:50.819 --> 02:35:52.979
The story what they'd done to the ice

02:35:52.979 --> 02:35:54.299
wings so long ago?

02:35:54.360 --> 02:35:56.760
Or did other tribes not know about it

02:35:56.760 --> 02:35:58.500
because they didn't particularly care?

02:35:58.559 --> 02:36:01.319
Or because the night wings had covered it

02:36:01.319 --> 02:36:03.719
up over the years, layering their own

02:36:03.719 --> 02:36:04.979
lies on top of the truth?

02:36:05.040 --> 02:36:07.200
That was certainly something they were

02:36:07.200 --> 02:36:08.280
particularly good at.

02:36:08.340 --> 02:36:12.120
A blast of sulfurous smoke came from one

02:36:12.120 --> 02:36:14.040
of the vents below, and he dodged around

02:36:14.040 --> 02:36:14.879
it, coughing.

02:36:15.000 --> 02:36:18.000
He'd always imagined the night wings

02:36:18.000 --> 02:36:19.920
lounging around their secret home in

02:36:19.920 --> 02:36:22.979
perfect security, feasting and laughing

02:36:22.979 --> 02:36:25.139
and reveling in their superiority.

02:36:25.200 --> 02:36:27.780
He'd imagine them living among marvels

02:36:27.780 --> 02:36:31.260
perhaps deep underground somewhere, smugly

02:36:31.260 --> 02:36:33.120
enjoying what they'd stolen from the ice

02:36:33.120 --> 02:36:33.600
wings.

02:36:33.659 --> 02:36:34.979
Not this.

02:36:35.040 --> 02:36:37.739
Not anything like this Hellscape.

02:36:37.799 --> 02:36:41.040
He banked to the left, searching the

02:36:41.040 --> 02:36:42.360
ground for any sign of icicle.

02:36:42.479 --> 02:36:44.219
Winter?

02:36:44.340 --> 02:36:47.100
He turned and found Moon following him.

02:36:47.159 --> 02:36:49.799
Please tell me, she said.

02:36:49.860 --> 02:36:52.319
I really don't know what the Night Wings

02:36:52.319 --> 02:36:54.780
did, and I think, I think I need to.

02:36:54.899 --> 02:36:57.420
She flicked her tail anxiously.

02:36:57.479 --> 02:37:00.299
Does it have something to do with dark

02:37:00.299 --> 02:37:00.899
stalker?

02:37:00.959 --> 02:37:02.639
It does.

02:37:02.760 --> 02:37:03.899
Winter said.

02:37:03.959 --> 02:37:06.600
Watching Kibley and Kinkaju flying over

02:37:06.600 --> 02:37:07.260
to join them.

02:37:07.319 --> 02:37:10.739
Well, if it was a secret, someone should

02:37:10.739 --> 02:37:12.000
have told him to keep it that way.

02:37:12.059 --> 02:37:15.000
The truth was, it was better for everyone

02:37:15.000 --> 02:37:17.760
to know, so they'd understand never to

02:37:17.760 --> 02:37:19.079
trust the night wings.

02:37:19.139 --> 02:37:22.559
But it begins with his thrice cursed

02:37:22.559 --> 02:37:24.000
mother, Foeslayer.

02:37:24.059 --> 02:37:26.459
She approached the ice wings under the

02:37:26.459 --> 02:37:28.860
guise of peace, to offer us an alliance

02:37:28.860 --> 02:37:31.739
against the sky wings, and instead, she

02:37:31.739 --> 02:37:32.819
abducted our prints.

02:37:32.940 --> 02:37:34.979
What for?

02:37:35.040 --> 02:37:36.299
Kibley asked.

02:37:36.360 --> 02:37:39.120
You know, all the ice wing princes I've

02:37:39.120 --> 02:37:40.920
met have been kind of grouchy.

02:37:40.979 --> 02:37:43.559
Why would someone want one around enough

02:37:43.559 --> 02:37:44.280
to steal him?

02:37:44.340 --> 02:37:46.440
Winter glared at him.

02:37:46.500 --> 02:37:49.260
Because Prince Arctic was our last

02:37:49.260 --> 02:37:50.040
animus.

02:37:50.100 --> 02:37:53.639
They all gazed back blankly, as though

02:37:53.639 --> 02:37:55.559
they'd completely missed the thunderbolt

02:37:55.559 --> 02:37:56.879
he'd just thrown at their feet.

02:37:57.180 --> 02:38:01.500
Our last animus, he growled.

02:38:01.559 --> 02:38:02.639
Don't you know anything?

02:38:02.760 --> 02:38:05.520
Not every tribe has animus dragons.

02:38:05.579 --> 02:38:08.040
Ice Wings haven't had any in centuries.

02:38:08.040 --> 02:38:09.299
And you know why?

02:38:09.360 --> 02:38:11.819
Because the Nightwing stole that power

02:38:11.819 --> 02:38:12.479
from us.

02:38:12.540 --> 02:38:14.700
That's crazy.

02:38:14.760 --> 02:38:16.500
Kibli protested.

02:38:16.559 --> 02:38:18.659
You can't steal a power like that.

02:38:18.719 --> 02:38:22.739
You can if it's genetic, Winter said.

02:38:22.799 --> 02:38:25.379
The Night Wings never had an animus

02:38:25.379 --> 02:38:27.899
dragon until they took Prince Arctic.

02:38:27.959 --> 02:38:30.180
Now they have them, and we don't.

02:38:30.299 --> 02:38:33.600
He took off, flying in a wide circle

02:38:33.600 --> 02:38:36.000
around the volcano as he eyed the lava

02:38:36.000 --> 02:38:36.899
strewn slopes.

02:38:36.959 --> 02:38:39.420
He kept hoping to see a flash of white

02:38:39.420 --> 02:38:41.340
scales, but the only colors on this

02:38:41.340 --> 02:38:44.219
island were black and red and gold and

02:38:44.219 --> 02:38:44.520
gray.

02:38:44.639 --> 02:38:48.600
Wait, Moon said, catching up to him.

02:38:48.719 --> 02:38:50.040
What are you saying?

02:38:50.100 --> 02:38:53.760
That faux slayer, and Prince Arctic.

02:38:53.760 --> 02:38:55.860
They had eggs together?

02:38:55.920 --> 02:38:58.440
A night wing and an ice wing?

02:38:58.500 --> 02:39:01.319
Sounds twisted, doesn't it?

02:39:01.379 --> 02:39:04.620
Winter hissed, ignoring the stab of guilt

02:39:04.620 --> 02:39:05.639
he felt at the thought.

02:39:05.760 --> 02:39:08.760
Especially when you realize that Arctic

02:39:08.760 --> 02:39:10.739
would never have agreed to it, would

02:39:10.739 --> 02:39:12.299
never have betrayed the royal family that

02:39:12.299 --> 02:39:15.000
way, unless Foe Slayer threatened him

02:39:15.000 --> 02:39:15.719
with something terrible.

02:39:15.780 --> 02:39:18.420
But whatever she did, it worked.

02:39:18.479 --> 02:39:21.780
Moon's wings missed a beat, and she

02:39:21.780 --> 02:39:22.739
nearly fell out of the sky.

02:39:22.799 --> 02:39:25.680
Winter, she cried.

02:39:25.739 --> 02:39:28.500
Are you saying Dark Stalker's father was

02:39:28.500 --> 02:39:29.340
an ice wing?

02:39:29.399 --> 02:39:32.219
Not just any ice wing?

02:39:32.280 --> 02:39:33.899
Winter snarled.

02:39:33.959 --> 02:39:37.139
Prince Arctic, the very last animus ever

02:39:37.139 --> 02:39:39.659
hatched in the ice wing tribe, father of

02:39:39.659 --> 02:39:41.760
the dark stalker, the 1st night wing

02:39:41.760 --> 02:39:42.239
animus.

02:39:42.299 --> 02:39:43.620
They planned it that way.

02:39:43.680 --> 02:39:48.420
That's complicated and devious.

02:39:48.479 --> 02:39:49.440
Kibley said.

02:39:49.500 --> 02:39:51.059
Congratulations.

02:39:51.180 --> 02:39:54.059
You've just summed up Nightwings, Winter

02:39:54.059 --> 02:39:54.479
said to him.

02:39:54.540 --> 02:39:57.299
They couldn't Arctic go home after that?

02:39:57.360 --> 02:39:58.799
Kinkaju asked.

02:39:58.860 --> 02:40:02.219
I mean, once they had his eggs, couldn't

02:40:02.219 --> 02:40:03.180
the Nightwings let him go?

02:40:03.239 --> 02:40:05.579
Why didn't he go back to the ice wings

02:40:05.579 --> 02:40:06.600
and have more eggs there?

02:40:06.659 --> 02:40:10.440
Winter saw moon falter again, and

02:40:10.440 --> 02:40:12.540
realized that somehow she knew the

02:40:12.540 --> 02:40:12.780
answer.

02:40:12.840 --> 02:40:17.280
Because Dark Stalker killed him, Winter

02:40:17.280 --> 02:40:17.520
said.

02:40:17.639 --> 02:40:20.520
His own son murdered him to make sure the

02:40:20.520 --> 02:40:22.500
ice wings never got their stolen power

02:40:22.500 --> 02:40:23.159
back.

02:40:23.219 --> 02:40:24.959
That's not?

02:40:24.959 --> 02:40:27.540
Moon cried, and then checked herself.

02:40:27.600 --> 02:40:30.899
I mean, that's not the reason I heard.

02:40:30.959 --> 02:40:34.620
Well, it's the truth, Winter said.

02:40:34.680 --> 02:40:37.620
The volcano rumbled threateningly, and

02:40:37.620 --> 02:40:39.540
spat a small shower of sparks into the

02:40:39.540 --> 02:40:39.780
air.

02:40:39.840 --> 02:40:42.420
They were flying over the far side of the

02:40:42.420 --> 02:40:44.280
island now, and there was still no sign

02:40:44.280 --> 02:40:45.059
of icicle.

02:40:45.120 --> 02:40:49.139
But, Kibley said cautiously.

02:40:49.200 --> 02:40:51.000
Is it that big a deal?

02:40:51.059 --> 02:40:54.540
I mean, I hear animus dragons are more

02:40:54.540 --> 02:40:55.379
trouble than they're worth.

02:40:55.440 --> 02:40:57.780
Don't they go crazy after a while?

02:40:57.840 --> 02:41:00.959
That's true, Moon said.

02:41:01.079 --> 02:41:03.600
I read about a sea wing animus who

02:41:03.600 --> 02:41:05.340
murdered almost his entire family.

02:41:05.459 --> 02:41:08.219
But we knew how to handle them.

02:41:08.340 --> 02:41:09.899
Winter scoffed.

02:41:09.959 --> 02:41:12.540
We perfected the use of anima's power.

02:41:12.659 --> 02:41:15.120
Ice Wings were the 1st tribe to figure

02:41:15.120 --> 02:41:17.639
out that too much use can damage the

02:41:17.639 --> 02:41:18.360
dragon's soul.

02:41:18.479 --> 02:41:21.180
So we were very careful with our animus

02:41:21.180 --> 02:41:21.659
dragons.

02:41:21.719 --> 02:41:24.719
We bred them into the royal line, watched

02:41:24.719 --> 02:41:27.120
each potential animus from hatching, and

02:41:27.120 --> 02:41:28.860
trained them carefully so they would

02:41:28.860 --> 02:41:29.700
understand their limits.

02:41:29.760 --> 02:41:32.879
Each ice wing animus spent years planning

02:41:32.879 --> 02:41:35.040
his or her one great enchantment.

02:41:35.100 --> 02:41:37.979
They could use their power just once, to

02:41:37.979 --> 02:41:39.420
create something that would benefit the

02:41:39.420 --> 02:41:40.020
whole tribe.

02:41:40.079 --> 02:41:42.659
Prince Arctic was only days away from his

02:41:42.659 --> 02:41:44.819
gifting ceremony when the Nightwings

02:41:44.819 --> 02:41:45.479
kidnapped him.

02:41:45.540 --> 02:41:48.479
Wait, Kibley said.

02:41:48.540 --> 02:41:50.940
What happened if an animist didn't do

02:41:50.940 --> 02:41:51.600
what he was told?

02:41:51.659 --> 02:41:54.000
What if he wanted to use his power for

02:41:54.000 --> 02:41:54.479
something else?

02:41:54.600 --> 02:41:56.760
Or what if he didn't want to marry

02:41:56.760 --> 02:41:58.799
whatever princess was chosen for him?

02:41:58.860 --> 02:42:02.760
I don't understand the question, Winter

02:42:02.760 --> 02:42:03.059
said.

02:42:03.120 --> 02:42:05.459
It is obviously an honor to marry into

02:42:05.459 --> 02:42:07.079
the Royal Ice Wing lineage.

02:42:07.139 --> 02:42:10.799
But if you take away all of a dragon's

02:42:10.799 --> 02:42:14.579
choices, Kibley trailed off, stop being

02:42:14.579 --> 02:42:15.180
obtuse.

02:42:15.299 --> 02:42:16.500
Winter shouted.

02:42:16.559 --> 02:42:18.299
You are missing the point entirely.

02:42:18.360 --> 02:42:21.659
Prince Arctic was our animus heritage, and

02:42:21.659 --> 02:42:23.459
everything would be different if the

02:42:23.459 --> 02:42:24.840
night wings hadn't stolen and killed

02:42:24.840 --> 02:42:25.139
him.

02:42:25.200 --> 02:42:28.020
I'm just wondering if there's another

02:42:28.020 --> 02:42:28.860
side of the story.

02:42:28.920 --> 02:42:31.799
Kibley suggested, shrugging his wings.

02:42:31.860 --> 02:42:34.979
No, Winter said, there isn't.

02:42:35.100 --> 02:42:38.520
What I'm wondering is why you're still so

02:42:38.520 --> 02:42:39.360
mad about it.

02:42:39.479 --> 02:42:41.399
Kinkaju interjected.

02:42:41.459 --> 02:42:44.219
It sounds like it happened 100s and 100s

02:42:44.219 --> 02:42:45.180
of years ago.

02:42:45.239 --> 02:42:46.559
Isn't it time to move on?

02:42:46.620 --> 02:42:49.260
Who cares about all that ancient

02:42:49.260 --> 02:42:49.620
history?

02:42:49.680 --> 02:42:53.100
It's not ancient history to us.

02:42:53.159 --> 02:42:54.659
Winter growled.

02:42:54.719 --> 02:42:57.120
We still live with a consequences every

02:42:57.120 --> 02:42:57.299
day.

02:42:57.360 --> 02:43:00.780
But you can't blame the night wings who

02:43:00.780 --> 02:43:01.440
are alive now.

02:43:01.500 --> 02:43:04.860
It wasn't their idea, she argued.

02:43:04.920 --> 02:43:06.479
And it's not like you can get your

02:43:06.479 --> 02:43:09.120
vengeance on Foe Slayer or Dark Stalker.

02:43:09.180 --> 02:43:12.000
Moon dropped suddenly down toward the

02:43:12.000 --> 02:43:14.459
fortress, startled and irritated.

02:43:14.520 --> 02:43:16.920
Winter had to wheel around in midair to

02:43:16.920 --> 02:43:17.280
follow her.

02:43:17.340 --> 02:43:18.719
When they caught up.

02:43:18.780 --> 02:43:20.639
She was sitting in the mouth of a half

02:43:20.639 --> 02:43:22.979
caved in tunnel, peering into the

02:43:22.979 --> 02:43:23.579
darkness.

02:43:23.639 --> 02:43:27.540
I don't think this is right, she said, as

02:43:27.540 --> 02:43:28.559
they all landed next to her.

02:43:28.620 --> 02:43:31.620
This isn't the lost city of night and the

02:43:31.620 --> 02:43:32.040
prophecy.

02:43:32.159 --> 02:43:33.780
It isn't?

02:43:33.899 --> 02:43:35.159
Kingaju said.

02:43:35.219 --> 02:43:36.000
Why not?

02:43:36.059 --> 02:43:39.420
There was a city before this one, Moon

02:43:39.420 --> 02:43:39.719
said.

02:43:39.840 --> 02:43:42.360
The Nightwings used to live somewhere on

02:43:42.360 --> 02:43:44.700
the continent, back in Darkstalker's time

02:43:44.700 --> 02:43:47.159
but they fled their city after he was

02:43:47.159 --> 02:43:51.540
once he was gone, and they came here, to

02:43:51.540 --> 02:43:53.459
hide from him in case he ever came back.

02:43:53.520 --> 02:43:56.940
She cast an odd, worried look at winter.

02:43:57.000 --> 02:43:59.940
I think that's the city we need to find

02:43:59.940 --> 02:44:02.579
the ancient one, the one that's really

02:44:02.579 --> 02:44:02.879
lost.

02:44:02.940 --> 02:44:06.299
Oh, Kinkaju said.

02:44:06.360 --> 02:44:08.399
You couldn't have maybe mentioned that a

02:44:08.399 --> 02:44:08.940
bit sooner?

02:44:09.000 --> 02:44:11.399
Sorry, Moon said.

02:44:11.459 --> 02:44:13.139
I was hoping this would work.

02:44:13.200 --> 02:44:16.500
So we don't have to go look for a dream

02:44:16.500 --> 02:44:17.340
visitor in there?

02:44:17.399 --> 02:44:19.860
Kibley said, nodding toward the tunnel

02:44:19.860 --> 02:44:23.340
because I am all in favor of not going

02:44:23.340 --> 02:44:25.379
into the creepy smoking lava filled

02:44:25.379 --> 02:44:25.620
tunnel.

02:44:25.739 --> 02:44:28.200
Me too, Moon agreed.

02:44:28.319 --> 02:44:30.540
Except that I thought I heard.

02:44:30.780 --> 02:44:32.100
Maybe.

02:44:32.100 --> 02:44:34.020
Icicle?

02:44:34.079 --> 02:44:34.979
Winter demanded.

02:44:35.040 --> 02:44:36.239
You think she's in there?

02:44:36.299 --> 02:44:39.299
I'm not sure, Moon said.

02:44:39.360 --> 02:44:42.239
But at almost the same time, they all

02:44:42.239 --> 02:44:45.899
heard a strange scrape sound from deep

02:44:45.899 --> 02:44:46.860
inside the volcano.

02:44:46.920 --> 02:44:50.280
Oh, dear, Kingaju whispered.

02:44:50.340 --> 02:44:52.799
Now I'm really wishing we had saved the

02:44:52.799 --> 02:44:54.840
ancient evil dragon stories for somewhere

02:44:54.840 --> 02:44:56.040
less spooky.

02:44:56.100 --> 02:44:58.079
Scray.

02:44:58.200 --> 02:45:00.959
Scrape.

02:45:00.959 --> 02:45:03.180
Scrape.

02:45:03.360 --> 02:45:06.540
Winter was sure, a moment before Moon

02:45:06.540 --> 02:45:07.799
turned to him with wide eyes.

02:45:07.860 --> 02:45:11.100
He saw the glint of silver pale scales

02:45:11.100 --> 02:45:12.659
shimmering toward him, as a figure

02:45:12.659 --> 02:45:15.000
crawled slowly out of the dark tunnel.

02:45:15.059 --> 02:45:16.739
It was icicle.

02:45:16.799 --> 02:45:18.780
They'd found her at last.

02:45:18.840 --> 02:45:23.219
Chapter 8.

02:45:23.280 --> 02:45:27.840
She's not all right, Moon whispered to

02:45:27.840 --> 02:45:28.020
him.

02:45:28.079 --> 02:45:30.600
Her mind is all scattered and foggy.

02:45:30.659 --> 02:45:31.559
I don't know why.

02:45:31.680 --> 02:45:35.399
A talon of ice trailed down winter's

02:45:35.399 --> 02:45:37.739
spine as he watched his sister stagger

02:45:37.739 --> 02:45:38.520
into the gray light.

02:45:38.579 --> 02:45:41.639
Her arctic blue eyes were bloodshot

02:45:41.639 --> 02:45:44.639
crackled with dark blue veins, and the

02:45:44.639 --> 02:45:46.260
scratches she'd gotten in the fight at

02:45:46.260 --> 02:45:48.180
Jade Mountain still hadn't healed.

02:45:48.239 --> 02:45:51.479
She was streaked with mud and blood, not

02:45:51.479 --> 02:45:53.760
just her own dark blue blood, but

02:45:53.760 --> 02:45:56.040
splatters of dark red that must have come

02:45:56.040 --> 02:45:57.420
from the night wing she'd killed.

02:45:57.479 --> 02:46:00.659
Icicle scales had always been wider than

02:46:00.659 --> 02:46:03.780
everyone else's, her claws sharper, her

02:46:03.780 --> 02:46:06.479
teeth gleaming, and her spikes pristine

02:46:06.479 --> 02:46:08.819
even after clubbing a walrus to death.

02:46:08.879 --> 02:46:11.819
She plunged into the frigid ocean 6 times

02:46:11.819 --> 02:46:14.340
a day, because she believed an ice wing

02:46:14.340 --> 02:46:16.500
who glittered like diamonds was a more

02:46:16.500 --> 02:46:17.459
menacing ice wing.

02:46:17.520 --> 02:46:21.180
In icicles view of the world, grubby, dull

02:46:21.180 --> 02:46:23.219
dragons deserve to be 7th circle.

02:46:23.280 --> 02:46:25.979
Winter could never have imagined her

02:46:25.979 --> 02:46:27.000
looking this wretched.

02:46:27.120 --> 02:46:30.059
She clutched the edge of the tunnel with

02:46:30.059 --> 02:46:32.280
her front talons, leaning against the

02:46:32.280 --> 02:46:33.840
rocky wall and glaring at him.

02:46:33.899 --> 02:46:36.000
Icicle?

02:46:36.000 --> 02:46:36.659
he said.

02:46:36.719 --> 02:46:37.799
Are you?

02:46:38.040 --> 02:46:39.840
Why are you here?

02:46:39.959 --> 02:46:43.319
she spat, to ruin yet another of my

02:46:43.319 --> 02:46:43.620
plans?

02:46:43.680 --> 02:46:46.260
You don't feel satisfied that you've

02:46:46.260 --> 02:46:48.420
already guaranteed Hailstorm's death?

02:46:48.479 --> 02:46:50.520
What's wrong with you?

02:46:50.579 --> 02:46:52.139
Kinkachu blurted.

02:46:52.200 --> 02:46:53.159
You look terrible.

02:46:53.219 --> 02:46:56.940
Could be worse, Icicle snarled.

02:46:57.000 --> 02:46:58.319
I could look like you.

02:46:58.379 --> 02:47:02.219
I want to help you find Hillstorm, Winter

02:47:02.219 --> 02:47:02.579
said.

02:47:02.639 --> 02:47:04.139
If he's really still alive.

02:47:04.200 --> 02:47:08.520
I don't need your help of all dragons.

02:47:08.579 --> 02:47:11.879
Icicles said with a hiss, limping forward

02:47:11.879 --> 02:47:12.420
a step.

02:47:12.479 --> 02:47:15.239
You don't have the claws to do what needs

02:47:15.239 --> 02:47:15.840
to be done.

02:47:15.899 --> 02:47:19.260
She touched her head, wiping away a

02:47:19.260 --> 02:47:20.879
trickle of blood from one of her horns.

02:47:20.940 --> 02:47:23.399
And she's probably killed him by now

02:47:23.399 --> 02:47:23.819
anyway.

02:47:23.879 --> 02:47:26.340
What did Scarlet say?

02:47:26.399 --> 02:47:27.659
Winter asked.

02:47:27.719 --> 02:47:30.239
He spread his wings, blocking her path.

02:47:30.299 --> 02:47:32.760
When she found out Starflight and the

02:47:32.760 --> 02:47:33.479
others were still alive.

02:47:33.540 --> 02:47:36.479
I haven't spoken to her.

02:47:36.540 --> 02:47:39.239
Icicle swayed a little on her feet.

02:47:39.360 --> 02:47:42.959
I can't, I don't want to see her.

02:47:43.079 --> 02:47:47.100
To admit, I failed your fault.

02:47:47.159 --> 02:47:49.860
But what if she kills him in front of

02:47:49.860 --> 02:47:50.100
me?

02:47:50.159 --> 02:47:52.680
Or what if he's already dead?

02:47:52.739 --> 02:47:56.219
And she shows me his body.

02:47:56.280 --> 02:47:59.700
She took another staggering step and

02:47:59.700 --> 02:48:01.680
Winter reached out to catch her, but she

02:48:01.680 --> 02:48:03.899
recoiled, snapping her teeth at him.

02:48:03.959 --> 02:48:06.360
But how have you?

02:48:06.840 --> 02:48:07.260
He started.

02:48:07.379 --> 02:48:09.659
She hasn't slept.

02:48:09.780 --> 02:48:11.940
Moon said wonderingly.

02:48:12.000 --> 02:48:14.040
Not since Jade Mountain.

02:48:14.100 --> 02:48:18.120
If I don't sleep, Icicle muttered

02:48:18.120 --> 02:48:20.459
triumphantly, then she can't get to me.

02:48:20.520 --> 02:48:23.399
She can't visit my dreams if I don't have

02:48:23.399 --> 02:48:23.700
any.

02:48:23.760 --> 02:48:25.020
Ha ha.

02:48:25.079 --> 02:48:27.840
But it's been days.

02:48:27.959 --> 02:48:29.280
Kingaju cried.

02:48:29.340 --> 02:48:31.139
You haven't slept in days?

02:48:31.200 --> 02:48:32.819
Don't you feel awful?

02:48:32.879 --> 02:48:36.840
I don't need to sleep, Isaacle said.

02:48:36.899 --> 02:48:40.379
Whenever I get tired, I lie down beside

02:48:40.379 --> 02:48:42.540
the lava until the pain wakes me up.

02:48:42.659 --> 02:48:46.319
She spread her wings, and winter saw with

02:48:46.319 --> 02:48:48.299
a shudder, that she had blisters and

02:48:48.299 --> 02:48:50.639
small burns bubbling in spots across her

02:48:50.639 --> 02:48:51.000
scales.

02:48:51.059 --> 02:48:55.680
This, he could imagine too easily.

02:48:55.739 --> 02:48:59.340
His fearless, stubborn sister angrily

02:48:59.340 --> 02:49:02.219
burning herself, slashing pain across the

02:49:02.219 --> 02:49:04.500
body that betrayed her by daring to be

02:49:04.500 --> 02:49:05.340
tired.

02:49:05.399 --> 02:49:07.200
And he understood what she was going

02:49:07.200 --> 02:49:07.680
through too.

02:49:07.799 --> 02:49:10.500
He'd lived with the guilt of losing

02:49:10.500 --> 02:49:12.239
hailstorm for the last 2 years.

02:49:12.299 --> 02:49:14.399
Icicle.

02:49:14.459 --> 02:49:16.440
We need to know if she's killed him.

02:49:16.500 --> 02:49:17.399
He said.

02:49:17.459 --> 02:49:20.639
I'd wager a few camels that she hasn't

02:49:20.639 --> 02:49:21.840
said Kibley.

02:49:21.899 --> 02:49:24.239
He's more used to her as a bargaining

02:49:24.239 --> 02:49:25.739
chip than as a corpse.

02:49:25.799 --> 02:49:28.860
Not very useful, corpses as a rule.

02:49:28.920 --> 02:49:31.200
All right, shutting up now.

02:49:31.260 --> 02:49:34.260
He added, catching the look moon was

02:49:34.260 --> 02:49:34.680
shooting him.

02:49:34.739 --> 02:49:37.739
Do you have any idea where she is?

02:49:37.799 --> 02:49:39.719
Winter asked Icicle.

02:49:39.780 --> 02:49:41.459
If we can get to her and find him.

02:49:41.520 --> 02:49:45.059
If it were that easy, I'd have done it.

02:49:45.180 --> 02:49:46.739
Icicle snapped.

02:49:46.799 --> 02:49:49.620
I've considered all the options. trust

02:49:49.620 --> 02:49:49.979
me.

02:49:50.040 --> 02:49:53.100
There's only one way to save him, and

02:49:53.100 --> 02:49:55.319
that's killing the rain wing queen.

02:49:55.379 --> 02:49:57.959
I'm not going to let you kill Queen

02:49:57.959 --> 02:49:58.500
Glory.

02:49:58.620 --> 02:50:00.479
Kinkaju said stoutly.

02:50:00.540 --> 02:50:03.120
Icicle barked a ragged laugh.

02:50:03.180 --> 02:50:05.340
And how are you going to stop me?

02:50:05.459 --> 02:50:07.739
You preposterous pink dragon.

02:50:07.799 --> 02:50:11.340
Kinkachu lunged at icicle. flying past

02:50:11.340 --> 02:50:13.979
winter in a red and orange blur before he

02:50:13.979 --> 02:50:15.000
realized what was happening.

02:50:15.059 --> 02:50:17.760
The little rain wing knocked icicle over

02:50:17.760 --> 02:50:19.920
onto her back and wrapped her talons

02:50:19.920 --> 02:50:21.180
around the ice wing's throat.

02:50:21.239 --> 02:50:24.000
Nobody threatens my queen.

02:50:24.059 --> 02:50:25.979
Kinkachu shouted.

02:50:26.040 --> 02:50:27.840
Hey, Winter shouted.

02:50:27.899 --> 02:50:29.819
Get off me!

02:50:29.879 --> 02:50:31.319
Icicle raged.

02:50:31.379 --> 02:50:33.959
She swung her tail at Kinkaju's wings, but

02:50:33.959 --> 02:50:34.319
missed.

02:50:34.379 --> 02:50:36.180
Her vicious claws went up.

02:50:36.239 --> 02:50:39.120
The serrated edges glittering dangerously

02:50:39.120 --> 02:50:41.760
ready for a killing blow at Kinkaju's

02:50:41.760 --> 02:50:42.180
underbelly.

02:50:42.239 --> 02:50:43.799
Kinkajou!

02:50:43.920 --> 02:50:45.899
Moon cried, jumping toward them.

02:50:45.959 --> 02:50:48.299
But before she could reach them, before

02:50:48.299 --> 02:50:50.819
icicle could strike, before winter could

02:50:50.819 --> 02:50:53.159
do anything, something small came

02:50:53.159 --> 02:50:55.139
whistling through the air, and thunked

02:50:55.139 --> 02:50:56.579
into icicle's neck.

02:50:56.700 --> 02:50:59.700
Icicle let out a gasp and jerked back.

02:50:59.760 --> 02:51:02.159
Kinkachu jumped off of her with a yelp

02:51:02.159 --> 02:51:03.299
and looked up at the sky.

02:51:03.360 --> 02:51:06.540
Winter followed her gaze to the clouds

02:51:06.540 --> 02:51:09.239
and then watched as the gray melted and

02:51:09.239 --> 02:51:11.819
shifted, like dragonettes bursting out of

02:51:11.819 --> 02:51:15.059
the snow, into 9 dragons in shades of red

02:51:15.059 --> 02:51:16.139
and gold and green.

02:51:16.200 --> 02:51:20.159
Icicle of the ice wings, Queen Glory

02:51:20.159 --> 02:51:22.799
announced, you are under arrest for

02:51:22.799 --> 02:51:24.239
murder and attempted murder.

02:51:24.299 --> 02:51:25.979
No!

02:51:26.100 --> 02:51:28.799
Icicle roared, clawing at her neck.

02:51:28.860 --> 02:51:30.959
She rolled over and shoved herself

02:51:30.959 --> 02:51:33.479
upright, but her legs wobbled, and her

02:51:33.479 --> 02:51:35.100
head was starting to droop.

02:51:35.159 --> 02:51:36.600
What have you done to me?

02:51:36.659 --> 02:51:38.159
What is happening?

02:51:38.280 --> 02:51:41.940
It's only a tranquilizer dot, said

02:51:41.940 --> 02:51:44.100
Deathbringer, winging down to land beside

02:51:44.100 --> 02:51:44.280
them.

02:51:44.340 --> 02:51:47.159
We find it makes transporting prisoners

02:51:47.159 --> 02:51:47.700
much simpler.

02:51:47.819 --> 02:51:50.040
You'll wake up just fine in a few hours.

02:51:50.100 --> 02:51:53.040
No, Icicle shrieked.

02:51:53.100 --> 02:51:54.420
I can't sleep.

02:51:54.479 --> 02:51:55.680
Don't make me sleep.

02:51:55.739 --> 02:51:59.340
She hurled herself at winter, dug her

02:51:59.340 --> 02:52:01.680
claws into his shoulders, and shook him

02:52:01.680 --> 02:52:03.239
with all of her fading strength.

02:52:03.299 --> 02:52:05.819
Winter, stop them.

02:52:05.879 --> 02:52:06.600
Help me.

02:52:06.659 --> 02:52:08.219
Tell them I can't.

02:52:08.340 --> 02:52:09.840
She'll find me.

02:52:09.899 --> 02:52:12.840
She'll tell me he's dead, and then it'll

02:52:12.840 --> 02:52:14.459
be over, and he'll be gone.

02:52:14.579 --> 02:52:15.840
Winter.

02:52:15.899 --> 02:52:17.340
Keep me awake.

02:52:17.399 --> 02:52:21.959
It's too late, Deathbringer said. studying

02:52:21.959 --> 02:52:23.159
her with a puzzled expression.

02:52:23.219 --> 02:52:25.020
It's not that bad.

02:52:25.079 --> 02:52:26.159
The dot sleep.

02:52:26.219 --> 02:52:29.100
Isicle slowly collapsed forward onto

02:52:29.100 --> 02:52:31.739
winter, her talons clenching open and

02:52:31.739 --> 02:52:34.020
closed, as if she was trying to claw

02:52:34.020 --> 02:52:34.979
herself back to waking.

02:52:35.100 --> 02:52:39.120
She'll come for me, Icicle whispered.

02:52:39.180 --> 02:52:42.479
So let her come, Winter said.

02:52:42.540 --> 02:52:45.180
He crouched as his sister's weight

02:52:45.180 --> 02:52:47.280
pressed him down, bringing his mouth

02:52:47.280 --> 02:52:48.239
close to her ear.

02:52:48.299 --> 02:52:51.000
Go ahead and sleep icicle.

02:52:51.059 --> 02:52:53.219
You can stay awake forever anyway.

02:52:53.280 --> 02:52:56.399
Talk to Scarlet, and tell her she can

02:52:56.399 --> 02:52:57.420
still get what she wants.

02:52:57.479 --> 02:52:59.940
But she can't.

02:53:00.000 --> 02:53:03.059
Icicle's voice was barely a mumble now.

02:53:03.120 --> 02:53:06.180
I'll be... prison.

02:53:06.239 --> 02:53:09.059
Winter glanced up at the faces around

02:53:09.059 --> 02:53:09.299
them.

02:53:09.360 --> 02:53:11.879
Nobody could hear what he and Icicle were

02:53:11.879 --> 02:53:13.979
whispering to each other, not unless they

02:53:13.979 --> 02:53:15.000
could read minds.

02:53:15.059 --> 02:53:18.180
Well, this was one way to find out if the

02:53:18.180 --> 02:53:19.200
Skyfire really worked.

02:53:19.260 --> 02:53:22.979
He leaned closer to icicle, close enough

02:53:22.979 --> 02:53:25.260
for the Skyfire pouch to touch her scales

02:53:25.260 --> 02:53:26.700
as well as his own.

02:53:26.760 --> 02:53:30.180
And then, as his sister's eyes closed, he

02:53:30.180 --> 02:53:33.600
whispered, Tell Scarlet, if she can prove

02:53:33.600 --> 02:53:34.920
that Hellstorm is still alive.

02:53:34.979 --> 02:53:37.799
I'll kill glory for her myself.

02:53:37.979 --> 02:53:42.420
Chapter 9.

02:53:42.479 --> 02:53:46.559
The healer's pavilion near the rain wing

02:53:46.559 --> 02:53:50.520
village was large, quiet, and sunlit, with

02:53:50.520 --> 02:53:52.559
curtains of green vines shielding the

02:53:52.559 --> 02:53:55.260
interior from curious onlookers, and

02:53:55.260 --> 02:53:58.020
there were plenty of curious dragons, ones

02:53:58.020 --> 02:54:00.180
winter could see, and ones he could only

02:54:00.180 --> 02:54:03.000
hear. murmuring and twittering, like a

02:54:03.000 --> 02:54:04.979
council of invisible birds in the trees.

02:54:05.040 --> 02:54:07.440
The rainforest was starting to give him

02:54:07.440 --> 02:54:10.079
the suffocating, spine crawling feeling

02:54:10.079 --> 02:54:12.239
that he was always being watched.

02:54:12.540 --> 02:54:15.059
Only rain wings were allowed to carry the

02:54:15.059 --> 02:54:16.020
unconscious prisoner.

02:54:16.079 --> 02:54:18.540
Glory ordered all the night wings to stay

02:54:18.540 --> 02:54:21.059
away and sent Deathbringer to make sure

02:54:21.059 --> 02:54:22.260
none of them came looking for her.

02:54:22.319 --> 02:54:25.680
She also didn't object when Winter pushed

02:54:25.680 --> 02:54:27.959
his way into the pavilion and stood next

02:54:27.959 --> 02:54:30.000
to his sister, glowering around

02:54:30.000 --> 02:54:30.840
defiantly.

02:54:30.899 --> 02:54:34.319
I'm staying right here, he said.

02:54:34.379 --> 02:54:37.860
Understood, Glory said with a nod.

02:54:37.979 --> 02:54:40.319
She turned to survey the others as they

02:54:40.319 --> 02:54:42.360
edged through the curtain and stood back

02:54:42.360 --> 02:54:43.920
against the wall, out of the way.

02:54:44.040 --> 02:54:46.139
Your majesty?

02:54:46.200 --> 02:54:47.819
How did you find us?

02:54:47.940 --> 02:54:49.799
Moon asked hesitantly.

02:54:49.860 --> 02:54:53.639
Glory glanced at Kinkaju, her scales

02:54:53.639 --> 02:54:55.860
shifting to starbursts of royal purple

02:54:55.860 --> 02:54:57.059
against deep blue.

02:54:57.120 --> 02:54:59.819
I left her a trail to follow.

02:54:59.940 --> 02:55:02.520
Kingaju admitted, looking guilty.

02:55:02.579 --> 02:55:05.579
Sorry, Moon, but she's our queen.

02:55:05.639 --> 02:55:07.979
I wanted her there in case we really did

02:55:07.979 --> 02:55:08.819
find icicle.

02:55:08.879 --> 02:55:12.059
Moon nodded thoughtfully, looking back at

02:55:12.059 --> 02:55:13.020
the sleeping ice wing.

02:55:13.079 --> 02:55:16.379
I guess it's lucky you did, she said.

02:55:16.440 --> 02:55:19.500
Winter wanted to disagree, but he

02:55:19.500 --> 02:55:21.959
remembered the desperate rage on icicle's

02:55:21.959 --> 02:55:22.139
face.

02:55:22.200 --> 02:55:24.420
She had been seconds away from killing

02:55:24.420 --> 02:55:27.059
Kinkaju, and even though Kinkaju was just

02:55:27.059 --> 02:55:30.000
a rain wing, he had to admit, only to

02:55:30.000 --> 02:55:31.920
himself that he didn't want her dead.

02:55:31.979 --> 02:55:35.940
Besides, whatever she has planned for my

02:55:35.940 --> 02:55:36.479
sister now.

02:55:36.540 --> 02:55:38.760
Queen Glory would have been much less

02:55:38.760 --> 02:55:40.979
merciful if Icicle had killed her

02:55:40.979 --> 02:55:41.159
friend.

02:55:41.219 --> 02:55:45.299
So it was lucky for Icicle 2. that glory

02:55:45.299 --> 02:55:46.079
had found them right then.

02:55:46.200 --> 02:55:49.379
A pair of sky blue rain wings was moving

02:55:49.379 --> 02:55:51.659
quietly around icicle, cleaning her

02:55:51.659 --> 02:55:55.079
wounds, another one, pale pink, stood by

02:55:55.079 --> 02:55:57.000
her head with a blowgun and darts at the

02:55:57.000 --> 02:55:58.379
ready, in case she woke up.

02:55:58.500 --> 02:56:02.280
Icicle's chest rose and fell in long

02:56:02.280 --> 02:56:04.860
peaceful movements, and her face was as

02:56:04.860 --> 02:56:06.420
still as winter had ever seen it.

02:56:06.540 --> 02:56:09.719
The tortured expression was gone, for

02:56:09.719 --> 02:56:10.020
now.

02:56:10.079 --> 02:56:12.540
He hoped she would get a few hours of

02:56:12.540 --> 02:56:15.120
real rest before Scarlet came hunting

02:56:15.120 --> 02:56:15.719
through her dreams.

02:56:15.780 --> 02:56:18.059
It's odd.

02:56:18.120 --> 02:56:20.819
One of the rain wing healers murmured to

02:56:20.819 --> 02:56:23.940
the other, look how much this scratch has

02:56:23.940 --> 02:56:25.139
bled, Bullfrog.

02:56:25.260 --> 02:56:29.340
She wasn't letting herself sleep, Kinkachu

02:56:29.340 --> 02:56:29.700
told them.

02:56:29.760 --> 02:56:31.979
She hasn't slept in 4 or 5 days.

02:56:32.040 --> 02:56:35.399
The healers both made alarmed clicking

02:56:35.399 --> 02:56:37.379
noises with their tongues and bent over

02:56:37.379 --> 02:56:39.479
icicle again, inspecting her more

02:56:39.479 --> 02:56:39.840
closely.

02:56:39.899 --> 02:56:43.979
Why would any dragon do that to herself?

02:56:44.100 --> 02:56:46.319
said the one named Bullfrog.

02:56:46.379 --> 02:56:48.239
It's worse than refusing to eat.

02:56:48.299 --> 02:56:50.819
Another day of it, and she'd probably be

02:56:50.819 --> 02:56:51.059
dead.

02:56:51.120 --> 02:56:53.639
At least she'll be able to heal now that

02:56:53.639 --> 02:56:54.299
she has to sleep.

02:56:54.420 --> 02:56:58.620
Going even 12 hours without sleep is one

02:56:58.620 --> 02:57:00.719
of my nightmares, said the other.

02:57:00.780 --> 02:57:04.139
Remember that rain wing a few years ago

02:57:04.139 --> 02:57:04.920
who couldn't sleep?

02:57:04.979 --> 02:57:07.920
That was the saddest case I ever saw.

02:57:07.979 --> 02:57:11.280
Bullfrog shook his head, and his tail

02:57:11.280 --> 02:57:13.079
turned a glum shade of gray.

02:57:13.139 --> 02:57:15.600
A rain wing who can't sleep?

02:57:15.659 --> 02:57:17.100
Glory echoed.

02:57:17.159 --> 02:57:19.379
Isn't that kind of like a sea wing who

02:57:19.379 --> 02:57:19.920
can't swim?

02:57:20.040 --> 02:57:23.219
It was worse than that, said the pink

02:57:23.219 --> 02:57:23.760
dragon.

02:57:23.819 --> 02:57:25.620
He couldn't change his scales either.

02:57:25.680 --> 02:57:30.899
Because he couldn't sleep, said Bullfrog

02:57:30.899 --> 02:57:33.600
we figured out he had a snout deformity

02:57:33.600 --> 02:57:36.059
that kept him from sleeping for more than

02:57:36.059 --> 02:57:38.340
an hour at a time, but there was no way

02:57:38.340 --> 02:57:38.879
to fix it.

02:57:38.940 --> 02:57:40.440
It was awful.

02:57:40.500 --> 02:57:44.100
He was awful, said the pink dragon.

02:57:44.159 --> 02:57:46.920
Sometimes I would wake up for my suntime

02:57:46.920 --> 02:57:48.959
nap, and he'd just be standing there

02:57:48.959 --> 02:57:50.700
staring at me.

02:57:50.760 --> 02:57:53.579
And he couldn't camouflage himself, and

02:57:53.579 --> 02:57:54.780
you could never tell what he was feeling

02:57:54.780 --> 02:57:59.459
by looking at scales. said the other

02:57:59.459 --> 02:58:01.920
healer, shuddering from talons to tail.

02:58:01.979 --> 02:58:05.280
It's like he wasn't even a rain wing at

02:58:05.280 --> 02:58:06.899
all, said Bullfrog.

02:58:06.959 --> 02:58:09.360
He was a lot grumpier than a real rain

02:58:09.360 --> 02:58:10.079
wing too.

02:58:10.139 --> 02:58:13.739
So, what color was he?

02:58:13.860 --> 02:58:15.000
If he couldn't change?

02:58:15.120 --> 02:58:16.920
Kibley asked curiously.

02:58:16.979 --> 02:58:21.059
Kind of an ordinary lime green all over.

02:58:21.120 --> 02:58:22.860
Bullfrog answered.

02:58:22.979 --> 02:58:25.620
He held out one talon, and shifted the

02:58:25.620 --> 02:58:28.500
scales along his arm to demonstrate, very

02:58:28.500 --> 02:58:29.159
boring.

02:58:29.219 --> 02:58:34.079
And unattractive, agreed the 2nd healer.

02:58:34.139 --> 02:58:36.959
She gathered the damp leaves stained with

02:58:36.959 --> 02:58:38.520
icicle's blood and bustled off.

02:58:38.579 --> 02:58:42.299
That's our cautionary tale of what

02:58:42.299 --> 02:58:45.059
happens when you don't sleep, said the

02:58:45.059 --> 02:58:45.780
pink dragon.

02:58:45.840 --> 02:58:48.000
Ahem your majesty.

02:58:48.059 --> 02:58:51.479
I do sleep, Glory protested.

02:58:51.540 --> 02:58:54.719
Maybe not as much as other rain wings, but

02:58:54.719 --> 02:58:57.120
I've been doing suntime every day, no

02:58:57.120 --> 02:58:58.200
matter how busy I am.

02:58:58.260 --> 02:59:00.360
So quit your scolding jambu.

02:59:00.479 --> 02:59:02.340
I'm just saying.

02:59:02.399 --> 02:59:05.219
Jambu resettled his wings, looking

02:59:05.219 --> 02:59:06.120
pleased with himself.

02:59:06.180 --> 02:59:08.819
What are you planning to do with my

02:59:08.819 --> 02:59:09.120
sister?

02:59:09.180 --> 02:59:10.979
Winter asked glory.

02:59:11.100 --> 02:59:13.440
I can take her back to the Ice Kingdom.

02:59:13.559 --> 02:59:16.319
I promise, Queen Glacier will see that

02:59:16.319 --> 02:59:16.920
she's punished.

02:59:16.979 --> 02:59:20.700
Glory circled Isicle's bed, studying the

02:59:20.700 --> 02:59:21.360
sleeping dragon.

02:59:21.420 --> 02:59:25.079
She's too dangerous, said the queen with

02:59:25.079 --> 02:59:25.799
a flick of her tail.

02:59:25.860 --> 02:59:27.959
She killed one of my subjects.

02:59:28.020 --> 02:59:30.600
On the way to killing you.

02:59:30.659 --> 02:59:32.819
Kinkaju interrupted to point out.

02:59:32.879 --> 02:59:35.700
Glory waved this away with one talon.

02:59:35.819 --> 02:59:38.520
I can't let her just fly out of here.

02:59:38.579 --> 02:59:40.079
She said to Winter.

02:59:40.139 --> 02:59:42.780
I need to be a true queen to the night

02:59:42.780 --> 02:59:44.760
wings, and that means letting them see

02:59:44.760 --> 02:59:45.239
justice.

02:59:45.299 --> 02:59:47.940
But I also don't want to start a war with

02:59:47.940 --> 02:59:50.579
the ice wings, and I believe a queen

02:59:50.579 --> 02:59:52.200
should have a say in what happens to her

02:59:52.200 --> 02:59:52.739
subjects.

02:59:52.799 --> 02:59:56.040
So I'll send for Queen Glacier, and

02:59:56.040 --> 02:59:58.200
together, we can decide what happens to

02:59:58.200 --> 02:59:58.680
Icicle.

02:59:58.739 --> 03:00:01.799
That was more fair than winter could have

03:00:01.799 --> 03:00:02.280
hoped for.

03:00:02.340 --> 03:00:05.879
And yet, it made his stomach twist in a

03:00:05.879 --> 03:00:08.219
painful, anxious way to think of his

03:00:08.219 --> 03:00:10.260
queen coming here to judge him and his

03:00:10.260 --> 03:00:10.559
sister.

03:00:10.620 --> 03:00:12.659
The rankings.

03:00:12.719 --> 03:00:13.680
He thought.

03:00:13.739 --> 03:00:16.500
And what will mother and father think?

03:00:16.620 --> 03:00:19.379
I need to find Hillstorm before she

03:00:19.379 --> 03:00:22.200
arrives, he thought, if I can free him

03:00:22.200 --> 03:00:25.079
Queen Glacier will understand why Icicle

03:00:25.079 --> 03:00:25.620
did what she did.

03:00:25.680 --> 03:00:29.700
In the meanwhile, Glory sighed.

03:00:29.819 --> 03:00:32.280
We'll have to keep her tranquilized, so

03:00:32.280 --> 03:00:34.260
she doesn't try to escape or hurt someone

03:00:34.260 --> 03:00:34.559
else.

03:00:34.620 --> 03:00:36.780
Wait, what?

03:00:36.840 --> 03:00:39.540
Winter rose to his feet, and got his

03:00:39.540 --> 03:00:42.000
wings caught in a woven leaf hammock that

03:00:42.000 --> 03:00:42.959
was hanging from the ceiling.

03:00:43.020 --> 03:00:45.239
He wrestled it off with a growl of

03:00:45.239 --> 03:00:45.719
frustration.

03:00:45.780 --> 03:00:47.399
I need to talk to her.

03:00:47.459 --> 03:00:51.360
And I need a decent prison, Glory said

03:00:51.360 --> 03:00:53.100
snapping her tail back and forth.

03:00:53.159 --> 03:00:55.739
The rain wings don't have anything.

03:00:55.799 --> 03:00:58.020
Where am I supposed to put misbehaving

03:00:58.020 --> 03:00:58.500
dragons?

03:00:58.559 --> 03:01:01.440
She turned to an older rain wing who was

03:01:01.440 --> 03:01:03.120
sitting in the corner, watching with

03:01:03.120 --> 03:01:04.020
stately composure.

03:01:04.079 --> 03:01:06.840
Has no rain wing and history ever

03:01:06.840 --> 03:01:07.799
required punishing?

03:01:07.860 --> 03:01:11.100
We don't imprison.

03:01:11.159 --> 03:01:14.100
We banish, said the older dragon with an

03:01:14.100 --> 03:01:15.000
elegant shrug.

03:01:15.059 --> 03:01:18.360
What could be worse than being thrown out

03:01:18.360 --> 03:01:19.200
of the rainforest?

03:01:19.319 --> 03:01:22.020
You see what I'm dealing with?

03:01:22.079 --> 03:01:23.819
Glory said to Winter.

03:01:23.879 --> 03:01:26.879
I have one prisoner right now. a night

03:01:26.879 --> 03:01:29.040
wing, and we basically had to stick him

03:01:29.040 --> 03:01:30.299
in a quicksand pit.

03:01:30.360 --> 03:01:33.000
Every few hours, his guards haul him out

03:01:33.000 --> 03:01:35.280
just enough so he doesn't die, and then

03:01:35.280 --> 03:01:36.299
he starts sinking again.

03:01:36.360 --> 03:01:39.479
Yuck, said Kinkachu.

03:01:39.540 --> 03:01:41.700
But he deserves it, actually.

03:01:41.760 --> 03:01:44.159
And there are 2 others I should deal

03:01:44.159 --> 03:01:44.459
with.

03:01:44.520 --> 03:01:46.739
But Queen Thorn has agreed to keep them

03:01:46.739 --> 03:01:49.500
in her sand wing prison instead, until I

03:01:49.500 --> 03:01:50.459
decide what to do with them.

03:01:50.520 --> 03:01:53.459
Glory Sloth poked its head out from

03:01:53.459 --> 03:01:55.379
behind the queen's shoulder and started

03:01:55.379 --> 03:01:57.180
climbing slowly up her neck.

03:01:57.239 --> 03:01:58.979
I'll figure out something else

03:01:58.979 --> 03:01:59.520
eventually.

03:01:59.579 --> 03:02:01.139
Glory said.

03:02:01.200 --> 03:02:03.659
But I'm guessing Queen Glacier wouldn't

03:02:03.659 --> 03:02:04.200
appreciate it.

03:02:04.260 --> 03:02:06.059
If I stuck one of her dragons in

03:02:06.059 --> 03:02:08.879
quicksand, so I'm afraid Icicle has to

03:02:08.879 --> 03:02:10.200
stay asleep for now.

03:02:10.260 --> 03:02:12.059
Your Majesty?

03:02:12.180 --> 03:02:15.000
said a peach and plum colored dragon

03:02:15.000 --> 03:02:16.500
poking her head through the curtain.

03:02:16.620 --> 03:02:18.180
Deathbringer would like a word?

03:02:18.239 --> 03:02:22.260
Excuse me, Glory said to Winter, with a

03:02:22.260 --> 03:02:22.739
small bow.

03:02:22.799 --> 03:02:25.799
The older dragon followed her out, leaving

03:02:25.799 --> 03:02:28.559
Jambu on guard, and bullfrog still gently

03:02:28.559 --> 03:02:30.059
cleaning icicles scales.

03:02:30.120 --> 03:02:32.700
Winter inspected Icicles' face with

03:02:32.700 --> 03:02:33.059
concern.

03:02:33.120 --> 03:02:35.579
A small fro had appeared between her

03:02:35.579 --> 03:02:35.879
eyes.

03:02:35.940 --> 03:02:38.100
Was she speaking with Scarlet at that

03:02:38.100 --> 03:02:38.520
very moment?

03:02:38.579 --> 03:02:42.239
He watched her for a long minute, but she

03:02:42.239 --> 03:02:44.579
didn't move, or speak, or give any other

03:02:44.579 --> 03:02:46.079
sign of what her dreams were about.

03:02:46.139 --> 03:02:49.020
Finally, he turned and stalked to the

03:02:49.020 --> 03:02:50.940
wall where Moon and Kingaju were sitting

03:02:50.940 --> 03:02:52.799
together, their tails entwined.

03:02:52.920 --> 03:02:55.500
Kibli was pacing around the healer's

03:02:55.500 --> 03:02:57.719
pavilion, poking his nose around curtains

03:02:57.719 --> 03:03:00.120
to see the other patients, sniffing piles

03:03:00.120 --> 03:03:02.700
of medicinal leaves, and scaring clouds

03:03:02.700 --> 03:03:04.260
of small yellow butterflies out of the

03:03:04.260 --> 03:03:04.739
rafters.

03:03:04.799 --> 03:03:07.260
Now what am I supposed to do?

03:03:07.379 --> 03:03:09.120
Winter hissed at him.

03:03:09.180 --> 03:03:11.639
It was your bright idea to come here, but

03:03:11.639 --> 03:03:14.040
I'm no closer to finding Hillstorm, and

03:03:14.040 --> 03:03:16.379
it's my fault my sister's been caught by

03:03:16.379 --> 03:03:17.459
a bunch of rain wings.

03:03:17.520 --> 03:03:20.639
We are closer to finding hailstorm.

03:03:20.700 --> 03:03:22.020
Kinkaju objected.

03:03:22.079 --> 03:03:24.840
We've found the only dragon who's spoken

03:03:24.840 --> 03:03:26.399
to Scarlet and knows the whole story.

03:03:26.459 --> 03:03:31.079
And she's fast asleep, Winter said, which

03:03:31.079 --> 03:03:32.340
does me any good how?

03:03:32.459 --> 03:03:35.879
Kibbe stopped next to Moon, brushing her

03:03:35.879 --> 03:03:36.840
wings with his.

03:03:36.899 --> 03:03:39.659
Winter's claws twitched, and he clenched

03:03:39.659 --> 03:03:40.020
his jaw.

03:03:40.139 --> 03:03:42.959
The other rain wings weren't paying any

03:03:42.959 --> 03:03:45.180
attention to them, but Kibley lowered his

03:03:45.180 --> 03:03:45.600
voice anyway.

03:03:45.659 --> 03:03:49.559
Didn't you say, you overheard icicle and

03:03:49.559 --> 03:03:50.520
scarlet conspiring?

03:03:50.639 --> 03:03:52.079
He asked Moon.

03:03:52.079 --> 03:03:54.299
Does that mean you can get into dreams

03:03:54.299 --> 03:03:54.719
too?

03:03:54.840 --> 03:03:57.840
A shock like lightning ran through

03:03:57.840 --> 03:03:58.739
Winter's veins.

03:03:58.799 --> 03:04:00.239
Is that true?

03:04:00.299 --> 03:04:01.079
he demanded.

03:04:01.200 --> 03:04:03.479
Can you listen in when Scarlet finds

03:04:03.479 --> 03:04:03.719
her?

03:04:03.780 --> 03:04:08.040
I will try, Moon said, leaning a little

03:04:08.040 --> 03:04:09.059
closer to Kinkaju.

03:04:09.120 --> 03:04:10.559
I am trying.

03:04:10.620 --> 03:04:13.440
It's all darkness in Icicle's mind right

03:04:13.440 --> 03:04:13.680
now.

03:04:13.739 --> 03:04:16.260
She's too deep in sleep for dreams.

03:04:16.319 --> 03:04:18.600
Three moons.

03:04:18.659 --> 03:04:20.040
Winter realized.

03:04:20.100 --> 03:04:22.379
If Moon hears their conversation.

03:04:22.440 --> 03:04:24.540
She'll know what I told icicle.

03:04:24.600 --> 03:04:26.940
She'll probably have glory arrest me

03:04:26.940 --> 03:04:27.180
too.

03:04:27.239 --> 03:04:29.399
I'll have to be ready to fly the moment

03:04:29.399 --> 03:04:30.959
she tells me what I need to know about

03:04:30.959 --> 03:04:31.440
Scarlet.

03:04:31.500 --> 03:04:33.420
So we wait.

03:04:33.479 --> 03:04:34.799
Kinkachu said.

03:04:34.860 --> 03:04:36.540
For Scarlet to come.

03:04:36.600 --> 03:04:40.620
It seemed as if a long time passed.

03:04:40.680 --> 03:04:43.860
As the shadows slowly lengthened, and

03:04:43.860 --> 03:04:46.139
night came creeping into the pavilion

03:04:46.139 --> 03:04:49.079
Winter arranged himself in the ice wing

03:04:49.079 --> 03:04:51.600
guarding stance, but after a while, all

03:04:51.600 --> 03:04:53.819
his training failed, and he fell asleep.

03:04:53.879 --> 03:04:56.340
Moon jolted him awake by touching one of

03:04:56.340 --> 03:04:57.659
her talons to his.

03:04:57.719 --> 03:05:00.120
She's here, she whispered.

03:05:00.180 --> 03:05:02.340
She's in icicles mind.

03:05:02.399 --> 03:05:06.719
The pavilion was dimly lit by a few beams

03:05:06.719 --> 03:05:09.299
of moonlight, and several jars hanging

03:05:09.299 --> 03:05:11.100
from the ceiling that appeared to be full

03:05:11.100 --> 03:05:12.000
of fireflies.

03:05:12.000 --> 03:05:15.059
Kibli and Kinkachu slept peacefully

03:05:15.059 --> 03:05:17.040
curled next to each other on the floor.

03:05:17.100 --> 03:05:20.340
Winter blinked into the shadows, and saw

03:05:20.340 --> 03:05:22.319
the bullfrog was still in the pavilion

03:05:22.319 --> 03:05:24.780
asleep in a hammock next to a snoring

03:05:24.780 --> 03:05:25.620
rain wing patient.

03:05:25.680 --> 03:05:28.379
Jambu had been replaced by another rain

03:05:28.379 --> 03:05:31.020
wing, who was watching icicle, her blow

03:05:31.020 --> 03:05:31.920
gun at the ready.

03:05:31.920 --> 03:05:35.100
He stepped quietly over to icicle's bed

03:05:35.100 --> 03:05:36.959
and saw that his sister was sleeping very

03:05:36.959 --> 03:05:37.500
differently now.

03:05:37.559 --> 03:05:40.799
All her muscles were tensed, as if she

03:05:40.799 --> 03:05:42.840
wanted to run, but couldn't, and her

03:05:42.840 --> 03:05:44.159
claws were twitching violently.

03:05:44.219 --> 03:05:46.860
Do you think she's about to wake up?

03:05:46.920 --> 03:05:49.260
The rain wing guard asked Winter.

03:05:49.319 --> 03:05:51.780
She just had another dart an hour ago, so

03:05:51.780 --> 03:05:53.639
she shouldn't, but I've never seen anyone

03:05:53.639 --> 03:05:54.600
fight sleep like that.

03:05:54.659 --> 03:05:56.760
She looks like she's eaten some kind of

03:05:56.760 --> 03:05:57.540
toxic burn.

03:05:57.600 --> 03:06:00.840
I don't think she'll wake up, Winter

03:06:00.840 --> 03:06:01.200
answered.

03:06:01.260 --> 03:06:02.399
He meant it.

03:06:02.459 --> 03:06:04.379
But he was still surprised when the rain

03:06:04.379 --> 03:06:05.700
wing nodded and sat back.

03:06:05.760 --> 03:06:08.219
Why would she trust the prisoner's

03:06:08.219 --> 03:06:09.239
brother to tell her the truth?

03:06:09.299 --> 03:06:11.879
Rain wings really had no sense at all.

03:06:11.940 --> 03:06:13.680
Winter?

03:06:13.799 --> 03:06:14.940
Moon whispered.

03:06:15.000 --> 03:06:18.360
His name and her voice, like a spell that

03:06:18.360 --> 03:06:20.879
ran warmth through his bones, he hurried

03:06:20.879 --> 03:06:24.180
back over to her, I need paper, she said

03:06:24.180 --> 03:06:26.219
grabbing one of his talons without

03:06:26.219 --> 03:06:28.379
opening her eyes, and something to write

03:06:28.379 --> 03:06:29.819
with, quickly.

03:06:29.879 --> 03:06:32.639
Winter searched all the corners and boxes

03:06:32.639 --> 03:06:33.540
and niches.

03:06:33.600 --> 03:06:35.159
He even checked under all the beds.

03:06:35.219 --> 03:06:38.040
He ransacked the entire pavilion and

03:06:38.040 --> 03:06:39.420
didn't find a single scroll.

03:06:39.479 --> 03:06:43.260
I'll be right back, he whispered to Moon

03:06:43.260 --> 03:06:45.479
hurrying past her to the outer curtain.

03:06:45.540 --> 03:06:47.940
She just nodded, her brow wrinkled with

03:06:47.940 --> 03:06:48.239
pain.

03:06:48.299 --> 03:06:51.299
He paused for a 2nd, watching her where

03:06:51.299 --> 03:06:52.739
she crouched in the moonlight.

03:06:52.860 --> 03:06:53.940
Did it hurt?

03:06:54.000 --> 03:06:56.399
listening to other dragon's dreams?

03:06:56.459 --> 03:06:58.979
Or was it particularly bad listening to

03:06:58.979 --> 03:07:00.180
Scarlet and Icicle?

03:07:00.239 --> 03:07:03.299
He pushed through the vine curtain and

03:07:03.299 --> 03:07:05.399
stared out at a very dark rainforest.

03:07:05.459 --> 03:07:08.219
In the ice kingdom, it was rare to find

03:07:08.219 --> 03:07:09.059
this kind of darkness.

03:07:09.120 --> 03:07:11.700
The gift of light had been passed along

03:07:11.700 --> 03:07:13.799
to every inhabited part of the kingdom

03:07:13.799 --> 03:07:16.079
and there were moon globes everywhere.

03:07:16.139 --> 03:07:20.280
His home also had so much open space, and

03:07:20.280 --> 03:07:22.079
the 3 moons always glittered on

03:07:22.079 --> 03:07:22.440
everything.

03:07:22.500 --> 03:07:25.860
The snow, the ice palace, the frozen

03:07:25.860 --> 03:07:27.420
lakes, the glaciers.

03:07:27.479 --> 03:07:29.879
He wished he had a moon globe.

03:07:30.000 --> 03:07:32.399
He wasn't used to flying into pitch black

03:07:32.399 --> 03:07:34.500
like this, especially when he couldn't

03:07:34.500 --> 03:07:36.059
tell where any of their rain wings were.

03:07:36.180 --> 03:07:39.659
He could hear some of them snoring amid

03:07:39.659 --> 03:07:42.299
the nighttime rainforest cacophony, but

03:07:42.299 --> 03:07:43.559
he couldn't actually see any other

03:07:43.559 --> 03:07:45.719
dragons, even in the spots where

03:07:45.719 --> 03:07:46.680
moonlight could reach.

03:07:46.739 --> 03:07:50.280
He thought of hailstorm, trapped in some

03:07:50.280 --> 03:07:52.979
kind of secret sky wing prison, probably

03:07:52.979 --> 03:07:54.899
in complete darkness for the last 2

03:07:54.899 --> 03:07:55.139
years.

03:07:55.260 --> 03:07:59.459
Wait, a voice called softly behind him.

03:07:59.520 --> 03:08:01.979
Kinkachu pushed through the curtain and

03:08:01.979 --> 03:08:02.459
stood next to him.

03:08:02.520 --> 03:08:04.860
You stay here, she said.

03:08:04.920 --> 03:08:06.540
I'll get moons and paper.

03:08:06.600 --> 03:08:07.500
I know where to go.

03:08:07.559 --> 03:08:09.840
The new rain wing school is close by.

03:08:09.899 --> 03:08:12.600
I should come with you, he said.

03:08:12.659 --> 03:08:13.920
No thanks.

03:08:14.040 --> 03:08:16.139
Kinkuchu nudged him out of her way.

03:08:16.200 --> 03:08:18.659
You'd probably wake the whole village

03:08:18.659 --> 03:08:21.479
thrashing and flailing around, stay and

03:08:21.479 --> 03:08:22.500
make sure moon is all right.

03:08:22.559 --> 03:08:26.159
She flashed away, vanishing quickly into

03:08:26.159 --> 03:08:29.100
the dark, and he had to admit, more or

03:08:29.100 --> 03:08:29.819
less soundlessly.

03:08:29.879 --> 03:08:32.399
He wondered if rain wings had better

03:08:32.399 --> 03:08:33.780
night vision than other tribes.

03:08:33.840 --> 03:08:36.540
The tribes of fire would just use that

03:08:36.540 --> 03:08:38.040
when they needed to light up the dark, he

03:08:38.040 --> 03:08:38.399
guessed.

03:08:38.459 --> 03:08:39.959
What about sea wings?

03:08:40.020 --> 03:08:41.340
Could they see in the dark?

03:08:41.399 --> 03:08:44.100
If he were still at school, he could

03:08:44.100 --> 03:08:45.959
probably get someone to let him test that

03:08:45.959 --> 03:08:48.059
theory by studying his fellow students.

03:08:48.120 --> 03:08:50.579
But I'm not still at school.

03:08:50.639 --> 03:08:53.340
And I'm not going back, and I shouldn't.

03:08:53.459 --> 03:08:56.879
I mean, I don't care what other tribes

03:08:56.879 --> 03:08:57.540
can do anyway.

03:08:57.600 --> 03:09:00.719
He returned to Moon and found her in a

03:09:00.719 --> 03:09:03.000
curtained off corner of the pavilion, next

03:09:03.000 --> 03:09:04.860
to the only window with a view of the

03:09:04.860 --> 03:09:08.100
starry night sky, a small blue frog with

03:09:08.100 --> 03:09:10.379
darker blue speckles, was sitting on one

03:09:10.379 --> 03:09:12.959
of her front talons, and they both seemed

03:09:12.959 --> 03:09:15.239
to be listening to the chorus of frogs

03:09:15.239 --> 03:09:17.879
and birds and insects, and whatever other

03:09:17.879 --> 03:09:19.860
mysterious creatures were making all that

03:09:19.860 --> 03:09:20.520
noise outside.

03:09:20.639 --> 03:09:23.940
Winter paused beside his sister for a

03:09:23.940 --> 03:09:24.180
moment.

03:09:24.239 --> 03:09:27.000
Icicle looked as though she was slowly

03:09:27.000 --> 03:09:28.440
relaxing back into real sleep.

03:09:28.559 --> 03:09:32.700
Scarlet's gone, Moon said, as winter

03:09:32.700 --> 03:09:33.299
approached.

03:09:33.360 --> 03:09:35.100
Was it terrible?

03:09:35.219 --> 03:09:38.040
Winter asked, is icicle all right?

03:09:38.100 --> 03:09:40.860
What did Scarlet say about Hailstorm?

03:09:40.979 --> 03:09:44.100
Moon gave him an odd, searching look.

03:09:44.219 --> 03:09:46.739
Her teardrop scales caught the moonlight

03:09:46.739 --> 03:09:49.200
on one side, and the firefly lamp on the

03:09:49.200 --> 03:09:52.500
other, gleaming as though one was ice, and

03:09:52.500 --> 03:09:53.399
the other was gold.

03:09:53.459 --> 03:09:55.559
Winter realized.

03:09:55.620 --> 03:09:57.540
This was the 1st time they'd been alone

03:09:57.540 --> 03:09:57.840
together.

03:09:57.959 --> 03:10:00.479
Apart from the sleeping dragons around

03:10:00.479 --> 03:10:02.760
them, since he found out she could read

03:10:02.760 --> 03:10:03.180
minds.

03:10:03.239 --> 03:10:06.000
Or was it the 1st time they'd ever been

03:10:06.000 --> 03:10:06.540
alone together?

03:10:06.600 --> 03:10:09.719
He felt the weight of the skyfire rock

03:10:09.719 --> 03:10:10.799
pouch around his ankle.

03:10:10.860 --> 03:10:14.219
Scarlet says your brother is still

03:10:14.219 --> 03:10:14.579
alive.

03:10:14.639 --> 03:10:18.059
Moon turned her talon over, gently

03:10:18.059 --> 03:10:20.159
sliding the frog onto the windowsill.

03:10:20.219 --> 03:10:23.879
Icicle asked for proof, but Scarlet only

03:10:23.879 --> 03:10:24.479
laughed at her.

03:10:24.540 --> 03:10:27.659
I wish I could read Scarlet's mind, but

03:10:27.659 --> 03:10:29.819
she's too far away, and it's not really

03:10:29.819 --> 03:10:32.760
her in Icicle's dream, only a projection

03:10:32.760 --> 03:10:33.059
of her.

03:10:33.120 --> 03:10:36.059
So I can't tell what she's thinking, or

03:10:36.059 --> 03:10:37.979
whether it's true about Hailstorm.

03:10:38.040 --> 03:10:39.420
I'm sorry.

03:10:39.479 --> 03:10:42.479
She gave him that quick confused look

03:10:42.479 --> 03:10:42.780
again.

03:10:42.840 --> 03:10:45.479
Icicle offered her a deal.

03:10:45.540 --> 03:10:49.200
You don't have to, he started.

03:10:49.260 --> 03:10:53.940
I'm not, she said, worried, I mean, I

03:10:53.940 --> 03:10:55.500
know you won't kill Queen Glory.

03:10:55.559 --> 03:10:58.620
Do you know that?

03:10:58.620 --> 03:10:58.920
he asked.

03:10:58.979 --> 03:11:00.180
How?

03:11:00.239 --> 03:11:04.200
Because I think she's the kind of dragon

03:11:04.200 --> 03:11:06.659
you respect, she said slowly.

03:11:06.719 --> 03:11:09.299
And I think you wouldn't want to start a

03:11:09.299 --> 03:11:11.760
war between the ice wings and both of her

03:11:11.760 --> 03:11:12.180
tribes.

03:11:12.299 --> 03:11:15.059
I think you can imagine what killing her

03:11:15.059 --> 03:11:17.819
would do to Pyria, and you know it would

03:11:17.819 --> 03:11:18.120
be bad.

03:11:18.180 --> 03:11:21.360
Also, you're her guest.

03:11:21.360 --> 03:11:23.639
She's welcomed and trusted you.

03:11:23.760 --> 03:11:26.340
You aren't the kind of dragon who betrays

03:11:26.340 --> 03:11:27.180
someone's trust.

03:11:27.239 --> 03:11:31.319
Winter studied her profile as she wound a

03:11:31.319 --> 03:11:32.459
vine between her claws.

03:11:32.520 --> 03:11:35.819
That's a lot of thoughts, he said.

03:11:35.879 --> 03:11:38.940
Weren't you paralyzingly shy at one

03:11:38.940 --> 03:11:39.180
point?

03:11:39.239 --> 03:11:42.000
What happened to that unobtrusive, quiet

03:11:42.000 --> 03:11:42.600
dragon?

03:11:42.659 --> 03:11:46.260
It turns out it's actually much easier to

03:11:46.260 --> 03:11:48.120
talk to you when I can't hear what you're

03:11:48.120 --> 03:11:50.760
thinking, Moon admitted, smiling.

03:11:50.819 --> 03:11:53.520
He stared into her dark eyes for a long

03:11:53.520 --> 03:11:53.940
moment.

03:11:54.000 --> 03:11:57.239
But all of that about Queen Glory.

03:11:57.360 --> 03:12:00.239
Are you sure you're not still reading my

03:12:00.239 --> 03:12:00.479
mind?

03:12:00.540 --> 03:12:03.239
He finally asked, quietly.

03:12:03.299 --> 03:12:06.360
I don't have to, she said.

03:12:06.420 --> 03:12:08.700
I've already been in there for one

03:12:08.700 --> 03:12:08.940
thing.

03:12:09.000 --> 03:12:10.319
I know you.

03:12:10.440 --> 03:12:12.299
And I've watched you.

03:12:12.360 --> 03:12:15.000
I saw you put out the fire in the history

03:12:15.000 --> 03:12:15.600
cave.

03:12:15.659 --> 03:12:18.659
I saw you save me and Starflight from

03:12:18.659 --> 03:12:19.379
your own sister.

03:12:19.440 --> 03:12:22.739
I think you can think bigger than just

03:12:22.739 --> 03:12:24.180
one tribe against another.

03:12:24.239 --> 03:12:27.000
You can think about what's best for all

03:12:27.000 --> 03:12:27.600
the tribes.

03:12:27.659 --> 03:12:29.520
I guess I just.

03:12:30.360 --> 03:12:31.500
I trust you.

03:12:31.559 --> 03:12:34.620
You seem very sure of certain things

03:12:34.620 --> 03:12:36.420
about me, Winter said.

03:12:36.479 --> 03:12:39.899
That I would never hurt a dragonette, that

03:12:39.899 --> 03:12:41.399
I would never kill Queen Glory.

03:12:41.459 --> 03:12:45.000
That I am somehow honorable and brave.

03:12:45.120 --> 03:12:48.059
I am, said Moon.

03:12:48.120 --> 03:12:49.979
I am sure of those things.

03:12:50.040 --> 03:12:52.559
Even when everything else inside you is

03:12:52.559 --> 03:12:54.540
confusion and mirrors and pain.

03:12:54.600 --> 03:12:56.340
Those things are true.

03:12:56.399 --> 03:12:59.940
He lifted the vine from her claws, and

03:12:59.940 --> 03:13:02.340
wrapped it around his own talons, luring

03:13:02.340 --> 03:13:03.120
his voice even more.

03:13:03.180 --> 03:13:07.920
Sometimes, I'm only sure of one thing, he

03:13:07.920 --> 03:13:08.219
said.

03:13:08.280 --> 03:13:10.920
That I hope I never hurt you.

03:13:10.979 --> 03:13:13.979
She gazed up at him in surprise.

03:13:14.040 --> 03:13:15.479
Me?

03:13:15.540 --> 03:13:17.819
But I thought you hated me.

03:13:17.879 --> 03:13:21.299
Then you're not much of a mind reader, are

03:13:21.299 --> 03:13:21.479
you?

03:13:21.600 --> 03:13:23.639
He said with a half smile.

03:13:23.700 --> 03:13:28.379
I mean, I should, but for some reason, I

03:13:28.379 --> 03:13:28.680
can't.

03:13:28.799 --> 03:13:31.379
He took another step closer.

03:13:31.440 --> 03:13:33.899
Tilting his wings forward to brush hers.

03:13:33.959 --> 03:13:39.000
Well, good, Moon said, looking at their

03:13:39.000 --> 03:13:40.260
wings instead of his face.

03:13:40.319 --> 03:13:41.700
I'm.

03:13:42.780 --> 03:13:44.100
I'm glad you can't hate me.

03:13:44.159 --> 03:13:45.899
Got it.

03:13:45.959 --> 03:13:48.299
Kinkachu's voice said eagerly behind

03:13:48.299 --> 03:13:48.540
them.

03:13:48.600 --> 03:13:50.280
Moon, where are you?

03:13:50.340 --> 03:13:53.100
Winter let out a breath he hadn't known

03:13:53.100 --> 03:13:53.700
he was holding.

03:13:53.760 --> 03:13:56.520
Here, Moon said.

03:13:56.579 --> 03:13:59.520
She touched one talon lightly to Winter's

03:13:59.520 --> 03:14:01.739
chest, then went past him and threw the

03:14:01.739 --> 03:14:02.040
curtain.

03:14:02.159 --> 03:14:05.639
Winter pressed his talons together, trying

03:14:05.639 --> 03:14:07.500
to stop them from shaking, and then

03:14:07.500 --> 03:14:07.920
followed her.

03:14:07.979 --> 03:14:11.459
Kinkaju was in the center of the pavilion

03:14:11.459 --> 03:14:14.219
under one of the firefly jars, spreading

03:14:14.219 --> 03:14:15.299
a blank scroll on the floor.

03:14:15.420 --> 03:14:18.299
She nudged an ink pot toward moon with

03:14:18.299 --> 03:14:18.600
her tail.

03:14:18.659 --> 03:14:20.520
What is this for?

03:14:20.579 --> 03:14:22.020
Kinkachu asked.

03:14:22.079 --> 03:14:25.680
I saw something, Moon said, crouching

03:14:25.680 --> 03:14:26.159
beside her.

03:14:26.219 --> 03:14:28.920
She took the long, thin reed that Kingaju

03:14:28.920 --> 03:14:30.299
was holding and dipped it in the ink.

03:14:30.420 --> 03:14:31.920
Behind Scarlet.

03:14:31.979 --> 03:14:33.899
I got a glimpse of what was behind her

03:14:33.899 --> 03:14:35.579
and I think it was a mountain.

03:14:35.639 --> 03:14:37.979
It was kind of an unusual shape.

03:14:38.040 --> 03:14:39.719
She started drawing.

03:14:39.780 --> 03:14:41.459
Maybe we can find it.

03:14:41.520 --> 03:14:44.340
Winter watched the lines appear under

03:14:44.340 --> 03:14:47.040
Moon's claws, swooping and turning back

03:14:47.040 --> 03:14:49.500
crisscrossing and diving like flights of

03:14:49.500 --> 03:14:50.340
dragons in the sky.

03:14:50.399 --> 03:14:54.299
This was a real clue, a clue that might

03:14:54.299 --> 03:14:55.559
lead them to hailstorm.

03:14:55.620 --> 03:14:59.459
It looked like a wall at first, tall and

03:14:59.459 --> 03:15:01.979
sheer, with silvery waterfalls trailing

03:15:01.979 --> 03:15:04.559
down it like dragon tails, along the top

03:15:04.559 --> 03:15:06.479
of the wall was a ridge of sharp peaks

03:15:06.479 --> 03:15:08.639
that looked like an ice wing spine

03:15:08.639 --> 03:15:11.280
leading up to one peak that looped up and

03:15:11.280 --> 03:15:13.979
back on itself, almost in the shape of an

03:15:13.979 --> 03:15:14.219
eye.

03:15:14.280 --> 03:15:16.860
Moon lifted the reed and studied the

03:15:16.860 --> 03:15:17.100
picture.

03:15:17.159 --> 03:15:19.200
That's close anyway.

03:15:19.260 --> 03:15:20.340
She said.

03:15:20.399 --> 03:15:22.559
Does it look familiar to either of you?

03:15:22.620 --> 03:15:24.600
Winter shook his head.

03:15:24.659 --> 03:15:27.479
I haven't spent much time in the Sky

03:15:27.479 --> 03:15:30.059
Kingdom though, he said, assuming that is

03:15:30.059 --> 03:15:30.840
the Sky Kingdom.

03:15:30.899 --> 03:15:33.600
I've never been anywhere but the

03:15:33.600 --> 03:15:36.780
rainforest, and Jade Mountain, Kinkachu

03:15:36.780 --> 03:15:39.000
said with a helpless shrug, and the

03:15:39.000 --> 03:15:39.959
Nightwing Island, of course.

03:15:40.020 --> 03:15:42.899
Hey, Kibli, wake up and look at this.

03:15:42.959 --> 03:15:46.440
The sand wing came instantly awake as

03:15:46.440 --> 03:15:48.540
Kinkachu poked him, jumping to his feet

03:15:48.540 --> 03:15:50.459
as if he was ready for a battle.

03:15:50.520 --> 03:15:52.440
Moon held the sketch out to him and

03:15:52.440 --> 03:15:53.639
explained where she'd seen it.

03:15:53.700 --> 03:15:56.459
Kimble studied it for a while, then shook

03:15:56.459 --> 03:15:56.700
his head.

03:15:56.819 --> 03:16:00.479
Never seen it, he said, but someone must

03:16:00.479 --> 03:16:00.780
have.

03:16:00.840 --> 03:16:02.399
Great work, Moon.

03:16:02.520 --> 03:16:04.319
Yeah, thanks.

03:16:04.379 --> 03:16:06.059
Winter added hastily.

03:16:06.120 --> 03:16:09.360
I didn't really do anything, she said

03:16:09.420 --> 03:16:10.620
taking the drawing back.

03:16:10.680 --> 03:16:14.280
It's only, I mean, I'm just...

03:16:14.280 --> 03:16:14.940
Lucky.

03:16:15.000 --> 03:16:16.200
Kingachu finished.

03:16:16.260 --> 03:16:18.180
I wish I had a cool power like that.

03:16:18.239 --> 03:16:20.280
Lucky?

03:16:20.340 --> 03:16:22.020
Moon said wonderingly.

03:16:22.079 --> 03:16:25.200
Above her head, 3 fireflies escaped their

03:16:25.200 --> 03:16:27.360
jar and darted off in a flicker of

03:16:27.360 --> 03:16:28.559
surprised sparks.

03:16:28.860 --> 03:16:32.100
Well, it's no use asking any rain wings

03:16:32.100 --> 03:16:34.799
where this is, Kinkachu said, flicking

03:16:34.799 --> 03:16:35.639
her tail at the sketch.

03:16:35.700 --> 03:16:38.520
None of us leave the rainforest if we can

03:16:38.520 --> 03:16:41.280
help it, because it is awesome and

03:16:41.280 --> 03:16:44.700
perfect here, she added, with a stern

03:16:44.700 --> 03:16:45.420
look at winter.

03:16:45.479 --> 03:16:49.500
Let's try Death Bringer, Moon suggested.

03:16:49.559 --> 03:16:51.659
He's been all over the continent.

03:16:51.719 --> 03:16:54.360
Kibli shot a sideways look at winter.

03:16:54.420 --> 03:16:56.280
Is that all right?

03:16:56.340 --> 03:16:57.299
He asked.

03:16:57.360 --> 03:16:59.700
He's not exactly your favorite dragon.

03:16:59.760 --> 03:17:02.459
Oh, survive, Winter said.

03:17:02.520 --> 03:17:05.159
If you can help me find Hailstorm, that's

03:17:05.159 --> 03:17:05.579
what matters.

03:17:05.639 --> 03:17:08.819
It was hard to focus on hating the night

03:17:08.819 --> 03:17:10.559
wings now that there was real hope in

03:17:10.559 --> 03:17:12.659
front of him, a chance of finding

03:17:12.659 --> 03:17:15.600
hailstorm before Scarlett killed him, if

03:17:15.600 --> 03:17:17.100
he'd bought enough time with his lie

03:17:17.100 --> 03:17:19.620
about killing glory for her, if he moved

03:17:19.620 --> 03:17:19.979
fast.

03:17:20.040 --> 03:17:23.100
If Moon had truly seen where Scarlet was

03:17:23.100 --> 03:17:25.079
and if Hailstorm was there too.

03:17:25.139 --> 03:17:28.860
If, if, if.

03:17:29.040 --> 03:17:32.700
If I can make this happen, I might really

03:17:32.700 --> 03:17:34.319
see my brother again after all.

03:17:34.379 --> 03:17:38.700
Part two.

03:17:38.819 --> 03:17:41.340
In the claws of the clouds.

03:17:41.399 --> 03:17:44.940
Chapter 10.

03:17:45.239 --> 03:17:48.780
Deathbringer didn't recognize the

03:17:48.780 --> 03:17:50.819
mountains moon had drawn, but he knew who

03:17:50.819 --> 03:17:51.059
might.

03:17:51.120 --> 03:17:54.899
The talons of peace, he said.

03:17:54.959 --> 03:17:57.420
He breathed out another small flame to

03:17:57.420 --> 03:17:58.020
study the drawing.

03:17:58.139 --> 03:18:01.799
Find them, or what's left of them, and

03:18:01.799 --> 03:18:03.239
ask one of their sky wings to help you.

03:18:03.299 --> 03:18:06.420
They'd found him on guard outside the

03:18:06.420 --> 03:18:08.700
royal tree house where glory slept.

03:18:08.760 --> 03:18:10.559
The darkness was not as thick up here

03:18:10.559 --> 03:18:13.020
close to the treetops, where more

03:18:13.020 --> 03:18:14.159
moonlight could filter through the

03:18:14.159 --> 03:18:14.579
leaves.

03:18:14.639 --> 03:18:16.620
The small glowing lights of

03:18:16.620 --> 03:18:18.780
phosphorescent insects trailed up and

03:18:18.780 --> 03:18:21.180
down the branches, and winter spotted a

03:18:21.180 --> 03:18:24.239
few eerie glow in the dark moths, nestled

03:18:24.239 --> 03:18:25.500
in the pale night orchids.

03:18:25.559 --> 03:18:28.739
All right, then, said Kibley.

03:18:28.799 --> 03:18:31.440
We'll go ahead and track down a shadowy

03:18:31.440 --> 03:18:33.360
underground group who move every few

03:18:33.360 --> 03:18:35.280
weeks and weren't caught for the entire

03:18:35.280 --> 03:18:35.639
war.

03:18:35.700 --> 03:18:36.840
Easy.

03:18:36.899 --> 03:18:39.959
Deathbringer swatted at him. and Kibley

03:18:39.959 --> 03:18:41.159
jumped out of the way with a grin.

03:18:41.219 --> 03:18:44.459
They're not all that shadowy now

03:18:44.459 --> 03:18:45.840
Deathbringer said.

03:18:45.959 --> 03:18:49.319
And nobody said you were coming, Winter

03:18:49.319 --> 03:18:50.159
said to Kibley.

03:18:50.219 --> 03:18:52.559
I don't know what this we business is all

03:18:52.559 --> 03:18:52.739
about.

03:18:52.799 --> 03:18:56.940
Ignore him, Kibley said to Deathbringer.

03:18:57.000 --> 03:18:58.260
We're growing on him.

03:18:58.319 --> 03:18:59.040
I'm pretty sure.

03:18:59.100 --> 03:19:01.319
Why did the talons of peace even still

03:19:01.319 --> 03:19:01.680
exist?

03:19:01.739 --> 03:19:03.120
Now that the war is over.

03:19:03.180 --> 03:19:06.360
Many of them aren't welcome back in their

03:19:06.360 --> 03:19:08.100
tribes, so they have nowhere else to go.

03:19:08.219 --> 03:19:09.540
Deathbringer said.

03:19:09.659 --> 03:19:11.459
Their goals are shifting though.

03:19:11.520 --> 03:19:13.559
I know the dragon has taken over the

03:19:13.559 --> 03:19:13.739
group.

03:19:13.799 --> 03:19:15.239
I can help you find them.

03:19:15.299 --> 03:19:17.100
If glory doesn't mind you leaving.

03:19:17.159 --> 03:19:20.280
Oh, how nice of you to check.

03:19:20.340 --> 03:19:23.579
Glory said, materializing suddenly out of

03:19:23.579 --> 03:19:24.120
the darkness.

03:19:24.180 --> 03:19:26.819
Winter jumped, wondering how long the

03:19:26.819 --> 03:19:29.399
rain wing queen had been there, and why

03:19:29.399 --> 03:19:31.620
she was camouflaged, because she was

03:19:31.620 --> 03:19:33.899
following him, or because she was spying

03:19:33.899 --> 03:19:34.680
on Deathbringer.

03:19:34.739 --> 03:19:39.000
As it happens, Queen Glory went on, I

03:19:39.000 --> 03:19:40.860
don't mind what Kibli and Prince Winter

03:19:40.860 --> 03:19:41.340
choose to do.

03:19:41.399 --> 03:19:42.899
I'm not their queen.

03:19:42.959 --> 03:19:46.139
But I do have a few reservations about

03:19:46.139 --> 03:19:48.180
allowing 2 of my favorite subjects to

03:19:48.180 --> 03:19:50.399
gallivant around the continent, chasing

03:19:50.399 --> 03:19:52.440
Paria's most dangerous dragon.

03:19:52.559 --> 03:19:53.819
Did you hear that?

03:19:53.879 --> 03:19:57.299
Kinkachu said, nudging Moon so vigorously

03:19:57.299 --> 03:19:58.500
she nearly knocked her over.

03:19:58.559 --> 03:20:00.299
Favorite.

03:20:00.360 --> 03:20:03.239
The part you are supposed to hear is

03:20:03.239 --> 03:20:05.219
dangerous, Glory said.

03:20:05.280 --> 03:20:07.920
With blister and burn both dead.

03:20:07.979 --> 03:20:10.440
Scarlet is probably the scariest dragon

03:20:10.440 --> 03:20:11.159
left alive.

03:20:11.219 --> 03:20:13.379
And she certainly hates us the most.

03:20:13.500 --> 03:20:16.379
Explain to me how it is a good idea to

03:20:16.379 --> 03:20:18.659
send a quartet of young dragonettes after

03:20:18.659 --> 03:20:18.840
her.

03:20:18.899 --> 03:20:22.379
No quartet necessary, Winter said.

03:20:22.500 --> 03:20:24.239
Just the one, that's me.

03:20:24.299 --> 03:20:27.299
Ice wing prints over here. going to save

03:20:27.299 --> 03:20:29.579
my brother without the entourage.

03:20:29.639 --> 03:20:31.260
Please order them to stay here.

03:20:31.319 --> 03:20:33.299
It would make my life a lot simpler.

03:20:33.420 --> 03:20:37.260
We are not going after Scarlet, Moon said

03:20:37.260 --> 03:20:37.799
to Glory.

03:20:37.860 --> 03:20:39.899
We're going to find Winter's brother.

03:20:39.959 --> 03:20:43.979
We are doing no such thing, Winter said

03:20:43.979 --> 03:20:44.520
firmly.

03:20:44.579 --> 03:20:47.520
I am going to find him just me.

03:20:47.579 --> 03:20:52.200
That's right, Kibley said, just him and

03:20:52.200 --> 03:20:52.920
the 3 of us.

03:20:52.979 --> 03:20:54.719
His best friends in the world.

03:20:54.780 --> 03:20:58.200
I can't even dignify that with a snort

03:20:58.200 --> 03:21:00.899
Winter said, looking down his nose at the

03:21:00.899 --> 03:21:01.559
sand wing.

03:21:01.620 --> 03:21:04.500
If we can figure out where she's got him

03:21:04.500 --> 03:21:05.040
locked up.

03:21:05.100 --> 03:21:07.739
Maybe we can set hailstorm free without

03:21:07.739 --> 03:21:10.200
Scarlet even seeing us, Moon said.

03:21:10.260 --> 03:21:12.959
Besides, Kinkaju said.

03:21:13.020 --> 03:21:15.059
We're not that much younger than you and

03:21:15.059 --> 03:21:17.040
your friends were, when you set out to

03:21:17.040 --> 03:21:18.899
save Paria from all the bad dragons.

03:21:19.020 --> 03:21:21.899
We'll be careful, Moon said.

03:21:21.959 --> 03:21:22.920
We promise.

03:21:22.979 --> 03:21:26.340
Don't listen to them, Winter said.

03:21:26.459 --> 03:21:28.139
I don't want them to come with me.

03:21:28.200 --> 03:21:30.780
In fact, if you could stick this sandwing

03:21:30.780 --> 03:21:32.520
in some quicksand while I get away from

03:21:32.520 --> 03:21:35.340
him, I will personally bring you a walrus

03:21:35.340 --> 03:21:37.440
to express my gratitude.

03:21:37.500 --> 03:21:40.680
Ew, said Kinkaju.

03:21:40.739 --> 03:21:43.920
His very best friends.

03:21:44.040 --> 03:21:45.719
Kibley said sincerely.

03:21:45.780 --> 03:21:48.600
In the moonlight, it was hard to tell

03:21:48.600 --> 03:21:50.340
what the colors were that were shifting

03:21:50.340 --> 03:21:51.719
across glory's scales.

03:21:51.780 --> 03:21:54.180
She curled her tail around the branch

03:21:54.180 --> 03:21:55.860
underneath her and sighed deeply.

03:21:55.920 --> 03:21:58.200
Death bringer.

03:21:58.319 --> 03:22:00.540
I think you should let them go

03:22:00.540 --> 03:22:02.040
Deathbringer said.

03:22:02.159 --> 03:22:05.219
I went on my 1st mission when I was 4 and

03:22:05.219 --> 03:22:06.000
I turned out fine.

03:22:06.059 --> 03:22:10.799
Well, that's debatable, Glory said, and

03:22:10.799 --> 03:22:12.959
if I wanted to go, you'd have an absolute

03:22:12.959 --> 03:22:13.500
heart attack.

03:22:13.559 --> 03:22:16.799
Yes, because you're the most important

03:22:16.799 --> 03:22:19.799
queen Empira, said Deathbringer, and also

03:22:19.799 --> 03:22:20.879
because I couldn't live without you.

03:22:20.940 --> 03:22:23.520
Not that you care, torturing me with your

03:22:23.520 --> 03:22:24.479
recklessness all the time.

03:22:24.600 --> 03:22:27.780
That's true, Glory said.

03:22:27.840 --> 03:22:29.579
You'd be an absolute mess.

03:22:29.639 --> 03:22:31.020
The way you were before you met me.

03:22:31.079 --> 03:22:34.860
I was only half a dragon before I met you

03:22:34.860 --> 03:22:38.219
he declared, and I would be even less if

03:22:38.219 --> 03:22:38.879
I lost you now.

03:22:38.940 --> 03:22:40.739
All right.

03:22:40.799 --> 03:22:43.739
Settle down, she said affectionately.

03:22:43.799 --> 03:22:46.020
She turned to Kinkaju and Moon.

03:22:46.079 --> 03:22:48.840
You may go, but here are my orders.

03:22:48.899 --> 03:22:51.180
Do not interact with Scarlet.

03:22:51.239 --> 03:22:53.819
Stay as far out of her way as you can.

03:22:53.879 --> 03:22:55.559
Don't let her know you're there.

03:22:55.620 --> 03:22:57.239
Don't fight with anyone.

03:22:57.299 --> 03:23:00.719
Don't make any queens mad, and most

03:23:00.719 --> 03:23:02.639
importantly, don't you dare die.

03:23:02.760 --> 03:23:04.260
Understood?

03:23:04.319 --> 03:23:07.319
The 2 dragons nodded, and Kinkachu

03:23:07.319 --> 03:23:08.819
clapped her front talons together with

03:23:08.819 --> 03:23:09.239
excitement.

03:23:09.299 --> 03:23:12.840
Am I speaking a language only Ice Wings

03:23:12.840 --> 03:23:13.319
understand?

03:23:13.379 --> 03:23:14.819
Winter demanded?

03:23:14.879 --> 03:23:19.260
Listen, Glory said, fixing her green eyed

03:23:19.260 --> 03:23:19.979
gaze on winter.

03:23:20.040 --> 03:23:22.379
I used to think I could do everything by

03:23:22.379 --> 03:23:23.100
myself too.

03:23:23.159 --> 03:23:24.959
I didn't want help from anyone.

03:23:25.020 --> 03:23:27.959
But I wouldn't be here now if it weren't

03:23:27.959 --> 03:23:28.379
for my friends.

03:23:28.440 --> 03:23:30.840
And I have a feeling, you'll be saying

03:23:30.840 --> 03:23:32.100
the same thing a year from now.

03:23:32.159 --> 03:23:36.659
That might apply if these dragons were, my

03:23:36.659 --> 03:23:38.280
friends, Winter objected.

03:23:38.340 --> 03:23:40.440
But there are actually strangers who

03:23:40.440 --> 03:23:41.760
happen to get thrown into a group with

03:23:41.760 --> 03:23:41.940
me.

03:23:42.059 --> 03:23:43.680
They're not even ice wings.

03:23:43.799 --> 03:23:45.600
Why should they care what happens to

03:23:45.600 --> 03:23:46.260
Hailstorm?

03:23:46.319 --> 03:23:50.520
They care what happens to you, Glory

03:23:50.520 --> 03:23:50.700
said.

03:23:50.760 --> 03:23:54.299
For some reason, added Death Bringer.

03:23:54.360 --> 03:23:57.659
Entertainment value, offered Kibley.

03:23:57.719 --> 03:24:01.559
So, Glory said, shooting a quelling look

03:24:01.559 --> 03:24:02.340
at the sand wing.

03:24:02.399 --> 03:24:05.219
I strongly suggest you stop fighting and

03:24:05.219 --> 03:24:05.879
take them along.

03:24:05.940 --> 03:24:08.700
You might be surprised to find how useful

03:24:08.700 --> 03:24:10.319
dragons from other tribes can be.

03:24:10.379 --> 03:24:13.139
Winter growled softly.

03:24:13.200 --> 03:24:14.520
He didn't want to give in.

03:24:14.579 --> 03:24:17.040
He wanted to prove to his family that he

03:24:17.040 --> 03:24:18.479
could save Hailstorm alone.

03:24:18.540 --> 03:24:21.600
And he really didn't want to admit how

03:24:21.600 --> 03:24:23.459
much he would rather have these dragons

03:24:23.459 --> 03:24:25.500
with him when he faced Scarlet.

03:24:25.559 --> 03:24:27.479
Moon's mind reading.

03:24:27.540 --> 03:24:30.719
Kinkaju's camouflage, and Kibli's

03:24:30.719 --> 03:24:34.200
aggravating intelligence, Yes, he could

03:24:34.200 --> 03:24:35.760
imagine how they'd all be useful.

03:24:35.819 --> 03:24:37.680
What was wrong with him?

03:24:37.739 --> 03:24:40.379
Where was his ice wing pride?

03:24:40.440 --> 03:24:42.659
But it would waste time if he tried to

03:24:42.659 --> 03:24:43.200
keep arguing.

03:24:43.319 --> 03:24:46.079
And saying yes meant a few more days with

03:24:46.079 --> 03:24:46.559
Moon.

03:24:46.620 --> 03:24:49.200
Which should have been a reason to say

03:24:49.200 --> 03:24:49.559
no.

03:24:49.620 --> 03:24:53.159
Very well, he said finally.

03:24:53.219 --> 03:24:56.219
Tell me how to find the talons of peace.

03:24:56.280 --> 03:25:00.899
The Winding Tail River began high in the

03:25:00.899 --> 03:25:03.120
claws of the Clouds Mountains, and ran

03:25:03.120 --> 03:25:05.159
down past Jade Mountain to the sea.

03:25:05.219 --> 03:25:08.040
Near a bend in the river, north of the

03:25:08.040 --> 03:25:10.620
rainforest, and west of Queen Morin's

03:25:10.620 --> 03:25:13.260
Lake, there was a scavenger den that was

03:25:13.260 --> 03:25:15.180
believed to be the biggest empirea.

03:25:15.239 --> 03:25:18.299
Unlike most scavenger dens, this one was

03:25:18.299 --> 03:25:19.020
not hidden away.

03:25:19.079 --> 03:25:22.260
Instead, it was well fortified, with

03:25:22.260 --> 03:25:24.899
stone walls, and defended fiercely by the

03:25:24.899 --> 03:25:26.340
little creatures who lived in it.

03:25:26.459 --> 03:25:29.159
I know some dragons who hunted there.

03:25:29.219 --> 03:25:31.860
Deathbringer had said, but most of them

03:25:31.860 --> 03:25:32.700
say it's not worth it.

03:25:32.760 --> 03:25:35.219
You'll just end up getting jabbed with

03:25:35.219 --> 03:25:37.200
sharp things, and pelt it with heavy

03:25:37.200 --> 03:25:37.979
things.

03:25:38.040 --> 03:25:40.079
There's much easier prey in the river and

03:25:40.079 --> 03:25:40.500
mountains.

03:25:40.559 --> 03:25:43.920
This was the new spot the talons of peace

03:25:43.920 --> 03:25:45.540
had chosen for their signals.

03:25:45.600 --> 03:25:47.940
Apparently, now that Jade Mountain was

03:25:47.940 --> 03:25:49.920
being watched by too many dragon eyes.

03:25:49.979 --> 03:25:52.379
This scavenger den was fairly high up

03:25:52.379 --> 03:25:54.840
built on a cliff overlooking the forest

03:25:54.840 --> 03:25:57.659
and any dragon flying over it would be

03:25:57.659 --> 03:25:59.159
visible for miles in every direction.

03:25:59.219 --> 03:26:02.459
Which wasn't Winter's favorite feeling, to

03:26:02.459 --> 03:26:04.620
be honest, but that was how it worked.

03:26:04.680 --> 03:26:06.540
The talent of peace were out there

03:26:06.540 --> 03:26:08.700
somewhere, with someone watching the

03:26:08.700 --> 03:26:11.340
skies in case of a signal like this, and

03:26:11.340 --> 03:26:12.540
he needed to find them.

03:26:12.600 --> 03:26:15.180
The 4 dragonettes reached the area

03:26:15.180 --> 03:26:17.879
shortly after midday, landing on one of

03:26:17.879 --> 03:26:20.760
the cliff tops below the scavenger den, a

03:26:20.760 --> 03:26:23.040
brisk wind buffeted their wings, and

03:26:23.040 --> 03:26:25.200
tossed hawks around far overhead with

03:26:25.200 --> 03:26:26.639
piercing hunting cries.

03:26:26.700 --> 03:26:30.180
The sun was brilliant yellow, white, in a

03:26:30.180 --> 03:26:32.700
perfectly clear sky, much like the day

03:26:32.700 --> 03:26:34.020
Hillstorm had been captured.

03:26:34.139 --> 03:26:37.319
We could wait until night, Moon

03:26:37.319 --> 03:26:37.920
suggested.

03:26:38.040 --> 03:26:40.500
Then Kibley and I can fly up and signal

03:26:40.500 --> 03:26:42.840
with fire, trails of flames in the night

03:26:42.840 --> 03:26:43.379
sky.

03:26:43.440 --> 03:26:45.059
Death Bringer said that would work.

03:26:45.120 --> 03:26:47.700
They're not just watching for fire

03:26:47.700 --> 03:26:48.899
breathing dragons, though.

03:26:48.959 --> 03:26:49.920
Winter said.

03:26:50.040 --> 03:26:51.540
I can take care of this part.

03:26:51.600 --> 03:26:52.680
Don't worry.

03:26:52.739 --> 03:26:55.139
He flung himself into the air before

03:26:55.139 --> 03:26:56.280
anyone could argue with him.

03:26:56.340 --> 03:26:59.879
The wind caught his wings, and lifted him

03:26:59.879 --> 03:27:03.059
in a wheeling spiral, up and up and up

03:27:03.059 --> 03:27:04.739
toward the blue dome overhead.

03:27:04.860 --> 03:27:07.559
It was such a relief to be out of the

03:27:07.559 --> 03:27:09.600
rainforest, and away from all the

03:27:09.600 --> 03:27:12.540
clinging damp vines and weird, ripe fruit

03:27:12.540 --> 03:27:13.079
smells.

03:27:13.139 --> 03:27:15.959
Winter felt as though his wings were 6

03:27:15.959 --> 03:27:18.299
times larger out here, with room to

03:27:18.299 --> 03:27:19.319
stretch and soar.

03:27:19.379 --> 03:27:23.100
He flew as high as he could, circled over

03:27:23.100 --> 03:27:25.379
the other dragonettes, and then plummeted

03:27:25.379 --> 03:27:27.479
swiftly down like a meteor slicing

03:27:27.479 --> 03:27:27.840
through the sky.

03:27:27.899 --> 03:27:31.379
He zoomed over their heads, banked upward

03:27:31.379 --> 03:27:33.299
and caught a wind where he could float

03:27:33.299 --> 03:27:33.780
like a leaf.

03:27:33.840 --> 03:27:35.579
Now for the signal.

03:27:35.639 --> 03:27:38.340
Winter angled his wings to catch the

03:27:38.340 --> 03:27:38.760
sun.

03:27:38.819 --> 03:27:41.459
He'd swum in the river and polished his

03:27:41.459 --> 03:27:43.440
scales this morning, so they glittered

03:27:43.440 --> 03:27:45.780
even more than usual, wintry blue and

03:27:45.780 --> 03:27:46.020
white.

03:27:46.079 --> 03:27:48.659
The sunlight reflected off him as he

03:27:48.659 --> 03:27:51.000
tilted his wings, flashing like a mirror

03:27:51.000 --> 03:27:52.739
to any watching dragons below.

03:27:52.799 --> 03:27:56.219
He twisted slowly, making sure he could

03:27:56.219 --> 03:27:58.440
be seen from any direction, although he

03:27:58.440 --> 03:27:59.819
guessed the talent of peace were

03:27:59.819 --> 03:28:01.559
somewhere in the long range of mountains

03:28:01.559 --> 03:28:04.559
that split the land like jagged claws

03:28:04.559 --> 03:28:05.340
pushing out of the ground.

03:28:05.399 --> 03:28:07.979
He could see the twin peaks of Jade

03:28:07.979 --> 03:28:09.120
Mountain far away to the south.

03:28:09.180 --> 03:28:12.479
To the west, the pale rolling dunes of

03:28:12.479 --> 03:28:14.340
the desert filled the horizon beyond the

03:28:14.340 --> 03:28:16.860
mountain range, and below him, to the

03:28:16.860 --> 03:28:18.899
east and north, where the swamps of the

03:28:18.899 --> 03:28:19.559
mud kingdom.

03:28:19.620 --> 03:28:22.319
Was hailstorm out there somewhere?

03:28:22.440 --> 03:28:24.420
Did he know the war was over?

03:28:24.479 --> 03:28:26.940
Did he know how Scarlet was using him

03:28:26.940 --> 03:28:27.180
now?

03:28:27.239 --> 03:28:30.360
Was he crouched in darkness, wishing

03:28:30.360 --> 03:28:31.379
someone would come save him?

03:28:31.500 --> 03:28:34.440
Winter shook those thoughts away.

03:28:34.559 --> 03:28:36.360
Turning his attention to the scavenger

03:28:36.360 --> 03:28:36.780
den.

03:28:36.840 --> 03:28:38.579
It was cleverly chosen.

03:28:38.639 --> 03:28:41.520
The scavengers had found a spot where a

03:28:41.520 --> 03:28:43.860
huge overhanging ledge sheltered much of

03:28:43.860 --> 03:28:46.200
their home from the sky, shielding them

03:28:46.200 --> 03:28:48.000
in one direction from flying predators.

03:28:48.059 --> 03:28:51.719
Cave entrances dotted the cliffside, and

03:28:51.719 --> 03:28:53.940
odd little structures were carved out of

03:28:53.940 --> 03:28:56.399
the rock, each probably large enough for

03:28:56.399 --> 03:28:58.559
9 or 10 scavengers to curl up inside.

03:28:58.680 --> 03:29:01.979
A wall of thick stones ran around the den

03:29:01.979 --> 03:29:04.079
ending at the cliff on each side

03:29:04.079 --> 03:29:05.459
barricading them in.

03:29:05.520 --> 03:29:08.159
He could also see several patches of

03:29:08.159 --> 03:29:09.780
greenery that looked almost like

03:29:09.780 --> 03:29:10.319
gardens.

03:29:10.379 --> 03:29:13.020
Could scavengers think far enough ahead

03:29:13.020 --> 03:29:14.040
to plant gardens?

03:29:14.100 --> 03:29:17.760
Next to the ledge, a waterfall cascaded

03:29:17.760 --> 03:29:19.920
cheerfully down the cliff, right past the

03:29:19.920 --> 03:29:20.520
den.

03:29:20.760 --> 03:29:22.799
Some kind of wooden contraption was built

03:29:22.799 --> 03:29:25.379
out into the spray, catching buckets full

03:29:25.379 --> 03:29:27.360
of water, and spinning them back toward

03:29:27.360 --> 03:29:28.440
the safety of the walls.

03:29:28.500 --> 03:29:31.739
Winter hovered watching the scavengers.

03:29:31.799 --> 03:29:33.899
Several of them were darting about

03:29:33.899 --> 03:29:36.059
calling to each other in their squeaky

03:29:36.059 --> 03:29:36.420
chirps.

03:29:36.479 --> 03:29:39.540
They seemed very active, much more so

03:29:39.540 --> 03:29:41.760
than bandit, almost like a pot of

03:29:41.760 --> 03:29:43.979
dolphins, flurrying about after you

03:29:43.979 --> 03:29:45.600
accidentally drop the remains of your

03:29:45.600 --> 03:29:46.620
well carcass on them.

03:29:46.680 --> 03:29:49.860
A few were peering over the wall at the

03:29:49.860 --> 03:29:50.760
nearby cliffs.

03:29:50.819 --> 03:29:53.879
He saw one point to the ledge where Moon

03:29:53.879 --> 03:29:56.040
Kibley, and Kinkaju were sitting in the

03:29:56.040 --> 03:29:58.680
sun together, resting their wings, black

03:29:58.680 --> 03:30:01.079
and pale yellow, and iridescent blue

03:30:01.079 --> 03:30:02.940
purple, green, side by side.

03:30:03.000 --> 03:30:05.579
Are they worried about dragons so close

03:30:05.579 --> 03:30:06.120
to their home?

03:30:06.180 --> 03:30:07.559
Winter wondered.

03:30:07.680 --> 03:30:08.879
That was cute.

03:30:08.940 --> 03:30:11.639
Of course, this particular group of

03:30:11.639 --> 03:30:13.979
dragons was possibly the least likely to

03:30:13.979 --> 03:30:16.739
eat a scavenger of any dragons in Pyria.

03:30:16.799 --> 03:30:19.440
But if they had wanted to, what would the

03:30:19.440 --> 03:30:20.340
scavengers do about it?

03:30:20.399 --> 03:30:23.100
The scavengers were rolling something up

03:30:23.100 --> 03:30:23.819
to the wall now.

03:30:23.879 --> 03:30:26.459
Something made of pieces of wood fitted

03:30:26.459 --> 03:30:28.739
together, with ropes and metal bits as

03:30:28.739 --> 03:30:28.920
well.

03:30:28.979 --> 03:30:32.459
The sharp pointed end of it slid into a

03:30:32.459 --> 03:30:34.379
slot in the wall and poked out the other

03:30:34.379 --> 03:30:34.559
side.

03:30:34.680 --> 03:30:38.159
Winters swooped lower, trying to figure

03:30:38.159 --> 03:30:38.879
out what they were doing.

03:30:38.940 --> 03:30:41.639
It didn't seem as if they'd noticed him

03:30:41.639 --> 03:30:42.959
yet, in the sky above them.

03:30:43.079 --> 03:30:46.379
A scavenger with long fur swooping off

03:30:46.379 --> 03:30:49.200
its head like a tail climbed nimbly onto

03:30:49.200 --> 03:30:51.479
the wall and leaned over, holding a torch

03:30:51.479 --> 03:30:53.159
that flickered with fire at the end.

03:30:53.280 --> 03:30:56.399
It lowered the torch to touch the end of

03:30:56.399 --> 03:30:57.899
the contraption that was sticking through

03:30:57.899 --> 03:30:58.200
the wall.

03:30:58.260 --> 03:31:01.260
The flames caught and licked around the

03:31:01.260 --> 03:31:03.780
point, and immediately the scavengers on

03:31:03.780 --> 03:31:05.100
the other side of the wall started

03:31:05.100 --> 03:31:07.500
bustling around, twisting the ropes and

03:31:07.500 --> 03:31:09.540
pulling things and pointing the device.

03:31:09.600 --> 03:31:12.059
At the dragons below.

03:31:12.120 --> 03:31:13.799
It was a weapon.

03:31:13.860 --> 03:31:17.219
These scavengers had some kind of fiery

03:31:17.219 --> 03:31:19.739
projectile weapon, and they were about to

03:31:19.739 --> 03:31:21.180
shoot it at Moon and the others.

03:31:21.239 --> 03:31:24.840
Winter folded his wings and plummeted

03:31:24.840 --> 03:31:26.639
toward the den as fast as gravity could

03:31:26.639 --> 03:31:28.860
take him, there was a shout from one of

03:31:28.860 --> 03:31:29.639
the scavengers.

03:31:29.700 --> 03:31:32.879
Suddenly the weapon fired, and a spear as

03:31:32.879 --> 03:31:35.520
long as a dragon came hurtling out of the

03:31:35.520 --> 03:31:38.040
wall, dancing with flames and wickedly

03:31:38.040 --> 03:31:38.579
sharp.

03:31:38.579 --> 03:31:42.239
It plunged down, straight toward Kibley's

03:31:42.239 --> 03:31:42.600
heart.

03:31:42.659 --> 03:31:44.040
Look out!

03:31:44.159 --> 03:31:45.299
Winter warred.

03:31:45.360 --> 03:31:47.459
He wasn't close enough to reach it, but

03:31:47.459 --> 03:31:50.760
he called up the cold from inside him, and

03:31:50.760 --> 03:31:52.620
blasted a spray of frost breath at the

03:31:52.620 --> 03:31:52.860
spear.

03:31:52.920 --> 03:31:56.100
The fire went out instantly, as ice

03:31:56.100 --> 03:31:58.139
crystals appeared all along the weapon.

03:31:58.200 --> 03:32:00.540
The extra weight, and the force of his

03:32:00.540 --> 03:32:02.459
breath, knocked the spear off course.

03:32:02.520 --> 03:32:05.219
It crashed into the cliff underneath

03:32:05.219 --> 03:32:07.680
Kibley's talons, and then dropped to the

03:32:07.680 --> 03:32:09.120
earth far below instead.

03:32:09.120 --> 03:32:13.500
Kinkaju shrieked, and Kibley leaped aside

03:32:13.500 --> 03:32:15.000
spreading his wings to Shield Moon.

03:32:15.120 --> 03:32:17.579
Winter wheeled over their heads and

03:32:17.579 --> 03:32:18.299
landed beside them.

03:32:18.360 --> 03:32:19.920
Time to move.

03:32:19.979 --> 03:32:21.000
He barked.

03:32:21.059 --> 03:32:23.399
The scavengers are shooting at us.

03:32:23.459 --> 03:32:25.020
Kinkachu cried.

03:32:25.079 --> 03:32:25.979
That's so mean.

03:32:26.100 --> 03:32:28.079
We didn't even try to eat them or

03:32:28.079 --> 03:32:28.379
anything.

03:32:28.440 --> 03:32:31.260
But other dragons have.

03:32:31.379 --> 03:32:32.879
Kibli pointed out.

03:32:32.940 --> 03:32:35.340
The 4 of them swiftly arrowed into the

03:32:35.340 --> 03:32:35.819
sky.

03:32:35.879 --> 03:32:38.100
Far out of range of the scavengers

03:32:38.100 --> 03:32:38.520
weapons.

03:32:38.579 --> 03:32:41.340
Winter glanced back and saw the small

03:32:41.340 --> 03:32:43.440
furry faces peering out to watch them fly

03:32:43.440 --> 03:32:44.040
away.

03:32:44.219 --> 03:32:48.000
Is it weird that I'm kind of impressed?

03:32:48.120 --> 03:32:48.540
Moon asked.

03:32:48.600 --> 03:32:50.579
I had no idea they could come up with

03:32:50.579 --> 03:32:51.120
something like that.

03:32:51.180 --> 03:32:55.319
I'm sticking with outraged, Kinkaju

03:32:55.319 --> 03:32:55.620
said.

03:32:55.680 --> 03:32:57.659
Hello, I'm a vegetarian.

03:32:57.719 --> 03:33:00.659
There is so no need to shoot me of all

03:33:00.659 --> 03:33:01.260
dragons.

03:33:01.319 --> 03:33:03.840
I should go down there and roar at them.

03:33:03.899 --> 03:33:07.379
Her scales were vibrantly alarmingly

03:33:07.379 --> 03:33:07.739
orange.

03:33:07.799 --> 03:33:10.620
Much brighter than any Sky Wings scales

03:33:10.620 --> 03:33:11.159
could be.

03:33:11.219 --> 03:33:14.280
Winter guessed that if the talons had

03:33:14.280 --> 03:33:16.620
somehow missed his mirror signal, a

03:33:16.620 --> 03:33:18.780
dragon this weirdly colored might still

03:33:18.780 --> 03:33:19.260
catch their eye.

03:33:19.319 --> 03:33:21.840
What in the world was it?

03:33:21.899 --> 03:33:23.280
Kibley asked.

03:33:23.340 --> 03:33:26.159
He soared in a tight circle, trying to

03:33:26.159 --> 03:33:27.120
see down into the den.

03:33:27.180 --> 03:33:28.799
How did it work?

03:33:28.860 --> 03:33:30.420
How do they make it?

03:33:30.479 --> 03:33:31.500
Could we make one?

03:33:31.559 --> 03:33:34.440
I mean, not us, not right now, but maybe

03:33:34.440 --> 03:33:36.000
one day for Thorn's palace.

03:33:36.120 --> 03:33:39.120
I've never seen anything quite like it

03:33:39.120 --> 03:33:40.319
Winter admitted.

03:33:40.379 --> 03:33:42.239
Can you draw it for me?

03:33:42.360 --> 03:33:43.260
Kibley asked.

03:33:43.319 --> 03:33:45.780
Um, sure.

03:33:45.899 --> 03:33:49.500
They found a place to wait for the talons

03:33:49.500 --> 03:33:51.479
above the scavengers, out of their sight

03:33:51.479 --> 03:33:53.879
this time, near the river that led to the

03:33:53.879 --> 03:33:56.639
waterfall, Kingachoo and Moon went off to

03:33:56.639 --> 03:33:58.860
find food, while Winter tried to sketch

03:33:58.860 --> 03:34:00.600
the weapon in the sandy banks beside the

03:34:00.600 --> 03:34:01.020
river.

03:34:01.079 --> 03:34:03.959
But did this pull it back?

03:34:04.020 --> 03:34:05.700
Kibli kept asking.

03:34:05.760 --> 03:34:08.340
He poked the drawing, scattering sand

03:34:08.340 --> 03:34:09.600
over winter's claws.

03:34:09.659 --> 03:34:11.879
Did this part fit into here?

03:34:11.940 --> 03:34:13.860
Wouldn't they need a piece like this?

03:34:13.920 --> 03:34:16.500
I have no idea.

03:34:16.559 --> 03:34:18.239
Winter finally erupted.

03:34:18.299 --> 03:34:20.819
I was a little busy saving your scales.

03:34:20.879 --> 03:34:22.860
That's true.

03:34:22.920 --> 03:34:25.799
Kibley said, sitting back and giving him

03:34:25.799 --> 03:34:26.700
a delighted smile.

03:34:26.760 --> 03:34:29.280
You totally saved my scales.

03:34:29.399 --> 03:34:31.559
I knew we were best friends.

03:34:31.620 --> 03:34:32.760
Did I say thank you yet?

03:34:32.819 --> 03:34:35.520
No, Winter grumbled.

03:34:35.579 --> 03:34:36.780
Thank you.

03:34:36.899 --> 03:34:40.079
Kibley said, entirely too sincerely for

03:34:40.079 --> 03:34:40.379
winter.

03:34:40.440 --> 03:34:44.459
Well, Winter said, I would have done the

03:34:44.459 --> 03:34:45.600
same thing for anyone, you know.

03:34:45.659 --> 03:34:48.420
I know, Kibley said.

03:34:48.479 --> 03:34:49.620
I like that about you.

03:34:49.680 --> 03:34:53.340
Winter saw, with surprise, that he meant

03:34:53.340 --> 03:34:53.579
it.

03:34:53.639 --> 03:34:57.059
Ghibli was as bad as a rain wing, flapping

03:34:57.059 --> 03:34:58.860
his feelings all over the place all the

03:34:58.860 --> 03:34:59.040
time.

03:34:59.100 --> 03:35:02.219
You would get eaten alive in the Ice

03:35:02.219 --> 03:35:03.840
Kingdom, Winter pointed out.

03:35:03.899 --> 03:35:05.340
Kibli shrugged.

03:35:05.399 --> 03:35:06.780
Maybe not.

03:35:06.840 --> 03:35:09.899
I survived the Scorpion den, he said.

03:35:09.959 --> 03:35:11.159
And my family.

03:35:11.219 --> 03:35:13.500
They would not have saved me in this

03:35:13.500 --> 03:35:14.879
situation, if you're curious.

03:35:14.940 --> 03:35:17.639
More likely they'd have grabbed the spear

03:35:17.639 --> 03:35:18.719
and stabbed me themselves.

03:35:18.780 --> 03:35:21.719
Mine would have waited to see if I could

03:35:21.719 --> 03:35:24.239
save myself, and then stood there shaking

03:35:24.239 --> 03:35:26.100
their heads in grave disappointment when

03:35:26.100 --> 03:35:26.579
I didn't.

03:35:26.700 --> 03:35:27.840
Winter said.

03:35:27.959 --> 03:35:30.299
Taking notes on all the things I did

03:35:30.299 --> 03:35:33.360
wrong stood in the wrong place, allowed

03:35:33.360 --> 03:35:35.819
Spear to penetrate scales, bleeding too

03:35:35.819 --> 03:35:37.200
much, and so forth.

03:35:37.260 --> 03:35:38.879
Kibling laughed.

03:35:39.000 --> 03:35:39.959
They sound great.

03:35:40.020 --> 03:35:42.840
They are, Winter said quickly.

03:35:42.899 --> 03:35:44.940
That's how I swing parents are supposed

03:35:44.940 --> 03:35:45.239
to be.

03:35:45.299 --> 03:35:46.440
I'm very lucky.

03:35:46.500 --> 03:35:49.079
Kibli gave him a strange look.

03:35:49.139 --> 03:35:51.360
I guess they did something right.

03:35:51.420 --> 03:35:53.040
He said after a moment.

03:35:53.100 --> 03:35:56.219
I mean, for you to be so determined to

03:35:56.219 --> 03:35:56.819
rescue your brother.

03:35:56.879 --> 03:36:00.180
If I were in a sky wing prison, my

03:36:00.180 --> 03:36:01.979
brother would definitely not come to

03:36:01.979 --> 03:36:02.520
rescue me.

03:36:02.579 --> 03:36:05.760
To be fair, I wouldn't go rescue him

03:36:05.760 --> 03:36:06.000
either.

03:36:06.120 --> 03:36:09.180
Pyrea would be much better off with him

03:36:09.180 --> 03:36:11.579
locked up, where he can't hurt anyone.

03:36:11.639 --> 03:36:14.760
A breeze sent ripples across the surface

03:36:14.760 --> 03:36:15.420
of the river.

03:36:15.479 --> 03:36:18.479
Winter stepped over his sketch and waded

03:36:18.479 --> 03:36:20.760
into the water, rinsing the sand off his

03:36:20.760 --> 03:36:21.239
claws.

03:36:21.299 --> 03:36:24.360
Tiny golden and silver fish darted around

03:36:24.360 --> 03:36:25.079
his talons.

03:36:25.139 --> 03:36:28.200
The water was bracingly cold, like a

03:36:28.200 --> 03:36:29.280
fleeting reminder of home.

03:36:29.340 --> 03:36:33.899
I have a sinister older sister too, Kibli

03:36:33.899 --> 03:36:34.260
offered.

03:36:34.319 --> 03:36:37.739
Icicle's not older than me, Winter said.

03:36:37.799 --> 03:36:39.239
We were in the same hatching.

03:36:39.360 --> 03:36:41.520
And sinister is a bit of an

03:36:41.520 --> 03:36:42.299
exaggeration.

03:36:42.360 --> 03:36:45.719
Mm-hmm, Kibley said skeptically.

03:36:45.780 --> 03:36:47.100
Winter sighed.

03:36:47.159 --> 03:36:50.280
My parents will probably be so proud of

03:36:50.280 --> 03:36:50.459
her.

03:36:50.579 --> 03:36:53.520
Up until the part where she failed, which

03:36:53.520 --> 03:36:55.920
they'll see is my fault, and then got

03:36:55.920 --> 03:36:58.319
caught by rain wings, also my fault.

03:36:58.440 --> 03:37:01.559
Going home is going to be excellent in

03:37:01.559 --> 03:37:02.219
all the ways.

03:37:02.280 --> 03:37:03.719
I can't wait.

03:37:03.780 --> 03:37:07.559
It'll be all right, because you'll be

03:37:07.559 --> 03:37:09.959
bringing hailstorm with you, Kibley said

03:37:09.959 --> 03:37:12.000
confidently, so they'll have to forgive

03:37:12.000 --> 03:37:12.180
you.

03:37:12.239 --> 03:37:14.100
Will they?

03:37:14.219 --> 03:37:15.600
Winter wondered.

03:37:15.659 --> 03:37:17.639
Would they be proud of him if he

03:37:17.639 --> 03:37:18.180
succeeded?

03:37:18.239 --> 03:37:20.399
Or would they be too horrified by his

03:37:20.399 --> 03:37:21.540
methods and his company?

03:37:21.600 --> 03:37:24.719
His sharp ears caught a quiet splash

03:37:24.719 --> 03:37:25.200
nearby.

03:37:25.260 --> 03:37:28.559
Alertly, he spun in a circle and scanned

03:37:28.559 --> 03:37:28.799
the river.

03:37:28.860 --> 03:37:31.860
Suddenly, he spotted a dark shape

03:37:31.860 --> 03:37:33.420
swarming through the water toward him

03:37:33.420 --> 03:37:34.920
moving faster than a shark.

03:37:34.979 --> 03:37:38.520
Before he could cry out, a dragon lunged

03:37:38.520 --> 03:37:40.079
out of the water and straight for his

03:37:40.079 --> 03:37:40.260
throat.

03:37:40.319 --> 03:37:44.639
Chapter 11.

03:37:45.000 --> 03:37:49.559
Winter let out a roar and swung his claws

03:37:49.559 --> 03:37:51.420
in a ferocious arc.

03:37:51.479 --> 03:37:53.399
The attacking dragon stopped himself at

03:37:53.399 --> 03:37:55.559
the last moment, just out of range of

03:37:55.559 --> 03:37:58.020
winter's talons, he yelped in surprise

03:37:58.020 --> 03:37:59.340
and fell back with a splash.

03:37:59.459 --> 03:38:03.360
Hey, the new dragon said indignantly

03:38:03.360 --> 03:38:04.200
rude?

03:38:04.260 --> 03:38:05.819
You could have taken my nose off.

03:38:05.879 --> 03:38:08.940
And you'd deserve it for jumping at me

03:38:08.940 --> 03:38:09.299
like that.

03:38:09.360 --> 03:38:10.920
Winter snarled.

03:38:11.040 --> 03:38:16.319
I was practicing my stealth approach, the

03:38:16.319 --> 03:38:18.719
dragon grumbled, standing up and shaking

03:38:18.719 --> 03:38:20.100
off his wet green wings.

03:38:20.159 --> 03:38:22.620
He was a sea wing, a bit older than

03:38:22.620 --> 03:38:24.479
winter, but much scrawnier.

03:38:24.540 --> 03:38:26.579
I wouldn't have actually hurt you.

03:38:26.639 --> 03:38:29.879
That's true, because I would have ripped

03:38:29.879 --> 03:38:31.260
off your tail and beaten you with it

03:38:31.260 --> 03:38:32.700
first, Winter said.

03:38:32.760 --> 03:38:36.239
Nice, Kibley said from the shore.

03:38:36.299 --> 03:38:38.040
Not the face this time.

03:38:38.100 --> 03:38:39.180
Very creative.

03:38:39.239 --> 03:38:41.760
Squid!

03:38:41.819 --> 03:38:43.319
someone shouted above them.

03:38:43.379 --> 03:38:45.059
Didn't you hear my orders?

03:38:45.120 --> 03:38:48.120
A sky blue sea wing with dark blue horns

03:38:48.120 --> 03:38:50.399
came soaring down from the clouds and

03:38:50.399 --> 03:38:52.860
landed next to the 1st with a splash.

03:38:52.920 --> 03:38:55.020
This dragon was bigger and frowning.

03:38:55.079 --> 03:38:57.059
What?

03:38:57.059 --> 03:38:58.559
Squid whined.

03:38:58.680 --> 03:39:02.040
I very clearly said, nobody approached

03:39:02.040 --> 03:39:04.379
the strangers, until I've had a chance to

03:39:04.379 --> 03:39:06.719
speak to them, said the new Sea Wing.

03:39:06.780 --> 03:39:08.879
What you're doing, the opposite of that.

03:39:09.000 --> 03:39:14.760
I was being stealthy, Squid said, smacking

03:39:14.760 --> 03:39:15.840
the water with his wings.

03:39:15.899 --> 03:39:18.719
Dad said I should practice.

03:39:18.780 --> 03:39:21.600
He thinks I'm really good at it.

03:39:21.659 --> 03:39:25.020
He said maybe I'll be an amazing spy one

03:39:25.020 --> 03:39:25.260
day.

03:39:25.379 --> 03:39:28.379
The other sea wing looked as though he

03:39:28.379 --> 03:39:30.420
had reached the farthest horizon of his

03:39:30.420 --> 03:39:31.139
patience.

03:39:31.319 --> 03:39:32.459
Squid.

03:39:32.520 --> 03:39:34.979
Take your lurking and snooping and her

03:39:34.979 --> 03:39:38.040
harassment somewhere else, right now.

03:39:38.100 --> 03:39:41.100
Fine, fine, fine.

03:39:41.159 --> 03:39:43.680
Squid floundered out of the water

03:39:43.680 --> 03:39:45.420
flapping his wings and grumbling.

03:39:45.479 --> 03:39:48.600
You know, my dad used to be the leader of

03:39:48.600 --> 03:39:49.739
the talents of peace.

03:39:49.799 --> 03:39:52.379
I don't know why he lets you boss him

03:39:52.379 --> 03:39:52.620
around.

03:39:52.680 --> 03:39:55.200
When he wanted to step aside, he could

03:39:55.200 --> 03:39:57.239
have let me take over.

03:39:57.299 --> 03:39:59.399
I mean, what was wrong with that plan?

03:39:59.459 --> 03:40:02.100
He took off into the sky.

03:40:02.159 --> 03:40:04.260
They could hear him muttering and whining

03:40:04.260 --> 03:40:05.579
for a while as he flew away.

03:40:05.639 --> 03:40:08.700
Winter and Kibley exchanged an amused

03:40:08.700 --> 03:40:09.120
glance.

03:40:09.180 --> 03:40:11.940
The blue sea wing took a deep breath and

03:40:11.940 --> 03:40:13.079
exhaled slowly.

03:40:13.200 --> 03:40:15.239
I apologize.

03:40:15.299 --> 03:40:18.479
He said, let's pretend that never

03:40:18.479 --> 03:40:18.840
happened.

03:40:18.899 --> 03:40:20.760
My name is riptide.

03:40:20.819 --> 03:40:21.840
I saw your signal.

03:40:21.899 --> 03:40:24.899
Are you looking for the talons of peace?

03:40:25.020 --> 03:40:27.719
Yes, Winter said.

03:40:27.780 --> 03:40:29.879
Climbing out of the river onto the

03:40:29.879 --> 03:40:30.180
grass.

03:40:30.239 --> 03:40:32.879
Deathbringer said we should come to you.

03:40:32.940 --> 03:40:35.100
We need a sky wing to help us with

03:40:35.100 --> 03:40:35.399
something.

03:40:35.459 --> 03:40:38.579
We don't have a lot of sky wings.

03:40:38.639 --> 03:40:40.020
Riptide admitted.

03:40:40.079 --> 03:40:42.840
Ruby pardoned almost everyone who'd had a

03:40:42.840 --> 03:40:45.180
disagreement with her mother, so all the

03:40:45.180 --> 03:40:46.979
fugitives who'd been hiding from Scarlet

03:40:46.979 --> 03:40:49.319
went home, but we still have a couple who

03:40:49.319 --> 03:40:50.399
don't feel safe going back.

03:40:50.459 --> 03:40:52.200
I can ask one of them.

03:40:52.260 --> 03:40:55.799
He let out an odd, high pitched whistle

03:40:55.799 --> 03:40:57.959
and 2 more dragons emerged from the

03:40:57.959 --> 03:40:58.260
trees.

03:40:58.319 --> 03:41:01.200
One was a mud wing with a crooked tail

03:41:01.200 --> 03:41:04.020
the other, Winter realized with a shock

03:41:04.020 --> 03:41:05.100
was an ice wing.

03:41:05.159 --> 03:41:08.340
Glittering silvery white, with pale

03:41:08.340 --> 03:41:09.479
purple underscales.

03:41:09.540 --> 03:41:12.000
But it was an ice wing he'd never seen

03:41:12.000 --> 03:41:12.299
before.

03:41:12.360 --> 03:41:14.219
And how was that possible?

03:41:14.280 --> 03:41:17.340
Winter had an excellent memory for faces

03:41:17.340 --> 03:41:19.620
and he thought he'd met every dragon in

03:41:19.620 --> 03:41:20.520
the tribe at least once.

03:41:20.579 --> 03:41:23.940
Please ask the sky wings to come here

03:41:23.940 --> 03:41:26.819
Riptide said to the mud wing, who nodded

03:41:26.819 --> 03:41:27.299
and flew away.

03:41:27.360 --> 03:41:29.280
Who are you?

03:41:29.340 --> 03:41:32.399
Winter asked the ice wing, who was

03:41:32.399 --> 03:41:34.440
regarding him with cold, snake-like

03:41:34.440 --> 03:41:34.680
eyes.

03:41:34.739 --> 03:41:38.100
Siri, of the ice wings.

03:41:38.159 --> 03:41:41.819
The strange dragon hissed, and you.

03:41:41.879 --> 03:41:43.920
That was even stranger.

03:41:44.040 --> 03:41:46.739
Every ice wing knew the royal family

03:41:46.739 --> 03:41:47.100
surely.

03:41:47.159 --> 03:41:51.239
I'm Prince Winter, he said slowly.

03:41:51.299 --> 03:41:53.579
He realized he didn't know what his

03:41:53.579 --> 03:41:55.799
current ranking was, which was a very

03:41:55.799 --> 03:41:57.959
unsettling feeling now that he was facing

03:41:57.959 --> 03:41:58.920
another ice wing.

03:41:58.979 --> 03:42:02.700
Could he still say, 2nd circle, and hope

03:42:02.700 --> 03:42:03.239
it was true?

03:42:03.299 --> 03:42:06.959
But then, Cyrus hadn't offered his circle

03:42:06.959 --> 03:42:07.440
number either.

03:42:07.559 --> 03:42:10.139
Because he wouldn't have one.

03:42:10.200 --> 03:42:12.540
Winter had to remind himself.

03:42:12.600 --> 03:42:14.819
He'd have been thrown off the list when

03:42:14.819 --> 03:42:16.680
he abandoned his post and joined the

03:42:16.680 --> 03:42:17.100
talents.

03:42:17.159 --> 03:42:19.319
Why don't I know you?

03:42:19.440 --> 03:42:22.379
Sirius flicked his dark blue tongue

03:42:22.379 --> 03:42:22.979
between his teeth.

03:42:23.040 --> 03:42:27.000
It's a big tribe, he said.

03:42:27.059 --> 03:42:28.920
Not really.

03:42:29.040 --> 03:42:32.219
Winter eyed him from horns to tail.

03:42:32.280 --> 03:42:34.440
Even without ranking circles.

03:42:34.500 --> 03:42:36.719
Sirius still should have known to bow to

03:42:36.719 --> 03:42:39.000
a prince, but it didn't seem like a good

03:42:39.000 --> 03:42:39.600
fight to start.

03:42:39.659 --> 03:42:42.360
Cyrus was quite a bit bigger than winter

03:42:42.360 --> 03:42:45.479
and fiercely thin, with claws that looked

03:42:45.479 --> 03:42:47.879
even sharper than normal ice wing claws.

03:42:47.940 --> 03:42:50.760
Sirius has been with the talons of peace

03:42:50.760 --> 03:42:53.399
for a long time, Riptide said, much

03:42:53.399 --> 03:42:54.059
longer than I have.

03:42:54.120 --> 03:42:56.579
He probably left the Ice Kingdom before

03:42:56.579 --> 03:42:57.239
you were hatched.

03:42:57.360 --> 03:42:59.879
That somewhat explained it.

03:42:59.940 --> 03:43:02.399
Although Winter was still surprised he'd

03:43:02.399 --> 03:43:03.239
never heard of Sirius.

03:43:03.299 --> 03:43:05.459
He hadn't realized there were any ice

03:43:05.459 --> 03:43:06.959
wings in the talons of peace.

03:43:07.020 --> 03:43:09.120
What kind of ice wing would choose

03:43:09.120 --> 03:43:11.579
banishment from the kingdom, to never

03:43:11.579 --> 03:43:14.639
return to the snow and the ice palaces, to

03:43:14.639 --> 03:43:16.139
give up your place and their rankings

03:43:16.139 --> 03:43:16.559
forever?

03:43:16.620 --> 03:43:18.959
Winter couldn't imagine it.

03:43:19.020 --> 03:43:21.780
Did you know my parents?

03:43:21.840 --> 03:43:23.100
he asked Cyrus.

03:43:23.159 --> 03:43:25.139
Tundra and Narwhal?

03:43:25.200 --> 03:43:28.860
Cyrus glanced up, tracking a rose colored

03:43:28.860 --> 03:43:31.440
butterfly with a malevolent gaze, as

03:43:31.440 --> 03:43:33.180
though he was considering eating it.

03:43:33.239 --> 03:43:35.819
Perhaps, he said.

03:43:35.879 --> 03:43:37.379
Long ago.

03:43:37.440 --> 03:43:40.979
He had to know that Narwhal was the

03:43:40.979 --> 03:43:41.520
queen's brother.

03:43:41.579 --> 03:43:44.040
How could anyone have grown up as an ice

03:43:44.040 --> 03:43:45.840
wing without learning the royal lineage?

03:43:45.899 --> 03:43:48.120
Before winter could ask any more

03:43:48.120 --> 03:43:51.120
questions, he heard snapping branches, and

03:43:51.120 --> 03:43:53.040
turned to see Moon and Kinkaju

03:43:53.040 --> 03:43:53.399
returning.

03:43:53.459 --> 03:43:56.040
Kinkachu was carrying a small pile of

03:43:56.040 --> 03:43:58.620
peaches and plums between her talons, and

03:43:58.620 --> 03:44:00.540
a pair of rabbits dangled from moon's

03:44:00.540 --> 03:44:00.840
jaws.

03:44:00.959 --> 03:44:02.760
There with us.

03:44:02.819 --> 03:44:05.700
Kibley said quickly, as riptide and

03:44:05.700 --> 03:44:06.959
Sirius both bristled.

03:44:07.020 --> 03:44:08.280
Really?

03:44:08.340 --> 03:44:09.479
Riptide said.

03:44:09.540 --> 03:44:12.239
Never thought I'd see a night wing and an

03:44:12.239 --> 03:44:13.379
ice wing traveling together.

03:44:13.440 --> 03:44:15.959
Or a rain wing outside the rainforest, for

03:44:15.959 --> 03:44:16.260
that matter.

03:44:16.319 --> 03:44:18.120
How did you all come together?

03:44:18.180 --> 03:44:21.780
Winter glanced over at Sirius again, and

03:44:21.780 --> 03:44:24.360
found him glaring at moon and Kikachu

03:44:24.360 --> 03:44:27.180
with an expression of searing hatred, so

03:44:27.180 --> 03:44:29.399
intense that Winter wanted to run across

03:44:29.399 --> 03:44:31.379
the clearing and fling up his wings to

03:44:31.379 --> 03:44:32.340
shield moon from it.

03:44:32.399 --> 03:44:35.760
Siris had left the ice wings, but his

03:44:35.760 --> 03:44:37.920
loathing of night wings, clearly still

03:44:37.920 --> 03:44:38.579
ran deep.

03:44:38.639 --> 03:44:41.459
We're from the Jade Mountain Academy.

03:44:41.520 --> 03:44:45.059
Kibley said to Riptide, I'm Kibley, and

03:44:45.059 --> 03:44:46.799
that's Moon and Kingaju.

03:44:46.860 --> 03:44:49.680
Guys, this is ribtide and Sirius.

03:44:49.739 --> 03:44:51.840
Sirius.

03:44:51.899 --> 03:44:53.760
The Ice Wing snarled.

03:44:53.819 --> 03:44:55.440
That's what I said.

03:44:55.500 --> 03:44:58.799
Kibley smiled disarmingly, but winter

03:44:58.799 --> 03:45:00.840
could tell by now when the sand wing was

03:45:00.840 --> 03:45:02.340
deliberately trying to annoy someone.

03:45:02.399 --> 03:45:04.799
Jade Mountain?

03:45:04.799 --> 03:45:07.500
Ribtide echoed, his whole face lighting

03:45:07.500 --> 03:45:07.680
up.

03:45:07.739 --> 03:45:09.479
You must know tsunami.

03:45:09.540 --> 03:45:10.200
How is she?

03:45:10.260 --> 03:45:11.159
Did she send you?

03:45:11.219 --> 03:45:12.600
Was there a message for me?

03:45:12.659 --> 03:45:15.540
No, Winter said.

03:45:15.600 --> 03:45:18.000
I mean, Deathbringer sent us.

03:45:18.059 --> 03:45:19.739
Tsunami doesn't know we're here.

03:45:19.799 --> 03:45:21.600
Oh.

03:45:21.659 --> 03:45:24.059
Riptides wings drooped.

03:45:24.120 --> 03:45:26.639
Moon took a nervous step toward him

03:45:26.639 --> 03:45:29.100
opened her mouth, closed it, and then

03:45:29.100 --> 03:45:31.680
blurted, but she thinks about you all the

03:45:31.680 --> 03:45:32.159
time.

03:45:32.219 --> 03:45:35.040
She made a face, as though she wasn't

03:45:35.040 --> 03:45:36.180
sure she should have said that.

03:45:36.239 --> 03:45:37.680
Really?

03:45:37.739 --> 03:45:40.860
The sea wings, phosphorescent scales

03:45:40.860 --> 03:45:42.420
flashed as he turned to look at her.

03:45:42.479 --> 03:45:46.559
Yes, she, she wants to hear from you.

03:45:46.620 --> 03:45:50.280
I'm not so sure about that, Ribtide

03:45:50.280 --> 03:45:50.579
said.

03:45:50.639 --> 03:45:52.680
I should probably wait until she contacts

03:45:52.680 --> 03:45:53.100
me.

03:45:53.159 --> 03:45:56.159
Oh, here's pyrite and avalanche.

03:45:56.219 --> 03:45:59.219
There was a wrestling in the trees, and

03:45:59.219 --> 03:46:01.079
then the mud wing was back, this time

03:46:01.079 --> 03:46:03.180
with 2 sky wings following behind her.

03:46:03.239 --> 03:46:05.760
The bigger Skywing had red scales.

03:46:05.819 --> 03:46:08.520
Smoke rising from her ears, and a bad

03:46:08.520 --> 03:46:09.420
tempered expression.

03:46:09.479 --> 03:46:11.520
There was something about the way she

03:46:11.520 --> 03:46:13.799
glared at them that made Winter's spine

03:46:13.799 --> 03:46:14.459
prickle.

03:46:14.520 --> 03:46:17.340
He followed her gaze and realized that

03:46:17.340 --> 03:46:19.379
her hostility was directed at Kibley.

03:46:19.440 --> 03:46:21.479
She almost looked as though she wanted to

03:46:21.479 --> 03:46:22.799
rip the bar right off his tail.

03:46:22.920 --> 03:46:24.719
Does she know him?

03:46:24.780 --> 03:46:26.819
Or does she have a problem with sand

03:46:26.819 --> 03:46:27.540
wings in general?

03:46:27.659 --> 03:46:31.139
Well, if she does know him, that would

03:46:31.139 --> 03:46:32.940
explain why she wants to kill him, ha

03:46:32.940 --> 03:46:33.659
ha.

03:46:33.719 --> 03:46:36.299
Winter let himself be amused for a second

03:46:36.299 --> 03:46:38.459
but he also found himself hoping she

03:46:38.459 --> 03:46:39.659
wouldn't be the one who helped them.

03:46:39.780 --> 03:46:43.379
The 2nd sky wing was smaller, and her

03:46:43.379 --> 03:46:45.600
wings twitched constantly, as if she

03:46:45.600 --> 03:46:46.680
might take off at any moment.

03:46:46.739 --> 03:46:49.139
Her scales were an interesting orange

03:46:49.139 --> 03:46:51.600
color that was close to yellow, like the

03:46:51.600 --> 03:46:53.819
inside of a peach, and her eyes were a

03:46:53.819 --> 03:46:55.979
darker shade of orange, like the amber

03:46:55.979 --> 03:46:57.120
earring Kibley wore.

03:46:57.239 --> 03:46:59.819
Around her neck was a small brown pouch

03:46:59.819 --> 03:47:02.879
on a gold chain, tight as a choker, and

03:47:02.879 --> 03:47:04.860
she also had a gold nose ring on one side

03:47:04.860 --> 03:47:07.079
of her snout, which was a jewelry

03:47:07.079 --> 03:47:08.579
decision winter I'd never seen before.

03:47:08.639 --> 03:47:13.260
Hi, she said. and then launched abruptly

03:47:13.260 --> 03:47:13.739
into a speech.

03:47:13.799 --> 03:47:16.620
Listen, whatever it is you need, I don't

03:47:16.620 --> 03:47:17.219
think I can help you.

03:47:17.280 --> 03:47:19.799
It's not that I wouldn't like to, I would

03:47:19.799 --> 03:47:22.200
like to, really, I wish I could do all

03:47:22.200 --> 03:47:24.540
kinds of things, but the truth is, I'm

03:47:24.540 --> 03:47:26.399
not very good at anything, and I'm sure

03:47:26.399 --> 03:47:28.319
I'm not the dragon you're looking for.

03:47:28.379 --> 03:47:30.719
So, She trailed off.

03:47:30.780 --> 03:47:32.459
Staring at them and twitching.

03:47:32.520 --> 03:47:36.120
We're not asking much, Winter said.

03:47:36.239 --> 03:47:38.940
We just want you to look at a sketch, and

03:47:38.940 --> 03:47:40.139
see if one of you recognizes it.

03:47:40.200 --> 03:47:42.659
And if you do, maybe you could give us

03:47:42.659 --> 03:47:43.739
directions on how to get there.

03:47:43.799 --> 03:47:46.319
Why should I help you?

03:47:46.379 --> 03:47:48.479
The Red Sky Wing demanded.

03:47:48.540 --> 03:47:52.079
Because word peace now, Riptide said

03:47:52.079 --> 03:47:54.659
sharply, and dragons at peace help each

03:47:54.659 --> 03:47:54.840
other.

03:47:54.899 --> 03:47:57.420
That is kind of the entire premise of the

03:47:57.420 --> 03:47:58.440
talons of peace.

03:47:58.559 --> 03:48:01.979
She growled deep in her throat, sending

03:48:01.979 --> 03:48:03.299
more smoke out her nostrils.

03:48:03.420 --> 03:48:05.940
The other Skywing touched the little bag

03:48:05.940 --> 03:48:08.159
on her necklace, rolling it anxiously

03:48:08.159 --> 03:48:09.659
between her claws.

03:48:09.719 --> 03:48:10.559
I don't know.

03:48:10.620 --> 03:48:13.680
I mean, I have a terrible memory, she

03:48:13.680 --> 03:48:15.840
said, and an awful sense of direction.

03:48:15.899 --> 03:48:20.159
Just give it a try, please, pyrite.

03:48:20.219 --> 03:48:21.360
Riptide said.

03:48:21.420 --> 03:48:23.520
There was something in his voice that

03:48:23.520 --> 03:48:25.799
gave Winter the impression, he'd spent a

03:48:25.799 --> 03:48:27.239
lot of time managing this particular

03:48:27.239 --> 03:48:28.079
dragon.

03:48:28.139 --> 03:48:30.840
Moon took the mini scroll with her sketch

03:48:30.840 --> 03:48:33.000
out of the satchel around her neck and

03:48:33.000 --> 03:48:35.459
spread it out on a flat boulder, revealing

03:48:35.459 --> 03:48:37.260
the odd mountain shapes she'd drawn.

03:48:37.379 --> 03:48:40.620
Avalanche stomped over and glowered at

03:48:40.620 --> 03:48:41.219
the drawing for a moment.

03:48:41.340 --> 03:48:43.260
Doesn't look familiar.

03:48:43.379 --> 03:48:44.639
She muttered.

03:48:44.700 --> 03:48:47.520
All right, Moon said with a sigh.

03:48:47.579 --> 03:48:48.719
Thank you anyway.

03:48:48.780 --> 03:48:50.879
Can I go now?

03:48:50.940 --> 03:48:53.879
Avalanche demanded, squinting at

03:48:53.879 --> 03:48:54.479
riptide.

03:48:54.540 --> 03:48:57.120
He nodded, and she leaped into the sky

03:48:57.120 --> 03:48:59.819
flapping away with noisy, powerful wing

03:48:59.819 --> 03:49:00.180
beats.

03:49:00.239 --> 03:49:04.500
Pyrite, ribtide said, indicating the

03:49:04.500 --> 03:49:04.860
scroll.

03:49:04.920 --> 03:49:07.799
The thin sky wing edged up to moon

03:49:07.799 --> 03:49:10.200
glanced quickly at the paper, then shook

03:49:10.200 --> 03:49:12.540
her head, saying, sorry, sorry, sorry.

03:49:12.600 --> 03:49:14.040
All trees look the same to me.

03:49:14.100 --> 03:49:19.079
It's not a tree, Moon said firmly, pinning

03:49:19.079 --> 03:49:21.600
pyrite with her gaze before the sky wing

03:49:21.600 --> 03:49:22.620
could retreat.

03:49:22.680 --> 03:49:24.899
It's a mountain, and you do recognize

03:49:24.899 --> 03:49:25.139
it.

03:49:25.200 --> 03:49:26.879
Tell us where it is.

03:49:27.000 --> 03:49:30.000
Pyrite gave her a surprised, guilty

03:49:30.000 --> 03:49:30.360
look.

03:49:30.420 --> 03:49:32.639
Winter wondered whether he should warn

03:49:32.639 --> 03:49:34.440
Moon to hide her mind reading a bit

03:49:34.440 --> 03:49:34.620
better.

03:49:34.680 --> 03:49:39.659
Oh, I suppose it's a bit familiar, Pyrite

03:49:39.659 --> 03:49:41.520
said, squinting at the sketch again.

03:49:41.579 --> 03:49:44.819
I'm sorry, I don't usually, um, do

03:49:44.819 --> 03:49:46.260
anything useful, so.

03:49:46.680 --> 03:49:49.079
Winter already wanted to smack this

03:49:49.079 --> 03:49:50.040
dithering dragon.

03:49:50.100 --> 03:49:53.040
Hailstorm was out there somewhere, alone

03:49:53.040 --> 03:49:53.760
and trapped.

03:49:53.819 --> 03:49:56.639
If Fidgety Pyrite thought she was going

03:49:56.639 --> 03:49:58.620
to be the one thing standing in Winter's

03:49:58.620 --> 03:50:01.139
way, He had a tail full of spikes ready

03:50:01.139 --> 03:50:02.040
to convince her otherwise.

03:50:02.100 --> 03:50:04.139
It's all right.

03:50:04.200 --> 03:50:06.659
Don't be nervous, Kinkachu said.

03:50:06.719 --> 03:50:09.299
Her scale's shifting to a warm golden

03:50:09.299 --> 03:50:10.860
color similar to pyrites.

03:50:10.920 --> 03:50:12.780
Anything you can tell us would be

03:50:12.780 --> 03:50:13.079
helpful.

03:50:13.139 --> 03:50:17.219
Well, I suppose it's not too far away

03:50:17.219 --> 03:50:18.780
Pyrite admitted.

03:50:18.840 --> 03:50:22.559
If I remember right, it's southwest of

03:50:22.559 --> 03:50:25.139
the Sky Palace, ish.

03:50:25.200 --> 03:50:29.879
Hmm, Kibli said, can you be any more

03:50:29.879 --> 03:50:30.360
specific?

03:50:30.420 --> 03:50:34.139
Maybe you can help us find it, Kinkaju

03:50:34.139 --> 03:50:34.620
suggested.

03:50:34.680 --> 03:50:39.059
Oh, dear no, Pyrite said, stammering and

03:50:39.059 --> 03:50:39.840
shuffling backward.

03:50:39.899 --> 03:50:41.159
I couldn't I'm sure.

03:50:41.280 --> 03:50:45.180
Why are you looking for this place?

03:50:45.239 --> 03:50:47.700
Sirius suddenly demanded.

03:50:47.760 --> 03:50:50.219
Winter had almost forgotten he was there

03:50:50.219 --> 03:50:52.799
but he'd somehow crept around until he

03:50:52.799 --> 03:50:54.840
could see the sketch over Pyrite's

03:50:54.840 --> 03:50:55.020
shoulder.

03:50:55.079 --> 03:50:57.420
What do you really want?

03:50:57.479 --> 03:51:01.379
It's a fair question, Riptide pointed

03:51:01.379 --> 03:51:01.559
out.

03:51:01.620 --> 03:51:04.620
If you want pyrite to go with you, we

03:51:04.620 --> 03:51:06.059
should all know what she's flying into.

03:51:06.180 --> 03:51:10.139
Winter liked the way Kibli looked to him

03:51:10.139 --> 03:51:11.879
waiting for Winter to decide whether to

03:51:11.879 --> 03:51:12.479
reveal the truth.

03:51:12.540 --> 03:51:17.159
We think this is where Queen Scarlet is

03:51:17.159 --> 03:51:19.559
hiding, Winter said cautiously.

03:51:19.620 --> 03:51:23.520
Riptide sucked in a startled breath, Cyrus

03:51:23.520 --> 03:51:25.920
sank lower to the ground and hissed, his

03:51:25.920 --> 03:51:27.239
tail lashing furiously.

03:51:27.299 --> 03:51:30.120
But Pyrite turned shining eyes to

03:51:30.120 --> 03:51:30.420
Winter.

03:51:30.540 --> 03:51:32.040
Queen Scarlet?

03:51:32.100 --> 03:51:32.940
She's all right?

03:51:33.000 --> 03:51:35.280
She picked up the drawing and held it

03:51:35.280 --> 03:51:36.180
close to her chest.

03:51:36.239 --> 03:51:37.620
And you think she's here?

03:51:37.680 --> 03:51:39.000
I'll take you there if she's there.

03:51:39.059 --> 03:51:42.959
I'm not sure that's wise.

03:51:43.079 --> 03:51:44.879
Sirius growled.

03:51:44.940 --> 03:51:47.280
Why would you get a vote?

03:51:47.340 --> 03:51:48.600
Winter demanded.

03:51:48.659 --> 03:51:50.459
She can help us if she wants to.

03:51:50.520 --> 03:51:53.579
He had to admit to himself that he did

03:51:53.579 --> 03:51:55.920
not love the idea of a fervent scarlet

03:51:55.920 --> 03:51:57.600
loyalist leading them to the queen.

03:51:57.659 --> 03:52:00.059
What if she betrayed them along the way?

03:52:00.120 --> 03:52:02.399
But perhaps if they kept their true

03:52:02.399 --> 03:52:04.260
mission a secret, they could still use

03:52:04.260 --> 03:52:04.440
her.

03:52:04.500 --> 03:52:07.739
I can try, Pyrite said.

03:52:07.799 --> 03:52:10.139
I mean, I might get us lost, but...

03:52:10.139 --> 03:52:11.579
I'll do my best.

03:52:11.639 --> 03:52:13.500
For Queen Scarlet.

03:52:13.559 --> 03:52:15.600
I always do my best for her.

03:52:15.659 --> 03:52:17.280
Did, I mean.

03:52:17.399 --> 03:52:20.639
She let out a little sigh, settling her

03:52:20.639 --> 03:52:21.000
wings.

03:52:21.059 --> 03:52:23.819
Thank you Winter said.

03:52:23.879 --> 03:52:26.399
I don't like this.

03:52:26.459 --> 03:52:28.319
Sirius interjected.

03:52:28.440 --> 03:52:31.860
What good could come of finding Queen

03:52:31.860 --> 03:52:32.760
Scarlet?

03:52:32.819 --> 03:52:35.520
What are you planning to do if she is

03:52:35.520 --> 03:52:35.819
there?

03:52:35.879 --> 03:52:38.760
He suddenly gave Winters sharp look.

03:52:38.819 --> 03:52:42.059
Did you say Prince Winter?

03:52:42.120 --> 03:52:44.459
Mind your own business.

03:52:44.520 --> 03:52:45.780
Winter snapped.

03:52:45.840 --> 03:52:49.319
It's all right, Cyrus, Pyrite said.

03:52:49.379 --> 03:52:51.420
Twisting her claws together, she gave

03:52:51.420 --> 03:52:52.860
Winter an apologetic smile.

03:52:52.920 --> 03:52:55.020
He kind of takes care of me.

03:52:55.079 --> 03:52:57.059
He's just being protective.

03:52:57.120 --> 03:53:01.200
Add that to the pile of weird mysteries

03:53:01.200 --> 03:53:02.159
about this ice wing.

03:53:02.280 --> 03:53:03.360
Winter thought.

03:53:03.420 --> 03:53:05.700
Why would he be so concerned about this

03:53:05.700 --> 03:53:07.860
rather annoying Skywing?

03:53:07.920 --> 03:53:10.260
He can't be in love with her, can he?

03:53:10.319 --> 03:53:13.319
Cyrus didn't have anything loving about

03:53:13.319 --> 03:53:13.979
his demeanor.

03:53:14.040 --> 03:53:16.379
He didn't even seem to particularly like

03:53:16.379 --> 03:53:17.280
pyrite.

03:53:17.340 --> 03:53:19.379
He barely glanced at her when she spoke.

03:53:19.500 --> 03:53:21.899
He certainly didn't look at her the way.

03:53:22.139 --> 03:53:24.659
The way I look at Moon.

03:53:24.780 --> 03:53:28.139
Winter glanced across the clearing, and

03:53:28.139 --> 03:53:29.760
finally admitted something to himself.

03:53:29.819 --> 03:53:33.540
Or the way Kibley looks at Moon.

03:53:33.600 --> 03:53:36.600
Did Moon look at either of them that

03:53:36.600 --> 03:53:36.780
way?

03:53:36.840 --> 03:53:38.340
He couldn't tell.

03:53:38.399 --> 03:53:39.840
It didn't matter.

03:53:39.899 --> 03:53:41.459
Neither of them could be with her

03:53:41.459 --> 03:53:41.879
anyway.

03:53:41.940 --> 03:53:44.280
Not if they wanted to remain loyal to

03:53:44.280 --> 03:53:45.420
their queens and tribes.

03:53:45.479 --> 03:53:49.079
Stop thinking about this, and focus on

03:53:49.079 --> 03:53:50.219
getting Hellstorm back.

03:53:50.280 --> 03:53:53.639
He stepped over to Pyrite, and reached

03:53:53.639 --> 03:53:55.260
for the drawing in her claws.

03:53:55.319 --> 03:53:57.959
As she held it out, their talons briefly

03:53:57.959 --> 03:54:00.840
touched, and Winter felt a sudden weird

03:54:00.840 --> 03:54:02.040
shifting of the world.

03:54:02.159 --> 03:54:04.920
Like something tugging apart his muscles

03:54:04.920 --> 03:54:05.700
from inside him.

03:54:05.760 --> 03:54:09.719
He froze, staring into the sky wing's

03:54:09.719 --> 03:54:10.860
innocent amber eyes.

03:54:10.920 --> 03:54:13.500
He felt something strange like this once

03:54:13.500 --> 03:54:16.200
before. at the tunnels in the rainforest

03:54:16.200 --> 03:54:18.719
where magic had made the world not quite

03:54:18.719 --> 03:54:19.020
right.

03:54:19.079 --> 03:54:22.680
And if he felt the same twisting of magic

03:54:22.680 --> 03:54:25.020
when he touched her talents, that could

03:54:25.020 --> 03:54:26.100
only mean one thing.

03:54:26.159 --> 03:54:28.979
Pyrite must be an animus.

03:54:29.040 --> 03:54:33.239
Chapter 12.

03:54:33.659 --> 03:54:37.440
Winter didn't have a chance to tell the

03:54:37.440 --> 03:54:39.479
others his theory about pyrite that day

03:54:39.479 --> 03:54:42.540
as it turned out, she was not only a very

03:54:42.540 --> 03:54:44.760
nervous dragon, but she was also

03:54:44.760 --> 03:54:46.319
extremely clingy.

03:54:46.379 --> 03:54:49.139
As soon as Cyrus and Riptide were out of

03:54:49.139 --> 03:54:51.420
sight, she attached herself to Winter's

03:54:51.420 --> 03:54:53.579
tail and followed him around as though he

03:54:53.579 --> 03:54:55.079
were made of delicious bear meat.

03:54:55.139 --> 03:54:58.079
Why he'd been chosen for this particular

03:54:58.079 --> 03:55:00.420
honor, Winter had no idea.

03:55:00.600 --> 03:55:03.360
Kinkatoo and Kibli were much nicer to

03:55:03.360 --> 03:55:05.639
Pyrite than he was, and yet she got all

03:55:05.639 --> 03:55:07.500
flappy and anxious whenever they talked

03:55:07.500 --> 03:55:08.219
to her.

03:55:08.280 --> 03:55:10.379
Maybe she was simply used to having an

03:55:10.379 --> 03:55:11.639
ice wing watch out for her.

03:55:11.700 --> 03:55:15.899
And maybe, Sirius knows exactly what she

03:55:15.899 --> 03:55:17.520
is, Winter guessed.

03:55:17.579 --> 03:55:20.399
Maybe that's why he's so interested in

03:55:20.399 --> 03:55:21.239
her whereabouts.

03:55:21.299 --> 03:55:24.000
Maybe he's planning to use her power for

03:55:24.000 --> 03:55:24.299
something.

03:55:24.360 --> 03:55:26.280
But what?

03:55:26.399 --> 03:55:29.159
What sort of sinister plans could alone

03:55:29.159 --> 03:55:30.540
ice wing be hatching?

03:55:30.600 --> 03:55:32.879
Brooding among the dwindling numbers of

03:55:32.879 --> 03:55:33.840
the talons of peace.

03:55:33.899 --> 03:55:36.479
Was he planning to deliver her to the ice

03:55:36.479 --> 03:55:37.020
wings?

03:55:37.079 --> 03:55:39.600
An animus to replace their long lost

03:55:39.600 --> 03:55:40.620
Prince Arctic?

03:55:40.620 --> 03:55:42.899
In exchange for letting him back into the

03:55:42.899 --> 03:55:43.139
tribe?

03:55:43.200 --> 03:55:46.260
Cyrus didn't seem to be in any hurry to

03:55:46.260 --> 03:55:47.520
get back to the ice kingdom, though.

03:55:47.579 --> 03:55:50.459
There must be a reason he left.

03:55:50.520 --> 03:55:51.840
What was he up to?

03:55:51.899 --> 03:55:55.620
It was also strange that Pyrite could

03:55:55.620 --> 03:55:58.379
possess such enormous magic, and not be

03:55:58.379 --> 03:55:59.100
more sure of herself.

03:55:59.159 --> 03:56:01.920
Didn't she know she was ananimous?

03:56:01.979 --> 03:56:03.540
Had she ever used her power?

03:56:03.600 --> 03:56:04.920
How often?

03:56:04.979 --> 03:56:06.540
And what had she done with it?

03:56:06.600 --> 03:56:09.479
He glanced over his shoulder at where she

03:56:09.479 --> 03:56:12.120
was flying, barely a wing beat behind him

03:56:12.120 --> 03:56:14.340
casting fearful looks at the mountains

03:56:14.340 --> 03:56:14.760
below them.

03:56:14.819 --> 03:56:17.340
The 1st animus he'd ever met.

03:56:17.399 --> 03:56:19.739
She was not at all what he would have

03:56:19.739 --> 03:56:20.100
expected.

03:56:20.159 --> 03:56:24.780
So, Pyrite, Kibley said in a friendly

03:56:24.780 --> 03:56:26.760
voice, swooping up on her other side.

03:56:26.819 --> 03:56:29.819
Pyrite jerked away from him, and nearly

03:56:29.819 --> 03:56:31.079
bowled winter out of the sky.

03:56:31.139 --> 03:56:33.959
Her wings thwacked around his snout for a

03:56:33.959 --> 03:56:36.600
moment, and once again he got that twisty

03:56:36.600 --> 03:56:37.200
ill feeling.

03:56:37.260 --> 03:56:39.420
He shoved her off him and righted

03:56:39.420 --> 03:56:39.899
himself.

03:56:39.959 --> 03:56:41.879
Watch it, he snapped.

03:56:41.940 --> 03:56:43.680
Sorry, sorry, sorry.

03:56:43.739 --> 03:56:44.819
She mumbled.

03:56:44.879 --> 03:56:47.159
She flicked her tail at Kibley.

03:56:47.219 --> 03:56:48.780
You startled me.

03:56:48.840 --> 03:56:52.139
Kibli made a, what is wrong with this

03:56:52.139 --> 03:56:52.860
dragon?

03:56:52.860 --> 03:56:54.120
Face in winter?

03:56:54.180 --> 03:56:56.879
I was just wondering how you ended up

03:56:56.879 --> 03:56:58.979
with the talons of peace, he said.

03:56:59.040 --> 03:57:02.040
You don't exactly seem like the type to

03:57:02.040 --> 03:57:04.319
desert your wing and strike out into the

03:57:04.319 --> 03:57:06.479
wilderness on your own, looking for a

03:57:06.479 --> 03:57:07.620
band of rebels to join.

03:57:07.680 --> 03:57:10.680
Oh no, Pyrite said.

03:57:10.739 --> 03:57:12.420
No, I'm not like that at all.

03:57:12.479 --> 03:57:14.520
I'm completely loyal.

03:57:14.579 --> 03:57:16.379
I would have kept fighting for Queen

03:57:16.379 --> 03:57:18.780
Scarlet as long as she needed me.

03:57:18.840 --> 03:57:21.600
She stretched her long neck and scanned

03:57:21.600 --> 03:57:23.579
the ground below them again, then

03:57:23.579 --> 03:57:25.200
twitched her wings to steer them a little

03:57:25.200 --> 03:57:25.920
more westward.

03:57:25.979 --> 03:57:29.219
But when Ruby took the throne, she made

03:57:29.219 --> 03:57:31.680
everyone swear an oath to her, and I

03:57:31.680 --> 03:57:33.000
couldn't do that, you know?

03:57:33.059 --> 03:57:35.819
I'm completely loyal to Queen Scarlet

03:57:35.819 --> 03:57:38.280
always and always and always.

03:57:38.340 --> 03:57:42.239
Winter noticed that Moon was frowning at

03:57:42.239 --> 03:57:44.520
pyrite, as if she were a book written in

03:57:44.520 --> 03:57:45.840
the language of narwhals.

03:57:45.899 --> 03:57:48.600
Had she also figured out that Pyrite was

03:57:48.600 --> 03:57:51.120
an animus, could she see it in Pyrite's

03:57:51.120 --> 03:57:51.299
mind?

03:57:51.360 --> 03:57:55.200
But if Scarlet had a completely loyal

03:57:55.200 --> 03:57:57.959
animus under her claws, why didn't she

03:57:57.959 --> 03:57:58.920
use her to win the war?

03:57:58.979 --> 03:58:03.239
So I left the Sky Palace and joined the

03:58:03.239 --> 03:58:04.079
talents of peace.

03:58:04.139 --> 03:58:06.059
Pyrite side.

03:58:06.120 --> 03:58:08.760
Sometimes I have dreams about Queen

03:58:08.760 --> 03:58:11.159
Scarlet telling me to come to her, but

03:58:11.159 --> 03:58:12.899
Sirius always says to ignore them.

03:58:12.959 --> 03:58:15.120
He says it isn't safe for me to go

03:58:15.120 --> 03:58:17.159
flapping around the continent looking for

03:58:17.159 --> 03:58:19.979
a dragon in exile, and the dreams don't

03:58:19.979 --> 03:58:20.340
mean anything.

03:58:20.399 --> 03:58:23.100
She smiled hopefully in winter.

03:58:23.159 --> 03:58:26.100
But this isn't a wild scavenger, Chase.

03:58:26.159 --> 03:58:27.420
You really think she'll be there.

03:58:27.479 --> 03:58:28.379
Right?

03:58:28.440 --> 03:58:31.079
I do, Winter said.

03:58:31.139 --> 03:58:33.360
Suddenly wondering if this was a terrible

03:58:33.360 --> 03:58:36.360
idea, bringing Queen Scarlet a pet

03:58:36.360 --> 03:58:37.020
animas?

03:58:37.079 --> 03:58:39.600
How many ways could that go horribly

03:58:39.600 --> 03:58:39.719
wrong?

03:58:39.780 --> 03:58:42.540
Would pyrite get in the way if they tried

03:58:42.540 --> 03:58:43.799
to save Hailstorm?

03:58:43.860 --> 03:58:45.899
What would she do if she knew that was

03:58:45.899 --> 03:58:46.319
their goal?

03:58:46.379 --> 03:58:49.500
They stopped to rest for the night in a

03:58:49.500 --> 03:58:51.540
valley dappled with clumps of small white

03:58:51.540 --> 03:58:52.200
flowers.

03:58:52.260 --> 03:58:54.120
It made it look as though someone had

03:58:54.120 --> 03:58:55.979
been tossing down snowballs from the

03:58:55.979 --> 03:58:56.700
peaks around them.

03:58:56.760 --> 03:58:59.760
Kibley started a fire, and cooked the

03:58:59.760 --> 03:59:02.040
squirrels moon caught, while Winter got

03:59:02.040 --> 03:59:03.899
himself a fish from the stream and ate it

03:59:03.899 --> 03:59:04.200
raw.

03:59:04.260 --> 03:59:06.600
He couldn't quite understand why anyone

03:59:06.600 --> 03:59:08.159
would want to scorch up their food before

03:59:08.159 --> 03:59:10.620
eating it, although it still sounded more

03:59:10.620 --> 03:59:12.600
appetizing than the wild cherries and

03:59:12.600 --> 03:59:14.159
plums Kinkaju had for dinner.

03:59:14.219 --> 03:59:16.920
Pyrite picked halfheartedly at her

03:59:16.920 --> 03:59:17.340
squirrel.

03:59:17.459 --> 03:59:19.379
Her scales glowing in the firelight.

03:59:19.440 --> 03:59:22.500
Every time winter looked over at her, he

03:59:22.500 --> 03:59:24.540
was sure she'd edged a little closer to

03:59:24.540 --> 03:59:24.780
him.

03:59:24.840 --> 03:59:28.319
She didn't say much, and barely seemed to

03:59:28.319 --> 03:59:30.299
be listening to Kibley as he told the

03:59:30.299 --> 03:59:32.819
story of the dragonettes, defeating Byrne

03:59:32.819 --> 03:59:34.799
and blister, and giving the sand wing

03:59:34.799 --> 03:59:35.940
throne to Queen Thorn.

03:59:36.000 --> 03:59:38.399
He'd been there and seen the whole thing

03:59:38.399 --> 03:59:41.040
and he was a compelling storyteller, too.

03:59:41.100 --> 03:59:44.100
Moon and Kinkachu were rapped, although

03:59:44.100 --> 03:59:45.059
they must have heard it all before.

03:59:45.120 --> 03:59:48.059
Finally, everyone curled up to sleep

03:59:48.059 --> 03:59:49.680
including pyrite.

03:59:49.739 --> 03:59:52.500
Winter volunteered to keep the 1st watch

03:59:52.500 --> 03:59:54.719
which was a concept that seemed to

03:59:54.719 --> 03:59:56.459
endlessly puzzle Kinkaju.

03:59:56.520 --> 03:59:58.620
Why did anyone have to stand guard?

03:59:58.680 --> 04:00:01.139
She'd asked the 1st night, Who would

04:00:01.139 --> 04:00:02.399
attack sleeping dragons?

04:00:02.459 --> 04:00:04.440
What do they have to fear now that the

04:00:04.440 --> 04:00:04.920
war was over?

04:00:05.040 --> 04:00:08.459
And other such inane, typically rain wing

04:00:08.459 --> 04:00:08.940
type questions?

04:00:09.000 --> 04:00:12.000
Darkness lay quietly over the valley.

04:00:12.059 --> 04:00:14.700
One of the moons was a sharp crescent

04:00:14.700 --> 04:00:17.159
just over the peaks, while the other 2

04:00:17.159 --> 04:00:18.959
were a little more full and higher in the

04:00:18.959 --> 04:00:19.319
sky.

04:00:19.379 --> 04:00:22.260
Winter waited until Pyrite's breathing

04:00:22.260 --> 04:00:24.059
was slow and steady, and then he

04:00:24.059 --> 04:00:25.680
carefully eased himself around the others

04:00:25.680 --> 04:00:27.299
to gently nudge Moon.

04:00:27.360 --> 04:00:30.780
She stretched her front talons and made a

04:00:30.780 --> 04:00:33.120
soft noise in her sleep, curling farther

04:00:33.120 --> 04:00:33.780
into her wings.

04:00:33.899 --> 04:00:37.620
He felt an almost unbearable longing to

04:00:37.620 --> 04:00:39.899
press himself against her scales and fall

04:00:39.899 --> 04:00:42.479
asleep with her star speckled wings over

04:00:42.479 --> 04:00:42.719
his.

04:00:42.780 --> 04:00:45.780
Moon, Winter whispered.

04:00:45.840 --> 04:00:47.100
Shaking her shoulder again.

04:00:47.159 --> 04:00:50.280
At last she opened her eyes and sat up

04:00:50.280 --> 04:00:50.879
yawning.

04:00:50.940 --> 04:00:52.500
What's wrong?

04:00:52.620 --> 04:00:53.819
She whispered.

04:00:53.879 --> 04:00:56.340
Is pyrite truly asleep?

04:00:56.399 --> 04:00:58.739
He asked, as softly as he could.

04:00:58.799 --> 04:01:01.680
She listened for a moment, then nodded.

04:01:01.739 --> 04:01:04.260
Winter beckoned for her to follow him out

04:01:04.260 --> 04:01:06.120
of earshot of the others, to be safe.

04:01:06.180 --> 04:01:09.000
They stopped below a tree wrapped in

04:01:09.000 --> 04:01:10.680
blooming vines of moonflowers.

04:01:10.739 --> 04:01:13.379
Pale ghost petals shivering in the

04:01:13.379 --> 04:01:13.620
breeze.

04:01:13.680 --> 04:01:18.299
I think pyrite is an animus, Winter

04:01:18.299 --> 04:01:18.600
said.

04:01:18.659 --> 04:01:21.120
Coming straight to the point, because he

04:01:21.120 --> 04:01:22.799
was afraid of what else he might say to

04:01:22.799 --> 04:01:24.540
moon alone in the dark.

04:01:24.600 --> 04:01:25.799
Oh.

04:01:25.860 --> 04:01:28.920
That's interesting, Moon said.

04:01:28.979 --> 04:01:32.100
If she is, she doesn't know it, or she

04:01:32.100 --> 04:01:32.819
never thinks about it.

04:01:32.879 --> 04:01:34.620
Wouldn't that be strange?

04:01:34.680 --> 04:01:37.500
To know you have the most powerful magic

04:01:37.500 --> 04:01:40.079
in Pyrea, and not think about it once all

04:01:40.079 --> 04:01:40.319
day.

04:01:40.379 --> 04:01:43.319
I'd imagine an animus would constantly be

04:01:43.319 --> 04:01:45.780
thinking, I could just enchant this one

04:01:45.780 --> 04:01:47.940
thing, and it would make my life easier.

04:01:48.000 --> 04:01:51.420
And, but what if I go too far and lose my

04:01:51.420 --> 04:01:51.600
soul?

04:01:51.659 --> 04:01:53.340
Is this one thing worth it?

04:01:53.399 --> 04:01:55.139
All day.

04:01:55.200 --> 04:01:56.819
I would think, it would go back and

04:01:56.819 --> 04:01:57.120
forth.

04:01:57.180 --> 04:01:59.700
Maybe that's just what my brain would do

04:01:59.700 --> 04:02:00.000
though.

04:02:00.059 --> 04:02:03.000
In any case, I didn't hear anything like

04:02:03.000 --> 04:02:04.200
that in Pyrite's head.

04:02:04.260 --> 04:02:06.479
What do you think of her?

04:02:06.540 --> 04:02:07.620
Winter asked.

04:02:07.680 --> 04:02:08.879
Well?

04:02:09.059 --> 04:02:12.120
I feel sorry for her, Moon said.

04:02:12.180 --> 04:02:15.299
She ran one claw lightly down the vine

04:02:15.299 --> 04:02:16.379
wrapped trunk of the tree.

04:02:16.440 --> 04:02:18.840
Her brain is very odd.

04:02:18.899 --> 04:02:21.120
It's like her thoughts are stuck in a

04:02:21.120 --> 04:02:21.479
circle.

04:02:21.540 --> 04:02:23.639
I don't know if she's been hit on the

04:02:23.639 --> 04:02:25.739
head really hard or something, but they

04:02:25.739 --> 04:02:27.239
just go round and around.

04:02:27.299 --> 04:02:30.239
I'm completely loyal to Queen Scarlet.

04:02:30.299 --> 04:02:31.559
I'm not very good at anything.

04:02:31.620 --> 04:02:33.420
I'm glad I'm a Skywing.

04:02:33.479 --> 04:02:35.459
I'm clumsy and not very bright and

04:02:35.459 --> 04:02:36.239
generally useless.

04:02:36.299 --> 04:02:39.420
And then back to I'm completely loyal to

04:02:39.420 --> 04:02:40.139
Queen Scarlet.

04:02:40.200 --> 04:02:43.979
Maybe she isn't very bright.

04:02:44.040 --> 04:02:45.420
Winter suggested.

04:02:45.479 --> 04:02:48.299
Or she's worried about the same things so

04:02:48.299 --> 04:02:50.760
much for so long that her thoughts have

04:02:50.760 --> 04:02:53.040
worn grooves in her mind, where they keep

04:02:53.040 --> 04:02:55.020
spinning and spinning, Moon said.

04:02:55.139 --> 04:02:57.959
I don't know I haven't read anyone like

04:02:57.959 --> 04:02:58.379
her before.

04:02:58.440 --> 04:03:00.540
It's very.

04:03:00.600 --> 04:03:03.360
Okay, this sounds weird, but it's very

04:03:03.360 --> 04:03:04.440
shallow in there.

04:03:04.500 --> 04:03:07.020
Really, Winter said.

04:03:07.079 --> 04:03:09.659
You've been surrounded by rain wings, but

04:03:09.659 --> 04:03:11.100
never met anyone shallow before.

04:03:11.159 --> 04:03:13.620
Moon poked him with her tail.

04:03:13.680 --> 04:03:16.440
That is a really narrow-minded view of

04:03:16.440 --> 04:03:17.760
rain wings, she said.

04:03:17.819 --> 04:03:20.639
You must have noticed that Kinkaju and

04:03:20.639 --> 04:03:22.020
Glory are anything but shallow.

04:03:22.079 --> 04:03:25.260
She paused, then added with a small laugh

04:03:25.260 --> 04:03:28.200
Well, all right, there's coconut.

04:03:28.260 --> 04:03:29.879
I suppose he isn't much deeper than

04:03:29.879 --> 04:03:32.639
pyrite, but it still feels unusually

04:03:32.639 --> 04:03:33.479
weird in her head.

04:03:33.540 --> 04:03:37.079
Maybe because she's inanimous, Winters

04:03:37.079 --> 04:03:37.319
said.

04:03:37.440 --> 04:03:39.959
Maybe she's using some kind of magic to

04:03:39.959 --> 04:03:41.459
hide her power from other dragons.

04:03:41.579 --> 04:03:45.120
A flurry of snowy petals swirl down from

04:03:45.120 --> 04:03:47.219
the tree and over their wings, Moon

04:03:47.219 --> 04:03:47.819
shivered.

04:03:47.879 --> 04:03:51.059
That makes her sound very ominous, she

04:03:51.059 --> 04:03:51.299
said.

04:03:51.360 --> 04:03:54.600
That's exactly what I'm worried about.

04:03:54.659 --> 04:03:57.840
Winter reached out and brushed a pedal

04:03:57.840 --> 04:03:58.799
off Moon's shoulder.

04:03:58.860 --> 04:04:01.440
What if she's a lot more dangerous than

04:04:01.440 --> 04:04:02.100
she seems?

04:04:02.159 --> 04:04:04.139
What if she can hide even from you?

04:04:04.260 --> 04:04:06.000
How can we trust her?

04:04:06.059 --> 04:04:08.700
They both turn to look back at the

04:04:08.700 --> 04:04:10.440
slumbering shapes beside the fading

04:04:10.440 --> 04:04:11.459
embers of the campfire.

04:04:11.520 --> 04:04:16.500
Beware one who is not what she seems, Moon

04:04:16.500 --> 04:04:19.020
whispered. sending a trail of ice along

04:04:19.020 --> 04:04:19.920
winter's wings.

04:04:19.979 --> 04:04:21.899
Could that be pyrite?

04:04:21.959 --> 04:04:24.360
We need her help, though.

04:04:24.420 --> 04:04:26.040
Winter said gruffly.

04:04:26.100 --> 04:04:28.559
It's not like we can just fly off and

04:04:28.559 --> 04:04:29.040
ditch her.

04:04:29.159 --> 04:04:31.200
He was starting to wish they could

04:04:31.200 --> 04:04:31.379
though.

04:04:31.500 --> 04:04:35.520
I guess we just have to be careful, Moon

04:04:35.520 --> 04:04:36.239
said softly.

04:04:36.299 --> 04:04:38.159
She tilted her head to the side.

04:04:38.219 --> 04:04:40.739
We should tell Kibley and see what he

04:04:40.739 --> 04:04:41.040
thinks.

04:04:41.100 --> 04:04:42.959
I'll tell him.

04:04:43.079 --> 04:04:46.079
Winter said, hoping he didn't sound as

04:04:46.079 --> 04:04:47.399
ungracious as he felt.

04:04:47.459 --> 04:04:49.799
It was true it would be smart to get the

04:04:49.799 --> 04:04:52.379
observant sandwing on the case, keeping

04:04:52.379 --> 04:04:54.600
an eye on pyrite, but he found himself

04:04:54.600 --> 04:04:57.120
picturing Kibley standing here, under

04:04:57.120 --> 04:04:59.579
this tree with moon, and it made him feel

04:04:59.579 --> 04:05:01.860
hollowed out, like an ice cave.

04:05:01.979 --> 04:05:05.280
When I wake him for the next watch, you

04:05:05.280 --> 04:05:06.059
can go back to sleep.

04:05:06.120 --> 04:05:09.299
All right, Moon said.

04:05:09.360 --> 04:05:12.659
She hesitated, then took a step closer to

04:05:12.659 --> 04:05:14.819
winter, so that their wings were nearly

04:05:14.819 --> 04:05:15.180
touching.

04:05:15.239 --> 04:05:17.639
He felt his breath catch in his throat.

04:05:17.700 --> 04:05:21.360
She was made for moonlight, all silver

04:05:21.360 --> 04:05:23.700
and ebony, or moonlight was made for

04:05:23.700 --> 04:05:23.879
her.

04:05:23.940 --> 04:05:26.760
He could imagine her in the ice kingdom

04:05:26.760 --> 04:05:29.159
silhouetted against the vast whiteness

04:05:29.159 --> 04:05:31.920
dark as the ocean, and glittering like

04:05:31.920 --> 04:05:32.700
the moonlit snow.

04:05:32.760 --> 04:05:36.540
Except, if she said one talent in the ice

04:05:36.540 --> 04:05:38.760
kingdom, someone would probably kill her

04:05:38.760 --> 04:05:41.459
or at the very least, throw her into

04:05:41.459 --> 04:05:43.920
glaciers, dungeon, where the cold would

04:05:43.920 --> 04:05:45.659
take care of her just as thoroughly.

04:05:45.719 --> 04:05:48.600
And his family would do the same, no

04:05:48.600 --> 04:05:50.639
matter where she was, if they had any

04:05:50.639 --> 04:05:52.260
idea how winter felt about her.

04:05:52.319 --> 04:05:55.139
He would never let that happen.

04:05:55.260 --> 04:05:56.879
Go on.

04:05:57.000 --> 04:06:00.360
Sleep, he said, his voice coming out

04:06:00.360 --> 04:06:01.440
rougher than he meant it to.

04:06:01.500 --> 04:06:03.659
We might need you to find Scarlet

04:06:03.659 --> 04:06:03.959
tomorrow.

04:06:04.020 --> 04:06:06.059
She dropped her gaze.

04:06:06.120 --> 04:06:09.360
Thank you for telling me about pyrite, she

04:06:09.360 --> 04:06:09.600
said.

04:06:09.659 --> 04:06:11.219
Good night.

04:06:11.280 --> 04:06:13.200
And then she was gone.

04:06:13.260 --> 04:06:16.379
Winter took this 2nd watch as well

04:06:16.379 --> 04:06:18.959
knowing sleep would be a long time coming

04:06:18.959 --> 04:06:19.799
for him tonight.

04:06:19.860 --> 04:06:24.360
Chapter 13.

04:06:24.540 --> 04:06:28.920
Kibley was the 1st to spot the eye shaped

04:06:28.920 --> 04:06:31.020
spire in the distance. early in the

04:06:31.020 --> 04:06:31.979
afternoon the next day.

04:06:32.040 --> 04:06:35.399
Gray clouds had rolled in, covering the

04:06:35.399 --> 04:06:37.799
sky in soggy blankets, and threatening to

04:06:37.799 --> 04:06:38.819
rain at any moment.

04:06:38.819 --> 04:06:41.639
Winter's wings felt like giant seal

04:06:41.639 --> 04:06:44.159
flippers hanging off his back, heavy and

04:06:44.159 --> 04:06:44.760
ponderous.

04:06:44.879 --> 04:06:47.940
He had barely slept, and his eyelids

04:06:47.940 --> 04:06:50.340
wanted nothing more than to slam shut and

04:06:50.340 --> 04:06:51.420
drag him into slumber.

04:06:51.479 --> 04:06:54.780
But when Kibley called, over there.

04:06:54.840 --> 04:06:55.860
I think I see it.

04:06:55.979 --> 04:06:58.620
A burst of energy jittered through

04:06:58.620 --> 04:06:59.340
winter's muscles.

04:06:59.399 --> 04:07:01.860
He soared over to Kibley's side, and

04:07:01.860 --> 04:07:03.600
squinted in the direction the sand wing

04:07:03.600 --> 04:07:03.959
was pointing.

04:07:04.020 --> 04:07:07.379
I don't see anything, Kinkichu said.

04:07:07.440 --> 04:07:10.739
That's because you're a rain wing, said

04:07:10.739 --> 04:07:11.459
Pyrite.

04:07:11.520 --> 04:07:12.299
I see it.

04:07:12.360 --> 04:07:14.639
Skywings can see much better and farther

04:07:14.639 --> 04:07:15.120
than you do.

04:07:15.180 --> 04:07:17.819
So can ice wings.

04:07:17.879 --> 04:07:20.280
Winter wanted to add, but he didn't want

04:07:20.280 --> 04:07:22.020
to sound anything like pyrite.

04:07:22.079 --> 04:07:24.180
I don't see it yet either.

04:07:24.239 --> 04:07:26.100
Moon said to Kinkachu.

04:07:26.159 --> 04:07:27.959
But if it's over there, let's go.

04:07:28.020 --> 04:07:30.780
She put on a burst of speed and shot

04:07:30.780 --> 04:07:31.559
ahead of the others.

04:07:31.620 --> 04:07:33.899
Race you to that peak!

04:07:33.959 --> 04:07:36.239
Kinkaju yelled, zipping pastor.

04:07:36.360 --> 04:07:38.520
The 2 of them swooped away, their

04:07:38.520 --> 04:07:40.860
laughter echoing back off the mountains.

04:07:40.920 --> 04:07:43.260
Kinkachu's scales were dappled gold and

04:07:43.260 --> 04:07:45.719
silver today, like some metallic treasure

04:07:45.719 --> 04:07:46.739
version of a dragon.

04:07:46.799 --> 04:07:49.559
She'd chatted happily with pyrite over

04:07:49.559 --> 04:07:51.719
breakfast, and winter had felt a pang of

04:07:51.719 --> 04:07:53.879
guilt that he hadn't woken her up to hear

04:07:53.879 --> 04:07:54.600
his theory too.

04:07:54.659 --> 04:07:57.719
Were rain wings even capable of regarding

04:07:57.719 --> 04:07:59.100
other dragons with suspicion?

04:07:59.159 --> 04:08:01.739
Terribly undignified.

04:08:01.860 --> 04:08:04.860
Kibley said in a haughty voice, tipping

04:08:04.860 --> 04:08:07.500
his snout at the racing dragons, we would

04:08:07.500 --> 04:08:09.780
never allow such higgledy piggledy

04:08:09.780 --> 04:08:11.219
shenanigans in the ice kingdom.

04:08:11.280 --> 04:08:13.799
Was that supposed to be me?

04:08:13.920 --> 04:08:15.239
Winter asked him.

04:08:15.299 --> 04:08:17.340
Terribly unimpressive if so.

04:08:17.399 --> 04:08:20.340
I haven't once said higgledy piggledy in

04:08:20.340 --> 04:08:20.760
my entire life.

04:08:20.819 --> 04:08:23.399
We would never allow such linguistic

04:08:23.399 --> 04:08:24.780
imprecision in the ice kingdom.

04:08:24.840 --> 04:08:28.200
Kibli barked a delighted laugh, and did a

04:08:28.200 --> 04:08:28.799
loop in the air.

04:08:28.860 --> 04:08:31.500
And their shadowy conversation last night

04:08:31.500 --> 04:08:34.020
Kibli hadn't quite believed that pyrite

04:08:34.020 --> 04:08:34.920
could be an animus.

04:08:34.979 --> 04:08:37.319
He'd pointed out that Sky Wings hadn't

04:08:37.319 --> 04:08:39.540
had one in centuries, possibly as long as

04:08:39.540 --> 04:08:41.760
the ice wings, which was something Winter

04:08:41.760 --> 04:08:42.780
should have remembered for himself.

04:08:42.840 --> 04:08:45.959
But he had agreed that there was

04:08:45.959 --> 04:08:47.399
something not quite right about the

04:08:47.399 --> 04:08:48.659
skittish sky wing.

04:08:48.719 --> 04:08:51.299
Winter found himself oddly comforted by

04:08:51.299 --> 04:08:52.920
the idea that Kibley was watching her.

04:08:52.979 --> 04:08:55.620
If anyone could figure out pyrites

04:08:55.620 --> 04:08:57.659
secrets, and strangeness, it was probably

04:08:57.659 --> 04:08:58.260
Kibley.

04:08:58.319 --> 04:09:01.559
I wonder if this is how mudwings feel

04:09:01.559 --> 04:09:03.420
working in teams all the time.

04:09:03.479 --> 04:09:06.840
He'd read about the mudwing sibling bond

04:09:06.840 --> 04:09:09.239
and how they lived and fought and died

04:09:09.239 --> 04:09:09.540
together.

04:09:09.600 --> 04:09:13.319
Father said it made them weak, because a

04:09:13.319 --> 04:09:14.639
mudwing warrior would listen to his

04:09:14.639 --> 04:09:16.319
brothers and sisters instead of his

04:09:16.319 --> 04:09:16.860
commander.

04:09:16.920 --> 04:09:19.200
Mother said they'd always be worrying

04:09:19.200 --> 04:09:20.760
about what might happen to the soldier

04:09:20.760 --> 04:09:22.620
next to them, instead of focusing on the

04:09:22.620 --> 04:09:22.860
battle.

04:09:22.920 --> 04:09:25.440
That's why it should be easy to defeat

04:09:25.440 --> 04:09:26.760
the mud wings, they said.

04:09:26.879 --> 04:09:29.340
But it hadn't been that easy.

04:09:29.399 --> 04:09:31.920
As many, many battles had taught them

04:09:31.920 --> 04:09:33.120
over the years of the Great War.

04:09:33.239 --> 04:09:36.780
Maybe I'd rather have allies like Kibley

04:09:36.780 --> 04:09:39.299
and Moon, making their own decisions, and

04:09:39.299 --> 04:09:41.219
trusting each other than a commander

04:09:41.219 --> 04:09:42.120
telling me what to do.

04:09:42.180 --> 04:09:43.620
Winter thought.

04:09:43.739 --> 04:09:45.180
Was that treasonous?

04:09:45.239 --> 04:09:47.579
Did it make him less of an ice wing?

04:09:47.639 --> 04:09:50.100
If he kept having thoughts like these

04:09:50.159 --> 04:09:52.440
Would he be completely ruined by the time

04:09:52.440 --> 04:09:52.979
he got home?

04:09:53.040 --> 04:09:56.100
They reached the spire not long after

04:09:56.100 --> 04:09:58.559
that, and found the jagged mountain wall

04:09:58.559 --> 04:10:00.000
that matched Moon's drawing.

04:10:00.059 --> 04:10:02.940
It overlooked a hidden valley, where the

04:10:02.940 --> 04:10:05.280
3 waterfalls turned into rivers, that led

04:10:05.280 --> 04:10:06.780
into a crystal blue lake.

04:10:06.840 --> 04:10:09.059
The lake bent and squiggled around the

04:10:09.059 --> 04:10:11.819
edges, like a new hatched dragonette's

04:10:11.819 --> 04:10:12.540
drawing of a circle.

04:10:12.600 --> 04:10:14.879
Winter and the others landed on the

04:10:14.879 --> 04:10:17.040
northern shore, staring up at the eye

04:10:17.040 --> 04:10:19.020
shaped rock formation far overhead.

04:10:19.079 --> 04:10:21.180
I don't like it here.

04:10:21.239 --> 04:10:23.159
Kinkaju said it once.

04:10:23.219 --> 04:10:25.799
She shivered, flicking her tail and

04:10:25.799 --> 04:10:27.719
turning a sort of pale jade green.

04:10:27.780 --> 04:10:30.239
It feels like we're being watched.

04:10:30.299 --> 04:10:32.940
I mean, as if the mountains themselves

04:10:32.940 --> 04:10:33.899
are watching us.

04:10:34.020 --> 04:10:37.559
And their rivers are whispering about us

04:10:37.559 --> 04:10:38.879
Kibley said.

04:10:38.940 --> 04:10:41.219
Kinkachu thwacked him with one of her

04:10:41.219 --> 04:10:43.020
wings, and he jumped back, looking

04:10:43.020 --> 04:10:43.500
injured.

04:10:43.559 --> 04:10:46.739
I was agreeing with you, he yelped.

04:10:46.860 --> 04:10:49.920
Oh, well, try to sound less sarcastic

04:10:49.920 --> 04:10:52.020
next time, Kingachu scolded.

04:10:52.079 --> 04:10:54.959
My point is, it's creepy here.

04:10:55.020 --> 04:10:58.260
Moon glanced around to make sure Pyrite

04:10:58.260 --> 04:10:58.799
wasn't listening.

04:10:58.860 --> 04:11:01.799
The Sky Wing had waded into the lake and

04:11:01.799 --> 04:11:03.299
was scanning the sky and trees

04:11:03.299 --> 04:11:03.600
hopefully.

04:11:03.659 --> 04:11:06.899
Sounds like the perfect place for Scarlet

04:11:06.899 --> 04:11:08.760
to hide, she whispered.

04:11:08.819 --> 04:11:11.399
A sudden flutter of wings made them all

04:11:11.399 --> 04:11:13.379
spin around, but it was only a group of

04:11:13.379 --> 04:11:17.040
crows taking flight from a nearby tree, a

04:11:17.040 --> 04:11:17.940
murder of crows.

04:11:18.000 --> 04:11:19.979
Winter thought with a shiver.

04:11:20.040 --> 04:11:22.139
There's something over there.

04:11:22.200 --> 04:11:25.200
Pyrite said, waving her tail toward the

04:11:25.200 --> 04:11:26.100
far side of the lake.

04:11:26.159 --> 04:11:28.500
They hopped over the water, following her

04:11:28.500 --> 04:11:30.479
and found what appeared to be the

04:11:30.479 --> 04:11:31.860
wreckage of a rough structure.

04:11:31.920 --> 04:11:34.440
Long branches stripped of their leaves

04:11:34.440 --> 04:11:37.020
were scattered across the ground, and

04:11:37.020 --> 04:11:39.600
vines still tied in knots, lay in crust

04:11:39.600 --> 04:11:41.819
piles, as if they had been trampled by

04:11:41.819 --> 04:11:42.840
angry talons.

04:11:42.899 --> 04:11:45.299
The entire mess was covered in ripped up

04:11:45.299 --> 04:11:48.120
flower petals, rose and violet, and

04:11:48.120 --> 04:11:49.979
daffodil yellow shredded scraps

04:11:49.979 --> 04:11:50.520
everywhere.

04:11:50.579 --> 04:11:53.520
The only remaining intact piece was a

04:11:53.520 --> 04:11:56.280
canopy, woven from vines, that tilted

04:11:56.280 --> 04:11:58.200
lopsidedly in the tree overhead.

04:11:58.260 --> 04:12:00.000
Yikes!

04:12:00.059 --> 04:12:01.139
Kinkachu said.

04:12:01.200 --> 04:12:03.180
Someone was not pleased about something.

04:12:03.239 --> 04:12:07.020
Winter glanced over at Moon, for the

04:12:07.020 --> 04:12:09.659
9000th time that day, and found her

04:12:09.659 --> 04:12:11.219
frowning up at the ridge that loomed over

04:12:11.219 --> 04:12:11.459
them.

04:12:11.520 --> 04:12:13.500
What is it?

04:12:13.559 --> 04:12:13.979
he asked her.

04:12:14.040 --> 04:12:17.819
Just a feeling, she said. letting a

04:12:17.819 --> 04:12:19.319
shiver run out to her wingtips.

04:12:19.379 --> 04:12:21.180
I don't know exactly.

04:12:21.239 --> 04:12:24.120
I do know, said Kinkachu.

04:12:24.180 --> 04:12:26.879
Creepy being watched feeling, as I have

04:12:26.879 --> 04:12:27.540
already mentioned.

04:12:27.659 --> 04:12:31.200
Pyrite let out a gasp and pounced on a

04:12:31.200 --> 04:12:32.700
stack of broken twigs.

04:12:32.760 --> 04:12:35.280
Caught on the point of one of them was a

04:12:35.280 --> 04:12:36.659
dark orange scale.

04:12:36.719 --> 04:12:39.120
It's Scarlet's, she cried.

04:12:39.180 --> 04:12:40.379
I know it is.

04:12:40.440 --> 04:12:41.940
I'd recognize her color anywhere.

04:12:42.000 --> 04:12:44.219
She looked around desperately.

04:12:44.280 --> 04:12:45.299
But where is she?

04:12:45.360 --> 04:12:46.260
What happened here?

04:12:46.319 --> 04:12:48.420
Did something terrible happen to her?

04:12:48.479 --> 04:12:50.879
There's no sign of violence.

04:12:51.000 --> 04:12:53.700
Kibley said, moving one of the branches

04:12:53.700 --> 04:12:54.840
aside to look underneath.

04:12:54.899 --> 04:12:58.020
No blood, no claw marks on the

04:12:58.020 --> 04:12:58.680
surrounding trees.

04:12:58.739 --> 04:13:01.079
It looks more like she destroyed her

04:13:01.079 --> 04:13:03.420
shelter in a temper and left.

04:13:03.479 --> 04:13:05.819
Perhaps she somehow found out we were

04:13:05.819 --> 04:13:06.120
coming.

04:13:06.180 --> 04:13:07.500
Winter said.

04:13:07.559 --> 04:13:10.680
Dread crept slowly under his claws and up

04:13:10.680 --> 04:13:11.459
along his spine.

04:13:11.579 --> 04:13:12.780
What?

04:13:12.899 --> 04:13:14.040
How would she know that?

04:13:14.100 --> 04:13:16.139
Kingachu said in alarm.

04:13:16.200 --> 04:13:18.959
Winter, Kibli, and Moon all looked at

04:13:18.959 --> 04:13:19.559
pyrite.

04:13:19.620 --> 04:13:22.139
The orangey yellow sky wing, was

04:13:22.139 --> 04:13:24.420
overturning bits of foliage, and scraping

04:13:24.420 --> 04:13:26.340
through the moss, as though she expected

04:13:26.340 --> 04:13:28.020
to find Scarlet buried in it somewhere.

04:13:28.079 --> 04:13:30.899
Preoccupied with muttering and hissing

04:13:30.899 --> 04:13:31.500
and grumbling.

04:13:31.559 --> 04:13:33.059
She didn't notice their attention on

04:13:33.059 --> 04:13:33.299
her.

04:13:33.360 --> 04:13:36.299
Pyrite, Kibley said.

04:13:36.360 --> 04:13:39.540
Did you happen to see Queen Scarlet in

04:13:39.540 --> 04:13:40.319
your dream last night?

04:13:40.379 --> 04:13:43.139
She glanced at him and shook her head

04:13:43.139 --> 04:13:43.620
doubtfully.

04:13:43.680 --> 04:13:45.659
I don't think so.

04:13:45.719 --> 04:13:47.159
I don't really remember.

04:13:47.219 --> 04:13:50.700
I think I had a weird dream about snow

04:13:50.700 --> 04:13:52.979
maybe, but that happens whenever I sleep

04:13:52.979 --> 04:13:53.879
near Sirius, too.

04:13:54.000 --> 04:13:56.399
It's still possible.

04:13:56.459 --> 04:13:59.100
Moon said, even if she doesn't remember

04:13:59.100 --> 04:13:59.399
it.

04:13:59.459 --> 04:14:01.979
Scarlett could have interrogated her in

04:14:01.979 --> 04:14:03.959
her dream and found out what she was

04:14:03.959 --> 04:14:05.399
doing and where she was going.

04:14:05.459 --> 04:14:07.319
It doesn't matter.

04:14:07.379 --> 04:14:10.680
Winter said, what matters is that

04:14:10.680 --> 04:14:12.899
Scarlet's gone and so is Hailstorm.

04:14:12.959 --> 04:14:15.420
He ripped a large branch off the nearest

04:14:15.420 --> 04:14:17.520
tree, and hurled it into the forest.

04:14:17.579 --> 04:14:19.020
Gone.

04:14:19.139 --> 04:14:21.719
Their one chance of finding his brother.

04:14:21.780 --> 04:14:24.239
Scarlett could have taken him anywhere in

04:14:24.239 --> 04:14:25.020
Pyria by now.

04:14:25.079 --> 04:14:27.659
Or she could have killed him.

04:14:27.659 --> 04:14:30.479
If she figured out that winter was not, in

04:14:30.479 --> 04:14:32.639
fact, in the rainforest trying to

04:14:32.639 --> 04:14:33.840
assassinate glory for her.

04:14:33.899 --> 04:14:37.440
It was strange to Winter that Hailstorm's

04:14:37.440 --> 04:14:40.440
death could still hurt so much every time

04:14:40.440 --> 04:14:40.979
it happened.

04:14:41.040 --> 04:14:43.319
He would have thought the 1st time would

04:14:43.319 --> 04:14:43.739
be the worst.

04:14:43.799 --> 04:14:46.379
The night a spy had burst into the royal

04:14:46.379 --> 04:14:48.479
dining room, shouting that all of

04:14:48.479 --> 04:14:50.700
Scarlet's ice wing prisoners were dead.

04:14:51.000 --> 04:14:53.639
The Nightwings killed them all, he

04:14:53.639 --> 04:14:54.180
shrieked.

04:14:54.239 --> 04:14:55.500
It made no sense.

04:14:55.559 --> 04:14:58.260
Why would Nightwings enter Skywing

04:14:58.260 --> 04:14:59.459
territory to kill prisoners?

04:14:59.520 --> 04:15:02.819
But it felt true nonetheless, like

04:15:02.819 --> 04:15:04.079
something Nightwings would do.

04:15:04.139 --> 04:15:06.780
If they could have attacked the night

04:15:06.780 --> 04:15:09.120
kingdom that very moment, if they'd known

04:15:09.120 --> 04:15:10.739
where it was, they would have.

04:15:10.799 --> 04:15:13.860
All the ice wings in Queen Glacier's

04:15:13.860 --> 04:15:16.200
domain would have risen up to avenge

04:15:16.200 --> 04:15:17.819
their murdered comrades.

04:15:17.879 --> 04:15:20.459
Winter's parents hadn't spoken to him for

04:15:20.459 --> 04:15:22.920
a month after that report, and he didn't

04:15:22.920 --> 04:15:23.219
blame them.

04:15:23.280 --> 04:15:25.139
He didn't want to speak to himself

04:15:25.139 --> 04:15:25.559
either.

04:15:25.620 --> 04:15:28.139
He couldn't bear to see his own pathetic

04:15:28.139 --> 04:15:30.059
face, and the icy reflections

04:15:30.059 --> 04:15:30.479
everywhere.

04:15:30.540 --> 04:15:33.600
Until then, there'd been hope that they

04:15:33.600 --> 04:15:35.700
could still negotiate Hellstorm's release

04:15:35.700 --> 04:15:37.440
or carry out a rescue plan.

04:15:37.500 --> 04:15:39.180
But there was no hope.

04:15:39.239 --> 04:15:42.360
He was gone, as dead as all the other

04:15:42.360 --> 04:15:43.559
lost ice wings.

04:15:43.620 --> 04:15:46.559
And now winter had the same crumbling

04:15:46.559 --> 04:15:49.860
feeling inside, except instead of a snow

04:15:49.860 --> 04:15:51.000
drift caving in.

04:15:51.059 --> 04:15:54.000
This was a whole avalanche, cascading

04:15:54.000 --> 04:15:56.219
heavily down into his bones.

04:15:56.280 --> 04:15:58.260
This time it was even more his fault.

04:15:58.319 --> 04:16:00.780
He had failed his brother, and then

04:16:00.780 --> 04:16:02.879
failed him again, and again and again.

04:16:02.940 --> 04:16:04.680
Stop.

04:16:04.739 --> 04:16:08.340
Stop it, Kibley said, suddenly in front

04:16:08.340 --> 04:16:10.200
of Winter, taking his shoulders and

04:16:10.200 --> 04:16:10.799
shaking him.

04:16:10.860 --> 04:16:13.799
I see you going to the giving up place in

04:16:13.799 --> 04:16:14.100
your head.

04:16:14.219 --> 04:16:16.200
Get yourself out of there right now.

04:16:16.260 --> 04:16:19.079
We do not know he's dead any more than we

04:16:19.079 --> 04:16:19.799
did an hour ago.

04:16:19.860 --> 04:16:22.020
What we have to do is keep searching

04:16:22.020 --> 04:16:24.299
because he's only definitely dead.

04:16:24.360 --> 04:16:26.940
If we give up and sit here like moping

04:16:26.940 --> 04:16:27.420
camels.

04:16:27.479 --> 04:16:29.879
You are not allowed to mourn until you

04:16:29.879 --> 04:16:30.600
see a dead body.

04:16:30.659 --> 04:16:31.620
Do you understand me?

04:16:31.680 --> 04:16:34.079
What else am I supposed to do?

04:16:34.139 --> 04:16:35.399
Winter snarled.

04:16:35.459 --> 04:16:37.200
What's your next brilliant idea?

04:16:37.319 --> 04:16:38.879
How can he still be alive?

04:16:38.940 --> 04:16:41.520
Who are we talking about?

04:16:41.579 --> 04:16:44.340
Pyrite asked, wrinkling her snout.

04:16:44.399 --> 04:16:45.540
What he?

04:16:45.659 --> 04:16:46.500
I'm confused.

04:16:46.559 --> 04:16:50.159
We split up and searched the whole valley

04:16:50.159 --> 04:16:51.840
Kibley said, ignoring her.

04:16:51.899 --> 04:16:54.299
I'll go with Kinkaju, and you go with

04:16:54.299 --> 04:16:54.600
Moon.

04:16:54.719 --> 04:16:57.239
Look for clues about how long Scarlet was

04:16:57.239 --> 04:16:58.680
here. and where she might have gone.

04:16:58.739 --> 04:17:01.559
Look for a cave or something else that

04:17:01.559 --> 04:17:02.639
could have been used as a prison.

04:17:02.700 --> 04:17:05.459
Figure out where and how she actually

04:17:05.459 --> 04:17:07.739
kept him, and see if we can guess how

04:17:07.739 --> 04:17:08.700
she's transporting him.

04:17:08.700 --> 04:17:11.100
Were there other Skywings helping her?

04:17:11.159 --> 04:17:12.899
Or how else was he guarded?

04:17:12.959 --> 04:17:14.459
Is she traveling in a group?

04:17:14.520 --> 04:17:16.799
With a chained ice wing behind her?

04:17:16.920 --> 04:17:18.420
Because that's going to be a little

04:17:18.420 --> 04:17:19.620
obvious, don't you think?

04:17:19.680 --> 04:17:21.719
Look for messages she might have left

04:17:21.719 --> 04:17:22.079
behind.

04:17:22.139 --> 04:17:24.959
Look for anything that will actually tell

04:17:24.959 --> 04:17:25.500
us something.

04:17:25.559 --> 04:17:29.520
Winter stared at him, breathing so hard

04:17:29.520 --> 04:17:31.200
his tail spikes were rattling.

04:17:31.260 --> 04:17:34.079
Kibley stared back, deadly serious.

04:17:34.139 --> 04:17:38.159
What kind of moon's dazzled dragon would

04:17:38.159 --> 04:17:40.020
do all this for a stranger from a

04:17:40.020 --> 04:17:40.440
different tribe?

04:17:40.500 --> 04:17:42.600
Why hasn't he given up?

04:17:42.659 --> 04:17:44.940
Why isn't he letting me give up?

04:17:45.059 --> 04:17:47.879
When it means he could go back to Jade

04:17:47.879 --> 04:17:49.620
Mountain and carry on with his life.

04:17:49.680 --> 04:17:53.819
Come on, Kinkaju, Kibley said, flicking

04:17:53.819 --> 04:17:54.540
his tail ladder.

04:17:54.600 --> 04:17:56.819
We'll take the valley south of the lake.

04:17:56.879 --> 04:17:58.379
The rest of you go north.

04:17:58.440 --> 04:18:02.700
You bet, Kingachu said, with ridiculous

04:18:02.700 --> 04:18:03.479
enthusiasm.

04:18:03.540 --> 04:18:06.360
He's letting me go with Moon.

04:18:06.420 --> 04:18:10.139
Winter realized, on purpose, even though

04:18:10.139 --> 04:18:11.819
he wants to be with her as badly as I

04:18:11.819 --> 04:18:12.059
do.

04:18:12.120 --> 04:18:13.440
But he knows.

04:18:13.500 --> 04:18:16.739
Or he hopes that searching with her will

04:18:16.739 --> 04:18:17.280
keep me going.

04:18:17.340 --> 04:18:19.620
Am I that obvious?

04:18:19.680 --> 04:18:23.700
I'll go with Winter, Pyrite declared.

04:18:23.760 --> 04:18:26.819
Not that anyone asked, but I figure

04:18:26.819 --> 04:18:27.780
that's okay, right?

04:18:27.840 --> 04:18:30.239
Although, what are we looking for?

04:18:30.299 --> 04:18:33.959
Signs of Scarlet being here, Winter told

04:18:33.959 --> 04:18:34.139
her.

04:18:34.260 --> 04:18:36.840
Anything that looks like the detritus of

04:18:36.840 --> 04:18:37.319
dragons.

04:18:37.379 --> 04:18:40.319
She accepted this with a puzzled shrug.

04:18:40.440 --> 04:18:43.319
He led the way back over the lake, and

04:18:43.319 --> 04:18:45.719
they started into the woods, methodically

04:18:45.719 --> 04:18:47.879
covering every square of ground all the

04:18:47.879 --> 04:18:49.379
way back to the mountain cliff ahead.

04:18:49.440 --> 04:18:52.319
Winter's eyes raked the dirt and trees

04:18:52.319 --> 04:18:55.079
and shrubs and streams, and all the small

04:18:55.079 --> 04:18:55.920
corners around them.

04:18:55.979 --> 04:18:58.200
Can you hear anyone?

04:18:58.260 --> 04:19:01.260
He whispered to Moon, when Pyrite was out

04:19:01.260 --> 04:19:01.739
of earshot.

04:19:01.799 --> 04:19:03.000
She shook her head.

04:19:03.120 --> 04:19:04.920
Only pyrite.

04:19:04.979 --> 04:19:05.940
Sorry, Winter.

04:19:06.059 --> 04:19:08.159
Kibble had a point though.

04:19:08.219 --> 04:19:10.920
Where had Scarlett been keeping Hailstorm

04:19:10.920 --> 04:19:12.059
for the last 2 years?

04:19:12.120 --> 04:19:13.379
Was he guarded?

04:19:13.440 --> 04:19:14.340
Chained up?

04:19:14.399 --> 04:19:16.440
Had he been moved here from somewhere

04:19:16.440 --> 04:19:16.799
else?

04:19:16.860 --> 04:19:19.860
Who had fed him and kept him alive while

04:19:19.860 --> 04:19:21.600
she was trapped in Burns stronghold?

04:19:21.659 --> 04:19:23.639
How did she keep him from trying to

04:19:23.639 --> 04:19:23.879
escape?

04:19:23.940 --> 04:19:26.459
Their brother Winter knew?

04:19:26.520 --> 04:19:28.379
Would have fought tooth and claw to be

04:19:28.379 --> 04:19:28.559
free.

04:19:28.680 --> 04:19:30.959
If he'd been imprisoned anywhere near

04:19:30.959 --> 04:19:31.379
here?

04:19:31.440 --> 04:19:32.520
There should be clues.

04:19:32.639 --> 04:19:35.340
Claw marks scored along the walls of a

04:19:35.340 --> 04:19:38.040
cave, or a tree with indentations of

04:19:38.040 --> 04:19:39.540
chains crushed into its trunk.

04:19:39.600 --> 04:19:41.639
Or most likely of all.

04:19:41.700 --> 04:19:44.159
Something hailstorm had used his frost

04:19:44.159 --> 04:19:44.639
breath on.

04:19:44.700 --> 04:19:46.979
They should look for signs of something

04:19:46.979 --> 04:19:47.819
that had been frozen.

04:19:47.879 --> 04:19:49.739
But there was nothing.

04:19:49.799 --> 04:19:52.079
They spent their rest of the daylight

04:19:52.079 --> 04:19:53.819
searching, with no success.

04:19:53.879 --> 04:19:56.520
The only sign of life in the whole valley

04:19:56.520 --> 04:19:58.860
was scarlet's scale in the destroyed

04:19:58.860 --> 04:19:59.340
structure.

04:19:59.399 --> 04:20:03.360
Otherwise, the grass waved peacefully, and

04:20:03.360 --> 04:20:06.000
the trees quietly filled with fruit, and

04:20:06.000 --> 04:20:07.739
it seemed as though no talons had ever

04:20:07.739 --> 04:20:08.940
disturbed the stillness.

04:20:08.940 --> 04:20:11.819
Winter couldn't imagine a prison here

04:20:11.819 --> 04:20:12.239
anywhere.

04:20:12.299 --> 04:20:14.940
There were no suitable caves for keeping

04:20:14.940 --> 04:20:17.700
prisoners in, at least not close to the

04:20:17.700 --> 04:20:18.180
valley floor.

04:20:18.239 --> 04:20:22.139
Perhaps hailstorm's prison is higher up

04:20:22.139 --> 04:20:22.680
in the mountains.

04:20:22.739 --> 04:20:25.260
Winter speculated around their campfire

04:20:25.260 --> 04:20:25.620
that night.

04:20:25.680 --> 04:20:28.020
He was keeping his distance from the

04:20:28.020 --> 04:20:28.860
flames.

04:20:28.920 --> 04:20:31.379
The heat made his scales feel all melty

04:20:31.379 --> 04:20:31.920
and sticky.

04:20:31.979 --> 04:20:35.219
We'll search up there tomorrow, Moon

04:20:35.219 --> 04:20:35.700
said.

04:20:35.760 --> 04:20:37.139
We'll find something.

04:20:37.260 --> 04:20:38.520
She shivered.

04:20:38.639 --> 04:20:40.500
It's so quiet out here.

04:20:40.620 --> 04:20:43.860
Winter actually found it distractingly

04:20:43.860 --> 04:20:45.719
noisy compared to the ice kingdom.

04:20:45.780 --> 04:20:48.840
For one thing, it sounded like 2 rival

04:20:48.840 --> 04:20:50.940
cricket symphonies were competing at top

04:20:50.940 --> 04:20:51.659
volume.

04:20:51.719 --> 04:20:53.760
The owls were hooting so much.

04:20:53.819 --> 04:20:56.100
It was a wonder they had time to fit prey

04:20:56.100 --> 04:20:57.000
in their mouths as well.

04:20:57.059 --> 04:21:00.180
Things flapped overhead, and small

04:21:00.180 --> 04:21:01.559
splashes came from the lake.

04:21:01.620 --> 04:21:05.399
The night felt extremely populated.

04:21:05.459 --> 04:21:08.879
Then it occurred to him that Moon might

04:21:08.879 --> 04:21:11.100
be talking about the noise inside her

04:21:11.100 --> 04:21:11.280
head.

04:21:11.340 --> 04:21:14.399
With all of them wearing Skyfire, the

04:21:14.399 --> 04:21:15.899
only voice she could hear and there was

04:21:15.899 --> 04:21:18.479
pyrites, presumably still treading in its

04:21:18.479 --> 04:21:19.440
odd, boring circle.

04:21:19.559 --> 04:21:22.500
That must be strange for her.

04:21:22.620 --> 04:21:26.100
He realized, to give that all up and

04:21:26.100 --> 04:21:27.120
trust us with her secret.

04:21:27.180 --> 04:21:29.579
Would any other night wing do that?

04:21:29.639 --> 04:21:32.459
Would any other dragon empire do that?

04:21:32.520 --> 04:21:35.159
He wanted to believe that he would.

04:21:35.219 --> 04:21:38.040
That if he had the power to read minds

04:21:38.040 --> 04:21:40.020
he'd tell other dragons right away

04:21:40.020 --> 04:21:42.059
instead of invading their minds in

04:21:42.059 --> 04:21:42.420
secret.

04:21:42.479 --> 04:21:43.979
But would he really?

04:21:44.040 --> 04:21:47.280
With a rare weapon like that, wouldn't he

04:21:47.280 --> 04:21:48.120
be tempted to use it?

04:21:48.180 --> 04:21:51.420
That night, he let Moon take the 1st

04:21:51.420 --> 04:21:51.719
watch.

04:21:51.780 --> 04:21:55.079
All he wanted to do was turn off the

04:21:55.079 --> 04:21:57.239
world and his brain for a while.

04:21:57.299 --> 04:22:00.479
He gazed up at the shadowy, hulking forms

04:22:00.479 --> 04:22:02.819
of the mountains, as sleep drifted

04:22:02.819 --> 04:22:05.340
through him, slowly leading him into odd

04:22:05.340 --> 04:22:07.739
half dreams about his brother in a cave

04:22:07.739 --> 04:22:10.500
up there, watching the valley below for 2

04:22:10.500 --> 04:22:11.219
lonely years.

04:22:11.340 --> 04:22:14.819
He wasn't sure how much time had passed

04:22:14.819 --> 04:22:17.340
wandering through a half seen labyrinth

04:22:17.340 --> 04:22:19.379
of stone passages, when he turned a

04:22:19.379 --> 04:22:22.139
corner, and suddenly the dream sharpened

04:22:22.139 --> 04:22:22.680
around the edges.

04:22:22.739 --> 04:22:26.940
An orange dragon stood before him, wearing

04:22:26.940 --> 04:22:29.639
veils of dark smoke that poured from her

04:22:29.639 --> 04:22:32.040
snout, and from the fire beside her.

04:22:32.100 --> 04:22:35.579
Blood and ice dripped across her face and

04:22:35.579 --> 04:22:38.520
wings until she shifted, and he realized

04:22:38.520 --> 04:22:41.399
it was only rubies and diamonds embedded

04:22:41.399 --> 04:22:43.500
in her scales, catching the firelight.

04:22:43.559 --> 04:22:47.280
She pinned him with her yellow gaze, sharp

04:22:47.280 --> 04:22:47.760
as talons.

04:22:47.879 --> 04:22:49.860
Tell me who you are.

04:22:49.920 --> 04:22:51.239
She ordered.

04:22:51.299 --> 04:22:52.920
Don't you know?

04:22:52.920 --> 04:22:53.579
he asked.

04:22:53.639 --> 04:22:55.020
I know who you are.

04:22:55.139 --> 04:22:57.840
Very flattering.

04:22:57.899 --> 04:23:00.360
She said, in a slithering voice.

04:23:00.479 --> 04:23:03.899
So perhaps, then you can also gather why

04:23:03.899 --> 04:23:06.600
I am not pleased to see you.

04:23:06.719 --> 04:23:10.139
She took a step toward him, and the dream

04:23:10.139 --> 04:23:11.399
cave trembled around them.

04:23:11.459 --> 04:23:14.579
Something wavered across her face, like a

04:23:14.579 --> 04:23:16.860
mask, slipping to reveal a glimpse of

04:23:16.860 --> 04:23:19.020
another disfigured face underneath.

04:23:19.079 --> 04:23:22.680
You're a long way from the rainforest

04:23:22.680 --> 04:23:24.000
prince of ice.

04:23:24.059 --> 04:23:26.579
There's no one who needs killing around

04:23:26.579 --> 04:23:27.420
where you are now.

04:23:27.479 --> 04:23:31.079
He was silent for a beat too long, and

04:23:31.079 --> 04:23:31.860
she began to laugh.

04:23:31.920 --> 04:23:34.260
Oh, you mean me?

04:23:34.379 --> 04:23:35.459
She said.

04:23:35.520 --> 04:23:37.139
Is that your clever plan?

04:23:37.200 --> 04:23:39.719
Find the most deadly queen Empirea?

04:23:39.780 --> 04:23:41.760
Kill her and take back your brother?

04:23:41.879 --> 04:23:43.920
She leaned toward winter.

04:23:43.979 --> 04:23:46.079
Every muscle taut with glee.

04:23:46.200 --> 04:23:48.420
Even if you could kill me.

04:23:48.540 --> 04:23:50.940
You would never find your lost ice

04:23:50.940 --> 04:23:51.479
swing.

04:23:51.540 --> 04:23:52.739
Never.

04:23:52.799 --> 04:23:56.399
The prison I've got him in is far too

04:23:56.399 --> 04:23:57.239
clever for that.

04:23:57.299 --> 04:23:59.579
Where is he?

04:23:59.639 --> 04:24:00.840
Winter demanded.

04:24:00.899 --> 04:24:01.979
Is he all right?

04:24:02.040 --> 04:24:05.879
He was, all right, she said.

04:24:05.940 --> 04:24:08.760
Her face twisted in a strange smirk of

04:24:08.760 --> 04:24:10.319
triumph and fury.

04:24:10.379 --> 04:24:13.319
But he won't be after this conversation.

04:24:13.379 --> 04:24:16.620
I gave your sister one last chance.

04:24:16.680 --> 04:24:19.979
She swore to me that you would kill

04:24:19.979 --> 04:24:20.520
glory.

04:24:20.579 --> 04:24:23.100
And yet, here you are.

04:24:23.159 --> 04:24:26.520
And I know that backstabbing face melting

04:24:26.520 --> 04:24:27.959
queen still lives.

04:24:28.020 --> 04:24:32.219
Queen Scarlet side hugely, and shook her

04:24:32.219 --> 04:24:34.139
head with a mockingly disappointed

04:24:34.139 --> 04:24:34.680
expression.

04:24:34.739 --> 04:24:38.579
I suppose if I won more dragon's dead.

04:24:38.639 --> 04:24:40.920
I'll just have to kill someone myself.

04:24:40.979 --> 04:24:42.780
And let's see.

04:24:42.899 --> 04:24:44.760
Who do I have?

04:24:44.819 --> 04:24:47.100
Right in my clutches.

04:24:47.159 --> 04:24:50.399
Don't kill him, Winter cried.

04:24:50.459 --> 04:24:51.659
What else do you want?

04:24:51.780 --> 04:24:54.180
Queen Glacier's treasury is vast.

04:24:54.239 --> 04:24:56.399
She would pay you his weight in diamonds

04:24:56.399 --> 04:24:57.239
for his safe return.

04:24:57.299 --> 04:24:59.219
Scarlett snorted.

04:24:59.280 --> 04:25:00.780
What use?

04:25:00.840 --> 04:25:02.340
Are diamonds to me.

04:25:02.399 --> 04:25:05.520
If I want something, I don't pay for it.

04:25:05.579 --> 04:25:06.840
I take it.

04:25:06.899 --> 04:25:10.020
And right now, groveling prince.

04:25:10.079 --> 04:25:11.520
I only want 2 things.

04:25:11.579 --> 04:25:13.500
My throne back.

04:25:13.500 --> 04:25:15.540
And vengeance.

04:25:15.659 --> 04:25:19.920
Her eyes narrowed to slits, and her tail

04:25:19.920 --> 04:25:21.000
lashed dangerously.

04:25:21.059 --> 04:25:24.239
Here's some interesting information for

04:25:24.239 --> 04:25:24.600
you.

04:25:24.659 --> 04:25:28.020
Your queen doesn't want her nephew bag as

04:25:28.020 --> 04:25:28.799
badly as you think.

04:25:28.860 --> 04:25:32.340
I visited her dreams with a proposal.

04:25:32.399 --> 04:25:36.059
Help me drag my conniving daughter off my

04:25:36.059 --> 04:25:37.680
throne, and she could have him.

04:25:37.799 --> 04:25:40.739
Would you believe she turned me down?

04:25:40.799 --> 04:25:44.700
She said he'd been mourned already, and

04:25:44.700 --> 04:25:47.579
her duty was to the yet unlost lives of

04:25:47.579 --> 04:25:48.059
her subjects.

04:25:48.180 --> 04:25:50.459
Doesn't that make you furious?

04:25:50.579 --> 04:25:52.559
Ice dragon?

04:25:52.620 --> 04:25:55.440
Winter stared down at his claws.

04:25:55.500 --> 04:25:56.879
Was Scarlet lying?

04:25:57.000 --> 04:25:59.280
Had she really tried to negotiate with

04:25:59.280 --> 04:26:00.059
Queen Glacier?

04:26:00.059 --> 04:26:02.219
And had his queen decided to leave

04:26:02.219 --> 04:26:03.360
Hailstorm to die?

04:26:03.420 --> 04:26:06.780
He realized, he could believe it.

04:26:06.840 --> 04:26:09.899
The ice wings had just survived 20 years

04:26:09.899 --> 04:26:12.899
of war over another tribe's throne, and

04:26:12.899 --> 04:26:15.059
with nothing to show for it, except too

04:26:15.059 --> 04:26:16.020
many dead warriors.

04:26:16.079 --> 04:26:18.840
Queen Glacier would not be eager to

04:26:18.840 --> 04:26:20.700
plunge them back into another conflict

04:26:20.700 --> 04:26:23.219
especially on behalf of a dragon she

04:26:23.219 --> 04:26:25.440
couldn't trust, and wouldn't want to see

04:26:25.440 --> 04:26:27.000
in charge of the sky kingdom again

04:26:27.000 --> 04:26:27.420
anyway.

04:26:27.479 --> 04:26:32.760
So, you're his only hope.

04:26:32.819 --> 04:26:36.479
Scarlett taunted him, or at least you

04:26:36.479 --> 04:26:37.260
were.

04:26:37.500 --> 04:26:38.819
It's all over now, though.

04:26:38.879 --> 04:26:42.540
I can see that you're far too useless to

04:26:42.540 --> 04:26:43.559
kill anyone for me.

04:26:43.620 --> 04:26:47.639
My only remaining pleasure is watching

04:26:47.639 --> 04:26:50.159
your face, as I tell you, your brother

04:26:50.159 --> 04:26:54.000
will be dead by morning. winter's head

04:26:54.000 --> 04:26:54.479
jerked up.

04:26:54.540 --> 04:26:55.860
Wait.

04:26:55.920 --> 04:26:58.860
He backed away from Scarlet, blinking

04:26:58.860 --> 04:26:59.280
rapidly.

04:26:59.340 --> 04:27:01.079
I have to wake up.

04:27:01.139 --> 04:27:04.379
He dug his claws ferociously into one

04:27:04.379 --> 04:27:05.520
shoulder, but felt nothing.

04:27:05.639 --> 04:27:08.520
The dream cave still held him, and

04:27:08.520 --> 04:27:10.559
Scarlet's yellow eyes watched with

04:27:10.559 --> 04:27:12.059
menacing amusement.

04:27:12.120 --> 04:27:15.719
Perhaps you'd like to hear how I plan to

04:27:15.719 --> 04:27:17.159
kill him, she mused.

04:27:17.219 --> 04:27:20.760
I could slowly burn him to death.

04:27:20.819 --> 04:27:23.819
That would be lengthy and painful.

04:27:23.879 --> 04:27:27.239
Winter turned and stumbled out of the

04:27:27.239 --> 04:27:27.600
cave.

04:27:27.659 --> 04:27:29.340
Was there a way out through the

04:27:29.340 --> 04:27:29.760
passages?

04:27:29.819 --> 04:27:32.520
He tried to visualize, snapping awake

04:27:32.520 --> 04:27:35.280
opening his eyes, sitting up and finding

04:27:35.280 --> 04:27:36.000
himself in the valley.

04:27:36.059 --> 04:27:37.680
It wasn't working.

04:27:37.739 --> 04:27:40.799
Scarlet's mocking laugh followed him

04:27:40.799 --> 04:27:43.079
through the narrow maze, echoing off

04:27:43.079 --> 04:27:45.239
smooth stone walls that all looked the

04:27:45.239 --> 04:27:45.479
same.

04:27:45.540 --> 04:27:49.559
Maybe, I'll gouge out his eyes 1st.

04:27:49.620 --> 04:27:50.819
She called.

04:27:50.879 --> 04:27:53.639
Maybe all stuff live goats into his

04:27:53.639 --> 04:27:55.260
throat until he suffocates.

04:27:55.319 --> 04:27:58.739
Winter stopped running and fumbled for

04:27:58.739 --> 04:27:59.159
his ankle.

04:27:59.219 --> 04:28:01.620
He felt the weight of the Skyfire pouch

04:28:01.620 --> 04:28:03.180
there, solid and heavy.

04:28:03.239 --> 04:28:05.940
Don't you want to beg?

04:28:06.059 --> 04:28:07.440
Scarlet shrieked.

04:28:07.500 --> 04:28:09.959
Don't you want to offer to do anything

04:28:09.959 --> 04:28:10.860
for me?

04:28:10.920 --> 04:28:13.500
What have I told you to kill the rain

04:28:13.500 --> 04:28:14.219
wing who's with you?

04:28:14.280 --> 04:28:16.379
What else could you throw at my feet?

04:28:16.440 --> 04:28:17.819
Desperate prince.

04:28:17.940 --> 04:28:21.059
With trembling claws, he ripped to the

04:28:21.059 --> 04:28:22.799
cord, binding the pouch to his scales.

04:28:22.860 --> 04:28:25.440
Finally, he yanked it free and dropped it

04:28:25.440 --> 04:28:25.799
on the ground.

04:28:25.860 --> 04:28:28.860
Moon, he yelled in his mind.

04:28:28.920 --> 04:28:30.000
Wake me up.

04:28:30.059 --> 04:28:31.440
Wake me up right now.

04:28:31.559 --> 04:28:35.819
Barely a moment later, he felt talons on

04:28:35.819 --> 04:28:37.860
his shoulders, shaking and shaking him

04:28:37.860 --> 04:28:40.979
until finally, the dream world tore away

04:28:40.979 --> 04:28:43.079
like wet paper, and he was sitting up on

04:28:43.079 --> 04:28:45.899
the grass, eyes popping open, wide

04:28:45.899 --> 04:28:46.260
awake.

04:28:46.319 --> 04:28:49.079
Moon let go of him and took a shaky

04:28:49.079 --> 04:28:49.319
breath.

04:28:49.379 --> 04:28:50.760
Are you all right?

04:28:50.819 --> 04:28:51.959
She whispered.

04:28:52.020 --> 04:28:54.540
Behind her was Kibley, rubbing his eyes

04:28:54.540 --> 04:28:55.200
sleepily.

04:28:55.260 --> 04:28:57.959
They all look down at the Skyfire pouch.

04:28:58.020 --> 04:29:00.840
Winter had really managed to tear it off

04:29:00.840 --> 04:29:03.420
in his sleep, and now it lay between them

04:29:03.420 --> 04:29:05.159
leaving Winter's mind exposed.

04:29:05.219 --> 04:29:08.459
Moon immediately picked it up and handed

04:29:08.459 --> 04:29:08.879
it to him.

04:29:08.940 --> 04:29:11.639
Tell me what happened, she said.

04:29:11.700 --> 04:29:15.780
Queen Scarlet was in my dream, Winter

04:29:15.780 --> 04:29:17.520
said, tying the pouch back on.

04:29:17.639 --> 04:29:20.879
Well, no wonder, Kibley said.

04:29:20.940 --> 04:29:22.739
You've been thinking about her all day.

04:29:22.799 --> 04:29:25.079
No, Winter said.

04:29:25.200 --> 04:29:27.180
I mean, it was really her.

04:29:27.239 --> 04:29:29.159
Dream visiting me.

04:29:29.280 --> 04:29:32.100
They both got it at the same moment.

04:29:32.159 --> 04:29:36.180
That means she's seen you, Kibley said.

04:29:36.239 --> 04:29:39.059
Completely awake now, his tail curled up

04:29:39.059 --> 04:29:39.959
into attack position.

04:29:40.020 --> 04:29:43.020
In order to visit your dream, she must

04:29:43.020 --> 04:29:45.659
have seen you, today, or she would have

04:29:45.659 --> 04:29:46.200
done it sooner.

04:29:46.260 --> 04:29:49.500
Scarlet saw you today.

04:29:49.559 --> 04:29:50.819
Moon echoed.

04:29:50.879 --> 04:29:53.399
She jumped to her feet, turning in a

04:29:53.399 --> 04:29:56.399
circle, in this valley, where we are

04:29:56.399 --> 04:29:57.180
right now.

04:29:57.239 --> 04:30:02.219
Exactly, Winter said, which means Scarlet

04:30:02.219 --> 04:30:03.659
is somewhere close by.

04:30:03.780 --> 04:30:08.340
Chapter 14.

04:30:08.579 --> 04:30:12.299
A breeze whipped through the trees

04:30:12.360 --> 04:30:14.760
hurtling wet droplets over their wings

04:30:14.760 --> 04:30:17.520
below embers of the fire made a hissing

04:30:17.520 --> 04:30:20.219
sound, and pyrite shifted in her sleep

04:30:20.219 --> 04:30:20.700
with a grunt.

04:30:20.819 --> 04:30:24.180
Scarlet is close enough to watch this

04:30:24.180 --> 04:30:24.540
valley.

04:30:24.659 --> 04:30:26.159
Moon said again.

04:30:26.219 --> 04:30:28.020
Kingachu was right.

04:30:28.079 --> 04:30:29.700
We were being spied on.

04:30:29.760 --> 04:30:33.180
She said, my brother will die in the

04:30:33.180 --> 04:30:34.739
morning, Winter said.

04:30:34.799 --> 04:30:37.620
He took a deep breath, trying to shut up

04:30:37.620 --> 04:30:38.520
his hammering heart.

04:30:38.579 --> 04:30:40.680
She said, now that she's seen me.

04:30:40.739 --> 04:30:42.780
She knows I'm not going to kill anyone

04:30:42.780 --> 04:30:43.379
for her.

04:30:43.440 --> 04:30:45.120
How could she tell?

04:30:45.120 --> 04:30:46.620
just by looking at me.

04:30:46.680 --> 04:30:50.399
That's a good thing that you're not that

04:30:50.399 --> 04:30:51.239
kind of dragon.

04:30:51.299 --> 04:30:53.760
Moon reminded him, nudging his side.

04:30:53.879 --> 04:30:56.100
Did you see any clues?

04:30:56.159 --> 04:30:59.100
Kibley asked, about where she is now.

04:30:59.159 --> 04:31:00.899
Winter shook his head.

04:31:00.959 --> 04:31:03.479
We were in a cave in my dream.

04:31:03.540 --> 04:31:06.000
It looked like any other cave.

04:31:06.059 --> 04:31:08.100
Underground or in a mountain somewhere

04:31:08.100 --> 04:31:12.239
except at one point, her face seemed to

04:31:12.239 --> 04:31:13.139
change in front of me.

04:31:13.260 --> 04:31:16.739
And the face I saw underneath, apart from

04:31:16.739 --> 04:31:19.500
being horrible, It looked like it was lit

04:31:19.500 --> 04:31:20.280
by moonlight.

04:31:20.340 --> 04:31:23.819
Kimley looked up at the sky, his black

04:31:23.819 --> 04:31:25.500
eyes darting from the moons to the

04:31:25.500 --> 04:31:25.860
peaks.

04:31:25.920 --> 04:31:28.440
Half the mountain range is in shadow

04:31:28.440 --> 04:31:28.860
right now.

04:31:28.920 --> 04:31:29.879
He said.

04:31:29.940 --> 04:31:32.280
We fly to the other side and search.

04:31:32.340 --> 04:31:34.379
Everywhere in view of this valley.

04:31:34.500 --> 04:31:35.459
We go now.

04:31:35.520 --> 04:31:38.879
Moon took a step toward Kinkachu and

04:31:38.879 --> 04:31:40.139
Winter reached out to stop her.

04:31:40.200 --> 04:31:43.139
The rain wing slept peacefully, a half

04:31:43.139 --> 04:31:46.139
smile on her face, her scales dappled in

04:31:46.139 --> 04:31:48.540
silver splotches, like the moonlight, that

04:31:48.540 --> 04:31:49.799
fell through the leaves and across her

04:31:49.799 --> 04:31:50.159
wings.

04:31:50.219 --> 04:31:53.340
This is what your queen said not to do.

04:31:53.459 --> 04:31:56.520
Winter reminded Moon in a low whisper.

04:31:56.579 --> 04:31:58.799
We're going to confront Scarlet.

04:31:58.860 --> 04:32:01.200
She could rip Kinkaju apart in a

04:32:01.200 --> 04:32:01.559
heartbeat.

04:32:01.680 --> 04:32:04.020
Glory would want her to stay out of it.

04:32:04.079 --> 04:32:05.100
And you too.

04:32:05.159 --> 04:32:09.360
I'm not staying out of it, Moon said

04:32:09.360 --> 04:32:09.840
fiercely.

04:32:09.899 --> 04:32:12.000
You need me if you're going to find her.

04:32:12.059 --> 04:32:13.379
I'm not going to hide.

04:32:13.440 --> 04:32:15.540
I don't do that anymore.

04:32:15.600 --> 04:32:18.600
Then keep at least half your promise to

04:32:18.600 --> 04:32:19.020
your queen.

04:32:19.079 --> 04:32:20.219
Winter said.

04:32:20.340 --> 04:32:22.559
Leave Kinkachu asleep and safe.

04:32:22.620 --> 04:32:26.219
He's right, Kibley said.

04:32:26.280 --> 04:32:28.680
Glory would definitely not want you both

04:32:28.680 --> 04:32:30.120
marching off to find Scarlet.

04:32:30.180 --> 04:32:33.000
Moon blew out a breath that ruffled the

04:32:33.000 --> 04:32:33.959
tree branches around them.

04:32:34.020 --> 04:32:37.799
She's going to kill me, she whispered

04:32:37.799 --> 04:32:39.659
glancing back at her sleeping friend.

04:32:39.719 --> 04:32:43.200
Better that, then Scarlet killing her.

04:32:43.319 --> 04:32:44.639
Winter pointed out.

04:32:44.700 --> 04:32:47.219
All right, Moon said.

04:32:47.280 --> 04:32:48.360
She shook her head.

04:32:48.420 --> 04:32:49.680
All right.

04:32:49.739 --> 04:32:50.399
Let's go.

04:32:50.459 --> 04:32:53.280
Winter was in the sky by the end of her

04:32:53.280 --> 04:32:55.620
sentence, winging toward the eye shaped

04:32:55.620 --> 04:32:56.340
rock formation.

04:32:56.399 --> 04:32:59.159
From there, they could sweep south and

04:32:59.159 --> 04:33:00.840
around the circumference of the valley

04:33:00.840 --> 04:33:02.579
checking the mountain crags and

04:33:02.579 --> 04:33:03.120
crannies.

04:33:03.180 --> 04:33:06.000
It was a lot of distance to cover, and

04:33:06.000 --> 04:33:07.860
perhaps Scarlet had flown off as soon as

04:33:07.860 --> 04:33:10.259
she saw him, ending up 100s of miles away

04:33:10.259 --> 04:33:10.680
by now.

04:33:10.740 --> 04:33:13.680
But now that he'd seen her thirst for

04:33:13.680 --> 04:33:16.319
vengeance firsthand, he had a strong

04:33:16.319 --> 04:33:18.240
suspicion she was still nearby.

04:33:18.299 --> 04:33:21.299
She'd want to watch Winter's despair the

04:33:21.299 --> 04:33:23.520
next morning, and whatever panicked

04:33:23.520 --> 04:33:24.599
action he took next.

04:33:24.659 --> 04:33:28.259
So if she was close, and if Moon could

04:33:28.259 --> 04:33:30.959
catch Scarlet's mind, maybe they had a

04:33:30.959 --> 04:33:33.360
chance to stop her while Hailstorm was

04:33:33.360 --> 04:33:33.659
still alive.

04:33:33.720 --> 04:33:37.740
If he even is still alive, and she isn't

04:33:37.740 --> 04:33:38.639
just torturing us.

04:33:38.700 --> 04:33:43.080
Let moon go first, Kibley said, soaring

04:33:43.080 --> 04:33:43.799
up beside him.

04:33:43.860 --> 04:33:46.740
No offense, but you're glowing like a 4th

04:33:46.740 --> 04:33:47.400
moon up here.

04:33:47.459 --> 04:33:49.799
And I'm not exactly the most shadowy

04:33:49.799 --> 04:33:50.520
dragon myself.

04:33:50.580 --> 04:33:53.099
She's practically invisible in the night

04:33:53.099 --> 04:33:53.580
sky.

04:33:53.639 --> 04:33:55.799
That's kind of the point of our whole

04:33:55.799 --> 04:33:56.580
tribe after all.

04:33:56.700 --> 04:34:00.000
Winter twisted around, and had to admit

04:34:00.000 --> 04:34:01.799
to himself that Kibley was right.

04:34:01.860 --> 04:34:04.439
It took him a minute to even see Moon

04:34:04.439 --> 04:34:04.919
behind him.

04:34:04.979 --> 04:34:08.040
She faded perfectly into the dark, and

04:34:08.040 --> 04:34:10.319
her silver scales, looked exactly like

04:34:10.319 --> 04:34:11.099
distant stars.

04:34:11.159 --> 04:34:13.740
But he wanted to lead the way.

04:34:13.860 --> 04:34:17.279
He wanted to find Scarlet 1st and sink

04:34:17.279 --> 04:34:18.479
his claws into her neck.

04:34:18.540 --> 04:34:20.819
He wanted to be the one who rescued

04:34:20.819 --> 04:34:21.599
Hailstorm.

04:34:21.659 --> 04:34:24.599
The hero who brought him back, the dragon

04:34:24.599 --> 04:34:26.279
who surpassed all his parents

04:34:26.279 --> 04:34:26.939
expectations.

04:34:27.000 --> 04:34:29.520
His wings wavered in the air.

04:34:29.580 --> 04:34:33.180
His luminous, treacherous wings, which

04:34:33.180 --> 04:34:34.979
reflected the moonlight to anyone below

04:34:34.979 --> 04:34:36.360
who might chance to look up.

04:34:36.419 --> 04:34:39.359
This is not about your place in the

04:34:39.359 --> 04:34:39.839
rankings.

04:34:39.900 --> 04:34:42.240
It's not about what mother and father and

04:34:42.240 --> 04:34:43.080
the queen think of you.

04:34:43.200 --> 04:34:45.599
It's about saving Hillstorm.

04:34:45.659 --> 04:34:49.080
He fell back, lifting up into the cloud

04:34:49.080 --> 04:34:49.439
cover.

04:34:49.500 --> 04:34:52.860
The dense, rain soaked clouds around him

04:34:52.860 --> 04:34:54.900
made it hard to see the land below, but

04:34:54.900 --> 04:34:56.759
they would also hide his gleaming blue

04:34:56.759 --> 04:34:58.619
white scales from anyone watching.

04:34:58.680 --> 04:35:02.279
Moon shot out ahead, sweeping low over

04:35:02.279 --> 04:35:03.060
the mountain ridge.

04:35:03.119 --> 04:35:05.819
Her head tilted from side to side

04:35:05.819 --> 04:35:08.999
listening, and she flew in long glides

04:35:08.999 --> 04:35:11.639
keeping her wing beats quiet and spaced

04:35:11.639 --> 04:35:12.119
apart.

04:35:12.180 --> 04:35:14.880
Kibley and Winter followed, imitating

04:35:14.880 --> 04:35:15.119
her.

04:35:15.180 --> 04:35:18.540
The folded, crooked peaks whooshed

04:35:18.540 --> 04:35:19.919
silently past below them.

04:35:20.040 --> 04:35:22.979
Winter felt the minutes ticking by with

04:35:22.979 --> 04:35:23.939
awful urgency.

04:35:24.000 --> 04:35:26.520
What a scarlet guest they were coming and

04:35:26.520 --> 04:35:26.819
left.

04:35:26.880 --> 04:35:29.639
What if she killed Hailstorm now instead

04:35:29.639 --> 04:35:30.659
of waiting until morning?

04:35:30.720 --> 04:35:32.520
How soon was morning?

04:35:32.580 --> 04:35:35.040
Was the sky getting lighter in the east?

04:35:35.099 --> 04:35:38.099
He remembered her awful yellow eyes fixed

04:35:38.099 --> 04:35:38.639
on his.

04:35:38.700 --> 04:35:41.159
He tried to remember his brother's eyes

04:35:41.159 --> 04:35:44.520
instead. bluer than winters or icicles

04:35:44.520 --> 04:35:46.979
cringled around the edges when he grinned

04:35:46.979 --> 04:35:49.500
which was all the time, because Hailstorm

04:35:49.500 --> 04:35:51.659
was the only ice wing winter I'd ever met

04:35:51.659 --> 04:35:53.759
who could laugh about what other dragons

04:35:53.759 --> 04:35:54.360
thought of him.

04:35:54.419 --> 04:35:57.599
Of course, it must be a lot easier to

04:35:57.599 --> 04:35:59.219
laugh from the top of the rankings.

04:35:59.279 --> 04:36:02.699
He'd never forgotten Hailstorm's last

04:36:02.699 --> 04:36:03.239
words to him.

04:36:03.299 --> 04:36:05.159
Had he truly meant them.

04:36:05.220 --> 04:36:07.619
Had he always been disappointed in his

04:36:07.619 --> 04:36:07.979
little brother?

04:36:08.040 --> 04:36:10.680
Would he feel differently if winter came

04:36:10.680 --> 04:36:11.819
flying in to rescue him?

04:36:11.880 --> 04:36:15.540
Moon suddenly checked herself, flaring

04:36:15.540 --> 04:36:17.580
her wings to come to a stop in midair.

04:36:17.639 --> 04:36:20.639
Winter and Kibley did the same, farther

04:36:20.639 --> 04:36:21.479
up in the clouds.

04:36:21.540 --> 04:36:24.360
Winter's heart was thudding so loud, he

04:36:24.360 --> 04:36:25.799
thought they must be able to hear it in

04:36:25.799 --> 04:36:26.819
Glacier's palace.

04:36:26.880 --> 04:36:28.979
He scanned the area.

04:36:29.040 --> 04:36:31.799
A stretch of rocky slope leading up to a

04:36:31.799 --> 04:36:34.139
peak, where several flat ledges and

04:36:34.139 --> 04:36:36.540
outcroppings directly overlooked the

04:36:36.540 --> 04:36:36.720
valley.

04:36:36.779 --> 04:36:39.719
From here, he could see the dim flicker

04:36:39.719 --> 04:36:42.059
of the fire they'd left behind, although

04:36:42.059 --> 04:36:44.819
kinkajus and pyrites sleeping shapes were

04:36:44.819 --> 04:36:46.019
obscured by the tree cover.

04:36:46.080 --> 04:36:48.720
But if Scarlet had watched from up here

04:36:48.720 --> 04:36:50.939
all day, she would have clearly seen

04:36:50.939 --> 04:36:53.040
winter traversing the open spaces below

04:36:53.040 --> 04:36:56.279
clearly enough to guess who he was, and

04:36:56.279 --> 04:36:57.779
then walk straight into his dreams.

04:36:57.840 --> 04:37:01.380
Moon beckoned them down to her, and they

04:37:01.380 --> 04:37:03.119
all dove under a narrow shelf of rock

04:37:03.119 --> 04:37:04.740
that hid them from the ridge above.

04:37:04.799 --> 04:37:08.220
She's up there, Moon whispered.

04:37:08.340 --> 04:37:10.259
Her and someone else.

04:37:10.380 --> 04:37:12.599
Hailstorm?

04:37:12.659 --> 04:37:15.599
Winter clenched his talons. holding in

04:37:15.599 --> 04:37:17.340
the wild prickles of energy that were

04:37:17.340 --> 04:37:18.779
stabbing through his scales.

04:37:18.840 --> 04:37:21.540
I don't think so, Moon said.

04:37:21.599 --> 04:37:24.119
It doesn't have the bright glare of an

04:37:24.119 --> 04:37:26.579
ice wing mind, although it feels a little

04:37:26.579 --> 04:37:27.059
familiar.

04:37:27.119 --> 04:37:28.919
I can't actually read it.

04:37:29.040 --> 04:37:31.919
Like, there's a wall of humming between

04:37:31.919 --> 04:37:32.700
me and it.

04:37:32.819 --> 04:37:35.580
Someone with Skyfire?

04:37:35.639 --> 04:37:36.659
Kibley asked.

04:37:36.720 --> 04:37:37.919
She shook her head.

04:37:37.979 --> 04:37:40.439
A bit like that, but not exactly the

04:37:40.439 --> 04:37:40.619
same.

04:37:40.740 --> 04:37:42.720
It might just be the distance.

04:37:42.779 --> 04:37:45.059
They're near the top of this mountain.

04:37:45.119 --> 04:37:48.179
She put one talent over winter suddenly

04:37:48.179 --> 04:37:49.799
making a sh gesture.

04:37:49.860 --> 04:37:52.500
Winter forced himself to sit in silence

04:37:52.500 --> 04:37:53.459
as she listened.

04:37:53.580 --> 04:37:55.439
They're arguing.

04:37:55.500 --> 04:37:56.700
Moon said.

04:37:56.759 --> 04:37:59.759
Scarlet's mind is loud and angry and all

04:37:59.759 --> 04:38:01.019
over the place.

04:38:01.080 --> 04:38:03.000
I think we can get closer without her

04:38:03.000 --> 04:38:03.419
noticing.

04:38:03.540 --> 04:38:06.900
Lead the way, Kibley said.

04:38:06.959 --> 04:38:10.080
She flowed silently over the ledge above

04:38:10.080 --> 04:38:12.299
them, and began creeping up the hill

04:38:12.299 --> 04:38:14.819
vanishing almost instantly into the night

04:38:14.819 --> 04:38:17.459
shrouded undergrowth, Winter hurried

04:38:17.459 --> 04:38:19.860
after her, trying to be as quiet as she

04:38:19.860 --> 04:38:20.220
was.

04:38:20.279 --> 04:38:21.779
It was almost impossible.

04:38:21.840 --> 04:38:24.419
His talons were shaking with impatience

04:38:24.419 --> 04:38:25.020
and tension.

04:38:25.080 --> 04:38:27.000
Halfway up the slope.

04:38:27.060 --> 04:38:28.319
He began to hear voices.

04:38:28.380 --> 04:38:32.819
I absolutely hate these narrow nosed ice

04:38:32.819 --> 04:38:33.299
wings.

04:38:33.360 --> 04:38:34.860
Spat a voice.

04:38:34.919 --> 04:38:36.899
That was unmistakably Scarlet's.

04:38:36.959 --> 04:38:39.659
This one was worse than his sister.

04:38:39.779 --> 04:38:41.399
He barely groveled at all.

04:38:41.459 --> 04:38:43.799
I don't think he ever had any intention

04:38:43.799 --> 04:38:45.959
of murdering anyone from me.

04:38:46.080 --> 04:38:47.700
The nerve.

04:38:47.759 --> 04:38:50.579
You couldn't convince him otherwise.

04:38:50.639 --> 04:38:52.080
Said a 2nd voice.

04:38:52.200 --> 04:38:55.799
Usually, you are very convincing.

04:38:55.860 --> 04:39:01.139
He was obviously a lost cause, Scarlett

04:39:01.139 --> 04:39:01.860
said with a snarl.

04:39:01.979 --> 04:39:05.400
Kept making this hero face at me, like

04:39:05.400 --> 04:39:07.740
I'm the bad guy, and he's coming to write

04:39:07.740 --> 04:39:08.639
all the wrongs.

04:39:08.700 --> 04:39:10.259
Excuse me.

04:39:10.319 --> 04:39:13.259
Who got attacked by her own artwork, and

04:39:13.259 --> 04:39:15.360
then kidnapped by her ally, and then

04:39:15.360 --> 04:39:18.419
blackmailed by her champion, mid rescue

04:39:18.419 --> 04:39:20.220
while meanwhile, her own daughter was

04:39:20.220 --> 04:39:21.299
stealing her throne.

04:39:21.360 --> 04:39:24.119
Who's the one with the hideous face

04:39:24.119 --> 04:39:24.840
maiming?

04:39:24.900 --> 04:39:28.439
whose throne is currently occupied by a

04:39:28.439 --> 04:39:31.139
pretender, who could never have beaten me

04:39:31.139 --> 04:39:34.200
in a challenge before, who had her whole

04:39:34.200 --> 04:39:37.380
life ruined and emolished and shattered

04:39:37.380 --> 04:39:40.619
by the stupid, horrible dragonettes.

04:39:40.619 --> 04:39:42.659
There was a pause.

04:39:42.720 --> 04:39:45.240
But before the other dragon could answer

04:39:45.240 --> 04:39:46.860
Scarlet shouted, Me.

04:39:46.979 --> 04:39:47.939
That's who?

04:39:48.060 --> 04:39:50.040
I'm the victim here.

04:39:50.099 --> 04:39:52.560
Someone should be all heroically trying

04:39:52.560 --> 04:39:54.299
to help me write all the wrongs.

04:39:54.360 --> 04:39:57.599
Where's my rotten cavalry of loyal

04:39:57.599 --> 04:39:58.020
idiots?

04:39:58.139 --> 04:40:03.599
Well, you have me, said the voice, with a

04:40:03.599 --> 04:40:04.979
notable lack of enthusiasm.

04:40:05.040 --> 04:40:09.360
You, barely count, said Scarlet.

04:40:09.419 --> 04:40:10.439
You're weird.

04:40:10.500 --> 04:40:12.299
And unreliable.

04:40:12.360 --> 04:40:15.540
Ahem, the voice bristled.

04:40:15.599 --> 04:40:18.840
I believe my talents have proven to be

04:40:18.840 --> 04:40:19.799
very useful to you.

04:40:19.860 --> 04:40:23.819
Not as useful, as if you were a proper

04:40:23.819 --> 04:40:26.040
animus, Scarlett grumbled.

04:40:26.159 --> 04:40:29.279
One limited power is not going to get me

04:40:29.279 --> 04:40:30.119
back my throne.

04:40:30.240 --> 04:40:32.700
An animus?

04:40:32.759 --> 04:40:35.220
Winter thought, like pyrite?

04:40:35.279 --> 04:40:38.340
Does Scarlet have 2 animus dragons loyal

04:40:38.340 --> 04:40:38.580
to her?

04:40:38.639 --> 04:40:41.639
By now they had crept close enough that

04:40:41.639 --> 04:40:43.619
Winter could see small spurts of flame

04:40:43.619 --> 04:40:45.479
coming from Scarlet's snout.

04:40:46.139 --> 04:40:48.360
She was pacing on a moonlit ledge, while

04:40:48.360 --> 04:40:50.099
her companion stood in the shadow of the

04:40:50.099 --> 04:40:51.240
mountain, hidden from view.

04:40:51.360 --> 04:40:54.299
Moon tugged him behind a tangle of

04:40:54.299 --> 04:40:55.259
boulders and shrubs.

04:40:55.319 --> 04:40:58.500
He crouched beside her, and Kibley crept

04:40:58.500 --> 04:40:59.159
up on her other side.

04:40:59.220 --> 04:41:01.979
Moon carefully spread her black wings

04:41:01.979 --> 04:41:04.500
over them, hiding as much of their pale

04:41:04.500 --> 04:41:05.580
scales as she could.

04:41:05.639 --> 04:41:08.400
Her wing across Winter's back was warm.

04:41:08.520 --> 04:41:11.040
Like a polar bear fur wrapped around your

04:41:11.040 --> 04:41:13.319
shoulders, after a swim in the Arctic

04:41:13.319 --> 04:41:13.560
Ocean.

04:41:13.619 --> 04:41:17.340
You are welcome to dismiss me from your

04:41:17.340 --> 04:41:19.799
service, said the stranger in a cold

04:41:19.799 --> 04:41:20.400
voice.

04:41:20.700 --> 04:41:22.619
Once you have paid me everything I am

04:41:22.619 --> 04:41:24.540
owed, of course.

04:41:24.599 --> 04:41:27.180
Scarlet growled low in her throat.

04:41:27.240 --> 04:41:29.340
What do I do now?

04:41:29.400 --> 04:41:30.659
She demanded.

04:41:30.720 --> 04:41:34.200
I have this ice wing pawn, who should be

04:41:34.200 --> 04:41:36.659
thrillingly useful, and it turns out

04:41:36.659 --> 04:41:39.119
nobody will do what it takes to get him

04:41:39.119 --> 04:41:39.900
back.

04:41:39.959 --> 04:41:42.540
All I am asking for is a little

04:41:42.540 --> 04:41:43.259
vengeance.

04:41:43.319 --> 04:41:45.959
Is that so much to expect?

04:41:46.080 --> 04:41:50.580
Perhaps a new strategy is in order.

04:41:50.639 --> 04:41:52.619
Said the stranger dryly.

04:41:52.680 --> 04:41:55.080
Scarlet let out a huffy sigh.

04:41:55.259 --> 04:41:58.319
I suppose I do have to kill him.

04:41:58.380 --> 04:41:59.400
She said.

04:41:59.520 --> 04:42:02.040
Now that I've promised to about 8 times.

04:42:02.099 --> 04:42:04.259
It will serve all of them right.

04:42:04.319 --> 04:42:05.880
Or maybe it won't.

04:42:06.000 --> 04:42:08.340
Since nobody even seems to care enough to

04:42:08.340 --> 04:42:12.119
commit just a little murder for me. 3

04:42:12.119 --> 04:42:12.779
moons.

04:42:12.840 --> 04:42:15.840
She fumed in silence for a few minutes.

04:42:15.900 --> 04:42:18.659
Smoke curled from her nostrils up to the

04:42:18.659 --> 04:42:18.840
sky.

04:42:18.900 --> 04:42:22.919
So, the stranger said after a while.

04:42:23.040 --> 04:42:26.279
Are you prepared to kill the prisoner?

04:42:26.340 --> 04:42:29.880
Scarlet flung a rock off the edge and

04:42:29.880 --> 04:42:31.380
watched it bounce and clatter down the

04:42:31.380 --> 04:42:31.619
hill.

04:42:31.680 --> 04:42:34.860
Winter held his breath, pressing closer

04:42:34.860 --> 04:42:35.580
to Moonside.

04:42:35.639 --> 04:42:38.220
She hooked her front claws in the bush in

04:42:38.220 --> 04:42:40.139
front of them and leaned forward, eyes

04:42:40.139 --> 04:42:42.720
closed, head tilted toward the arguing

04:42:42.720 --> 04:42:43.200
dragons.

04:42:43.319 --> 04:42:46.500
Yes, Scarlet said.

04:42:46.560 --> 04:42:47.880
Very well.

04:42:47.939 --> 04:42:49.799
Bring me pyrite.

04:42:49.919 --> 04:42:53.880
Chapter 15.

04:42:54.240 --> 04:42:58.860
Moon's eyes flew open, and her bewildered

04:42:58.860 --> 04:43:00.000
gaze met Winters.

04:43:00.060 --> 04:43:01.619
Pyrite?

04:43:01.680 --> 04:43:04.200
What does she have to do with hailstorm?

04:43:04.259 --> 04:43:05.759
Did she do something to him?

04:43:05.819 --> 04:43:07.439
Does she know where he is?

04:43:07.500 --> 04:43:09.900
If she does, we have to get to her

04:43:09.900 --> 04:43:10.200
first.

04:43:10.259 --> 04:43:13.439
Winter started to scramble to his feet

04:43:13.439 --> 04:43:15.419
but Moon pushed him back down with her

04:43:15.419 --> 04:43:17.159
wing, pointing up at the ledge.

04:43:17.279 --> 04:43:20.759
A moment later, a dragon leaped off it

04:43:20.759 --> 04:43:23.639
and spiraled up into the sky, banking

04:43:23.639 --> 04:43:24.119
toward the valley.

04:43:24.180 --> 04:43:26.580
Winter only caught a glimpse of his

04:43:26.580 --> 04:43:28.979
scales, as the firelight flickered over

04:43:28.979 --> 04:43:30.659
them, but he was sure of what he saw.

04:43:30.720 --> 04:43:33.659
Scarlet's ally was a night wing.

04:43:33.720 --> 04:43:35.700
Who is that?

04:43:35.759 --> 04:43:36.720
he demanded.

04:43:36.779 --> 04:43:38.159
I have no idea.

04:43:38.220 --> 04:43:40.680
Moon whispered back, but if he's a

04:43:40.680 --> 04:43:42.900
Nightwing, Maybe that's why I can't hear

04:43:42.900 --> 04:43:43.259
him think.

04:43:43.319 --> 04:43:45.900
Maybe he's been trained to shield from

04:43:45.900 --> 04:43:46.919
mind readers or something.

04:43:46.979 --> 04:43:50.580
We have to get to pyrite before he does.

04:43:50.639 --> 04:43:52.860
Kibli whispered from Moon's other side.

04:43:52.919 --> 04:43:54.360
He was right.

04:43:54.419 --> 04:43:56.520
They didn't have time for the mystery of

04:43:56.520 --> 04:43:58.380
a Nightwing who worked for a deposed

04:43:58.380 --> 04:43:59.340
Skywing Queen.

04:43:59.400 --> 04:44:02.220
Winter slid out from under Moon's wing

04:44:02.220 --> 04:44:03.779
and started crawling back down the

04:44:03.779 --> 04:44:06.240
mountainside as fast as he could, looking

04:44:06.240 --> 04:44:07.740
for a spot where he could take off

04:44:07.740 --> 04:44:09.659
without Scarlet seeing him.

04:44:09.720 --> 04:44:12.180
Pebbles bounced past him as Kibley and

04:44:12.180 --> 04:44:12.720
Moon followed.

04:44:12.840 --> 04:44:16.200
Now, Moon breathed suddenly.

04:44:16.319 --> 04:44:18.540
She launched herself off the mountain and

04:44:18.540 --> 04:44:19.680
winter hurtled after her.

04:44:19.740 --> 04:44:22.860
He arrowed down toward their camp, his

04:44:22.860 --> 04:44:24.720
eyes fixed on that small flicker of

04:44:24.720 --> 04:44:25.259
firelight.

04:44:25.319 --> 04:44:28.200
The night wing won't go straight there.

04:44:28.259 --> 04:44:30.119
Kibley panted behind him.

04:44:30.180 --> 04:44:33.000
He'll want to sneak up and take pyrite

04:44:33.000 --> 04:44:34.080
while the rest of us are sleeping.

04:44:34.139 --> 04:44:36.659
He'll land and approach the camp

04:44:36.659 --> 04:44:37.139
quietly.

04:44:37.200 --> 04:44:38.400
We'll get there first.

04:44:38.459 --> 04:44:42.299
Only if you shut up and fly, Winter

04:44:42.299 --> 04:44:42.720
growled.

04:44:42.779 --> 04:44:45.959
Kibli didn't say another word as they

04:44:45.959 --> 04:44:48.060
shot down the cliffs and over the trees.

04:44:48.060 --> 04:44:50.580
Winter plunged through the leaves and

04:44:50.580 --> 04:44:52.380
landed with a skidding crash beside

04:44:52.380 --> 04:44:53.099
Kinkaju.

04:44:53.159 --> 04:44:54.299
Yikes!

04:44:54.360 --> 04:44:56.459
The rain wing yelped, leaping to her

04:44:56.459 --> 04:44:56.700
feet.

04:44:56.759 --> 04:44:59.580
For a wild, breathless moment.

04:44:59.639 --> 04:45:00.900
Winter thought pyrite was gone.

04:45:00.959 --> 04:45:03.419
But then she sat up on the other side of

04:45:03.419 --> 04:45:04.799
the fire, rubbing her face.

04:45:04.860 --> 04:45:07.380
What's all the noise?

04:45:07.439 --> 04:45:08.340
She mumbled.

04:45:08.400 --> 04:45:09.959
Yeah, really?

04:45:10.020 --> 04:45:12.720
Kingaju said, flaring the rough behind

04:45:12.720 --> 04:45:13.380
her ears.

04:45:13.439 --> 04:45:15.000
Is someone on fire?

04:45:15.060 --> 04:45:17.459
Why are you smashing around waking up

04:45:17.459 --> 04:45:19.319
perfectly happy sleeping dragons?

04:45:19.380 --> 04:45:20.340
Beep!

04:45:20.400 --> 04:45:22.860
she cried, as Moon and Kibli came

04:45:22.860 --> 04:45:24.959
thudding down behind winter, trailing

04:45:24.959 --> 04:45:27.119
broken branches, with leaves and twigs

04:45:27.119 --> 04:45:28.259
caught in their wings and tails.

04:45:28.380 --> 04:45:30.419
You!

04:45:30.540 --> 04:45:33.240
Winter leaped over the fire and bold

04:45:33.240 --> 04:45:34.319
pyrite to the ground.

04:45:34.380 --> 04:45:37.200
She screamed, flapped her wings at him

04:45:37.200 --> 04:45:39.479
and tried to wriggle away, but he leaned

04:45:39.479 --> 04:45:41.459
all his weight on her back, and pinned

04:45:41.459 --> 04:45:43.380
her down with his deadly ice wing claws.

04:45:43.439 --> 04:45:46.439
Even though she was bigger than him, she

04:45:46.439 --> 04:45:47.580
stopped resisting quickly.

04:45:47.639 --> 04:45:50.580
Her talons twitched in the grass, and she

04:45:50.580 --> 04:45:51.959
twisted her neck to look back at him.

04:45:52.080 --> 04:45:55.979
This is mean, she protested.

04:45:56.040 --> 04:45:58.319
What do you know about my brother?

04:45:58.439 --> 04:45:59.520
he demanded.

04:45:59.580 --> 04:46:02.040
Nothing at all, she said.

04:46:02.099 --> 04:46:03.540
Now, can I get up?

04:46:03.659 --> 04:46:09.000
You know something, he said, in a low

04:46:09.000 --> 04:46:09.900
dangerous voice.

04:46:10.020 --> 04:46:14.279
He's an ice wing named Hailstorm, a

04:46:14.279 --> 04:46:15.360
couple of years older than me.

04:46:15.419 --> 04:46:19.080
The bravest dragon Empirea, Scarlet's

04:46:19.080 --> 04:46:20.459
prisoner for the last 2 years.

04:46:20.520 --> 04:46:22.200
He shook her roughly.

04:46:22.259 --> 04:46:24.060
You know where he is.

04:46:24.119 --> 04:46:27.419
All right, all right, she whined.

04:46:27.479 --> 04:46:29.639
But you don't have to attack me.

04:46:29.700 --> 04:46:32.159
I would have told you if you just asked.

04:46:32.220 --> 04:46:35.099
Queen Scarlet's prisoners are kept in an

04:46:35.099 --> 04:46:36.540
arena in the Sky Palace.

04:46:36.599 --> 04:46:38.939
I can draw you a map of the place if you

04:46:38.939 --> 04:46:39.419
want.

04:46:39.479 --> 04:46:41.040
I don't think there are any ice wings

04:46:41.040 --> 04:46:43.619
there anymore, though, and Ruby traded

04:46:43.619 --> 04:46:45.479
back almost all the prisoners of war.

04:46:45.540 --> 04:46:49.619
Frustration surged through winter, and he

04:46:49.619 --> 04:46:51.720
dug his claws in just a little, making

04:46:51.720 --> 04:46:54.180
pyrite wince across the fire.

04:46:54.180 --> 04:46:56.340
Kinkachu was watching them with wide

04:46:56.340 --> 04:46:57.119
bewildered eyes.

04:46:57.180 --> 04:47:00.720
Don't toy with me, Skywing.

04:47:00.840 --> 04:47:02.220
Winter hissed.

04:47:02.279 --> 04:47:04.380
Scarlet needs you in order to kill

04:47:04.380 --> 04:47:05.220
Hellstorm.

04:47:05.279 --> 04:47:06.360
So why is that?

04:47:06.419 --> 04:47:07.380
Where is he?

04:47:07.439 --> 04:47:09.360
Did you use your magic on him?

04:47:09.419 --> 04:47:11.159
What?

04:47:11.279 --> 04:47:12.119
Magic?

04:47:12.240 --> 04:47:13.680
Pyrite protested.

04:47:13.740 --> 04:47:15.180
I don't have any magic.

04:47:15.240 --> 04:47:17.880
I never did anything special for Queen

04:47:17.880 --> 04:47:18.419
Scarlet.

04:47:18.479 --> 04:47:19.979
Winter.

04:47:20.040 --> 04:47:22.799
I think she's telling the truth, Moon

04:47:22.799 --> 04:47:23.159
said.

04:47:23.220 --> 04:47:25.560
She had her front talons pressed to her

04:47:25.560 --> 04:47:28.020
head, and an expression of pain scrawled

04:47:28.020 --> 04:47:28.740
across her face.

04:47:28.740 --> 04:47:30.959
She has no idea what you're talking

04:47:30.959 --> 04:47:31.200
about.

04:47:31.319 --> 04:47:33.599
What she said?

04:47:33.659 --> 04:47:34.919
Pyrite yelped.

04:47:34.979 --> 04:47:35.520
No idea.

04:47:35.639 --> 04:47:39.479
She's blocking you somehow, Winter said

04:47:39.479 --> 04:47:40.080
furiously.

04:47:40.139 --> 04:47:41.639
She is magic.

04:47:41.700 --> 04:47:42.540
I can feel it.

04:47:42.659 --> 04:47:46.139
With the sky wing pinioned below him, the

04:47:46.139 --> 04:47:48.180
muscle wringing sensation of powerful

04:47:48.180 --> 04:47:50.279
animus magic was beating through him

04:47:50.279 --> 04:47:51.119
stronger than ever.

04:47:51.180 --> 04:47:54.240
He glared down at the dragon and spotted

04:47:54.240 --> 04:47:56.220
the necklace tangled around her neck.

04:47:56.279 --> 04:47:57.840
Maybe with her necklace.

04:47:57.900 --> 04:48:00.240
Maybe she enchanted it to hide her mind

04:48:00.240 --> 04:48:00.540
from you.

04:48:00.599 --> 04:48:02.580
He reached for the chain.

04:48:02.639 --> 04:48:07.380
Don't touch that, roared Pyrite, surging

04:48:07.380 --> 04:48:09.180
to her feet, and throwing him off with

04:48:09.180 --> 04:48:10.500
sudden powerful violence.

04:48:10.500 --> 04:48:13.020
Winter was flung straight into the fire.

04:48:13.080 --> 04:48:15.900
The burning embers sizzled against his

04:48:15.900 --> 04:48:18.180
scales and back talons, and he leaped

04:48:18.180 --> 04:48:19.439
away with a howl of pain.

04:48:19.500 --> 04:48:22.200
It took a moment for his head to clear

04:48:22.200 --> 04:48:25.020
but when it did, he saw 2 shapes

04:48:25.020 --> 04:48:26.520
grappling through the smoke of the

04:48:26.520 --> 04:48:27.299
scattered fire.

04:48:27.360 --> 04:48:30.540
Kibley's tail was poised like a scorpions

04:48:30.540 --> 04:48:32.159
as he wrestled pyrite.

04:48:32.220 --> 04:48:34.860
Her arms were longer than his, and her

04:48:34.860 --> 04:48:37.020
claws slashed at his underbelly, while

04:48:37.020 --> 04:48:38.520
her wings beat him away from her.

04:48:38.580 --> 04:48:41.580
The sky wing's teeth were bared, and her

04:48:41.580 --> 04:48:43.200
face was a grimace of fury and

04:48:43.200 --> 04:48:43.680
determination.

04:48:43.740 --> 04:48:47.700
Winter's burns were sending fiery bolts

04:48:47.700 --> 04:48:50.159
of pain along all the nerves in his body

04:48:50.159 --> 04:48:52.139
but he staggered forward to help Kibley.

04:48:52.259 --> 04:48:55.860
And then, Kingachu shrieked, and a black

04:48:55.860 --> 04:48:58.200
dragon was suddenly there, appearing from

04:48:58.200 --> 04:48:58.740
the shadows.

04:48:58.799 --> 04:49:02.279
He pounced on Kinkaju, striking her 3

04:49:02.279 --> 04:49:04.680
times with swift brutality, and then

04:49:04.680 --> 04:49:06.180
slamming her out of the way with a

04:49:06.180 --> 04:49:07.380
powerful blow from his tail.

04:49:07.439 --> 04:49:10.139
The little rain wing was thrown into a

04:49:10.139 --> 04:49:11.880
tree trunk with a sickening crack.

04:49:11.939 --> 04:49:14.700
She crumbled to the ground, her scales

04:49:14.700 --> 04:49:15.540
fading to white.

04:49:15.599 --> 04:49:17.700
Kinkajoo?

04:49:17.759 --> 04:49:18.659
Moon cried.

04:49:18.720 --> 04:49:21.599
The black dragon turned on her, and she

04:49:21.599 --> 04:49:24.180
roared a jet of blazing fire straight at

04:49:24.180 --> 04:49:24.659
his face.

04:49:24.720 --> 04:49:27.659
He reared back, covering his eyes, and

04:49:27.659 --> 04:49:30.119
she leaped at him, slashing furiously at

04:49:30.119 --> 04:49:31.139
his wings and neck.

04:49:31.200 --> 04:49:33.720
A bright gash of red appeared along his

04:49:33.720 --> 04:49:36.360
throat, and he roared, seizing moon's

04:49:36.360 --> 04:49:36.779
talons.

04:49:36.840 --> 04:49:39.299
Blisters were starting to bubble along

04:49:39.299 --> 04:49:41.580
the edges of his mouth and nose, and he

04:49:41.580 --> 04:49:43.500
kept shaking his head, as though it was

04:49:43.500 --> 04:49:45.900
hard to see, but he was strong and huge

04:49:45.900 --> 04:49:47.939
and he flung moon to the ground with

04:49:47.939 --> 04:49:48.240
ease.

04:49:48.360 --> 04:49:50.580
Winter didn't remember choosing.

04:49:50.639 --> 04:49:52.439
Although there must have been a moment

04:49:52.439 --> 04:49:55.259
when his head said, go after pyrite.

04:49:55.319 --> 04:49:57.659
She's the key to finding Hillstorm, while

04:49:57.659 --> 04:50:00.119
his heart shouted, no, help moon.

04:50:00.240 --> 04:50:03.180
But as far as he could tell, there was no

04:50:03.180 --> 04:50:04.200
conscious thought involved.

04:50:04.259 --> 04:50:05.759
He was just there.

04:50:05.819 --> 04:50:08.459
Barreling into the night wing before the

04:50:08.459 --> 04:50:10.799
monster could stamp his sharp talons down

04:50:10.799 --> 04:50:11.580
on Moon's neck.

04:50:11.639 --> 04:50:14.639
The 2 of them rolled across the clearing

04:50:14.639 --> 04:50:17.639
black and white scales clashing, both of

04:50:17.639 --> 04:50:18.900
them roaring at full blast.

04:50:18.959 --> 04:50:21.959
Winter felt metal tangle and clatter

04:50:21.959 --> 04:50:22.740
around his claws.

04:50:22.799 --> 04:50:25.439
The night wing was wearing a mess of dark

04:50:25.439 --> 04:50:27.540
jewelry, and things that felt like

04:50:27.540 --> 04:50:30.720
compact iron boxes on chains, as they

04:50:30.720 --> 04:50:32.639
smacked into winter's jaws and knuckles.

04:50:32.700 --> 04:50:36.000
He ducked his head, as the Nightwing shot

04:50:36.000 --> 04:50:37.619
a burst of flames past his ear.

04:50:37.740 --> 04:50:40.020
The ice was rising in his throat.

04:50:40.080 --> 04:50:42.959
He twisted to bring his mouth up to the

04:50:42.959 --> 04:50:45.360
night wing's face, and hissed frost

04:50:45.360 --> 04:50:47.279
breath straight into the dragon's eyes.

04:50:47.340 --> 04:50:49.860
The night wing slammed his eyes shut at

04:50:49.860 --> 04:50:52.139
the last second, but ice immediately

04:50:52.139 --> 04:50:54.900
began spreading across his snout, sealing

04:50:54.900 --> 04:50:57.240
his eyelids in place, and melting into

04:50:57.240 --> 04:50:58.560
the burns moon had given him.

04:50:58.619 --> 04:51:02.340
The black dragon's bellow of agony was

04:51:02.340 --> 04:51:03.779
like nothing winter had ever heard

04:51:03.779 --> 04:51:04.380
before.

04:51:04.439 --> 04:51:07.080
He threw winter often, and bolted into

04:51:07.080 --> 04:51:07.439
the sky.

04:51:07.500 --> 04:51:10.200
For a moment, winter could see him

04:51:10.200 --> 04:51:13.020
weaving and dipping from side to side as

04:51:13.020 --> 04:51:14.279
he tried to fly without sight.

04:51:14.400 --> 04:51:17.220
And then the night wing's black scales

04:51:17.220 --> 04:51:19.139
vanished into the dark and the heavy

04:51:19.139 --> 04:51:20.040
storm clouds.

04:51:20.099 --> 04:51:23.580
At some point, it had started to rain.

04:51:23.639 --> 04:51:26.159
Scattered fat droplets that plopped into

04:51:26.159 --> 04:51:28.319
the dying fire with dragon like hisses.

04:51:28.380 --> 04:51:31.080
The raindrops were soothing on winter's

04:51:31.080 --> 04:51:32.880
burns as he dragged himself back to

04:51:32.880 --> 04:51:33.180
moon.

04:51:33.240 --> 04:51:36.840
She was crouched beside Kinkaju, shaking

04:51:36.840 --> 04:51:38.040
the little rain wing gently.

04:51:38.159 --> 04:51:41.340
Please be all right, Moon whispered.

04:51:41.400 --> 04:51:43.439
Kinkachu, please wake up.

04:51:43.560 --> 04:51:45.959
Her voice snagged into a sob.

04:51:46.080 --> 04:51:47.400
I can't hear her.

04:51:47.459 --> 04:51:49.439
I can't hear anything from her mind at

04:51:49.439 --> 04:51:49.619
all.

04:51:49.680 --> 04:51:54.000
She's just unconscious, Winters said, but

04:51:54.000 --> 04:51:54.599
he wasn't sure.

04:51:54.659 --> 04:51:56.939
The dragonette looked as if she'd been

04:51:56.939 --> 04:51:59.400
dropped from a great height, crumpled, and

04:51:59.400 --> 04:51:59.639
still.

04:51:59.759 --> 04:52:03.119
He went for her first, Moon said.

04:52:03.180 --> 04:52:04.139
Did you see that?

04:52:04.200 --> 04:52:07.080
He could have attacked any of us, but he

04:52:07.080 --> 04:52:08.639
started with Kinkachu on purpose.

04:52:08.700 --> 04:52:10.439
Why would anyone do that?

04:52:10.500 --> 04:52:13.860
Why target a tiny rain wing, the smallest

04:52:13.860 --> 04:52:14.220
of us?

04:52:14.279 --> 04:52:17.340
She straightened one of Kinkaju's crooked

04:52:17.340 --> 04:52:19.259
wings and smoothed it back into place.

04:52:19.319 --> 04:52:22.200
Maybe he was worried about her venom

04:52:22.200 --> 04:52:23.340
Winter said.

04:52:23.400 --> 04:52:26.040
Scarlet has probably talked about rain

04:52:26.040 --> 04:52:28.259
wing venom quite a lot, given her

04:52:28.259 --> 04:52:28.860
experience.

04:52:28.919 --> 04:52:31.979
Moon lifted and dropped her wings with a

04:52:31.979 --> 04:52:32.880
doubtful expression.

04:52:32.939 --> 04:52:35.759
Her eyes never left Kinkachu's pale

04:52:35.759 --> 04:52:36.060
face.

04:52:36.060 --> 04:52:38.220
Winter turned and saw.

04:52:38.279 --> 04:52:40.439
Finally, what should have been his 1st

04:52:40.439 --> 04:52:40.680
thought?

04:52:40.740 --> 04:52:43.619
Kimley had subdued pyrite, and was

04:52:43.619 --> 04:52:45.060
standing over her on the other side of

04:52:45.060 --> 04:52:47.700
the clearing, his venomous tail suspended

04:52:47.700 --> 04:52:49.080
over the midpoint of her spine.

04:52:49.139 --> 04:52:52.139
Winter limped over, and looked down at

04:52:52.139 --> 04:52:53.279
the traitorous sky wing.

04:52:53.340 --> 04:52:56.400
That night wing could come back with

04:52:56.400 --> 04:52:58.740
Scarlet any minute, Kibble warned him.

04:52:58.799 --> 04:53:00.959
We should get out of here as fast as we

04:53:00.959 --> 04:53:01.200
can.

04:53:01.319 --> 04:53:03.240
Winter nodded.

04:53:03.299 --> 04:53:05.279
He reached for Pyrite's necklace.

04:53:05.340 --> 04:53:08.939
No, Pyrite said, with a hysterical edge

04:53:08.939 --> 04:53:09.419
to her voice.

04:53:09.540 --> 04:53:12.119
Please, I'm not supposed to take it off

04:53:12.119 --> 04:53:12.840
ever.

04:53:12.900 --> 04:53:14.159
It's lie or death.

04:53:14.279 --> 04:53:15.299
I need to wear it.

04:53:15.360 --> 04:53:16.500
Please leave it alone.

04:53:16.560 --> 04:53:17.459
Don't take it.

04:53:17.520 --> 04:53:18.000
Don't.

04:53:18.299 --> 04:53:20.939
He ripped it off her neck, yanking 3

04:53:20.939 --> 04:53:23.279
times before the chain finally snapped.

04:53:23.400 --> 04:53:26.580
The sky wing let out a cry of despair.

04:53:26.639 --> 04:53:29.220
Winter felt the pouch crinkle between his

04:53:29.220 --> 04:53:29.819
claws.

04:53:29.880 --> 04:53:32.880
Whatever was inside was very light, and

04:53:32.880 --> 04:53:34.740
crunched, like a talon full of snow.

04:53:34.799 --> 04:53:37.740
He was about to open the pouch, when

04:53:37.740 --> 04:53:39.900
pyrite scales began to slide off.

04:53:39.959 --> 04:53:43.319
At least, that was Winter's 1st

04:53:43.319 --> 04:53:43.680
impression.

04:53:43.799 --> 04:53:45.959
It looked almost as though she was

04:53:45.959 --> 04:53:48.659
melting and growing, and snapping into

04:53:48.659 --> 04:53:49.680
place at the same time.

04:53:49.740 --> 04:53:52.619
Her snout narrowed and lengthened.

04:53:52.680 --> 04:53:55.139
The orange color bled swiftly out of each

04:53:55.139 --> 04:53:55.619
scale.

04:53:55.680 --> 04:53:58.740
Sharp spikes shoved up through the skin

04:53:58.740 --> 04:54:01.380
all along her back, and at the tip of her

04:54:01.380 --> 04:54:01.560
tail.

04:54:01.680 --> 04:54:04.139
Kibley leaped off her with a shout of

04:54:04.139 --> 04:54:04.860
surprise.

04:54:04.919 --> 04:54:06.720
It was over in a matter of seconds.

04:54:06.779 --> 04:54:10.319
The dragon, who was no longer pyrite

04:54:10.319 --> 04:54:13.200
arched his back, unfolded his long white

04:54:13.200 --> 04:54:16.020
wings, and opened eyes as blue as the

04:54:16.020 --> 04:54:16.680
Arctic sky.

04:54:16.740 --> 04:54:19.740
He coughed, and stared around him in

04:54:19.740 --> 04:54:20.700
utter bewilderment.

04:54:20.759 --> 04:54:23.459
His gaze landed on winter and Kibley.

04:54:23.520 --> 04:54:28.139
Winter, he said, in a shaky, hoarse

04:54:28.139 --> 04:54:28.380
voice.

04:54:28.439 --> 04:54:31.319
Winter stared up at him, his talons

04:54:31.319 --> 04:54:33.659
rooted to the earth, his wings prickling

04:54:33.659 --> 04:54:34.080
with fear.

04:54:34.139 --> 04:54:38.700
He was too shocked to speak Holy snakes

04:54:38.700 --> 04:54:40.080
said Kibley.

04:54:40.139 --> 04:54:42.119
Is that, are you?

04:54:42.240 --> 04:54:44.220
Pyrite was gone.

04:54:44.340 --> 04:54:45.959
Standing in her place.

04:54:46.020 --> 04:54:48.119
Was hailstorm.

04:54:48.180 --> 04:54:52.560
Chapter 16.

04:54:52.740 --> 04:54:55.799
Hailstorm?

04:54:55.860 --> 04:54:57.119
Winter whispered.

04:54:57.180 --> 04:54:58.319
But how?

04:54:58.380 --> 04:55:01.619
You were just, you were a Sky Wing.

04:55:01.680 --> 04:55:02.639
I saw you.

04:55:02.700 --> 04:55:03.599
How did you?

04:55:03.779 --> 04:55:06.599
What happened to the throne room?

04:55:06.720 --> 04:55:09.119
Hailstorm asked, his voice getting

04:55:09.119 --> 04:55:09.840
stronger.

04:55:09.900 --> 04:55:13.500
And what have you been eating to get so

04:55:13.500 --> 04:55:14.040
big?

04:55:14.159 --> 04:55:17.400
He stopped, swaying in place and rubbing

04:55:17.400 --> 04:55:17.939
his eyes.

04:55:18.000 --> 04:55:19.259
Wait.

04:55:19.319 --> 04:55:20.880
I have to find the queen.

04:55:20.939 --> 04:55:24.599
Why are my scales the wrong color?

04:55:24.659 --> 04:55:28.259
He held out his talons and then recoiled

04:55:28.259 --> 04:55:29.759
from them with an expression of terror.

04:55:29.819 --> 04:55:31.439
What have you done to me?

04:55:31.500 --> 04:55:33.299
Why am I so cold?

04:55:33.360 --> 04:55:36.900
He seized Winter's front claws in a grip

04:55:36.900 --> 04:55:39.540
that sent shockwaves of desperation along

04:55:39.540 --> 04:55:40.619
Winter's arms?

04:55:40.860 --> 04:55:42.000
Who am I?

04:55:42.119 --> 04:55:43.680
Hellstorm demanded.

04:55:43.740 --> 04:55:46.919
You're my brother, Winter said.

04:55:46.979 --> 04:55:48.599
That was clear.

04:55:48.659 --> 04:55:49.380
That was true.

04:55:49.439 --> 04:55:51.900
They could deal with spells and lingering

04:55:51.900 --> 04:55:52.740
side effects later.

04:55:52.799 --> 04:55:55.979
He leaned into Hailstorm's grasp, locking

04:55:55.979 --> 04:55:56.580
their eyes together.

04:55:56.639 --> 04:55:59.580
And we have to get you out of here before

04:55:59.580 --> 04:56:00.479
Scarlett finds you.

04:56:00.599 --> 04:56:02.819
Queen Scarlet.

04:56:02.880 --> 04:56:04.979
Hailstorm corrected automatically.

04:56:05.040 --> 04:56:06.479
She wouldn't hurt me.

04:56:06.540 --> 04:56:09.779
I am completely lo- His face twisted.

04:56:09.840 --> 04:56:12.240
Horror warring with despair and

04:56:12.240 --> 04:56:12.720
confusion.

04:56:12.779 --> 04:56:14.459
What am I saying?

04:56:14.580 --> 04:56:15.840
Winter.

04:56:15.900 --> 04:56:17.340
What am I saying?

04:56:17.459 --> 04:56:21.000
We'll fix it, but right now, we have to

04:56:21.000 --> 04:56:22.439
fly, Winter said.

04:56:22.500 --> 04:56:24.840
Kibley darted across the clearing and

04:56:24.840 --> 04:56:25.740
said something to Moon.

04:56:25.799 --> 04:56:28.619
She immediately slid her talons under

04:56:28.619 --> 04:56:31.259
Kinkaju and tried to hoist the rain wing

04:56:31.259 --> 04:56:33.419
onto Kibley's back, struggling as

04:56:33.419 --> 04:56:35.580
Kinkaju's tail flopped sideways and

04:56:35.580 --> 04:56:36.360
overbalanced her.

04:56:36.419 --> 04:56:39.419
The unconscious dragon's wings wapped

04:56:39.419 --> 04:56:41.700
moon in the face, and her head lulled

04:56:41.700 --> 04:56:42.959
awkwardly on her long neck.

04:56:43.020 --> 04:56:45.959
Winter took a step toward them, but

04:56:45.959 --> 04:56:47.220
Hailstorm wouldn't let go of him.

04:56:47.279 --> 04:56:49.020
Are you real?

04:56:49.080 --> 04:56:51.240
The tall Ice Wing asked.

04:56:51.299 --> 04:56:52.919
Is any of this real?

04:56:52.979 --> 04:56:55.979
Hillstorm, snap into it.

04:56:56.040 --> 04:56:57.240
Winter barked.

04:56:57.299 --> 04:56:59.040
We need to help my friends and get out of

04:56:59.040 --> 04:56:59.220
here.

04:56:59.340 --> 04:57:01.500
Friends?

04:57:01.560 --> 04:57:02.639
Hellstorm echoed.

04:57:02.700 --> 04:57:05.099
He squinted over at the tangle of dragons

04:57:05.099 --> 04:57:06.720
on the edge of the dying firelight.

04:57:06.779 --> 04:57:08.279
But winter.

04:57:08.400 --> 04:57:11.220
I think there's a night wing over there.

04:57:11.279 --> 04:57:14.580
Winter's guilt came slamming back through

04:57:14.580 --> 04:57:17.400
him, along with a 2nd wave of guilt that

04:57:17.400 --> 04:57:19.380
came from remembering how much moon had

04:57:19.380 --> 04:57:20.700
done to help him.

04:57:20.759 --> 04:57:22.200
She's on our side.

04:57:22.259 --> 04:57:23.939
She's helping me rescue you.

04:57:24.000 --> 04:57:25.860
Hillstorm, move.

04:57:25.919 --> 04:57:28.860
He finally got his claws free and ran

04:57:28.860 --> 04:57:29.459
over to the others.

04:57:29.580 --> 04:57:32.939
He reached Moon's side in time to catch

04:57:32.939 --> 04:57:35.639
Kinkaju as she slid sideways off the sand

04:57:35.639 --> 04:57:36.180
wing.

04:57:36.240 --> 04:57:38.759
Kibley had his teeth gritted and his eyes

04:57:38.759 --> 04:57:41.220
closed, his legs bowed under her weight.

04:57:41.279 --> 04:57:44.159
Kinkachu was small, but not that much

04:57:44.159 --> 04:57:46.319
smaller than Kibley, who was wiry and

04:57:46.319 --> 04:57:47.099
narrow shouldered.

04:57:47.099 --> 04:57:49.979
Winter couldn't imagine how the sand wing

04:57:49.979 --> 04:57:51.599
could even take off with her on top of

04:57:51.599 --> 04:57:54.180
him, let alone keep up a breakneck escape

04:57:54.180 --> 04:57:54.540
pace.

04:57:54.659 --> 04:57:56.580
And winter couldn't do it either.

04:57:56.639 --> 04:57:59.340
He was broader than Kibley, but not any

04:57:59.340 --> 04:57:59.580
bigger.

04:57:59.700 --> 04:58:01.799
But what's the alternative?

04:58:01.860 --> 04:58:03.240
Leave her here?

04:58:03.299 --> 04:58:06.119
He was astonished to find that he

04:58:06.119 --> 04:58:07.619
couldn't even consider that possibility.

04:58:07.740 --> 04:58:11.279
He wouldn't abandon her, not even to save

04:58:11.279 --> 04:58:12.000
hailstorm.

04:58:12.119 --> 04:58:14.459
He could feel his brother watching him

04:58:14.459 --> 04:58:17.099
the needles of centuries of ice wing

04:58:17.099 --> 04:58:18.720
judgment pricking along his spine.

04:58:18.779 --> 04:58:23.220
We need someone as big as clay, Moon said

04:58:23.220 --> 04:58:25.799
ruefully, resting Kinkajoo's head in the

04:58:25.799 --> 04:58:26.939
crook of her shoulder and wing.

04:58:27.060 --> 04:58:29.639
Hillstorm might be big enough.

04:58:29.700 --> 04:58:32.700
But he's too confused, and he has no love

04:58:32.700 --> 04:58:35.520
for rainwings, either as pyrite or as

04:58:35.520 --> 04:58:35.880
himself.

04:58:35.939 --> 04:58:38.459
I don't know what he might do with her

04:58:38.459 --> 04:58:39.119
mid-flight.

04:58:39.240 --> 04:58:41.759
If only Kibley and I could carry her

04:58:41.759 --> 04:58:42.119
together.

04:58:42.240 --> 04:58:46.020
Winter darted over to the trees, leaped

04:58:46.020 --> 04:58:48.060
up, and wrenched the canopy loose from

04:58:48.060 --> 04:58:49.200
the trunk it was bound to.

04:58:49.319 --> 04:58:52.200
The weave of branches and vines was thick

04:58:52.200 --> 04:58:53.159
enough to keep out rain.

04:58:53.220 --> 04:58:55.500
If they were lucky, it would be strong

04:58:55.500 --> 04:58:57.000
enough to hold Kinkajou.

04:58:57.119 --> 04:58:59.759
He spread it out beside Moon, who

04:58:59.759 --> 04:59:01.080
understood without words what he was

04:59:01.080 --> 04:59:01.259
doing.

04:59:01.319 --> 04:59:04.560
Awkwardly, they shifted Kinkaju onto the

04:59:04.560 --> 04:59:06.840
makeshift stretcher, curling her tail

04:59:06.840 --> 04:59:08.639
close around her body and tucking in her

04:59:08.639 --> 04:59:08.880
wings.

04:59:08.939 --> 04:59:11.400
There was no sign of life from her as

04:59:11.400 --> 04:59:13.740
they did this, although Winter thought he

04:59:13.740 --> 04:59:15.419
could feel a pulse in the palm of her

04:59:15.419 --> 04:59:16.020
talons.

04:59:16.080 --> 04:59:18.240
The pouch was still crushed in his

04:59:18.240 --> 04:59:18.599
claws.

04:59:18.659 --> 04:59:21.360
He needed to look at it more closely, but

04:59:21.360 --> 04:59:23.700
not right now, and he wasn't about to

04:59:23.700 --> 04:59:25.919
risk wearing it, after seeing what it did

04:59:25.919 --> 04:59:26.759
to Hailstorm.

04:59:26.819 --> 04:59:29.700
Carefully, he tucked it beside Kinkachu

04:59:29.700 --> 04:59:31.619
snagging the chain securely around

04:59:31.619 --> 04:59:32.279
several branches.

04:59:32.400 --> 04:59:35.639
Kibley took one side of the canopy in his

04:59:35.639 --> 04:59:36.419
front talons.

04:59:36.479 --> 04:59:38.939
Winter reached for the other, but Moon

04:59:38.939 --> 04:59:39.540
interceded.

04:59:39.599 --> 04:59:41.580
I'll do it, she said.

04:59:41.639 --> 04:59:43.020
You take care of your brother.

04:59:43.139 --> 04:59:45.659
She hooked her claws in the web of

04:59:45.659 --> 04:59:47.400
branches and nodded at Kibley.

04:59:47.459 --> 04:59:49.020
Beating their wings together.

04:59:49.080 --> 04:59:51.900
They lifted up into the air, wobbling and

04:59:51.900 --> 04:59:52.799
lopsided for a moment.

04:59:52.919 --> 04:59:55.799
Winter jumped to catch Kinkaju in case

04:59:55.799 --> 04:59:57.599
they dropped her, but they righted

04:59:57.599 --> 04:59:59.939
themselves and flew higher, their wings

04:59:59.939 --> 05:00:01.020
finding the same rhythm.

05:00:01.080 --> 05:00:04.020
They shot up into the clouds as the rain

05:00:04.020 --> 05:00:06.419
began cascading down harder and harder.

05:00:06.479 --> 05:00:09.659
Winter ran back over to Hailstorm.

05:00:09.720 --> 05:00:12.299
Fly, he shouted. follow me.

05:00:12.360 --> 05:00:15.659
Maybe I should wait here for Queen

05:00:15.659 --> 05:00:16.439
Scarlet.

05:00:16.500 --> 05:00:18.720
Hailstorm said uncertainly.

05:00:18.779 --> 05:00:21.479
She could probably explain what's

05:00:21.479 --> 05:00:22.200
happening to my head.

05:00:22.319 --> 05:00:25.319
No, Winter shouted.

05:00:25.380 --> 05:00:28.380
He shook his wings furiously, which did

05:00:28.380 --> 05:00:29.639
not help dry him off at all.

05:00:29.700 --> 05:00:31.680
She is the enemy.

05:00:31.740 --> 05:00:32.340
Come on.

05:00:32.400 --> 05:00:34.919
He couldn't believe Scarlet wasn't here

05:00:34.919 --> 05:00:35.220
already.

05:00:35.279 --> 05:00:37.680
How long could it take the nightwing to

05:00:37.680 --> 05:00:38.459
fly back to get her?

05:00:38.520 --> 05:00:41.580
Even with his face burned and frostbitten

05:00:41.580 --> 05:00:44.520
maybe he'd gotten lost, unable to see.

05:00:44.580 --> 05:00:46.919
But Scarlet still should have heard the

05:00:46.919 --> 05:00:47.939
noise of the battle.

05:00:48.000 --> 05:00:49.979
She could be flying down to investigate

05:00:49.979 --> 05:00:50.400
right now.

05:00:50.459 --> 05:00:53.819
He launched himself into the air, and to

05:00:53.819 --> 05:00:56.400
his relief, Hailstorm only hesitated a

05:00:56.400 --> 05:00:57.299
moment before following.

05:00:57.360 --> 05:01:01.139
The rain smashed down on them, harder and

05:01:01.139 --> 05:01:01.500
harder.

05:01:01.560 --> 05:01:04.080
Winter wished it were snow instead.

05:01:04.139 --> 05:01:07.319
He tried imagining the drops, as light

05:01:07.319 --> 05:01:10.020
fluffy flakes of comforting snow, but it

05:01:10.020 --> 05:01:10.439
didn't help.

05:01:10.500 --> 05:01:13.560
Lightning flashed overhead, and he caught

05:01:13.560 --> 05:01:15.720
a glimpse of the odd flapping shape that

05:01:15.720 --> 05:01:17.639
was Kibley and Moon and the sagging

05:01:17.639 --> 05:01:18.779
canopy.

05:01:18.840 --> 05:01:21.119
They were flying west, hopefully out of

05:01:21.119 --> 05:01:22.799
the mountains and toward the kingdom of

05:01:22.799 --> 05:01:23.040
sand.

05:01:23.099 --> 05:01:26.759
And beyond that, the ice kingdom.

05:01:26.819 --> 05:01:27.779
Winter thought.

05:01:27.840 --> 05:01:31.200
He glanced sideways at Hailstorm, now

05:01:31.200 --> 05:01:33.419
keeping up with long, powerful strokes of

05:01:33.419 --> 05:01:34.139
his wings.

05:01:34.200 --> 05:01:35.099
I did it.

05:01:35.159 --> 05:01:36.240
I found him.

05:01:36.299 --> 05:01:37.979
I can take him home.

05:01:38.040 --> 05:01:41.279
He looked forward again, at the dragons

05:01:41.279 --> 05:01:43.200
winging their way over the mountain range

05:01:43.200 --> 05:01:45.720
and felt a strange, stabbing feeling in

05:01:45.720 --> 05:01:46.080
his chest.

05:01:46.139 --> 05:01:47.759
Home.

05:01:47.819 --> 05:01:50.220
Where none of my friends can go.

05:01:50.279 --> 05:01:52.619
Where I must be.

05:01:53.400 --> 05:01:56.520
I mean, where I can be a true ice wing

05:01:56.520 --> 05:01:57.119
once again.

05:01:57.240 --> 05:02:00.720
They flew without stopping for the rest

05:02:00.720 --> 05:02:01.200
of the night.

05:02:01.259 --> 05:02:04.380
Winter and hailstorm soon caught up to

05:02:04.380 --> 05:02:06.299
the others, and then slowed to match

05:02:06.299 --> 05:02:06.720
their speed.

05:02:06.840 --> 05:02:09.599
Although hailstorm gave winter a puzzled

05:02:09.599 --> 05:02:10.200
look as he did.

05:02:10.259 --> 05:02:13.259
After a while, Winter moved in to take

05:02:13.259 --> 05:02:16.020
the canopy from Moon, and she let him, a

05:02:16.020 --> 05:02:18.000
short time after that, she took it from

05:02:18.000 --> 05:02:20.520
Kibley, and the 3 of them traded off

05:02:20.520 --> 05:02:23.220
turns silently for hours, saving their

05:02:23.220 --> 05:02:24.180
breath for flying.

05:02:24.240 --> 05:02:27.419
Hailstorm did not offer to help, but he

05:02:27.419 --> 05:02:29.220
stayed with them, to winter's relief.

05:02:29.279 --> 05:02:32.520
Finally, they flew out of the edge of the

05:02:32.520 --> 05:02:35.159
storm, straight into a cool gray morning

05:02:35.159 --> 05:02:37.139
somewhere in the borderlands between the

05:02:37.139 --> 05:02:39.060
sky kingdom and the kingdom of sand.

05:02:39.060 --> 05:02:41.580
The mountains were behind them, and the

05:02:41.580 --> 05:02:43.259
sun had not yet climbed high enough to

05:02:43.259 --> 05:02:45.360
make it past the peaks, but everything

05:02:45.360 --> 05:02:48.180
was lit in that barely dawn, colorless

05:02:48.180 --> 05:02:49.560
way that makes your eyes tired.

05:02:49.680 --> 05:02:52.619
A small herd of spring box turned

05:02:52.619 --> 05:02:54.900
graceful, antlered heads to the sky

05:02:54.900 --> 05:02:57.060
spotted the dragons, and bounded

05:02:57.060 --> 05:02:59.340
instantly away, their white tails

05:02:59.340 --> 05:03:00.659
flickering as they fled south.

05:03:00.720 --> 05:03:04.259
We can rest at the river, Kibley called.

05:03:04.319 --> 05:03:05.159
Almost there.

05:03:05.220 --> 05:03:08.099
Winter hefted his side of the sling

05:03:08.099 --> 05:03:10.380
trying to adjust his aching talons.

05:03:10.439 --> 05:03:12.959
The entire front half of his body felt

05:03:12.959 --> 05:03:13.680
numb.

05:03:13.740 --> 05:03:15.959
As though he had turned to stone and

05:03:15.959 --> 05:03:18.000
someone had decided to hang a rain wing

05:03:18.000 --> 05:03:19.080
off his petrified arms.

05:03:19.139 --> 05:03:21.659
His head was fuzzy with exhaustion.

05:03:21.720 --> 05:03:24.900
Soon he saw the great 5 tail river ahead

05:03:24.900 --> 05:03:25.200
of them.

05:03:25.259 --> 05:03:28.860
A vast green, brown, blue vein, stretching

05:03:28.860 --> 05:03:30.119
from the desert to the delta.

05:03:30.180 --> 05:03:32.279
According to the history schools.

05:03:32.400 --> 05:03:34.500
This was the most disputed piece of

05:03:34.500 --> 05:03:37.139
territory in all of Pyria, as the sky

05:03:37.139 --> 05:03:39.000
wings and sand wings had fought over

05:03:39.000 --> 05:03:41.040
ownership of the river for centuries.

05:03:41.099 --> 05:03:43.740
Winter wondered if Byrne had promised it

05:03:43.740 --> 05:03:45.840
to the Sky Wings in exchange for their

05:03:45.840 --> 05:03:47.759
alliance in the War of Sand Wings

05:03:47.759 --> 05:03:48.540
succession.

05:03:48.599 --> 05:03:50.459
He wondered if it was only a matter of

05:03:50.459 --> 05:03:52.860
time before Queen Ruby and Queen Thorn

05:03:52.860 --> 05:03:55.439
resumed the battle that had raged for so

05:03:55.439 --> 05:03:55.919
long.

05:03:55.919 --> 05:03:59.040
But for now, the banks of the river were

05:03:59.040 --> 05:03:59.459
peaceful.

05:03:59.520 --> 05:04:02.639
Near the delta, the sand wing settlement

05:04:02.639 --> 05:04:05.279
on the west side, had slowly merged with

05:04:05.279 --> 05:04:07.560
the sky wing village on the east over the

05:04:07.560 --> 05:04:10.860
last 20 years, so that now, red and

05:04:10.860 --> 05:04:13.259
orange and sandy yellow wings dotted the

05:04:13.259 --> 05:04:15.419
sky and the streets side by side.

05:04:15.479 --> 05:04:18.119
A wide white stone bridge had been built

05:04:18.119 --> 05:04:20.580
across the river. lined with shops where

05:04:20.580 --> 05:04:22.680
dragons traded and bartered all day.

05:04:23.099 --> 05:04:25.619
Winter knew this from reports he'd heard

05:04:25.619 --> 05:04:26.340
in the throne room.

05:04:26.400 --> 05:04:28.799
Icewing reconnaissance had kept a close

05:04:28.799 --> 05:04:30.540
eye on the tentative piece that was

05:04:30.540 --> 05:04:33.060
forged between Byrne and Scarlet, would

05:04:33.060 --> 05:04:34.439
it last be on the war?

05:04:34.680 --> 05:04:36.299
Where would that lead the ice wings?

05:04:36.419 --> 05:04:38.939
The next border where the sand wings

05:04:38.939 --> 05:04:40.080
might look for new territory.

05:04:40.200 --> 05:04:43.139
But he had only ever flown over the great

05:04:43.139 --> 05:04:43.500
river.

05:04:43.560 --> 05:04:46.139
He'd only seen the growing town from a

05:04:46.139 --> 05:04:46.380
distance.

05:04:46.439 --> 05:04:49.979
Now, seeing it take shape ahead of them

05:04:49.979 --> 05:04:51.900
he realized that was Kibley's

05:04:51.900 --> 05:04:52.319
destination.

05:04:52.380 --> 05:04:55.380
Winter had expected to stop in a clump of

05:04:55.380 --> 05:04:57.779
trees somewhere, but the sand wing was

05:04:57.779 --> 05:04:59.279
clearly leading them to the town itself.

05:04:59.340 --> 05:05:03.659
Wait, he said, and Kibli immediately

05:05:03.659 --> 05:05:06.360
circled back to take Kinkachu's stretcher

05:05:06.360 --> 05:05:06.659
from him.

05:05:06.720 --> 05:05:09.659
Winter shook out his talons, feeling the

05:05:09.659 --> 05:05:11.700
blood slowly tinkling back into motion.

05:05:11.759 --> 05:05:13.919
Where are you taking us?

05:05:13.979 --> 05:05:15.240
Shouldn't we hide somewhere?

05:05:15.299 --> 05:05:18.240
He gestured at the wild landscape below

05:05:18.240 --> 05:05:18.479
them.

05:05:18.540 --> 05:05:21.060
The sand dotted with palm trees that

05:05:21.060 --> 05:05:23.400
stretched away south, the muddier banks

05:05:23.400 --> 05:05:25.860
farther north, the thicker greenery near

05:05:25.860 --> 05:05:26.939
the town in the Delta.

05:05:27.000 --> 05:05:28.560
There was something about bringing

05:05:28.560 --> 05:05:30.659
hailstorm into a crowded settlement that

05:05:30.659 --> 05:05:31.439
made him nervous.

05:05:31.500 --> 05:05:34.860
Possibility is the best place to hide.

05:05:34.919 --> 05:05:36.299
Kibli argued.

05:05:36.360 --> 05:05:38.939
There are 100s of dragons there, from all

05:05:38.939 --> 05:05:41.159
the tribes these days will blend right in

05:05:41.159 --> 05:05:43.560
and Scarlet won't dare show her face in

05:05:43.560 --> 05:05:46.080
the town, with so many of Ruby's dragons

05:05:46.080 --> 05:05:47.220
patrolling the streets.

05:05:47.220 --> 05:05:49.799
Besides, Kinkaju needs a doctor.

05:05:49.860 --> 05:05:53.819
As usual, Kibli's 9000 very good points

05:05:53.819 --> 05:05:55.439
were impossible to counter.

05:05:55.500 --> 05:05:58.139
Winter glanced at Kinkaju's still white

05:05:58.139 --> 05:05:59.520
face and nodded.

05:05:59.580 --> 05:06:02.880
The town is called possibility?

05:06:03.000 --> 05:06:04.139
Moon asked.

05:06:04.200 --> 05:06:06.779
Her voice was strained, but when winter

05:06:06.779 --> 05:06:08.700
reached for her side of the canopy, she

05:06:08.700 --> 05:06:11.520
flicked her wing at him, No, take a

05:06:11.520 --> 05:06:12.900
longer break, she said.

05:06:12.959 --> 05:06:15.000
I can handle it for another few minutes.

05:06:15.060 --> 05:06:18.299
When the 2 sides merged.

05:06:18.360 --> 05:06:19.860
Neither wanted to take the other's

05:06:19.860 --> 05:06:21.959
original name, Kibley said.

05:06:21.959 --> 05:06:23.520
This was about 7 years ago.

05:06:23.580 --> 05:06:26.400
They talked and disagreed, and talked

05:06:26.400 --> 05:06:28.439
some more, throwing around names like

05:06:28.439 --> 05:06:30.779
hope and peace and union.

05:06:30.840 --> 05:06:33.779
But finally, they put it to a vote, and

05:06:33.779 --> 05:06:35.580
the majority of the citizens chose

05:06:35.580 --> 05:06:36.540
possibility.

05:06:36.599 --> 05:06:39.779
I like that, Moon said.

05:06:39.840 --> 05:06:42.959
The possibility of hope and peace, but

05:06:42.959 --> 05:06:43.799
it's not guaranteed.

05:06:43.860 --> 05:06:45.479
They still have to work for it.

05:06:45.540 --> 05:06:47.939
You know someone here?

05:06:48.000 --> 05:06:49.799
Winter asked Kibley.

05:06:49.860 --> 05:06:52.560
A lot of someone's, Kibley said.

05:06:52.619 --> 05:06:54.840
I met practically the whole sandwing

05:06:54.840 --> 05:06:57.240
tribe after Thorn became queen, as

05:06:57.240 --> 05:06:59.759
everyone came to pay tribute, and to see

05:06:59.759 --> 05:07:01.799
if they could support her as queen, which

05:07:01.799 --> 05:07:04.560
they can, and do, of course, because she

05:07:04.560 --> 05:07:04.979
is amazing.

05:07:05.040 --> 05:07:07.560
Anyway, several of them were from

05:07:07.560 --> 05:07:08.340
possibility.

05:07:08.400 --> 05:07:10.319
I just have to find one who can help us.

05:07:10.439 --> 05:07:13.319
They flew down to land on one of the

05:07:13.319 --> 05:07:15.959
islands in the river as the sun clambered

05:07:15.959 --> 05:07:18.180
over the peaks, scattering warm yellow

05:07:18.180 --> 05:07:20.220
light that outlined the palm trees and

05:07:20.220 --> 05:07:20.400
gold.

05:07:20.459 --> 05:07:23.580
A hippo was planted in the mud, on the

05:07:23.580 --> 05:07:24.419
island's shore.

05:07:24.479 --> 05:07:27.000
It gave the dragons a resigned look as

05:07:27.000 --> 05:07:30.119
they landed, like, fine, go ahead and eat

05:07:30.119 --> 05:07:30.419
me.

05:07:30.479 --> 05:07:32.099
I knew it would happen eventually.

05:07:32.159 --> 05:07:34.560
But they were all too tired to kill

05:07:34.560 --> 05:07:37.319
anything, and after a moment, the hippo

05:07:37.319 --> 05:07:39.119
splashed loudly into the river and

05:07:39.119 --> 05:07:41.759
submerged, probably congratulating itself

05:07:41.759 --> 05:07:43.080
on its impressive stealth.

05:07:43.139 --> 05:07:46.560
Moon climbed onto the canopy.

05:07:46.619 --> 05:07:47.580
As soon as it was spread out on the

05:07:47.580 --> 05:07:50.159
ground, She picked up Kinkaju's talons

05:07:50.159 --> 05:07:51.900
trying to rub warmth into them.

05:07:51.959 --> 05:07:55.619
I'll be back as soon as I can, Kibley

05:07:55.619 --> 05:07:55.979
promised.

05:07:56.040 --> 05:07:58.740
He darted off to the bridge, not far away

05:07:58.740 --> 05:08:00.720
where merchants were already unrolling

05:08:00.720 --> 05:08:02.759
carpets and setting out trays of food

05:08:02.759 --> 05:08:04.619
that exhaled clouds of steam.

05:08:04.680 --> 05:08:07.200
Winter could see Kibley in the gaps

05:08:07.200 --> 05:08:09.360
between the stalls, pacing along the

05:08:09.360 --> 05:08:10.860
length of the bridge and speaking to

05:08:10.860 --> 05:08:11.759
dragons here and there.

05:08:11.819 --> 05:08:15.779
This is weird, Hailstorm said behind

05:08:15.779 --> 05:08:16.319
winter.

05:08:16.380 --> 05:08:19.139
All those dragons from different tribes

05:08:19.139 --> 05:08:22.200
just acting like it's totally normal to

05:08:22.200 --> 05:08:24.959
be together, not as weird as you bonding

05:08:24.959 --> 05:08:26.459
with your strange little trio, though.

05:08:26.520 --> 05:08:28.979
Winter turned to look up at his older

05:08:28.979 --> 05:08:31.500
brother, although it wasn't as far up as

05:08:31.500 --> 05:08:32.159
it used to be.

05:08:32.159 --> 05:08:35.400
Hailstorm looked so exactly like he had

05:08:35.400 --> 05:08:36.720
the day he'd been captured.

05:08:36.779 --> 05:08:39.419
There were no new scars, no signs of

05:08:39.419 --> 05:08:42.060
starvation or beating, or anything winter

05:08:42.060 --> 05:08:43.740
would have expected him to go through in

05:08:43.740 --> 05:08:44.639
a sky wing prison.

05:08:44.700 --> 05:08:47.819
But then, if Hailstorm hadn't been

05:08:47.819 --> 05:08:48.840
himself all this time.

05:08:48.900 --> 05:08:51.959
What do you remember about being

05:08:51.959 --> 05:08:52.919
Scarlett's prisoner?

05:08:52.979 --> 05:08:54.000
Winter asked.

05:08:54.060 --> 05:08:55.799
Hailstorm shook his head.

05:08:55.860 --> 05:08:58.740
I was never her prisoner, he said.

05:08:58.799 --> 05:09:01.439
I've been a loyal soldier to her for.

05:09:01.439 --> 05:09:03.840
I thought it was my whole life, but

05:09:03.840 --> 05:09:04.560
now...

05:09:04.740 --> 05:09:07.380
All my memories of being a sky wing

05:09:07.380 --> 05:09:08.279
dragonette are fading.

05:09:08.340 --> 05:09:11.220
I think I hatched as an ice wing.

05:09:11.279 --> 05:09:13.979
You did, Winter said.

05:09:14.040 --> 05:09:15.959
You're my brother, Hellstorm.

05:09:16.020 --> 05:09:17.700
You've always been an ice wing.

05:09:17.759 --> 05:09:21.240
Hillstorms shuddered in a big, bone

05:09:21.240 --> 05:09:22.619
racking way.

05:09:22.680 --> 05:09:25.560
But I know I've been fighting for Queen

05:09:25.560 --> 05:09:27.540
Scarlet in the war, he said.

05:09:27.599 --> 05:09:29.520
I remember bowing to her.

05:09:29.580 --> 05:09:31.020
Worshiping her.

05:09:31.080 --> 05:09:35.279
I fought, I killed ice wings for her.

05:09:35.340 --> 05:09:38.520
He drew his wings in closer and clenched

05:09:38.520 --> 05:09:39.119
his talons.

05:09:39.240 --> 05:09:40.680
Or was it a dream?

05:09:40.740 --> 05:09:44.700
Maybe I'm still myself, and I'm only

05:09:44.700 --> 05:09:46.319
hallucinating memories of being a nice

05:09:46.319 --> 05:09:46.619
wing.

05:09:46.680 --> 05:09:49.979
With trepidation, he held out his claws

05:09:49.979 --> 05:09:52.200
saw that they were still white, and

05:09:52.200 --> 05:09:53.400
slammed his eyes shut.

05:09:53.459 --> 05:09:56.520
Winter's veins felt as if they were iced

05:09:56.520 --> 05:09:58.560
over and cracking, bits of him

05:09:58.560 --> 05:10:00.060
splintering off inside his body.

05:10:00.119 --> 05:10:04.319
Hailstorm looked the same, but inside, he

05:10:04.319 --> 05:10:05.639
was nothing like the brother winter

05:10:05.639 --> 05:10:06.240
remembered.

05:10:06.299 --> 05:10:10.560
This lost dragon, torn in two, who had

05:10:10.560 --> 05:10:12.659
killed some of his own tribe in service

05:10:12.659 --> 05:10:13.740
to a queen he hated.

05:10:13.799 --> 05:10:16.439
It was worse than all the things winter

05:10:16.439 --> 05:10:18.060
had imagined Scarlet doing to him.

05:10:18.119 --> 05:10:22.439
Hellstorm Focus, Winter said, flicking

05:10:22.439 --> 05:10:23.340
his brother's tail.

05:10:23.400 --> 05:10:25.619
If he treated him like their parents did

05:10:25.619 --> 05:10:28.979
sharp and demanding, Maybe Hailstorm's

05:10:28.979 --> 05:10:30.180
real personality would come back.

05:10:30.240 --> 05:10:32.700
You are my brother Hailstorm.

05:10:32.759 --> 05:10:34.619
You are under some kind of enchantment

05:10:34.619 --> 05:10:35.819
but you're back.

05:10:35.880 --> 05:10:37.979
Just forget about pyrite and be you

05:10:37.979 --> 05:10:38.220
again.

05:10:38.340 --> 05:10:40.740
But which me?

05:10:40.860 --> 05:10:42.599
Hailstorm protested.

05:10:42.659 --> 05:10:46.020
I look at that river and think, I can't

05:10:46.020 --> 05:10:46.319
swim.

05:10:46.380 --> 05:10:49.380
But I remember diving into dark green

05:10:49.380 --> 05:10:51.540
oceans studded with drifting pieces of

05:10:51.540 --> 05:10:51.779
ice.

05:10:51.840 --> 05:10:55.380
I look at my claws and think, I'm clumsy

05:10:55.380 --> 05:10:55.979
and useless.

05:10:56.040 --> 05:10:58.139
But I remember winning every

05:10:58.139 --> 05:10:58.919
competition.

05:10:58.979 --> 05:11:00.900
I remember being at the top of the

05:11:00.900 --> 05:11:01.380
rankings.

05:11:01.439 --> 05:11:04.979
I feel like the air is too warm, and I

05:11:04.979 --> 05:11:07.020
think, I can't wait to go home and roll

05:11:07.020 --> 05:11:10.200
in snow, but I imagine being surrounded

05:11:10.200 --> 05:11:12.779
by ice wings, and I immediately want to

05:11:12.779 --> 05:11:14.459
kill them all to protect my queen.

05:11:14.520 --> 05:11:18.240
He made a noise of despair and pressed

05:11:18.240 --> 05:11:19.979
his forehead, as though he were trying to

05:11:19.979 --> 05:11:21.659
keep his brains from spilling out.

05:11:21.720 --> 05:11:25.319
Winter exchanged a glance with Moon, who

05:11:25.319 --> 05:11:26.759
looked as horrified as he felt.

05:11:26.819 --> 05:11:29.819
Was it even safe to bring hailstorm back

05:11:29.819 --> 05:11:30.540
to the ice kingdom?

05:11:30.599 --> 05:11:33.299
Had he been too badly damaged by living

05:11:33.299 --> 05:11:34.619
as a sky wing for so long?

05:11:34.680 --> 05:11:38.040
Would he ever truly be Winter's brother

05:11:38.040 --> 05:11:38.340
again?

05:11:38.400 --> 05:11:42.959
Chapter 17.

05:11:43.200 --> 05:11:47.400
A trio of red and orange dragons flew

05:11:47.400 --> 05:11:47.880
overhead.

05:11:47.939 --> 05:11:50.279
The wind from their wings sending ripples

05:11:50.279 --> 05:11:52.139
across the river to wash up on the shore

05:11:52.139 --> 05:11:53.400
near winter's talons.

05:11:53.520 --> 05:11:56.819
Hailstorm squinted up at the sky, as if

05:11:56.819 --> 05:11:58.259
he was thinking about following the sky

05:11:58.259 --> 05:11:58.680
wings.

05:11:58.740 --> 05:12:02.639
You just need some time, Winter said

05:12:02.639 --> 05:12:04.860
although it sounded stupid as soon as it

05:12:04.860 --> 05:12:05.580
escaped his mouth.

05:12:05.639 --> 05:12:08.639
The longer your hailstorm again, the more

05:12:08.639 --> 05:12:09.419
you'll feel like yourself.

05:12:09.479 --> 05:12:12.000
At least he hoped that was true.

05:12:12.060 --> 05:12:15.479
He looked down at his claws, and picked a

05:12:15.479 --> 05:12:16.799
piece of wet reed off one of them.

05:12:16.860 --> 05:12:19.319
How long were you like that?

05:12:19.380 --> 05:12:21.540
Trapped in the body of a sky wing?

05:12:21.599 --> 05:12:25.560
I have no idea, Hailstorm answered.

05:12:25.619 --> 05:12:28.020
The Skywing Patrol took me straight to

05:12:28.020 --> 05:12:29.159
Queen Scarlet, I think.

05:12:29.220 --> 05:12:31.740
And then there was a yellowy orange

05:12:31.740 --> 05:12:34.919
dragon who did something to me.

05:12:34.979 --> 05:12:36.599
Wait.

05:12:36.659 --> 05:12:39.240
He dropped his talons and frowned at

05:12:39.240 --> 05:12:39.419
them.

05:12:39.479 --> 05:12:41.520
She looked like me.

05:12:41.580 --> 05:12:43.919
How did I do that to myself?

05:12:43.979 --> 05:12:48.599
I bet pyrite is a kind of mask, Moon

05:12:48.599 --> 05:12:49.139
offered.

05:12:49.200 --> 05:12:52.020
She was still watching Kinkaju, so she

05:12:52.020 --> 05:12:53.700
didn't see the look of repugnance that

05:12:53.700 --> 05:12:56.040
hailstorm shot at her, but winter did.

05:12:56.099 --> 05:12:58.740
Not a real dragon at all.

05:12:58.799 --> 05:13:01.259
I bet the other dragon was wearing the

05:13:01.259 --> 05:13:04.200
pyrite mask when you saw her, and he or

05:13:04.200 --> 05:13:05.459
she put it on you.

05:13:05.520 --> 05:13:07.380
She looked up at winter.

05:13:07.500 --> 05:13:10.740
Maybe it was that night wing, Scarlet's

05:13:10.740 --> 05:13:11.099
ally.

05:13:11.159 --> 05:13:13.439
Scarlet had a lot of confused thoughts

05:13:13.439 --> 05:13:15.540
about what he could do for her, changing

05:13:15.540 --> 05:13:16.979
dragons into other dragons.

05:13:17.040 --> 05:13:19.020
I couldn't understand them because I had

05:13:19.020 --> 05:13:20.279
no idea this was even possible.

05:13:20.340 --> 05:13:23.040
Your sand wing is coming back.

05:13:23.099 --> 05:13:25.919
Hillstorm said, nodding at the river

05:13:25.919 --> 05:13:27.659
where Kibley was swooping toward them.

05:13:27.720 --> 05:13:31.740
Directions to a doctor, he said as he

05:13:31.740 --> 05:13:34.020
landed, brandishing a small scribbled

05:13:34.020 --> 05:13:34.200
map.

05:13:34.259 --> 05:13:36.840
Meerkat is going to fly ahead and tell

05:13:36.840 --> 05:13:37.380
her we're coming.

05:13:37.439 --> 05:13:40.139
He took the side of the canopy again as

05:13:40.139 --> 05:13:41.159
Moon climbed off it.

05:13:41.220 --> 05:13:44.159
Winter took the other side, checking as

05:13:44.159 --> 05:13:45.900
he did that the necklace and pouch were

05:13:45.900 --> 05:13:48.060
still securely tucked beside Kinkaju.

05:13:48.119 --> 05:13:49.919
They were the key to whatever had been

05:13:49.919 --> 05:13:52.560
done to Hailstorm, they must be animus

05:13:52.560 --> 05:13:52.919
touched.

05:13:52.979 --> 05:13:56.279
So the night wing is an animus, but

05:13:56.279 --> 05:13:57.299
pyrite wasn't.

05:13:57.360 --> 05:13:59.939
The magic he'd felt when he touched her

05:13:59.939 --> 05:14:01.799
must have been the spell on Hellstorm.

05:14:01.860 --> 05:14:04.200
Had he felt anything like that from the

05:14:04.200 --> 05:14:04.799
night wing?

05:14:04.860 --> 05:14:07.080
It was hard to remember in the confusion

05:14:07.080 --> 05:14:08.459
of the fight, but he thought so.

05:14:08.520 --> 05:14:11.700
Their little group got a few odd looks as

05:14:11.700 --> 05:14:13.680
they flew through the town, but not as

05:14:13.680 --> 05:14:14.819
many as winter would have expected.

05:14:14.880 --> 05:14:18.000
Most dragons were still asleep, and those

05:14:18.000 --> 05:14:19.680
that were up were busy getting ready for

05:14:19.680 --> 05:14:19.979
the day.

05:14:20.099 --> 05:14:22.740
The smell of bread, baking, and meat

05:14:22.740 --> 05:14:25.020
cooking wove through the streets, and

05:14:25.020 --> 05:14:26.700
winter could hear the tink, tink of small

05:14:26.700 --> 05:14:29.520
hammers, the clattering of mugs, and

05:14:29.520 --> 05:14:31.200
voices calling to each other within the

05:14:31.200 --> 05:14:33.659
walls of the houses, some kind of

05:14:33.659 --> 05:14:35.639
stringed instrument greeted the sunrise

05:14:35.639 --> 05:14:38.040
with musical scales, and hints of half

05:14:38.040 --> 05:14:38.880
played melodies.

05:14:38.939 --> 05:14:41.520
They were on the west side of the river

05:14:41.520 --> 05:14:44.700
now, originally on the sand wing side, but

05:14:44.700 --> 05:14:45.959
winter wouldn't have been able to guess

05:14:45.959 --> 05:14:47.700
which tribe had settled here first.

05:14:47.759 --> 05:14:50.099
The structures were spread out in a

05:14:50.099 --> 05:14:53.040
haphazard, lazy way, some with gardens

05:14:53.040 --> 05:14:55.139
planted around them, some pressed up

05:14:55.139 --> 05:14:57.060
against a crowded row of other buildings

05:14:57.060 --> 05:14:59.700
some were magnificent towers that could

05:14:59.700 --> 05:15:01.380
have fit into any queen's palace.

05:15:01.439 --> 05:15:04.799
Others were barely more than mud huts, he

05:15:04.799 --> 05:15:06.959
saw cascading fountains, and several

05:15:06.959 --> 05:15:09.299
bejeweled statues of stone dragons.

05:15:09.360 --> 05:15:12.000
He also saw a discarded, bloated

05:15:12.000 --> 05:15:14.880
crocodile carcass gathering flies, and a

05:15:14.880 --> 05:15:17.040
brackish puddle with a red tint that

05:15:17.040 --> 05:15:17.819
looked like blood.

05:15:17.880 --> 05:15:20.639
Not ice wing blood, at least.

05:15:20.700 --> 05:15:24.659
What a strange place, Winter said to

05:15:24.659 --> 05:15:25.139
Kibley.

05:15:25.259 --> 05:15:27.419
There's no order to it at all.

05:15:27.479 --> 05:15:30.360
Not like the Ice Kingdom, where your

05:15:30.360 --> 05:15:31.979
ranking on your 7th hatching day

05:15:31.979 --> 05:15:33.900
determined where you would be assigned to

05:15:33.900 --> 05:15:34.139
live.

05:15:34.200 --> 05:15:36.900
The highest ranked lived within the walls

05:15:36.900 --> 05:15:39.000
of the palace itself, like winter's

05:15:39.000 --> 05:15:39.299
parents.

05:15:39.299 --> 05:15:42.119
After you turned 7, you were shifted to

05:15:42.119 --> 05:15:44.040
the adult rankings, where if you worked

05:15:44.040 --> 05:15:46.319
hard enough and moved high enough, you

05:15:46.319 --> 05:15:47.700
might be able to request a transfer

05:15:47.700 --> 05:15:49.380
closer to the center of power.

05:15:49.439 --> 05:15:53.159
Let me guess, all your igloos look

05:15:53.159 --> 05:15:53.819
exactly the same.

05:15:53.880 --> 05:15:55.200
Kibley asked.

05:15:55.259 --> 05:15:58.740
We don't live in igloos, Winter said

05:15:58.740 --> 05:16:01.139
looking down his nose at Kibley, not

05:16:01.139 --> 05:16:03.000
aristocrats, anyway.

05:16:03.060 --> 05:16:04.919
Oh, that's right.

05:16:04.979 --> 05:16:06.119
Kibley said.

05:16:06.180 --> 05:16:07.919
Didn't you say you're related to someone

05:16:07.919 --> 05:16:08.400
important?

05:16:08.520 --> 05:16:11.580
Very funny, Winter said.

05:16:11.639 --> 05:16:13.080
Yes.

05:16:13.139 --> 05:16:16.080
Hellstorm interjected at the same time, a

05:16:16.080 --> 05:16:17.340
little too loudly.

05:16:17.400 --> 05:16:20.220
We're Queen Glacier's nephews.

05:16:20.279 --> 05:16:22.139
Everyone knows that.

05:16:22.259 --> 05:16:25.500
He lifted his chin and regarded a pair of

05:16:25.500 --> 05:16:27.360
passing sand wings with enormous

05:16:27.360 --> 05:16:27.900
disdain.

05:16:27.959 --> 05:16:31.860
To his credit, Kibli managed not to laugh

05:16:31.860 --> 05:16:34.139
although Winter was glad that Hailstorm

05:16:34.139 --> 05:16:36.000
didn't notice the mischievous glint in

05:16:36.000 --> 05:16:36.959
the sand wing's eyes.

05:16:37.020 --> 05:16:40.860
So, you're not igloos don't look like

05:16:40.860 --> 05:16:41.040
this?

05:16:41.159 --> 05:16:42.060
Kibley asked.

05:16:42.119 --> 05:16:45.180
Our cities are all very carefully planned

05:16:45.180 --> 05:16:46.380
Winter explained.

05:16:46.439 --> 05:16:48.540
It's always clear where the power and the

05:16:48.540 --> 05:16:51.119
wealth is, and who has it, and who can

05:16:51.119 --> 05:16:51.840
influence it.

05:16:51.900 --> 05:16:55.380
Hailstorm was nodding, which winter found

05:16:55.380 --> 05:16:56.099
reassuring.

05:16:56.159 --> 05:16:58.319
Maybe his ice wing memories were taking

05:16:58.319 --> 05:16:58.560
over.

05:16:58.619 --> 05:17:01.619
Order and clarity are built into our

05:17:01.619 --> 05:17:03.419
architecture, Winter said.

05:17:03.479 --> 05:17:05.340
The only thing that seems to be built

05:17:05.340 --> 05:17:07.799
into the architecture here is absurdity.

05:17:07.860 --> 05:17:09.900
I love it.

05:17:09.959 --> 05:17:12.119
Kibley inhaled deeply.

05:17:12.180 --> 05:17:14.099
It smells like freedom.

05:17:14.159 --> 05:17:17.040
Freedom to be whoever you want to be, not

05:17:17.040 --> 05:17:18.900
who someone tells you you have to be.

05:17:18.959 --> 05:17:22.319
It smells like rotting water buffalo.

05:17:22.380 --> 05:17:23.639
Winter said.

05:17:23.700 --> 05:17:25.740
He couldn't help but notice the way moon

05:17:25.740 --> 05:17:28.319
was looking at Kibley, as if what he said

05:17:28.319 --> 05:17:30.479
made more sense than what winter had

05:17:30.479 --> 05:17:30.659
said.

05:17:30.779 --> 05:17:32.400
Was that what she wanted?

05:17:32.459 --> 05:17:34.680
Freedom at the expense of order?

05:17:34.740 --> 05:17:37.200
Didn't everyone want to know where they

05:17:37.200 --> 05:17:38.040
fit into the world?

05:17:38.099 --> 05:17:41.819
A few young dragonets burst past them

05:17:41.819 --> 05:17:45.000
laughing. 2 sky wings, 2 sand wings, and

05:17:45.000 --> 05:17:47.459
a mud wing, and veered toward a bigger

05:17:47.459 --> 05:17:49.500
building with pictures of tumbling

05:17:49.500 --> 05:17:51.119
acrobatic dragons painted on the side.

05:17:51.180 --> 05:17:54.119
Does Sonny know about this place?

05:17:54.180 --> 05:17:56.819
Moon asked Kibley, her eyes on the group

05:17:56.819 --> 05:17:57.779
of dragonettes.

05:17:57.840 --> 05:17:59.639
It seems like her dream come true.

05:17:59.700 --> 05:18:03.060
Well, it's not quite as utopian as that

05:18:03.060 --> 05:18:04.200
Kibley said.

05:18:04.259 --> 05:18:06.360
He pointed to an alley where someone had

05:18:06.360 --> 05:18:09.419
scrawled, desert munchers go home, in red

05:18:09.419 --> 05:18:09.840
paint.

05:18:09.900 --> 05:18:13.259
A few doors down, a mudwing sat on a

05:18:13.259 --> 05:18:15.240
corner with one leg wrapped in bandages

05:18:15.240 --> 05:18:16.619
and his wings drooping.

05:18:16.680 --> 05:18:19.259
A hollow coconut half shell sat next to

05:18:19.259 --> 05:18:21.479
him, into which someone had dropped a

05:18:21.479 --> 05:18:24.060
pitiful couple of fried grasshoppers.

05:18:24.119 --> 05:18:26.580
But it's the right idea, Moon said.

05:18:26.639 --> 05:18:28.799
Dragons from different tribes living

05:18:28.799 --> 05:18:30.959
together and getting along, for the most

05:18:30.959 --> 05:18:34.259
part, That's true, and Sonny does know

05:18:34.259 --> 05:18:34.560
about it.

05:18:34.619 --> 05:18:36.779
Kibley said, checking his map.

05:18:36.840 --> 05:18:38.759
But I don't think she's been here yet.

05:18:38.819 --> 05:18:40.500
Look, that's the house.

05:18:40.560 --> 05:18:43.439
He nodded at a compact structure with

05:18:43.439 --> 05:18:45.599
walls of whitewashed bricks and a roof of

05:18:45.599 --> 05:18:46.319
dried reeds.

05:18:46.439 --> 05:18:48.840
A small green flag stuck out of the wall

05:18:48.840 --> 05:18:51.659
by the door, with the word doctor, neatly

05:18:51.659 --> 05:18:52.200
printed on it.

05:18:52.319 --> 05:18:55.680
A young, handsome sandwing came bustling

05:18:55.680 --> 05:18:57.479
out of the door as they approached, and

05:18:57.479 --> 05:18:58.860
reached for winter's side of the

05:18:58.860 --> 05:18:59.159
stretcher.

05:18:59.220 --> 05:19:01.439
Hello, I'm your cat.

05:19:01.500 --> 05:19:03.180
He said with a friendly nod.

05:19:03.240 --> 05:19:04.080
Wait out here.

05:19:04.139 --> 05:19:07.259
We are staying with Kinkaju, Winter

05:19:07.259 --> 05:19:07.740
insisted.

05:19:07.799 --> 05:19:09.299
The Sandwing shook his head.

05:19:09.360 --> 05:19:11.400
Sorry, there's not enough room in there

05:19:11.400 --> 05:19:12.240
for 7 dragons.

05:19:12.299 --> 05:19:14.279
Mayfly is very strict about her space.

05:19:14.340 --> 05:19:15.959
Extra visitors can wait in the garden.

05:19:16.080 --> 05:19:18.720
He pointed to the back of the house, where

05:19:18.720 --> 05:19:20.700
a riot of greenery was trying to vault

05:19:20.700 --> 05:19:21.659
over the roof.

05:19:21.720 --> 05:19:23.700
Mayfly?

05:19:23.759 --> 05:19:24.479
Winter said.

05:19:24.540 --> 05:19:27.360
He kept his grip on the canopy, his claws

05:19:27.360 --> 05:19:28.619
tingling suspiciously.

05:19:28.680 --> 05:19:31.680
Your doctor is a mudwing?

05:19:31.740 --> 05:19:35.279
The best impossibility, said meerkat.

05:19:35.340 --> 05:19:37.619
Winter would not have thought there were

05:19:37.619 --> 05:19:39.900
any mud wings smart enough to be doctors

05:19:39.900 --> 05:19:41.580
let alone the best in town.

05:19:41.639 --> 05:19:43.799
Maybe there wasn't much competition.

05:19:43.860 --> 05:19:45.959
Or maybe this was the wrong place to

05:19:45.959 --> 05:19:46.919
bring Kinkachu.

05:19:46.979 --> 05:19:50.279
One of you can come in with her, meerkat

05:19:50.279 --> 05:19:50.580
said.

05:19:50.639 --> 05:19:53.220
He reached out again, and this time

05:19:53.220 --> 05:19:54.900
Winter relinquished his grasp.

05:19:55.020 --> 05:19:56.400
What choice did they have?

05:19:56.459 --> 05:19:57.900
Where else could they take her?

05:19:57.959 --> 05:20:00.419
But he reached in and fished out the

05:20:00.419 --> 05:20:01.740
animus touched pouch first.

05:20:01.799 --> 05:20:04.200
He wasn't letting magic like that out of

05:20:04.200 --> 05:20:04.560
his sight.

05:20:04.680 --> 05:20:07.740
Kibli opened his wings to let Moon take

05:20:07.740 --> 05:20:09.360
the stretcher from him, and she

05:20:09.360 --> 05:20:11.279
disappeared into the house with meerkat

05:20:11.279 --> 05:20:12.720
and the unconscious dragonette.

05:20:12.779 --> 05:20:15.419
There was an awkward pause.

05:20:15.479 --> 05:20:18.900
Winter, hailstorm and Kibley, glanced

05:20:18.900 --> 05:20:21.180
sideways at one another, shuffled their

05:20:21.180 --> 05:20:23.279
wings, and squinted thoughtfully at the

05:20:23.279 --> 05:20:23.400
sky.

05:20:23.520 --> 05:20:25.860
I'll be in the garden.

05:20:25.979 --> 05:20:28.259
Kibley said finally, edging away.

05:20:28.319 --> 05:20:31.200
Hailstorm stomped over to stick his nose

05:20:31.200 --> 05:20:33.000
in the neighbor's pond, muttering

05:20:33.000 --> 05:20:35.400
something like, don't even know why I'm

05:20:35.400 --> 05:20:35.580
here.

05:20:35.639 --> 05:20:38.880
This seemed like a good time for pacing.

05:20:38.939 --> 05:20:43.080
Which winter did, until he realized he

05:20:43.080 --> 05:20:44.700
had accidentally trampled some bright

05:20:44.700 --> 05:20:46.500
yellow flowers poking up around the base

05:20:46.500 --> 05:20:48.900
of the house, he stepped back and tried

05:20:48.900 --> 05:20:49.860
to keep still.

05:20:49.979 --> 05:20:51.840
Maybe he could see something through the

05:20:51.840 --> 05:20:52.139
windows.

05:20:52.200 --> 05:20:55.020
He explored around the side of the house

05:20:55.020 --> 05:20:57.419
until he found a window open and large

05:20:57.419 --> 05:20:58.439
enough to poke his head in.

05:20:58.500 --> 05:21:01.139
From here, he could see a round, sunlit

05:21:01.139 --> 05:21:03.180
room, clean and uncluttered.

05:21:03.240 --> 05:21:05.759
The only furniture was a large, plain

05:21:05.759 --> 05:21:07.740
white table in the middle, and a few

05:21:07.740 --> 05:21:09.659
shelves on one wall that held neatly

05:21:09.659 --> 05:21:10.740
labeled bottles and jars.

05:21:10.860 --> 05:21:13.259
Kingaju was lying on her back on the

05:21:13.259 --> 05:21:16.020
table, looking smaller than ever, with

05:21:16.020 --> 05:21:17.819
her wings flopping helplessly to either

05:21:17.819 --> 05:21:18.119
side.

05:21:18.180 --> 05:21:21.959
A brown dragon with a wide, flat face was

05:21:21.959 --> 05:21:23.220
examining Kinkachu.

05:21:23.279 --> 05:21:25.680
Her talons moved professionally over the

05:21:25.680 --> 05:21:28.680
dragonette, checking her wings, her bones

05:21:28.680 --> 05:21:29.099
her head.

05:21:29.159 --> 05:21:32.099
She paused for a moment, glancing from

05:21:32.099 --> 05:21:33.720
Kinkaju's tail to her snout.

05:21:33.779 --> 05:21:36.060
Is this a rain wing?

05:21:36.119 --> 05:21:38.220
Yes, Moon answered.

05:21:38.340 --> 05:21:39.900
Her name is Kinkaju.

05:21:39.959 --> 05:21:42.419
Interesting, said the doctor.

05:21:42.479 --> 05:21:43.799
Never seen one before.

05:21:43.860 --> 05:21:46.200
The white scales made me think I swing at

05:21:46.200 --> 05:21:46.319
first.

05:21:46.439 --> 05:21:49.319
She looks nothing like an ice wing.

05:21:49.380 --> 05:21:52.740
Hailstorm exploded with great indignation

05:21:52.740 --> 05:21:55.139
poking his nose over Winter's shoulder

05:21:55.139 --> 05:21:56.220
and making winter jump.

05:21:56.279 --> 05:21:58.439
Get out of my window.

05:21:58.500 --> 05:22:00.599
The doctor snapped with a hiss.

05:22:00.720 --> 05:22:02.159
Stop blocking the light.

05:22:02.220 --> 05:22:02.880
Shoo!

05:22:02.939 --> 05:22:05.400
She flapped her wings, taking a few

05:22:05.400 --> 05:22:06.900
limping steps in their direction.

05:22:06.959 --> 05:22:10.080
Winter realized that the doctor's back

05:22:10.080 --> 05:22:12.840
left leg and half her tail were covered

05:22:12.840 --> 05:22:15.299
in unmistakable frost breath scars

05:22:15.299 --> 05:22:18.360
blackened and blistered, with 2 claws

05:22:18.360 --> 05:22:18.599
missing.

05:22:18.659 --> 05:22:21.240
She'd been in a battle with ice wings.

05:22:21.299 --> 05:22:23.400
Within the last year, if he had to guess

05:22:23.400 --> 05:22:25.619
which meant she probably didn't feel too

05:22:25.619 --> 05:22:27.599
kindly toward ice dragons in general.

05:22:27.659 --> 05:22:32.340
Sorry, sorry, he said, pushing Hailstorm

05:22:32.340 --> 05:22:32.639
back.

05:22:32.700 --> 05:22:36.479
Go sit in the garden, she barked, slamming

05:22:36.479 --> 05:22:37.919
a jar down on the windowsill.

05:22:37.979 --> 05:22:39.779
The smelled like something was stabbing

05:22:39.779 --> 05:22:40.680
his eyeballs.

05:22:40.740 --> 05:22:44.580
Garden, yes, absolutely, Winter said.

05:22:44.639 --> 05:22:47.279
He grabbed Hailstorm's tail and tugged

05:22:47.279 --> 05:22:48.240
him toward the back of the house.

05:22:48.299 --> 05:22:50.819
Winter didn't have a lot of experience

05:22:50.819 --> 05:22:53.340
with gardens, but he suspected they

05:22:53.340 --> 05:22:55.919
didn't usually go up quite as much as

05:22:55.919 --> 05:22:56.700
this one did.

05:22:56.759 --> 05:22:59.580
Seven trees ringed the small plot of land

05:22:59.639 --> 05:23:01.740
each of them exploding with different

05:23:01.740 --> 05:23:02.880
fruits and flowers.

05:23:02.939 --> 05:23:05.639
Vines scaled the back wall of the house

05:23:05.639 --> 05:23:08.400
covered in blue and gold flowers, and

05:23:08.400 --> 05:23:10.680
various ferns and shrubs took up almost

05:23:10.680 --> 05:23:12.060
all the ground space.

05:23:12.119 --> 05:23:14.099
In the center of everything, there was a

05:23:14.099 --> 05:23:16.020
tower that looked as if it was made of

05:23:16.020 --> 05:23:18.959
glass, with overflowing flower pots and

05:23:18.959 --> 05:23:21.659
seed trays on each level, piled up to the

05:23:21.659 --> 05:23:22.319
height of the trees.

05:23:22.380 --> 05:23:25.380
Kibley was flying around the top of the

05:23:25.380 --> 05:23:27.840
greenhouse tower, studying a plant that

05:23:27.840 --> 05:23:29.939
looked like dark purple dragon tongues

05:23:29.939 --> 05:23:31.919
but he flew down when he saw them step

05:23:31.919 --> 05:23:32.520
through the trees.

05:23:32.580 --> 05:23:36.720
Kind of a great idea, he said, flipping

05:23:36.720 --> 05:23:38.700
one wing at the ascending levels of glass

05:23:38.700 --> 05:23:40.740
I'll have to remember to tell Thorn.

05:23:40.799 --> 05:23:45.060
Excuse me, Hailstorm said bossily to

05:23:45.060 --> 05:23:46.619
Winter, ignoring Kibley.

05:23:46.680 --> 05:23:49.860
Why are we obeying a mud wings orders?

05:23:49.919 --> 05:23:52.439
This sounded so much like his real

05:23:52.439 --> 05:23:54.779
brother that Winter's spirits rose.

05:23:54.840 --> 05:23:59.340
Until Hailstorm added, they report to Sky

05:23:59.340 --> 05:24:01.020
Wings, not the other way around.

05:24:01.080 --> 05:24:03.659
Kibley regarded him thoughtfully.

05:24:03.720 --> 05:24:07.500
He's really confused, isn't he?

05:24:07.560 --> 05:24:10.619
You think, Winter growled.

05:24:10.680 --> 05:24:13.259
Imagine being a totally different dragon

05:24:13.259 --> 05:24:15.599
all of a sudden, Kibley said, with

05:24:15.599 --> 05:24:16.619
completely different memories.

05:24:16.680 --> 05:24:19.500
That would be very unsettling.

05:24:19.560 --> 05:24:21.479
Oh, really?

05:24:21.540 --> 05:24:22.319
Winter said.

05:24:22.380 --> 05:24:23.819
Do you think that's what's wrong?

05:24:23.880 --> 05:24:25.380
What a useful insight.

05:24:25.439 --> 05:24:26.340
I hadn't thought of that.

05:24:26.400 --> 05:24:28.619
All right, grouchy.

05:24:28.680 --> 05:24:30.900
Kibley said, giving Winter an

05:24:30.900 --> 05:24:32.939
affectionately exasperated glare.

05:24:33.000 --> 05:24:35.400
I'm just expressing sympathy over here.

05:24:35.459 --> 05:24:38.700
I realize that's an unfamiliar concept

05:24:38.700 --> 05:24:39.720
for ice wings.

05:24:39.779 --> 05:24:43.139
I don't need a sandwing feeling sorry for

05:24:43.139 --> 05:24:43.380
me.

05:24:43.439 --> 05:24:45.419
Hailstorm said stiffly.

05:24:45.479 --> 05:24:48.299
It seems like an awfully complicated

05:24:48.299 --> 05:24:50.459
spell, though, Kibley said after a

05:24:50.459 --> 05:24:50.639
moment.

05:24:50.759 --> 05:24:53.279
What kind of animus would agree to waste

05:24:53.279 --> 05:24:56.520
his power, and lose bits of his soul, just

05:24:56.520 --> 05:24:57.419
to hide a prisoner?

05:24:57.479 --> 05:25:00.060
Why wouldn't Queen Scarlet demand

05:25:00.060 --> 05:25:01.139
something more dramatic?

05:25:01.200 --> 05:25:02.759
Come to think of it?

05:25:02.819 --> 05:25:06.479
If she has an animus nightwing, why isn't

05:25:06.479 --> 05:25:07.439
she queen again right now?

05:25:07.500 --> 05:25:10.200
She could use him to get rid of Ruby in a

05:25:10.200 --> 05:25:11.099
1000000 different ways.

05:25:11.159 --> 05:25:13.259
Winter had no idea.

05:25:13.319 --> 05:25:15.240
It didn't make sense to him either.

05:25:15.299 --> 05:25:17.880
He opened his talons and looked down at

05:25:17.880 --> 05:25:19.560
the crumpled pouch and chain that

05:25:19.560 --> 05:25:20.639
Hailstorm had been wearing.

05:25:20.700 --> 05:25:23.880
At the side of them, hailstorms shuddered

05:25:23.880 --> 05:25:24.299
violently.

05:25:24.360 --> 05:25:27.599
I'm supposed to wear that, he cried.

05:25:27.659 --> 05:25:28.919
It can't ever come off.

05:25:28.979 --> 05:25:30.419
I'll die if it does.

05:25:30.540 --> 05:25:33.419
He stopped, felt his throat for a moment

05:25:33.419 --> 05:25:35.040
and covered his eyes with a groan.

05:25:35.099 --> 05:25:38.040
All right, I hear myself.

05:25:38.099 --> 05:25:40.139
What's in there?

05:25:40.259 --> 05:25:43.020
Kibley asked. leaning closer to study the

05:25:43.020 --> 05:25:46.020
necklace Winter carefully picked at the

05:25:46.020 --> 05:25:47.400
knot that tied the pouch closed.

05:25:47.520 --> 05:25:49.560
He wished his claws were a little

05:25:49.560 --> 05:25:49.919
smaller.

05:25:49.979 --> 05:25:51.419
The knot was very tight.

05:25:51.540 --> 05:25:54.060
Whatever was in here was never meant to

05:25:54.060 --> 05:25:54.360
come out.

05:25:54.419 --> 05:25:57.659
Finally, he was able to hook one claw

05:25:57.659 --> 05:25:59.099
under the knot and slice it loose.

05:25:59.159 --> 05:26:01.979
The rope fell away, and he poked the

05:26:01.979 --> 05:26:04.380
pouch open, shaking the contents into his

05:26:04.380 --> 05:26:05.040
other palm.

05:26:05.099 --> 05:26:07.740
A small folded piece of paper fell out

05:26:07.740 --> 05:26:09.360
crumpled around the corners.

05:26:09.419 --> 05:26:11.580
He peeked into the pouch and shook it a

05:26:11.580 --> 05:26:11.880
bit more.

05:26:11.939 --> 05:26:13.439
There was nothing else in there.

05:26:13.500 --> 05:26:17.459
Careful, Kibley said, his talons

05:26:17.459 --> 05:26:18.479
twitching toward the paper.

05:26:18.540 --> 05:26:19.979
Don't rip it.

05:26:20.040 --> 05:26:22.500
Unfolding the paper was an even more

05:26:22.500 --> 05:26:24.540
delicate operation than opening the pouch

05:26:24.540 --> 05:26:27.180
but at last it was done, revealing words

05:26:27.180 --> 05:26:28.979
scribbled in a dark red ink.

05:26:29.040 --> 05:26:31.860
Some of them were faded, or caught in the

05:26:31.860 --> 05:26:32.759
wrinkles and hard to read.

05:26:32.819 --> 05:26:35.700
Winter found a patch of sunlight, where

05:26:35.700 --> 05:26:37.259
you could smooth it out on a flat rock.

05:26:37.319 --> 05:26:39.419
What does it say?

05:26:39.479 --> 05:26:40.619
Kibley asked.

05:26:40.680 --> 05:26:43.259
Hailstorm was watching curiously now

05:26:43.259 --> 05:26:43.500
too.

05:26:43.560 --> 05:26:46.439
Maybe if he heard the spell, he'd realize

05:26:46.439 --> 05:26:48.599
that it wasn't real and be able to stop

05:26:48.599 --> 05:26:49.860
thinking about pyrite.

05:26:49.919 --> 05:26:54.060
Okay, Winter said, puzzling over the

05:26:54.060 --> 05:26:54.419
note.

05:26:54.479 --> 05:26:58.680
I think it says, enchant this paper so

05:26:58.680 --> 05:27:00.540
that when any dragon wears it in the form

05:27:00.540 --> 05:27:03.360
of a necklace, he or she shall fully

05:27:03.360 --> 05:27:05.880
become a female sky wing named Pyrite

05:27:05.880 --> 05:27:07.560
with the following conditions.

05:27:07.619 --> 05:27:11.340
One, completely loyal to Queen Scarlet

05:27:11.340 --> 05:27:12.540
and the Skywing tribe.

05:27:12.599 --> 05:27:14.880
Two, insecure and weak.

05:27:15.000 --> 05:27:15.720
3.

05:27:15.720 --> 05:27:18.540
No memory of his or her former identity.

05:27:18.599 --> 05:27:21.479
Four, compelled to wear this necklace at

05:27:21.479 --> 05:27:23.520
all times with life or death urgency.

05:27:23.639 --> 05:27:27.180
The writing was cramped and filled every

05:27:27.180 --> 05:27:29.340
inch of the paper, front and back.

05:27:29.400 --> 05:27:31.919
Winter suspected that everything from

05:27:31.919 --> 05:27:34.619
with the following conditions on, had

05:27:34.619 --> 05:27:37.319
been added after the 1st part, as though

05:27:37.319 --> 05:27:39.659
it had been tailored specifically, and

05:27:39.659 --> 05:27:41.700
spitefully for Hailstorm.

05:27:41.759 --> 05:27:45.959
Wow, Kibley said, that is weird.

05:27:46.020 --> 05:27:49.680
I thought animus dragons just thought

05:27:49.680 --> 05:27:51.659
their spells to enchant whatever they

05:27:51.659 --> 05:27:52.860
wanted to animus touch.

05:27:52.979 --> 05:27:54.779
I didn't know they ever wrote them down.

05:27:54.840 --> 05:27:57.840
He leaned over to tap the edges of the

05:27:57.840 --> 05:27:58.619
scrap of paper.

05:27:58.680 --> 05:28:01.439
This looks like it was torn from a larger

05:28:01.439 --> 05:28:01.860
piece.

05:28:01.919 --> 05:28:04.560
Maybe a scroll, since it still wants to

05:28:04.560 --> 05:28:04.979
roll that way.

05:28:05.040 --> 05:28:06.720
Did you hear that?

05:28:06.779 --> 05:28:09.599
Winter asked, turning toward Hailstorm.

05:28:09.659 --> 05:28:10.439
See?

05:28:10.500 --> 05:28:12.119
Pyrite was just a spell.

05:28:12.180 --> 05:28:14.279
Now you're your own real self.

05:28:14.400 --> 05:28:17.939
It was staggering to him how unconvinced

05:28:17.939 --> 05:28:19.259
hailstorm looked.

05:28:19.319 --> 05:28:21.959
Here was evidence. written proof that his

05:28:21.959 --> 05:28:23.759
life as pyrite was all a lie.

05:28:23.880 --> 05:28:27.060
And yet, Hailstorm kept sneaking looks at

05:28:27.060 --> 05:28:29.040
his claws, as if they might change back

05:28:29.040 --> 05:28:29.639
at any moment.

05:28:29.700 --> 05:28:33.000
Winter folded the paper back up and

05:28:33.000 --> 05:28:34.380
crammed it into the pouch.

05:28:34.439 --> 05:28:36.779
He took the chain, threaded it through

05:28:36.779 --> 05:28:39.180
the pouch strings again, and tied a knot

05:28:39.180 --> 05:28:40.020
with a broken links.

05:28:40.080 --> 05:28:42.360
What are you doing?

05:28:42.419 --> 05:28:45.479
Kibley asked, in a tone of voice that

05:28:45.479 --> 05:28:47.220
suggested he knew perfectly well what

05:28:47.220 --> 05:28:47.880
winter was doing?

05:28:47.939 --> 05:28:51.299
I sense a terrible idea coming on.

05:28:51.360 --> 05:28:55.020
I need to see what it feels like, Winter

05:28:55.020 --> 05:28:55.319
said.

05:28:55.380 --> 05:28:56.580
Well, you're here to.

05:28:57.659 --> 05:28:58.380
Well, I'm not alone.

05:28:58.439 --> 05:29:02.880
But it'll turn you into pyrite, who, let's

05:29:02.880 --> 05:29:05.099
face it, is no great loss to the world.

05:29:05.099 --> 05:29:08.099
I mean, it's a tough call, but I'm pretty

05:29:08.099 --> 05:29:09.240
sure we'd rather have you.

05:29:09.299 --> 05:29:10.740
Reasonably sure.

05:29:10.799 --> 05:29:13.380
Like 80% sure.

05:29:13.439 --> 05:29:16.680
Winter whacked one of Kibley's wings with

05:29:16.680 --> 05:29:17.040
his own.

05:29:17.099 --> 05:29:18.659
This isn't a joke.

05:29:18.720 --> 05:29:20.220
I want to know how it works.

05:29:20.279 --> 05:29:22.619
I want to know what hailstorm felt like

05:29:22.619 --> 05:29:23.400
being her.

05:29:23.459 --> 05:29:27.540
I think, well, maybe it'll help me

05:29:27.540 --> 05:29:28.799
understand what he's going through.

05:29:28.860 --> 05:29:33.119
I get it, Kibley said, nodding slowly.

05:29:33.180 --> 05:29:35.159
It just seems like a risk.

05:29:35.220 --> 05:29:37.200
I mean, look at him.

05:29:37.259 --> 05:29:39.540
What if it messes you up the same way?

05:29:39.599 --> 05:29:43.259
That's not going to happen, Winter said.

05:29:43.319 --> 05:29:45.000
I'll only wear it for a moment.

05:29:45.060 --> 05:29:46.740
But that's what you're here for.

05:29:46.799 --> 05:29:49.500
To take the necklace off me, because I

05:29:49.500 --> 05:29:50.639
won't be able to do it myself.

05:29:50.700 --> 05:29:53.520
Don't let me be a Skywing for more than 3

05:29:53.520 --> 05:29:54.240
minutes, all right?

05:29:54.360 --> 05:29:56.639
I don't want her in my head any longer

05:29:56.639 --> 05:29:57.119
than that.

05:29:57.180 --> 05:30:00.299
Hang on, let me see the paper.

05:30:00.360 --> 05:30:02.939
Khibli held out its talons and winter

05:30:02.939 --> 05:30:03.840
passed over the necklace.

05:30:03.959 --> 05:30:06.779
The sandwing fished the scrap out of the

05:30:06.779 --> 05:30:09.180
pouch and read it over, and then, before

05:30:09.180 --> 05:30:11.759
winter realized what he was doing, Kibli

05:30:11.759 --> 05:30:13.319
carefully tore a tiny peas off the

05:30:13.319 --> 05:30:13.560
bottom.

05:30:13.619 --> 05:30:15.599
What did you just do?

05:30:15.720 --> 05:30:18.299
Winter demanded, flaring his wings.

05:30:18.360 --> 05:30:21.299
I ripped off number four, Kibley said.

05:30:21.360 --> 05:30:23.040
The part about needing to wear the

05:30:23.040 --> 05:30:23.819
necklace all the time.

05:30:23.880 --> 05:30:26.159
Let's see if that makes it possible for

05:30:26.159 --> 05:30:26.939
you to take it off yourself.

05:30:27.000 --> 05:30:29.639
He stuffed the spell back into the

05:30:29.639 --> 05:30:30.000
pouch.

05:30:30.060 --> 05:30:32.340
Winter accepted the necklace back

05:30:32.340 --> 05:30:33.659
disgruntled.

05:30:33.720 --> 05:30:35.400
It hadn't even occurred to him to try

05:30:35.400 --> 05:30:36.360
changing the spell.

05:30:36.419 --> 05:30:38.099
What if it didn't work now?

05:30:38.159 --> 05:30:41.220
He realized, though, that he wasn't

05:30:41.220 --> 05:30:41.939
really upset.

05:30:42.000 --> 05:30:44.520
A large part of him didn't expect the

05:30:44.520 --> 05:30:45.779
spell to work on him anyway.

05:30:45.840 --> 05:30:49.619
Even with a high right mask on, as Moon

05:30:49.619 --> 05:30:51.419
had called it, he'd still be winter

05:30:51.419 --> 05:30:51.900
underneath.

05:30:51.959 --> 05:30:55.619
All right, he said, taking a deep

05:30:55.619 --> 05:30:55.979
breath.

05:30:56.099 --> 05:30:57.419
Here we go.

05:30:57.479 --> 05:31:00.540
He dropped the necklace over his head.

05:31:00.599 --> 05:31:04.799
Chapter 18.

05:31:04.979 --> 05:31:07.740
Whoa.

05:31:07.799 --> 05:31:09.119
Where am I?

05:31:09.180 --> 05:31:12.060
Pyrite looked around blinking.

05:31:12.119 --> 05:31:13.200
Was this a garden?

05:31:13.259 --> 05:31:15.900
Why did everything smell like peaches and

05:31:15.900 --> 05:31:16.259
the ocean?

05:31:16.319 --> 05:31:18.360
Hadn't she been in the mountains just a

05:31:18.360 --> 05:31:18.900
minute ago?

05:31:18.959 --> 05:31:19.979
At night?

05:31:20.040 --> 05:31:22.259
Her brain was so useless.

05:31:22.319 --> 05:31:24.360
There were so many things she couldn't

05:31:24.360 --> 05:31:26.819
remember, because she wasn't any good at

05:31:26.819 --> 05:31:28.560
anything. 3 moons.

05:31:28.619 --> 05:31:30.419
It was awful being so pathetic.

05:31:30.479 --> 05:31:32.400
What just happened?

05:31:32.520 --> 05:31:35.040
she asked, turning in a lumbering

05:31:35.040 --> 05:31:35.400
circle.

05:31:35.459 --> 05:31:38.639
There go my stupid talons, getting in my

05:31:38.639 --> 05:31:39.240
way as usual.

05:31:39.299 --> 05:31:41.580
I wish I weren't so clumsy and useless.

05:31:41.639 --> 05:31:44.520
The sand wing was standing nearby

05:31:44.520 --> 05:31:46.680
watching her in a super weird way.

05:31:46.740 --> 05:31:49.020
Did we find Queen Scarlet?

05:31:49.139 --> 05:31:49.979
She asked.

05:31:50.099 --> 05:31:53.400
A surge of powerful emotion rolled

05:31:53.400 --> 05:31:56.159
through her scales, the queen, her most

05:31:56.159 --> 05:31:59.040
wondrous majesty, Queen Scarlet always

05:31:59.040 --> 05:31:59.700
knew what to do.

05:31:59.819 --> 05:32:02.159
She was such an amazing dragon.

05:32:02.220 --> 05:32:04.380
Pyrite missed her awfully.

05:32:04.439 --> 05:32:07.319
When she'd lived in the Sky Palace, she'd

05:32:07.319 --> 05:32:09.659
found a way to see the queen every day

05:32:09.659 --> 05:32:10.860
even if it was just from a distance.

05:32:10.919 --> 05:32:14.159
I'm glad I'm a Sky Wing.

05:32:14.220 --> 05:32:17.340
She looked up at the clouds, streaked

05:32:17.340 --> 05:32:19.139
with pink and gold in a blue sky.

05:32:19.200 --> 05:32:22.500
She could be soaring up there, her wings

05:32:22.500 --> 05:32:25.439
fully extended, diving and spinning like

05:32:25.439 --> 05:32:27.119
she used to with the other Skywing

05:32:27.119 --> 05:32:27.779
dragonettes.

05:32:27.840 --> 05:32:31.020
They were freer than any other tribe, more

05:32:31.020 --> 05:32:33.000
loyal to one another and more

05:32:33.000 --> 05:32:33.479
independent.

05:32:33.540 --> 05:32:35.939
Queen Scarlet trusted them to make

05:32:35.939 --> 05:32:37.319
decisions in battle without her.

05:32:37.380 --> 05:32:40.500
They were the smartest, fastest dragons

05:32:40.500 --> 05:32:41.520
in all of Pyria.

05:32:41.580 --> 05:32:44.939
I am completely loyal to Queen Scarlet.

05:32:45.000 --> 05:32:47.580
One day she would see her queen again.

05:32:47.639 --> 05:32:49.319
And then everything would be all right.

05:32:49.380 --> 05:32:51.119
It would feel like coming home.

05:32:51.180 --> 05:32:53.040
It would feel like flying.

05:32:53.099 --> 05:32:55.619
Pirate.

05:32:55.680 --> 05:32:57.659
The sand wing said slowly.

05:32:57.779 --> 05:32:58.979
What was his name again?

05:32:59.040 --> 05:33:01.080
How do you feel?

05:33:01.139 --> 05:33:04.740
Oh, fine, she said.

05:33:04.799 --> 05:33:07.259
Her memory was a little fuzzy, but that

05:33:07.259 --> 05:33:07.979
wasn't worth mentioning.

05:33:08.040 --> 05:33:09.659
Where are the other three?

05:33:09.720 --> 05:33:13.139
Do you remember anything about winter?

05:33:13.139 --> 05:33:13.919
he asked.

05:33:13.979 --> 05:33:17.340
You mean like that he's an enormous

05:33:17.340 --> 05:33:17.880
grump?

05:33:17.939 --> 05:33:19.319
Pyrite said.

05:33:19.380 --> 05:33:22.020
She saw silvery scales moving out of the

05:33:22.020 --> 05:33:24.360
corner of her eye and turned, but it was

05:33:24.360 --> 05:33:26.700
a different ice wing, bigger than winter

05:33:26.700 --> 05:33:27.779
staring at her.

05:33:27.840 --> 05:33:29.819
What was his problem?

05:33:29.819 --> 05:33:31.919
He looked as if she was his mother back

05:33:31.919 --> 05:33:34.259
from the dead or something, like he knew

05:33:34.259 --> 05:33:34.500
her.

05:33:34.560 --> 05:33:36.779
Although she was sure she'd never seen

05:33:36.779 --> 05:33:37.139
him before.

05:33:37.200 --> 05:33:39.419
Eee, ugh.

05:33:39.479 --> 05:33:40.259
Ice Wings.

05:33:40.319 --> 05:33:43.020
Can I look at your necklace?

05:33:43.080 --> 05:33:44.759
The Sandwing asked.

05:33:44.819 --> 05:33:48.000
Pyrite glanced down and realized she had

05:33:48.000 --> 05:33:49.799
some kind of pouch on a chain around her

05:33:49.799 --> 05:33:50.040
neck.

05:33:50.099 --> 05:33:52.020
Huh, she said.

05:33:52.080 --> 05:33:53.520
Sure, I guess.

05:33:53.580 --> 05:33:56.639
As she reached for it, She felt a twinge

05:33:56.639 --> 05:33:58.080
of, should I do this?

05:33:58.200 --> 05:34:01.020
And then she was lifting it over her neck

05:34:01.020 --> 05:34:02.279
and then she was gone.

05:34:02.340 --> 05:34:05.819
Winter dropped the necklace as if it were

05:34:05.819 --> 05:34:07.439
made of lava and leaped away from it.

05:34:07.560 --> 05:34:08.939
Yah!

05:34:09.000 --> 05:34:09.779
He shouted.

05:34:09.840 --> 05:34:11.159
He clawed at his head.

05:34:11.220 --> 05:34:12.540
Get her out.

05:34:12.599 --> 05:34:13.080
Get her out.

05:34:13.139 --> 05:34:16.979
Winter, it's over, Kibley called, catching

05:34:16.979 --> 05:34:17.580
his talons.

05:34:17.639 --> 05:34:18.659
You're you again.

05:34:18.720 --> 05:34:19.619
She's not real.

05:34:19.740 --> 05:34:23.400
But winter could still feel pyrites

05:34:23.400 --> 05:34:26.220
scraping banal thoughts, like a damp

05:34:26.220 --> 05:34:28.139
mildew lingering around his mind.

05:34:28.200 --> 05:34:30.779
No wonder a hailstorm was so disturbed.

05:34:30.840 --> 05:34:33.360
Pyrite thinking was not just different

05:34:33.360 --> 05:34:36.119
from his own personality, but it had an

05:34:36.119 --> 05:34:38.639
insidious dullness to it that left a

05:34:38.639 --> 05:34:40.439
miasma after only a few minutes.

05:34:40.500 --> 05:34:43.259
He couldn't imagine living with it for 2

05:34:43.259 --> 05:34:45.299
entire years, and then trying to shake it

05:34:45.299 --> 05:34:45.659
all off.

05:34:45.720 --> 05:34:49.919
Except for the part about being a Skywing

05:34:49.919 --> 05:34:52.680
loyal to Scarlet, that part was crystal

05:34:52.680 --> 05:34:54.959
clear in a shiny way that was equally

05:34:54.959 --> 05:34:55.380
horrible.

05:34:55.439 --> 05:34:58.979
Winter had known, with a logical part of

05:34:58.979 --> 05:35:01.380
his mind, that other dragons were loyal

05:35:01.380 --> 05:35:03.540
to their own tribes, but obviously they

05:35:03.540 --> 05:35:03.840
were wrong.

05:35:03.900 --> 05:35:06.479
Ice Wings were the greatest tribe in

05:35:06.479 --> 05:35:08.099
Pyria, and that was a fact.

05:35:08.159 --> 05:35:10.919
Except now he had this memory of

05:35:10.919 --> 05:35:13.080
believing the same thing about Skywings

05:35:13.080 --> 05:35:15.299
and believing it with all his heart.

05:35:15.360 --> 05:35:18.060
Was that really how Skywings felt?

05:35:18.119 --> 05:35:20.700
And sea wings and rain wings?

05:35:20.700 --> 05:35:22.139
and even night wings?

05:35:22.200 --> 05:35:24.840
He did not want to try turning into any

05:35:24.840 --> 05:35:26.159
other dragons to find out.

05:35:26.220 --> 05:35:28.680
He turned to pick up the pouch again

05:35:28.680 --> 05:35:31.619
perhaps to destroy it, to rip the scroll

05:35:31.619 --> 05:35:33.779
and pyrites very existence into tiny

05:35:33.779 --> 05:35:36.900
shreds, and found hailstorm reaching for

05:35:36.900 --> 05:35:37.139
it.

05:35:37.200 --> 05:35:41.040
No, Winter shouted, snatching it out of

05:35:41.040 --> 05:35:41.400
his grasp.

05:35:41.520 --> 05:35:43.680
Hillstorm, don't even touch it.

05:35:43.740 --> 05:35:47.580
Maybe I should change back, Hellstorm

05:35:47.580 --> 05:35:47.880
said.

05:35:47.939 --> 05:35:50.880
His face twisting, as though crocodiles

05:35:50.880 --> 05:35:52.259
might come crawling out of it.

05:35:52.439 --> 05:35:54.360
At least when I'm pyrite.

05:35:54.419 --> 05:35:56.520
I only have one set of memories, right?

05:35:56.580 --> 05:35:58.080
That's what the scroll said.

05:35:58.139 --> 05:36:00.599
And I was happy as a sky wing.

05:36:00.659 --> 05:36:02.819
It was easier than being a nice wing.

05:36:02.880 --> 05:36:05.459
No rankings, no one comparing me to

05:36:05.459 --> 05:36:06.360
everyone else all the time.

05:36:06.419 --> 05:36:09.360
No mother and father expecting me to be

05:36:09.360 --> 05:36:09.720
perfect.

05:36:09.840 --> 05:36:11.340
And I had fire.

05:36:11.400 --> 05:36:12.720
Fire was amazing.

05:36:12.779 --> 05:36:15.599
Winter, please, let me change back.

05:36:15.659 --> 05:36:18.060
That is completely insane.

05:36:18.119 --> 05:36:19.560
Winter said.

05:36:19.619 --> 05:36:21.720
He tried to make his voice as cutting as

05:36:21.720 --> 05:36:22.200
their mother's.

05:36:22.319 --> 05:36:24.419
When you're fully yourself again.

05:36:24.479 --> 05:36:26.639
You'll recognize that there is nothing

05:36:26.639 --> 05:36:28.799
preferable about being a sky wing.

05:36:28.860 --> 05:36:30.900
No one would ever choose to be anything

05:36:30.900 --> 05:36:31.979
but an ice wing.

05:36:32.040 --> 05:36:35.279
Kibley cleared his throat significantly

05:36:35.279 --> 05:36:36.659
and Winter shot him a glare.

05:36:36.779 --> 05:36:40.860
The problem was, he felt it now, not the

05:36:40.860 --> 05:36:43.139
desire to be pyrite, but the appeal of

05:36:43.139 --> 05:36:43.979
being a sky wing.

05:36:44.040 --> 05:36:46.439
He couldn't let hailstorm see that

05:36:46.439 --> 05:36:46.560
though.

05:36:46.619 --> 05:36:49.139
He needed to be strong so that hailstorm

05:36:49.139 --> 05:36:49.979
could be too.

05:36:50.040 --> 05:36:53.220
You will never be pyrite again, Winter

05:36:53.220 --> 05:36:53.459
said.

05:36:53.520 --> 05:36:55.319
Get that through your frozen head.

05:36:55.439 --> 05:36:59.580
Hailstorm growled furiously, and for a

05:36:59.580 --> 05:37:00.959
moment Winter wondered if he would

05:37:00.959 --> 05:37:02.520
actually attack his brother to get the

05:37:02.520 --> 05:37:03.119
necklace back.

05:37:03.180 --> 05:37:06.060
But finally, hailstorm spun on his heels

05:37:06.060 --> 05:37:08.400
and marched to the far end of the garden

05:37:08.400 --> 05:37:11.099
where the trees gave way to a street that

05:37:11.099 --> 05:37:12.779
was starting to be crowded with dragons

05:37:12.779 --> 05:37:13.680
and rolling carts.

05:37:13.799 --> 05:37:16.799
Good speech, Kibley said.

05:37:16.860 --> 05:37:19.200
All kind of mean, but in a convincing

05:37:19.200 --> 05:37:19.380
way.

05:37:19.439 --> 05:37:22.680
I need to be alone for a moment, winter

05:37:22.680 --> 05:37:23.099
said.

05:37:23.159 --> 05:37:26.580
Kibli raised his wings and stepped back

05:37:26.580 --> 05:37:28.740
with a little bow of acknowledgment.

05:37:28.799 --> 05:37:30.959
Winter needed to straighten out his own

05:37:30.959 --> 05:37:31.319
brain.

05:37:31.380 --> 05:37:35.040
He'd wanted to step into pyrite talons so

05:37:35.040 --> 05:37:37.560
he could understand hailstorm, but he

05:37:37.560 --> 05:37:39.119
didn't want to understand him this well.

05:37:39.240 --> 05:37:42.119
He sat down under a fig tree and closed

05:37:42.119 --> 05:37:44.459
his eyes, taking deep breaths.

05:37:44.580 --> 05:37:47.340
I am Winter the Ice Wing.

05:37:47.340 --> 05:37:49.799
I have always been an ice wing.

05:37:49.860 --> 05:37:53.400
Slowly, the pyriteness began to clear.

05:37:53.459 --> 05:37:55.860
I am Winter the Ice Wing.

05:37:55.919 --> 05:37:58.020
I am loyal to Queen Glacier.

05:37:58.080 --> 05:38:00.959
I will reach the top of the rankings one

05:38:00.959 --> 05:38:01.139
day.

05:38:01.259 --> 05:38:03.900
What would life have been like as a

05:38:03.900 --> 05:38:04.500
skywing?

05:38:04.560 --> 05:38:07.139
Would he really have loved the tribe of

05:38:07.139 --> 05:38:08.340
Sky Dragons that much?

05:38:08.400 --> 05:38:11.580
I am Winter the Ice Wing.

05:38:11.700 --> 05:38:15.060
Be strong, be vigilant, strike first

05:38:15.060 --> 05:38:16.200
trust nobody.

05:38:16.259 --> 05:38:19.380
His father's mantra didn't quite sit

05:38:19.380 --> 05:38:21.779
right in his mind anymore, but that

05:38:21.779 --> 05:38:22.979
wasn't because of pyrite.

05:38:23.040 --> 05:38:26.700
It was because of Kibli and Kinkaju, and

05:38:26.700 --> 05:38:28.259
most of all, Moon.

05:38:28.319 --> 05:38:30.959
As he thought of her, he heard a door

05:38:30.959 --> 05:38:33.360
close, and opened his eyes to see her

05:38:33.360 --> 05:38:34.979
emerging from the back of the doctor's

05:38:34.979 --> 05:38:35.220
house.

05:38:35.279 --> 05:38:38.700
I am Winter, the ice wing.

05:38:38.759 --> 05:38:41.159
I do not make friends with dragons from

05:38:41.159 --> 05:38:41.700
other tribes.

05:38:41.759 --> 05:38:44.880
I am not in love with a dragon.

05:38:44.939 --> 05:38:45.720
I am sworn to hate.

05:38:45.779 --> 05:38:48.360
Is Kinkaju all right?

05:38:48.419 --> 05:38:49.860
Kibley asked Moon.

05:38:49.919 --> 05:38:52.080
Winter stood up and went over to join

05:38:52.080 --> 05:38:52.439
them.

05:38:52.560 --> 05:38:54.720
He glanced over at his brother as he did

05:38:54.720 --> 05:38:57.180
and saw him standing under a tree with

05:38:57.180 --> 05:38:59.700
round orange fruit, banging his head on

05:38:59.700 --> 05:39:00.540
the trunk.

05:39:00.599 --> 05:39:01.680
Winter sighed.

05:39:01.740 --> 05:39:04.919
Moon shook her head, curling her tail

05:39:04.919 --> 05:39:05.639
around her talons.

05:39:05.700 --> 05:39:08.639
She has a skull fracture, and 3 or 4

05:39:08.639 --> 05:39:09.299
broken ribs.

05:39:09.360 --> 05:39:10.439
She said.

05:39:10.500 --> 05:39:12.720
She sounded as though she was trying to

05:39:12.720 --> 05:39:14.220
imitate the doctor's professional

05:39:14.220 --> 05:39:16.619
delivery, but her voice wavered as she

05:39:16.619 --> 05:39:16.860
spoke.

05:39:16.919 --> 05:39:20.819
Also, a hairline break near one elbow, and

05:39:20.819 --> 05:39:22.799
bruising all along her spine and left

05:39:22.799 --> 05:39:23.580
side.

05:39:23.639 --> 05:39:25.319
The doctor says she needs to stay

05:39:25.319 --> 05:39:27.540
completely still for probably a month

05:39:27.540 --> 05:39:28.439
maybe longer.

05:39:28.500 --> 05:39:30.720
Is she awake?

05:39:30.779 --> 05:39:31.799
Winter asked.

05:39:31.860 --> 05:39:32.880
No.

05:39:32.939 --> 05:39:35.459
Moon ducked her head, shaking back

05:39:35.459 --> 05:39:35.819
tears.

05:39:35.880 --> 05:39:37.200
The.

05:39:37.439 --> 05:39:39.959
The doctor doesn't know when Kinkachu

05:39:39.959 --> 05:39:40.380
might wake up.

05:39:40.439 --> 05:39:43.560
Mayfly stuck her snout out one of the

05:39:43.560 --> 05:39:45.180
back windows and beckoned to moon.

05:39:45.240 --> 05:39:48.360
I need your authorization on this, she

05:39:48.360 --> 05:39:48.720
said.

05:39:48.779 --> 05:39:51.119
Brandishing a small scroll and an ink

05:39:51.119 --> 05:39:51.419
pot.

05:39:51.479 --> 05:39:54.299
To have her transferred to the clinic

05:39:54.299 --> 05:39:55.919
they'll take care of her, although

05:39:55.919 --> 05:39:57.240
they'll want to know what really happened

05:39:57.240 --> 05:39:57.659
to her.

05:39:57.720 --> 05:40:01.319
I told you, Moon said, with a hint of

05:40:01.319 --> 05:40:02.099
exasperation.

05:40:02.159 --> 05:40:03.720
A dragon attacked her.

05:40:03.779 --> 05:40:05.880
Are you sure?

05:40:05.939 --> 05:40:06.900
the doctor asked.

05:40:06.959 --> 05:40:09.900
She wasn't hit by an avalanche, or thrown

05:40:09.900 --> 05:40:12.000
off a cliff, or trampled by a herd of

05:40:12.000 --> 05:40:12.479
hippos?

05:40:12.540 --> 05:40:14.400
That really happened to a patient of mine

05:40:14.400 --> 05:40:14.759
once?

05:40:14.819 --> 05:40:16.680
There's no shame in admitting it.

05:40:16.740 --> 05:40:18.299
Hippos can happen to anybody.

05:40:18.360 --> 05:40:22.139
Just a dragon. knocking her into a tree

05:40:22.139 --> 05:40:23.759
Moon said firmly.

05:40:23.819 --> 05:40:27.060
She took the scroll and ink pot, dipped

05:40:27.060 --> 05:40:28.979
her claw into the black ink, and signed

05:40:28.979 --> 05:40:29.279
her name.

05:40:29.340 --> 05:40:30.659
I promise.

05:40:30.720 --> 05:40:33.779
I saw it too, Winter agreed.

05:40:33.840 --> 05:40:35.580
He was really big.

05:40:35.639 --> 05:40:37.200
Kibley offered.

05:40:37.259 --> 05:40:40.860
With Super Dragon strength, Mayfly

05:40:40.860 --> 05:40:41.759
muttered skeptically.

05:40:41.819 --> 05:40:44.220
She took the scroll back from Moon and

05:40:44.220 --> 05:40:44.880
stomped back inside.

05:40:44.939 --> 05:40:47.759
Moon looked around, then carefully set

05:40:47.759 --> 05:40:49.020
the ink pot on the windowsill.

05:40:49.080 --> 05:40:51.959
Oh, good, Kibley said.

05:40:52.020 --> 05:40:55.200
So our new mystery nightwing friend has

05:40:55.200 --> 05:40:58.439
inexplicable animus powers and unusual

05:40:58.439 --> 05:40:59.580
strength.

05:40:59.639 --> 05:40:59.939
Super.

05:41:00.000 --> 05:41:02.580
Also, now he hates us.

05:41:02.639 --> 05:41:04.439
Don't forget, Winter added.

05:41:04.500 --> 05:41:07.020
But you saw what we did to his face.

05:41:07.080 --> 05:41:08.159
Moon said.

05:41:08.220 --> 05:41:11.099
Between my fire and your frost breath.

05:41:11.159 --> 05:41:12.840
He's probably much less dangerous now.

05:41:12.900 --> 05:41:16.560
The creeping spider legs feeling under

05:41:16.560 --> 05:41:19.080
Winter's scales suggested otherwise.

05:41:19.139 --> 05:41:22.139
In his experience, no good could come of

05:41:22.139 --> 05:41:24.180
adding vengeance to a dragon's list of

05:41:24.180 --> 05:41:25.259
reasons to get up in the morning.

05:41:25.319 --> 05:41:27.240
Eagle!

05:41:27.299 --> 05:41:30.060
Hailstorm shouted suddenly, sending a

05:41:30.060 --> 05:41:31.259
jolt of alarm through winter.

05:41:31.319 --> 05:41:33.540
He rolled around to see his brother at

05:41:33.540 --> 05:41:35.759
the back gate, craning his neck to see

05:41:35.759 --> 05:41:37.740
over a sea wing pulling a fish laden

05:41:37.740 --> 05:41:38.159
cart.

05:41:38.220 --> 05:41:39.599
Eagle!

05:41:39.659 --> 05:41:42.060
Hailstrong called again, his voice full

05:41:42.060 --> 05:41:42.659
of excitement.

05:41:42.720 --> 05:41:44.159
Eagle, over here.

05:41:44.220 --> 05:41:47.099
Uh-oh, Kibley muttered.

05:41:47.159 --> 05:41:49.560
Winter bolted over to his brother's side

05:41:49.560 --> 05:41:52.259
as a large sky wing, the color of raw

05:41:52.259 --> 05:41:54.119
tuna, shouldered his way through the

05:41:54.119 --> 05:41:55.319
crowd and stared down at them.

05:41:55.380 --> 05:41:58.139
Two more burly sky wings stepped up

05:41:58.139 --> 05:41:59.459
behind him, glowering.

05:41:59.580 --> 05:42:01.439
How do you know my name?

05:42:01.500 --> 05:42:03.000
The Sky Wing demanded.

05:42:03.060 --> 05:42:03.900
Who are you?

05:42:03.959 --> 05:42:09.299
I'm Hailstorm faltered, but don't you, I'm

05:42:09.299 --> 05:42:11.759
we fought together under General Ruby.

05:42:11.819 --> 05:42:15.720
She's queen, Ruby, now, Eagle snapped, and

05:42:15.720 --> 05:42:17.459
I don't remember fighting any ice wings

05:42:17.459 --> 05:42:18.360
and leaving them alive.

05:42:18.419 --> 05:42:21.119
He eyed hailstorm up and down.

05:42:21.180 --> 05:42:24.060
I suppose if I did, that's a mistake that

05:42:24.060 --> 05:42:24.659
could be corrected.

05:42:24.720 --> 05:42:26.700
But how did he know your name?

05:42:26.819 --> 05:42:29.220
asked one of the other Skywings.

05:42:29.279 --> 05:42:30.659
Right.

05:42:30.779 --> 05:42:33.299
Eagles said, his eyes narrowing to

05:42:33.299 --> 05:42:33.840
slits.

05:42:33.900 --> 05:42:36.000
Explain that, whale leader.

05:42:36.119 --> 05:42:37.799
He doesn't?

05:42:37.860 --> 05:42:38.700
Winter started.

05:42:38.759 --> 05:42:41.279
But Eagle growled low in his throat

05:42:41.279 --> 05:42:42.060
cutting him off.

05:42:42.119 --> 05:42:44.159
Let the lizard speak.

05:42:44.220 --> 05:42:47.400
Hailstorm stammered for a minute and

05:42:47.400 --> 05:42:51.599
finally mumbled, I, I, I thought we were

05:42:51.599 --> 05:42:52.020
friends.

05:42:52.080 --> 05:42:54.299
He rubbed his eyes miserably.

05:42:54.360 --> 05:42:56.819
The 2 flanking sky wings looked

05:42:56.819 --> 05:42:57.659
incredulous.

05:42:57.720 --> 05:42:59.639
Eagles swelled with fury.

05:42:59.700 --> 05:43:00.599
What?

05:43:00.720 --> 05:43:01.680
he roared.

05:43:01.740 --> 05:43:04.619
He lashed out, reaching over the gate, and

05:43:04.619 --> 05:43:06.299
grabbed hailstorm by the throat.

05:43:06.360 --> 05:43:07.619
How dare you?

05:43:07.680 --> 05:43:09.419
I would never be friends with an ice

05:43:09.419 --> 05:43:09.840
wing.

05:43:09.959 --> 05:43:10.860
Is this a joke?

05:43:10.919 --> 05:43:12.779
Did someone pay you to make a fool out of

05:43:12.779 --> 05:43:12.959
me?

05:43:13.020 --> 05:43:14.880
He didn't mean it.

05:43:14.939 --> 05:43:17.700
Winter yelled, trying to pull eagle's

05:43:17.700 --> 05:43:18.540
talons off his brother.

05:43:18.599 --> 05:43:20.040
He's just confused.

05:43:20.159 --> 05:43:23.459
Kibley darted up on Hailstorm's other

05:43:23.459 --> 05:43:25.740
side and grabbed the Sky Wing too.

05:43:25.799 --> 05:43:27.299
He was hit on the head.

05:43:27.419 --> 05:43:30.779
Kibley explained quickly, a war injury.

05:43:30.840 --> 05:43:32.580
His memory is all messed up.

05:43:32.700 --> 05:43:34.680
Please don't hurt him.

05:43:34.799 --> 05:43:36.000
Winter cried.

05:43:36.060 --> 05:43:38.639
Hillstorm's face was turning bluer than

05:43:38.639 --> 05:43:38.939
usual.

05:43:39.000 --> 05:43:42.479
Drop that ice wing right now, said

05:43:42.479 --> 05:43:43.740
another voice behind Winter.

05:43:43.799 --> 05:43:46.680
He turned and saw meerkat standing in the

05:43:46.680 --> 05:43:49.259
garden beside Moon, arching his venomous

05:43:49.259 --> 05:43:50.159
tail menacingly.

05:43:50.220 --> 05:43:52.259
I order you by the authority of the

05:43:52.259 --> 05:43:52.799
enclave.

05:43:52.860 --> 05:43:55.979
To winter's surprise, Eagle immediately

05:43:55.979 --> 05:43:57.119
let go of Hailstorm.

05:43:57.180 --> 05:43:59.400
The ice wing collapsed back against the

05:43:59.400 --> 05:44:00.900
tree, gasping for breath.

05:44:00.959 --> 05:44:05.400
Sorry, the Sky Wing said to Meerkat, all

05:44:05.400 --> 05:44:06.659
the rage gone from his voice.

05:44:06.720 --> 05:44:09.060
Didn't realize he was with you, meerkat.

05:44:09.119 --> 05:44:10.500
He took a step back.

05:44:10.560 --> 05:44:12.720
He was saying some mighty stupid things

05:44:12.720 --> 05:44:13.139
that's all.

05:44:13.200 --> 05:44:15.119
Head injury.

05:44:15.180 --> 05:44:16.560
Kibley said again.

05:44:16.619 --> 05:44:19.380
Winter crouched beside his brother, but

05:44:19.380 --> 05:44:20.459
Hailstorm pushed him away.

05:44:20.520 --> 05:44:24.360
Oh, another wounded veteran, Eagles

05:44:24.360 --> 05:44:24.659
said.

05:44:24.720 --> 05:44:26.939
All 3 Skywings were nodding.

05:44:27.000 --> 05:44:28.200
I've seen plenty of those.

05:44:28.319 --> 05:44:29.700
Hope he recovers.

05:44:29.759 --> 05:44:32.700
He jerked his chin at winter, then turned

05:44:32.700 --> 05:44:34.740
and shoved his way back into the throng

05:44:34.740 --> 05:44:36.779
half of whom had stopped to stare at the

05:44:36.779 --> 05:44:37.020
fight.

05:44:37.080 --> 05:44:41.639
Moving right along, Mirkat said, waving

05:44:41.639 --> 05:44:42.900
at the audience until they all started

05:44:42.900 --> 05:44:43.500
moving again.

05:44:43.560 --> 05:44:47.759
It was just a mistake, Hillstorm, Winter

05:44:47.759 --> 05:44:49.380
said to his brother, in a low voice.

05:44:49.380 --> 05:44:51.659
You've only been out from under the spell

05:44:51.659 --> 05:44:52.380
for a few hours.

05:44:52.500 --> 05:44:53.880
Give it some time.

05:44:53.939 --> 05:44:56.040
You'll forget all about pyrite once

05:44:56.040 --> 05:44:57.720
you're surrounded by ice wings again.

05:44:57.779 --> 05:44:59.819
Hailstorm shook his head.

05:44:59.880 --> 05:45:01.740
Winter didn't know if that meant

05:45:01.740 --> 05:45:03.479
disagreement or despair.

05:45:03.540 --> 05:45:05.639
Winter.

05:45:05.639 --> 05:45:07.860
Hailstorm croaked softly.

05:45:07.919 --> 05:45:10.740
Winter leaned closer to here, and

05:45:10.740 --> 05:45:13.020
Hailstorm turned hopeless blue eyes up

05:45:13.020 --> 05:45:13.319
toward him.

05:45:13.380 --> 05:45:14.939
Winter.

05:45:15.000 --> 05:45:16.919
I want to go home.

05:45:16.979 --> 05:45:21.360
Chapter 19.

05:45:21.599 --> 05:45:24.659
You're leaving now?

05:45:24.720 --> 05:45:26.700
Moon asked, dismayed.

05:45:26.759 --> 05:45:29.459
I have to get him back to the Ice Kingdom

05:45:29.459 --> 05:45:32.400
Winter said, glancing over Tailstorm.

05:45:32.459 --> 05:45:34.619
His brother was sitting at the base of

05:45:34.619 --> 05:45:36.599
the greenhouse tower, with his wings

05:45:36.599 --> 05:45:38.459
folded close around him, and his face

05:45:38.459 --> 05:45:38.939
hidden.

05:45:39.060 --> 05:45:42.479
I feel like he won't be safe until he's

05:45:42.479 --> 05:45:43.259
with our tribe again.

05:45:43.319 --> 05:45:45.299
And then he'll remember he's really an

05:45:45.299 --> 05:45:45.840
ice wing.

05:45:45.900 --> 05:45:47.340
I hope.

05:45:47.580 --> 05:45:49.919
But Kinkaju.

05:45:50.040 --> 05:45:52.020
Moon started then trailed off.

05:45:52.080 --> 05:45:54.659
There's nothing I can do for her.

05:45:54.720 --> 05:45:56.159
Winter pointed out.

05:45:56.279 --> 05:45:57.240
Right?

05:45:57.299 --> 05:45:59.400
We're just waiting until she wakes up.

05:45:59.520 --> 05:46:02.639
Moon looked down at her clause, leaving

05:46:02.639 --> 05:46:05.159
the if she wakes up, unsaid.

05:46:05.220 --> 05:46:08.279
None of you can come with us to the Ice

05:46:08.279 --> 05:46:09.900
Kingdom anyway, Winter said.

05:46:10.020 --> 05:46:12.180
You should go back to Jade Mountain.

05:46:12.299 --> 05:46:14.220
No way.

05:46:14.279 --> 05:46:16.740
Kibley said, and Moon glanced up at him

05:46:16.740 --> 05:46:17.340
in surprise.

05:46:17.400 --> 05:46:20.040
We have to find the lost city of night.

05:46:20.099 --> 05:46:22.080
Remember the Thunder and Eyes.

05:46:22.139 --> 05:46:24.540
Earth shaking, ground being scorched, all

05:46:24.540 --> 05:46:24.779
of that?

05:46:24.900 --> 05:46:27.360
I don't know about you, but I'm in favor

05:46:27.360 --> 05:46:29.880
of that prophecy, not coming true.

05:46:29.939 --> 05:46:31.919
Now that we've found hailstorm.

05:46:31.979 --> 05:46:33.900
I say it's time to get on top of the

05:46:33.900 --> 05:46:34.919
whole saving the world thing.

05:46:34.979 --> 05:46:38.400
That's what I was going to do, Moon

05:46:38.400 --> 05:46:38.939
cried.

05:46:39.000 --> 05:46:41.220
I've been having these awful nightmares

05:46:41.220 --> 05:46:41.700
every night.

05:46:41.759 --> 05:46:44.099
I mean, worse than ever.

05:46:44.159 --> 05:46:46.439
I've got to figure out the prophecy.

05:46:46.500 --> 05:46:49.080
But I wasn't sure if anyone would want to

05:46:49.080 --> 05:46:49.439
come with me.

05:46:49.500 --> 05:46:52.020
Um, me.

05:46:52.080 --> 05:46:55.319
Kibble said, waving a wing at himself as

05:46:55.319 --> 05:46:57.000
though that was as obvious as the sun.

05:46:57.060 --> 05:46:58.319
Sign me up.

05:46:58.439 --> 05:47:01.200
Moon turned hopeful eyes toward winter.

05:47:01.259 --> 05:47:04.380
Maybe after you take hailstorm home?

05:47:04.439 --> 05:47:05.040
she asked.

05:47:05.099 --> 05:47:07.619
Then you could come back, and we could

05:47:07.619 --> 05:47:09.060
all look for the lost city of night

05:47:09.060 --> 05:47:09.360
together.

05:47:09.419 --> 05:47:12.060
He wanted to say yes.

05:47:12.119 --> 05:47:14.220
He wasn't even sure which reason was

05:47:14.220 --> 05:47:14.700
strongest.

05:47:14.700 --> 05:47:17.099
Was it because he believed the world

05:47:17.099 --> 05:47:17.939
needed saving?

05:47:18.000 --> 05:47:20.040
Because he wanted to protect Jade

05:47:20.040 --> 05:47:20.520
Mountain?

05:47:20.580 --> 05:47:22.740
Or because he couldn't stand the idea of

05:47:22.740 --> 05:47:25.319
Moon and Kibley searching Pyria, alone

05:47:25.319 --> 05:47:26.580
together.

05:47:26.700 --> 05:47:30.959
I, I can't, he said.

05:47:31.020 --> 05:47:33.479
Ah, that was why.

05:47:33.540 --> 05:47:35.759
Because he hadn't wanted to watch her

05:47:35.759 --> 05:47:38.340
face do this, this crumbling into

05:47:38.340 --> 05:47:39.060
disappointment.

05:47:39.119 --> 05:47:42.060
But there were 50,000 reasons why he

05:47:42.060 --> 05:47:42.900
couldn't say yes.

05:47:43.020 --> 05:47:45.840
Reasons like Moon's safety of Winter's

05:47:45.840 --> 05:47:46.860
parents found out about her.

05:47:46.919 --> 05:47:49.439
Reasons like needing to prove his loyalty

05:47:49.439 --> 05:47:51.599
to the ice wings and struggle back into

05:47:51.599 --> 05:47:52.259
the rankings.

05:47:52.319 --> 05:47:54.599
Reasons like his own sanity.

05:47:54.659 --> 05:47:56.759
I can't.

05:47:56.880 --> 05:47:58.439
He said again.

05:47:58.500 --> 05:48:01.380
All at once, he was aware of hailstorms

05:48:01.380 --> 05:48:04.560
standing behind him, listening, hailstorms

05:48:04.560 --> 05:48:06.779
blue eyes, watching Winter's next move.

05:48:06.900 --> 05:48:10.020
Listen, get this into your head.

05:48:10.139 --> 05:48:11.639
I'm an ice wing.

05:48:11.759 --> 05:48:14.340
He hated that it came out sounding almost

05:48:14.340 --> 05:48:15.119
like a question.

05:48:15.180 --> 05:48:17.759
He wasn't like Hillstorm.

05:48:17.819 --> 05:48:18.779
He knew who he was.

05:48:18.840 --> 05:48:22.860
I'm an ice wing, he said again, firmly.

05:48:22.919 --> 05:48:25.500
That means I belong in the Ice Kingdom

05:48:25.500 --> 05:48:26.580
with my own tribe.

05:48:26.639 --> 05:48:28.740
I should never have gone to Jade

05:48:28.740 --> 05:48:29.099
Mountain.

05:48:29.159 --> 05:48:30.720
This prophecy.

05:48:30.779 --> 05:48:32.880
If it's even real, has nothing to do with

05:48:32.880 --> 05:48:34.979
me, and I should have nothing to do with

05:48:34.979 --> 05:48:35.159
you.

05:48:35.220 --> 05:48:41.099
But, Moon said, I thought, She reached

05:48:41.099 --> 05:48:43.319
toward him, her dark eyes puzzled and

05:48:43.319 --> 05:48:43.619
hurt.

05:48:43.680 --> 05:48:44.939
What?

05:48:45.000 --> 05:48:46.319
That we were friends?

05:48:46.380 --> 05:48:49.020
Winter spat, shoving her talons away.

05:48:49.080 --> 05:48:51.000
We can't be friends.

05:48:51.060 --> 05:48:53.040
We can't be anything.

05:48:53.099 --> 05:48:56.520
We can never, never be what I dream of us

05:48:56.520 --> 05:48:56.700
being.

05:48:56.759 --> 05:48:59.939
You're my sworn enemy, Nightwing.

05:49:00.000 --> 05:49:01.740
I never asked for you to follow me

05:49:01.740 --> 05:49:01.979
around.

05:49:02.099 --> 05:49:05.099
Hey, Kibley said.

05:49:05.159 --> 05:49:06.720
He sounded genuinely angry.

05:49:06.840 --> 05:49:08.520
Don't talk to her like that.

05:49:08.580 --> 05:49:11.520
She helped you find your brother, and she

05:49:11.520 --> 05:49:12.540
risked her life to do it.

05:49:12.599 --> 05:49:13.799
What is wrong with you?

05:49:13.860 --> 05:49:18.000
It's all right, Moon said, brushing

05:49:18.000 --> 05:49:19.139
Kibley's wing with her own.

05:49:19.259 --> 05:49:22.319
Her eyes flickered to Hillstorm, close

05:49:22.319 --> 05:49:23.040
behind winter.

05:49:23.099 --> 05:49:25.200
He's striking first.

05:49:25.259 --> 05:49:25.860
That's all.

05:49:25.979 --> 05:49:27.540
Winter.

05:49:27.599 --> 05:49:29.639
I believe that you're one of the best

05:49:29.639 --> 05:49:32.520
bravest, truest dragons in Pyria.

05:49:32.639 --> 05:49:35.400
I'll never be your enemy, no matter what

05:49:35.400 --> 05:49:35.759
you say.

05:49:35.819 --> 05:49:38.880
But go ahead and leave, if that's what

05:49:38.880 --> 05:49:39.180
you want.

05:49:39.240 --> 05:49:41.880
It's not what I want.

05:49:41.939 --> 05:49:45.119
His chest felt as if it might burst.

05:49:45.180 --> 05:49:47.400
Spilling shattered ice everywhere.

05:49:47.459 --> 05:49:49.799
It's how things have to be.

05:49:49.860 --> 05:49:53.459
We'll wait for you, Kibley said.

05:49:53.520 --> 05:49:54.540
Right here.

05:49:54.599 --> 05:49:57.180
In case you change your mind and realize

05:49:57.180 --> 05:49:59.819
that stopping a big world destroying

05:49:59.819 --> 05:50:01.680
prophecy is what you were hatched to do.

05:50:01.740 --> 05:50:06.060
Don't bother, Winter said, hoping his

05:50:06.060 --> 05:50:08.340
cold snarl was still as intimidating as

05:50:08.340 --> 05:50:09.479
he'd once been able to make it.

05:50:09.540 --> 05:50:14.040
One week, Moon said, glancing at Kibley

05:50:14.040 --> 05:50:14.700
for confirmation.

05:50:14.759 --> 05:50:17.580
We can wait one week, and then we're

05:50:17.580 --> 05:50:17.759
leaving.

05:50:17.819 --> 05:50:20.340
Then you're idiots.

05:50:20.400 --> 05:50:21.180
I don't care.

05:50:21.240 --> 05:50:22.919
Winter nearly shouted.

05:50:22.979 --> 05:50:25.200
Why did it have to be so impossible?

05:50:25.259 --> 05:50:27.479
How could they still even want to be his

05:50:27.479 --> 05:50:29.340
friends when he was pushing them away so

05:50:29.340 --> 05:50:29.639
hard?

05:50:29.700 --> 05:50:31.799
Three moons.

05:50:31.860 --> 05:50:32.459
Leave me alone.

05:50:32.580 --> 05:50:34.560
He turned to Hailstorm.

05:50:34.619 --> 05:50:35.580
Let's go.

05:50:35.639 --> 05:50:38.040
As he spread his wings and leaped into

05:50:38.040 --> 05:50:38.520
the sky.

05:50:38.580 --> 05:50:40.799
Kibli called, don't be a stranger.

05:50:40.919 --> 05:50:44.040
And he thought he heard Moon say, We'll

05:50:44.040 --> 05:50:44.279
miss you.

05:50:44.340 --> 05:50:48.299
Hailstorm soared into the lead, his wings

05:50:48.299 --> 05:50:50.279
glittering silver and white, with

05:50:50.279 --> 05:50:52.259
reflections of rose from the setting sun

05:50:52.259 --> 05:50:52.799
ahead of them.

05:50:52.860 --> 05:50:55.259
He grinned over his shoulder at his

05:50:55.259 --> 05:50:55.680
little brother.

05:50:55.740 --> 05:50:58.319
The 1st happy expression Winter had seen

05:50:58.319 --> 05:50:58.860
from him all day.

05:50:58.919 --> 05:51:01.560
Winter forced himself to look forward.

05:51:01.619 --> 05:51:03.840
He would not look back at the garden.

05:51:03.900 --> 05:51:06.599
At the black and pale yellow dragons

05:51:06.599 --> 05:51:07.139
watching him go.

05:51:07.200 --> 05:51:10.500
He would not admit to himself that he

05:51:10.500 --> 05:51:11.159
would miss them too.

05:51:11.279 --> 05:51:14.819
He would ice over the hole in his chest

05:51:14.819 --> 05:51:16.979
the way he'd cleared out the pyrite

05:51:16.979 --> 05:51:20.159
memories, ahead were his parents and

05:51:20.159 --> 05:51:22.380
Queen Glacier, and he would need to be

05:51:22.380 --> 05:51:23.939
perfect again before he faced them.

05:51:24.000 --> 05:51:27.000
The Ice Kingdom was waiting for him.

05:51:27.060 --> 05:51:31.439
Part three.

05:51:31.500 --> 05:51:33.419
Beneath the ice.

05:51:33.479 --> 05:51:37.139
Chapter 20.

05:51:37.500 --> 05:51:41.340
Winter and Hailstorm reached the southern

05:51:41.340 --> 05:51:43.200
border of the Ice Kingdom the next day at

05:51:43.200 --> 05:51:43.799
Twilight.

05:51:43.799 --> 05:51:46.860
A few stars and one claw shaped moon were

05:51:46.860 --> 05:51:48.599
already glimmering in the violet sky.

05:51:48.659 --> 05:51:51.659
Winter could see the great ice cliff that

05:51:51.659 --> 05:51:53.759
marked the border, stretching from one

05:51:53.759 --> 05:51:56.040
horizon to the other in a sheer unbroken

05:51:56.040 --> 05:51:56.279
line.

05:51:56.400 --> 05:51:59.099
Hillstorm squinted at it as they

05:51:59.099 --> 05:52:00.060
approached.

05:52:00.119 --> 05:52:01.380
Is that a wall?

05:52:01.439 --> 05:52:02.279
He asked.

05:52:02.340 --> 05:52:03.959
What's the point of that?

05:52:04.020 --> 05:52:05.819
A wall can't keep out dragons.

05:52:05.939 --> 05:52:08.880
You don't remember the great ice cliff?

05:52:08.939 --> 05:52:10.560
Winter replied, startled.

05:52:10.619 --> 05:52:13.439
It's probably our oldest animus gift.

05:52:13.500 --> 05:52:15.540
Hailstorm shrugged.

05:52:15.599 --> 05:52:18.000
Seems like a waste of magic, he said.

05:52:18.060 --> 05:52:19.560
We're going to fly right over it.

05:52:19.619 --> 05:52:22.860
Right, because we're ice wings.

05:52:22.919 --> 05:52:23.700
Winter said.

05:52:23.819 --> 05:52:26.700
But if we were from any other tribe, the

05:52:26.700 --> 05:52:28.799
great ice cliff would shoot icicle spears

05:52:28.799 --> 05:52:30.779
at us and most likely kill us.

05:52:30.840 --> 05:52:32.700
It's secret defense of magic.

05:52:32.759 --> 05:52:34.860
The other tribes don't know about it.

05:52:34.919 --> 05:52:37.500
Usually no one else ventures this far

05:52:37.500 --> 05:52:38.159
north anyway.

05:52:38.220 --> 05:52:40.860
But if they did, they'd get a chilly

05:52:40.860 --> 05:52:41.880
pointy surprise.

05:52:41.939 --> 05:52:44.580
Hailstorm balked in midair.

05:52:44.639 --> 05:52:47.099
What if it doesn't let me pass?

05:52:47.159 --> 05:52:48.119
he cried.

05:52:48.180 --> 05:52:51.299
It will, Winter said, a little

05:52:51.299 --> 05:52:51.900
irritated.

05:52:51.959 --> 05:52:54.240
You're an ice wing hillstorm.

05:52:54.299 --> 05:52:57.180
The wall will recognize that, and so will

05:52:57.180 --> 05:52:57.720
everyone else.

05:52:57.779 --> 05:53:01.319
His brother did not look convinced, but

05:53:01.319 --> 05:53:03.180
some of his old bravados seem to be

05:53:03.180 --> 05:53:05.880
coming back, even if he was scared, he

05:53:05.880 --> 05:53:07.619
was clearly determined not to show it.

05:53:07.680 --> 05:53:10.740
Of course, the wall did not react as they

05:53:10.740 --> 05:53:11.279
flew over it.

05:53:11.340 --> 05:53:13.680
Winter remembered the last time it had

05:53:13.680 --> 05:53:15.959
gone off, a year and a half ago when one

05:53:15.959 --> 05:53:17.880
of Blaze's sand wings had apparently

05:53:17.880 --> 05:53:20.400
decided to wrap herself in a few blankets

05:53:20.400 --> 05:53:22.740
and explore the mysterious ice kingdom.

05:53:22.799 --> 05:53:25.439
They'd found her, what must have been

05:53:25.439 --> 05:53:28.380
days later, on the north side of the wall

05:53:28.380 --> 05:53:30.659
she was half buried in a snowdrift, with

05:53:30.659 --> 05:53:31.799
a spear through her heart.

05:53:31.860 --> 05:53:34.680
Her sky colored blankets frozen to her

05:53:34.680 --> 05:53:37.139
scales, so at 1st they thought she was a

05:53:37.139 --> 05:53:37.740
sea wing.

05:53:37.799 --> 05:53:40.380
Other than that, the wall had been quiet

05:53:40.380 --> 05:53:41.580
for winter's entire life.

05:53:41.639 --> 05:53:44.759
The other tribes didn't know about it, but

05:53:44.759 --> 05:53:46.259
they did know about the subzero

05:53:46.259 --> 05:53:48.240
temperatures and freezing wind in the ice

05:53:48.240 --> 05:53:48.659
kingdom.

05:53:48.720 --> 05:53:51.060
Even during the war of Sandwing

05:53:51.060 --> 05:53:53.759
succession, no one had dared send troops

05:53:53.759 --> 05:53:54.599
into their territory.

05:53:54.659 --> 05:53:56.819
It would have been a complete massacre if

05:53:56.819 --> 05:53:57.060
they had.

05:53:57.119 --> 05:54:00.240
Which made Winter think about the animus

05:54:00.240 --> 05:54:01.680
who had built and enchanted the wall

05:54:01.680 --> 05:54:04.380
1000s of years ago, the gift of defense

05:54:04.380 --> 05:54:05.099
it was called.

05:54:05.159 --> 05:54:07.319
Was it worth it at the time?

05:54:07.380 --> 05:54:09.599
Were there more attacks on the kingdom

05:54:09.599 --> 05:54:10.020
back then?

05:54:10.080 --> 05:54:12.779
Were there dragons from other tribes who

05:54:12.779 --> 05:54:14.520
had figured out how to survive in the

05:54:14.520 --> 05:54:16.680
Arctic cold long enough to stage an

05:54:16.680 --> 05:54:18.060
invasion, at least?

05:54:18.060 --> 05:54:21.000
Or perhaps the animus was looking forward

05:54:21.000 --> 05:54:22.020
not back.

05:54:22.139 --> 05:54:25.080
Perhaps he anticipated a day when some

05:54:25.080 --> 05:54:27.599
other tribe's animus might craft heat

05:54:27.599 --> 05:54:29.520
generating armor that could carry

05:54:29.520 --> 05:54:31.500
soldiers into the farthest reaches of the

05:54:31.500 --> 05:54:31.740
north.

05:54:31.799 --> 05:54:35.040
But even if someone did that, why conquer

05:54:35.040 --> 05:54:36.540
a land you couldn't possibly live in?

05:54:36.659 --> 05:54:39.959
In any case, if winter were an animus

05:54:39.959 --> 05:54:42.000
dragon, building a wall like that would

05:54:42.000 --> 05:54:43.919
not have been his major contribution to

05:54:43.919 --> 05:54:45.180
ice wing society.

05:54:45.240 --> 05:54:47.700
The Ice Kingdom didn't need defensive

05:54:47.700 --> 05:54:48.060
magic.

05:54:48.180 --> 05:54:50.819
What it needed now was something to help

05:54:50.819 --> 05:54:52.860
them conquer other tribes.

05:54:52.919 --> 05:54:55.319
If they still had Animas Dragons, they

05:54:55.319 --> 05:54:56.880
could have won the War of Sandwing

05:54:56.880 --> 05:54:57.959
succession in no time at all.

05:54:58.020 --> 05:55:00.840
And then all the territory Blaze had

05:55:00.840 --> 05:55:02.520
promised Queen Glacier would now be

05:55:02.520 --> 05:55:02.819
theirs.

05:55:02.880 --> 05:55:06.299
More important, no ice wing soldiers

05:55:06.299 --> 05:55:07.080
would have had to die.

05:55:07.139 --> 05:55:09.720
And Hailstorm would never have ended up

05:55:09.720 --> 05:55:10.860
as Scarlet's prisoner.

05:55:10.919 --> 05:55:14.040
It all goes back to Faux Slayer.

05:55:14.099 --> 05:55:16.740
If she had never stolen Prince Arctic

05:55:16.740 --> 05:55:18.659
imagine how powerful we could be now.

05:55:18.720 --> 05:55:21.900
We'd have another 2000 years of animus

05:55:21.900 --> 05:55:22.319
gifts.

05:55:22.380 --> 05:55:24.240
We could have been the rulers of all

05:55:24.240 --> 05:55:24.840
Pyria.

05:55:24.900 --> 05:55:27.119
We definitely have something that helped

05:55:27.119 --> 05:55:27.659
us in battle.

05:55:27.720 --> 05:55:30.360
Exploding snowballs that kill every

05:55:30.360 --> 05:55:33.060
dragon they touch, or maps that tell us

05:55:33.060 --> 05:55:35.520
exactly where all our enemies are, or

05:55:35.520 --> 05:55:38.040
diamonds that hypnotize every other queen

05:55:38.040 --> 05:55:39.240
into surrendering to us.

05:55:39.299 --> 05:55:42.240
When he thought of the ice wing lives

05:55:42.240 --> 05:55:44.880
lost in the war, and for nothing in the

05:55:44.880 --> 05:55:47.099
end, he wished he could climb back

05:55:47.099 --> 05:55:49.680
through time, find an animus ice wing

05:55:49.680 --> 05:55:51.599
maybe the one who wasted her gift on

05:55:51.599 --> 05:55:53.639
defense, and force her to make something

05:55:53.639 --> 05:55:55.259
that would wipe out all the night wings

05:55:55.259 --> 05:55:55.560
at once.

05:55:55.680 --> 05:55:59.040
Uneasiness whispered through his bones at

05:55:59.040 --> 05:55:59.400
that thought.

05:55:59.459 --> 05:56:02.040
I thought he'd had a 100 times before.

05:56:02.099 --> 05:56:04.500
But now he could picture the night wings

05:56:04.500 --> 05:56:06.720
in their ramshackle rainforest village

05:56:06.720 --> 05:56:09.180
trying to rebuild after the horrors of

05:56:09.180 --> 05:56:09.840
the volcano.

05:56:09.900 --> 05:56:11.819
He could remember the shivering

05:56:11.819 --> 05:56:13.860
dragonette and the wingery. and the

05:56:13.860 --> 05:56:16.380
protective parents he'd seen, including

05:56:16.380 --> 05:56:17.340
Moon's mother.

05:56:17.400 --> 05:56:20.040
It was actually completely terrifying to

05:56:20.040 --> 05:56:22.380
think that any dragon with magic could

05:56:22.380 --> 05:56:25.020
easily wipe out an entire tribe with just

05:56:25.020 --> 05:56:26.040
one enchanted object.

05:56:26.099 --> 05:56:29.040
It was even more terrifying to realize

05:56:29.040 --> 05:56:31.319
that your own tribe no longer had that

05:56:31.319 --> 05:56:31.740
magic.

05:56:31.799 --> 05:56:33.840
But your worst enemies did.

05:56:33.900 --> 05:56:37.139
Why hadn't the Night Wings used Anna's

05:56:37.139 --> 05:56:39.119
power to destroy the ice wings long ago?

05:56:39.240 --> 05:56:41.819
Did they have so little control over

05:56:41.819 --> 05:56:43.080
their animus dragons?

05:56:43.139 --> 05:56:45.720
Or so little vision of what their stolen

05:56:45.720 --> 05:56:46.380
magic could do?

05:56:46.439 --> 05:56:49.500
He worried around these questions as he

05:56:49.500 --> 05:56:51.360
and Hailstorm flew over the snowy

05:56:51.360 --> 05:56:54.299
landscape, dotted with sheer cliffs, and

05:56:54.299 --> 05:56:57.180
pure blue lakes, and the sky grew darker

05:56:57.180 --> 05:56:57.840
and darker.

05:56:57.900 --> 05:57:00.959
A couple of white owls swept past below

05:57:00.959 --> 05:57:03.900
them, pale flickers, like moths in the

05:57:03.900 --> 05:57:06.900
moonlight, screeching to each other, a

05:57:06.900 --> 05:57:09.000
herd of shaggy caribou surrounded one of

05:57:09.000 --> 05:57:11.220
the lakes, stamping nervously as the

05:57:11.220 --> 05:57:12.240
dragons passed overhead.

05:57:12.299 --> 05:57:14.939
Winter thought about grabbing one to eat

05:57:14.939 --> 05:57:16.740
but they'd already stopped earlier that

05:57:16.740 --> 05:57:19.919
day to hunt, and now, with home so close

05:57:19.919 --> 05:57:22.200
he just wanted to get there and face the

05:57:22.200 --> 05:57:22.799
queen already.

05:57:22.919 --> 05:57:25.439
It was close to midnight when they saw

05:57:25.439 --> 05:57:27.360
the lights of Queen Glacier's Palace

05:57:27.360 --> 05:57:29.520
ahead of them, shimmering blue, green

05:57:29.520 --> 05:57:31.439
silver, like captured starlight.

05:57:31.500 --> 05:57:34.619
The dark ocean acted as a mirror, sending

05:57:34.619 --> 05:57:36.540
the same lights dancing in blurred

05:57:36.540 --> 05:57:38.279
mimicry around the base of the palace.

05:57:38.340 --> 05:57:41.520
A galaxy of smaller lights spiraled out

05:57:41.520 --> 05:57:43.979
in 5 curved arms from the palace

05:57:43.979 --> 05:57:46.080
illuminating the dwellings of lower

05:57:46.080 --> 05:57:46.919
aristocrats.

05:57:46.979 --> 05:57:49.080
The training schools that were open all

05:57:49.080 --> 05:57:51.419
night, and the shimmering ice sculpture

05:57:51.419 --> 05:57:51.779
gardens.

05:57:51.840 --> 05:57:54.900
Winter heard hailstorm catch his breath

05:57:54.900 --> 05:57:55.500
beside him.

05:57:55.560 --> 05:57:58.500
It's beautiful, he murmured.

05:57:58.560 --> 05:57:59.880
I'd forgotten.

05:57:59.939 --> 05:58:03.240
Wait until you see it up close, Winter

05:58:03.240 --> 05:58:03.599
said.

05:58:03.659 --> 05:58:05.639
His chest swelling with pride.

05:58:05.700 --> 05:58:08.340
The ice kingdom was beautiful, without

05:58:08.340 --> 05:58:08.880
question.

05:58:08.939 --> 05:58:11.040
He wished he could show it to Moon.

05:58:11.099 --> 05:58:14.099
But she would never get past the great

05:58:14.099 --> 05:58:16.799
ice cliff alive, and his parents would

05:58:16.799 --> 05:58:18.479
send her to the bottom of a frozen lake

05:58:18.479 --> 05:58:19.080
if she did.

05:58:19.139 --> 05:58:22.080
They swooped down to land at the grand

05:58:22.080 --> 05:58:24.720
entrance of the palace, a set of crystal

05:58:24.720 --> 05:58:26.459
studded gates about halfway up the

05:58:26.459 --> 05:58:27.240
central keep.

05:58:27.240 --> 05:58:29.400
The gates were carved in the shape of

05:58:29.400 --> 05:58:31.919
giant dragon wings, making the small ice

05:58:31.919 --> 05:58:33.900
sculptures of dragons and wings and

05:58:33.900 --> 05:58:36.240
talons that topped all the columns and

05:58:36.240 --> 05:58:36.779
vinials.

05:58:36.900 --> 05:58:39.299
Although it was possible to fly over the

05:58:39.299 --> 05:58:41.459
palace walls straight into the interior

05:58:41.459 --> 05:58:44.400
courtyards, it was considered gauche, and

05:58:44.400 --> 05:58:45.840
therefore career suicide.

05:58:45.900 --> 05:58:48.900
According to protocol, visitors waited at

05:58:48.900 --> 05:58:49.799
the gates to be admitted.

05:58:49.860 --> 05:58:53.340
Queen Glacier's Astonishing Palace was

05:58:53.340 --> 05:58:56.459
also animus touched, the gift of splendor

05:58:56.459 --> 05:58:59.400
designed, built, and enchanted centuries

05:58:59.400 --> 05:59:02.700
ago by a pair of animus twins, with magic

05:59:02.700 --> 05:59:04.380
that ensured its walls of ice would never

05:59:04.380 --> 05:59:07.500
melt, never crack, and never be harmed by

05:59:07.500 --> 05:59:08.340
outside attack.

05:59:08.400 --> 05:59:11.520
It soared miles into the air, with towers

05:59:11.520 --> 05:59:14.220
and balconies and spires that pierced the

05:59:14.220 --> 05:59:14.520
clouds.

05:59:14.580 --> 05:59:16.799
There were so many rooms on so many

05:59:16.799 --> 05:59:19.439
levels that Winter, who had lived there

05:59:19.439 --> 05:59:21.419
his entire life, had never seen them

05:59:21.419 --> 05:59:21.720
all.

05:59:21.779 --> 05:59:24.540
A low ranked guard stood outside the

05:59:24.540 --> 05:59:27.659
gates. wearing the chain of 5 concentric

05:59:27.659 --> 05:59:30.360
silver circles that marked him as 5th

05:59:30.360 --> 05:59:31.799
circle in the adult rankings.

05:59:31.860 --> 05:59:34.319
His posture and form were perfect

05:59:34.319 --> 05:59:36.240
although his eyelids were drooping

05:59:36.240 --> 05:59:37.020
dangerously.

05:59:37.080 --> 05:59:39.360
He snapped to attention as they landed

05:59:39.360 --> 05:59:41.040
stamping his spear twice.

05:59:41.099 --> 05:59:44.459
Nephews of Queen Glacier, Winter

05:59:44.459 --> 05:59:46.500
announced, although he was sure the guard

05:59:46.500 --> 05:59:47.400
must recognize them.

05:59:47.459 --> 05:59:48.720
He hesitated.

05:59:48.779 --> 05:59:51.599
I swing etiquette demanded that the

05:59:51.599 --> 05:59:53.340
higher ranked dragon should be introduced

05:59:53.340 --> 05:59:53.700
first.

05:59:53.759 --> 05:59:56.639
But hailstorm wasn't even listed in the

05:59:56.639 --> 05:59:57.299
rankings anymore.

05:59:57.360 --> 05:59:59.880
His name had been scratched out along

05:59:59.880 --> 06:00:01.799
with all the other murdered ice wing

06:00:01.799 --> 06:00:02.220
prisoners.

06:00:02.279 --> 06:00:04.860
But surely the correct introduction was

06:00:04.860 --> 06:00:07.740
still hailstorm and winter, wasn't it?

06:00:07.799 --> 06:00:09.599
The guard saved him the trouble.

06:00:09.659 --> 06:00:11.520
Hillstorm?

06:00:11.580 --> 06:00:13.200
He blinked and rubbed his eyes

06:00:13.200 --> 06:00:13.799
violently.

06:00:13.860 --> 06:00:16.560
Aren't you hailstorm?

06:00:16.619 --> 06:00:18.479
I guess.

06:00:18.540 --> 06:00:20.819
Hailstorm answered, in the least

06:00:20.819 --> 06:00:22.380
convincing tone of voice possible.

06:00:22.439 --> 06:00:25.020
The guard couldn't hide how rattled he

06:00:25.020 --> 06:00:26.819
was, although he did his best.

06:00:27.000 --> 06:00:29.880
My apology, sir, he said, bowing.

06:00:29.939 --> 06:00:31.380
We believed you were dead.

06:00:31.439 --> 06:00:33.659
It is a wondrous day indeed that you are

06:00:33.659 --> 06:00:34.619
returned to us.

06:00:34.680 --> 06:00:36.900
We should report straight to the queen

06:00:36.900 --> 06:00:37.919
Winter said.

06:00:37.979 --> 06:00:39.959
She'll want to be woken for this, if

06:00:39.959 --> 06:00:40.799
she's not still awake.

06:00:40.860 --> 06:00:44.520
Thousands of years ago, Ice Wings must

06:00:44.520 --> 06:00:47.220
have been restricted to daylight hours, or

06:00:47.220 --> 06:00:49.619
as some speculated, perhaps their night

06:00:49.619 --> 06:00:51.959
vision had once been stronger, but nobody

06:00:51.959 --> 06:00:54.479
said that too loud, lest it sound like

06:00:54.479 --> 06:00:56.759
criticism of the animus gifts or the

06:00:56.759 --> 06:00:57.659
royal family.

06:00:57.720 --> 06:01:00.119
But ever since the gift of light, they

06:01:00.119 --> 06:01:01.500
could stay up all night long if they

06:01:01.500 --> 06:01:04.259
wanted to, and many of them did, seizing

06:01:04.259 --> 06:01:05.759
every hour they could for working and

06:01:05.759 --> 06:01:06.060
training.

06:01:06.119 --> 06:01:09.540
Queen Glacier is on a diplomatic mission

06:01:09.540 --> 06:01:13.020
the guard said, flinching in a strange

06:01:13.020 --> 06:01:13.560
embarrassed way.

06:01:13.619 --> 06:01:16.619
Her brother Narwhal is overseeing palace

06:01:16.619 --> 06:01:17.639
matters in her absence.

06:01:17.700 --> 06:01:19.799
Right now, he's at work on the rankings

06:01:19.799 --> 06:01:20.939
in the courtyard.

06:01:21.000 --> 06:01:23.939
Our father, Winter thought.

06:01:24.000 --> 06:01:27.240
Beside him hailstorm's wings twitched.

06:01:27.299 --> 06:01:30.720
Thank you, Winter said to the guard, with

06:01:30.720 --> 06:01:32.220
a small nod.

06:01:32.279 --> 06:01:33.840
The older ice wing looked slightly

06:01:33.840 --> 06:01:36.240
outraged, but he stepped aside and let

06:01:36.240 --> 06:01:37.380
them pass without further comment.

06:01:37.439 --> 06:01:40.080
It wasn't until they were through the

06:01:40.080 --> 06:01:42.659
gates, that Winter realized he might have

06:01:42.659 --> 06:01:44.580
handled that interaction entirely wrong.

06:01:44.639 --> 06:01:47.220
He'd approached it with his last known

06:01:47.220 --> 06:01:48.060
rank in mind.

06:01:48.119 --> 06:01:50.340
He'd been in the 2nd circle the day he

06:01:50.340 --> 06:01:51.779
left for Jade Mountain Academy.

06:01:51.840 --> 06:01:54.119
But perhaps his position had slipped in

06:01:54.119 --> 06:01:54.659
his time away.

06:01:54.720 --> 06:01:57.540
Especially if Queen Glacier knew what had

06:01:57.540 --> 06:01:58.500
happened with Icicle.

06:01:58.560 --> 06:02:01.200
If he'd fallen into a circle below that

06:02:01.200 --> 06:02:03.180
of the guard, Winter should have been

06:02:03.180 --> 06:02:04.020
much more deferential.

06:02:04.080 --> 06:02:06.840
But surely it couldn't have dived so low

06:02:06.840 --> 06:02:08.819
in just a few weeks, could it?

06:02:08.939 --> 06:02:10.919
Into the 6th circle?

06:02:10.979 --> 06:02:13.860
Winter, I'd only ever gone that low after

06:02:13.860 --> 06:02:15.119
hailstorm's capture.

06:02:15.180 --> 06:02:18.180
Hailstorm was silent as they flew through

06:02:18.180 --> 06:02:20.639
the vast entrance hall, spiraling down

06:02:20.639 --> 06:02:23.580
toward the 3 arched openings that led to

06:02:23.580 --> 06:02:24.419
the central courtyard.

06:02:24.479 --> 06:02:27.840
Winter glanced sideways at him, wondering

06:02:27.840 --> 06:02:29.700
if the familiar surroundings were helping

06:02:29.700 --> 06:02:30.659
clarify his memories.

06:02:30.720 --> 06:02:34.740
All around them, pale blue stars seemed

06:02:34.740 --> 06:02:36.180
to be drifting slowly through the

06:02:36.180 --> 06:02:38.639
otherwise bare, translucent walls of the

06:02:38.639 --> 06:02:39.000
palace.

06:02:39.060 --> 06:02:41.220
It wasn't until you got close to the

06:02:41.220 --> 06:02:43.439
walls that you could see the small glass

06:02:43.439 --> 06:02:46.500
snowflakes encased in the ice, glowing

06:02:46.500 --> 06:02:48.959
silvery blue as they fell, mimicking the

06:02:48.959 --> 06:02:49.439
weather outside.

06:02:49.500 --> 06:02:52.979
This was the gift of elegance, which

06:02:52.979 --> 06:02:54.840
winter appreciated for its beauty, but

06:02:54.840 --> 06:02:56.099
thought was a waste of magic.

06:02:56.159 --> 06:02:59.159
The phosphorescent snowflakes must have

06:02:59.159 --> 06:03:01.500
been created, in a time when ice wings

06:03:01.500 --> 06:03:03.060
were comfortable, and did need anything

06:03:03.060 --> 06:03:05.279
more urgent, a time when they thought

06:03:05.279 --> 06:03:08.340
they would always have animus dragons, or

06:03:08.340 --> 06:03:10.200
perhaps it was enchanted by an animus who

06:03:10.200 --> 06:03:12.180
was artistic, but not very practical.

06:03:12.240 --> 06:03:14.880
Ice wing history included a few animus

06:03:14.880 --> 06:03:16.979
dragons, who chose their gifts against

06:03:16.979 --> 06:03:18.360
the wishes of their queens.

06:03:18.419 --> 06:03:21.060
The gift of subsistence was one.

06:03:21.119 --> 06:03:24.180
A trio of holes in the ice located on the

06:03:24.180 --> 06:03:26.040
outskirts of the kingdom, where the

06:03:26.040 --> 06:03:28.500
poorest, weakest ice wings could reach

06:03:28.500 --> 06:03:30.840
into the dark ocean beneath, and always

06:03:30.840 --> 06:03:31.860
pull out a seal.

06:03:31.919 --> 06:03:34.439
No ice dragon who cared about the

06:03:34.439 --> 06:03:35.159
rankings.

06:03:35.220 --> 06:03:38.040
In other words, no aristocrat, would ever

06:03:38.040 --> 06:03:40.080
accept food that came so easily to their

06:03:40.080 --> 06:03:40.919
claws, however.

06:03:40.979 --> 06:03:43.439
It was a gift that only benefited the

06:03:43.439 --> 06:03:45.479
lowest of the kingdom, which made it seem

06:03:45.479 --> 06:03:47.520
narrow minded and useless to all the ice

06:03:47.520 --> 06:03:48.479
wings winter knew.

06:03:48.599 --> 06:03:51.419
But perhaps it would seem like a kinder

06:03:51.419 --> 06:03:53.520
wiser gift in the eyes of the other

06:03:53.520 --> 06:03:56.400
tribes, rain wings, for instance, who

06:03:56.400 --> 06:03:58.619
took care of one another so easily, and

06:03:58.619 --> 06:04:00.599
had, apparently, no hierarchy at all.

06:04:00.659 --> 06:04:03.119
Winter thought uncomfortably of all the

06:04:03.119 --> 06:04:05.819
dragons and possibility, like the wounded

06:04:05.819 --> 06:04:07.740
mudwing, who could use a source of food

06:04:07.740 --> 06:04:08.159
like that.

06:04:08.279 --> 06:04:11.099
Stop thinking about other tribes.

06:04:11.159 --> 06:04:13.560
Father will smell doubt on you.

06:04:13.619 --> 06:04:16.439
Winter had once dreamed that he was an

06:04:16.439 --> 06:04:19.439
animus dragon, and in his dream, he gave

06:04:19.439 --> 06:04:21.240
his tribe the gift of observation.

06:04:21.299 --> 06:04:23.939
A scavenger den in the ice kingdom

06:04:23.939 --> 06:04:25.979
constructed so the scavengers could

06:04:25.979 --> 06:04:28.619
survive without freezing, a perfect setup

06:04:28.619 --> 06:04:29.520
for winter to study them.

06:04:29.580 --> 06:04:33.299
That was probably another example of a

06:04:33.299 --> 06:04:34.919
gift that a queen wouldn't approve of.

06:04:34.979 --> 06:04:37.860
A couple of dragons in the hall did a

06:04:37.860 --> 06:04:40.380
double take as the brothers flew by, but

06:04:40.380 --> 06:04:41.639
Hailstorm didn't seem to notice.

06:04:41.700 --> 06:04:44.220
He swept unerringly through the center

06:04:44.220 --> 06:04:47.279
archway into the snow covered courtyard, a

06:04:47.279 --> 06:04:49.380
vast space dominated by the 2 most

06:04:49.380 --> 06:04:51.240
important animus gifts and ice wing

06:04:51.240 --> 06:04:53.880
history, the gifts of light, and order.

06:04:53.939 --> 06:04:57.479
As a young dragonette, Winter had loved

06:04:57.479 --> 06:05:00.299
to climb the tree of light, his small

06:05:00.299 --> 06:05:02.220
serrated claws would dig into the ice of

06:05:02.220 --> 06:05:04.200
the trunk and propel him up into the

06:05:04.200 --> 06:05:06.659
branches, where he could curl up and

06:05:06.659 --> 06:05:08.040
pretend he was sitting on one of the

06:05:08.040 --> 06:05:08.340
moons.

06:05:08.400 --> 06:05:10.979
Sometimes he would imagine he was the

06:05:10.979 --> 06:05:13.439
animus who'd created the tree, a dragon

06:05:13.439 --> 06:05:15.479
named Frostbite, according to his history

06:05:15.479 --> 06:05:17.939
tutor, who had spent more time and care

06:05:17.939 --> 06:05:20.819
on her gift than perhaps any other animus

06:05:20.819 --> 06:05:21.779
the tribe had ever seen.

06:05:21.840 --> 06:05:24.900
She had an enchanted the eyes to sculpt

06:05:24.900 --> 06:05:27.360
itself, like the designers of the palace

06:05:27.360 --> 06:05:28.799
or the great ice cliff.

06:05:28.860 --> 06:05:31.799
She'd spent years painstakingly carving

06:05:31.799 --> 06:05:34.380
the tree with her own claws, each branch

06:05:34.380 --> 06:05:36.479
in twig and frost kissed leaf.

06:05:36.599 --> 06:05:39.840
For the 1st time, Winter wondered if

06:05:39.840 --> 06:05:41.520
frostbite had left the kingdom for a

06:05:41.520 --> 06:05:42.840
while to study real trees.

06:05:42.900 --> 06:05:45.540
He'd spent enough time in actual forests

06:05:45.540 --> 06:05:47.520
now, to realize that she had gotten the

06:05:47.520 --> 06:05:48.540
details exactly right.

06:05:48.599 --> 06:05:51.720
The magic came once the tree was

06:05:51.720 --> 06:05:52.139
finished.

06:05:52.200 --> 06:05:54.659
The animus touch gave the tree a kind of

06:05:54.659 --> 06:05:57.959
eternal life, and most important, the

06:05:57.959 --> 06:05:59.759
moon globes that grew on it all year

06:05:59.759 --> 06:06:00.180
round.

06:06:00.240 --> 06:06:03.840
To Winter's surprise, Hailstorm went to

06:06:03.840 --> 06:06:05.400
the tree and picked a globe right away

06:06:05.400 --> 06:06:07.560
like most dragons did when they 1st

06:06:07.560 --> 06:06:08.700
arrived at the palace.

06:06:08.759 --> 06:06:10.740
Did that mean his instincts were kicking

06:06:10.740 --> 06:06:10.919
in?

06:06:10.979 --> 06:06:13.680
The glow floated quietly over his left

06:06:13.680 --> 06:06:16.439
shoulder, casting pale light that

06:06:16.439 --> 06:06:18.000
accentuated the shadows between his

06:06:18.000 --> 06:06:18.419
horns.

06:06:18.479 --> 06:06:21.659
Winter followed, choosing a light of his

06:06:21.659 --> 06:06:23.159
own, and releasing it over his own

06:06:23.159 --> 06:06:26.159
shoulder, a small bud appeared instantly

06:06:26.159 --> 06:06:28.500
in its place on the branch, where a new

06:06:28.500 --> 06:06:30.119
moon globe would grow within a day or

06:06:30.119 --> 06:06:30.299
two.

06:06:30.360 --> 06:06:33.720
He turned and realized that everyone in

06:06:33.720 --> 06:06:35.340
the courtyard was staring at them.

06:06:35.400 --> 06:06:37.979
He hadn't even noticed the quiet murmur

06:06:37.979 --> 06:06:39.779
of conversation in the air. until it

06:06:39.779 --> 06:06:43.259
abruptly stopped. 9 ice wings watched in

06:06:43.259 --> 06:06:45.900
silence as hailstorm and winter walked

06:06:45.900 --> 06:06:48.540
under the tree and down the long path to

06:06:48.540 --> 06:06:49.500
the wall of rankings.

06:06:49.560 --> 06:06:52.080
Standing in front of the rankings

06:06:52.080 --> 06:06:54.180
watching them approach with a cold

06:06:54.180 --> 06:06:56.459
unreadable expression, was their father

06:06:56.459 --> 06:06:57.599
Narwhal.

06:06:57.659 --> 06:07:00.240
Winter didn't wait for hailstorm to bow

06:07:00.240 --> 06:07:02.700
first, whatever their respective ranking

06:07:02.700 --> 06:07:04.979
was in whoever's mind, he couldn't face

06:07:04.979 --> 06:07:07.500
his father's gaze anymore, he dropped

06:07:07.500 --> 06:07:09.900
into a crouch, spread his wings, and

06:07:09.900 --> 06:07:10.439
bowed his head.

06:07:10.500 --> 06:07:13.979
The wet snow crept between his scales

06:07:13.979 --> 06:07:15.419
comforting and chilling at the same

06:07:15.419 --> 06:07:15.659
time.

06:07:15.720 --> 06:07:19.500
Beside him, more slowly, Hailstorm did

06:07:19.500 --> 06:07:19.740
the same.

06:07:19.799 --> 06:07:23.939
In the long silence that followed, Winter

06:07:23.939 --> 06:07:25.979
imagined he could hear glaciers moving

06:07:25.979 --> 06:07:29.340
the world spinning, the stars weeping

06:07:29.340 --> 06:07:29.639
softly.

06:07:29.700 --> 06:07:32.099
What is father thinking?

06:07:32.159 --> 06:07:34.080
He didn't dare look up.

06:07:34.139 --> 06:07:36.479
He knew Narwhal's expression wouldn't

06:07:36.479 --> 06:07:37.380
hold any clues anyway.

06:07:37.439 --> 06:07:42.599
So, Narwhal finally hissed, in a voice

06:07:42.599 --> 06:07:45.599
that could slice an iceberg in half, my 2

06:07:45.599 --> 06:07:46.860
sons have returned to me.

06:07:46.919 --> 06:07:50.279
One I thought would never come back, the

06:07:50.279 --> 06:07:52.020
other I hoped, never would.

06:07:52.080 --> 06:07:55.560
Winter lifted his eyes, shocked into

06:07:55.560 --> 06:07:58.139
meeting narwhal's gaze, behind his father

06:07:58.139 --> 06:08:00.599
the 7 circles of dragonette rankings

06:08:00.599 --> 06:08:02.880
blazed like comets against a dark sky.

06:08:02.939 --> 06:08:06.659
This wall was the gift of order, where

06:08:06.659 --> 06:08:08.340
every dragon in the aristocracy was

06:08:08.340 --> 06:08:08.639
listed.

06:08:08.700 --> 06:08:11.340
Their names were all carved into the ice

06:08:11.340 --> 06:08:13.860
but enchanted, so that the queen and her

06:08:13.860 --> 06:08:16.200
chosen advisors could slide them around

06:08:16.200 --> 06:08:17.880
like beads on an abacus.

06:08:17.939 --> 06:08:20.400
Every dragonette that hatched appeared

06:08:20.400 --> 06:08:22.319
here as soon as he or she was given a

06:08:22.319 --> 06:08:23.099
name.

06:08:23.159 --> 06:08:25.560
Every night, the queen considered the

06:08:25.560 --> 06:08:27.540
current standings and changed them

06:08:27.540 --> 06:08:28.979
according to the rules and her own

06:08:28.979 --> 06:08:29.400
judgment.

06:08:29.459 --> 06:08:31.979
Winter spotted his name right away.

06:08:32.040 --> 06:08:36.240
In dead last, at the bottom of the 7th

06:08:36.240 --> 06:08:39.540
circle, was icicle's name, and one step

06:08:39.540 --> 06:08:42.959
above her, 2nd to last, lower than all

06:08:42.959 --> 06:08:45.180
the new hatched dragonettes on the list

06:08:45.180 --> 06:08:47.580
lower than any royal had ever been before

06:08:47.580 --> 06:08:49.319
was winter.

06:08:49.319 --> 06:08:53.939
Chapter 21.

06:08:54.119 --> 06:08:58.259
A gust of wind swept a cloud across one

06:08:58.259 --> 06:09:00.000
of the moons, and it began to snow

06:09:00.000 --> 06:09:00.419
harder.

06:09:00.540 --> 06:09:03.119
Winter stared down at the tracks of

06:09:03.119 --> 06:09:04.860
dragon prints that crisscrossed the

06:09:04.860 --> 06:09:05.340
courtyard.

06:09:05.400 --> 06:09:06.540
He couldn't think.

06:09:06.599 --> 06:09:08.040
He could barely breathe.

06:09:08.099 --> 06:09:11.520
We did not think you could possibly be

06:09:11.520 --> 06:09:12.840
alive, Hellstorm.

06:09:12.900 --> 06:09:15.959
Narwhal said, inspecting his older son

06:09:15.959 --> 06:09:17.279
from wings to claws.

06:09:17.340 --> 06:09:19.500
Congratulations on your survival.

06:09:19.619 --> 06:09:22.319
The queen will be pleased to welcome you

06:09:22.319 --> 06:09:23.159
back to her army.

06:09:23.220 --> 06:09:27.240
Hailstorm swept his tail in a slow arc

06:09:27.240 --> 06:09:29.099
through the snow, his head drooping

06:09:29.099 --> 06:09:29.340
lower.

06:09:29.400 --> 06:09:34.919
As for you, winter, Narwhal went on, we

06:09:34.919 --> 06:09:36.779
have heard a lot of stories about your

06:09:36.779 --> 06:09:37.380
behavior.

06:09:37.439 --> 06:09:40.319
Perhaps you can clarify some of them for

06:09:40.319 --> 06:09:40.500
us.

06:09:40.560 --> 06:09:43.020
Attacking your own sister at Jade

06:09:43.020 --> 06:09:45.180
Mountain Academy, leaving the school

06:09:45.180 --> 06:09:46.680
without your queen's permission.

06:09:46.799 --> 06:09:49.200
Traveling with a night wing.

06:09:49.259 --> 06:09:51.779
Leading the rain wing straight to

06:09:51.779 --> 06:09:53.819
Icicle's hiding place, so she could be

06:09:53.819 --> 06:09:56.159
imprisoned, and then abandoning her

06:09:56.159 --> 06:09:59.099
unconscious in the rainforest, where any

06:09:59.099 --> 06:10:00.360
night wing might have murdered her.

06:10:00.419 --> 06:10:03.000
Disappearing into Pireo without

06:10:03.000 --> 06:10:03.840
consulting your queen.

06:10:03.959 --> 06:10:07.020
Consorting with dragons from other tribes

06:10:07.020 --> 06:10:10.619
gone for days with no message sent home

06:10:10.619 --> 06:10:12.659
and no oversight or explanation for your

06:10:12.659 --> 06:10:13.200
behavior.

06:10:13.259 --> 06:10:17.099
He took a step toward winter, his talons

06:10:17.099 --> 06:10:18.119
crunching in the snow.

06:10:18.180 --> 06:10:20.159
What were we supposed to think?

06:10:20.220 --> 06:10:22.860
How are we supposed to account for you in

06:10:22.860 --> 06:10:23.459
the rankings?

06:10:23.520 --> 06:10:24.900
What choice?

06:10:25.020 --> 06:10:26.400
Did the queen have?

06:10:26.459 --> 06:10:29.279
He swept one wing toward the wall.

06:10:29.340 --> 06:10:32.580
That's where she's gone, Winter

06:10:32.580 --> 06:10:33.060
realized.

06:10:33.119 --> 06:10:35.939
Queen Glacier is in the rainforest to

06:10:35.939 --> 06:10:37.500
deal with the icicle situation.

06:10:37.560 --> 06:10:39.900
He wondered if his sister was still

06:10:39.900 --> 06:10:42.299
asleep, and whether Scarlet had returned

06:10:42.299 --> 06:10:43.500
to torment her dreams.

06:10:43.560 --> 06:10:46.500
How would the queens decide to punish his

06:10:46.500 --> 06:10:47.939
sister for everything she had done?

06:10:48.000 --> 06:10:50.520
Queen Glory wasn't likely to accept

06:10:50.520 --> 06:10:53.340
demotion to the bottom of the 7th circle

06:10:53.340 --> 06:10:55.680
of the rankings as sufficient justice.

06:10:55.680 --> 06:10:58.080
No one but an ice wing would understand

06:10:58.080 --> 06:10:58.799
what that meant.

06:10:58.860 --> 06:11:02.880
Father, Hailstorm said suddenly.

06:11:02.939 --> 06:11:05.400
I see I am no longer listed in the

06:11:05.400 --> 06:11:07.380
rankings, but may I have permission to

06:11:07.380 --> 06:11:08.040
speak?

06:11:08.279 --> 06:11:10.020
Narwhal inclined his head.

06:11:10.080 --> 06:11:12.240
Briefly, if you please.

06:11:12.299 --> 06:11:15.299
My brother acted rashly, and without

06:11:15.299 --> 06:11:18.479
oversight, said Hailstorm, but he did so

06:11:18.479 --> 06:11:19.380
to save my life.

06:11:19.380 --> 06:11:21.779
I would have been executed within hours

06:11:21.779 --> 06:11:23.580
if he had not saved me in time.

06:11:23.639 --> 06:11:26.580
He was courageous, and honorable in his

06:11:26.580 --> 06:11:27.840
time away from the ice kingdom.

06:11:27.900 --> 06:11:30.060
I am prepared to attest to that before

06:11:30.060 --> 06:11:30.479
the queen.

06:11:30.540 --> 06:11:33.840
His eyes flickered sideways to winter.

06:11:33.900 --> 06:11:36.000
The only betrayal that he was not telling

06:11:36.000 --> 06:11:36.840
the entire truth.

06:11:36.900 --> 06:11:39.840
Winter knew he couldn't possibly approve

06:11:39.840 --> 06:11:42.299
of Winter's friendship with Kibley, Moon

06:11:42.299 --> 06:11:44.279
and Kinkaju, but would he hide it to

06:11:44.279 --> 06:11:45.000
protect Winter?

06:11:45.060 --> 06:11:47.459
Was he expecting winter to hide the truth

06:11:47.459 --> 06:11:48.900
about pyrite in exchange?

06:11:48.959 --> 06:11:53.520
Come to my chambers, Narwhal said, shaking

06:11:53.520 --> 06:11:54.540
snow off his wings.

06:11:54.599 --> 06:11:56.340
Tell me the whole story there.

06:11:56.400 --> 06:11:59.340
Winter, go to your room, and I will

06:11:59.340 --> 06:12:00.119
summon you shortly.

06:12:00.240 --> 06:12:03.599
Hailstorm shot Winter another significant

06:12:03.599 --> 06:12:05.819
look as he followed their father away.

06:12:05.880 --> 06:12:08.520
A minute later, the other ice wings in

06:12:08.520 --> 06:12:10.259
the courtyard had dispersed, leaving

06:12:10.259 --> 06:12:10.919
winter alone.

06:12:10.979 --> 06:12:13.860
He spent several minutes scanning the

06:12:13.860 --> 06:12:15.959
rankings, taking note of what had changed

06:12:15.959 --> 06:12:17.340
in his absence.

06:12:17.400 --> 06:12:20.580
His cousin Snowfall was the new top of

06:12:20.580 --> 06:12:22.619
the 1st circle on the dragonette side

06:12:22.619 --> 06:12:24.840
which was disheartening, as she was

06:12:24.840 --> 06:12:26.639
already abundantly blessed with mean

06:12:26.639 --> 06:12:27.479
smugness.

06:12:27.540 --> 06:12:31.080
Lynx was in 2nd place behind Snowfall, and

06:12:31.080 --> 06:12:32.700
that was much better news.

06:12:32.759 --> 06:12:34.319
She was only the daughter of a minor

06:12:34.319 --> 06:12:36.599
noble, but a hard worker, and very

06:12:36.599 --> 06:12:36.779
smart.

06:12:36.840 --> 06:12:40.020
On the adult side, he saw that his

06:12:40.020 --> 06:12:42.360
parents had fallen several spots, nearly

06:12:42.360 --> 06:12:44.639
into the 3rd circle, which meant they

06:12:44.639 --> 06:12:46.259
were almost in danger of losing their

06:12:46.259 --> 06:12:47.459
right to live in the palace.

06:12:47.459 --> 06:12:50.939
That's our fault, he realized.

06:12:51.060 --> 06:12:54.000
Having me and Icicle at the bottom of our

06:12:54.000 --> 06:12:55.500
rankings reflects badly on them.

06:12:55.560 --> 06:12:57.119
We drag them down.

06:12:57.180 --> 06:12:59.639
No wonder father's so angry.

06:12:59.700 --> 06:13:03.060
At least Winter thought he was angry.

06:13:03.119 --> 06:13:04.439
It was hard to tell.

06:13:04.500 --> 06:13:07.080
Narwhal's outward demeanor was much the

06:13:07.080 --> 06:13:09.180
same whether he was proud or furious.

06:13:09.240 --> 06:13:12.599
That wasn't quite the homecoming I was

06:13:12.599 --> 06:13:13.020
hoping for.

06:13:13.080 --> 06:13:16.080
He admitted to himself, but he hadn't

06:13:16.080 --> 06:13:17.580
exactly expected a parade either.

06:13:17.639 --> 06:13:20.400
A nod of approval was as much as his

06:13:20.400 --> 06:13:22.439
imagination had been able to come up with

06:13:22.439 --> 06:13:24.540
but apparently that was still hoping for

06:13:24.540 --> 06:13:24.959
too much.

06:13:25.020 --> 06:13:28.020
He dragged himself through the palace to

06:13:28.020 --> 06:13:30.599
his old room, bowing low to everyone he

06:13:30.599 --> 06:13:32.939
passed, most of whom were too startled by

06:13:32.939 --> 06:13:34.200
his appearance to respond.

06:13:34.259 --> 06:13:37.080
In a way, it did make things simple, being

06:13:37.080 --> 06:13:37.979
at the very bottom.

06:13:38.040 --> 06:13:40.080
He didn't have to keep the list memorized

06:13:40.080 --> 06:13:41.400
when he knew that everyone was above

06:13:41.400 --> 06:13:41.880
him.

06:13:41.939 --> 06:13:44.279
He hoped seeing his old room would cheer

06:13:44.279 --> 06:13:44.639
him up.

06:13:44.700 --> 06:13:47.099
But instead it struck him as a bare

06:13:47.099 --> 06:13:47.880
joyless box.

06:13:47.939 --> 06:13:49.740
They seemed to have shrunk while he was

06:13:49.740 --> 06:13:49.919
away.

06:13:49.979 --> 06:13:52.740
The one window overlooked the courtyard

06:13:52.740 --> 06:13:54.479
which he definitely did not want to look

06:13:54.479 --> 06:13:54.959
at right now.

06:13:55.020 --> 06:13:57.720
The snowflakes in the walls had become a

06:13:57.720 --> 06:14:00.299
blizzard, matching the oncoming snowstorm

06:14:00.299 --> 06:14:01.020
outside.

06:14:01.080 --> 06:14:03.720
Winter set the moon globe on his desk

06:14:03.720 --> 06:14:06.299
turning it one rotation to dim the light

06:14:06.299 --> 06:14:07.860
to a sleep appropriate glow.

06:14:07.919 --> 06:14:10.319
He dropped onto the shelf of ice that

06:14:10.319 --> 06:14:12.659
served as a bed, and then after an

06:14:12.659 --> 06:14:14.759
uncomfortable minute, he got up and

06:14:14.759 --> 06:14:16.919
pulled the 2 polar bear rugs up onto the

06:14:16.919 --> 06:14:17.340
bed with him.

06:14:17.400 --> 06:14:20.279
Perhaps sleeping in grass had made him

06:14:20.279 --> 06:14:22.619
soft, but he was too tired to punish his

06:14:22.619 --> 06:14:24.060
aching bones anymore.

06:14:24.119 --> 06:14:26.700
He curled into the warm white fur

06:14:26.700 --> 06:14:28.740
remembering the bright colors of the

06:14:28.740 --> 06:14:31.740
rainforest, the busy sounds and smells of

06:14:31.740 --> 06:14:32.220
possibility.

06:14:32.279 --> 06:14:35.220
The voices calling and talons thumping

06:14:35.220 --> 06:14:36.419
through the halls of the Jade Mountain

06:14:36.419 --> 06:14:36.840
Academy.

06:14:36.900 --> 06:14:40.200
The flash of silver scales against black

06:14:40.200 --> 06:14:42.060
dark eyes in the moonlight.

06:14:42.180 --> 06:14:45.000
The fire that roared forth to protect her

06:14:45.000 --> 06:14:45.360
friends.

06:14:45.419 --> 06:14:50.099
Don't dream about Moon, he told himself

06:14:50.099 --> 06:14:52.680
with his last waking thought, and then

06:14:52.680 --> 06:14:54.299
fell asleep knowing perfectly well that

06:14:54.299 --> 06:14:56.759
he would, and unable to feel anything but

06:14:56.759 --> 06:14:58.020
relief at the prospect.

06:14:58.020 --> 06:15:01.979
He had expected to be prodded into

06:15:01.979 --> 06:15:04.020
wakefulness with sharp claws by some

06:15:04.020 --> 06:15:05.040
messenger from his father.

06:15:05.099 --> 06:15:08.159
So it was unsettling to wake up slowly

06:15:08.159 --> 06:15:10.319
and realized that morning light was

06:15:10.319 --> 06:15:10.979
pouring through the window.

06:15:11.040 --> 06:15:14.459
It was even more unsettling to roll over

06:15:14.459 --> 06:15:16.619
and find his mother's eyes fixed on him

06:15:16.619 --> 06:15:18.000
from only a few inches away.

06:15:18.060 --> 06:15:21.840
Winter let out a yelp and set up fast

06:15:21.840 --> 06:15:23.520
knocking one of the rugs to the floor.

06:15:23.580 --> 06:15:26.939
Tundra frowned at it for a moment, looking

06:15:26.939 --> 06:15:29.340
more puzzled than disapproving, and

06:15:29.340 --> 06:15:30.720
finally kicked it out of her way with one

06:15:30.720 --> 06:15:30.959
foot.

06:15:31.020 --> 06:15:34.380
The sky wing teeth in her necklace made

06:15:34.380 --> 06:15:37.080
the jittery, small, clattering sound they

06:15:37.080 --> 06:15:39.540
always made when she moved, a sound that

06:15:39.540 --> 06:15:41.400
still made winter want to run and hide in

06:15:41.400 --> 06:15:41.880
a snowbank.

06:15:42.000 --> 06:15:45.540
The sun has been out for an hour, she

06:15:45.540 --> 06:15:45.779
said.

06:15:45.840 --> 06:15:48.540
Winter took a deep, stabilizing breath

06:15:48.540 --> 06:15:50.159
and tried to match her flat.

06:15:50.220 --> 06:15:52.380
Here is some information tone.

06:15:52.439 --> 06:15:55.020
I did not stop to sleep after finding

06:15:55.020 --> 06:15:56.580
Hillstorm. said.

06:15:56.639 --> 06:15:58.619
We flew home as fast as we could.

06:15:58.680 --> 06:16:02.159
Apart from one detour to drop an injured

06:16:02.159 --> 06:16:04.380
rain wing, in a town of overlapping

06:16:04.380 --> 06:16:06.180
dragon tribes that you would hate on

06:16:06.180 --> 06:16:06.599
site.

06:16:06.659 --> 06:16:09.959
He wondered how Kinkaju was doing, and

06:16:09.959 --> 06:16:11.459
whether she'd woken up yet.

06:16:11.580 --> 06:16:14.459
Tundras studied him for a moment with her

06:16:14.459 --> 06:16:15.540
stormy gray eyes.

06:16:15.599 --> 06:16:18.360
Good, she said at length.

06:16:18.479 --> 06:16:21.180
No apologies, but now it is time to

06:16:21.180 --> 06:16:21.479
rise.

06:16:21.540 --> 06:16:23.880
There will be a ceremony in the courtyard

06:16:23.880 --> 06:16:25.560
in 7 minutes that you must attend.

06:16:25.619 --> 06:16:29.939
Yes, mother, Winter said, stepping off

06:16:29.939 --> 06:16:30.720
the bed shelf.

06:16:30.779 --> 06:16:33.540
A ceremony, most likely restoring

06:16:33.540 --> 06:16:35.700
hailstorm to the rankings, but where?

06:16:35.819 --> 06:16:38.279
At the top, where he'd been when he was

06:16:38.279 --> 06:16:38.700
captured?

06:16:38.759 --> 06:16:41.759
Winter hoped he'd get to see Snowfall's

06:16:41.759 --> 06:16:42.479
face if that happened.

06:16:42.540 --> 06:16:44.939
That would make the torture of a rankings

06:16:44.939 --> 06:16:46.439
ceremony worthwhile.

06:16:46.500 --> 06:16:49.200
His mother paused in the doorway and gave

06:16:49.200 --> 06:16:50.459
him another assessing look.

06:16:50.520 --> 06:16:53.939
Finally, she said, Thank you for bringing

06:16:53.939 --> 06:16:54.720
Hillstorm home.

06:16:54.779 --> 06:16:57.720
What is this feeling?

06:16:57.779 --> 06:16:58.860
Winter wondered.

06:16:58.919 --> 06:17:00.000
Elation?

06:17:00.060 --> 06:17:01.080
Pride?

06:17:01.200 --> 06:17:03.720
He'd never felt anything quite like this

06:17:03.720 --> 06:17:05.400
swelling in his chest before.

06:17:05.459 --> 06:17:07.680
He dared to give her the smallest of

06:17:07.680 --> 06:17:08.040
smiles.

06:17:08.159 --> 06:17:10.259
Tundra blinked slowly.

06:17:10.319 --> 06:17:12.779
It was the least you could do.

06:17:12.840 --> 06:17:15.720
She added, and then she turned and left.

06:17:15.840 --> 06:17:19.020
Winter could practically hear Kibley's

06:17:19.020 --> 06:17:19.979
voice in the room beside him.

06:17:20.040 --> 06:17:22.979
So that didn't last very long.

06:17:23.040 --> 06:17:25.380
He startled himself by laughing.

06:17:25.439 --> 06:17:27.419
I'd better not do that again.

06:17:27.479 --> 06:17:29.340
Not in front of mother and father.

06:17:29.459 --> 06:17:31.619
I'm going to have to work harder than

06:17:31.619 --> 06:17:33.299
ever to climb back up the rankings.

06:17:33.360 --> 06:17:36.599
He scooped some snow off the windowsill

06:17:36.599 --> 06:17:38.459
and rubbed it all over his scales

06:17:38.459 --> 06:17:40.560
polishing them as clean as he could get

06:17:40.560 --> 06:17:41.220
them in 3 minutes.

06:17:41.279 --> 06:17:44.220
He made it down to the courtyard 2

06:17:44.220 --> 06:17:45.240
minutes before the ceremony.

06:17:45.299 --> 06:17:48.000
Almost every dragonette in the palace was

06:17:48.000 --> 06:17:51.119
there, lined up in order, wings folded in

06:17:51.119 --> 06:17:51.840
attention position.

06:17:51.900 --> 06:17:54.360
He found his way to the end of the line

06:17:54.360 --> 06:17:56.880
in the back corner farthest from the

06:17:56.880 --> 06:17:57.599
rankings wall.

06:17:57.720 --> 06:18:00.419
The tiny dragonettes back there with him

06:18:00.419 --> 06:18:03.299
gave him curious looks, and whispered to

06:18:03.299 --> 06:18:04.979
one another in voices that were really

06:18:04.979 --> 06:18:05.939
not whispers at all.

06:18:06.000 --> 06:18:08.759
Adult dragons were gathered around the

06:18:08.759 --> 06:18:09.779
perimeter of the courtyard.

06:18:09.900 --> 06:18:12.419
More than were ever usually present for a

06:18:12.419 --> 06:18:13.919
dragonette ranking ceremony.

06:18:13.919 --> 06:18:16.799
The sun glinted off white scales in many

06:18:16.799 --> 06:18:19.139
of the windows, indicating that even more

06:18:19.139 --> 06:18:20.220
were watching from overhead.

06:18:20.279 --> 06:18:23.580
They want to see how father will handle

06:18:23.580 --> 06:18:25.500
this situation, Winter thought.

06:18:25.619 --> 06:18:27.900
Can he be impartial with his own son?

06:18:27.959 --> 06:18:30.479
Will everyone still think his decision is

06:18:30.479 --> 06:18:30.720
fair?

06:18:30.840 --> 06:18:35.340
Tundra, Narwhal, and Hailstorm, swept

06:18:35.340 --> 06:18:36.900
into the courtyard in a triangle

06:18:36.900 --> 06:18:38.939
formation, with narwhal at the front?

06:18:39.000 --> 06:18:41.580
This was something winter had seen so

06:18:41.580 --> 06:18:43.740
many times growing up, but had never

06:18:43.740 --> 06:18:44.939
expected to see again.

06:18:44.939 --> 06:18:47.819
Their tails swept majestically through

06:18:47.819 --> 06:18:50.400
the snow, leaving long, snaking trails

06:18:50.400 --> 06:18:50.819
behind them.

06:18:50.880 --> 06:18:54.060
Narwhal pivoted to face the gathered

06:18:54.060 --> 06:18:56.040
dragonettes, who all fell instantly

06:18:56.040 --> 06:18:56.700
silent.

06:18:56.759 --> 06:18:59.639
We have some changes to make to the

06:18:59.639 --> 06:19:01.259
rankings of which you all should be

06:19:01.259 --> 06:19:01.619
aware.

06:19:01.680 --> 06:19:03.599
Winter's father said.

06:19:03.659 --> 06:19:06.000
His resonant voice echoing around the

06:19:06.000 --> 06:19:06.419
courtyard.

06:19:06.479 --> 06:19:08.880
He sounded just like Queen Glacier

06:19:08.880 --> 06:19:10.680
straight to business, without any

06:19:10.680 --> 06:19:12.299
meandering preambles.

06:19:12.360 --> 06:19:14.220
Several months ago.

06:19:14.279 --> 06:19:16.740
A dragonette was removed from the wall

06:19:16.740 --> 06:19:18.180
due to reports of his death.

06:19:18.240 --> 06:19:21.900
He has now returned to us, alive after

06:19:21.900 --> 06:19:22.139
all.

06:19:22.200 --> 06:19:25.919
This is my son, Queen Glacier's nephew

06:19:25.919 --> 06:19:27.180
Hailstorm.

06:19:27.240 --> 06:19:30.360
Norwhal indicated Winter's brother with a

06:19:30.360 --> 06:19:31.560
sideways flick of his wing.

06:19:31.680 --> 06:19:35.220
Therefore, he must be added back to the

06:19:35.220 --> 06:19:35.580
rankings.

06:19:35.639 --> 06:19:39.360
He turned to Tundra, who flexed her claws

06:19:39.360 --> 06:19:40.080
ready to write.

06:19:40.200 --> 06:19:44.220
At the time of his capture, Hailstorm was

06:19:44.220 --> 06:19:45.000
in 1st place.

06:19:45.060 --> 06:19:48.720
Winter risked craning his neck to see

06:19:48.720 --> 06:19:50.880
snowfall, right at the front of the

06:19:50.880 --> 06:19:51.240
crowd.

06:19:51.299 --> 06:19:53.759
Her face was turned away from him, but he

06:19:53.759 --> 06:19:55.439
could see rigid tension all the way

06:19:55.439 --> 06:19:56.580
through her spine and wings.

06:19:56.639 --> 06:20:00.240
But he has been without oversight for

06:20:00.240 --> 06:20:03.000
almost 2 years, and by his own admission

06:20:03.000 --> 06:20:05.939
and that time has not behaved according

06:20:05.939 --> 06:20:07.919
to our ice wing standards.

06:20:07.979 --> 06:20:11.639
We must also factor in the clumsiness of

06:20:11.639 --> 06:20:14.099
allowing himself to be caught by sky

06:20:14.099 --> 06:20:15.720
wings in the 1st place.

06:20:15.779 --> 06:20:18.000
Winter flinched.

06:20:18.060 --> 06:20:20.340
What a thing for hailstorm to hear upon

06:20:20.340 --> 06:20:21.180
his homecoming.

06:20:21.240 --> 06:20:25.500
Therefore, after careful consideration

06:20:25.500 --> 06:20:29.159
Narwhal announced, we are slotting

06:20:29.159 --> 06:20:32.819
Hailstorm into last place in the 7th

06:20:32.819 --> 06:20:33.119
circle.

06:20:33.180 --> 06:20:36.119
May he claw his way back up with his own

06:20:36.119 --> 06:20:36.779
talents.

06:20:36.900 --> 06:20:40.020
A collective gasp and a murmur of

06:20:40.020 --> 06:20:42.000
bewilderment ran through the gathered

06:20:42.000 --> 06:20:42.479
dragons.

06:20:42.540 --> 06:20:45.119
Even the most rigorously trained ice

06:20:45.119 --> 06:20:46.740
wings couldn't suppress their reactions.

06:20:46.860 --> 06:20:50.939
No one had ever, ever expected to see

06:20:50.939 --> 06:20:52.799
hailstorm's name at the bottom of the

06:20:52.799 --> 06:20:53.520
rankings list.

06:20:53.580 --> 06:20:57.000
Tundra bent toward the wall, scratching

06:20:57.000 --> 06:20:59.580
hailstorm's name below icicles.

06:20:59.639 --> 06:21:00.599
Wow.

06:21:00.659 --> 06:21:03.180
Winter felt faintly dizzy.

06:21:03.240 --> 06:21:05.520
It had to be unprecedented in ice wing

06:21:05.520 --> 06:21:07.860
history for one set of parents to have

06:21:07.860 --> 06:21:10.560
all 3 of their nearly grown dragonettes

06:21:10.560 --> 06:21:11.939
in the last 3 spots.

06:21:12.000 --> 06:21:15.060
This would be devastating for tundras and

06:21:15.060 --> 06:21:16.259
narwhals rankings as well.

06:21:16.319 --> 06:21:18.240
Would they all have to move out of the

06:21:18.240 --> 06:21:18.840
palace?

06:21:18.900 --> 06:21:20.159
Where would they be assigned?

06:21:20.220 --> 06:21:22.380
What would mother and father do if they

06:21:22.380 --> 06:21:23.880
were no longer advisors to the queen?

06:21:23.939 --> 06:21:27.119
At least no one could accuse Narwhale of

06:21:27.119 --> 06:21:28.680
sentimentality or favoritism.

06:21:28.799 --> 06:21:31.619
Hailstorm was watching their mother with

06:21:31.619 --> 06:21:33.180
a perfectly impassive expression.

06:21:33.240 --> 06:21:35.700
Did he remember that he'd once been on

06:21:35.700 --> 06:21:37.619
track to be ranked even higher than his

06:21:37.619 --> 06:21:38.099
parents?

06:21:38.220 --> 06:21:40.560
No one had ever been number one in the

06:21:40.560 --> 06:21:42.659
Dragonette rankings for as long as he had

06:21:42.659 --> 06:21:42.840
been.

06:21:42.959 --> 06:21:45.840
Expectations had been high for where he

06:21:45.840 --> 06:21:48.779
might climb once he turned 7 and shifted

06:21:48.779 --> 06:21:49.740
to the adult rankings.

06:21:49.799 --> 06:21:52.860
A deep chill suddenly ran through winter

06:21:52.860 --> 06:21:54.720
scales, turning seven.

06:21:54.779 --> 06:21:56.340
He'd completely forgotten.

06:21:56.400 --> 06:21:58.259
He hadn't even thought about how old

06:21:58.259 --> 06:21:59.279
Hellstorm was.

06:21:59.340 --> 06:22:02.400
Hailstorm's 7th hatching day was only 12

06:22:02.400 --> 06:22:03.000
days away.

06:22:03.060 --> 06:22:06.180
And wherever he was in the rankings on

06:22:06.180 --> 06:22:08.580
that day, would determine the course of

06:22:08.580 --> 06:22:09.299
the rest of his life.

06:22:09.419 --> 06:22:12.599
Could even hailstorm rise back to the top

06:22:12.599 --> 06:22:13.200
that fast?

06:22:13.259 --> 06:22:16.380
Would he choose to risk the trial?

06:22:16.439 --> 06:22:18.060
Or would he be exiled to an island

06:22:18.060 --> 06:22:19.560
outpost 2 weeks from now?

06:22:19.619 --> 06:22:22.319
Perhaps winter had rescued his brother

06:22:22.319 --> 06:22:24.900
from one terrible fate, only to doom him

06:22:24.900 --> 06:22:25.319
to another.

06:22:25.380 --> 06:22:29.759
One more announcement, father said

06:22:29.759 --> 06:22:30.479
brusquely.

06:22:30.540 --> 06:22:33.779
Another dragonette was recently shifted

06:22:33.779 --> 06:22:36.060
to the bottom of the list due to

06:22:36.060 --> 06:22:38.819
unsupervised, unauthorized activity.

06:22:38.819 --> 06:22:42.419
However, new light has been shed on his

06:22:42.419 --> 06:22:43.619
behavior for the last week.

06:22:43.680 --> 06:22:47.340
According to the newest information, he

06:22:47.340 --> 06:22:49.439
has conducted himself with courage and

06:22:49.439 --> 06:22:51.720
intelligence befitting an ice swing.

06:22:51.840 --> 06:22:55.200
While we cannot approve of any dragonette

06:22:55.200 --> 06:22:57.659
acting outside approved orders as he

06:22:57.659 --> 06:22:58.080
has.

06:22:58.200 --> 06:23:02.159
In this case, the final result, returning

06:23:02.159 --> 06:23:05.580
a missing dragon to the tribe, outweighs

06:23:05.580 --> 06:23:06.599
our disapproval.

06:23:06.659 --> 06:23:09.419
Winter could scarcely believe his father

06:23:09.419 --> 06:23:10.439
was talking about him.

06:23:10.500 --> 06:23:14.040
The balance of praise to criticism, had

06:23:14.040 --> 06:23:15.479
never tilted in his direction before.

06:23:15.540 --> 06:23:17.939
Would this get him back up to the 4th

06:23:17.939 --> 06:23:18.360
circle?

06:23:18.419 --> 06:23:19.680
Maybe even the third?

06:23:19.740 --> 06:23:24.119
Therefore, we are obligated to adjust his

06:23:24.119 --> 06:23:25.680
ranking accordingly.

06:23:25.740 --> 06:23:28.979
All present advisors have been

06:23:28.979 --> 06:23:29.639
consulted.

06:23:29.700 --> 06:23:33.360
And by general agreement, We are slotting

06:23:33.360 --> 06:23:37.080
my other son, winter, into 1st place. in

06:23:37.080 --> 06:23:37.619
the rankings.

06:23:37.740 --> 06:23:41.520
Tundra lifted her talents and stabbed

06:23:41.520 --> 06:23:42.599
Winter's name on the wall.

06:23:42.720 --> 06:23:45.779
With a crackling sound and a shower of

06:23:45.779 --> 06:23:48.299
icy sparks, she slid the name sideways

06:23:48.299 --> 06:23:50.759
and up, flapping her wings to reach the

06:23:50.759 --> 06:23:52.799
very top of the 1st circle.

06:23:52.919 --> 06:23:55.200
First place.

06:23:55.319 --> 06:23:56.580
Me?

06:23:56.639 --> 06:23:57.540
What?

06:23:57.659 --> 06:24:00.360
Hundreds of eyes were staring at winter

06:24:00.360 --> 06:24:00.599
now.

06:24:00.659 --> 06:24:03.479
The crowd reaction was less shocked than

06:24:03.479 --> 06:24:05.220
the reaction to hailstorms placement.

06:24:05.279 --> 06:24:08.220
Other dragons had performed deeds worthy

06:24:08.220 --> 06:24:09.659
of jumping to the front of the rankings

06:24:09.659 --> 06:24:12.000
before, although perhaps there was an

06:24:12.000 --> 06:24:13.560
undercurrent of surprise that it was

06:24:13.560 --> 06:24:16.139
winter, of all dragonettes who'd managed

06:24:16.139 --> 06:24:16.380
it.

06:24:16.439 --> 06:24:18.779
Did I really earn it though?

06:24:18.840 --> 06:24:19.979
Winter wondered.

06:24:20.099 --> 06:24:22.020
What did Hailstorm tell them?

06:24:22.139 --> 06:24:25.259
Also, although he didn't want to admit

06:24:25.259 --> 06:24:27.360
this to himself, he couldn't fight off

06:24:27.360 --> 06:24:29.340
the lurking suspicion that this was truly

06:24:29.340 --> 06:24:31.680
narwhal's way of maintaining his own

06:24:31.680 --> 06:24:34.919
status, a son in 1st place would

06:24:34.919 --> 06:24:36.900
counterbalance the weight of one and last

06:24:36.900 --> 06:24:39.240
and if the story of his heroic rescue was

06:24:39.240 --> 06:24:41.279
impressive enough, it might even drag

06:24:41.279 --> 06:24:43.080
tundra and narwhal back up a few

06:24:43.080 --> 06:24:43.319
numbers.

06:24:43.380 --> 06:24:48.240
Winter, his father said, indicating the

06:24:48.240 --> 06:24:50.759
front row with his tail, Winter wondered

06:24:50.759 --> 06:24:52.380
if he was the only one who could hear the

06:24:52.380 --> 06:24:54.599
tiny note of impatience in narwhal's

06:24:54.599 --> 06:24:54.720
voice.

06:24:54.779 --> 06:24:57.720
He spread his wings and rose into the air

06:24:57.720 --> 06:25:00.119
feeling the wide eyed gaze of baby

06:25:00.119 --> 06:25:01.560
dragonettes following him.

06:25:01.619 --> 06:25:04.080
As he flew to the front, he passed

06:25:04.080 --> 06:25:06.720
Hailstorm in midair, but his brother only

06:25:06.720 --> 06:25:07.740
nodded on his way by.

06:25:07.799 --> 06:25:11.159
The glare winter got from snowfall should

06:25:11.159 --> 06:25:12.599
have melted all the ice in the

06:25:12.599 --> 06:25:13.200
courtyard.

06:25:13.259 --> 06:25:15.779
She edged sideways to let him take her

06:25:15.779 --> 06:25:17.340
spot, fuming.

06:25:17.400 --> 06:25:19.259
First place.

06:25:19.380 --> 06:25:21.000
Number one.

06:25:21.060 --> 06:25:22.979
It was really up there.

06:25:23.040 --> 06:25:25.799
His own name shining at the very top of

06:25:25.799 --> 06:25:26.459
the rankings.

06:25:26.520 --> 06:25:29.279
Maybe I can take a minute to enjoy it

06:25:29.279 --> 06:25:31.619
even if I'm not quite sure how I got

06:25:31.619 --> 06:25:31.979
there.

06:25:32.099 --> 06:25:35.759
He gave Snowfall a dazzling smile, and

06:25:35.759 --> 06:25:37.319
she hunched her wings with a scowl.

06:25:37.439 --> 06:25:40.500
On her other side, Lynx smiled back

06:25:40.500 --> 06:25:42.900
mouthing the words, so great.

06:25:42.959 --> 06:25:45.720
Narwhal cleared his throat.

06:25:45.779 --> 06:25:49.740
As per the usual protocol, the queen will

06:25:49.740 --> 06:25:51.540
review the new assignments upon her

06:25:51.540 --> 06:25:53.819
return, which we anticipate will be

06:25:53.819 --> 06:25:54.180
tomorrow.

06:25:54.240 --> 06:25:57.360
Further changes may be in order then.

06:25:57.419 --> 06:26:00.720
Winter saw his mother glance at Icicle's

06:26:00.720 --> 06:26:02.939
name, then drop an expressionless mask

06:26:02.939 --> 06:26:06.840
over her features, but for now, these are

06:26:06.840 --> 06:26:07.799
your new rankings.

06:26:07.860 --> 06:26:10.919
Dragonettes dismissed.

06:26:11.040 --> 06:26:13.979
The courtyard instantly filled with a

06:26:13.979 --> 06:26:15.360
murmur of shocked conversations.

06:26:15.419 --> 06:26:18.360
Winter saw a few older, extremely high

06:26:18.360 --> 06:26:19.919
ranked dragons coming toward him.

06:26:19.979 --> 06:26:22.200
He wished he could cover himself in snow

06:26:22.200 --> 06:26:22.619
and hide.

06:26:22.680 --> 06:26:27.240
Well, Snowfall said, looking down her

06:26:27.240 --> 06:26:29.400
nose at a spot just behind his left ear

06:26:29.400 --> 06:26:31.500
that was unexpected.

06:26:31.619 --> 06:26:34.680
Yes, he agreed.

06:26:34.740 --> 06:26:37.919
Congratulations, Link said.

06:26:37.979 --> 06:26:39.659
You must have had such an adventure.

06:26:39.779 --> 06:26:42.840
She had an unusual pattern of dark blue

06:26:42.840 --> 06:26:45.299
scales scattered across her white snout

06:26:45.299 --> 06:26:45.720
and wings.

06:26:45.779 --> 06:26:48.419
Winter had always found them pretty, but

06:26:48.419 --> 06:26:50.159
now they just reminded him of Moon's

06:26:50.159 --> 06:26:51.060
silver scales.

06:26:51.119 --> 06:26:53.340
He wished he could tell Moon that he was

06:26:53.340 --> 06:26:55.619
number one in the rankings, although, of

06:26:55.619 --> 06:26:57.000
course, that wouldn't mean anything to

06:26:57.000 --> 06:26:57.180
her.

06:26:57.299 --> 06:27:00.479
Indeed, said Snowfall.

06:27:00.540 --> 06:27:03.060
I can't wait to hear all the details.

06:27:03.119 --> 06:27:07.020
On that ominous note, winter was swept

06:27:07.020 --> 06:27:09.000
into a whirlwind of congratulations

06:27:09.000 --> 06:27:11.159
questions, bowing, and advice.

06:27:11.220 --> 06:27:14.340
Every adult dragon in the palace had an

06:27:14.340 --> 06:27:16.799
opinion on how to maintain your spot, and

06:27:16.799 --> 06:27:18.299
many of them had suggestions for his

06:27:18.299 --> 06:27:20.819
future, if he could keep 1st place all

06:27:20.819 --> 06:27:22.560
the way until his 7th hatching day.

06:27:22.680 --> 06:27:26.099
Behind them, snowfall's smirk clearly

06:27:26.099 --> 06:27:28.319
expressed that she didn't expect it to

06:27:28.319 --> 06:27:29.099
last even a week.

06:27:29.159 --> 06:27:31.560
One week.

06:27:31.619 --> 06:27:34.319
Kibley's voice echoed in Winter's head.

06:27:34.380 --> 06:27:36.659
He still had 5 days to decide to go back

06:27:36.659 --> 06:27:39.180
to them, for since one would be needed

06:27:39.180 --> 06:27:39.779
for traveling.

06:27:39.840 --> 06:27:41.819
What am I thinking?

06:27:41.880 --> 06:27:44.580
No one would ever leave after reaching

06:27:44.580 --> 06:27:45.299
1st place.

06:27:45.360 --> 06:27:48.060
This is every ice wing dragonette's

06:27:48.060 --> 06:27:48.240
dream.

06:27:48.299 --> 06:27:51.599
Firmly, he focused his mind on the nobles

06:27:51.599 --> 06:27:51.959
around him.

06:27:52.020 --> 06:27:54.720
Was it hours later that the courtyard

06:27:54.720 --> 06:27:55.380
finally cleared?

06:27:55.439 --> 06:27:58.319
The last noble gave him a respectful nod

06:27:58.319 --> 06:27:58.860
and flew away.

06:27:58.919 --> 06:28:02.340
Only a few dragonettes remained, including

06:28:02.340 --> 06:28:04.860
snowfall and hailstorm, who were both

06:28:04.860 --> 06:28:06.720
staring at their rankings, as if they

06:28:06.720 --> 06:28:08.159
could reshape them with the sheer force

06:28:08.159 --> 06:28:09.659
of their eyeballs.

06:28:09.720 --> 06:28:12.900
Winter's stomach ached with hunger, but

06:28:12.900 --> 06:28:14.520
he needed to talk to Hillstorm before

06:28:14.520 --> 06:28:15.119
going hunting.

06:28:15.180 --> 06:28:17.220
Maybe they could even go together.

06:28:17.340 --> 06:28:19.439
One of the things Winter had missed most

06:28:19.439 --> 06:28:20.819
while Hailstorm was away.

06:28:20.880 --> 06:28:23.819
Was the dragonette in 1st place allowed

06:28:23.819 --> 06:28:25.740
to hunt with a dragonette in last?

06:28:25.799 --> 06:28:28.200
Could he lose his new ranking if he

06:28:28.200 --> 06:28:29.639
associated with someone in the 7th

06:28:29.639 --> 06:28:30.060
circle?

06:28:30.119 --> 06:28:32.400
There had never been such a gap between

06:28:32.400 --> 06:28:33.479
family members before.

06:28:33.540 --> 06:28:35.880
So I wasn't quite sure what the protocol

06:28:35.880 --> 06:28:36.540
should be.

06:28:36.599 --> 06:28:38.639
But he was going to talk to Hailstorm

06:28:38.639 --> 06:28:38.880
anyway.

06:28:38.939 --> 06:28:41.520
The watching dragons could eat the moons

06:28:41.520 --> 06:28:42.119
if they cared.

06:28:42.180 --> 06:28:44.520
He needed to reassure his brother that

06:28:44.520 --> 06:28:46.080
climbing back up their rankings could be

06:28:46.080 --> 06:28:48.479
done and remind him that it had to be

06:28:48.479 --> 06:28:51.360
done fast, in case hailstorm's muddled

06:28:51.360 --> 06:28:53.040
memory couldn't recall his hatching day.

06:28:53.099 --> 06:28:56.279
The snow was packed down by the 100s of

06:28:56.279 --> 06:28:57.779
dragon feet that had passed through this

06:28:57.779 --> 06:28:58.080
morning.

06:28:58.139 --> 06:29:01.020
Shards of blue sunlight reflected off the

06:29:01.020 --> 06:29:03.479
tallest towers, illuminating odd

06:29:03.479 --> 06:29:04.500
splotches of the courtyard.

06:29:04.560 --> 06:29:06.840
Snowfall watched the brothers with

06:29:06.840 --> 06:29:08.939
slitted eyes as winter slid up to

06:29:08.939 --> 06:29:09.419
Hillstorm.

06:29:09.540 --> 06:29:11.400
Are you all right?

06:29:11.459 --> 06:29:12.540
Winter whispered.

06:29:12.599 --> 06:29:14.459
Hailstorm frowned at him.

06:29:14.520 --> 06:29:17.700
That's not a very ice wing question, he

06:29:17.700 --> 06:29:18.240
pointed out.

06:29:18.299 --> 06:29:21.060
He hesitated and then bowed deeply to

06:29:21.060 --> 06:29:21.419
Winter.

06:29:21.479 --> 06:29:23.159
Stop it.

06:29:23.220 --> 06:29:23.819
Stand up.

06:29:23.880 --> 06:29:25.139
Winter hissed.

06:29:25.200 --> 06:29:27.599
What a horrible feeling to have his

06:29:27.599 --> 06:29:29.639
exceptional older brother bowing to him

06:29:29.639 --> 06:29:30.299
like that.

06:29:30.360 --> 06:29:32.700
It made the whole world feel out of order

06:29:32.700 --> 06:29:34.740
as if the palace had been flipped upside

06:29:34.740 --> 06:29:34.919
down.

06:29:35.040 --> 06:29:37.979
He tried to hide how flustered he was as

06:29:37.979 --> 06:29:38.939
hailstorm stood back up.

06:29:39.000 --> 06:29:41.580
It seems like a good sign that you

06:29:41.580 --> 06:29:44.040
remember what is and isn't a nice wing

06:29:44.040 --> 06:29:44.340
question.

06:29:44.459 --> 06:29:45.479
He pointed out.

06:29:45.599 --> 06:29:47.400
Of course I do.

06:29:47.459 --> 06:29:50.040
Hailstorm said in a distant way.

06:29:50.099 --> 06:29:52.680
Everything is very clear.

06:29:52.740 --> 06:29:54.060
Now that I'm home.

06:29:54.180 --> 06:29:57.779
And yet, the way he glanced at the sky?

06:29:57.900 --> 06:30:00.119
Winter wondered if he had really shaken

06:30:00.119 --> 06:30:01.919
off all those sky wing memories yet.

06:30:01.979 --> 06:30:04.500
Perhaps he remembered how to be a nice

06:30:04.500 --> 06:30:06.479
wing, but he hadn't yet found his way

06:30:06.479 --> 06:30:07.799
back to being hailstorm.

06:30:07.919 --> 06:30:10.500
The brother Winter had missed for so long

06:30:10.500 --> 06:30:12.779
would have had a laughing comment about

06:30:12.779 --> 06:30:13.619
Winter's new rank.

06:30:13.740 --> 06:30:15.720
Hillstorm.

06:30:15.779 --> 06:30:17.459
Winter said hesitantly.

06:30:17.580 --> 06:30:19.979
What did you tell mother and father?

06:30:20.040 --> 06:30:22.560
He wished they'd thought to compare

06:30:22.560 --> 06:30:24.060
stories before coming home.

06:30:24.119 --> 06:30:26.040
He needed to know what he should say

06:30:26.040 --> 06:30:28.860
about pyrite and where hailstorm had been

06:30:28.860 --> 06:30:29.639
for the last 2 years.

06:30:29.700 --> 06:30:32.279
I told them the truth.

06:30:32.340 --> 06:30:35.040
Hailstorm drew himself up, looking

06:30:35.040 --> 06:30:35.759
offended.

06:30:35.819 --> 06:30:37.200
What else would I tell them?

06:30:37.319 --> 06:30:41.040
The truth about everything?

06:30:41.099 --> 06:30:44.580
Winter asked, about, about my friends

06:30:44.580 --> 06:30:45.000
too.

06:30:45.060 --> 06:30:48.659
Hailstorm's expression now was pure Ice

06:30:48.659 --> 06:30:49.080
Wing.

06:30:49.139 --> 06:30:52.439
If that's what you want to call them, he

06:30:52.439 --> 06:30:55.200
spat, yes, I told them about your little

06:30:55.200 --> 06:30:56.279
band of misfits.

06:30:56.340 --> 06:30:58.380
I hoped they would promote you up the

06:30:58.380 --> 06:30:58.919
rankings.

06:30:58.979 --> 06:31:01.560
I owed you that much, but I did not

06:31:01.560 --> 06:31:03.840
expect them to raise you so high, not

06:31:03.840 --> 06:31:05.159
with the entire truth in front of them.

06:31:05.220 --> 06:31:08.400
He fell silent, scowling at the wall

06:31:08.400 --> 06:31:08.700
again.

06:31:08.759 --> 06:31:13.319
This is so interesting, isn't it?

06:31:13.380 --> 06:31:15.779
Snowfall strutted toward them.

06:31:15.840 --> 06:31:19.139
Casting arch looks at the circles. 3

06:31:19.139 --> 06:31:20.340
moon's hailstorm.

06:31:20.400 --> 06:31:22.919
I bet you feel so peculiar right now.

06:31:22.979 --> 06:31:26.580
Leave him alone, Winter growled.

06:31:26.639 --> 06:31:27.540
She laughed.

06:31:27.599 --> 06:31:31.200
There's not quite enough distance between

06:31:31.200 --> 06:31:32.939
our numbers for you to be giving me

06:31:32.939 --> 06:31:34.439
orders, she said.

06:31:34.500 --> 06:31:37.259
Her snout was smiling, but her voice was

06:31:37.259 --> 06:31:38.819
all murderous stalactites.

06:31:38.880 --> 06:31:42.659
Besides, she added, I'm sure I won't be

06:31:42.659 --> 06:31:44.220
the only dragon who wants to ask

06:31:44.220 --> 06:31:46.380
Hailstorm about the diamond trial.

06:31:46.439 --> 06:31:48.540
Are you considering it?

06:31:48.599 --> 06:31:49.680
Hellstorm, dear?

06:31:49.740 --> 06:31:52.380
With only 12 days until you're 7?

06:31:52.439 --> 06:31:53.400
I certainly hope so.

06:31:53.459 --> 06:31:56.340
Hailstorm didn't answer her.

06:31:56.400 --> 06:31:58.680
Winter wondered if he remembered what the

06:31:58.680 --> 06:31:59.279
trial was.

06:31:59.400 --> 06:32:01.799
It had never been attempted in Winter's

06:32:01.799 --> 06:32:02.159
lifetime.

06:32:02.220 --> 06:32:04.380
He wasn't even sure it had happened in

06:32:04.380 --> 06:32:05.340
his father's lifetime.

06:32:05.400 --> 06:32:08.220
It was so rare for a dragonette to still

06:32:08.220 --> 06:32:10.740
be in the 6th or 7th circle when he

06:32:10.740 --> 06:32:13.319
reached his 7th hatching day, and rarer

06:32:13.319 --> 06:32:15.900
still, for any dragonette that inadequate

06:32:15.900 --> 06:32:17.880
to risk his life on the mysterious

06:32:17.880 --> 06:32:18.240
trial.

06:32:18.299 --> 06:32:21.060
But Hailstorm wasn't inadequate.

06:32:21.119 --> 06:32:23.759
It was pure bad luck that had him so low

06:32:23.759 --> 06:32:24.180
right now.

06:32:24.240 --> 06:32:27.299
Whatever the trial involved, surely he

06:32:27.299 --> 06:32:28.020
could conquer it easily.

06:32:28.080 --> 06:32:32.159
I mean, if you succeed, you'll move up to

06:32:32.159 --> 06:32:32.759
1st place.

06:32:32.819 --> 06:32:36.599
Snowfall said archly, your life would be

06:32:36.599 --> 06:32:39.299
right back on track instantaneously.

06:32:39.360 --> 06:32:42.119
You're going to do it, aren't you?

06:32:42.180 --> 06:32:43.799
Winter asked his brother.

06:32:43.860 --> 06:32:46.799
He couldn't understand why Hailstorm was

06:32:46.799 --> 06:32:48.479
staring fixedly down at his talons.

06:32:48.540 --> 06:32:50.880
Oh, how funny.

06:32:50.939 --> 06:32:53.819
I wouldn't have thought you'd want him to

06:32:53.819 --> 06:32:57.180
Snowfall went on, her voice sugary sweet

06:32:57.180 --> 06:32:58.080
and mocking.

06:32:58.139 --> 06:33:00.779
Have you forgotten that the diamond trial

06:33:00.779 --> 06:33:03.000
must also be undertaken by defending

06:33:03.000 --> 06:33:03.659
Challenger?

06:33:03.779 --> 06:33:06.720
That's whoever is currently in 1st place

06:33:06.720 --> 06:33:09.240
of course, but only one dragon can

06:33:09.240 --> 06:33:09.840
survive the trial.

06:33:09.900 --> 06:33:11.279
Dear me.

06:33:11.340 --> 06:33:13.619
It means it'll be brother against brother

06:33:13.619 --> 06:33:14.040
won't it?

06:33:14.099 --> 06:33:15.900
Tisk, tisk.

06:33:15.959 --> 06:33:18.900
What a conundrum for poor Hellstorm.

06:33:18.959 --> 06:33:22.919
Winter felt ice grip his heart and spread

06:33:22.919 --> 06:33:24.959
down to his talons, rooting him to the

06:33:24.959 --> 06:33:25.200
snow.

06:33:25.259 --> 06:33:28.080
He had forgotten about that part of the

06:33:28.080 --> 06:33:30.840
trial rules, or rather, it had never

06:33:30.840 --> 06:33:32.520
occurred to him that he might be on the

06:33:32.520 --> 06:33:34.799
other end, the defending 1st place

06:33:34.799 --> 06:33:37.020
dragonette, instead of the struggling

06:33:37.020 --> 06:33:38.340
lower circle challenger.

06:33:38.459 --> 06:33:40.680
But Hailstorm knew exactly how it

06:33:40.680 --> 06:33:40.979
worked.

06:33:41.040 --> 06:33:44.520
He knew it would have to be him or winter

06:33:44.520 --> 06:33:46.319
that only one could survive.

06:33:46.380 --> 06:33:49.740
And of course, Winter's parents did too.

06:33:49.860 --> 06:33:51.959
This was their plan.

06:33:52.080 --> 06:33:55.380
To move a dragon into 1st place, who

06:33:55.380 --> 06:33:56.939
would be no trouble for hailstorm to

06:33:56.939 --> 06:33:57.240
defeat.

06:33:57.360 --> 06:34:00.540
Snowfall was Glacier's daughter, and

06:34:00.540 --> 06:34:01.799
formidable in her own way.

06:34:01.860 --> 06:34:04.080
Only a few months from her hatching day

06:34:04.080 --> 06:34:05.400
but winter.

06:34:05.459 --> 06:34:07.500
Winter was expendable.

06:34:07.560 --> 06:34:10.319
Sacrifice one brother.

06:34:10.380 --> 06:34:11.639
To save the other.

06:34:11.700 --> 06:34:14.459
They couldn't give both of us high

06:34:14.459 --> 06:34:14.819
rankings.

06:34:14.880 --> 06:34:16.680
Someone would have called it unfair.

06:34:16.740 --> 06:34:20.040
This is more dramatic, more like my

06:34:20.040 --> 06:34:20.400
parents.

06:34:20.520 --> 06:34:23.459
A higher risk for much higher gain.

06:34:23.520 --> 06:34:25.619
They had to do it.

06:34:25.680 --> 06:34:28.439
Hailstorm's future is too valuable to

06:34:28.439 --> 06:34:28.860
throw away.

06:34:28.919 --> 06:34:31.979
He understood his parents' motivations

06:34:31.979 --> 06:34:32.400
completely.

06:34:32.520 --> 06:34:35.040
Whatever happened at the diamond trial

06:34:35.040 --> 06:34:38.400
they'd end up with a son in 1st place, and

06:34:38.400 --> 06:34:40.319
they'd get rid of a disgraceful last

06:34:40.319 --> 06:34:41.340
place offender.

06:34:41.400 --> 06:34:43.139
But hailstorm.

06:34:43.200 --> 06:34:46.680
His brother finally looked up at him, with

06:34:46.680 --> 06:34:48.419
his blue eyes sharp and alert once

06:34:48.419 --> 06:34:49.020
again.

06:34:49.080 --> 06:34:51.540
This is what you told me to do.

06:34:51.599 --> 06:34:55.139
His eyes seemed to say, You wanted me to

06:34:55.139 --> 06:34:56.279
be a true ice wing again.

06:34:56.340 --> 06:34:57.959
Well, here I am.

06:34:58.020 --> 06:35:01.740
And without a word, Hailstorm turned and

06:35:01.740 --> 06:35:04.500
left the courtyard, leaving winter behind

06:35:04.500 --> 06:35:06.779
as a new snow softly began to fall.

06:35:06.840 --> 06:35:11.520
Chapter 22.

06:35:11.759 --> 06:35:15.479
The summons arrived later that day.

06:35:15.540 --> 06:35:18.720
Hillstorm's messenger found winter on one

06:35:18.720 --> 06:35:21.180
of the tallest spires, gloomily picking

06:35:21.180 --> 06:35:22.619
apart the seal he'd caught.

06:35:22.680 --> 06:35:24.900
He hadn't been able to find anywhere else

06:35:24.900 --> 06:35:25.740
to eat in peace.

06:35:25.799 --> 06:35:29.040
Everywhere he went, dragons bowed or

06:35:29.040 --> 06:35:31.259
hurried over to offer him things, or

06:35:31.259 --> 06:35:32.880
buzzed around with a 1000000 questions.

06:35:32.939 --> 06:35:36.299
And as the day wore on, he'd heard the

06:35:36.299 --> 06:35:37.619
whispered phrase more and more.

06:35:37.680 --> 06:35:41.279
The diamond trial, the diamond trial.

06:35:41.340 --> 06:35:44.700
Every dragon over the age of 3 knew what

06:35:44.700 --> 06:35:46.799
it was, but no one could give him any

06:35:46.799 --> 06:35:47.159
details.

06:35:47.220 --> 06:35:50.639
The trial was shrouded in mystery, and

06:35:50.639 --> 06:35:52.200
there was no one left in the palace who'd

06:35:52.200 --> 06:35:54.299
survived it, since it hadn't been used in

06:35:54.299 --> 06:35:54.599
so long.

06:35:54.659 --> 06:35:58.380
Prince Winter, said a clipped voice

06:35:58.380 --> 06:36:00.540
behind him, shaking Winter out of his

06:36:00.540 --> 06:36:00.779
thoughts.

06:36:00.900 --> 06:36:03.599
The messenger handed over a small slab of

06:36:03.599 --> 06:36:05.939
ice, marked with precisely carved

06:36:05.939 --> 06:36:06.360
letters.

06:36:06.419 --> 06:36:08.580
She stepped back and bowed deeply.

06:36:08.639 --> 06:36:10.080
Good luck, sir.

06:36:10.139 --> 06:36:12.779
According to the brief, impersonal

06:36:12.779 --> 06:36:13.259
message.

06:36:13.319 --> 06:36:15.360
The trial was scheduled for sunset the

06:36:15.360 --> 06:36:15.659
next day.

06:36:15.720 --> 06:36:18.540
What would happen if I did something

06:36:18.540 --> 06:36:20.099
terrible between now and then?

06:36:20.159 --> 06:36:23.279
Winter wondered, if I snubbed the wrong

06:36:23.279 --> 06:36:25.740
dragon, or dripped seal blood in the

06:36:25.740 --> 06:36:28.319
pristine courtyard, or broke one of the

06:36:28.319 --> 06:36:29.400
queen's ice sculptures?

06:36:29.459 --> 06:36:31.139
Would I drop down the ranks?

06:36:31.200 --> 06:36:33.180
Would someone else have to face the trial

06:36:33.180 --> 06:36:34.020
with hailstorm?

06:36:34.080 --> 06:36:36.779
He had a feeling nothing like that would

06:36:36.779 --> 06:36:37.020
work.

06:36:37.080 --> 06:36:38.880
The plan was in motion.

06:36:38.939 --> 06:36:41.700
And Narwhal wouldn't put snowfall into

06:36:41.700 --> 06:36:44.040
the trial, no matter what winter did

06:36:44.040 --> 06:36:46.979
Queen Glacier would be too furious if she

06:36:46.979 --> 06:36:48.540
came back and found her daughter's life

06:36:48.540 --> 06:36:49.139
in jeopardy.

06:36:49.200 --> 06:36:52.319
And if he fled, or tried to refuse the

06:36:52.319 --> 06:36:54.360
challenge, he brings shame upon his whole

06:36:54.360 --> 06:36:57.000
family, and caused Hailstorm any chance

06:36:57.000 --> 06:36:58.799
he had at climbing their rankings before

06:36:58.799 --> 06:36:59.639
his hatching day.

06:36:59.700 --> 06:37:02.819
For a moment, winter turned the message

06:37:02.819 --> 06:37:05.279
slab over in his talons, and then he

06:37:05.279 --> 06:37:05.880
spread his wings.

06:37:05.939 --> 06:37:07.979
The only thing he could do was fight.

06:37:08.040 --> 06:37:10.259
Fight for his new position at the top of

06:37:10.259 --> 06:37:12.900
the rankings, fight for his family's

06:37:12.900 --> 06:37:15.840
melting honor, fight for his own life.

06:37:15.900 --> 06:37:18.840
It was what Hailstorm and his parents

06:37:18.840 --> 06:37:21.479
would want him to do, even if they hoped

06:37:21.479 --> 06:37:22.619
he would lose in the end.

06:37:22.680 --> 06:37:25.080
He still had to go down like an ice wing

06:37:25.080 --> 06:37:25.500
warrior.

06:37:25.560 --> 06:37:28.259
He spent the rest of the day in the

06:37:28.259 --> 06:37:30.479
palace library, looking for the diamond

06:37:30.479 --> 06:37:32.040
caves mentioned in the summons.

06:37:32.099 --> 06:37:34.740
He'd never heard of them, but there they

06:37:34.740 --> 06:37:36.180
were, on an old map.

06:37:36.240 --> 06:37:39.419
If the ice kingdom's peninsula was shaped

06:37:39.419 --> 06:37:41.639
like a dragon's head, the caves were

06:37:41.639 --> 06:37:43.200
located where her frost breath would come

06:37:43.200 --> 06:37:43.380
out.

06:37:43.439 --> 06:37:46.139
Diamond Caves.

06:37:46.200 --> 06:37:49.259
The most famous diamond and ice wing

06:37:49.259 --> 06:37:51.840
history was Queen Diamond, the mother of

06:37:51.840 --> 06:37:54.000
Prince Arctic, the animas who had been

06:37:54.000 --> 06:37:55.680
stolen by Foe Slayer, and the Night

06:37:55.680 --> 06:37:56.159
Wings.

06:37:56.159 --> 06:37:59.099
As a young dragon, Queen Diamond had

06:37:59.099 --> 06:38:01.500
given the tribe the gift of healing, 5

06:38:01.500 --> 06:38:04.020
narwhal horns enchanted to cure frost

06:38:04.020 --> 06:38:06.360
breath injuries, in case any ice wing

06:38:06.360 --> 06:38:08.580
ever wounded another, but there had been

06:38:08.580 --> 06:38:10.080
a few other diamonds over the years as

06:38:10.080 --> 06:38:10.259
well.

06:38:10.319 --> 06:38:12.959
He wondered if the caves and the trial

06:38:12.959 --> 06:38:14.459
were named after one of the historic

06:38:14.459 --> 06:38:15.779
diamonds, and why.

06:38:15.900 --> 06:38:19.560
He slept poorly that night, troubled by

06:38:19.560 --> 06:38:22.380
dreams of moon, and Kibley, and hailstorm

06:38:22.380 --> 06:38:25.020
all in danger, their scales melting and

06:38:25.020 --> 06:38:27.000
shifting into other colors, as he

06:38:27.000 --> 06:38:28.439
searched for them in the halls of the ice

06:38:28.439 --> 06:38:28.979
palace.

06:38:29.040 --> 06:38:32.159
Every time he woke, he wondered why he

06:38:32.159 --> 06:38:33.659
hadn't been visited by Scarlet again.

06:38:33.720 --> 06:38:36.779
He could only imagine her wrath when she

06:38:36.779 --> 06:38:39.000
discovered that pyrite hailstorm was

06:38:39.000 --> 06:38:39.419
gone.

06:38:39.479 --> 06:38:42.419
The next morning he found links, and

06:38:42.419 --> 06:38:43.500
asked her to train with him.

06:38:43.560 --> 06:38:45.659
The familiar fighting patterns came

06:38:45.659 --> 06:38:48.180
naturally, and focusing on her attacks

06:38:48.180 --> 06:38:50.279
helped drive out all the other worries in

06:38:50.279 --> 06:38:50.939
his head.

06:38:51.000 --> 06:38:52.919
They leaped and wrestled in the snow

06:38:52.919 --> 06:38:54.479
outside the palace until they were

06:38:54.479 --> 06:38:55.020
exhausted.

06:38:55.080 --> 06:38:57.840
Afterward, as they washed each other's

06:38:57.840 --> 06:38:59.520
dark blue blood off their claws and

06:38:59.520 --> 06:39:01.740
scales, they heard wing beats and looked

06:39:01.740 --> 06:39:02.279
up.

06:39:02.459 --> 06:39:03.840
Queen Glacier was back.

06:39:03.900 --> 06:39:07.619
Behind her flew 2 generals, and icicle.

06:39:07.680 --> 06:39:10.500
Winter watched them soar into the

06:39:10.500 --> 06:39:10.799
palace.

06:39:10.860 --> 06:39:13.139
He wondered what the queen would think of

06:39:13.139 --> 06:39:14.279
narwhal scheme.

06:39:14.340 --> 06:39:15.360
Would she stop it?

06:39:15.419 --> 06:39:17.759
Would she rearrange their rankings before

06:39:17.759 --> 06:39:18.180
sunset?

06:39:18.240 --> 06:39:19.560
Could she do that?

06:39:19.619 --> 06:39:21.900
Even with a summons already issued?

06:39:21.959 --> 06:39:24.659
If she could, she didn't.

06:39:24.720 --> 06:39:27.479
A few hours later, she was among the 12

06:39:27.479 --> 06:39:29.819
dragons assembling in the courtyard to

06:39:29.819 --> 06:39:31.020
fly to the diamond caves.

06:39:31.080 --> 06:39:35.819
Prince Winter, she said, and he bowed as

06:39:35.819 --> 06:39:36.540
deeply as he could.

06:39:36.599 --> 06:39:39.900
The ice wing queen was huge and majestic

06:39:39.900 --> 06:39:42.720
far more beautiful and imposing than any

06:39:42.720 --> 06:39:43.919
other queen in Pyria.

06:39:43.979 --> 06:39:46.560
He wondered if he was only imagining that

06:39:46.560 --> 06:39:48.360
he could see sympathy in her eyes.

06:39:48.419 --> 06:39:52.619
You've served the tribe well, returning

06:39:52.619 --> 06:39:55.740
Prince Hailstorm to us, she said, I wish

06:39:55.740 --> 06:39:57.180
you luck in the trial.

06:39:57.240 --> 06:39:59.639
Thank you, Your Majesty.

06:39:59.759 --> 06:40:00.720
He said.

06:40:00.779 --> 06:40:03.180
There was an uncomfortable prickle at the

06:40:03.180 --> 06:40:05.279
back of his neck, that he suspected meant

06:40:05.279 --> 06:40:07.860
hailstorm was nearby, staring at him.

06:40:07.919 --> 06:40:11.220
You will fly alongside me on the way to

06:40:11.220 --> 06:40:12.659
the caves, she said.

06:40:12.779 --> 06:40:15.000
I wish to hear about everything that has

06:40:15.000 --> 06:40:16.799
happened since you left us for Jade

06:40:16.799 --> 06:40:17.220
Mountain.

06:40:17.279 --> 06:40:19.680
I've heard your sister's version of

06:40:19.680 --> 06:40:22.380
events, but I suspect another perspective

06:40:22.380 --> 06:40:23.340
would be instructive.

06:40:23.400 --> 06:40:26.459
Yes, Your Majesty, he said.

06:40:26.520 --> 06:40:29.040
May I ask what's going to happen to

06:40:29.040 --> 06:40:29.580
Icicle?

06:40:29.639 --> 06:40:31.319
She looked grave.

06:40:31.380 --> 06:40:33.000
It's a good question.

06:40:33.060 --> 06:40:37.439
Queen Glory is not like other queens.

06:40:37.560 --> 06:40:40.560
I thought she would demand icicles

06:40:40.560 --> 06:40:43.619
execution, but instead she said she would

06:40:43.619 --> 06:40:46.439
leave icicles punishment, entirely to me

06:40:46.439 --> 06:40:49.080
in exchange for something unusual.

06:40:49.200 --> 06:40:51.959
A cutting from our moon globe tree.

06:40:52.080 --> 06:40:54.540
What does that mean?

06:40:54.599 --> 06:40:55.740
Winter asked.

06:40:55.799 --> 06:40:58.680
I wasn't sure either, said the Queen.

06:40:58.740 --> 06:41:00.840
Apparently with plans.

06:41:00.900 --> 06:41:03.360
You can take a piece of it, and bury that

06:41:03.360 --> 06:41:05.700
somewhere else, and then a new plant will

06:41:05.700 --> 06:41:06.419
grow from that piece.

06:41:06.479 --> 06:41:09.840
The idea, I think, is that she wants to

06:41:09.840 --> 06:41:12.000
grow moon globe trees in her rainforest

06:41:12.000 --> 06:41:14.580
to bring the gift of light to the rain

06:41:14.580 --> 06:41:15.959
wings and night wings.

06:41:16.020 --> 06:41:20.279
Oh, Winter said, startled.

06:41:20.340 --> 06:41:22.319
He didn't know quite how to wrap his head

06:41:22.319 --> 06:41:22.740
around this.

06:41:22.799 --> 06:41:24.720
Will it work?

06:41:24.779 --> 06:41:28.020
It might, said Queen Glacier.

06:41:28.080 --> 06:41:30.900
The tree is enchanted to behave like a

06:41:30.900 --> 06:41:31.380
real tree.

06:41:31.439 --> 06:41:33.779
And I can see how such a thing would

06:41:33.779 --> 06:41:35.340
benefit her tribes greatly.

06:41:35.400 --> 06:41:39.000
Although, as I said, it's an unusual

06:41:39.000 --> 06:41:40.680
queen who would choose a path toward

06:41:40.680 --> 06:41:43.740
peace and cooperation over clear and

06:41:43.740 --> 06:41:44.400
simple vengeance.

06:41:44.459 --> 06:41:47.520
She flicked her wings, frowning

06:41:47.520 --> 06:41:47.939
thoughtfully.

06:41:48.000 --> 06:41:51.000
The question is whether her tribes will

06:41:51.000 --> 06:41:52.380
be satisfied with this solution.

06:41:52.500 --> 06:41:54.299
I suppose we'll see.

06:41:54.419 --> 06:41:57.659
It may partly depend on how I ultimately

06:41:57.659 --> 06:42:00.720
punish icicle, but I haven't decided that

06:42:00.720 --> 06:42:00.900
yet.

06:42:00.959 --> 06:42:04.500
They lifted off into a cloudy gray sky

06:42:04.500 --> 06:42:07.919
flying southwest, with tundra and narwhal

06:42:07.919 --> 06:42:10.259
in the lead, and hailstorm trailing at

06:42:10.259 --> 06:42:12.240
the back, as befitted his last place

06:42:12.240 --> 06:42:12.840
ranking.

06:42:12.900 --> 06:42:15.240
Winter had to struggle to keep up with

06:42:15.240 --> 06:42:17.459
Queen Glacier's pace, but she didn't seem

06:42:17.459 --> 06:42:18.299
to notice.

06:42:18.360 --> 06:42:20.520
And since he had a feeling he was about

06:42:20.520 --> 06:42:22.799
to die, He told her almost everything

06:42:22.799 --> 06:42:25.979
about icicle trying to kill Starflight

06:42:25.979 --> 06:42:27.959
and how winter stopped her, about the

06:42:27.959 --> 06:42:30.419
rainforest and the volcano, about going

06:42:30.419 --> 06:42:33.360
in search of Scarlet, meeting Pyrite, and

06:42:33.360 --> 06:42:35.040
encountering the mysterious night wing in

06:42:35.040 --> 06:42:35.340
the valley.

06:42:35.459 --> 06:42:39.060
He left out a few things, though, Moon's

06:42:39.060 --> 06:42:40.139
powers and her prophecy.

06:42:40.200 --> 06:42:42.119
The fact that his friends were waiting

06:42:42.119 --> 06:42:43.799
for him in possibility at that very

06:42:43.799 --> 06:42:46.080
moment, the way he felt about them

06:42:46.080 --> 06:42:47.819
especially Moon.

06:42:47.939 --> 06:42:50.639
The queen only stopped him once during

06:42:50.639 --> 06:42:51.119
his story.

06:42:51.180 --> 06:42:53.040
Who?

06:42:53.040 --> 06:42:53.700
she asked.

06:42:53.759 --> 06:42:56.639
He paused, startled.

06:42:56.700 --> 06:42:57.659
Your majesty?

06:42:57.720 --> 06:43:00.959
You said there was an ice wing with the

06:43:00.959 --> 06:43:01.680
talons of peace.

06:43:01.740 --> 06:43:04.500
Queen Glacier shot a glance at the hole

06:43:04.500 --> 06:43:06.540
in the clouds where a piece of sunlight

06:43:06.540 --> 06:43:07.319
had muscled through.

06:43:07.380 --> 06:43:09.000
Who was it?

06:43:09.060 --> 06:43:12.540
His name was Sirius, Winter answered.

06:43:12.599 --> 06:43:14.580
I didn't know him, and he didn't know

06:43:14.580 --> 06:43:14.819
me.

06:43:14.880 --> 06:43:17.340
He was confusing.

06:43:17.400 --> 06:43:22.080
We haven't had a seris in many years, the

06:43:22.080 --> 06:43:22.680
queen mused.

06:43:22.799 --> 06:43:25.619
And I don't recall any ice wings leaving

06:43:25.619 --> 06:43:28.799
us for the talons of peace. unless they

06:43:28.799 --> 06:43:31.020
were from the lower classes, outside the

06:43:31.020 --> 06:43:31.560
rankings.

06:43:31.619 --> 06:43:33.659
Perhaps that's why I don't know him.

06:43:33.720 --> 06:43:36.360
Or perhaps he changed his name.

06:43:36.419 --> 06:43:40.319
He acted like an aristocrat, winter

06:43:40.319 --> 06:43:40.740
said.

06:43:40.799 --> 06:43:43.020
It hadn't even occurred to him that

06:43:43.020 --> 06:43:44.819
Sirius might be from the outskirts of the

06:43:44.819 --> 06:43:45.360
ice kingdom.

06:43:45.419 --> 06:43:47.340
That would explain why he didn't tell

06:43:47.340 --> 06:43:48.360
winter his ranking, though.

06:43:48.419 --> 06:43:51.779
He implied that he knew my parents, but

06:43:51.779 --> 06:43:53.459
in a way that seemed like he was lying.

06:43:53.520 --> 06:43:56.819
Hmm, Queen Glacier said.

06:43:56.880 --> 06:43:59.279
I'll look into it Go on.

06:43:59.340 --> 06:44:02.580
Most of the clouds had cleared, and the

06:44:02.580 --> 06:44:04.319
sky was shading into a brilliant orange

06:44:04.319 --> 06:44:06.659
red, when they finally dove out of the

06:44:06.659 --> 06:44:09.180
sky toward a snow covered evergreen

06:44:09.180 --> 06:44:11.400
forest, clustered at the base of an

06:44:11.400 --> 06:44:12.779
enormous white cliff.

06:44:12.840 --> 06:44:16.740
Pine needles jabbed Winter's snout as he

06:44:16.740 --> 06:44:18.180
dropped through the trees to the forest

06:44:18.180 --> 06:44:18.479
floor.

06:44:18.540 --> 06:44:21.240
The scent of the pines surrounded them

06:44:21.240 --> 06:44:23.819
and the snow crunched, like crushed paper

06:44:23.819 --> 06:44:25.020
under their talons.

06:44:25.080 --> 06:44:28.380
He thought of the pyrite scroll spell, now

06:44:28.380 --> 06:44:30.119
carefully tucked away in the skyfire

06:44:30.119 --> 06:44:31.139
pouch around his ankle.

06:44:31.200 --> 06:44:34.139
A cave mouth yawned in the side of the

06:44:34.139 --> 06:44:36.720
cliff, glittering with stalactites as

06:44:36.720 --> 06:44:39.360
sharp as teeth, eyes cover the walls

06:44:39.360 --> 06:44:41.459
floor, and ceiling all the way into the

06:44:41.459 --> 06:44:43.860
tunnel, as far as winter could see before

06:44:43.860 --> 06:44:44.759
darkness took over.

06:44:44.819 --> 06:44:47.220
He touched the moon globe over his

06:44:47.220 --> 06:44:49.319
shoulder. making sure it was there and

06:44:49.319 --> 06:44:49.740
still working.

06:44:49.799 --> 06:44:53.639
Prince his winter and hailstorm, the

06:44:53.639 --> 06:44:56.040
queen said briskly, your task is simple.

06:44:56.099 --> 06:44:59.220
Enter the diamond caves and search until

06:44:59.220 --> 06:45:01.080
you find the frozen dragon by the river

06:45:01.080 --> 06:45:01.680
chasm.

06:45:01.740 --> 06:45:04.080
Touch one of these spears to her.

06:45:04.139 --> 06:45:07.619
She took 2 gleaming diamond tipped spears

06:45:07.619 --> 06:45:09.840
from one of her guards and handed them to

06:45:09.840 --> 06:45:11.459
the brothers, one apiece.

06:45:11.520 --> 06:45:14.939
Whoever returns shall take 1st place in

06:45:14.939 --> 06:45:15.419
the rankings.

06:45:15.479 --> 06:45:16.500
The other.

06:45:16.560 --> 06:45:18.299
We bid farewell.

06:45:18.419 --> 06:45:20.639
Huh.

06:45:20.759 --> 06:45:26.040
Ominous and unspecific, snarked Kibley's

06:45:26.040 --> 06:45:26.939
voice in Winter's head.

06:45:27.060 --> 06:45:30.299
Norwhal stepped forward and tipped his

06:45:30.299 --> 06:45:31.979
long snout down to study his son's.

06:45:32.040 --> 06:45:37.139
Remember, be strong, he said, be vigilant

06:45:37.139 --> 06:45:38.340
strike first.

06:45:38.459 --> 06:45:42.659
We still are our families rank, added

06:45:42.659 --> 06:45:43.200
tundra.

06:45:43.259 --> 06:45:46.380
Narwhal's gaze rested on winter for a

06:45:46.380 --> 06:45:46.560
moment.

06:45:46.619 --> 06:45:48.599
Farewell.

06:45:48.659 --> 06:45:50.040
He said finally.

06:45:50.099 --> 06:45:52.080
Whichever of you does not return.

06:45:52.139 --> 06:45:54.840
I know you will accept defeat with

06:45:54.840 --> 06:45:55.200
honor.

06:45:55.319 --> 06:45:59.400
Sounds great, Winter thought, feeling

06:45:59.400 --> 06:46:00.180
lightheaded.

06:46:00.240 --> 06:46:02.459
Always wanted some defeat with a side of

06:46:02.459 --> 06:46:02.819
honor.

06:46:02.880 --> 06:46:05.340
He had a feeling he should say something

06:46:05.340 --> 06:46:08.040
here, but Hailstorm was already pivoting

06:46:08.040 --> 06:46:09.060
and marching into the cave.

06:46:09.119 --> 06:46:11.580
Winter glanced around at the assembled

06:46:11.580 --> 06:46:12.720
ice wings one more time.

06:46:12.779 --> 06:46:15.299
Was this the last time he would see his

06:46:15.299 --> 06:46:15.720
parents?

06:46:15.779 --> 06:46:18.119
His queen, and the sky.

06:46:18.240 --> 06:46:21.720
When he'd said goodbye to Moon, had it

06:46:21.720 --> 06:46:22.560
really been forever?

06:46:22.680 --> 06:46:25.259
He found he didn't have anything to say

06:46:25.259 --> 06:46:26.340
to his parents after all.

06:46:26.459 --> 06:46:29.700
Winter turned in silence and followed

06:46:29.700 --> 06:46:31.740
hailstorm into the icy tunnel.

06:46:31.799 --> 06:46:36.119
The diamond caves, according to the one

06:46:36.119 --> 06:46:38.159
map Winter had found, apparently

06:46:38.159 --> 06:46:40.080
stretched for miles in a kind of

06:46:40.080 --> 06:46:42.360
underground labyrinth with only one

06:46:42.360 --> 06:46:43.259
exit.

06:46:43.319 --> 06:46:46.139
Walls of ice hemmed them in on all sides

06:46:46.139 --> 06:46:48.240
glittering blue white in the light of

06:46:48.240 --> 06:46:49.020
their moon globes.

06:46:49.080 --> 06:46:52.139
In places, the ceiling brushed the horns

06:46:52.139 --> 06:46:52.860
on winter's head.

06:46:52.919 --> 06:46:56.099
In others, they had to creep along narrow

06:46:56.099 --> 06:46:59.279
ledges, over dark crevasses, gripping the

06:46:59.279 --> 06:47:01.259
ice with their claws, because if they

06:47:01.259 --> 06:47:03.599
tried to fly into that vast dark space

06:47:03.599 --> 06:47:05.939
they might not find their way back before

06:47:05.939 --> 06:47:07.619
tiring and falling to their deaths.

06:47:07.680 --> 06:47:11.099
Hailstorm glanced back at winter once or

06:47:11.099 --> 06:47:13.500
twice with a frown, as if he'd expected

06:47:13.500 --> 06:47:14.700
winter to choose a different path.

06:47:14.759 --> 06:47:17.520
But winter did not want to wander this

06:47:17.520 --> 06:47:19.799
labyrinth alone, with no way to know if

06:47:19.799 --> 06:47:21.900
hailstorm had completed the task yet or

06:47:21.900 --> 06:47:24.180
not, better to stick together and know

06:47:24.180 --> 06:47:24.540
for sure.

06:47:24.599 --> 06:47:28.080
They wandered for hours, perhaps in

06:47:28.080 --> 06:47:28.560
circles.

06:47:28.619 --> 06:47:31.020
Perhaps in spirals ever downward.

06:47:31.080 --> 06:47:33.540
Winter was beginning to wonder if the

06:47:33.540 --> 06:47:36.060
frozen dragon even existed at all, when

06:47:36.060 --> 06:47:37.860
they came out of a narrow tunnel and

06:47:37.860 --> 06:47:39.299
found the river chasm before them.

06:47:39.360 --> 06:47:41.040
This had to be it.

06:47:41.099 --> 06:47:43.619
A wide slash in the ice ahead of them

06:47:43.619 --> 06:47:46.380
with sheer walls that plunged down into a

06:47:46.380 --> 06:47:48.840
darkness that echoed with a rushing sound

06:47:48.840 --> 06:47:49.259
of a river.

06:47:49.380 --> 06:47:52.380
Winter lifted his moon globe higher

06:47:52.380 --> 06:47:55.020
scanning the cave, and felt a terrible

06:47:55.020 --> 06:47:56.459
chill run through his veins.

06:47:56.520 --> 06:48:00.599
The cave was filled with frozen dragons.

06:48:00.659 --> 06:48:04.080
Nearly 100 of them, glittered in the moon

06:48:04.080 --> 06:48:06.419
globe's light, some on this side of the

06:48:06.419 --> 06:48:08.159
chasm, but most of them on the other

06:48:08.159 --> 06:48:08.340
side.

06:48:08.400 --> 06:48:10.919
The one closest to him looked like an

06:48:10.919 --> 06:48:12.900
ordinary ice wing, with an almost

06:48:12.900 --> 06:48:15.720
cheerful expression on his face, stepping

06:48:15.720 --> 06:48:17.159
toward winter as though he were about to

06:48:17.159 --> 06:48:18.060
saunter out the door.

06:48:18.119 --> 06:48:21.000
But others were frozen in positions of

06:48:21.000 --> 06:48:23.700
terror, their talons covering their faces

06:48:23.700 --> 06:48:25.799
or their wings flung out as though they

06:48:25.799 --> 06:48:28.020
were trying to leap away, and he could

06:48:28.020 --> 06:48:29.759
see a few that had clearly been fighting

06:48:29.759 --> 06:48:31.380
when they were frozen, wearing

06:48:31.380 --> 06:48:32.520
expressions of fury.

06:48:32.639 --> 06:48:36.720
There were no other ways in or out, apart

06:48:36.720 --> 06:48:38.099
from the chasm and the tunnel behind

06:48:38.099 --> 06:48:38.459
him.

06:48:38.520 --> 06:48:41.400
Eerie blue bubbles morphed and twisted

06:48:41.400 --> 06:48:44.759
within the shining ice walls, moving, as

06:48:44.759 --> 06:48:46.439
though the cave itself was breathing.

06:48:46.500 --> 06:48:50.400
Which statue was the frozen dragon?

06:48:50.459 --> 06:48:52.139
Which one were they supposed to touch

06:48:52.139 --> 06:48:52.799
with a spear?

06:48:52.860 --> 06:48:55.860
Hailstorm was staring around at the ice

06:48:55.860 --> 06:48:57.419
sculptures as though he were one of

06:48:57.419 --> 06:48:57.720
them.

06:48:57.779 --> 06:49:00.720
Winter took a step into the cave, and

06:49:00.720 --> 06:49:02.700
noticed a sparkling pile of crushed ice

06:49:02.700 --> 06:49:03.479
near the entrance.

06:49:03.540 --> 06:49:06.240
He nudged his moon globe toward it

06:49:06.240 --> 06:49:08.880
wondering why the pile was so big, and

06:49:08.880 --> 06:49:11.040
then he saw a dragon's talon buried in

06:49:11.040 --> 06:49:13.439
the ice, with a few of its claws snapped

06:49:13.439 --> 06:49:13.680
off.

06:49:13.740 --> 06:49:16.979
Maybe this one had been mid-flight when

06:49:16.979 --> 06:49:19.139
he was frozen, and he smashed to pieces

06:49:19.139 --> 06:49:20.279
when he fell to the ground.

06:49:20.279 --> 06:49:22.919
Or maybe whoever froze him decided to

06:49:22.919 --> 06:49:24.840
finish the job by bashing his frozen

06:49:24.840 --> 06:49:26.340
corpse to smithereens.

06:49:26.400 --> 06:49:27.900
Winter shuddered.

06:49:27.959 --> 06:49:30.180
His tail spikes rattling along the

06:49:30.180 --> 06:49:30.360
floor.

06:49:30.419 --> 06:49:33.659
Suddenly, hailstorm leaped forward.

06:49:33.720 --> 06:49:36.479
Winter whirled and saw him racing toward

06:49:36.479 --> 06:49:39.060
a dragon on the far side of the chasm, a

06:49:39.060 --> 06:49:41.400
dragon larger than any of the others, with

06:49:41.400 --> 06:49:43.560
her claws outstretched, and her wings

06:49:43.560 --> 06:49:44.040
flared.

06:49:44.159 --> 06:49:47.880
Hailstorm sailed across the gap, landed

06:49:47.880 --> 06:49:50.099
pivoted, and struck the statue with his

06:49:50.099 --> 06:49:50.340
spear.

06:49:50.400 --> 06:49:53.400
It all happened in a moment, like a burst

06:49:53.400 --> 06:49:53.819
of lightning.

06:49:53.939 --> 06:49:56.340
By the time winter landed beside him

06:49:56.340 --> 06:49:58.380
Hailstorm was in battle position

06:49:58.380 --> 06:50:00.180
brandishing the spear against whatever

06:50:00.180 --> 06:50:00.959
happened next.

06:50:01.020 --> 06:50:04.740
A crackling sound came from the dragon

06:50:04.740 --> 06:50:08.580
and then, slowly, bits of ice began to

06:50:08.580 --> 06:50:11.040
break off, splintering into falling

06:50:11.040 --> 06:50:12.900
shards and shattering against the floor.

06:50:12.959 --> 06:50:16.979
The frozen dragon comes to life, Winter

06:50:16.979 --> 06:50:17.520
realized.

06:50:17.580 --> 06:50:18.779
It made sense.

06:50:18.840 --> 06:50:21.599
Then we fight her, and she kills one of

06:50:21.599 --> 06:50:22.919
us, and the other wins.

06:50:22.979 --> 06:50:25.860
He looked around at the frozen statues

06:50:25.860 --> 06:50:26.580
and winced.

06:50:26.639 --> 06:50:28.799
Or she freezes one of us.

06:50:28.860 --> 06:50:31.500
These must be all the dragons who've lost

06:50:31.500 --> 06:50:34.020
the trial, and I could be one of them

06:50:34.020 --> 06:50:34.200
soon.

06:50:34.259 --> 06:50:37.619
He looked back at the large frozen dragon

06:50:37.619 --> 06:50:39.599
and realized that she was not actually

06:50:39.599 --> 06:50:41.340
made of ice.

06:50:41.400 --> 06:50:44.459
She was encased inside the ice, and as

06:50:44.459 --> 06:50:46.979
her prison came apart, he saw her scales

06:50:46.979 --> 06:50:49.200
and they were as dark as a moonless

06:50:49.200 --> 06:50:49.500
night.

06:50:49.500 --> 06:50:51.779
This was a night wing.

06:50:51.900 --> 06:50:55.200
She pulled in her wings, and then flung

06:50:55.200 --> 06:50:57.360
out her claws, shaking the last of the

06:50:57.360 --> 06:50:57.900
ice off.

06:50:57.959 --> 06:51:00.720
Only 2 spots still glittered against her

06:51:00.720 --> 06:51:03.000
scales, a pair of shackles around her

06:51:03.000 --> 06:51:05.159
back ankles, although they didn't seem to

06:51:05.159 --> 06:51:06.060
be connected to anything.

06:51:06.119 --> 06:51:09.840
With a hiss, she turned in a circle, then

06:51:09.840 --> 06:51:11.819
whipped around to drop the full force of

06:51:11.819 --> 06:51:13.080
her glare on the princes.

06:51:13.139 --> 06:51:15.720
Oh, good.

06:51:15.779 --> 06:51:17.520
She rasped in a hoarse voice.

06:51:17.639 --> 06:51:20.759
More ice swing dragonettes with spears.

06:51:20.819 --> 06:51:23.159
I'm here to kill you.

06:51:23.220 --> 06:51:26.099
Hellstorm announced, without a tremor of

06:51:26.099 --> 06:51:27.419
insecurity in his voice.

06:51:27.479 --> 06:51:31.080
Aren't you all, she said dryly.

06:51:31.139 --> 06:51:33.299
Shall we introduce ourselves first?

06:51:33.360 --> 06:51:36.479
Hailstorm and Winter exchanged glances.

06:51:36.540 --> 06:51:37.799
Was that normal?

06:51:37.860 --> 06:51:40.380
Conversation with a creatively imprisoned

06:51:40.380 --> 06:51:41.099
night wing?

06:51:41.159 --> 06:51:45.479
I'm Prince Winter, said Winter, after an

06:51:45.479 --> 06:51:48.060
awkward pause, and this is my brother

06:51:48.060 --> 06:51:49.259
hailstorm.

06:51:49.319 --> 06:51:51.180
Brothers?

06:51:51.299 --> 06:51:54.900
Oh my, how devastating. said the night

06:51:54.900 --> 06:51:55.380
wing.

06:51:55.439 --> 06:51:56.939
Welcome to my prison.

06:51:57.000 --> 06:51:59.459
I am Those Slayer.

06:51:59.520 --> 06:52:02.819
Winter started back, his head reeling.

06:52:02.880 --> 06:52:06.299
Foe Slayer, the same foe Slayer who stole

06:52:06.299 --> 06:52:08.220
the Ice Wing Animus Prince, Arctic?

06:52:08.279 --> 06:52:11.099
The mother of Dark Stalker?

06:52:11.159 --> 06:52:15.479
Chapter 23.

06:52:15.720 --> 06:52:21.000
You've heard of me, she observed, with a

06:52:21.000 --> 06:52:21.720
hint of amusement.

06:52:21.779 --> 06:52:27.240
That's your, you don't mean, Winter

06:52:27.240 --> 06:52:28.619
couldn't seem to put the words together.

06:52:28.740 --> 06:52:31.860
Yes, the night wing said.

06:52:31.919 --> 06:52:34.740
You are ancient and terrible enemy.

06:52:34.799 --> 06:52:36.959
Everyone is always surprised.

06:52:37.080 --> 06:52:39.659
I want to know what the point is, of

06:52:39.659 --> 06:52:42.119
abducting and freezing your arch nemesis

06:52:42.119 --> 06:52:43.979
and then never telling anyone about it.

06:52:44.220 --> 06:52:45.959
Don't you want to shout it from the

06:52:45.959 --> 06:52:48.419
clouds, so everyone will know how

06:52:48.419 --> 06:52:50.159
dangerous and powerful you are.

06:52:50.220 --> 06:52:53.340
You can be alive after all this time

06:52:53.340 --> 06:52:53.520
though.

06:52:53.580 --> 06:52:56.159
Winter finally managed to get out.

06:52:56.220 --> 06:52:58.259
She folded in her wings.

06:52:58.319 --> 06:53:00.840
A curl of smoke rose from her snout.

06:53:00.900 --> 06:53:05.400
After a moment, she said, No, don't tell

06:53:05.400 --> 06:53:05.639
me.

06:53:05.700 --> 06:53:07.919
I don't want to know how long it's been.

06:53:07.979 --> 06:53:10.380
I'll never see them again anyway.

06:53:10.500 --> 06:53:13.560
Her tail flicked toward the icy cave

06:53:13.560 --> 06:53:13.979
walls.

06:53:14.040 --> 06:53:17.580
It's part of your queen's gift, ice

06:53:17.580 --> 06:53:18.000
wing.

06:53:18.060 --> 06:53:21.659
I've been frozen in time, so I only age

06:53:21.659 --> 06:53:23.459
in the moments when I'm unfrozen like

06:53:23.459 --> 06:53:23.639
this.

06:53:23.700 --> 06:53:28.259
The plan, evidently, is to keep me here a

06:53:28.259 --> 06:53:30.299
very, very long time.

06:53:30.360 --> 06:53:32.400
Thousands of years.

06:53:32.459 --> 06:53:34.560
Winter thought, aghast.

06:53:34.680 --> 06:53:37.380
She's been down here for 2000 years

06:53:37.380 --> 06:53:37.979
already.

06:53:38.040 --> 06:53:41.580
The gift of vengeance, he said.

06:53:41.639 --> 06:53:44.159
But Queen Diamond had already given the

06:53:44.159 --> 06:53:46.619
tribe her gift. long before her son was

06:53:46.619 --> 06:53:49.139
stolen, which meant she must have used

06:53:49.139 --> 06:53:51.119
her animus magic again to create this

06:53:51.119 --> 06:53:53.400
prison, had it driven her mad?

06:53:53.459 --> 06:53:55.619
He couldn't remember anything in the

06:53:55.619 --> 06:53:57.299
history books about what happened to her

06:53:57.299 --> 06:53:58.619
after Prince Arctic was gone.

06:53:58.740 --> 06:54:02.159
Indeed, said Foslayer.

06:54:02.279 --> 06:54:04.860
You could say my mother-in-law and I have

06:54:04.860 --> 06:54:06.540
a complicated relationship.

06:54:06.599 --> 06:54:09.779
He heard the scratch of claws on ice

06:54:09.779 --> 06:54:12.000
behind him, and then suddenly there was a

06:54:12.000 --> 06:54:13.139
blur of blue white motion.

06:54:13.200 --> 06:54:16.200
Hailstorm launched himself at Faux Slayer

06:54:16.200 --> 06:54:18.119
swinging the spear around to stab her

06:54:18.119 --> 06:54:18.599
through the heart.

06:54:18.659 --> 06:54:21.479
The night wing dodged aside and seized

06:54:21.479 --> 06:54:24.060
the spear, jerking it out of his talons.

06:54:24.119 --> 06:54:26.939
Hailstorm caught his balance, whirled, and

06:54:26.939 --> 06:54:27.900
attacked again.

06:54:27.959 --> 06:54:30.720
His claws slashed at her throat, and she

06:54:30.720 --> 06:54:32.279
slammed the blunt end of the spear

06:54:32.279 --> 06:54:34.200
against his side, knocking him into the

06:54:34.200 --> 06:54:34.380
wall.

06:54:34.439 --> 06:54:38.099
With a roar, he was up again, this time

06:54:38.099 --> 06:54:40.439
seizing her tail, and clambering up it

06:54:40.439 --> 06:54:43.259
onto her back, he sank his fierce claws

06:54:43.259 --> 06:54:44.639
into the flesh between her shoulder

06:54:44.639 --> 06:54:47.459
blades, and heaved up as though he was

06:54:47.459 --> 06:54:48.659
trying to yank out her spine.

06:54:48.720 --> 06:54:52.080
Thoslayer shrieked and threw herself into

06:54:52.080 --> 06:54:54.540
a roll, tucking her wings and landing

06:54:54.540 --> 06:54:55.619
heavily on Hellstorm.

06:54:55.680 --> 06:54:58.680
He lost his grip on her, amid an

06:54:58.680 --> 06:55:01.200
explosion of sharp cracks, which sounded

06:55:01.200 --> 06:55:02.939
to winter like bones snapping.

06:55:03.000 --> 06:55:06.180
The night wing leaped free again, and

06:55:06.180 --> 06:55:08.220
came straight at Hailstorm, while his

06:55:08.220 --> 06:55:09.299
underbelly was exposed.

06:55:09.360 --> 06:55:13.020
Her back talons pinned down his tail, and

06:55:13.020 --> 06:55:14.880
she raised the spear to impale him

06:55:14.880 --> 06:55:15.240
through the heart.

06:55:15.360 --> 06:55:18.119
Winter threw himself at her without a 2nd

06:55:18.119 --> 06:55:19.919
thought, tackling her to the ground.

06:55:19.979 --> 06:55:22.799
They rolled and twisted, and slid across

06:55:22.799 --> 06:55:25.020
the icy floor, kicking at each other with

06:55:25.020 --> 06:55:25.680
their claws.

06:55:25.799 --> 06:55:28.619
You idiot, she yelled at him.

06:55:28.740 --> 06:55:31.500
His head bashed into the cave wall, and

06:55:31.500 --> 06:55:33.479
tears of pain sprang into his eyes.

06:55:33.540 --> 06:55:36.299
Do ice wings get dumber every year.

06:55:36.360 --> 06:55:37.619
Don't you want to win?

06:55:37.740 --> 06:55:39.720
He flung her off so hard.

06:55:39.840 --> 06:55:42.119
She spun across the ice and nearly slid

06:55:42.119 --> 06:55:43.500
over the edge into the chasm.

06:55:43.560 --> 06:55:47.040
That's not what I want, Winter shouted.

06:55:47.099 --> 06:55:49.740
I don't want to win if it means hailstorm

06:55:49.740 --> 06:55:50.159
has to die.

06:55:50.279 --> 06:55:53.520
He whirled to face his brother, who was

06:55:53.520 --> 06:55:54.659
on his feet and panting.

06:55:54.720 --> 06:55:57.060
His sides splattered with red and blue

06:55:57.060 --> 06:55:57.419
blood.

06:55:57.479 --> 06:56:00.000
What are we fighting for?

06:56:00.060 --> 06:56:01.380
A number on a wall?

06:56:01.439 --> 06:56:03.540
Your life is more important to me than

06:56:03.540 --> 06:56:04.740
the rankings hailstorm.

06:56:04.799 --> 06:56:06.840
Hailstorm growled.

06:56:06.900 --> 06:56:09.299
I would have said the same thing, brother

06:56:09.299 --> 06:56:12.659
he said, but I sacrificed myself for you

06:56:12.659 --> 06:56:13.259
once already.

06:56:13.319 --> 06:56:15.419
And it was the worst thing that ever

06:56:15.419 --> 06:56:15.900
happened to me.

06:56:15.959 --> 06:56:19.560
You can't imagine how it feels to know

06:56:19.560 --> 06:56:20.159
what I've done.

06:56:20.279 --> 06:56:23.099
To have these memories in my head.

06:56:23.159 --> 06:56:24.900
He clawed at his temples.

06:56:24.959 --> 06:56:26.939
I want my life back.

06:56:27.000 --> 06:56:28.799
I want myself back.

06:56:28.919 --> 06:56:30.479
And I won't get it.

06:56:30.540 --> 06:56:32.520
If I reach my hatching day in last

06:56:32.520 --> 06:56:32.819
place.

06:56:32.880 --> 06:56:34.799
I have to be 1st again.

06:56:34.860 --> 06:56:38.400
The old familiar guilt with surging back

06:56:38.400 --> 06:56:38.819
through winter.

06:56:38.880 --> 06:56:40.259
My fault.

06:56:40.319 --> 06:56:42.240
My fault, my fault.

06:56:42.360 --> 06:56:44.639
I didn't think it would be you.

06:56:44.700 --> 06:56:47.040
I'd have to destroy. in order to get back

06:56:47.040 --> 06:56:47.400
to first.

06:56:47.459 --> 06:56:49.439
Hellstorm admitted.

06:56:49.500 --> 06:56:51.240
But it had to be someone.

06:56:51.360 --> 06:56:53.880
I won't be a traitor to my tribe

06:56:53.880 --> 06:56:54.180
anymore.

06:56:54.240 --> 06:56:55.799
When I'm number one.

06:56:55.860 --> 06:56:56.939
I can prove it.

06:56:57.000 --> 06:57:00.720
Winter looked back at Foslayer, who had

06:57:00.720 --> 06:57:02.459
slowly risen to her feet, and was

06:57:02.459 --> 06:57:03.779
listening with a curious expression.

06:57:03.900 --> 06:57:06.240
Is there any other way?

06:57:06.360 --> 06:57:07.380
He asked her.

06:57:07.439 --> 06:57:09.299
A way we can both live?

06:57:09.360 --> 06:57:12.720
I'm not the right dragon to ask, she

06:57:12.720 --> 06:57:13.080
said.

06:57:13.139 --> 06:57:15.599
Frankly, I'd rather see you all dead.

06:57:15.659 --> 06:57:19.139
I'll take last place, Winter said to

06:57:19.139 --> 06:57:19.740
Hailstorm.

06:57:19.799 --> 06:57:21.540
What if we told the queen that?

06:57:21.599 --> 06:57:22.799
Would you let a switch?

06:57:22.860 --> 06:57:24.779
Hailstorm snorted.

06:57:24.840 --> 06:57:26.819
Where's the honor in that for me?

06:57:26.819 --> 06:57:27.900
he asked.

06:57:27.959 --> 06:57:30.119
No, they won't agree to it.

06:57:30.180 --> 06:57:32.880
If we both come out of the caves, they'll

06:57:32.880 --> 06:57:35.340
just kill one of us, and probably leave

06:57:35.340 --> 06:57:36.419
the other and last place.

06:57:36.479 --> 06:57:39.540
He picked up the spear Foslayer had

06:57:39.540 --> 06:57:41.099
dropped and twisted it between his

06:57:41.099 --> 06:57:41.520
talons.

06:57:41.580 --> 06:57:44.639
The Nightwing breathed a jet of flame

06:57:44.639 --> 06:57:46.740
that melted the wing of the statue

06:57:46.740 --> 06:57:47.759
closest to her.

06:57:47.819 --> 06:57:49.919
This is very moving.

06:57:49.979 --> 06:57:52.259
But would one of you please kill me

06:57:52.259 --> 06:57:52.619
already?

06:57:52.740 --> 06:57:55.680
She paced toward them, her dark eyes

06:57:55.680 --> 06:57:57.000
reflecting the light of their moon

06:57:57.000 --> 06:57:57.540
globes.

06:57:57.659 --> 06:57:59.159
I'm tired.

06:57:59.220 --> 06:58:01.979
I haven't eaten in 100s of years, and

06:58:01.979 --> 06:58:03.659
these days it's more painful to be awake

06:58:03.659 --> 06:58:05.459
than to go through the process of dying

06:58:05.459 --> 06:58:05.639
again.

06:58:05.759 --> 06:58:07.740
Dying?

06:58:07.799 --> 06:58:08.700
Winter asked.

06:58:08.759 --> 06:58:12.240
Yes, she said, stopping in front of them

06:58:12.240 --> 06:58:13.200
and spreading her wings.

06:58:13.259 --> 06:58:16.799
You stab me, I die painfully, and then I

06:58:16.799 --> 06:58:18.299
go back to being frozen until someone

06:58:18.299 --> 06:58:18.959
wakes me up again.

06:58:19.020 --> 06:58:21.180
It's a cunning enchantment.

06:58:21.240 --> 06:58:24.299
The 1st 40 times Queen Diamond killed me

06:58:24.299 --> 06:58:24.599
herself.

06:58:24.659 --> 06:58:27.419
Voslayer let out a bitter chuckle.

06:58:27.479 --> 06:58:30.479
I suspect, the original point of the

06:58:30.479 --> 06:58:32.580
spell was that she wasn't satisfied with

06:58:32.580 --> 06:58:33.840
killing me just once.

06:58:33.900 --> 06:58:36.119
But then the 401st time.

06:58:36.180 --> 06:58:37.919
There were 2 dragonettes here.

06:58:37.979 --> 06:58:40.619
So she must have decided I could be used

06:58:40.619 --> 06:58:41.700
for this other purpose.

06:58:41.759 --> 06:58:43.979
Whatever you 2 are here for.

06:58:44.040 --> 06:58:46.860
So you just get murdered?

06:58:46.860 --> 06:58:49.020
Over and over again?

06:58:49.080 --> 06:58:49.919
Winter asked.

06:58:49.979 --> 06:58:52.979
That's my punishment.

06:58:53.099 --> 06:58:55.500
Beauslayer shrugged eloquently.

06:58:55.560 --> 06:58:57.540
Here's some advice for you.

06:58:57.599 --> 06:59:00.419
Never make an animus angry.

06:59:00.540 --> 06:59:03.419
Winter turned to hailstorm, puzzled.

06:59:03.479 --> 06:59:06.180
Then how did all these other dragons get

06:59:06.180 --> 06:59:06.540
frozen?

06:59:06.659 --> 06:59:09.180
Maybe that's part of the spell too.

06:59:09.240 --> 06:59:12.180
One kills Foe Slayer, and then the other

06:59:12.180 --> 06:59:12.720
one freezes.

06:59:12.840 --> 06:59:15.900
It seemed more complicated than the usual

06:59:15.900 --> 06:59:16.680
animus spell.

06:59:16.799 --> 06:59:19.319
Hailstorm's eyes were fixed on the

06:59:19.319 --> 06:59:19.740
spear.

06:59:19.799 --> 06:59:22.560
You do it, he said gruffly.

06:59:22.619 --> 06:59:23.759
You kill her.

06:59:23.819 --> 06:59:26.400
No Winter said.

06:59:26.459 --> 06:59:28.740
Hillstorm, you're right.

06:59:28.799 --> 06:59:31.080
You've already sacrificed yourself for

06:59:31.080 --> 06:59:31.319
me.

06:59:31.439 --> 06:59:33.540
I've been waiting for 2 years to make it

06:59:33.540 --> 06:59:33.959
up to you.

06:59:34.020 --> 06:59:37.560
Winter, Hellstorm said.

06:59:37.619 --> 06:59:40.200
I'm not going to be responsible for your

06:59:40.200 --> 06:59:42.779
death a 2nd time, Winter insisted.

06:59:42.840 --> 06:59:45.360
It's my turn, and let's face it.

06:59:45.419 --> 06:59:47.759
This is what mother and father would

06:59:47.759 --> 06:59:48.000
want.

06:59:48.060 --> 06:59:51.360
Hailstorm winced, but didn't argue.

06:59:51.419 --> 06:59:55.259
Just be a great ice wing, Winter said.

06:59:55.319 --> 06:59:57.419
Help keep the tribes at peace.

06:59:57.479 --> 06:59:58.979
That's what I would want.

06:59:59.040 --> 07:00:04.319
This is peculiar, Those Slayer spoke up

07:00:04.319 --> 07:00:06.659
but not as peculiar as you might think.

07:00:06.720 --> 07:00:09.180
I've seen a surprising amount of this

07:00:09.180 --> 07:00:10.259
I'll die for you.

07:00:10.319 --> 07:00:11.819
No, I'll die for you.

07:00:11.880 --> 07:00:14.520
No, let me be the brave sacrifice.

07:00:14.580 --> 07:00:17.040
Nonsense from ice wings over the years.

07:00:17.099 --> 07:00:21.000
Do it, Winter said to Hellstorm.

07:00:21.060 --> 07:00:22.080
I'm ready.

07:00:22.139 --> 07:00:25.439
Me too, said Foslayer.

07:00:25.560 --> 07:00:27.779
As fast and clean as you can, please.

07:00:27.840 --> 07:00:31.619
Hailstorm took the spear, leveled it at

07:00:31.619 --> 07:00:33.840
Thoe Slayer's heart and drove it swiftly

07:00:33.840 --> 07:00:34.380
through her chest.

07:00:34.439 --> 07:00:37.560
She gritted her teeth, her face twisted

07:00:37.560 --> 07:00:40.080
in pain, and then the ice came crawling

07:00:40.080 --> 07:00:41.759
up from the shackles on her ankles

07:00:41.759 --> 07:00:44.700
freezing her from her tail forward to her

07:00:44.700 --> 07:00:46.139
wings, neck, and head.

07:00:46.200 --> 07:00:49.020
Hailstorm pulled the spear free before

07:00:49.020 --> 07:00:51.419
the ice got there, and Winter saw the

07:00:51.419 --> 07:00:54.060
wound heal over just before Foslayer was

07:00:54.060 --> 07:00:54.659
completely frozen.

07:00:54.720 --> 07:00:57.720
He closed his eyes, expecting the world

07:00:57.720 --> 07:00:59.819
to go dark, but it didn't.

07:00:59.939 --> 07:01:01.380
Nothing happened at all.

07:01:01.439 --> 07:01:04.380
After a moment, he opened his eyes again

07:01:04.380 --> 07:01:07.319
and saw a hailstorm, standing by the edge

07:01:07.319 --> 07:01:07.860
of the chasm.

07:01:07.979 --> 07:01:10.080
Why didn't it work?

07:01:10.080 --> 07:01:11.220
Winter asked.

07:01:11.279 --> 07:01:12.720
I'm not frozen.

07:01:12.779 --> 07:01:15.299
He looked around at the other statues.

07:01:15.360 --> 07:01:17.279
Something whispered in his mind.

07:01:17.340 --> 07:01:20.520
An explanation, although it still didn't

07:01:20.520 --> 07:01:21.240
quite fit together.

07:01:21.299 --> 07:01:25.020
Right, Hailstorm said.

07:01:25.080 --> 07:01:27.000
He turned to look at his brother.

07:01:27.060 --> 07:01:29.880
That's because it's not part of the

07:01:29.880 --> 07:01:30.779
original enchantment.

07:01:30.840 --> 07:01:33.779
The spell on the night wing isn't what

07:01:33.779 --> 07:01:34.860
froze these dragons.

07:01:34.979 --> 07:01:36.779
He lifted the spear.

07:01:36.840 --> 07:01:38.700
That's what these do.

07:01:38.759 --> 07:01:40.319
That's what.

07:01:40.799 --> 07:01:43.080
That's what I'm supposed to do to you.

07:01:43.139 --> 07:01:45.840
Winter was silent.

07:01:45.900 --> 07:01:48.479
Everything was starting to make a kind of

07:01:48.479 --> 07:01:49.619
awful sense.

07:01:49.680 --> 07:01:53.340
Mother and father told me earlier today.

07:01:53.400 --> 07:01:56.520
Hailstorm's wings drooped to the floor.

07:01:56.580 --> 07:01:59.459
They told me that no matter who killed

07:01:59.459 --> 07:02:00.419
Foslayer.

07:02:00.479 --> 07:02:02.220
I was the one chosen to win.

07:02:02.279 --> 07:02:05.639
That I was to take this spear, and stab

07:02:05.639 --> 07:02:07.080
you the same way I stabbed her.

07:02:07.139 --> 07:02:09.299
Freezing you like all these other

07:02:09.299 --> 07:02:09.900
dragons.

07:02:09.959 --> 07:02:13.139
Then I was guaranteed, 1st place.

07:02:13.200 --> 07:02:16.020
Do they do this every time?

07:02:16.139 --> 07:02:17.340
Winter wondered.

07:02:17.400 --> 07:02:19.919
Choose one dragonette to win?

07:02:19.979 --> 07:02:22.919
Tell only that dragonette the secret of

07:02:22.919 --> 07:02:24.659
the spears, and how to freeze the other.

07:02:24.720 --> 07:02:27.900
He shouldn't have felt surprised. or

07:02:27.900 --> 07:02:28.380
betrayed.

07:02:28.439 --> 07:02:30.360
Of course his parents would choose

07:02:30.360 --> 07:02:31.200
hailstorm.

07:02:31.259 --> 07:02:34.200
This was really quite normal, given the

07:02:34.200 --> 07:02:37.200
patterns of their lives so far, but it's

07:02:37.200 --> 07:02:37.380
still.

07:02:37.500 --> 07:02:39.599
It still hurt.

07:02:39.659 --> 07:02:42.779
Deep inside him, where he'd thought his

07:02:42.779 --> 07:02:44.040
family couldn't hurt him anymore.

07:02:44.099 --> 07:02:48.479
Moon, Kibli, and Kinkachu wouldn't do

07:02:48.479 --> 07:02:49.319
something like this to me.

07:02:49.380 --> 07:02:50.759
He thought.

07:02:50.939 --> 07:02:53.700
All right, he said out loud.

07:02:53.759 --> 07:02:56.340
Then I guess that's what you have to do.

07:02:56.400 --> 07:02:59.580
He set down his own spear and braced

07:02:59.580 --> 07:02:59.939
himself.

07:03:00.000 --> 07:03:04.259
You know I can't, Hellstorm snapped.

07:03:04.319 --> 07:03:06.119
You're the one who rescued me.

07:03:06.180 --> 07:03:07.319
You're my brother.

07:03:07.439 --> 07:03:09.360
I'm not going to murder you now.

07:03:09.419 --> 07:03:11.279
So you're just going to have to do it to

07:03:11.279 --> 07:03:11.459
me.

07:03:11.520 --> 07:03:14.340
He tossed his spirit to winter, who

07:03:14.340 --> 07:03:16.319
jumped aside and let it clatter to the

07:03:16.319 --> 07:03:16.500
ground.

07:03:16.560 --> 07:03:19.139
They stared at each other for a long

07:03:19.139 --> 07:03:21.840
moment as the rush of the river below

07:03:21.840 --> 07:03:22.560
filled the cavern.

07:03:22.680 --> 07:03:25.680
All the frozen dragons seemed to be

07:03:25.680 --> 07:03:28.259
waiting, like a captive audience enjoying

07:03:28.259 --> 07:03:29.040
the suspense.

07:03:29.040 --> 07:03:32.880
If we can't kill each other, Winter

07:03:32.880 --> 07:03:33.180
said.

07:03:33.240 --> 07:03:35.279
Maybe we leave it like this.

07:03:35.340 --> 07:03:38.700
You go out and claim victory, and I wait

07:03:38.700 --> 07:03:39.419
to sneak out later.

07:03:39.479 --> 07:03:41.459
We both live.

07:03:41.520 --> 07:03:43.860
Hailstorm shook his head.

07:03:43.919 --> 07:03:47.040
As soon as you got home, they throw me

07:03:47.040 --> 07:03:49.259
back into last place, and probably you as

07:03:49.259 --> 07:03:49.439
well.

07:03:49.500 --> 07:03:51.599
I won't go home.

07:03:51.659 --> 07:03:53.220
Winter said.

07:03:53.279 --> 07:03:56.040
He felt a lump forming in his throat.

07:03:56.099 --> 07:03:58.200
Like frost breath icing over his

07:03:58.200 --> 07:03:58.740
windpipe.

07:03:58.799 --> 07:04:01.860
I'll stay away from the ice kingdom.

07:04:01.919 --> 07:04:04.319
It didn't sound possible.

07:04:04.380 --> 07:04:06.959
His whole life was about being an ice

07:04:06.959 --> 07:04:07.439
wing.

07:04:07.500 --> 07:04:10.919
Being Queen Glacier's nephew, proving

07:04:10.919 --> 07:04:12.479
something to tundra and narwhal.

07:04:12.540 --> 07:04:14.939
He believed in the perfection and

07:04:14.939 --> 07:04:16.560
superiority of the ice kingdom.

07:04:16.619 --> 07:04:19.259
How could he ever be happy anywhere

07:04:19.259 --> 07:04:19.439
else?

07:04:19.500 --> 07:04:22.259
But now he'd been to so many other

07:04:22.259 --> 07:04:23.099
places.

07:04:23.159 --> 07:04:25.380
He'd seen the world beyond the ice

07:04:25.380 --> 07:04:25.919
kingdom.

07:04:25.979 --> 07:04:27.959
And it wasn't so terrible, really.

07:04:28.020 --> 07:04:31.259
Because happiness is not where I am.

07:04:31.319 --> 07:04:33.540
It's who I'm with.

07:04:33.599 --> 07:04:37.139
And he knew exactly who he wanted to be

07:04:37.139 --> 07:04:37.380
with.

07:04:37.439 --> 07:04:41.400
Hailstorm's claws curled in and out as he

07:04:41.400 --> 07:04:41.639
thought.

07:04:41.700 --> 07:04:44.159
He reached out and picked up one of the

07:04:44.159 --> 07:04:46.919
diamond tipped spears, and Winter felt a

07:04:46.919 --> 07:04:48.900
quick bolt of fear that his brother had

07:04:48.900 --> 07:04:50.099
decided to kill him anyway.

07:04:50.159 --> 07:04:53.520
But Hailstorm just bowed, and took a step

07:04:53.520 --> 07:04:53.939
backward.

07:04:54.000 --> 07:04:57.299
Thank you, brother, he said.

07:04:57.360 --> 07:04:58.500
I hope.

07:04:58.619 --> 07:05:01.200
I hope one day I'll see you again.

07:05:01.259 --> 07:05:05.040
Winter nodded, not trusting himself to

07:05:05.040 --> 07:05:05.400
speak.

07:05:05.459 --> 07:05:08.279
Hailstorm turned and flew across the

07:05:08.279 --> 07:05:08.759
chasm.

07:05:08.819 --> 07:05:11.580
In the entrance to the tunnel, he paused

07:05:11.580 --> 07:05:14.639
glancing back at Winter, and then he fled

07:05:14.639 --> 07:05:16.979
his footsteps echoing behind him.

07:05:17.040 --> 07:05:19.680
A long time past.

07:05:19.740 --> 07:05:22.560
Winter tried to keep track of the hours

07:05:22.560 --> 07:05:25.020
in his head, calculating when it would be

07:05:25.020 --> 07:05:25.319
dawn.

07:05:25.380 --> 07:05:29.400
Finally, he stood up, stretched, and

07:05:29.400 --> 07:05:31.020
picked up the other diamond tipped

07:05:31.020 --> 07:05:31.439
spear.

07:05:31.560 --> 07:05:36.060
Taking a deep breath, he reached out and

07:05:36.060 --> 07:05:37.319
tapped Foe Slayer with it.

07:05:37.380 --> 07:05:41.700
Chapter 24.

07:05:41.939 --> 07:05:46.020
The ice around the night wing cracked and

07:05:46.020 --> 07:05:48.840
splintered, just as it had before, and

07:05:48.840 --> 07:05:51.119
Thoe Slayer slowly opened her eyes.

07:05:51.419 --> 07:05:54.000
Surprise flashed across her face when she

07:05:54.000 --> 07:05:54.720
saw winter there.

07:05:54.779 --> 07:05:58.259
This is a first, she said.

07:05:58.380 --> 07:06:00.540
I've never been brought back by the same

07:06:00.540 --> 07:06:01.500
dragonettes before.

07:06:01.560 --> 07:06:03.479
Did you want a chance to kill me too?

07:06:03.540 --> 07:06:06.119
Seems a little over the top if you don't

07:06:06.119 --> 07:06:06.900
mind my saying so.

07:06:06.959 --> 07:06:09.840
Listen, Winter said.

07:06:09.900 --> 07:06:13.259
I don't know if you even realize how much

07:06:13.259 --> 07:06:15.240
you stole from us when you took away our

07:06:15.240 --> 07:06:16.020
animus magic.

07:06:16.080 --> 07:06:20.939
The gifts of light, of order, and running

07:06:20.939 --> 07:06:22.860
like a hidden current through every

07:06:22.860 --> 07:06:25.680
dragonette's understanding of himself, the

07:06:25.680 --> 07:06:28.080
gift of faith in their tribe that came

07:06:28.080 --> 07:06:30.180
from the indisputable wisdom of how ice

07:06:30.180 --> 07:06:31.560
wings handled their magic.

07:06:31.619 --> 07:06:35.580
Imagine what our kingdom would be like if

07:06:35.580 --> 07:06:38.040
we still had animus dragons, Winter went

07:06:38.040 --> 07:06:38.220
on.

07:06:38.340 --> 07:06:40.139
What else would we have invented?

07:06:40.259 --> 07:06:43.860
I suspect, you wouldn't have stayed in

07:06:43.860 --> 07:06:46.799
your little kingdom much longer, Thoslayer

07:06:46.799 --> 07:06:47.220
answered him.

07:06:47.279 --> 07:06:49.799
Have you considered that your perfect

07:06:49.799 --> 07:06:51.900
tribe might have used the magic for evil

07:06:51.900 --> 07:06:52.979
as well as good?

07:06:53.040 --> 07:06:55.139
Was that true?

07:06:55.200 --> 07:06:57.900
Would we have done something terrible

07:06:57.900 --> 07:06:58.259
with it?

07:06:58.319 --> 07:07:01.319
What kind of gift might Queen Glacier

07:07:01.319 --> 07:07:02.880
have asked for during the War of Sand

07:07:02.880 --> 07:07:03.720
Wing succession?

07:07:03.779 --> 07:07:05.880
He shook out his wings.

07:07:05.939 --> 07:07:09.540
When you stole Prince Arctic, you stole

07:07:09.540 --> 07:07:12.060
all our future gifts, everything that we

07:07:12.060 --> 07:07:12.599
might have become.

07:07:12.659 --> 07:07:15.240
And I can see why some dragons would

07:07:15.240 --> 07:07:16.439
think that's unforgivable.

07:07:16.500 --> 07:07:19.979
His scales felt heavier and heavier as he

07:07:19.979 --> 07:07:20.220
went on.

07:07:20.279 --> 07:07:26.220
But, this, this imprisonment, for

07:07:26.220 --> 07:07:26.759
centuries.

07:07:26.819 --> 07:07:29.700
Keeping you alive only to die over and

07:07:29.700 --> 07:07:30.240
over again.

07:07:30.299 --> 07:07:34.919
I feel like I feel like perhaps you've

07:07:34.919 --> 07:07:35.639
been punished enough.

07:07:35.700 --> 07:07:40.139
Foslayer turned away from him, and rested

07:07:40.139 --> 07:07:41.520
her talons on one of the frozen

07:07:41.520 --> 07:07:43.500
dragonettes, hiding her face.

07:07:43.560 --> 07:07:47.340
After a moment, she said, in a muffled

07:07:47.340 --> 07:07:50.459
fractured voice, I didn't steal him.

07:07:50.520 --> 07:07:53.880
Prince Arctic, Winter said.

07:07:53.939 --> 07:07:56.580
I didn't steal him.

07:07:56.639 --> 07:07:59.639
Though Slayer lifted one wing so she

07:07:59.639 --> 07:08:00.659
could meet Winter's eyes.

07:08:00.720 --> 07:08:02.639
I fell in love with him.

07:08:02.759 --> 07:08:06.060
An entire history of a tribe.

07:08:06.119 --> 07:08:09.900
The story of a war, the foundation of an

07:08:09.900 --> 07:08:10.740
ancient hatred.

07:08:10.799 --> 07:08:14.159
It all shivered in winter's mind, like

07:08:14.159 --> 07:08:16.259
stepping onto the thinnest layer of ice.

07:08:16.319 --> 07:08:20.580
And he loved me too, Those Slayer said.

07:08:20.639 --> 07:08:22.139
That's the truth.

07:08:22.200 --> 07:08:24.659
Although no ice wing has ever listened

07:08:24.659 --> 07:08:25.680
long enough to hear it before.

07:08:25.740 --> 07:08:29.400
Everything, was splintering apart.

07:08:29.459 --> 07:08:33.180
We didn't mean to ruin everything. she

07:08:33.180 --> 07:08:36.720
said, or start a terrible war, or make 2

07:08:36.720 --> 07:08:38.340
tribes hate each other for all eternity.

07:08:38.400 --> 07:08:40.799
We just wanted to be together.

07:08:40.860 --> 07:08:42.959
He believed her.

07:08:43.020 --> 07:08:45.119
He wouldn't have a month ago.

07:08:45.180 --> 07:08:48.240
But now he believed her, because he knew

07:08:48.240 --> 07:08:49.200
exactly how that felt.

07:08:49.259 --> 07:08:51.659
Because he could imagine throwing

07:08:51.659 --> 07:08:54.119
everything away too, for the chance to be

07:08:54.119 --> 07:08:54.599
with Moon.

07:08:54.659 --> 07:08:57.599
If they dared to start something.

07:08:57.659 --> 07:09:01.259
Could he and Moon end as badly as Foe

07:09:01.259 --> 07:09:02.159
Slayer and Arctic?

07:09:02.220 --> 07:09:03.840
Would he risk it?

07:09:03.900 --> 07:09:05.939
Even after seeing where it might lead?

07:09:06.000 --> 07:09:09.360
It's different, he told himself.

07:09:09.419 --> 07:09:12.060
Queen Diamond cared very much what

07:09:12.060 --> 07:09:13.319
happened to Prince Arctic.

07:09:13.439 --> 07:09:15.599
No one cares at all what happens to me.

07:09:15.659 --> 07:09:18.240
So now you know.

07:09:18.360 --> 07:09:21.060
Beauslayer said, rolling the spear over

07:09:21.060 --> 07:09:21.419
to him.

07:09:21.479 --> 07:09:23.459
Ready to kill me?

07:09:23.580 --> 07:09:25.259
He shook his head.

07:09:25.319 --> 07:09:27.540
I'm getting you out of here.

07:09:27.659 --> 07:09:31.259
The Nightwing's eyes gleamed, dark and

07:09:31.259 --> 07:09:32.580
glittering in the light from his moon

07:09:32.580 --> 07:09:33.060
globe.

07:09:33.180 --> 07:09:36.779
That's impossible, I'm afraid, she said.

07:09:36.840 --> 07:09:39.299
Every time I've tried to cross the chasm

07:09:39.299 --> 07:09:41.520
some kind of invisible wool drives me

07:09:41.520 --> 07:09:41.819
back.

07:09:41.880 --> 07:09:44.220
I assume the enchantment was crafted to

07:09:44.220 --> 07:09:45.720
keep me here forever.

07:09:45.840 --> 07:09:48.900
Maybe, winter said.

07:09:48.959 --> 07:09:51.419
But ice wings are careful planners

07:09:51.419 --> 07:09:53.520
especially when it comes to animus

07:09:53.520 --> 07:09:53.819
gifts.

07:09:53.880 --> 07:09:56.819
I'm sure Diamond left away to free you, in

07:09:56.819 --> 07:09:58.200
case they needed you to negotiate with

07:09:58.200 --> 07:09:58.860
the Nightwings.

07:09:58.919 --> 07:10:02.099
He stepped back, studying her from wings

07:10:02.099 --> 07:10:02.580
to tail.

07:10:02.639 --> 07:10:05.279
It must be your shackles.

07:10:05.340 --> 07:10:07.919
That's what's been animus touched, right?

07:10:07.979 --> 07:10:10.860
She lifted one back foot and then the

07:10:10.860 --> 07:10:11.040
other.

07:10:11.099 --> 07:10:15.419
Well, they're impervious to fire, she

07:10:15.419 --> 07:10:16.259
said.

07:10:16.380 --> 07:10:17.759
And nothing happens when I smash them

07:10:17.759 --> 07:10:19.680
against the walls, except it makes my

07:10:19.680 --> 07:10:21.840
angles really hurt, so I'm guessing

07:10:21.840 --> 07:10:22.740
they're enchanted, yes.

07:10:22.799 --> 07:10:26.520
Whatever will break them, Winter said.

07:10:26.580 --> 07:10:29.220
I bet can only be done by a member of the

07:10:29.220 --> 07:10:29.819
Royal Family.

07:10:29.880 --> 07:10:32.040
If I know ice wings anyway.

07:10:32.099 --> 07:10:34.740
But you're in luck, because that's what I

07:10:34.740 --> 07:10:34.979
am.

07:10:35.040 --> 07:10:37.919
He tried not to think about his name on

07:10:37.919 --> 07:10:38.939
the rankings wall.

07:10:39.000 --> 07:10:42.119
His name glittering at the top, and then

07:10:42.119 --> 07:10:44.220
tundras claws scratching through it

07:10:44.220 --> 07:10:45.299
marking him as dead.

07:10:45.360 --> 07:10:48.419
He picked up one of the spears and

07:10:48.419 --> 07:10:49.740
pointed it at the shackles.

07:10:49.799 --> 07:10:51.299
Hold still.

07:10:51.360 --> 07:10:55.080
Oh, dear, Boslayer said, closing her

07:10:55.080 --> 07:10:55.319
eyes.

07:10:55.380 --> 07:10:58.799
With a swift jabbing motion, Winter

07:10:58.799 --> 07:11:00.540
struck the closest shackle with a tip of

07:11:00.540 --> 07:11:00.959
the spear.

07:11:01.020 --> 07:11:03.720
It bounced off, reverberating in his

07:11:03.720 --> 07:11:04.139
claws.

07:11:04.200 --> 07:11:06.299
The shackle looked untouched.

07:11:06.360 --> 07:11:09.000
Winter set the spear down again, and

07:11:09.000 --> 07:11:10.560
crouched to examine the shackles.

07:11:10.619 --> 07:11:13.560
There was a small diamond shape indented

07:11:13.560 --> 07:11:14.400
on the side of each one.

07:11:14.459 --> 07:11:17.819
Carefully, he poked the diamond with one

07:11:17.819 --> 07:11:19.439
claw, but that didn't do anything

07:11:19.439 --> 07:11:19.680
either.

07:11:19.740 --> 07:11:23.880
One more possibility, something only an

07:11:23.880 --> 07:11:26.279
ice wing could do, which made it safe

07:11:26.279 --> 07:11:29.580
because no ice wing would ever, ever free

07:11:29.580 --> 07:11:30.360
a night wing.

07:11:30.419 --> 07:11:33.180
He reached inside him for the lurking

07:11:33.180 --> 07:11:36.419
snowstorm and then breathed out, covering

07:11:36.419 --> 07:11:37.619
the diamond with frost breath.

07:11:37.680 --> 07:11:41.400
The shackles sprang apart, clattered to

07:11:41.400 --> 07:11:43.139
the floor, and shattered into tiny

07:11:43.139 --> 07:11:43.680
pieces.

07:11:43.680 --> 07:11:46.979
Foslayer sat up, staring at the other

07:11:46.979 --> 07:11:49.259
shackle with hope and disbelief warring

07:11:49.259 --> 07:11:49.680
in her eyes.

07:11:49.740 --> 07:11:52.560
Wait, Winter said.

07:11:52.619 --> 07:11:54.299
He touched the other shackle.

07:11:54.360 --> 07:11:56.220
I should.

07:11:56.279 --> 07:11:57.720
I have to make sure one thing.

07:11:57.779 --> 07:11:59.400
If I free you.

07:11:59.520 --> 07:12:01.560
You have to promise you won't go hurt any

07:12:01.560 --> 07:12:02.220
ice wings.

07:12:02.279 --> 07:12:04.560
I don't want a whole new cycle of

07:12:04.560 --> 07:12:05.700
vengeance and war to start.

07:12:05.759 --> 07:12:06.900
Do you understand?

07:12:06.959 --> 07:12:08.400
It ends here.

07:12:08.459 --> 07:12:11.580
I never want to see an ice wing ever

07:12:11.580 --> 07:12:12.360
again in my whole life.

07:12:12.479 --> 07:12:14.459
Those Slayer said fervently.

07:12:14.520 --> 07:12:17.220
Set me free, and I'll go straight home to

07:12:17.220 --> 07:12:18.840
the night kingdom, and you'll never see

07:12:18.840 --> 07:12:19.319
me again.

07:12:19.380 --> 07:12:21.540
The Night Kingdom.

07:12:21.659 --> 07:12:24.180
The lost city of night.

07:12:24.240 --> 07:12:26.939
Boslayer knew exactly where it was.

07:12:27.000 --> 07:12:28.860
She could help them stop the prophecy.

07:12:28.919 --> 07:12:33.060
Actually, Winter said, I want to come

07:12:33.060 --> 07:12:33.299
with you.

07:12:33.419 --> 07:12:37.919
This was his future now, not prints among

07:12:37.919 --> 07:12:41.159
ice wings, not Queen Glacier's nephew, not

07:12:41.159 --> 07:12:42.720
a warrior struggling his way up their

07:12:42.720 --> 07:12:45.119
rankings, under the disapproving gaze of

07:12:45.119 --> 07:12:46.139
his parents.

07:12:46.200 --> 07:12:48.479
He was a dragon, who had friends from

07:12:48.479 --> 07:12:50.700
other tribes, and he was going to save

07:12:50.700 --> 07:12:51.840
Jade Mountain with them.

07:12:51.900 --> 07:12:54.840
He leaned forward to breathe frost breath

07:12:54.840 --> 07:12:55.799
on the last shackle.

07:12:55.919 --> 07:12:59.819
Moon, Kibli, Kingajoo.

07:12:59.880 --> 07:13:00.779
I'm coming.

07:13:00.900 --> 07:13:02.040
Wait for me.

07:13:02.099 --> 07:13:03.299
I'll be there soon.

07:13:03.419 --> 07:13:07.860
Epilogue.

07:13:07.979 --> 07:13:11.520
Alone and buried in rock.

07:13:11.580 --> 07:13:16.259
Dark Stalker waited, and listened. 26

07:13:16.259 --> 07:13:18.720
dragonettes remained of the 35 who had

07:13:18.720 --> 07:13:21.119
started at Jade Mountain Academy, and

07:13:21.119 --> 07:13:22.799
their minds were full of secrets.

07:13:22.919 --> 07:13:26.819
In the art cave, a Nightwing wondered

07:13:26.819 --> 07:13:28.380
where Moon Watcher and the rest of the

07:13:28.380 --> 07:13:29.400
jade winglet had gone.

07:13:29.459 --> 07:13:32.520
He dipped his brush and paint and worried

07:13:32.520 --> 07:13:34.020
about the secret letter he had just

07:13:34.020 --> 07:13:35.340
received from old friends.

07:13:35.340 --> 07:13:36.959
Is it true?

07:13:37.020 --> 07:13:39.360
Have they escaped Thorn's prison?

07:13:39.419 --> 07:13:41.700
Are they really coming back soon with an

07:13:41.700 --> 07:13:42.000
army?

07:13:42.060 --> 07:13:45.479
And does mother know?

07:13:45.540 --> 07:13:48.360
And will she join them?

07:13:48.419 --> 07:13:50.759
Which side of the coup would she be on?

07:13:50.880 --> 07:13:53.939
And would I want her to?

07:13:54.000 --> 07:13:56.459
Or all things may be better the way they

07:13:56.459 --> 07:13:58.860
are, even with a rain wing for our

07:13:58.860 --> 07:13:59.220
queen.

07:13:59.279 --> 07:14:01.080
He didn't know.

07:14:01.200 --> 07:14:02.939
He'd have to make a choice.

07:14:03.000 --> 07:14:04.919
Probably sooner than he wanted to.

07:14:04.979 --> 07:14:07.380
And he had no idea what the right

07:14:07.380 --> 07:14:07.979
decision would be.

07:14:08.040 --> 07:14:10.680
Dark Stalker knew.

07:14:10.740 --> 07:14:13.200
He knew which option would lead this

07:14:13.200 --> 07:14:16.139
dragonette to a long, safe life, and

07:14:16.139 --> 07:14:17.580
which would end in death within the

07:14:17.580 --> 07:14:18.299
year.

07:14:18.360 --> 07:14:20.880
He also knew which choice would be better

07:14:20.880 --> 07:14:22.139
for his own plans.

07:14:22.200 --> 07:14:24.659
But which path a dragonette would take.

07:14:24.720 --> 07:14:26.819
That was still uncertain.

07:14:26.880 --> 07:14:30.840
Outside, on the sandy bank of a mountain

07:14:30.840 --> 07:14:33.959
stream, the mind shrouded sandwing took

07:14:33.959 --> 07:14:36.000
off her necklace, hit it carefully under

07:14:36.000 --> 07:14:38.520
a rock, and waded into the frigid water.

07:14:38.580 --> 07:14:42.599
Dark Stalker narrowed in on her, knowing

07:14:42.599 --> 07:14:44.220
this was a rare few minutes of exposure.

07:14:44.279 --> 07:14:46.740
Cold, cold, cold.

07:14:46.799 --> 07:14:49.139
She was cursing as she splashed.

07:14:49.200 --> 07:14:52.979
Stupid, stupid, stupid, 3 moons.

07:14:53.040 --> 07:14:53.700
Why is it so cold?

07:14:53.759 --> 07:14:55.380
I've got to get back to the desert.

07:14:55.500 --> 07:14:59.040
Abruptly out loud, she said, are you

07:14:59.040 --> 07:14:59.400
listening?

07:14:59.459 --> 07:15:00.540
You'd better be.

07:15:00.599 --> 07:15:03.720
For a moment, Dark Stalker was startled

07:15:03.720 --> 07:15:05.880
into thinking she meant him, but then she

07:15:05.880 --> 07:15:06.180
went on.

07:15:06.299 --> 07:15:08.639
This plan is inane.

07:15:08.700 --> 07:15:11.220
I haven't learned anything new here, and

07:15:11.220 --> 07:15:12.540
I can barely get near the daughter

07:15:12.540 --> 07:15:15.659
especially after all the aggravation, with

07:15:15.659 --> 07:15:18.360
caves exploding and other inconvenient

07:15:18.360 --> 07:15:19.740
nuisances.

07:15:19.799 --> 07:15:22.080
I thought I had an idea, but then he up

07:15:22.080 --> 07:15:22.979
and vanished from the school.

07:15:23.040 --> 07:15:25.619
You have no idea how frustrating it is.

07:15:25.680 --> 07:15:28.560
It's like 400 other stories are going on

07:15:28.560 --> 07:15:31.439
around me, and nobody has noticed that

07:15:31.439 --> 07:15:33.180
I'm the one who's going to shape the

07:15:33.180 --> 07:15:34.259
future of Pyria.

07:15:34.319 --> 07:15:37.619
She brooded for a moment, thinking

07:15:37.619 --> 07:15:40.020
jumbled thoughts about castles and crowns

07:15:40.020 --> 07:15:40.560
and power.

07:15:40.680 --> 07:15:44.340
Finally she said, There's one more

07:15:44.340 --> 07:15:45.419
possible option.

07:15:45.479 --> 07:15:46.919
If I stay a bit longer.

07:15:46.979 --> 07:15:50.220
A dragonette, as loyal to that thorn

07:15:50.220 --> 07:15:51.360
character as anyone.

07:15:51.419 --> 07:15:53.639
And I think she's connected to one of

07:15:53.639 --> 07:15:54.659
Thorn's generals.

07:15:54.720 --> 07:15:56.639
She might be my inn.

07:15:56.700 --> 07:15:58.200
I'll give it a try.

07:15:58.259 --> 07:16:00.779
But if it gets too annoying, I'm coming

07:16:00.779 --> 07:16:02.099
back to the Scorpion Den.

07:16:02.220 --> 07:16:05.340
Onyx climbed out of the stream and shook

07:16:05.340 --> 07:16:06.360
her wings furiously.

07:16:06.479 --> 07:16:08.939
Send me a message the usual way.

07:16:09.000 --> 07:16:10.500
She snapped.

07:16:10.560 --> 07:16:13.619
I will be queen within the month.

07:16:13.680 --> 07:16:16.319
Whether that old dragon helps me, or

07:16:16.319 --> 07:16:17.700
whether I have to kill him and do it

07:16:17.700 --> 07:16:17.939
myself.

07:16:18.000 --> 07:16:21.360
She dropped the necklace over her head

07:16:21.360 --> 07:16:23.520
and all dark stalker could hear was

07:16:23.520 --> 07:16:23.939
fuzz.

07:16:24.060 --> 07:16:26.099
Interesting.

07:16:26.159 --> 07:16:28.439
Who was she talking to?

07:16:28.500 --> 07:16:29.400
And how?

07:16:29.459 --> 07:16:32.520
He wished he could tell Moon Watcher.

07:16:32.580 --> 07:16:34.259
He wished he could tell anyone.

07:16:34.319 --> 07:16:37.319
But with her gone, he had no one left who

07:16:37.319 --> 07:16:37.740
could hear him.

07:16:37.799 --> 07:16:41.040
Come back soon, little moon watcher.

07:16:41.159 --> 07:16:44.279
Bring me my talisman, and come back

07:16:44.279 --> 07:16:44.520
soon.

07:16:44.580 --> 07:16:47.700
Deep in the underground lake.

07:16:47.759 --> 07:16:50.279
Another dragonette was swimming, although

07:16:50.279 --> 07:16:51.479
the temperature of the water didn't

07:16:51.479 --> 07:16:51.959
bother her.

07:16:52.020 --> 07:16:55.799
Fathoms, great, great, great, great, great

07:16:55.799 --> 07:16:57.720
great, great, great, great, great, great

07:16:57.720 --> 07:17:00.360
great, great, dove to the bottom, and

07:17:00.360 --> 07:17:02.939
then shot up out of the lake, soaring to

07:17:02.939 --> 07:17:04.680
the ceiling and spiraling back down with

07:17:04.680 --> 07:17:05.220
a splash.

07:17:05.279 --> 07:17:09.180
Very impressive, princess, called the sea

07:17:09.180 --> 07:17:11.400
wing named Pike, paddling in a small

07:17:11.400 --> 07:17:12.299
circle nearby.

07:17:12.360 --> 07:17:14.759
Such speed and grace.

07:17:14.939 --> 07:17:17.759
The sea wing with a skyfire bracelet

07:17:17.759 --> 07:17:19.200
snorted from the top of a rock.

07:17:19.259 --> 07:17:22.319
Anybody can do that, he said.

07:17:22.319 --> 07:17:25.619
Not when you're tied to your mother, his

07:17:25.619 --> 07:17:27.840
sister said, squirting water at him with

07:17:27.840 --> 07:17:28.319
her talons.

07:17:28.380 --> 07:17:31.740
I've never flown as fast as I wanted, or

07:17:31.740 --> 07:17:33.000
soared as high as I could go.

07:17:33.060 --> 07:17:36.659
Now I can do anything, anything I want.

07:17:36.720 --> 07:17:39.180
Stop being such a mope, turtle.

07:17:39.240 --> 07:17:41.159
So what if your entire winglet is gone?

07:17:41.220 --> 07:17:42.240
You've still got us.

07:17:42.360 --> 07:17:44.759
She thwacked her tail into the water

07:17:44.759 --> 07:17:47.340
sending a wave over the other 3 sea wings

07:17:47.340 --> 07:17:48.060
in the lake with her.

07:17:48.119 --> 07:17:51.299
Unless mother comes and tries to take me

07:17:51.299 --> 07:17:53.340
home, but I won't let her.

07:17:53.400 --> 07:17:54.180
I won't.

07:17:54.240 --> 07:17:56.819
I might be the most powerful dragon in

07:17:56.819 --> 07:17:58.799
the world, and if she didn't learn that

07:17:58.799 --> 07:18:01.200
from what I did to Whirlpool, I can teach

07:18:01.200 --> 07:18:01.860
her some other way.

07:18:01.919 --> 07:18:04.979
The spell on Aucklett's harness should

07:18:04.979 --> 07:18:05.880
keep her away from me, though.

07:18:06.000 --> 07:18:08.700
If it doesn't, I'll come up with

07:18:08.700 --> 07:18:09.299
something stronger.

07:18:09.419 --> 07:18:12.000
Tag, you're it.

07:18:12.119 --> 07:18:15.180
Barracuda called, tapping anemone's tail

07:18:15.180 --> 07:18:15.959
and racing away.

07:18:16.080 --> 07:18:18.900
The rest of the sea wing princess

07:18:18.900 --> 07:18:20.700
thoughts scattered into laughter and the

07:18:20.700 --> 07:18:20.880
game.

07:18:20.939 --> 07:18:24.419
Dark Stalker studied her possible futures

07:18:24.419 --> 07:18:27.240
thoughtfully, then tucked them away and

07:18:27.240 --> 07:18:27.900
moved on.

07:18:27.959 --> 07:18:29.520
There.

07:18:29.580 --> 07:18:32.580
Now this was the most interesting mind in

07:18:32.580 --> 07:18:32.939
the school.

07:18:33.000 --> 07:18:37.500
This poor dragon, pacing in an empty cave

07:18:37.500 --> 07:18:39.540
afraid of her own scales.

07:18:39.599 --> 07:18:43.619
Her mind was a blazing mess of flames, hot

07:18:43.619 --> 07:18:45.599
and fierce, and self destructive.

07:18:45.659 --> 07:18:48.720
Her dreams were haunted by hissing queen

07:18:48.720 --> 07:18:49.680
with a melted face.

07:18:49.799 --> 07:18:53.340
Her heart was given entirely and forever

07:18:53.340 --> 07:18:55.799
to the only dragon she couldn't hurt.

07:18:55.860 --> 07:18:59.340
Was she the talons of power and fire?

07:18:59.400 --> 07:19:01.860
Dark Stalker wasn't sure.

07:19:01.919 --> 07:19:04.799
The paths ahead of her were all confusion

07:19:04.799 --> 07:19:07.200
like trying to follow a map into a forest

07:19:07.200 --> 07:19:07.560
fire.

07:19:07.619 --> 07:19:10.439
But on the other side, something

07:19:10.439 --> 07:19:12.959
flickered through the smoke, something

07:19:12.959 --> 07:19:16.020
like hope, something shaped, like a

07:19:16.020 --> 07:19:16.380
scroll.

07:19:16.500 --> 07:19:19.319
He didn't have to see exactly what would

07:19:19.319 --> 07:19:19.619
happen.

07:19:19.680 --> 07:19:21.900
He was already sure of one thing.

07:19:21.959 --> 07:19:25.740
This dragon could change everything.

07:19:25.799 --> 07:19:32.220
A letter from Smolder of the Sandwings, to

07:19:32.220 --> 07:19:33.779
Vermilion of the Sky Wings.

07:19:33.900 --> 07:19:37.259
On the challenges and joys of scavenger

07:19:37.259 --> 07:19:38.040
pet ownership.

07:19:38.099 --> 07:19:41.400
Dear Vermilion.

07:19:41.520 --> 07:19:44.700
Greetings from the kingdom of sand to the

07:19:44.700 --> 07:19:45.240
Sky Kingdom.

07:19:45.299 --> 07:19:48.959
My sister tells me that you might get a

07:19:48.959 --> 07:19:50.700
pet scavenger like mine.

07:19:50.759 --> 07:19:52.799
It's a splendid idea.

07:19:52.860 --> 07:19:56.459
They are highly entertaining, but I must

07:19:56.459 --> 07:19:59.580
warn you, scavengers are not easy pets to

07:19:59.580 --> 07:19:59.819
keep.

07:19:59.880 --> 07:20:03.119
Mine is probably the only one to have

07:20:03.119 --> 07:20:04.860
survived longer than 5 years.

07:20:04.919 --> 07:20:08.040
So might I offer some advice?

07:20:08.099 --> 07:20:10.380
Rule number one.

07:20:10.439 --> 07:20:13.080
Protect your scavenger.

07:20:13.139 --> 07:20:16.319
Someone will definitely try to eat her

07:20:16.319 --> 07:20:19.560
whether by accident or not.

07:20:19.619 --> 07:20:22.740
I recommend you clearly label your pet

07:20:22.740 --> 07:20:25.200
with some kind of collar or bell.

07:20:25.259 --> 07:20:28.500
If you make the color sparkly, the

07:20:28.500 --> 07:20:30.900
scavenger will probably love it, they

07:20:30.900 --> 07:20:32.400
adore shiny things.

07:20:32.459 --> 07:20:35.880
Keep in mind that scavengers have no

07:20:35.880 --> 07:20:36.959
natural weapons.

07:20:37.020 --> 07:20:41.040
No claws, no wings, no scales, no fire

07:20:41.040 --> 07:20:43.259
and absolutely useless teeth.

07:20:43.319 --> 07:20:46.799
Also, they are shockingly squishy.

07:20:46.860 --> 07:20:50.939
So do not squeeze them, even lovingly, or

07:20:50.939 --> 07:20:53.580
shake them, even if they are very wicked

07:20:53.580 --> 07:20:55.500
or poke them too hard.

07:20:55.560 --> 07:20:58.860
They also love making things with their

07:20:58.860 --> 07:20:59.700
little paws.

07:20:59.759 --> 07:21:03.119
So rule number 2 is protect your

07:21:03.119 --> 07:21:03.840
belongings.

07:21:03.900 --> 07:21:08.099
If you have anything made of cloth, say, a

07:21:08.099 --> 07:21:10.500
favorite blanket or new curtains, for

07:21:10.500 --> 07:21:13.020
instance, keep it far out of your

07:21:13.020 --> 07:21:13.919
scavenger's reach.

07:21:13.979 --> 07:21:17.099
Otherwise, it will end up with holes in

07:21:17.099 --> 07:21:20.279
it, and those scraps of cloth will be

07:21:20.279 --> 07:21:22.799
transformed into mysterious scavenger

07:21:22.799 --> 07:21:23.459
coverings.

07:21:23.520 --> 07:21:27.119
They must get rather cold, as all the

07:21:27.119 --> 07:21:29.520
scavengers I've ever seen come wrapped in

07:21:29.520 --> 07:21:30.720
fabric at all times.

07:21:30.779 --> 07:21:34.500
As for the care and feeding of your

07:21:34.500 --> 07:21:37.380
scavenger, they eat a lot more than you'd

07:21:37.380 --> 07:21:40.500
expect, for their tiny size, and they

07:21:40.500 --> 07:21:43.799
prefer meat only after it's been set on

07:21:43.799 --> 07:21:44.040
fire.

07:21:44.099 --> 07:21:47.880
I offered flour a live desert mouse once

07:21:47.880 --> 07:21:51.060
and later discovered, she'd kept it as a

07:21:51.060 --> 07:21:51.540
pet.

07:21:51.599 --> 07:21:55.200
They also require a daily supply fresh

07:21:55.200 --> 07:21:58.560
water, and get very floppy, or very loud

07:21:58.560 --> 07:21:59.580
if you forget to provide it.

07:21:59.700 --> 07:22:04.139
Remember, scavengers are endangered, and

07:22:04.139 --> 07:22:06.900
can be hard to acquire, as the few that

07:22:06.900 --> 07:22:08.819
are left are increasingly skilled at

07:22:08.819 --> 07:22:10.200
hiding from dragons.

07:22:10.680 --> 07:22:12.419
I've heard that some are impossible to

07:22:12.419 --> 07:22:13.080
tame too.

07:22:13.139 --> 07:22:15.779
And of course, there are those stories

07:22:15.779 --> 07:22:18.720
about pet scavengers trying to stab their

07:22:18.720 --> 07:22:20.279
owners in the middle of the night.

07:22:20.400 --> 07:22:24.599
But flower has always been a loyal

07:22:24.599 --> 07:22:27.360
amusing pet, and I'm terribly fond of

07:22:27.360 --> 07:22:27.599
her.

07:22:27.659 --> 07:22:30.779
So I say don't worry about all the

07:22:30.779 --> 07:22:31.259
rumors.

07:22:31.380 --> 07:22:33.659
Worst case scenario.

07:22:33.720 --> 07:22:37.139
If your scavenger is wildly annoying, you

07:22:37.139 --> 07:22:38.279
can always eat him.

07:22:38.340 --> 07:22:41.819
Best of luck, and do send me a picture of

07:22:41.819 --> 07:22:43.139
your scavenger whenever you get it.

07:22:43.200 --> 07:22:45.900
My scavenger drew this picture of us

07:22:45.900 --> 07:22:46.319
herself.

07:22:46.380 --> 07:22:48.000
Isn't she clever?

07:22:48.060 --> 07:22:50.340
I like the fierce look on her little face

07:22:50.340 --> 07:22:50.700
here.

07:22:50.759 --> 07:22:53.819
Rather a good likeness of me too, I must

07:22:53.819 --> 07:22:54.119
say.

07:22:54.180 --> 07:22:58.200
Wishing you bride sun and strong winds.

07:22:58.319 --> 07:22:59.459
Smolder.

07:22:59.580 --> 07:23:05.639
A guide to the dragons of Pyria.

07:23:05.700 --> 07:23:08.700
Updated and edited by Starflight of the

07:23:08.700 --> 07:23:09.299
